Are you in need of aid?
Do you have business on my land, stranger?
What're you doing on my land?
If i don't get my work done, Jerall will give me the axe.
Not now, friend. Please, not now.nnWe have so much work to do, and I'm not sure how we'll get it all done.
Welcome, stranger.  Care for a pint?
Good to see a friendly face out here.
Hello, what can I do for you?
You look new in town.  Take my advice, don't stay long.

You come to save Ranser? You come too late. Ranser is dead. He was slaughtered in my house!nnBlood will follow blood: I have been blamed for his death, but my subjects will suffer for it. This will mean war, and we are not ready!
I do hope you're in town to curb this plague of werewolf attacks. If you're looking for ways to help, speak to Warden Godwin. He's my fiancee, you know!
Eagle's Watch is under siege. The last thing we need right now is graverobbing.
Obviously, there's other things I'd like to do than liason with the Magis Order. But someone has to do it.
Interesting. You seem to think I have nothing better to do than yap at strangers.
And what is it you're looking for?
You'll live longer if you move along
Have you come to ask about herbs? I know a few things, but I'm no expert.
If you're quiet and still, you can hear the forest whispering its discontent. nnSomething is not right here.
I did everything I could, but it wasn't enough
There are few things the right potion won't cure or kill.
Welcome to the finest inn in Grayborne.  It's the only inn in Grayborne, but we won't split hairs.  What can I do for you?
What? There's much to be done around here and too much lollygagging. Are you a lollygagger, or do you plan on helping me out?
Hello, friend. Are you here to aid the Hands of Northmoor? We can always use another set of capable hands there is much to do.
Hello. If you're here to help out, excellent. Otherwise, please don't bother me unless it's important.
Keep your head low, friend. Camlorn's been a mess lately.
I'll cook when I cook. I'm off duty, now.
How can people continue to butcher each other this way?
With every wound I sew back up, some of this madness bleeds its way into me. Eventually, I will be so filled with madness, I won't see it as madness anymore.
There are werewolves running around, the dead walk, and I've got to teach a bunch of farmers and laborers how to soldier.  I'd rather just be sticking men with the pointy bit of my sword.
Without a plan, we are lost.
<The citizen does not acknowledge you. His eyes are distant and glazed.>
Good day to you. Go carefully, and beware the Magis Order.
There's nothing so important in life than the bear necessities.
Grayborne's overrun with strangers. I cannot wait for all these folks to return to their own homes!
This damn well water... can't drink from it, and bathing in it makes you smell like a cow's hind quarters.
Drink a cup of ale? Play some dice?  Maybe you'd care to make a small wager...
We've had bad luck with strangers, of late.  What do you want?
The spirits here? No, they don't seem to bother me much. What can I do for you?
Arkay's blessings upon you. This has not been a safe place recently.
Be careful out there. We're having trouble keeping the undead back.
Throw a coin, make a wish! Maybe I'll get a tasty dish! Hehe...
What can I do for you?
You come at a difficult time, friend.
A shame what's happening on the docks
Adults aren't welcome here. You'd better go.
Bother and more bother! How am I to make a profit if my shipments keep vanishing?
It's dangerous out here. Be careful.
What do you want with me?
Grayborne means nothing to me personally. I cannot wait until I am recalled to Camlorn.
I came to Camlorn as a diplomat, but now I am a hunter. This nefarious assassin must be found before he destroys the High King's grand design.
The Magis Order write their own laws and must not be trusted - be mindful in your dealings with them.
Welcome, traveler. You've come to Grayborne.
I have broken no laws!  You must believe me.
I do hope Adwyn made it to Glenumbra safely.
I serve Countess Virolynn, and the Hands of Northmoor.
I must not falter under the weight of Aldcroft's burdens.
I serve the good lady Virolynn.
Best not to bother the Countess.
Well. If it isn't the great hero of Glenumbra! I am honored.
Watch yourself, stranger. Unholy forces are turning nature against us. Death itself is on the hunt here, hungry for our souls!
<Paine Oges is nursing a heavily bandaged leg.>rnrnBlasted wolves...
I've fine potions, unguents, and elixirs to sell, the best in Northmoor!
Good day to you! I've no wares to sell at present, though I'm busier than ever! They say war is coming, but I know little of such things -- all I need know is that I have work to do.
Greetings.  Slow 'round here these days, isn't it?
We must move quickly. Arkay favors our task, but it is up to us to complete it. If we get separated, I will meet you back at the hallowed brazier. Light it and I shall join you.
I'm can't thank you enough for freeing me.
Can you believe that! Dock urchins today think they can just take anything they please!
You don't look a werewolf, but that's no guarantee... what can I do for you?
Grayborne's a jewel, but goblins, wolves, and witches take the shine off a bit.
And what is it you're looking for?
For now, we abide in Grayborne, and we do what we can for its people.
Our law is one of peaceful cohabitation with all of nature's creatures.
I'm free of it at last. Thank you.
Ugh, my head. The witch gra-Muzgob is close.
It's dark, dank. You get used to it.
It's better no home than no life, I suppose
Be careful. We're close to Camlorn, but even this near it's unsafe.
They must be alive oh please, they must be.
Stay back. This place is not for the untrained.
We are none of us perfect. Only Arkay can promise that.
Do you know where you are?
My constables and I have been hunting bandits along this stretch of road for weeks, and still they plague travelers and caravans.  Be careful!
Stay back! There's an injured man here!
<Marc scowls at you, ready to attack.>rnrnWhose side are you on, then? Ours or theirs?
<Ravsten looks at you thoughtfully.>rnrnYou haven't been in Camlorn long, have you?
I'm not leaving. Not without her.
Things have been a bit uneasy beyond the town's walls. I keep my blades sharpened and my potions handy. You never know when we'll be sent to war.
In time you will all fall before us...
Greetings, stranger. What do you...Agnes! Not so close to the pig!
I don't believe I know you, and that can't be a good thing.
I did everything I could, but it wasn't enough...
I hate it! I hate swamps. Hate hate hate!
You're the hero of Glenumbra, truly? Thank the Gods, I've been sent to find you. King Drugo sends me with dire news.
Werewolves from the south, undead from the north, and Zenithar knows what else from up in Shornhelm. It's a bad time to be a Watcher, I'll tell you that.
Difficult times here, friend. So many sick and wounded to tend to...
It's good to see a friendly face out here!
Brr. The nights sure have been cold, haven't they?
Help! Let us out of here!!
Oh Grit, where could you have gone off too?
<Grit stares at you mournfully, begging to be freed from its cage.>
Greetings, traveler. Be cautious as you travel throughout Northmoor.
This town is doomed! Doomed I say! Their leader is oblivious to everything around him.rnrnWhat a fool.
Who are you stranger? If you hail from Coldun, you will not leave our grounds alive. Speak quickly or ready your weapon!
If you have business with the Bloody Eye, speak with Sly.
Your eyes are filled with a light I have not seen for some years..
All of this hiding in the mountains, as if we were bandits or outcasts simply because we use the power of the Veil? It sickens me. The people of Alaygon should welcome our presence, not shun it!
What you want? Can't you see? Crazy mens and wolfies all around!rnrnThey scared of herbies though.. wonder why..
I'm can't thank you enough for freeing me.
<Germaine scowls at you, ready to attack.>rnrnWhose side are you on, then? Ours or theirs?
<Ravsten looks at you thoughtfully.>rnrnYou haven't been in Camlorn long, have you?
<Marc scowls at you, ready to attack.>rnrnWhose side are you on, then? Ours or theirs?
You must excuse me. The undead threaten us even now, and I've no time for idle chat.
How are things in the city? I hope things aren't too tense between my father's men and the Magis Order. Lady Kallath has been doing her best.
Excuse me. Do you know the way back to the redoubt?
Hmmm, I seem to be lost. Do you know the way back to camp?
Aldcroft, like all of Northmoor, must be protected. Even against itself.

Oh, don't mind me, good traveler. Are you hungry, thirsty? I've fine drink and warm stew, just the thing to brighten a dark day. Camlorn's no Daggerfall, but I can offer you honeyed wine as fine as any you'll find in Daggerfall or Wayrest!
What a mess. I've never seen the like. What to do?
My father believes this town is doomed. Unlike him however, I can not simply pack my belongings and leave the only place I've ever called home.
Greetings child of man. It is good of you to call upon me in this hour. I know of the situation you face and the dark times that seek to consume the town of Alaygon.
Hah, see how fast Scag is?
The enemy approaches, we must be ready.
Forest Spirit protects us from coming fight!
I no want to turn into anything nasty! We stop the Coldun here!
Doogie will be revenged! My piggies will brings them down!
Coldun's dark magic will not work here. The Bloody Eye will make sure of it.
The time for battle has come!
May the Veil give us protection.
Coldun will not get past us this day. No more innocent lives shall be lost..
As long as you're off duty, there's always a pint waiting for you here, hon!
Strange times in Grayborne these days...
Is there something I can do for you?
My jokes may be dull, but my blades are sharp!
Sorry, but you are not authorized to use the flight path at this time.
You do not have authorization to use the flight at this time, I am sorry.
Never thought I'd be in the same tavern with those Order blokes. Odd times.
Hear about the screaming in the east tower? Ghosts, they say. As if ghosts would frighten us!
Inquisitor Alden says one must always be vigilant, even off-duty. That's why I never leave my sword at home.
Pierre needs to learn to relax. Vigilance and all that, that's nice, but settle down after work!
It takes more than a low cut top and some swaying hips to defend Eagle's Watch. *Some* women forget that.
Considering she's a Hand, Sabine and I get along *famously*. There's more to a tavern then groping the wenches, thank the Divines.
Greetings, stranger. Ah, it's good to stop working for a moment!
Only by remaining vigilant may we hope to stop those who would threaten Northmoor. Keep that in mind, friend.
Order never gets tired of swinging those blades around. Beats grooming horses, I suppose.
Suri, groom the horses. Suri, clean the stables. Suri, do my work while I watch the Order swing their blades around all day. You'd do my a favor by staying out of my way.
Do you mind? I'm having a private meal with my husband.
There's few enough women in the Watch, friend. Best find your own.
Me? Jump? You're silly. Why would I go and do a fool thing like that? I'm looking at the dumb dumb Shornhelm soldiers. I bet we could spit on 'em from here!
Hmph. I see you made it out of the Cultists' cave in one piece. Shame about that.

While my husband works to recruit and direct new Hands members, I've been teaching the new militia members how to take care of themselves and their equipment. It seems the commoners are much better at it, which should keep our nobles humble.
Francois isn't allowed to join the Hands, but I don't hold that against him. My admiration for him knows no bounds!
This Hands of Northmoor speaker makes some interesting claims. I wonder if there is any truth to the story she tells?
Ssh, I'm trying to listen to the orator!

Alas, my beautiful Marcella and I must hide our love from her parents! For now, that is. Soon, they'll realize my worth and give us leave to be together. We will travel the world, and I shall protect her as one protects a precious jewel.
Hah! Listen to this girl, speaking out against those who would protect us. A classic case of biting the hand that feeds you.
My daughter is a gifted alchemist. You could do much worse than her potions and tinctures.
Ah, brought any cattle with you? Sheep or oxen, with good supple hides? Too bad. I tire of working wolf hide, yet that's all there is, lately.  Wolves, wolves, wolves. You think we'd run out!

It is true! The signs are fulfilled, the stars whisper of death! These fools are blind, but- Wait... No! You are one of Them! Your soul bears the mark, I can see it! Begone, deathless fiend! Get thee back!!
<The citizen does not acknowledge you. There is a glazed look on her face.>

Dark times, these, when beast and ghost run riot! There was a time when the Old Ways kept such things down, when the Wyrd-women tamed the wild. But now the Old Ways fade, and these Magis firebrands drive the Wyrd witches out. The fools.

I fear there will be no market here today, stranger: the roads are so dangerous that the outer farms cannot send stock nor sheaves. My best mutton and beef is long since gone. The way things are going, I'll have naught to sell but rancid wolf steaks!
I'm free of it at last. Thank you.
This will end badly, yes it will. So much to do... how will we ever recover?
Welcome to my bar, what will it be?
Settle down or you'll be out on your ass!
Gah! Damned wolves tore me up but good.
I used to have quests, back when an NPC like myself could carry 4 or 5 of 'em at a time.  And we liked it that way!!
Still haven't any time to spare. Camlorn's walls will need fixing soon enough.
We guard the King. If you've questions, speak to Oron, the Redguard Emissary.
Please leave me. Can you not tell that I am in mourning for my sister's husband?
I hope you're not looking for trouble.
Greetings, stranger! Throat dry from your travels?
No one enters this room, traveler. Away with you.
You gave me quite the fright, especially after what we've been through! What're you up to, sneaking around?
What can I do for you?
A lumberjack's job is never done!
These wolves are still too close for comfort. Be cautious, stranger!
Foreman's been glad enough for your help, but we're still hard at work.
What brings you to the Order of Arkay, my child?
Your help was most welcome. It is good to be working again.
The Magis Order is not the protector it once was.
Watch yourself in these parts. The roads haven't been safe for ages.
Anything I can do for you, friend?
Look all you like, but don't pick it up 'less you intend to buy it!
I've recovered enough that I can take up the fight. Have your efforts been successful?
I'm just watching over the proceedings.  Don't mind me.
I'm just watching over the proceedings.  Don't mind me.

A big to-do up at the Manor. They say King Ranser dropped dead of a fit, right before supper! A fit! Can you imagine? That's what comes of marrying foreign women. May Akatosh preserve our King Sebastien and save him from such a fate!
Why won't anyone play with me?
Well. They'll let anyone near Camlorn Manse these days, won't they? No wonder the king was murdered. Hmph.
You should not speak until spoken to, stranger. It is no surprise that a murderer walks amongst us. People nowadays are so ill-bred.
I'll handle it from here, citizen.
I learn much by watching...I mean, listening to Orator Bovie.
The missus drags me here every day to hear Orator Bovie speak. I have no idea what he's talking about.
Orator Bovie shouldn't speak such rubbish about the Order. What does he know of these things?
Anything to report? No? Then step aside, traveler.
From what my patrollers have said, tales of your deeds are already spreading through town. This is good.
Do I look like I have time to talk? A king was just murdered! Off with you.
Can I interest you in some fine silk garments?
I take care of the shipments that we receive from the logging camp to the South of Camlorn.
Have you heard the news? King Ranser of Shornhelm gave all his kingdom to our own King Sebastien, right before he died!
I don't know who killed King Ranser, so don't bother asking me anything else.
King Ranser of Shornhelm was murdered in his sleep. War is sure to follow. About time, too.
I wonder if Queen Parvani will come to Camlorn to retrieve her husband's body? My sister who lives in Shornhelm says the Queen is very pretty...and now she's single.
The Order is sure to blame one of us for King Ranser's murder. Zenithar, save us!
Shornhelm is sure to want retribution for the death of their king.
I cannot wait to return to war with Shornhelm. I'd like to thank the murderer personally.
If you ask me, King Ranser was slain by someone who knew his habits. Someone he brought with him from Shornhelm, no doubt!
All this talk of murder is unsettling. I'd rather speak of death in battle.
There are so many people passing through Camlorn these days. King Ranser could have been killed by any of them!
I haven't been to war in so longI look forward to it! If war should happen with Shornhelm again, I am ready!
They say King Ranser's murderer has not been apprehended. No doubt one of the riff-raff from the village. They should all be tortured until one of them confesses.
I knew the King was cursed the moment I saw him. He had an aura of death about him!
All this trouble will delay shipments again. You'd think Shornhelm's king could have died upon his own soil!
I hope King Ranser's murder does not affect Camlorn's commerce.
Things are unsettled up at the Manse. I doubt we'll sleep easy until King Ranser's murderer is found.
King Sebastien should double the Royal Guards now. That'll be my chance to be hired on with them.
Anything to report? No? Then step aside, traveler.
Can't you see that I am thinking? Now I've forgotten everything! Bah!
Everyone has been a bit jumpy lately, what with King Ranser's murder and all.
<This man does not appear to have died of natural causes.>
We haven't seen a shipment in awhile.  Hopefully everything is ok at the camp.
The undead are so numerous. How long until they are freed from their misery?
Your presence brings me hope that we will win against the undead, stranger.
Thank the Divines I found you. My drake allowed me to reach you here - and I see you have slain our mysterious enemy. This is good.
Good day, traveler. May the blessings of Arkay always be upon you.
<Varic Aston is in a deep slumber, recovering from grevious wounds.>
These entities are a danger to us all.
Hello to you, revered Numinous. How can these old bones be of service?
Already, I sense the spiritual strength of our Wyrd Tree. You have cleansed the evil influence within it.
<Varic Aston is in a deep slumber, recovering from grevious wounds.>
King Ranser he is gone, isn't he? It's hard to imagine. My family has served him for decades. And now the thing that slew him in his own bedchamber comes for me - oh, sweet Divines, protect me!
You may wish to turn back, friend. Westtry is no place for the living.
We meet again, my friend - you have followed the trail as well as I.
No spectres will threaten Grayborne while we hold this hill.
We will pull the One Who Hungers from the nether. Be ready.
Though we can not aid you, we will keep the One Who Hungers from escaping.
After this day, that cowardly spirit will not threaten Westtry. Toss those essences in the fire, and we shall pull it into the light.
It will be time to go home, soon.
Westtry lies in ruins, overrun by the undead. How will I ever return my parents' ashes to their home?
The weight of my guilt has robbed me of youth.rnrnA transformation I deserved...
Aldcroft was a quiet town... before the Magis Order arrived.
I don't care what Thetis the Poisoner calls himself; he's just lazy, plain and simple.
The one is pleased to meet a great hero.

I must clear King Sebastien's name. King Ranser was murdered in King Sebastien's house, and now Ranser's allies blame Northmoor's king and threaten war.nnI must find Ranser's real assassin, before he destroys the High King's grand design.
Who let all those Wyrd women into Grayborne anyway? They make me nervous. Who knows what they're really up to?
The Wyrd don't bother me none. They've been pushed out of their homes, same as the good folks of Westtry. The missus don't like 'em, though.
My cousin lived in Westtry before it was sacked. He's dead now, Arkay bless him. May Grayborne not suffer Westtry's fate!
Even now, I cannot believe that Westtry is gone. The Wyrd are to blame, I am sure of it.
It's been a year...why won't they let us build a real home inside Grayborne? What are they afraid of? They let the Wyrd live in Grayborne, but not us. It's unfair.
On a clear day, we can see Westtry from here. I still don't know if that's good or bad.
What are you bothering me for? I'm fine.
Nothing good can be done until the Magis Order are gone.
Collectin's a job like any other.  Just requires a bit more force, time to time.
I have phat loots... buy them!
It's too dangerous to work out in the woods. Not until those accursed beasts are dealt with.
If they want lumber in Camlorn, let them come out and cut it. That's what I say. See how they like dealing with them things out there!
The woods are cursed.  It's the work of evil spirits for certain!
The high folks in Camlorn don't care what happens to us.Let the soldiers set things right here -- then we can go back to work.
By the Eight, I'll cut down any accursed wolf that crosses my path!
Foreman sent us out here to watch for those wolf-beasts. It ain't right. Why hasn't Camlorn sent any guardsmen to help us?
This is ugly business. My axe is cutting trees, not taking on daedra-touched wolves.
This is no safe place, traveler. We Gravebinders will protect you in our camp, but go further at your peril.
I can sell you wares to help fight the undead here. It pains me to admit it, but the Ashen Order is sadly short of coin.
Have you come to fight beside us? My Gravebinders and I hold the line as best we can,  but we can make no headway against this undead tide.
We are the Lion Guard, the sorcery and steel of the High King. nnNo matter what the cost, we'll retake Camlorn.
Incompetents! Idiots! How could they allow this to happen? Thank the Eight for the Lion Guard.

Daggerfall sent me to cure the corruption in the tarn.nnThe tarn is not only a source of beauty, but also a source of fish, plants, and provisions. nnWe need to cure it quickly. The survival of the land depends on it.
If you're looking for my father, Duke Sebastien, he's not seeing anyone right now.nnIf you want to help, however, I could certainly use it.
My mind... is a little unclear.nnHow did I get out here?
The town to the north is Eagle's Brook. Its people fled when the werewolves took Camlorn. Now the Red Rook Bandits have seized it.
Here I am, safe and sound back in Aldcroft. nnI have you to thank for that.
Come closer. Let me look upon you with these weary eyes.nnYou are not one of Angof's minions. Help us, and we will help you defeat him.
You are here at last. Come closer, friend.
These swamps may look dark to some, but for a long time they were a beautiful garden to Shava.  Shava could once get many plants here, but now Shava hardly ventures from the path.
It's me... or a projection of me. nnI felt an enormous surge of energy when you used my potion.nnAre you all right? What happened?
We can feel the flow of the spring. You have done it, <<1>>!nnThe hags, the hags! Angof has corrupted those foul women. Now they test their fate against ours.nnWe will see. You shall make their fate!

The painful venom that courses through my spirit prevents my eternal rest. nnDamnable Namira! Though I worshipped her in life, she has placed this curse upon me.nnNow I must suffer endlessly in a realm beyond death.

General Faolchu created and led the werewolves that sacked Camlorn. nnOne bite from him turns his victim into a mindless werewolf. It can happen in a heartbeat.nnWe need someone powerful enough to take the battle to General Faolchu.

See that cold pile of undead flesh right there? We just killed it!nnSomeone's creating undead wolves, and they're giving us no end of grief.nnThey stink like death, they don't feel pain, and they chomp any arm or leg in reach.
Faolchu is dead, and his army is falling before us. nnSoon, Camlorn will be ours again.
Be careful in this damned place. The anguish of the dead is palpable.
So rarely do we have visitors...
Why would the rootlings attack? We've always been at peace with them. nnNow I've lost everything. Without coin, I'm without hope.
Three shipments of lumber to send up the coast, and what do I have? Cutters cowering in their barracks. Trees with teeth, they're saying. nnIt's madness.
I've heard disturbing news of an invasion in Camlorn. I pray it isn't true.
Seems an odd thing to me, all them nobles with more than enough to eat while I can't trap a single hare for my empty belly.  A crime, to hunt my supper?  Where's the law in that?
My sister Ileana and I were exploring the Dresan Ruins when spriggans attacked us. nnWe escaped, but we never found what we were looking for....
The Bloodthorn cult has corrupted our beloved Wyrd Tree. nnBefore we can return home, someone must cleanse it.nnWe need your help.

Day and night, it's politics and strife. My family's caught up in the worst of it.nn"Alain tell them this... Alain tell them that...." All I want is a bit of quiet.nnA bit of fishing, I thought, would be just the thing.
I think harpies are fascinating. Don't you?
Once the Beldama Wyrd came here to summon the spirits of the land. nnSince our Wyrd Tree was corrupted, however, the spirits have ignored our sacrifices. This worries me.
Many of my sisters grew sick when corruption took our Wyrd Tree. nnI'm tending two of the most afflicted now, hoping to keep their fever from consuming them.
Corruption threatens the people of Glenumbra and many rare plants throughout the land.
Those soldiers are everywhere now. We're just farmers. Why'd those foolish lords of High Rock bring their armies here? It's not our fight. It never was!
You have slipped into the spirit world... why have you come here?
So Duke Bealton killed Prince Gideon. So what? Why do we have to suffer for it?nnWe're just farmers. A pox on these soldiers and their war.
Can I interest you in a scented candle? How about a nice fur to keep back the cold in that chilly moor?
If they want lumber in Camlorn, let them come out here and cut it themselves. That's what I say! nnLet's see how they like dealing with those things!
Until those accursed beasts are dealt with properly, it's too dangerous to work out in the woods.
I must... be free! Help... the mistress...
Lucky to be back here... mark my words, this'll be the best dinner we've ever eaten.
We are running low on supplies, but our Supplier should have what you're looking for.
Those soldiers are everywhere now. We're just farmers... why'd those foolish lords of High Rock have to bring their armies here? It's not our fight. It never was!
You find a tarnished locket on the floor of the abandoned house. Engraved on the locket are the initials "C. A."
I'll help you take those tools to the camp.  Truth to be told, I'm deadly afraid of those murdering trees.  Never seen anything like that!
Would you like to go up or down?
I should have listened to my father's advice. I should have become a sailor.
It's bad enough working out here at all, much less in the dark.
Ormax is mad, insisting we should keep working under these conditions.
Would you like to go up or down?
<You hear the piteous howls of a trapped wolf.>
I was once an adventurer like you, but I left those days of swordplay and violence behind me. nnSadly, the goblins have forced me to return to my old ways.
Would you like to go up or down?
Would you like to enter the portal?
Would you like to enter the portal?
Would you like to enter the portal?
Would you like to enter the portal?
Would you like to enter the portal?
Would you like to go up or down?
A would-be hero needs more than a blade and bold words to impress me. nnMost of the wanderers we meet who want to join the Lion Guard just aren't cut out for it.
I'll follow you wherever you take us.
I am breath and life, wind and soul.nnWhy do you summon me?
I am the oceans and the rain. I am the lifegiver.nnWhy do you summon me?
All things come from me. All things return to me.nnWhy do you summon me?
My brother says our family ring has been lost. It's been in our family for years. I hope we can find it... or the scoundrel who took it.
Did you see them? Spriggans! All around! nnI think I'll stick with this log. Yes, here's a spot that needs chopping!
What? Oh! Blessings of the Eight upon you, and all that rot. nnI'm sorry. I don't have much time for talking to strangers while those trees are killing my friends.
Did you hear about poor old Zacharia? Dead! Killed by one of those tree beasts! nnYou won't catch me going back out in those woods.
We can't keep loading ships to Stormhaven if there's nothing to load. nnSomeone needs to get those cowards in the woods moving.
These days, I'm happy I'm safely here at the docks instead of working in the woods.

Well met, traveler! Did you hear about the spriggans? nnIt's like my cousin says. "There's always something worse in the forest!"nnA sane person would never leave Daggerfall.nnMy cousin told me that, too. I wonder when he'll be back?
There's nothing like the smell of the sea air! You couldn't pay me enough to chop wood. nnI'd hate to be surrounded by the forest all day. You can't see the sea from there!
I used to speak with the Spirit of Air, but it's been so long since any of the Spirits have answered our calls.
These warm lands are very different from the cold plains of my homeland in the north. Yet even I can sense that the land is suffering.
I'm in a bit of a hurry, if you don't mind. Gotta put wood on the boats.nnWood doesn't just float on its... nevermind.
Some may blame the Wyrd for changes to the land, but we are not responsible for these transformations.nnWe've been driven from our home. Whatever hurts the land hurts the Wyrd.
<It appears this merchant was freshly murdered by something from the swamp...>
I tire of blood, death, and destruction. nnOne day, I hope to use my magic for research again.
A lord and his squire passed us some time ago to go fishing on the western shore beyond the harpies. Fishing! Can't they see the land is under a magical siege! rnrnSelfish brutes.

Nothing like the taste of venison.  Though these days, it's dodging trees to get the deer, which is a strange thing indeed, if you ask me.  Sit down, sit down, I'll tell you all about it.  Just the other day my - what?  Ah, another time, then.
Be careful. This place isn't safe with all those spriggans around.
Good day. I'm sorry if I seem somewhat distracted. I've recently lost something very precious.
Well met, traveler. Welcome to Deleyn's Mill! nnI'm glad to see you aren't a talking tree, like the ones we've been seeing out in the forest.
I don't feel much like talking, what with the forest coming alive and all.
You are not one of my soldiers - but you fight alongside them, and so you have my trust.nnYou are safe in my camp.
I fletch arrows for both the foresters and the trappers around here. Requests have gone up since the trees began to move.
The Lion Guard stands ready. We'll take back Camlorn from those dogs.
You! What were you doing by my boat?
Numinous you may be, but your true worth is yet to be determined.
And what may I do for you?
Hail, Optimate. Are you here to enjoy the Imago Serry?
My soul is bound to this Imago Serry. Meditate, be well, and find the same peace I find in this blessed sanctum.
Pray carry out your part in this war with diligence, Optimate.
The Aquiferi Elementals ravage the land they should cultivate. What a revolting waste!
This Imagerie is the pride of the Kinlord. Ponder its patterns, appreciate its artifice, and feel solace.
We speak again across the ages. I prayed you would prevail, <<1>>.
I'm not one to complain, but I'll be glad when those folks from Camlorn go back home.
Soldiers are all around us while those Red Rooks rule the docks unchallenged. nnSomeone should do something about those thugs. They're a menace!
We've had hard times, especially when the wolves took Camlorn. nnStill, the Aldcroft harbor helps when it can.
You know, I might just join forces with those wolves in Camlorn. nnWerewolves probably stink less than all these new people in Aldcroft.
I may need to leave my job at the docks and join the army. nnA soldier's life might pay less, but it would certainly smell better.
Those Camlorn folks need to take their city back. I'm tired of tripping over them.
An entire city is gone, and their families were eaten by wolves. nnI feel for those Camlorn people.
I hope our lives get back to normal soon. nnI hear even that witch Sibellec is having trouble... not that the thought bothers me too much.
I miss my mother! I want my mother! nnWhy can't we go home?
It's a pleasure to meet you. These days, it's always a pleasure to meet someone who isn't a refugee from Camlorn.
Those wolves killed my family. Not just one or two of them. All of them. nnWhat can an old man do?
If it's not those Camlorn refugees whining, it's the Lion Guard wanting something.nn I can't wait until they're all gone and Aldcroft is ours again.
Duke Sebastien is useless. Why didn't he defend Camlorn?nnKing Casimir should have forced him out for good.
King Casimir's safe enough in Daggerfall. nnMeanwhile, Aldcroft is filled with Camlorn's dregs, and soon, the wolves will be at our doorstep, too.
What is King Casimir doing? Why is he sitting in Daggerfall doing nothing while everything is falling apart? nnThe wolves will be howling at his door before long. Surely, he has to see that!
Ahnarra lost her new home in Camlorn. nnThis one is saddened that Fadomai gave birth to Hircine and his dogs.
Make fun of me all you want, but these moors are better suited to me than Camlorn ever was.
Camlorn has been my family's home since the battles on Glenumbra Moors. nnDuke Sebastien needs to get my home back.
Camlorn is going to be ours again. nnI'm not afraid of those damn werewolves. I don't care how many legs they walk on.
Enough! No more chasing phantom lights around the marshes!nnI want a chance at those Red Rooks. They've been a threat long enough!
Duke Sebastien needs to give the order to take back Camlorn.nnIf he doesn't do it soon, we won't have enough people left to fill the walls.
As with many other people, Camlorn was my home. nnI had good fortune there... until this war started.
I lost everything... everything....nnPlease, can you help? Anything will help.
We're just sitting here at this damn port while wolves prowl through our city.
I wish Duke Sebastien would order the attack already. I'm tired of waiting.
All I want right now is to feel the heft of steel in my hand as it slices through wolf entrails.
Take back Camlorn or go home to Orsinium? I'm not sure which I'll do.
We crossed Iliac Bay to take back Camlorn and put down those curs.
Malauch will grant us victory in taking back Camlorn.
I can't wait to go home. This harbor stinks.
This is my first trip to the moors. The stink is as bad as I thought it would be.
They say there's a Reach Mage to the north. nnAfter we take back Camlorn, we'll have to deal with him.
This will be my first battle fighting beside the Magis Order. nnI look forward to unleashing what I've learned.
Have you heard of Faolchu? He's the big werewolf they say started this whole thing. nnHe's been dead over a hundred years, but now he's walking around. nnWe live in strange times.
Good day to you. Are you here to join our crusade to retake Camlorn?
I hope today is the day Averos will let us retake Camlorn. Then we can march on to Cath Bedraud!
The time for waiting is over. nnI want to go north to Cath Bedraud. I want to plant my spear in that witch.
So this is the port of Aldcroft? Really?nnAveros can't get us out of here fast enough!
I'll admit it. When I first heard we were coming here to take back Camlorn, I wasn't happy. nnNow that I've seen these poor people, I know we're doing the right thing.
I'll be happy to fulfill my obligation and finally go back to the desert. nnAll this water travel has made me ill.
Two months ago, I left home to join the Lion Guard. nnNow I'm back in the moors again.
Glenumbra is less like Stormhaven than I thought it would be. nnI'm just glad to be helping these poor people.
It wasn't two months ago that I left to join the Magis Order. Here I am back in the moors.
Please, take the time to connect with the heritage of the Altmer by standing within our Serries!
A Serry is a reflection of the Altmer race as a whole. It contains perfection that is a direct projection of our own perfection.
Hail and salute! I confess I do not recognize your face - but is there aught I can do for you?
If you seek audience with the Kinlord, you may find him preoccupied with events in the south.
Grim misgivings guide me this day, Numinous, to whither I know not. rnrnAm I to fall on this enchanted beach, my breath carried off across the befouled sea?

Isque is not unfamiliar with your exploits, Optimate - and we are a Kinship in distress.rnrnIn ages past my people created weapons of sound to fend off the Maormer. Obtaining a Blessed Bell would allow us to reclaim Sunhold and our Varla Lens.
The Maormer siege engines on Sunhold Island are devastating our lands. I could use the aid of a Numinous: even if killed, you can return to report.
F-fivefold venerations, Optimate. Mind not my t-tears.
Are you in need, my child?
Could I risk leaving my shrine, the Orrery would be littered with dead Maormer.
I hope you bring aid - our needs are urgent.
I wondered why the Serpent was coiling about the Kinhouse. It swallowed the Varla Lens - how entertaining!
The pale cowards dare to plague the Orrery!
Strike hard, strike fast, and get out. That's how we do things, and you should too.
I see you, Numinous. Your soul is of Mundus and of Coldharbour. I can rejoin your soul to your body in Mundus, but there is a cost...
Well done, my friend. Now that you've placed our beacons, I can teleport you directly back to our camp, if you like.
The sooner we can reclaim Camlorn, the better.nnI'm supposed to find comfortable chambers for His Lordship. It would be easier to spin gold from straw.
If we don't cure these soldiers, they'll become agents of Faolchu. May the Divines curse his name!
Was that a spoonful, or a dram? I'm so busy I can't keep track of everything!
In two more months, we would have been married....nnI'm trained to kill undead, but now... how can I raise my sword against my love?
Precision is the highest virtue, Optimate.
My mother... she has gone to the Deadsands in her desperation.
My son loved the sea. To him it brought death, and to me, despair.
I am here under orders from the king to investigate the increase in crime.nnIt would seem some are willing to use our recent troubles to their advantage.
So thirsty... and my head hurts....

When a Breton is born in Crosswych, his family plants a flowering tree. When he dies, his children spread the flowers on his grave.nnI came here to honor my father by his grave, but there are far too many undead here.
Thank you for your kind words. I don't know what came over me, but I believe I have emerged from the darkness at last.

You there! Listen to me! The others all think I'm crazy, but I'm telling you... these children aren't right.nnYou've seen them, haven't you? Prowling around Crosswych? Have you seen their dead eyes?nnSomething is wrong.
Mind your own business. Get lost!
I barely escaped the mine this time! nnThere's still some miners in there. I hope they'll come soon.
And what may I do for you?
And what may I do for you?

Traveler! I am Raymonde Chevalier! Please, view my wares. nnYou have heard of the famous Chevalier brothers, yes? After all your time on the road, how could you not?nnI, Raymonde Chevalier, assure you: out of all my siblings, I have best prices!

Welcome, friend! Please, view my wares. I am Ronald, one of the famous Chevalier brothers! nnIf you come across my brothers during your time in Glenumbra, know that I, Ronald, will have more to offer you than they ever will! nnRemember me!

Friend! Please come and view my wares. I am Remi and I am one of the famous Chevalier brothers. Certainly you have heard of us. I am not the smartest brother, not the most handsome, but definitely the most generous. Fortunate for you, yes?
May the beauty of Mara fill your senses.
I look forward to this battle.
I am eager to test the new spell I crafted with the Daedric Soul Gems you brought me.  You have my apologizes, should I accidentally set you aflame... or worse.
My blade is coated with a Fire Salt poison. It will cut a poisoned wound then burn it shut to fester. The Serpent will suffer in its demise.
Honor and praise, Optimate.nnSuch tribulations: our Varla Lens, devoured! Our planet Auri-El, downed and replaced by an impostor world!
Enough chasing phantom lights around the marshes.  rnrnWhat I want is a chance at Astrid's Lot, down on the docks.  They've been a threat to shipping and business here long enough!
The world's changed from when I was a lad. nnNow a fellow can't even fish in peace, what with the wolfmen, and the will-o-the-wisps, and those Red Rooks roaming the docks. nnIt's disgraceful.
Welcome to the Orrery, Optimate. It pains me that you must see it in this condition.
The Maormer profane our skies with their hideous new planet: Orgnavar.
The Aetherius is simply the first layer. I have seen outside the Aetherius.
With Suuniqwe gone I am responsible for maintaining the Orrery - a burden I may not be fit to bear.
Tell me, do you ever dream about... Sload?
All things are in place here. Should you venture further south or east, you will find disarray.
Greetings, Optimate. Remain vigilant, the Deadsands are rife with the possessed corpses of our fallen comrades.

Blessing a weapon is a difficult task. Each campaign requires new enchantments.nnFirst, it's flame to deal with zombies. Then it's cold to destroy with fire atronarchs. nnIt's enough to wear an old man down.
F-fivefold venerations, Optimate. Mind not my t-tears.
Angof the Reachmage holds Cath Bedraud. nnFrom there, he's launched waves of undead against the people of Glenumbra. We're here to stop him.
Greetings and salutations, Optimate. Might I borrow a moment of your time?

Numinous! Look what has happened! Look what Hainen has done to me!rnrnAs the stone took over my body I slipped through the cracks, but now my essence is trapped outside. The High Kinlord should hear of this. Go to him now!
Welcome to our home. I trust you've met my lovely children?
Mother will take care of you.
We must hurry, before the Stormwitch attacks the Orrery again.
<You've found a dead body. It's the remains of Arturo Charascel, and it's wearing the leather necklace his mother mentioned.>
Please help us! Something terrible has happened.nnOur expedition is in grave danger!
Welcome to my humble establishment. I've been serving the miners of Crosswych for almost 10 years now.

The Mages Guild came here for the Reach Cloak, an important relic in the fight against Angof.nnWe were ambushed. Many of my brethren are still trapped down below us.nnOthers are doomed to wander the ruins as spectres... forever.
We can't allow Angof to spread his curse throughout Glenumbra. Calmorn will be the last city to fall.
Do you know Arturo Charascel? He's my son. nnI came to look for him among the injured, but I can't find him.
If you'll excuse me, I'll be doing what I can to keep the undead from flooding Crosswych.nnUnless you're here to help, wanderer, kindly step aside.
Crosswych Mine is famous for its ore. Well, it was famous, at any rate. nnFirst, the mine collapses. Now there's undead. We've been out of work for weeks.
Zhian might need to leave Crosswych if the mine doesn't reopen soon. nnThis one's family constantly asks for things Zhian can no longer buy.
Crosswych would be better off without cats of any sort, if you ask me.
We must raise the Lens into the Varline. If you take this Varline Focuser and use it on the Varla Lens, I can do the rest.
Good day! What news have you?
The ruins here in Glenumbra are among the most intriguing I've ever studied. Were it not for the restless spirits here, I would have already charted and cataloged their depths.
My dreams were dark and violent, but I suddenly feel a little better.
The town's surrounded by undead, but I don't care.nnWe aren't running out of ale anytime soon, and <<1>> is staying open for business.

Welcome to Crosswych Inn, traveler. Sad times bring everyone to the inn. nnWe have undead everywhere. The mine has collapsed. nnSad times, indeed.nnWhat can <<1>> get you that would help you forget your sorrows?
For anyone who forges steel, dangerous times can be good times.nnHopefully, every blade I make finds a home... in an undead skull.
I don't care where they post me, as long as I get to kill undead.nnWhenever I'm protecting the people of Glenumbra, I'm content.
Folks in Crosswych trust us with their lives. nnMy job would be a lot easier if the things I killed stayed dead.
Even the horses are uneasy when they're caught between the living and the undead.nnSo, what can I do for you today?

I can't stay still, not while the undead are attacking. nnThe undead keep coming from the mine and the barrows. nnThey just keep coming....nnRunning helps clear my mind. It's better than sitting around and waiting to die.
Blackhand Cultists hide in the mines. nnI could take them on all by myself! I'm not afraid of them!nnIt's the undead that worry me. I'm powerless against them.
We're going into the mines again. They say we're insane. nnI say it's crazy to let a few undead stop us from going into a highly profitable mine.

The only place I feel safe right now is outside these buildings. Outside! Not inside!nnAfter all, what if I go inside and there's undead lurking in there? No! Never again!nnAt least out here, I can see them coming for me.
With all the undead nearby, I wonder whether I'd be better off moving somewhere safer... somewhere like Crosswych. nnThis is such a small town. How are we going to survive?
Helping people leave Crosswych is disheartening. nnThey always leave for the same reason. They want to live somewhere safer.nnCrosswych was more prosperous before the mine was filled with undead.
I became a guard because I wanted some action. nnLooks like I found it.
My family has lived in Crosswych for many years. I've never seen such horrible things.nnWhat brought the undead here? We have to do something. We have to save people from these horrors!
We have to guard against whatever comes out of the mines... and whatever rises from the burial mounds beyond the wall.nnI'm not really worried about the mines.
Crosswych has enough dangers outside our village. We don't need you making more trouble here.nnI've got my eye on you.
<The resonance chamber emits a low hum.>
<The resonance chamber emits a flat hum.>
<The resonance chamber emits a high-pitched hum.>
I'll have to return to Wayrest soon. nnThere's no library here. Being surrounded by books just makes me feel safer.nnI know one thing for certain: I won't be going anywhere near the Dwynnarth Ruins.
The damned undead are everywhere. This is as close as I can get to the mine.nnI heard the miners calling for help, but now they're silent. We have to get the survivors out of there!
You can't get both parts of the talisman. nnYou won't! You never will!
Al'kari is pleased to meet you. This one has great respect for one who travels the roads in such times.
Werewolves from the south, undead in the mine, and Zenithar knows what else in Stormhaven.nnWe've got a lot to watch out for, I'll tell you that.
Welcome to the Phidian Menagerie, Optimate.
Greetings, Optimate, and welcome to the Phidian Menagerie.
I don't know how Ormax will be able to pay us. He's already paying for all the wardens guarding us.
Chopping wood is what I do.
To hear Ormax talk, we're a bunch of lazy sods who haven't done a day's work in our lives. nnI'd like to see him out here, breaking his back.
Don't listen to Pierre. He does nothing but complain.
When I was a child, I dreamed about being a knight. Now late at night, I dream of being a child.
Where's my help, you might ask? Seems they all took sick - sick of dealing with spriggans, if you want my take.
My job is standing guard against the spriggans. nnIt's my chance to chop wood, if you take my meaning.
Ormax pays me well. If he didn't, I'd be back on the docks, where the real excitement is.
No need to fear, traveler. Warden Phiencel is ready for any threat!
I hope you're here to help us retake the tower.
I hope you're here to help. After we light that signal fire, we'll need to get back to Camlorn.
I'm tired of being stuck here. I want to retake that tower. nnI want to drive their army back into the sea!
Are you here to help us fight those Altmer dogs?
Please! Please! You must help us!
Greetings, <<1>>. It's a shame we couldn't meet under better circumstances.
Old Man Murrell sent me here to find an ancient relic: the Thornbane Cloak. I didn't expect a welcoming party.nnDon't worry. This isn't as bad as it looks. Lael's taking good care of me.
Hey! Let me go! I'm telling Mother!
Don't pick on me! Get your hands off!
A visitor? How peculiar.rnrnMy studies are not often interrupted. I trust you have good cause for this... visit?
We fought off the undead in the mine for months, but lately they are much bolder. With so many injured, I'm short on the ingredients for my remedies.nnStill, I do what I can for these poor souls.
My arm... I need help....nnIf Didier can't heal me, I'll never work again. Who will feed my family then?
This greeting does not exist in the WoW version of the character.
Hey, citizen! You look like a stout one. We guards are spread a little thin out here, and I could use your help...
We must hurry, before the Stormwitch attacks the Orrery again.
The Wyrd strive to be in balance with nature. But that becomes difficult when nature is in tumult and turns against us.

By blade and shield, the Fighters Guild maintains order throughout Tamriel. nnWord of your actions against Angof's corruption is spreading far and wide. nnOur guild has ears everywhere. You've made quite a name for yourself.
Come, browse my wares. Are you looking for anything in particular?
We live in strange days, Optimate. It is wise to go armed.
Hello, I will begin you on the journey that is quest smoke testing. You fool!
I am unable to focus.... Orgnavar blocks my attempt to harmonize with the planet Xarxes.
I worry for Skyharker Vilmo. Ever since Suuniqwe went missing he became plagued with nightmares.
Born in slime,rnashore with time.rnrnIn Orgnavarrnone now does climb.
Our supplies are low, but you are welcome to browse what we have.
Honor and praise to you. I regret that you find us in such a trying hour.
Honor and praise to you. I regret that you must find us in such a trying hour.
It pains me to think that the undead that the ocean has awoken were once our companions, our friends... our lovers.
By Lorkhan's right eye, that stings! Ah, excuse my outburst, Optimate... even with the blessings of Phynaster, the healers have yet to find a way to make injuries less painful.
Pardon, but I am busy healing those who have returned from fighting the Maormer.rnrnIf you require a healer, speak to my assistant Solcalin.
My apologies for the inconvenience, but the library is closed until further notice.
The day is short, and I must verify each of the Imageries is being maintained to the highest standard.
My mother Shannae is not in her right mind at this moment. Please do not mind her.
The magicka sings down from the air. But so discordant! Is your head not full of static and shadow?
Perhaps another might answer your questions. I am awaiting an audience with the Kinlord.

With all the recent refugees coming from Camlorn, I'm afraid my stocks are running low. nnI might weave a blanket here or a tunic there, but making a profit can be quite daunting. nnIt's especially difficult when folks can't pay you much.
Harmonious day to you, Optimate. Please enjoy your time in contemplation of this Imago Serry.
Have you come to bask in the radiance of the Imagerie?
Harmonious day to you, Optimate. Please enjoy your time in contemplation of the Imagerie.
We'll never make it out of here with all the undead skulking about. I'm scared out of my mind!
The mine is filled with undead! We can't escape!nnThey're going to feast on us. We're next....
The Mages Guild is searching Glenumbra for interesting artifacts.nnIf you come across any ancient magical items, we may be interested in purchasing them from you.
Fivefold venerations, Numinous. It is pleasant to see a living face.
The Mages Guild is searching Glenumbra for interesting artifacts.nnIf you come across ancient magical items, we may be interested in purchasing them from you.
The Mages Guild is searching Glenumbra for interesting artifacts. If you come across ancient magical items we may be interested in purchasing them from you.

I didn't think anyone would come help.  So much has happened and I just don't know what to do.  We were just here for research and now three of my best friends... dead...  Would you be able to help me?
Blessed the Divines,  are the others alive?
The serries are but a shadow of the majesty of the Imagerie, yet they are all a part of the celebration of the perfect form of the Altmer.
Dead is dead, whether you're killed by a werewolf or some ruffian on the docks.nnBe careful.
You! You're not a mudcrab, are you? nnAre you one of those damned poachers wandering about and stealing my shells? nnYou seem a bit taller, but you won't fool me! I know you're up to no good.
This one's head... it just fell right off.
Tread safely, Optimate. The times are fierce, even in our gardens.
A shame they don't have voices to hear them squeal while they die...
Mother told us to go play... Would you like to play?
Hail to thee. Welcome to the Alinor Scrutinarium. What service do you require?
I will buy all of your junk!
PHEW!  Thought I'd never get out of there.  Thank you!
Welcome to RL_DungeonTest. Be careful in your exploring, things in here can kill you.
Another time would be preferable, Optimate.
Another time would be preferable, Optimate.
Strike hard, strike fast, and get out. That's how we do things.
I've learned my lesson.  I'll be staying away from the puppy from now on.
Corpses everywhere. Have the Pallid Devils no shame? No sense of propriety? No... tidiness?
I would recommend you tread elsewhere, Optimate. This is no place for the uninitiated.
We must starve and disarm the Maormer - a blow to morale is a lethal one.
The Battlereeve is waiting for my report.
I must get the soldiers back to the beach defenses.
Bask in the radiance of Mara, Optimate.
I got promoted to Warden. Can you believe it?
Hail to thee, Optimate! Take heed in these unsound times.
Mind not my form, Optimate. I am merely speaking through my familiar.
This is the fabled RL_DungeonTest.  Rumored home of the all powerful magical tome.
Behold the all powerful Important Mage.
Bask in the radiance of Mara, Optimate.
What? What will I do? What will become of me?
Please, leave me to my duties.
Bask in the radiance of Mara, Optimate.
All follow the path of the stars. It is an irresistable pull that moves us all.
Dawn breaks as you arrive, yet you eclipse the sun with your majesty. Will you not tarry a while?
May the umbra of Auri-El ever shade your path.
Anything you can imagine, I can create with but a thought. It only requires concentration and patience.
Blessings upon you and your family. How may I aid you?
If what you seek is hidden, you must simply find it. If what you seek is locked away, that's quite another matter....
So! The Numinous nuisance has found a way to peer inside of orbiting Orgnavar! By accident, presumably.
May the blessings of Mara be upon you, Optimate.
I envy your ignorance. Could you know what horrors stir outside the... no. It must not be true!
With Suuniqwe gone I am responsible for maintaining the Orrery. A burden I may not be fit to carry.

Be on your guard if you value your life here, citizen. There is evil about and it has almost overwhelmed us all. My men and I are doing our best to hold them back, but I'm afraid we are about to lose this fight.
I'll never be able to get my work done under these conditions!
You have found one of Commander Lafavre's soldiers. He didn't make it.
You have found one of Commander Lafavre's soldiers. He didn't make it.
You have found one of Commander Lafavre's soldiers. He didn't make it.
You have found one of Commander Lafavre's soldiers. He didn't make it.

This is our chance. The Baron thinks himself safe in his own keep, and that he can continue his crimes from here with impunity. Let us show him and all who think the same that stone walls and guards are no obstacle to the Dark Brotherhood.
Another time would be preferable, Optimate.
Can you not see that we are under siege here?
Forgive me, Numinous, but surely you have more pressing needs than the company of one such as I.
A Maormer came... I was caught unawares.... rnrnNenwe assigned me to guard this trail against the invaders. It would seem I have failed in my duty.
Howdy folks. I'm the questor NPC
You seem surprised to see an obvious Ouster in a Kinhouse!
The lines of your face present a most symmetrical aspect, Optimate. Truly you are one blessed by Mara!
Ach, my wounds are aflame with pain! I will never underestimate a Kirin again.
Yes, it's me - the Ouster Sky-Mage. It seems things are even worse in Isque than in Varyllis.
I greet you on behalf of the Syldarim Kinship.
I Rez every 15 seconds....suck it up and wait!
Well met, Optimate. Your appearance is timely - and a touch careworn. Have you been fighting?
I'm an Ouster - you really should pretend not to see me, Optimate. But you're not quite like the others, are you?
I Rez every 15 seconds....suck it up and wait!

Ah, the Optimate! Still running others' errands? Then carry the embryo of Auri-El up this ramp to the Throne Tower. Begin the ritual by placing Auri-El upon the cradle. Then use the Enkindle Rods to return it to the sky. I will speed you on your way.
Guard me well, Optimate. I will move as quickly as I can.
Greetings, Optimate. I cannot deviate from my patrols, for our lands are not suitably safe at the moment.
Vigilance, Optimate -- vigilance at all times.
May the constellations watch over you, Optimate.
May the constellations watch over you, Optimate.
The Maormer will overwhelm the Orrery any day now. Soldiers are bred to throw their lives away on the battlefield, not Skyharkers.
May the constellations watch over you, Optimate.
Hail to thee, Optimate. I pray that your visit to our Kinship will be impeccably harmonious.
Hail to thee, Optimate. I pray that your visit to our Kinship will be impeccably harmonious.
I feel sadness, Numinous, for I seem to have lost my mount. I fear the Maormer have found him, and even now sup upon his sturdy haunches.
Strong and steady, just as Master Sinderon always says.
By the all-seeing eyes of Xarxes, how can this be? The rectilinear quotient of this pathway is two-fifths of a degree off!
I am disgraced, Optimate! The Masters have rejected my entreaty for an apprenticeship at the Anquillius Forge. Decades of study, and all for naught!
Oh joy. Another Numinous, sent by the great Queen Ayarynne to save us all from the terrible Maormer invaders. You should go, before I faint from excitement.
Fair greetings to you! I find myself a bit fatigued at the moment, but I can say with certainty I shall be feeling better in a moment.
May the divines watch over you, Optimate.
The Serpent has been more aggressive than usual ever since Auri-El fell.
Take caution, Optimate. These are not safe times.
May the constellations keep your path safe, Optimate.
Be watchful if you venture into the Stonewake, Optimate.
My own court conspires against me. Whispers of "that Redguard witch" fly through the servants' quarters. nnMy own Knights of the Flame treat me with suspicion. Dark times indeed.

I've heard rumors of Daedric cultists to the south, ships crashing on the shore, slavers on the coast, and scamps overrunning my subjects' farms.nnForgive me if I don't have time to speak with you right now.
A life without death would best be spent with love and beauty.rnrnPerhaps a prayer or two to Mara will do you good.
An Optimate I am but a Numinous I am not. rnrnI have earned my place in the Isquer Kinhouse.
The Bretons here are all as mad as Sep!nnI lose sleep at night worrying about what they might do.

I don't know you, but you have to listen. You've got to help. They're going to execute me. I didn't do anything! I'm innocent!nnMy husband is missing, and Koeglin Village has gone insane! If only Maelys was here....
<You've found the body of Duchess Lakana. A huge sword cut runs from her neck to her sternum.>nn<After suffering such a blow, she would have died quickly.>
An Optimate I am but a Numinous I am not. rnrnI have earned my place in the Isquer Kinhouse.
If I were affected by the Planemeld as you are, I would be able to better serve the Kinlord.
Unless you've got business with these farms, you should run to the main road... and keep running.
Unholy enchantment binds Farmer Vanne to a makeshift Daedric altar. nnPeering through the haze, you can see his unconscious form shows signs of rough treatment.
Have I really awakened? Is the nightmare over?nnI've seen such horrors, such terrible things  was it you who woke me?
You found Inwold, and someone from the Glenmoril Coven attacked you? If they're involved here, things are worse than I feared.

You must be <<1>>. Duchess Lakana bade me to wait for you.nnShe went to her quarters some time ago alongside Sir Hughes. I know not what it's about, but she asked me to direct you there. nnHer quarters are around the other side of the main building.

Yours is a face I do not recognize.nnI can only assume you've recently arrived in Shornhelm. I should warn you to watch your step, lest you find yourself in Montclair's district to the north. The people there are not as kind as we are.
We were ambushed. Montclair's forces poured out of the canyons from all sides.
I'm so hungry, I'm starting to see things. Who's there? nnYou'd best leave this place. There's no hope! We're all doomed!
The Fighters Guild was good enough to let us set up shop in here. Since then, business has been wonderful!
<This body has been stabbed repeatedly by multiple blades. Judging by lacerations on the victim's hands and arms, he was attempting to defend himself.>
By the Divines! We've been so busy with affairs in the city that we haven't seen what's going on out here.
<This victim's back was slashed open from the shoulder to the waist. The wound appears to have been made by a two-handed axe.>
<<1>> of House Tamrith actually cares about us, unlike the nobles who parade around as our "saviors."
I lead all who guard Pariah Abbey, under Durak the Wise. What brings you here?

Please, help us m'lord! We've managed to get away from the slave pits to the north, but so many off us still are held captive under Montclair's bloodfiends. The noble houses must know of this cruelty.
Please, don't let them take me away again...
She cannot really be dead, can she?nnWhat am I to do now? Go back to Sentinel I guess.nnI cannot believe this has happened.

Dark times are upon us, friend. My family struggles to survive, while our beloved nobles bicker ceaselessly about the most meaningless things.nnI tell you, just the thought of it makes my stomach want to heave.

Congratulations! I haven't been this impressed in decades. You've been such good sports, you know, and you can make your way out of my little game through the portal stone up on the dias there. Be sure to collect your prize!
Please, don't hurt me! I only swore allegiance to Montclair because he held my family hostage. It was the only way I could save them!
I have my eyes and ears all over Stormhaven, little happens here without my knowing.
I have eyes and ears all over Stormhaven. Little happens here without my knowing.
With all the problems in Alcaire, I worry about my safety in the keep.
I fear there might be a conspiracy against Duke Nathaniel. nnI'm an honest man, but I worry about being implicated even more. Someone's going to accuse me of being a part of this.
Danger on the roads! Riots in the streets! nnAt least Alcaire Keep is still safe.nnIt is, isn't it?
Something's not right. Something must be done.
I am the proud leader of the Knights of the Flame, the sworn protectors of Alcaire.nnWe'll eliminate any threat to Duke Nathaniel, no matter what it takes.
Stendarr's Mercy! If you won't save us, at least put us out of our misery!
I've seen to the captives. You've done good work here.nnTime will tell if <<1>> can protect them from Lord Montclair  and themselves. With the arrival of <<2>>, I'm unsure how to proceed.
Long after mortals leave this world, I will still be here, serving my Lady Meridia's shrine.nnAlas! I cannot do battle with those who would corrupt it.
Who are you? Didn't I see you lurking about on the docks the other day? nnYou're up to no good, I bet.
There are thieves everywhere these days. Everyone wants to steal from my shop.nnState your business, and keep your hands off my wares. We wouldn't want you to lose a hand.
Do you have any idea how many coven witches, Aldmeri spies, and slavers are prowling around our town? We're surrounded!

They're out to get us, you know. These people... even my own brother wouldn't help me!nnAs soon as I can, I'm going to Wayrest, where I can start over. nnNo one will judge me, accusing me of evil things. I only wish my Inwold was with me....
We all train hard to impress Master Ahtah, yet I doubt I will ever be as skilled with a blade as he is.
The tension is thick around here. I'm not used to Bretons and Redguards at odds. Aren't we supposed to be allies?

I already feel my life slipping away.nnThe bonds of this barrier constrict more with each passing second. With each breath, I draw closer to death.nnI know not who you are, but you must find out what they're doing to us. Find out who they are!
I'm sorry. We're not ready for business yet.
Arkay watch over you, my child. How can I help you?
We're trying our best to get some fortifications in place, but we're short on supplies and manpower.
Flesh is so soft, so easily shredded. I can still feel the rake of their claws.nnWhy did my brother ignore my warnings? Does he feel the same pain I do?
Please don't hurt me anymore! What do you want?
I never thought I'd see so many wounded and dying after the war. I suppose there's always suffering somewhere.
My wounds are graver than I thought. I might not last through the night.nnCome closer. We must plan what to do next.
So you've come. I wasn't sure if the worries of this region were a priority to the Numinous.
When Captain Janeve saw me, she growled.nnI thought she was going to attack me!
The body is frozen solid. The mage's eyes stare back as if still filled with life.

Testing the random text to ensure that the text does not appear cut off, missing, or with strange text characters. Now I am just going on and on because I'm trying to fill  in more text in the greeting window.

Bravo! Bravo! You've done it!nnYou've exceeded my expectations and done it with very little training. I knew I was right about you! nnOf course, I've thought I was right about a dozen others before you, but we'll ignore that for now.
This is Hammerdeath Arena. Did you come here to wager ... or fight?
Huh? Who are you? And who am I? Leave me alone and let me drink in peace.
Greetings! If you find treasure in the Crypt of Hearts, feel free to come by afterwards and sell to me! I'll offer a fair price and save you the trouble of hauling it all to the nearest town.
Sister Agnes. How delightful to see you. I trust you bring us a worthy sacrifice?
What can I do for you, traveler? Are you looking for someone?

One fights for the fame and glory of being heralded as the savior of Shornhelm, recklessly throwing her soldiers' lives away. The other still so bitter over betrayal that revenge clouds his every thought, blinding him.nnThis city will indeed fall.

Constable Sal has agreed to let us stay at the inn free of charge... at least until we can retake our farm. nnI think he feels bad about the way the village treated me.nnThank you so much for all you've done, <<1>>.

Don't worry about the farm. It's just a place. We can build another one.nnWhat's important is that you saved me and my wife. As long as we're together, we can weather anything.nnThank you so much. May the Eight watch over you.
There's nothing like a good excavation! I do hope that the, ah, more enterprising adventurers headed into the Crypt don't run off with priceless magical relics, though.
Welcome to Pariah Abbey. We are the Spirit Wardens. All are welcome here.
Attack today. Tomorrow, we may die.
Hoarfrost Downs used to be a grand little town. Now look at it! Nothing's been the same since Ranser's War.
My guards are over worked and my resources are running thin trying to put down all of the squabbles in Alcaire.
This one is called Fahjiri. Fahjiri was trapped, and you ended the nightmare. Fahjiri is overjoyed!

Be wary. Brigands gather near the roads like carrion birds. We don't have many able-bodied defenders here. Even the ones who can wield a sword balk at defending their home, my husband included. nnHe's more concerned about the wailing spirits.
Fahjiri is miserable. Durak is lost, and is is all Fahjiri's fault!
Durak's eyes are open as he stares into nothingness.

The trials test us in many ways, <<1>>.nnOnly those with the traits of the Raven will rise. You must show compassion, wisdom, strength, and honor -- even in the most desperate of times.nnThose are the traits of the Raven.
The vampire fills your mind with lies... lies! Tricks and deceit, how else... how else would he outlive us all... the Council of Ranser...

You must be the nobles' hand. It's a pleasure. I wish we could have met under more civilized terms.nnI believe you and I share the same purpose, although you may not know it yet. Perhaps we can help each other.
You are in a deep slumber.
Help me! You must save Ahtah's Book of Circles. I am too weak....

S'rashi welcomes you on behalf of The Even Hand. As a neutral organization, we deal in information, legal and otherwise. This one would be a useful friend.nnS'rashi has heard of your exploits. If you're looking for work, S'rashi could use a favor.
No one gets in without an invitation. Don't have one, do you?
Move along, vagabond. Unless you've got an invitation?nnDidn't think so.
If the count gets mad at you .nnSo watch it.
Who did you say gave you a letter of introduction? S'Rashi?nnOh, that's wonderful! Our servants refuse to play games anymore. I do so miss our games together.nnPerhaps you and I can play a game now!

I apologize for my wife's delay in bringing your arrival to my attention. She has been preoccupied of late, but as you know, one must of course allow a woman her... fancies.rnrnSo, S'Rashi sent you. What business brings you to my palatial retreat?
<I have been waiting for you. Do not be alarmed. This is how I speak... within your mind.>

The wine cellar is off-limits. In addition to rare vintages, it holds a great many of the Count's treasures.rnrnConsider this a warning. The cellar is patrolled at all times, and trespassers are killed on sight.rnrnEnjoy the rest of your visit.
It is good to finally be back among friends.
<I have been waiting for you. Do not be alarmed. This is how I speak... within your mind.>
Be wary. We don't know what we're up against.
The duchess died by my hand. My crime is unforgivable, and I accept full responsibility.nnDo what must be done.
Yes, what is it? If you don't have business with the treasurer, I would suggest you be on your way.
If you seek to scale the Serrated Crests, be wary of the foul creatures inhabiting its halls.
Everyone has made sacrifices, whether to help others survive or to help their own survival.

We could not dissuade King Ranser from his prideful stand. I would not watch as my men were needlessly slaughtered.nnNow you know the truth of my betrayal. I can call upon Ranser's wraith, but you must defeat him to end this curse.
This Khajiit is in a deep sleep.
We must uphold the Daggerfall Covenant, no matter what the cost.nnWe must purge the unclean filth from all Covenant territories, starting with Stormhaven.

I once served the king and the Daggerfall Covenant. I was a general! I knew things. Important things. Secrets. That's why Azura chose me.nnShe talks to me. In my head. Azura will save <<1>>. She will!
I never thought it would come to this. A civil war has begun in Rivenspire. Finn and I are all that's left of Shornhelm's militia.nnWe never had a chance.
First the war, and now this plague! nnCurse these undead monsters! Will we ever find peace in Rivenspire?

My friend, you're healthy now, but you never know when a bloodfiend may strike. One bite dooms you to a slow, painful death... unless you have one of my curatives! nnDespite what authorities may have you believe, my salubrious remedies are authentic!
I couldn't stop myself. He killed my Charlotte with his lies!
Who are you? Did Moric send you to end my misery?
We protect the walls of Pariah Abbey against those who bear us ill intent. None enter or exit unless we allow it.
Yes? Please do not waste my time. What is it?
Yes? Welcome to our library. Is there something I can help you with?

Countess Tamrith returns here for her father's funeral, and what does House Montclair do? They attack the upper city!nnThe bastards killed more Shornhelm Guards and civilians than I care to think about. It's like Ranser's War all over again!
<<1>> has seen more than its share of strife. Has there ever been a time when the city wasn't under siege?nnI often sense what is unseen. I can hear their cries.
How did you get in here? Did Lord Montclair send you?nnI'm doing the best I can with his prisoners. Tell him that!
Our end is at hand. What greater glory than to charge into battle one final time? rnrnWe must take fight to these lithesome Ogres.
Something must be done about Godrun, and soon.
We've saved this town from Imperial tyranny.nnWe've brought the Aldmeri Dominion one step closer to victory!nnNow we must slay the murderer leading the Imperials. <<1>> must die!
Everyone's dead.nnBy the Divines, what has Montclair done?
I almost pity Cinas and his silly Green Pact.
I would rather stand guard with a Maormer or a Wood Orc than this Khajiit.
There's nothing like the spectacle of bloodsports and the company of a good woman or two.nnI'm still searching for a way to indulge in both at once.
Please don't talk to me. You'll upset him.nnMy life gets worse when he's upset.
Why would a great one such as yourself bother to speak with a lowly slave like me?

Begone, accursed undead! I  uh, you're not a walking corpse. nnPlease, traveler. The souls of Crestshade's dead are caught in the Gray Maybe. You must rally them if we're ever to pass on to our well-deserved rest.
These creatures are fascinating. Wouldn't you agree?
I must be dreaming. I'm standing outside the arena with my son, and we're free. You did this?
I didn't like being with that creepy old man. nnI'm glad to be back with my mother.
The war with the Empire has come to Southpoint.nnWe've recently taken the town back from the Imperials, but the battle rages on... and the casualties continue.
Numinous! You must help me. Death holds no rest. I am haunted by memories that should be long forgotten.
This is maddening. Volenfell might be the discovery of a lifetime, but we've been plagued by disaster after disaster since we started this excavation.
The portal to the Dreamworld crackles before you.
This is a great day for Stormhaven.
We will not let anyone steal the Dream Shard again.
The Omen has been slain. Thank the Divines!
You helped us keep our pact with Azura. Thank you.
Imagine! Walking into our town and just burning everything!nnHow dare the Imperials think they can hurt us without retaliation!
The portal to the Dreamworld awaits you, traveler.
You shouldn't be here.  This is your only warning, stranger.
I'm so close to a breakthrough I can taste it! Soon, we will be able to crack the secrets of the Dwemer constructs, and even build them ourselves! Is that not amazing?
This dream is the same every night, but you... you've never appeared in my dreams before....
They come to Alcaire, not as friends, but as foes.nnThey camp at our doorstep. They claim diplomacy, but they lie.nnThe Covenant is a lie. Our dreams tell it true.

She brought them here: Lakana the Faithless. Lakana the Sorceress!nnAlcaire suffers as long as she lives. I honored her once, but now she brings misery and death.nnNo! What am I saying? Yet these nightmares began with her. She caused this madness!
Please, you must help. nnThis nightmare never ends.
The Imperials aren't our only concern. Undead are roaming about the Bonebarrow, our ancestral burial site!
I'm afraid Alard doesn't like me conversing with strangers. If you have business with our house, you should speak with him.
Aha! The thief!nnHand over the Akaviri poison! Give me everything else you stole from the barrow!nnBe quick about it. Don't compound your theft with insolence!
This place is dangerous.nnI'm sorry. I've got a bad habit of stating the obvious. nnYou should be careful.
We're not coming any closer to that cursed mountain than this. nnIf you want to leave before you get killed, let me know!
Oi! Glad to see a face that isn't some bloody spider construct or some risen grave robber! I appreciate the rescue, friend.
I heard the fighting just now. I guess you gave those undead bastards what for! Well done! I could've handled 'em, but one of them got a lucky hit on my leg, you know how it goes.
Is it over? I've been trapped in here for far too long. I just want to go home!
A deep, threatening creak rumbles up from within the Swamp Cypress.
Coming through the Man-Grove is not the friendliest path to Elden Root.
In my day, I might have been able to help defend <<1>>, but it's getting harder to lift a pick, let alone a sword.
Sir Edmund sent for me, and I came as soon as I could. nnSir Hughes does not plead for clemency, yet he says his mind was not his own?

Most people don't appreciate the importance of my craft. I provide comfort in times of woe. I create a final resting place for loved ones. nnIf only I could do something to aid the restless spirits about the Downs. Their cries are most unsettling.
I will honor the memory of my former master by fighting valiantly alongside the Oldgate mages.
Damned wolves! I was just trying to earn a living by digging in these parts.nnWhy did that beast have to bite me?
Death is ... not what I'd expected.
Why won't this stupid ache in my head go away? Been going on for days now and it just keeps getting worse. You aren't helping either, being in my face like you are!
My stomach... it won't stop hurting. Why does it hurt? I feel like I'm falling apart.
Whaddaya want? Out of my face, stranger!
This place is damned. Only way to try and forget that fact is to let loose in a little bit of drink I say!
The prey is worthy to speak to this one.
I'm continuing my studies, thanks to you. My mind is clearer now, but there are still things I can't remember. nnPerhaps it's better this way.
My nephew and I owe your our freedom. We won't forget.
Thank you for helping me regain my memory.
