I don't suppose you have time to help a Priest of Arkay?
What...happened? How did I get here? My head aches!
I like this place! Mister Ahtah and Mister Durak are nice.rnrnI want to be a Spirit Warden when I grow up!

Verandis put me in charge. I'm keeping this area safe from the creatures wandering the tunnels.nnCan't say it's been easy, but the Ravenwatch Keeper's magic is incredible. Some of the things he can do... let's just say they've made my life easier.
Shadowhiskers is just resting. He is a Master Thief. These walls could not hold him if he wasn't resting.
Greetings. Welcome to Elden Root. I am pleased to have you with us.
I'll have the money on Tirdas! Wait. Who are you?
Some of my cattle have disappeared. I know that weasel Arniel is responsible, but he won't admit it.nnIf I don't get my cows back, I'll take matters into my own hands.
You tread a dangerous path. Step lightly.
You want something? Talk to Cutter.
I don't think you belong here.

You know. It's actually ironic. Iprobably the most unworthy man in all the kingdomwound up being High King. It makes the entire Covenant look like some kind of circus. nnYes, it's better that someone else takes the throne. I accept my fate.
I'm sorry. I just don't feel much like talking, now that the forest is coming alive.
I'm a Knight of the Flame. We're sworn to protect Alcaire.
I don't know if we can trust these Orcs, but it seems like we have no choice.nnAt this point, we have to find a way to work together.
Would you like to go up or down?
First my land, and now my pride!nnDo those fools in Wayrest think they can strip us of everything we own?
The floor broke apart and you are actually falling to the room below.  Let me help you along your way...
I don't understand where all my feathers went. They were here a moment ago.
You fool, get out of the street! Do you want to anger the brushstrokes?
She promised she'd be here after the vivisection. What's taking her so long?
Have you seen my coat? It's oh so cold here, and... oh! You aren't my Thomas.
Don't you dare touch my chickens.
It's you... you're the serpent thing. They told me about you! Stay away!
My arms won't move. How am I to fight a proper duel without my arms?
You should know better than to be wandering around while the magpies are out.
I'm a wolf! I'm a wolf! Don't pet me. You'll make it all fall out.
I miss the bunnies. Don't you?
My Senche-Tiger and I were ambushed by bravos - they had an Imperial look about them. My cat drew them off, but hasn't returned. Have you seen him?
You have done much to displease my mistress, yet she is not without mercy.nnCome. Listen to my words.

We meet again, mortal, for we have met before, whether you know it or not.nnWhen you mutter in your sleep, you speak to me. When you awaken wet with sweat, you've just left my house. I savor your nightmares.

Well done, <<1>>.nnFinally! I'm finally standing inside the Plane Merge. It's a strange feeling, as if it were long ago, before this curse flowed through my veins.nnBeing so close to life and death inside this realm... it affects us all differently.
Isn't she wonderful? So elegant. So graceful.nnThis is what love feels like, isn't it? A million butterflies in my chest, ready to burst at any moment. nnMaybe it could have been what I ate....

Our recent battles gave us reasons to research our enemies... and the curse that runs through them: vampirism.nnMost think them horrible creatures, but I believe we judge too quickly. The ones who can control their powers are really a lot like us....

I wish Marcach would be still for a moment. These cuts won't bind themselves. He'll need to be strong when the Horsemen of Rivenspire are helping the Lion Guard.nnAnd yes, we're willing to help them at Oldgate, though we have problems of our own.
No! They'll get me, just like they got my mother and father! nnPlease, help me! I don't like coming here. Stop her. Please, stop Jenny!
Even when the world falls apart, people still need candles and string. nnWhat can I help you with today, traveler?
The Horsemen of Rivenspire will do what we can to help the Magis Order.nnWe'll do what we can here at Oldgate, although we still have problems of our own.
Those damn Dorell guards better stay on their side of the city.
The goblins and witches have not gotten along in the past.
It's madness out here.nnWe're one of the strongest regiments in Tamriel.  How it came to this, we'll never know.
We got the order to march out of Shornhelm. That was strange enough.  nnThen we were attacked here on the plain by the Eight knows what....
This far from Oldgate, and three score of us routed. It doesn't make sense.  nnNothing I've seen out here makes sense.nnThose were no common soldiers.
It's good to see you again, <<1>>.nnComing here wasn't the greatest idea I've ever had, that's for sure. nnI've failed, and now my Leah will have to live her life without me.
Godrun caught me escaping. Now this is where I shall die.
Thank you for rescuing me, but now I am a bit worse for wear.

The Fellwatch think of themselves as heirs to the throne. Their chosen regent depends on the day of the week.nnStranger, I know you're here to stop them, but at this point, I'm not sure whether to help or hinder you. Maybe I should just thank you.

I've found the corpse of Treethane Orthendor's pet Senche-Tiger, Helethrun.rnrnHe's still bleeding from several gashes. The edges of the wounds are too clean for claws or teeth - he was attacked by edged weapons.
I have the upmost respect for Godrun but I do not know how much longer our battalion will hold out under his command.
Not all Bosmer in Leaftower are traitors. There are loyalists. They need our help to throw off the Imperial yoke!
I haven't got time to talk, stranger. I've got work to do, and not enough time to do it.
Tivel of Drivel is my name. My friends call me Tiv. You should follow my attitude, stranger. What is my attitude, you ask?nnI say what I want and I get what I want.
Does this day seem endless to you? I feel like I've been waiting all day.
This is a military camp, <<1>>. If you were not sent here on business, I have much to do.

While the duchess attempts diplomacy, the Gripdjur corsairs burn and pillage their way across our coasts. War is inevitable, but until it starts, our hands are tied.nnI fear the people will have lost their faith by then.
I'm glad to be back in my rightful home again, and Wayrest's stipend is a fine compensation for all the trouble I've had to endure.
We finally have some peace. I was beginning to think I'd have to do something about that man.

fifteen  sixteen  seventeen  seve-nnWhat? Now look what you've done, silly child. You've made me lose count of our taxes.nnTaxes are important. They give us something to count. Now run off and play. One, two, three, four .
Don't interrupt me; I'm counting the stairs.
Never worked a farm before. Can't say I like it much.

Since Ranser's demise, this city has never truly flourished. nnWars reduce it to ashes, bringing new rulers with empty promises to restore Shornhelm's former glory.nnIt is all for naught. This city is cursed and will remain in ruins.
This is none of your concern, stranger.
Every man has a right to earn his living. It's a shame some people don't see that.
There's a bit of unrest around Leaftower. I'm sure it will settle down soon.
I killed them, and I'll kill you!

It's damn cold in here. And who makes flames that give no heat?nnYou! You can see me? Thank the Eight! Someone has cast a horrible invisibility curse upon me. nnSure it has its benefits here and there, but it's rather been dull for the most part.
Let's hurry. I feel as if something is trying to keep me here.
Elin's been so upset lately. I wish we could do something about it, but there are too many parties to attend. I'd hate to miss any!

My wife ran into Montclair's forces on the road near the Hinault's farm. She managed to make it home, but she's been ill ever since. nnNothing seems to help. I just pray this isn't that blood-curse we've been hearing about.
Please, don't hurt her! She was showing signs of turning. I needed to get her out of the city as quickly as possible.
The body shows an indication of a recent struggle, but no longer holds signs of life.
I... I don't feel so well. Tildus needs to get away... needs to go far far away.

If you seek the Falon family, they've abandoned their home. Scarlette sent us ahead to keep an eye out, but they had already evacuated by the time we arrived. We've found tracks leading to the west gate. I'd check that way.
My daughter's still out there. I know she's alive. Those Nord dogs couldn't lay a finger on her.

We cannot take two steps in this part of the forest without running into more Imperial soldiery.nnLuckily I have managed to survive thus far in the forest, thanks to these Bosmer and their... really quite appealing leader, <<1>> as well.
Haven Trace is no longer safe for the casual traveler. Not that it was ever very safe to begin with - but now it's just plain dangerous!

I had to lie to him to slip away... I hope one day he will forgive me. If I had told him the truth he would not have allowed me to leave, putting himself in danger. He will live on now however. That is what matters to me the most.
No matter what the hardship, we survive. That is the Orcish way.
I don't know if we can trust these Orcs, but it seems we have no choice.
I'm sorry, but this room is reserved.
I'm a simple woman. I spin. I tend my pigs. I poke any Nords who come too close with a pitchfork.nnIt's a good life.
Thorkan and Normar keep talking about unity, but what are they actually doing about it?
Thorkan and Normar keep talking about unity, but what are they actually doing about it?
All I ask is rain and sun for my crops. nnIf any blight should come, it should fall on those Nords.
So lonely in these halls. I do ever so wonder if I would find someone to keep me... company.
You can't travel the roads without fearing for your life. You can't tend your fields or herd your goats without a Nord trying to cut you down.nnWhen will Northpoint act?
Mor! nnCalm down now! nnDon't worry, these men won't hurt you!
The duchess sits in her castle serving Nord officers candied pears.nnMeanwhile, the Nord soldiers spill our blood in the fields.nnWhere are the troops? Why won't they do something?
You can barely get from the town to the farms without risking your life. nnI'm sure the duchess has her reasons for negotiating with those wretches, but I'd rather see them struck down.

My, my, this is rather fascinating. nnThe prey walks into the lion's den with no second thoughts. It would seem my pretty Scarlette has a new puppet for her errands. I rather did hope she would show her lovely face.
The Aldmeri Dominion awaits the arrival of our reinforcements.nnOnce they are here, the Empire will be reminded why victory against the Dominion is preposterous.
So the puppet arrives with no signs of the puppeteer.nnDoes Scarlette intend to act as if her life before Verandis turned her was non-existent? As if she should not be responsible for her actions?
The Imperials are driven out, fled to their palisade, but many are missing. Even I, Ra'Vardo, have heard rumors that the Treethane's daughter, Farah, searches for her parents.
Something must be done about Godrun, and soon.

Aha! You're another infiltrator, aren't you? Ri'Zama is glad to see you.nnThis one has a plan to cause some trouble inside the palisade.nnPerhaps this will help in your endeavors? This one sincerely hopes so.
I am going back to Hammerfell and I am going to build a forge just like this one.nnImagine how much business I can do. I could have three smiths working around the clock!

So the puppet arrives, but with no signs of the master? Does Scarlette intend to act as if her life before that bastard Verandis turned her was non-existant? As if she should not be responsbile for her actions?
Something must be done about Godrun, and soon.
Be cautious where you tread. The miasmata of Cold Harbor have begun to seep down from Gil-Var-Delle.
What we became, what we did ... I couldn't stand it. I ran. I tried to stop them, but they were too strong. nnHelp me end this nightmare.
You look into the mirror seeking answers, but there are no answers here for you. nnI am here for the countess and the countess alone. You would be wise to be on your way.
The prey is worthy to speak to this one. What shall I call you, kine-creature?
I want to protect Count Hosni, but I'm too old. Too old.
Once could have saved the Count from the Omen. But now I'm so old. I can barely lift my pike.
My teeth are falling out. My skin is rotting. I am moments from death. I cannot help anyone.
If only I was younger faster. I can barely move. I've lived to be a toothless dog.

I am tasked with the research of magic for Lord Fahara'jad, and as such my time is quite valuable. I am pleased if you are here to help me, but I would ask that you disrupt my work as little as you can manage, unless you have great need.
Hail and homage! I am here to remind you what you learned in Studium Vale.
Constancy and courage, Optimate! I am here to remind you what you learned in Alinor.

The harpies are leaving their aeries to attack us. We can't gather grain or tend our horses in safety. Last week, they killed my brother.nnI want to make our village safe from those scavenging hags. I have an idea, but the elders won't listen to me.

So this is the source of all of our troubles, eh? Our salvation lies somewhere in the <<1>>. I hope that soon, we'll all walk out of this and continue on as if today was any other day.nnI know better, though. After all, this is war.

We shouldn't be here. This war isn't ours to fight. I'm starting to wonder about Lady Eselde's decisions. She listens to fools from the Ravenwatch, and she actually believes them!nnMeanwhile, House Tamrith is forced to deal with House Dorell's men.
The healer says I might not be able to ride again.nnHerd Mother, hear my pleas! Knit my wounds and keep my family safe!
I've heard so many good things about you, my friend.nnSit down. Have some wine with me. Let's chat a bit about this unfortunate situation with the Nords.
I'm relieved that we see eye to eye.nnI knew you were a person of both bravery and reason. Now maybe we can work together on this issue.
Yes? Tell me, what do you want? I'm a busy man, you know.
You're not part of the Ravenwatch. You're not wearing the heraldry of Dorrell or Tamrith.nnYou know, I'd love to hear why you're up here, but first, I'm going to ask a favor of you.
Can't chop anything when we haven't got the tools, eh?
Now that we have these tools, Ormax will want us to work three times faster.
I'd enjoy this break a lot more if we weren't surrounded by spriggans!
This is the only rest I expect to get now that my wife and I have the baby. The little one keeps us up all night with its wailing.
They say the Divines reward those who wait. I really wish my reward wasn't hard work.
I enjoyed taking it easy, but there's nothing like an honest day's work.
What is it? Can't you see I'm speaking with my wife?
Truth be told, I've been enjoying the break.
I'd rather work day and night than stand around doing nothing.
Blessings of Arkay upon you, friend.
Now that we're not busy chopping down trees, you can actually hear the birds singing.
If our tools don't show up soon, I'll have to move again. Ormax won't pay us when we're just standing around like this.
We're going to hear Ormax berating us all the way out here. After those tools show up, we'll have to work twice as hard to make up for the delay.
No time to talk. Must get back to work!
Well, this is very interesting. Our enemy becomes our ally. What a snake you've turned out to be!  nnWhat do you have for me?
Many good men and women died to get us here. nnWe won't let their sacrifices be in vain.
I came as fast as I could. Is my lady hurt? Any news about the Nords?

We've lost too many soldiers these past few days.nnThe death toll continues to rise, and we're on the wrong end of it. Only a handful of us actually made it this far. Even our scouting party in the Merge hasn't returned. nnWe're losing hope.

This fight has gone on far too long. The Ravenwatch's forces have been decimated, and we can barely hold on to what we've got left.nnThe Dark Council cannot win this fight! We need to penetrate that barrier!
The baron is grateful you've been so reasonable. He's retired upstairs, if you wish to speak with him.

Northpoint is a city of history... a city of wonders... a city that can withstand whatever troubles those terrible Nords inflict upon us.nnOnce this region  teemed with life. Now our people hide, fearing the Nords who harass our shores.

I've finally been granted my greatest wish.  How very strange. I can finally turn into the creature we sought to slay.nnThe cost was great. Everyone around me is gone. How I managed to live, I don't know. Why was I the only survivor?
War can be good for business, but not if I can't reach my market.nnI desperately want to make it to Shornhelm, but the guard refuses to let me through. They say it isn't safe!
Unless you're buying something from Lanbaar, I'd suggest you move along.
I'm tired of wasting my time here. I've got places to be. What do you want?
Sorry. My skills are reserved for the Shornhelm guard. Even if I'm not busy, I have be ready in case they need me.
Blessed Arkay, take these poor souls under your care.
This Imagerie is the pride of the Kinlord. Ponder its patterns, appreciate its artifice, and feel solace.
Are you here to help? Oh, this is a disaster....
Our mistress appears to have turned to stone. This is most peculiar.
Fancy a bit of fishing? We old fools have been fishing here longer than any of us can remember.nnThen again, most of us can't remember what we had for breakfast this morning. Aye, it's a good life.

This is as far as I go. I don't want to get caught up in a fight. If those monsters up on the crag attack the camp, I'm casting off and getting out!nnIf you need a ride back to Northpoint, and I'm still here, just come back and talk to me again.

It's like we're living inside a tale told around a campfire, and it's a dark tale, indeed!nnDriven from our home by vampires  forced to watch as friends and family become bloodfiends. And then there was that  that  abomination!
It is said that a book is good for the mind.rnrnI've had nothing but headaches.
Why do you disturb us? We're trying to restore the land!
I can no longer hear the song of the woods, yet I shall always carry its tune in my heart.
Good day. I'm sorry if I seem distracted. I've recently lost something very precious.
Beware! The spriggans have risen up for reasons unknown, and the woods are no longer safe.

I can't sleep. I keep thinking about those fiends. What's to stop them from following us and finishing what they started in Crestshade?nnAnd to top it all off, I was forced to leave my beloved wife behind when we fled.
Everyone wants something from the woodcarver today. Spears, tent poles, fire wood  how do they expect me to keep up this pace?
More and more folks are passing through Deleyn's Mill these days. Makes me wonder what's happening out there in the wilds.
I'm just taking a breather. I've been working out in the fields for too long. Between chopping down trees and running away from the spriggans, I'm exhausted.

Please, help us m'lord! We've managed to get away from the slave pits to the north, but so many off us still are held captive under Montclair's bloodfiends. The noble houses must know of this cruelty.
target: Per favore, aiutaci mio signore. Noi siamo riusciti a fuggire dalle fosse degli schiavi a nord, ma cos tanti di noi sono tenuti prigionieri dai demoni di sangue di Montclair. I nobili casati devono sapere di questa crudelt.

source: I hurt my back working down at the docks, but there's no work for me up here. I'm not a forester. As soon as I heal, I'll be on my way... somewhere.
That's what I want to do. I want to work on the docks! I wouldn't have to worry about those spriggans if I was down by the water.
The Fane of Breath suffers without Isrisa's song. Her voice was otherworldly! Noble Optimate, you must help recover it!
I will never understand the purpose of this noise you mortals call music.
I can't do this. No weapon, no skills, no time. How can I hunt mudcrabs without any tools?
Be wary. We don't know what we're up against.
The fiends are coming from the pass! I have to light the signal fire, but the tower has already fallen!nnThen again, if I don't light the fire, all of Crestshade will fall... and everyone will die...
Haven't seen any shady individuals have you?
It was an honor to be given this position, but I mourn Balmont's death.  We're all shocked, and many wish to see justice done.
The noise is gone. I am so tired. Do you think I can sleep now?
The Ravenwatch fears nothing, not even death itself.
Those damn Bitterkites think they can raid our stores anytime they want.nnNext time they try that, they'll be in for a surprise.
You know it's bad when a Bosmer can't find his way home.
We've been here weeks doing little more than holding the Thornvenom tribe at bay. It's good to have some reinforcements - truthfully, I'm glad to see a seasoned <<1>> here.
Oi! I got my eyes on you fancypants!
Have you a need for the hands of mercy?
The Lion Guard will get theirs soon enough. nnThere's a reckoning coming! You better better be on the right side!
You've put to rest a generation of soldiers and secured peace for those who survived them.nnRanser's bloody legacy has ended.
You look like you need some coin...I got an offer for ya!
Would you like to go up or down?
Welcome to Varyllis, Optimate. Did you need me for something?
I have considered moving to the Kinhouse until the Maormer are beaten. It is well defended.
These men were attacked by the Red Rook Bandits. Their wounds won't heal.nnI suspect poison.
Have you seen those horrid statues in Varyllis? As if cold stone could match the peerless majesty of Isquer music!
Spare some gold for a worker down on his luck?
Nothing can save us! They're coming for you, for me, for all of us!
Need something to ride? Most of my stock was killed, stolen, or commandeered by the guard, but the mounts I do have are healthy and strong.
That's a fine how do you do! Do you make a habit of barging into a person's house?nnYou're lucky. If I weren't so exhausted, I'd knock you over the head with my broomstick.
Who are you? Why are you here? You can't arrest me! I'm not breaking any laws!
With all the recent trouble, these streets aren't safe at night. You should be careful and keep a hand on your gold pouch.
Come closer. My hearing isn't what it used to be. Are you a soldier? Not one of Montclair's, I hope. Those ruffians! They're cowards, the lot of them, to hit an old woman like me.
Please don't disturb my mother. She needs her rest.
Ranser may have been an idiot, and Montclair isn't any better, but Shornhelm could really use a king.
What is it? Why can't you leave a poor man to his sorrows?
Dry as a bone. I think this well's been cursed!
Gladsome salutations, Optimate.rnrnMy shop is open rain or shine but the invasion of Sunhold was something I did not foresee. My inventory is thin due to the lack of shipments.
I must not... stop playing... it will... burn me...
(you wouldn't be reading this if Invisible mobs were invisible)
Summerset is a lovely Isle - the trees complain too much, however.
Please do not alert the guards... If I play just the right note I will change back.
Please do not alert the guards... If I play just the right note I will change back.
Please do not alert the guards... If I play just the right note I will change back.
The Lord Magister and I came up through the ranks together. nnGlenumbra has problems, but we know the Lion Guard can solve them.

<You've found a dead body. Madier's neck has been slit from ear to ear. He's clutching a note:>nn"Averos, I was right. Astrid the White and the Red Rooks are working for Angof.nnThey're hiding in Aldcroft's lighthouse. I'll return when I know more."
If we wanted to take Northpoint for our own, we could take it. nnIf the Bretons here are smart, they'll do what we want and avoid any more trouble.
Anyone too weak to keep what they have deserves to have it taken.
You have to help me! I lost my husband. I lost my children. What else do I have to live for now?
What is a Vartisan without the Varlines?
Without the Varlines the simplest of tasks, such as binding spirits of Discarnates into servitude, becomes nearly impossible.
We must remain vigilant against the enemy.
Optimate, are you here to fix the Varla Lens?
Hail, Optimate. With the Varlines down my usefulness here is limited.
With this power we can defend against the Maormer.nnI pray for you a speedy path to help the other Kinships.
The magical energies flow through me!nnI am whole again!
You have restored the Varlines! Praise to you.
I feel it!nnThe power of the Varlines!
Hail, Optimate. With the Varlines down my usefulness here is limited.
Optimate, are you here to find the Varla Lens?
Without the Varlines the simplest of tasks, such as binding spirits of Discarnates into servitude, becomes nearly impossible.
What is a Vartisan without the Varlines?
My kitty, Jenkles, has come back to me!
We shall fear those Pallid Devils no more!
The magical energies flow through me!nnI am whole again!
You have restored the Varlines! Praise to you.
A pleasure, Optimate. Were I not preoccupied with the channeling of this Varline, I would love to continue this conversation further.
I could use a break. I hope Alexandra doesn't run out of ale again.
Care for a drink, traveler? nnFell's Run has the best Nordic Ale on tap this side of the bay!
Urgh. Go away! nnIt's not time to march yet....
You're fortunate to have found me, friend! I was just about to pack up and look for a better location.
Where has that silly girl gone? She should have been back by now.
Don't get any clever ideas. I'm watching you.
I admire your courage. You venture so brazenly into my domain.nnTarry a while, and perhaps we may both learn something.
Terrible, what's happening to Fell's Run. This used to be a safe, quiet place to raise a family
Please leave me be. I just want to drink.
Hail, Optimate. With the Varlines down my usefulness here is limited.
Greetings and salutations, Optimate. Might I borrow a moment of your time?
With this power we can defend against the Maormer.nnI pray for you a speedy path to help the other Kinships.
The magical energies flow through me!nnI am whole again!
You have restored the Varlines! Praise to you.
I feel it!nnThe power of the Varlines!
It's a sad time for me. Please leave me to my grief.
My home is lost. I... I can't talk right now.
We barely escaped Camlorn with our lives.
If you ask me, we should just give up and move on.
Hail, Optimate. With the Varlines down my usefulness here is limited.
Optimate, are you here to find the Varla Lens?
Without the Varlines the simplest of tasks, such as binding spirits of Discarnates into servitude, becomes nearly impossible.
What is a Vartisan without the Varlines?
After we're finished here, I think I'm gonna get promoted. nnThen hopefully, I can ask for a post in Wayrest. That's where my family lives now.
With this power we can defend against the Maormer.nnI pray for you a speedy path to help the other Kinships.
The magical energies flow through me!nnI am whole again!
You have restored the Varlines! Praise to you.
I feel it!nnThe power of the Varlines!
Life has been a bit more cheerful since the Magis Order arrived. They keep our spirits up. nnThey're not like those poor folks from Camlorn.
I enjoyed taking it easy, but there's nothing like an honest day's work. Right?
Just passing through? I'm about to head out myself. Between the bandits and the vampires and the rumors of war, I want to get out of Rivenspire as fast as I can.

If that Captain Thayer comes around here again, someone's going to get hurt! That wench called me a coward because I prefer to work here rather than join the Shornhelm Guard. nnSense of duty? Pfft! That's a pile of guar-dung!

Just resting the legs for a few minutes here and letting my friends graze. No matter how bad things get, I'm always grateful that I have work that I love.nnIt's not everyone who finds their true calling.
Ah, the ringing of hammers. One must admire the industry of the Scintillants, eh <<1>>? Just remember to speak loudly when you talk to them.
Welcome to Isque, Numinous. I trust you had a pleasant journey east?
Welcome to the Orrery, <<1>>. Do mind your head. You never know why might fly by around here.
This one wishes she had some catnip.
Thank you for helping Varyllis. Now we must help the Dominion.
Thank you for helping Isque. Now we must help the Dominion.
Thank you for helping the Orrery. Now we must help the Dominion.
Thank you for helping Dusk. Now we must help the Dominion.
This came to pass because that idiot child-queen.nnIf she had not stripped our garrisons for her foolish mainland adventures, the Maormer could have been repulsed!

Many of Camlorn's residents were slain by wolves.nnOf course, some of the survivors were unfortunate enough to become werewolves.nnGives me the shivers to think of what I'm actually killing in battle.

The werewolves came at Camlorn quickly. Fortunately, Duke Sebastien was able to get to Aldcroft and send for aid, or I doubt these wolves would have stopped here.nnWe're able to contain them, but just barely.
Our brothers and sisters fought with us valiantly to the bitter end. nnWhat you see here is simply the remains of the Ravenwatch.
So you got past the mutinous dogs who were once my crew, did you?
I hold the finest magicwork straight from the Anquillius Forge! Would you like to take a look?
The Anquillius Forge, the greatest in all of Summerset, crafts specifically and exclusively for this store. nnCome and marvel at the stock!
Gladsome salutations, Optimate.rnrnMy shop is open rain or shine but the invasion of Sunhold was something I did not foresee. My inventory is thin due to the lack of shipments.
Greetings, Optimate, and welcome to the Phidian Menagerie.
<You see fear and confusion in the giant's eyes.>

Dark times fall upon our lands. Shornhelm is but a glimpse of the chaos that spreads across this kingdom. nnA strong, noble house must unite our city once again. Only through unity can we conquer this undead threat to Rivenspire.
The rending of Shornhelm just proves the city needs a strong hand if we hope to retain what little order is left within these walls.
Our only choice is to flee! nnI'm sure I can secure a villa in Wayrest at least until this whole situation dies down.
My family has lived in Rivenspire for generations. nnNo man or beast will make me flee my home.
Something I can help you with today? Feel free to browse and just holler if you need help.
I'm not afraid of dying. I'm afraid of Nords!

Oh thank the Heavens! Thank the Divines! I thought I would never be rid of those Rogue Discarnates, until you happened upon them.nnSuch a valiant deed must be returned with a gift. Please, take it with all my gratitude.
We'll save Camlorn yet, mark my words! Sure, it's filled with werewolves now, but the Lion guard will soon set things right.nnWe'll clear them out and get Duke Sebastien back in his manor.
At least the shipping lanes are open again. Montclair's foolishness has cost me more gold than I care to think about.
It is my great pleasure to welcome to the Phidian Menagerie. Did you happen to see a Kirin on the way in?
My chickens are dying and I can't figure out why. I come out in the morning, and they're just dead. No blood or nothing. Doesn't make sense.
War, war - everywhere.nnWhy not take a rest and visit the Phidian Menagerie to the north?
Greetings, Optimate, and welcome to the Phidian Menagerie.
I'm fine, really.nnAdradan and I were just no, never mind what we were doing.nnWe were distracted, and we got attacked. It happens.
Hah! Come to spoil my adventure, are you?nnI suppose I'm ready to go home.nnI'm glad Jillae's all right. I assumed she would be, of course. nnShe's nearly as good a fighter as I am! Nearly.
Hail, Optimate. With the Varlines down my usefulness here is limited.
Optimate, are you here to find the Varla Lens?
Without the Varlines the simplest of tasks, such as binding spirits of Discarnates into servitude, becomes nearly impossible.
What is a Vartisan without the Varlines?
Beautiful day, isn't it? The cackling of the chickens is music to my ears. And the crowing of the rooster makes such sweet poetry. They're almost in harmony.
I thought that was the end of me!
How can a man make a living when everyone's out to sabotage him?
I can't get to him. They'll kill him! They're gonna kill my only brother!nnAnd then... then they'll come after me.
Stonebridge Mill is broken down and these new River Dreugh are a constant nuisance. nnSometimes I feel like The Eight themselves are conspiring against me.

Hmm, interesting.nnIt appears the trickery bestowed upon us by our hosts continues. I was not... expecting this. The key to the puzzle no doubt is the same as before. Slay everything in your path, especially those who might seem familiar.

Pushed like a mere pawn being moved about in her quest for power. Was it her soft voice filling your ear with whispers of lust filled nights? Was it her promise of power to rule by her side?nnAll lies sharp enough to kill a man.
What do you want? Do I need to call the constable? Get away from me!
Who are you? Why are you talking to me? nnThey sent you, didn't they? Didn't they?

When you see a man like me in the stocks, you might think I did something wrong. That's a bald-faced lie!nnI stand accused of destroying the Koeglin Lighthouse and wrecking ships in the cove, but I didn't.nnI am an innocent man.
I didn't see anything, and don't let anyone tell you different!
I rather enjoy walking about the village again.
I saw someone like you in my nightmares. nnI'll be keeping an eye on you, stranger. Stay out of trouble.
By Arkay's Breath! It's good to be free of those wretched things.
What do you want? Can't you see I'm busy guarding Koeglin Village? nnYou should head down to the coast and bother the slavers instead.

I was just doing my job when they arrested me. Now they're going to kill us all! nnBy Arkay, we know what they're doing here. We know the truth!nnThat's why they've locked us up. That's why I'll never see my family again.

Can you help me? Someone has to drive these Daedra away from the lighthouse. They doused the signal fire at the top. They want the passing ships to crash!nnOnce they get tired of looting ships, they're going to attack Koeglin Village!
A moment of your time? I can't offer much, but really, who can put a price on true love?
All this cargo, and no way to unload it. I curse the winds that blew us to this miserable port!
Please... you must help. I can't hold these pirates out for much longer.
Who are you? Why do you want to speak to me?
Kind traveler! A moment of your time?
Shhh! If the Duke sees anyone speaking to us, we are cast out of the Keep!
Please don't let them take me!
What do you want? Can't you see I'm feeding what's left of my chickens?nnSomeone's been stealing them. I had a dozen or more before I had to move into town.nnNow look what's left of 'em.
Have you heard the noises from the forest? It sounds like something's in there, east of us. Something angry.
The Dominion soldiers bought most of Ma'Dyi's wares and she thinks no new supplies will be arriving soon. She is happy to sell you what she has, though.
Herb gathering has become a dangerous task.
Just because the Imperials fell back when the Altmer arrived doesn't mean that we just gave up when the attack began.nnWe just did a really good job at hiding is all.
The Imperials destroyed all the vessels that we used to get out and trade with the neighboring tribes. We haven't heard word from Greenshade in weeks.
Haven't had a good night's rest since my neighbor got those chickens.nnThey sent him to Alcaire to drive us mad. I know they did!
Hoodlums, that's what they are! They'll kill us in our sleep!nnThe duke has done nothing to protect us. Nothing!
I can see them from here. That's why I keep watch, lest they attack us unawares.
Pardon my poor welcome, stranger. Ever since I took in those poor mages from the Guild, there's nothing left to eat in our house but the chairs and tables.
I'm sorry I can't be more help. We've got a crisis on our hands!
Who told you that I'd be here? Where can I hide? nnYou've ruined everything! Everything!
If you're not here with food or firewood, I'm not getting out of bed.
The shops charge too much, and I don't think they're entirely honest. nnAs soon as the roads are a bit safer, I'm going back to Wayrest.
This is dangerous territory, stranger. What are you doing outside the town?
We didn't feel safe at the farm. I feel even less safe in town. nnI can't find a moment's peace anywhere. They're always watching us.
It's nothing personal, stranger. I just don't trust you.nnWe don't like strangers around here.
Such beautiful flowers. Enjoy them while you can, wanderer.
The history of this region is fascinating.
Why doesn't the duke do something? He could save us, but he does nothing. We're at his mercy.
Get away from me! I don't know who you are!
General Cruor is over there in that palisade - the palisade built from the felled trees of Mara's Grove! nnMay he and his Imperial vermin contract Jungle Flux!
J'Hriss believes the Imperials hold secrets that we all would benefit from. Why else would one guard a ship that is all but lost?nnMakes no sense to J'Hriss.
Can't you see I'm busy here?
Don't bother me and I won't bother you.
By the Eight, could anything else go wrong?nnFather's gone mad, Mother's disappeared. Now scamps are feasting on what's left of our livestock! nnSomeone has it out for us.
I'm not sure how much longer I can wait here without losing my mind. nnOnce my brother arrives, we'll head to Daggerfall as quickly as possible.
This battlefield is ripe for the plucking! Many in Valenwood would pay good coin for these... abandoned articles.
I am a placeholder for push content tech.
With Senie in ruins and half our city in panic, I don't really have time for an audience, stranger.nnIf your need is urgent, however, I will grant you a moment of my attention.
I have precious little time to address the questions of common rabble. nnMake your request quick. Do not waste my time... or test my patience.

A strange affliction fell upon our city less than a month ago. nnWe lacked the resources to oppose it, so House Dres offered Councilor Bravosi to aid us.nnCouncilor Miluru trusts his judgment, but does she know how far he has gone?
Seems a shame to let so much fine armor go to rust on the seashore, don't you think?
So many unpleasantries! I do wish we did not have to resort to such brutish measures, but Bravosi is quite insistent. Hopefully this will all be over soon.
If we hadn't already lost half the crew, I'd have half a mind to teach these village guards a lesson.
Davon's Watch is under strict control. No one enters without submitting to quarantine.nnOh, you are the <<1>> we've heard so much about. Tales of your deeds have traveled far, friend.
When it comes right down to it, things never really change. nnDon't let anyone tell you otherwise.
General Cruor! His father was a scamp, and his mother was a dog! May Auri-El eat them!
I should have fought the Imperials... we lost everything.
Have you seen these prices? These merchants are all trying to reduce us to poverty. It's their fault we're in such a terrible state.
What little we owned was lost when the Imperials burned our homes.
Foul servant of ignoble houses! We suffer for your hubris! nnIf I had the strength, I'd kill you where you stand. nnBegone, accursed n'wah!
No work for an old eelmer these days....
We will push the Imperials off of Grahtwood and into the sea.
The body is Blight-ridden and cold.  It's clear that those here at Fort Arand perished from the Blight not that long ago.nnAn insignia of Fort Arand lies on the body.
They won't laugh at our mead after this, will they? nnThey made fun of me. Now they'll pay....
The body is Blight-ridden and cold.  It's clear that those here at Fort Arand perished from the Blight not that long ago.
Few among the living would venture into a city of the dead. nnI must warn you. Our guardians do not distinguish unannounced visitors from scavengers.
Nori-ja is listening to the forest. It sounds different.
Be careful here.  House Redoran's men died quickly, and you may succumb to the same fate.
What'll ya have, <<1>>? nnI've set aside some of my best mead for you.
Welcome to the Old Goat Inn.nnMind your manners, or the Redguards will kick you out.
Tsajivi can see you are headed into town.nnPerhaps you are brave enough to help Tsajivi?
I have heard of you.  Blightbane - that is what they call you.  We will see.  We will see.
I'm sure she was only joking about bringing your corpse home.
I do not remember asking you to speak.
Any business you have with Sera Orvona, you'll conduct through me. No need to trouble him with any trifling matters.
I don't know you. What business do you have with me?
You're not from Sugar, are you? Tell him I'm not selling!
I'm just waiting for the next boat to get off this rock, friend. Best move along.

Keep your voice low, stranger. nnDamn near legion of goblins infest the ruins here.  Most horrible little beasts I've ever seen! My parents always told me tales of them to keep me in line when I was just a lad, but these are far worse!
I, Ahjiivi, wear no chains. We fought to escape our bonds, and we will fight you as well, if you threaten our freedom.
I beseech you, hold your blade if you have any pity for a hunted creature!
The fish are easier to catch when they bite the lure. When they're floating next to it, dead, I can't catch em.
I should be on the front line, not peering into the forest.
Salutations, my dear traveler! Why so heavily dressed on such a fine day? The springs are truly wondrous!nnI'd be in the water myself, if not for a little mishap with my ... um ... with my pants.
Please don't disturb my Spinners. They're deep in the Green Time.
Bubbles between my toes, breeze in my hair, half-clothed beautiful bodies all around ... how much closer could one be to Aetherius?
Have you brought my wine? A servant was supposed to be here with my wine.nnI hope he wasn't eaten by a dreugh.
I remember this place. Here, I met my untimely demise. nnI followed the outlaws here. My brothers sealed me in with them.nnThen the Four found me.
Welcome to Reywell, stranger. You know, I've been told that strangers are just friends we haven't met. nnI'm pleased to meet you. We should get to know each other, so we can be friends.
All the ale in Wayrest could not make these springs any nicer! Just look at the scenery, my friend!
One has only to sink into the soothing mud and steam to know what the Divines must feel like on high!
Welcome to our humble camp under the Thramble eaves.
Greetings, comrade! My knave's senses tell me there is much potential for mischief in you.

There are a lot of hoarvor in the lower areas of the Thrambles. They're big insects that suck blood.nnThe small ones are more dangerous - they're more hungry. The bigger ones have eaten, and usually won't attack anything they come across.
The hunting here is strange. nnI can't remember anyone hunting in the Thrambles. It should be the easiest hunting in Grahtwood, I imagine. nnThe animals might even be friendly!
I do not know why I haven't come here to dance before! It's very soothing!
Join us, friend! The mud is warm, and the courtiers will welcome you! It's very inviting.

I don't know why the Daedric priest placed those idols around the barrow. In fact, I don't want to know.nnUnfortunately, I think the priest stole some sorrowbloom from the vault down there. I can't turn a blind eye to a crime like that one.
The watch captain knows I can't swim. nnWhy would he post me so close to the water? I swear, it's as though he wants me to drown.
You seem unaffected by The Fervor. This is good, for we are but two and the lamia are dozens.

No enemy, living or dead, will harm Lady Idah while I'm by her side. Those dreugh don't stand a chance against me.nnI enjoy a good fight, but they've learned to fear me. Now they run whenever they see me. nnIf they try to harm her, they will suffer.
I think my legs are broken and my ribs but I can't go back to Ebonheart! Ahjiivi will find me there, after she finishes with Omaynia!nnJust stay away from me!
Thank the gods. Help has arrived!nnYou're here to help me, right?
Everyone talks about our mead. After all, it's the finest in all of Stormhaven!
Didn't I see you talking to those traitors?
I'm really grateful for your help.nnWho knows what might have become of me if you hadn't come along?nnI have a favor to ask, though. By the gods, I'm begging you: don't tell anyone about it!
My wife is missing. Have you seen my wife? Oh, where could she be?
You saved my wife from a fate worse than death. Thank you!
You reunited me with my husband. Thank you! I'm never wandering off alone again!
What? Who are you? What do you want with me? I'll bet your with them, aren't you? I'll get my grandson if you cause any trouble.
Why the long face? One would think you were a horse!
This was a private conversation!nnNow that you are here, perhaps you'd like to join us?
You don't look like an Imperial.nnGood. Maybe you can help me.
I could run all day...and drink wine all night!
It's hard to think about the past. It's over and done.nnBesides, what would the neighbors think?
Good day to you, <<1>>. I hear you helped solve the murder of our Duchess. Thank you.
What business do you have in House Dres' holdings?
Can't you see I'm very busy?nnApologies for my sharp tongue. It's been a long day. nnIt seems I'm not allowed to do my job anymore, until House Dres requires it. Most frustrating.
Please, I don't want to die!
Arkay's mercy! You almost scared me to death!nnKeep your head down. There are Imperials everywhere!
Tokutu, <<1>>! nnWelcoming a new friend to Ookvoot!

<<1>> has suitors. They are mere shadows compared to the glow of my desire.nnI must have her, even though I am too shy to speak with her directly.nnMy passion drives me mad. I cannot approach her in such a state of longing. Please! Help me woo her!
Juggling food. Standing too close. nnNot seeing Gulpyougone! Shouting with surprise!nnThe suffocation of sorrow. The horror of realization. The gnashing of teeth!nnMissing Lug. Realizing he is gone.
All I want to do is give my friends a good show! Why would anyone have a problem with that?
You! I've seen you before haven't I? You were the one causing trouble back at that Inn!
Welcome, <<1>>. It was you what helped bring Sir Hughes to justice. You've my thanks.

It's about time the Baron's soldiers arrived! nnWhere are the rest of you? Surely an entire legion would be sent for a rescue of such a high ranking noble as I. What? You look at me as if you are unaware of who you stand before.
P-please. Can you help me? Please?
What is it? Here now, don't stand around. You'll ruin my work if you stand around.
Welcome, <<1>>. I can't say I liked seeing Sir Hughes go down for a crime, but I respect what you did and why.
House Redoran and House Dres do nothing but compete for business. It makes my task much more strenuous than it need be.
They say those who dance at Reywell will never age.
I heard you were helping the Champion.  I mean... how are you?  I mean... are you leaving the Conclave?  Can I go with you?  As your squire?  nn...I meant as your squire.
Can no one help me? My son is not far from here! Please, I ask for your assistance. Those slave traders will not wait much longer!

Meridia may have blessed us with our health, but we have been cursed by these unclean outsiders.  Look at them, crowding our boundaries.  It's not our fault that they are weak and without the Divines' favor.
Did you come here to beat Dalos as well?
Dalos knows you, <<1>>. I know you helped bring one of those knights to justice. What is it to me? I'm little better than a slave.
Hush, stranger. This one must not be seen.
I finally get a little peace in my life. I finally go fishing at the Sand Cove south of here. Then what happens?nnLooks like the dreugh had the same idea. They swarmed the place. Damn it all.

Ugh! Those hideous creatures have tainted our sand coves south of here. They've ruined my picnic! nnThe grandest Wayrest nobles were going to attend. How is one to divert one's self with fun when giant crabs are trying to turn one into hors d'oerves?

Taste. nnIt's such a simple, but pleasing enjoyment that we all partake in daily. Why limit ourselves to the simple and usual though? Why not open up our possibilities? We should try what the world has to offer us even outside our realm of comfort.
Please help me.  I know that they have the cure here; if they would only share it with me I could be saved!
The Conclave is untouched while the rest of us suffer the blight's affliction.  They should help us.  If they have a cure, they should share it with everyone.
I'm the strongest gladiator in all of Stormhaven!
I'm the strongest gladiator in all of Stormhaven!
I'm the strongest gladiator in all of Stormhaven!
I'm the strongest gladiator in all of Stormhaven!
I'm the strongest gladiator in all of Stormhaven!
I'm the strongest gladiator in all of Stormhaven!
I'm the strongest gladiator in all of Stormhaven!
I'm the strongest gladiator in all of Stormhaven!
I'm the strongest gladiator in all of Stormhaven!
I'm the strongest gladiator in all of Stormhaven!
This arena is filled with blood and death. nnI do what I can to resurrect gladiators who foolishly give their lives to the slaughter.
Proving Hoom's skills are better than Wud's! nnKnowing Hoom will beat Wud in the Scavenger Hunt!
Disliking Hoom intensely.nnTiring of the frequency of his practical jokes! nnBemoaning the vanity of the obviously inferior!
It's better our brothers and sisters bodies become food for the creatures of Grahtwood instead of rotting away to nothingness.
Please... soon I'll be dead of the Blight.  The Conclave has answers, I know they do.  Tell them to help me.
I've heard of you.  You're the Blightbane, aren't you?  Can you convince the Ashlanders to help us?
It's wrong that the Conclave hoard the secret of the cure for themselves!  Why should we suffer when they have the remedy?
They say the Ashlanders have the secret to protect them from the Blight.  Help me, help my family, or we will all perish!
The hatred of the noxious Hoom. The  fear of the sea denizens. nnWill the <<1>> be helping Wud in the scavenger hunt?nnPromising the infinity of Wud's gratitude!
Will the <<1>> be noticing something shiny at the end? nnWill the <<1>> be getting it for Hoom? nnThe assertion of Hoom's desire for it!
I guess this place isn't so bad, even with those Spinners chanting and whooping all the time.
Did you come to buy a slave today? Or are you volunteering to be one?

I can cope with bugs the size of steer. I can choke down the disgusting concoctions the Bosmer drink instead of a decent wine. But Imperial invasion? Simply intolerable.nnThat Altmer Queen will be getting a letter that will blister her eyeballs!
This one plans to return to Elsweyr, whence he came.
Another day at the forge. Another suit of armor hacked apart for me to put back together. nnAh, yes. I love my work.
Alcaire is no safer than Koeglin Village. Things are worse here than I imagined. But at least, I am no longer a slave, thanks to you, <<1>>.
There are times when I wonder whether Solon would have been better off as a slave than being treated so poorly here in Alcaire.
How will we get back to our ship? There are too many pirates!
You look like someone who's seen plenty of danger. I wager you'd do well in the Grand Melee!

I am the Great and Deadly Mura, your incomparable announcer for the Grand Melee!nnBe grateful I'm not competing. You'd be dead in the blink of an eye!nnMy pronouncement of your untimely demise would echo through the arena before you hit the ground!
As soon as my lady's son is recovered, we can leave these filthy pirate slavers to their business.
You'd be surprised how tasty a good, fat maggot can be.
This corpse is crawling with live maggots.
This corpse is crawling with live maggots.
This corpse is crawling with live maggots.
There just aren't enough of us to take down these pirates and get to our ship!
There just aren't enough of us to take down these pirates and get to our ship!
How will we get back to our ship? There are too many pirates!
There's not much for me to do without any thunderbugs.
I'd like to say I'm a busy man but these days with every import restricted... I've got nothing but time.  What can I do for you?
You're new here. I can tell.
I strongly suggest you mind your own business.
Welcome to our home. You, and so many others.
Have you seen these prices? These merchants are trying to reduce us all to poverty!
I don't care if you're with Duke Bealton or Baron Gradwyn. Get out and leave us to our misery.
I've lived in Daggerfall all my life. nnI still get turned around inside the city walls.
We're well-protected here.nnI feel safe in Daggerfall.
I don't care if you're with Duke Bealton or Baron Gradwyn. Get out and leave us to our misery.
I don't care if you're with Duke Bealton or Baron Gradwyn. Get out and leave us to our misery.
I don't care if you're with Duke Bealton or Baron Gradwyn. Get out and leave us to our misery.
Wayrest is nothing compared to Daggerfall.nnThis place can't compare to our beautiful town!
Do you know how much the armorer is charging for greaves these days? It's scandalous!
Old King Casimir's a good leader.nnHe saved us from being overrun like Camlorn... at least, that's what they say.
Before my marriage, I had never been to Daggerfall. nnIt's so much larger than Aldcroft!
This shouldn't have happened. They're all dead because of us.nnMara forgive us for what we did.
Glenumbra's being invaded, and feathered freaks want to tear my head off.nnDon't worry. This wound isn't as bad as it looks. I'm just catching my breath.

Rebuilding Senie is imperative to House Redoran. nnWe're attempting to gather resources for the effort, but the Orlishkaarn Ashlanders plague us at every turn. nnThey attack our workers, claiming we're responsible for spreading disease. Nonsense.
When I came here to investigate Dresan Ruins, spriggans attacked me. nnI escaped, but I still haven't explored the ruins.
My family has lived in Daggerfall for a very long time.nnI think the Daggerfall Covenant will finally bring us peace.
There are so many new faces in Daggerfall these days!nnIt's getting harder to keep track of everyone. Say, have we met before?
I should have known things would get worse before they'd get better.nnPoachers are running rampant over my plantation. nnI suppose they want to snatch up what's valuable before things get even worse.
I travelled to Crosswych once.nnIt's a pleasant little village, but certainly not worth seeing twice.
No, I don't know when your shipment will be released.  nnNo, I can't speed up the process. No, I won't bribe the harbormaster.nnWait. You're not a trader! What can I do for you?
Don't disturb my sister. The loss of our father... she's not ready to accept it.  She's not ready to bring him to the Bonebarrow.
Please help us! We were ambushed suddenly and before we knew what was going on, we were surrounded.
My grandfather took part in the Reachmen War. My father was in Ranser's War.nnI still don't believe war is ever profitable. Even when you win, you still lose.
Daggerfall is the finest Breton city ever built.
I've heard stories about Daggerfall all my life.nnThis city has a sound structure, just as the tales say. I'm impressed.
The Bretons aren't as friendly to others as they are to their own kind.
I was expecting Daggerfall to be much more civilized.nnWhat a shame.
It's no wonder Daggerfall isn't the capital city.nnI can only hope Wayrest lives up to my expectations.
Have you been outside the city gates?nnThe woods are wondrous!
The Bretons are certainly proud of Daggerfall, aren't they? nnI like it well enough. After all, it's surrounded by thriving, beautiful woods.
What are you looking at?nnDidn't you expect to see Dunmer in Daggerfall?
Daggerfall is certainly amusing, but I can't wait to return to Vvardenfell.
This one is pleased to greet you!
Daggerfall is surrounded by woods, water, and walls. nnThis one just doesn't understand. The residents want to separate themselves from everything.
I'm a patron of the Fighter's Guild, but really, the politics between the guilds don't interest me. nnAll I really want in life is time to train and a chance to learn.
Glenumbra is much too cold for me.nnI miss the heat of the desert.
My family's trading improves each day the Daggerfall Covenant continues.
Our skalds have a saying:nn"Great Lorkhan protects and looks after his own, nNo matter how far his Nord children may roam."
Keep quiet.  I can't be seen talking to you.
Blessings of the Three upon you. What brings you to this holy place?
Colovians don't belong in the jungle. Divines... why did I ever come here?
Do not think your deeds will go unanswered. My death means little to the plans of House Dres!
You weren't as easy a mark as I thought.
Colovians don't belong in the jungle. Divines... why did I ever come here?
The years weigh on me like barnacles gathering on a hull. nnI'm tired, but the sea keeps calling me. Lea keeps calling me.
It's such a long drop. I wonder if it will hurt?
I've heard stories about Daggerfall most of my life.nnIt's got a solid foundation and good structure, just as the tales say. I'm impressed.
The Bretons aren't as friendly to others as they are to their own kind.
I was expecting Daggerfall to be much more civilized.
It is no wonder Daggerfall isn't the capital city.nnI just hope Wayrest lives up to my expectations.
There aren't enough trees inside the city walls.nnOutside the walls, the forest is really quite beautiful.
I don't know what them Bosmer are doing, but it sure looks pretty.nnThat lady priestess is real pretty too, if you don't mind me saying.
The Bretons are certainly proud of Daggerfall, aren't they?
What are you looking at?nnDidn't you expect to see Dunmer in Daggerfall these days?
Daggerfall is certainly amusing, but I can't wait to return to Vvardenfell.
This one is pleased to greet you!
Daggerfall is surrounded by woods, water, and walls. nnThis one just doesn't get it. It's as though the residents want to separate themselves from everything.
I hone my skills at the Fighters Guild almost every day. All that training keeps me sharp.
Glenumbra is much too cold for me.nnI miss the heat of the desert.
I work aboard my cousin's trade ship. nnThis time, we won't be in Daggerfell for long... at least, that's what my cousin says.
Some days, I think Daggerfall is too warm. nnAll these stone walls take in too much of the day's heat.
For the first time I can remember, the pain is gone.
These men might not make it through the night if we can't get a sample of the bandits' poison.
My parents were laid inside the Bonebarrows. They might be part of that tower in Haven now.
The Imperials could attack at any minute.
I know there's a war on, but did the Wood Elves have to just dump these supplies in a pile? It's slovenly!
To tell the truth, I'm looking for another place to buy wine. The last shop was completely sold out.
Daggerfall is well-protected, especially with our help.
There is nothing more satisfying than victory in the face of incredible odds.
What are these Bosmer doing? This one has seen nothing like this before.
The Razorvine tribe is generous to grant us shelter. I wish the others appreciated it more.
I hope Thistlewhip's hunters return soon. I should be out there with him. With them, I mean.
I represent the Aldmeri Dominion in Southpoint.
I'm new to the Lion Guard, but I have faith in its purpose.
What crime did I commit in life to deserve this fate? nnI will not toil here any longer. In our service, we have forgotten our very names!
The king's guards stand ready. We live to serve.
May the Eight bless you, traveler.
Yes? Did you have a question, traveler?
May the Eight bless you, traveler.
Good day to you, traveler. Is there something you need?
May the Eight walk beside you, traveler.
You've saved me from an eternity of suffering, mortal. nnMere words are insufficient to express my eternal gratitude.
What mortal trespasses upon our land? Do not torment us so!
The mill had some room, so they allowed us to set up our alchemy stations in here. Now I have to make sure we haven't forgotten anything.
Steel and stone! You just gonna gawk at that anvil or are you gonna do something with it?nnBah. If you're gonna linger you may as well buy something.
What do you need, my friend? My outfitting supplies are without equal. If you want something to research I have a few well-made Jacks available. Only one to a customer, please.
Good day to you. I can supply all the basic supplies you need to learn the art and science of runecrafting!nnFor a modest price, of course.
Mauloch's jawbone  needled myself again! Got hands like an ogre, I do! You look nimble though. Need something?
And what can the guild of outfitters do for you?
Anything can be made better through enchantment. Anything. Don't believe me? Give it a try.
In the name of our Lady Kynareth, I welcome you to Daggerfall.
What business would you like to discuss?
I sell many types of armor. What's your preference?
What do you need today? I restock my wares fairly often.
If you need anything to combine with something to make a completely different thing, I probably sell it ... in one form or another. nnDon't believe me? Go, ahead. Ask!
I have sources throughout Tamriel who can keep my shop well-stocked. nnIf we don't make it here, we can always order it from elsewhere.
Blessings of the Eight! Welcome to my humble shop. nnI made many of these items by hand. Take your time! Find one you really like!
Greetings and blessings upon you, traveler! Welcome to the Hare and Dragon Inn.nnWhat brings you to Daggerfall, my friend?
Something to sate your hunger and slake your thirst, friend?
Blessings of the Three upon you!nnThey've already forsaken me.
I don't know how long I've been waiting outside this Dumac-cursed city. nnI might just turn around and take my wares to Ebonheart.

Stay a moment! I bet you'd be interested in this health-bestowing anointing oil!nnThis miraculous tincture is guaranteed to cure baldness, facial blemishes, and other symptoms of the mysterious affliction infecting our land!nnThe cure is right here!
I've never seen so many begging to get into this infested dunghole. nnIf I were them, I'd get out of Stonefalls until this all blows over.
Oh! Galas, my love! Will someone bring him back to me?
Would you mind moving to the right a bit?
If you're from House Dres, take a seat over there, I'm busy.   Otherwise, what can I do for you?
This is no business of yours. Move along.
Ah, this man will be the death of me!
Another traveler has come to visit me! nnIt's always good to see another fresh face. nnDo you need healing?
<You've found a dead body. The forest has already begun to reclaim it.>

The ordinators came to <<1>> to protect our shores from this unknown affliction. nnNo ships can dock or leave here without a proper inspection. nnEven the cursed creatures of the sea can't seem to escape this wretched plague!
I slipped on a mountain trail and broke my leg.nnReme's already got it splinted, though. I think it's healing quickly.
Never had a cold this bad, but Reme... she fixed it. She healed me. nnI'm already feeling better.
This one asks that the stranger be silent.nnI, Raijo, must hide from my mistress, lest she command me to return with her.
Have you seen my Raijo?nnHe's a handsome Khajiit, very well-spoken and polite.nnI haven't seen him in a while, and I'm beginning to worry. This market is not safe!
No other house could accomplish what we've accomplished here.  Look at this wall, that was so perilous and costly to build.  It is a monument to the greatness of House Dres.
The best work in Varanis is done right here in my shop, if I do say so myself.  What will it be today; a new shirt?  A new pair of breeches?
Have you come to pay your respects to our house?  Or hurry with your petition, if you have one.  I'm a busy woman.
Ah, we were both fools. I should have known no one beats the house.
Oh, leave me be! I'm ruined. Ruined!
Care to play a hand, friend?
Why are you staring at me like that?
There is no spark of life in the form of this Lurcher. The wood of its limbs is black with mold.
I don't know how we're going to recover from this...
I feared all was lost. That beautiful woman called me here...nnWhere did she go? I must find her!
You must be the attractive <<1>> my sisters saw wandering among the cypresses.
Hello, my child.nnWelcome to my home. nnPlease, come stay with me.
You are not like the others. You are... alive.nnI am Prince Gideon of House Gradwyn. Are you here to grant my last wish?
Your kind have been here time and again, stirring the bones, scavenging.  Let us rest!

Those brutes haven't seen the marvelous fortune this coral creature has brought to us!nnThese grounds were once the landing point of the Akaviri invasion.nnNow they're brimming with untold history. We're on the brink of countless revelations!
<You've found an unconscious wyress. Her skin is pale and damp.>
To be wondering what you are looking at. The rudeness of strangers! The loneliness of difference!
Let me rest!  You  have no business here, you and that cursed House Dres digging up what should lie undisturbed.
What disrespect for a warrior's rest is this, to unseal my tomb and pilfer my bones?
The hoarvor hisses cheerfully as you approach.
<You find <<1>> lying in silent repose. You can colllect her root charm.>
<You find <<1>> lying in silent repose. You can collect her root charm.>
<You find <<1>> lying in silent repose. You can collect her root charm.>
To be wondering what you want?
Who are you, to speak to me?
Perhaps... that last cap wasn't the best plan...
Who are you, to speak to me?
It's good to be home again.
Oh, I feel so much better! Everything is so much clearer now! What's that you say? Ha, a werewolf! A fine jest, friend!nnWhy can I smell colors?
Please help me!  Llameni's been taken!
Welcome to my humble camp, traveller. I'm sorry to say I have none of my wares for sale at this time. The shalk here are simply too aggressive!
You're not supposed to be back here.
These are no ordinary swine you see before you!nnThey belong to the Outfitters Guild, the finest guild in all of Daggerfall.
Hey! You... you're real? nnHelp me. Please, help me!
The Rock Biter goblins are hateful things. They hate trees, people, and all the forest's children.
The Rock Biter goblins have committed many crimes against the forest.nnThe worst of their transgressions is their cruel enslavement of wolves.
In life, I was a Knight of the Dragon, a proud servant of Daggerfall. In death, I am cursed to relive my greatest failure... and the slaughter of those I held dear.
Please, do not alert Toves to my presence.
My Arynia, why do you spurn me so? I will follow you to the far reaches of the land and sea, my love! nnStranger, have you seen my vision of beauty my Arynia?
Mind your toes, <<1>>. I've got a line you don't want to cross.
If those Ashlander animals come near our keep, I'll wring their necks with my bare hands.nnThey deserve a dog's death.
I don't belong here. There's been a mistake!
Is... is it safe out there yet?
Jone and Jode, you saved me, stranger! Those Blacksap bastards were about to end me.
After what I've seen I will believe almost anything, but the rumors of King Faume still being alive in the Barrows... he's long dead. nnThat silly tribal superstition should rest with him.

Blighted storms beat at the lands of Stonefalls, fiercer than ever before. This one knows it is not natural. There is magic in the wind, in the dark clouds that spread out above us. I have a theory that I am eager to explore.
There's no one here left alive; why shouldn't we find shelter in what they left behind?  The Conclave won't take us back; we must live somewhere.
I'm new to the Lion Guard, but I have faith in its purpose.
Why do you pester me?nnHouse Dres has no time for insignificant matters when the blight spreads so rapidly across these lands!
What's your name, <<1>>?nnAh. Good name. Fine name.nnWell now, <<2>>, I may have what you're looking for.
Welcome to Maleron's Renowned Hoarvor Circus!nnHave you sampled the slouchbear patties at our concession tent?
The Imperials invaded the Colovian trading town of Haven. They're moving north and digging trenches around my village.
The body of Treethane Dangor lies before you. Beneath the blood splatters you can see strange runic symbols carved into his skin. It appears this problem took care of itself....
These days, no one comes in or out of Kragenmoor without proof of health.  House Dres - Divines bless them - built that Blightfence for a reason.
Fair tidings to you, dear gentleperson.
Hey. Hey you there. Yeah, I'm talkin' to you, you... ugly-face! Yeah. Heh heh.nnGet your face out of my head!
The harbor is closed until the Tribunal contains this disease. nnNo cargo can enter or leave <<1>> without a proper inspection.
Affliction! Nix-hounds! Mewling foreigners at our gate. Who knows what will darken our next dawn?nnSo you made it here alive, and through all of that! No ordinary soul you are. That I swear.

Oh, another who seeks my company?nnDo not look at me so. I was simply brought here to raise the morale. Listening to the tales they weave, praising their strength, and warming their beds.  In return they let me know their secrets their fears.
I'd kill them all if I could. Tear their filthy faces off and feast on their corpsesnnHm, apologies. I get a bit angry when thinking about our current situation.
That old man thinks he can keep me away from what's rightfully mine.nnAre you going into Necris?nnIf you have a moment to listen, I have a proposition for you.
Without having to look over my shoulder all the time, I can finally have some rest.
Hard to pull tree out of ground, yes? Hard to push tree over, no? Take saws from men, they stop cutting trees.
The liberation of Yoon! nnThe confounding of Imperials!nnGreat joy.
It's hot here on the docks, but I'd rather work here than beyond the city gates.
You traversed a dangerous path to find me.  I will hear you.
It's hot here on the docks, but I'd rather work here than beyond the city gates.
It's hot here on the docks, but I'd rather work here than beyond the city gates.
We must stay alert. Invaders could strike at any moment.
If I'm going to be posted outside the town someday, I'll have to concentrate on my training.
We train as many soldiers as we can.nnUnfortunately, the more we train, the more we need. Our work never ends.
Please! Help me.nnI'll die like the others if you can't get me out of here.
At this rate, I won't be able to set up shop until the next moon!
Who're you? I haven't seen you in the ranks before.
Greetings, stranger. Any suspicious activity to report?
Long ago, I fought the Alessian Order at the Battle of Glenumbra Moors. nnThe time of the Direnni Hegemony is long past, but our charge to protect this kingdom remains.
Who are you? You're not a Red Rook. What are you doing here?
I love festivals this time of year!

My mother is going to be enraged when she finds out what I've been up to. Submitting to the Wardens is going to save me from her wrath.nn The Wardens understood my situation and I am going to help them in any way I can. nnThank you, <<1>>.
You!nnI should have never listened to you. I overhear that buffoon over there telling his men that I'm going to get tortured.nnI should have stayed with the Red Rooks.
The Great Houses look down on the poor and destitute, but we were meant to serve and protect them. nnHow can I turn my back on them?
The Wood Orcs appear to tolerate the Imperials - their alliance must be prevented.nnIf an Imperial were to insult the Orc Chieftan...
I'm out of stock at the moment. I'm expecting a shipment from Deshaan sometime next week.nnThe only good thing about this affliction is that it's driven up sales for alchemists and apothecaries.
I did not call upon you, Imperial.
Did that bastard Sakoth-ja send you? No? Good.nnDo you have business with me, then?
By the light of Arkay! I can't imagine why you've come here, but please listen - you must help me!
Lledas! Don't leave me! nnI can't go on without you.
One of the prisoners escaped - a priest named Lotheri. Find him! He will be able to help us.
Darkness take me! The pain is too great to endure.
May your deeds please the Three.
This is too much work for an army, let alone one man!
You there!nnYou can see me? Oh, please help me. I was part of a terrible accident.
I'm sure I can't be of help. Perhaps you should talk to someone else?
Diviner Andalii sent me to attend to the many pilgrims who have come for the Temple's blessing, but I... cannot do as she asks.
I think... you have something for me. Do you bear the love letters, my friend?
If you are going to the temple, could you ask someone to attend to us? We've come so far to be seen....
If you are going to the temple, could you ask someone to attend to us? We've come so far to be seen....
If you are going to the temple, could you ask someone to attend to us? We've come so far to be seen....
Werewolves are the worst kind of foe. nnIt's hard to stab something in the back when it can smell you twenty paces away.
You might think of me as a curiosity. Yes, I'm a talking wolf. nnIt's a curse I've lived with for years now. Can you help me exact my revenge?
Excuse me, do you work here? nnThis asylum has truly fallen into disrepair.nnYou ought to be ashamed of yourself!nnOh, apologies. I just assumed from your dress that you were hired help.
Almost there! I think I can see the gatehouse!

The merchants here think we'll overlook shady business practices while Davon's Watch is in crisis. nnI am here to state quite demonstratively that this will not be tolerated.nnThe law is always the law.
Hail and welcome! Have you given your thanks to the benevolence of the Almsivi today?
I escaped thanks to your help. I am glad to see you have returned as well, <<1>>.
Do not meddle in matters that do not concern you, s'wit.
You'd best leave before the Ordinators falsely accuse you as well!

Free, yet still chained to this accursed city... I cannot leave without my belongings!nnI have no friends here, and no one else will lend me aid. Please, good stranger, help me find my belongings so I may return to the marshes.
House Dres depends on me not to be distracted by idle banter. State your business and I will see what I can do for you.
I will not rest until that serpent is put down!
<You've found a dead body. Closer examination reveals the early signs of lycanthropy... and the grim telltales of a suicide. It's holding a note.>
Business is slow today, friend, so I've time for a quick word or two.
If you value your hide, turn around and head back to whatever hole you crawled out of. nnThis place isn't too friendly to newcomers.
We are looking for bergamont seeds.nnIt's a common plant and has pink flowers with green leaves. There should be a bit of it around the Tarn.
What is it like to be out of breath? Shadowhiskers wonders this, never tiring himself.
Praise Mara! A rescue!nnYou're the first person we've seen in Camlorn who hasn't been turned into a werewolf.
By the Green! A living, breathing being. How did you get in here?nnWait a moment... my barrier! What have you done?
We're holding a teleportation portal open in case there are any survivors in Camlorn. We could use your help.

Great!nnNow we can get started on making the potion. Just take a drop from the purple vial on the table and a dash of reagent from the sack on the ground.nnCombine those both in the alchemy set along with the bergamont seeds you collected.
Being suspended in the air was quite comfortable, but alas, there are riches to be burgled. nnYou should investigate the Molag Bal temple to the north.
By the Three, my rights and duties.  What business have you here?
I have no time for the unworthy.
I'm afraid I can be of no help to you. You should seek the counsel of another.
Here I have the finest wines anywhere.  Come and taste, stay and buy!
I left off soldiering to become an innkeeper.  Prosperity and an easy life, I thought.  Then the Blight came.  In the end, all you can do is laugh.  How can I help you, my friend?
Have you come for diamonds?  Maybe some glass or emeralds?  I just got in a shipment of beautiful ebony; you must see it to appreciate it.
I'm ready to drive the Altmer all the way back to Summerset!
I'm tired of being stuck here. I want to retake that tower. nnI want to drive those mongrels back into the sea!
I hope you're here to help. We need to light that signal fire so can get back to Camlorn.
I hope you're here to help us retake that tower.
I hope you're here to help us retake Farwatch Tower.
I'm tired of being stuck here. I want to retake Farwatch Tower. nnI want to drive those mongrels back into the sea!
I hope you're here to help us retake the tower.
I'm tired of waiting. I'm ready to fight!
As long as House Redoran is keeping Davon's Watch safe, I don't care what happens outside the city. nnThose folks are mostly Ashlanders, anyway.
Dark times, friend.nnI'd stay out of the way of those Ordinators. They're riled up and looking for blood.
What are you doing in my home? Did one of the Great Houses send you?
I can't believe we escaped! Thank you, <<1>>.
I can't believe we escaped. Thank you, <<1>>.
I can't believe we escaped. Thank you, <<1>>.
I cannot believe we escaped. Thank you, <<1>>.
I cannot believe we escaped. Thank you, <<1>>.
The wolf gives you a sad look.
The Blight has devasted the wildlife here. It's terrible.nnI've pledged to help those who remain unblighted however I can.
Please, don't come too close. I would not wish my fate upon you!
The time has come for Black Log to be cured of its Daedric plague.

With the tarn as corrupted as it is, finding food has become very difficult.nnWe've been out here so long that we've run out of provisions. In fact, we've resorted to foraging.nnIf you see something moving, kill it. Then maybe we can eat it.
I've almost finished my apprenticeship with Master Drathal, and now this! Who knew those little kwama beasts could be so formidable?
Ah, many many thanks for your help with that rat, brave <<1>>.  I thought I'd be stuck here for days with that filthy thing menacing me!

We've been tracking <<1>> for weeks. Finally, one of his minions has fallen into our trap. nnI'll enjoy seeing your head on the end of a pike, criminal unless, of course, you're willing to tell us how to find <<1>>.
We've been waiting for this chance for weeks.
The Elder Tree Lifetimber is sending blossoms down from Gil-Var-Delle, but Scamps have appeared to destroy these blossoms. nnThey must be stopped!
What? Did you need something? Ask someone who cares. I suggest looking somewhere over there. nnI'll be keeping a lookout for illegal ale and wine over here.
The Eight walk beside you, traveller.
Distilling is an art form. The flavors must meld, but not be overwhelmed.
The best part about being a guard is finding out where the best parties are!
Yes? Did you have a question, traveller?
The city of Wayrest is truly the jewel of Stormhaven. I'm proud to serve here.
Serving in Wayrest is a privilege. I'm proud to live in such a great city.
Have you got any ale to spare?
