Haven't slept in days, but I feel just fine so long as the ale continues to flow!
I know I'm a long way from home, but I figure as long as I do my job, my life is nice and quiet.nnI do miss the forest, though.
When you live in one of the largest cities in the kingdom, you can gather the best ingredients.nnOh, and being able to hire an assistant certainly helps!
Welcome to Wayrest, stranger! We have an abundance of shoppers and gawkers from all over Menevia.nnI really hope you move along to another city soon.
Where did I put that wineskin?
I can't dance as well as some do, but I certainly enjoy trying!
Seems like the campaign against the ogres never ends!nnI heard they're still close to Wayrest.
Dear me! I've spiilled some wine on my shirt again.
I cannot remember the last time I enjoyed myself so much.
Stay a while, friend. We've got plenty of supplies.
Don't tell the boss I've been tapping into the comberry brandy.
I had no idea Wayrest was such a friendly city! nnEveryone's inviting someone to celebrate something. It's rather nice!
I am so tired from all my socializing. Even when I do sleep, it is without rest.
What is this? One of the flesh aboard our ship? nnThe captain refuses to speak to any who do not swear by the Oath of the Sea.nnDo you know the Oath?
Did you bring me things?  Did you bring me gold or ebony?  Did you bring me silks?  What did you bring me?
I'm enjoying myself more than I have at any other time in my life.
There are many festivities throughout Wayrest these days.
There's nothing more pleasant than a day of wallowing in the mud baths!
Meet me at the hot springs later. We'll have more privacy there.
I'm going to the wine merchant's home for a celebration. You should meet us there!
Later tonight, I'm going to enjoy some quiet time aboard my ship with a lovely lady or two.
My sleep is troubled, so I'm not troubling to sleep!

That's right. I have a Breton name. I sing Breton songs, and I craft Breton lutes and drums. I actually enjoy it more than bashing in goblin heads with a jagged piece of metal.nnI'd rather sing about bashing in goblin heads.
The nobles can have their wine. It's not strong enough for an Orc!
It's not time to get up yet. Let me sleep a little longer.
The fools drank themselves into a stupor last night. It's a wonder we still have our goods intact.
Greetings, stranger. If you have the time, I would like to learn more about you.
It's so difficult to find a decent intoxicating beverage these days.
Strong fermented drinks are acceptable within the Green Pact's rules! nnBring on the ale!
I had no idea the Bretons were so friendly! They keep inviting me to their homes for little festivals!
I've never been happy living so far away from Morrowind, but the people of Wayrest have been very welcoming.
By Saint Veloth! The ground sways as though we're standing on Red Mountain during a tremor!
You don't have any sweets to spare, do you?
Where did you come from? Do they have more ale there?
Does your blood run as hot as mine does? I must cool off. nnPerhaps some ale will help.
What brings you to Wayrest, friend? nnWant to meet for an ale later, or would you prefer something stronger?
I haven't had enough to drink today. I'm still standing.
The war has taken many lives, but that's not the worst of it. Innocent souls are being raised as undead.nnThere is no greater affront to Arkay. We must put a stop to this blasphemy.
I didn't think my cart would give out so quickly.nnI wonder. Should I turn back to Davon's Watch or continue on to Ebonheart?
Greetings, traveler! I'm not just here to drink. I'm here to buy and sell.nnDoing business here was the best idea I've ever had.
Something to sate your hunger and slake your thirst, friend?
I was sent here to scout Barkbite - to learn if the Orcs and Imperials are working together.
The pain wracks every part of my body. I've not long for this world. If only I could see my wife again...
Thank you! Oh gods above, thank you!

I was taken captive by the Blacksap. They were marching me up to Gil-Var-Delle from Brukbrook - they were going to sacrifice me!nnA brave hero took pity and set me free. Now I wait, hoping they will some day return here.
Nothing to see here. Move along.nnThat means "I better not see your face around here again."
It tastes like music. It's like the Temple chorus!
You don't look like a Bloodthorn cultist. I assume this is a rescue attempt?
Thanks, friend. But I'm not the cult's only prisoner.
I have to give it up. I must give it up.nnThis is the last time.
May the Eight bless you, traveler.
Watch yourself. This place is thick with Bloodthorn cultists.
Welcome, welcome, to Graylin's Little Shop of Pleasures!nnWe have everything you need here. You want it, we got it. It just comes down to a matter of... payment, of course.
You can't pass through he- hic! Here.
There's work to do. Training these new recruits would usually take me years, but the front lines are calling them now.
This is not a place for the living. nnAhji was badly injured trying to retrieve the Werereaver.
Greetings, newfound friend! What are you bringing to our festivities?
I can't sleep. I should probably find a place to drink instead.
Cannot find quality skooma anywhere beyond Elsweyr. nnCannot find... need to find something. Lost. Cannot find it.nnNeed sweet.
Well, what have we here? A traveler? nnNeed some companionship?
Want to fight? No? nnThen leave me alone!
The rich think they own the hot springs outside of Wayrest.nnThey don't! I've been there many a time myself!
I'm really honored to get first-hand training from you.nnI'll follow wherever you lead.
Looking to collect my head, are ya? I'm thinking that reward will remain unclaimed.

You are standing at the edge of Branglebracken, friend. This is where the local Bosmer do their hunting.nnWe have an understanding with the forest. We only collect what we need.nnIt is reasonably safe here... as safe as the forest can be, I suppose.
You've returned. I hope you have good news.
It looks to speak with me?
Find a deep hole to die in.
Oh, you're just the hero I've been looking for! I'm under an awful curse! Won't you save me?
How... how did I get out here?nnI know I was on my way to Aldcroft, but I just can't remember what happened.
Welcome to the bank of Wayrest. You can trust our security and discretion.
You don't leave town without proper equipment, do you? What can I get you?nnChoosing the right gear can be a matter of life and death!

Well hello there! I'm sorry it's a bit of a mess in herewe're doing some remodeling.nnI have a wide assortment of goods that might interest you. I might have to move some things around, but would you care to take a look?
Sure are a lot of people around here! It's a pity there aren't more mages.nnWhat can I do for you?
My father, Noah Georence, crafts the finest armor in Stormhaven.nnSo  are you here to admire his handiwork, or are you going to actually buy something? Let's make a deal.
After years in the army, I can tell you nothing is better than some solid protection when you're in a fight.
We're here to do something important, but I can't remember what it is.
There is nothing more interesting than seeing everyone else suffering after a party. It's rather amusing.
My feet are killing me. I've been walking across Wayrest from house party to house party for weeks!
Wine always gives me a headache. It's ale or nothing for me.
It pains me to remain, but I must not leave my duties unfinished.
You'd best stay back from our camp, friend, unless you're willing to risk catching the Blight.
We don't want any trouble. nnWe're just trying to survive for as long as we can, until the Tribunal finds a way to rid their followers of this blight.
I can't take the pain anymore, Garma! nnPlease, end my suffering before I go mad with agony.
I Rez every 15 seconds.suck it up and wait!
The guide stands immobile, frozen by a layer of sulphuric crystal.
The guide stands immobile, frozen by a layer of sulphuric crystal.
The Ashlander Champion stands immobile, frozen by a layer of sulphuric crystal.
What are you willing to learn today?
How can I help you today?
What will you learn about yourself today?
I can teach you much, but only if you're willing to learn.
Come. Learn what I have to teach you.
I teach the essential skills of a ranger.
Let us prepare a mnemonic ritual together. I will teach, and you will learn.
I am highly skilled in my craft. I can teach you a thing or two....
You will learn much from me, but only if you pay attention!
Many pursue the arcane arts, but few truly master them.
Few master the arcane arts, but many students pursue them.
Too much heavy armor gets in the way. I'd rather rely on swift weapons.nnThe enemy can't hit you when they're already dead.
Sometimes, I forget that my fellow mages are not my minions.
Yes? Can I help you with something deadly?
The Eight are all the armor I need, but heavy plate certainly helps.
Some question why we choose to heal others instead of hurting them.nnAnyone who has lost a friend or loved one should never ask that question.
Armor is for those who can't learn how to avoid being hit.nnI can teach you how to take down anyone in armor.
Anyone can pick up a sword.nnLearning to wield it properly requires dedication and constant practice.
I'll get stronger. I swear it.
Knowing that Wood Orc raiders have been looting Karthdar since the Imperials left burns at me.nnBefore I was injured, no Orc dared harass a Bosmer within a day's march of Moss Lord!
I love Danae, but I can't leave my home. nnI've lived in Stonefalls my whole life. I don't know anywhere else to go.
Tolvia, let's just get out of Stonefalls! There's nothing but death here nowadays. nnMaybe maybe we could finally settle down in Mournhold.
My, a traveling adventurer. Do you never tire of all that running about?
Please let me be. I must concentrate on the escape portal for Camlorn survivors.
All my focus must be on the portal. Please leave.
I can't talk now. Holding this portal open takes intense focus.
I thought my luck had finally run out. It seems I owe you my life, <<1>>.
My family has looked after this city of the dead for generations.
If you've come to use the docks, you're too late. They're closed until further notice. nnYou can direct any complaints you have to House Redoran.
I won't survive long if I don't slip past these Orcs. nnInside my house, there's a potion on my shelf. Bring it to me.
This Dunmer wears the garb of a sailor.
Even in these trying and dangerous times, my beloved Asharom and I travel all of Stonefalls to find the best merchandise for you.  Stop and buy - you will not find such quality and value anywhere.
Greetings, greetings.  My Fadron and I have many fine wares here.  Come and see.  Armor from Shalk chitin.  Very nice snake leather shoes.
The blight makes travel difficult, and prices may rise accordingly.  For you, special prices, of course.
The blight makes travel difficult, and prices may rise accordingly.  For you, special prices, of course.
Who are you? You aren't one of those Ordinators, are you?
I wonder if they'll still pay us.
Qa-Dur thought that he could escape his slavery when the mine was taken over.  Sadly, this is not the case.
I'm a miner, not a soldier.  I can tend and harvest eggs better than anyone but fighting for my life?  I didn't sign up for that.
I thought I was dead when I saw you coming toward me, but I guess you're not a poacher.nnNo job is worth this. I quit!
Someone has been dumping these bodies in the tarn.nnMost of the bodies are on the northern end of the lake. nnThat makes me fear for the people who live north of here.
The <<1>> has heard my cries and summoned me!

I was wrong in my judgment. Too many have treaded upon these grounds seeking to disrespect those who rest here. nnYou are free to journey through Othrenis from here on forth. Be warned, many others besides our own guard occupy this ground now.
Eugene Frendrick, at your service. I assume you're not out here for sightseeing.nnThe lake has been corrupted, and I've been asked to find out why. nnI'm ashamed to say that I haven't had much luck.
Hnngh. You are small. But you will do.
Ah, to have failed at my most sacred duty! I cannot die like this!

Are you looking to restock your wares, traveler? nnI'll only be here for a short time before I continue on to my next area. If you are looking to buy or sell, this would be the best opportunity for you!
War should be exciting, but all the Altmer do is sit around and plan. It's hurting Bosmer morale. We like action!nnYou look like a quick one... you might be able to lift our spirits!
Cast off by the only ones I knew my life is forfeit. There is no salvation for me. Leave me to die.
We stayed in the mine as long as we could.  I need my pay as much as the next man, after all.  But in the end, I like my life more.  There's little we can do now.
Please, you must help me. I think they plan to use me for something horrible.
This body was altered after its death and has an unnatural hue.  nnThe vine nearby seems to be feeding of this body.
You've got to help me! They're going to kill us all for their sick rituals!
There's a lot to be done around here, but not much I can help with. That makes me feel a little useless.
May the Eight watch over you.
It's bad enough that these hairless dogs keep us enslaved.  Worse still when there is no work to do and no pay for anyone.  We must retake this mine, and soon.
I do not wish to speak. I need some time to think about what happened.
Leave me alone. I've suffered enough!
What is it? Have you news of my family? Did they make it out okay?
Go away! Let us heal in peace.
We're just trying to make a bit of coin, friend. nnHow were we supposed to know the treasure was cursed? It's not like the dead needed it!
We need healing, not curiosity-seekers. If you really want to help, talk to one of soldiers out there.
Be wary when you leave the tomb. The necromancer's foul magic still infects the dead outside these walls. In time, perhaps, this will be a place of rest again.
I brought the Ordinators back with me, thinking you would need aid. It seems I underestimated your prowess!
Curse you and your ilk! Rathell will rise again, and you will rue the day you came to this place!
Have you ever seen such hideous artifacts? One cannot help but admire the work they put into their experiments, no matter how vile they may be.
I'll never get these remains separated at this rate. How are we to put their spirits to rest when they are but a pile of bones in a corner?
It's a good thing you came when you did. There's no telling what horrors these crazed zealots would have conjured up, given enough time.

Fascinating. Amazing! nnTo stand for so long and still be in such pristine condition. The Dwemer were certainly remarkable! nnThe Mages Guild will surely accept us when we bring them the results of these tests!
Shaali is too impatient, and she's far too free with her tales of hunting.
For weeks, we've hunted three "eaters-of-mer." They're animals that delight in killing our children and elders. nnFor weeks, we've been outmatched.nn<<1>>! <<2>>! <<3>>! I curse your names!

In times past, the Wise Woman would consult with our ancestors - our most sacred guides.nnBut even as I have asked her, she refuses to invoke their presence, saying they are a distraction in these trying times.

Fascinating. These creatures respond when I channel various tones to them.nnSee this one? It moves in an odd rhythm when I channel this talisman's emanations at it. nnSurely this discovery will gain me an audience with the Mage's Guild!
You are not known to me. What are you doing amongst my children?
Who dares summon me without proper ceremony? What right do you have to be in our home, stranger?
I would not have thought a stranger would know the ways of our tribe. What compels you to summon me?
Those poor folks up in Camlorn didn't have a chance.
Let's take the fight to Angof!
My sword is at your service.
You're alive. Good news for you, I guess.
That cliff racer queen had us pinned down for far too long; we had little hope of survival until you came.  Thank you again.
Under sun and sky, friend.  I owe you my life.
You're not a Jaqspur! How'd you get up here?
The conclave... so sheltered, so naive. They know nothing of what goes on here. I almost pity them!
Whatever you can spare will certainly be appreciated. nnMy children haven't eaten a decent meal in far too long.
You do not seem ill. nnThough all are welcome, you may want to seek shelter elsewhere. nnContagious citizens enter these halls seeking aid. I would not think of turning them away.
The troops could use your support in the north, under Leaftower.
Oooooh, have I got some stories for YOU.
Greetings again, friend! Thank you for your help in clearing me name.nnSee, Jivon! I told you the Ordinators were mistaken!
I have failed my beloved Andre! He died to save me, and I cannot fulfill his last wish.nnMay Arkay let me live long enough to see this through....
These docks aren't safe for anyone anymore. What, are you here to rob me too?
You look like you're strong and capable. Would you be willing to do me a favor?
I don't see how we have anything to talk about.
Look at all the lights...they are so beautiful...
Look at all the lights...they are so beautiful...
Look at all the lights...they are so beautiful...
Look at all the lights...they are so beautiful...
Look at all the lights...they are so beautiful...
I'd like to be in the fight against Angof, but Marcel is too important to risk.
Don't have time to talk. They'll fall upon us any minute now, and we've got nothing but pitchforks and sticks.
Irresponsible youths! nnI have them to thank for my injuries. nnI should be seeing to Orlishkaarn agitators, not chasing our own ordinators and investigating necromancy!

The Akavari Battlebarge to the north draws a great interest from the Mages Guild. To think of the secrets that sit upon that boat; to think of what we could learn from them! Thus the reason we were sent here.nnA shame we cannot get to the barge.

That ship holds far too many secrets to be just left sitting about. A good thing those damned fire creatures have taken up residence on it. Keeps all the good for nothing scavengers out.nnCourse, it's keeping us out too!

The Magmer are drawn to the flames in which they were created - not to a vassal that has been washed up during our last war. Residing upon this ship is not their doing. Something must be drawing them there - something the Akavari left behind.

Please, help me! I am but a lighthouse-keeper who helps slaves in need.nnI've gotten this far from the lighthouse, but even so, my warnings will come far too late. If you have but a bit of compassion, listen to my story!
Hold there, stranger.nnWhat business do you have in this watchtower?
If I am correct, which I hope I am not, the horror that caused this devastation was summoned nearby.
I can't believe this happened. All I have left is the clothes on my back.
I don't care what you've been told about me. I just lost everything I had in life, and I'm not in the mood.
There are no apparant signs of death on the corpse of the young Ordinator. He wears a medallion that identifies him as an Ordinator.
What? I've done nothing wrong! Sure, I'm not a patient here, but...nnWait, you don't belong here either. Interested in helping a fellow out?
Not enough time. The night comes, and with it our doom.nnI must not sleep, lest the voices come again.
Gods above, why can't these were-beasts see they are not welcome here?
Welcome! Welcome!nnYou look quite healthy, I must say.nnNo symptoms yet? Or are you just visiting?
What a tragedy!nnI came to this cursed place to meet with my love. He's fallen ill with corprus.nnHe told me to meet him by the tower, but he't not here!
You! You're not one of the guards. nnAre you a patient here?nnPerhaps we can help each other!
<You've found a dead body.>nn<This Dunmer's remains show symptoms of the Blight, but he has a wide smile on his face.>
<You've found a dead body.>nn<This Dunmer's remains show symptoms of the Blight, but she has a wide smile on her face.>
This site right here was where one of the war's biggest battles would have transpired.  I say 'would have' because it was in the midst of this battle that the volcano up there erupted.
We've been working on excavating this site for some time now.  We're on the verge of proving Aldanis' theory that it was indeed the Argonians who caused the volcano to erupt.

While my colleagues at the main camp delve into the mysteries of the Akaviri battle barges, I lead this team of experts in my quest to prove that it was indeed the Argonians who caused the fateful volcanic eruption that ended the battles here.
Imperials to the north. Blacksap to the east. I hate to admit it, but we need the Dominion right now.
What are we going to do?
Welcome to our camp. Carelleth calls it Residue.nnI suppose there's a joke in there somewhere. Y'ffre take me if I know what it is.

I can't believe the Blacksap would attack Brukbrook like that. They weren't trying to steal ransom items, or rustle our slouchbears, or replace a dead tribe member.nnAnd I know they weren't bored. It doesn't make sense!
I don't suppose you want to buy anything?nnNo one ever wants to buy anything.
Tresspassing on my boat, distracting the cabin boy Give me one good reason I shouldn't gut you now, s'wit.
Ten cases of the Blight were confirmed here in Ebonheart.  There have been three deaths already.  Quarantine is a necessary evil; it protects everyone.
I feel fine.  I swear.  It's just that I'm tired from working on the docks.
Don't get too close, friend.  I'm not sure what sickness has taken me, but I fear it's the Blight.  What will I do
I can barely take care of my business here.  I know I should rest, but there's so much to do
My sister took sick a few days ago, and I followed not long after.  I've been using this curative Tonas the Apothecary gave me, but it doesn't seem to do anything.
Stay out!  Get out of the house. Get out of here, unless you want to wind up like me!
What do you want?  I'm busy today.  I don't have time to talk to people.

We cannot cure this disease.nnNo matter what remedies the charlatans purport to have, all we can do is ease the suffering of the afflicted.nnThen when it's time, we'll have to say Mara's blessings over the dead.
Sorry, I'm quite busy at the moment.
Hello. Hello! Who are you...?nnI am <<1>>. I am not a werebeast. They are here though. The beasts, they rule this village. I do not approve.
Who do you think you're talking to, s'wit? Best step away, before you find a knife between your ribs.
You'd best not get involved. I owe her some money.
You don't have much time left!  The Blight has arrived in Ebonheart, and if you want to escape a certain death, I can help you with one of my many potions
Gone! My Farvyn is gone!nnWhat life will I have without her?
This one is on pilgrimage.  Do you see that tree?  That Hist Tree is very important to the People of the Root.  This one's people.
Thank the Divines!nnHelp me out of here before the hags see you. I think they're planning something terrible!
Are you are you from Virak? Have they finally sent someone for me? You must get word back and soon the Ashlanders - they prepare to overtake the Fort!
Are you are you from Virak? Have they finally sent someone for me? You must get word back and soon the Ashlanders - they prepare to overtake the Fort!
This is a war not just for the lives of my people, but for their very souls.
Oh, how things have gotten worse. Here I thought we hit the bottom, that things were improving.
Infernal beasts! I'd clip their wings and throw them from this mountain if I could.nnAh, welcome to the Iliath Temple. Please be wary of the cliff racers that plague these cliffs.
We must rid Crosswych Mine of the undead. That should give hope to the townsfolk. nnOnce their hope is renewed, anything will seem possible again.nnI have a plan, but need help executing it.
My life wastes away at this temple.nnI feel naught but emptiness in my heart when I pray to the Tribunal.nnWhat if they're nothing but a myth?

We've traveled the lands searching out Dwemer Ruins for what seems like weeks now, but never have I seen a Daedric foce like this just come rushing out of Oblivion knows where. They're looking for something all right but what?

Just one more step and we would have been inside the ruins! We were so very close to a great discovery, I just know it! nnUnfortunately with the appearance of the Daedric creatures, we've had to sit and wait, hoping that they will just up and vanish.
It is not often the prey walks into the predator's mouth. What are you doing here, brave hare?
Goreclaw taunts us. He offers freedom to anyone who can survive the gauntlet and beat him in combat. nnNo one has made it through the gauntlet.
We don't know what hell is about to come through that thing but we could use all the help that we can.
Glenumbra will not fall on our watch.
What sort of fool are you, treading in the lair of the Huntress? Flee if you dare. She will catch you same as all the others.
It is not often the prey walks into the predator's mouth. What are you doing here, brave hare?
What am I doing? Nothing, certainly nothing suspicious!nnOh, you aren't a guard. What a relief.
Keep your voice down if you want to keep your head.nnI should apologize. You are not from House Dres. nnI can see you've got more of a spine than they do. Are you interested in helping a slave?
What business do you have up here?

It's good that Camlorn is built the way it is... and it's bad. There's less chance for those werewolves to sneak out and escape, but it's fortified, so we can't easily make a direct assault.nnIt's a stand-off for the moment.
Some of those wolves are former citizens of Camlorn. We can't let that stop us from doing what has to be done.

Duke Sebastien sent for the Lion Guard as soon as he reached Aldcroft. It's a good thing he did! We could keep the wolves from rampaging across the countryside, but that's about it.nnWe need help to eliminate them entirely.
The werewolves are unnatural, even for their kind. They say the wolves are minions of a Reachmage. That's why they don't need to wait for a full moon before they enact their evil schemes.
Aldcroft will be next if Camlorn cannot be saved. It's small, but a good port for a city of Camlorn's size.nnI know we'll be able to stop the wolves. It's just a question of when.
My husband and I had a small villa in Omaynia before the uprising. nnI've never seen such rampant violence!
I thought Heimlyn Keep would be a safe place for my family to weather the storm. nnUnforunately, the madness has reached Dres' highest point.nnIt's time to get out of Stonefalls altogether.
I'm cursed, doomed to die by another's hand! I've seen the signs, the looks people give me, the whispers... it's only a matter of time!
Help me, please. I can't see... can't see....

I worry for our future, despite the Gulakhan's outlook. nnI've lived in Stonefalls my entire life. I know the hunting grounds here. nnHow can I hunt effectively in Deshaan without knowing anything about it?
I hear the anguish from every living creature in Stonefalls. This land is cursed, and we must flee. You would do well to flee as well.
I hear Davon's Watch is even worse than this place. nnThat's scary.
May the Three protect you on your travels.nnYou'll need their blessings in Ebonheart.
Watch your back in Ebonheart. nnThis has always been a rough town, but now the criminals don't even try to hide what they're doing.
I didn't think I'd see another living soul before the end.nnIt's too late for me. I can feel the darkness closing in around me.

What curious flora! nnI'm sure the Mages Guild would be ecstatic to see the specimens I've collected! nnTruly, the Blight creates a wondrous number of altered and variegated life forms for me to study!
I am humbled by your grace, Silvenar.
I don't know how much longer I can last. I don't want to die like this!
We've heard people are being healed at the Iliath Temple. It's not far from here, but getting there is a challenge nonetheless.
The future is uncertain. In times like this, we must rely on the guidance of our ancestors.
Glad tidings, stranger. nnYou are welcome to what we have, but I must ask that you not indulge in mischief. nnWe have our own trials to withstand.
The Farseer does not know how much danger we're in. nnWe were foolish to not follow the others and leave this accursed land.
If you have nothing to trade, I must ask you to move along. nnThe Farseer has little time for idle banter.
Blast this wheel! nnIt held up all through the Grieving Grounds and the ruins up north. Now it breaks on a pothole here?nnWhat cursed luck I have.

I hope you do not seek refuge at the temple to the east, stranger. All that waits there are false worshipers who are soon to be punished by the order of Illiath Temple. nnThough it pains me to slay one who does not threaten me, I do what I must.
I think I broke my leg when my cart overturned. nnBy the ancestors! Let it just be a sprain!
We'll be out of Stonefalls soon, I hope. This place holds nothing but pain and death.
The Gulakhan risked much to guide us out of our home. She is braver than any of the Dunmer of the Houses!

Please, do not disturb my brothers and sisters during our worship to the Lady Meridia. For many this is their first time to this shrine. I would not have it be disturbed by the chatter of a stranger if you can control your tongue.
Why would you bother the Silvenar?
Hrr. <RACE> you may smell and <<1>> you may be, but to us you are just meat.
Troublesome descendants!nnFor so many years, we rested in peace and silence.nnNow one lowly distant cousin has rousted the entire family into furor.
I've lost my comb! My beautiful little ebony comb!nnHave you seen it?
We will fight and die on this bloodied field!nnFor our Great House, for our noble family, for each other!nnTo arms, my soldiers! To arms!
If I could only hear the sound of my own thoughts, but these horrible little cousins won't be quiet...
I can't sleep! Let me sleep!nnDid I not earn my rest in my time walking above? Did I not earn this tomb's restful slumber?nnWhy can I not rest?
The Gulakhan is gone. I wish the Farseer would have reconsidered her decision.nnPerhaps I should have followed the Gulakhan.

Since the Farseer and the Gulakhan parted ways, our tribe has been a shadow of its former self. nnThe Farseer insisted on staying in Stonefalls. I hope the rest of the tribe survives the journey to Deshaan.
Welcome to Heimlyn Keep, the stronghold of House Dres in Stonefalls. I'm afraid if you wish to talk business, you should schedule a meeting with someone working in Kragenmoor.
Oh, hello. I'm afraid you'd have to talk to my masters if you need your horse stabled. House Dres is very particular about who has their animals stabled in the fort.
If I stop to talk to you, I get punished. I've got work to do.
Sorry, I'm in the middle of training.nnCan't talk!
The <<1>> greets us as friends, yes?
This one greets the wayfarer. nnHave you come to bask in the glory of Fel'tha?
Our roots tangle. They gather the children to me. nnThey are all within me, sheltered under our twisted branches.
What sadness you must have! To be a single creature, so isolated! nnOur roots sing to us, comforting us, even in the darkest times.
I wait to see the child of our tree. nnWe are far from the comfort of the Black Marsh, but perhaps it has come here to give us hope.
The Redorans constantly make false accusations against our Great House.nnThey have no proof. They never have any proof, but the others believe them anyway!
It wasn't really necromancy, I swear.nnThere's a rumor of Solir Nath family treasure.nnI hoped I could awaken my ancestors, so they could tell me about it.

Please! You must help me! You must make these two stop before they hurt each other! Why did we come this way... it's all my fault. I should have never mentioned it, never! Stop it you two! Stop it! Please, stranger, please help me!
I was bound, but now am free. What magic have you unearthed to perform this deed?
House Dres takes pride in protecting Kragenmoor. I wouldn't want to live anywhere else!
Kragenmoor is the safest place in Stonefalls now. I don't plan to leave here until the Blight dies down.

Please! You must help me! You must make these two stop before they hurt each other! Why did we come this way... it's all my fault. I should have never mentioned it, never! Stop it you two! Stop it! Please, stranger, please help me!
Watching the bandits destroy my farm was a heartbreaking experience.nnWhen the Red Rook Bandits are done, I may never be able to grow crops here again.

I lived on that farm with my son, Depaul, for many years.nnAll we have now are a few simple belongings. We weren't even able to take our valuables with us. nnI lost a necklace my love once made for me. That pains me almost as much as losing the farm.
Thank you again for saving me, <<1>>.  I hope that the rest of my scouting party finds their way back to camp sometime soon.
<You've found a dead body. Sharp claws ripped it open from stomach to neck.>
I pray you have no relations at rest here.nnNecris has been beset by necromancy.nnNo spirits will find rest here as long as the source remains unchecked.
Have you seen that lovely woman singing in the swamp?
Thank you for finding Adradan.nnEventually, he found his way here after he was done getting himself into trouble.
Living guests at my party? Wonderful! Welcome, friends! It is a pleasure to be your host, and an honor to have such exotic company as yourselves.
I'm sorry, the party is inside. Things are a bit busy out here.
One of Angof's undead knifed me in the back while I was out searching for a friend. Don't suppose you'd be willing to help out?
Josaja feels weak. The swamp is blurry - both hot and cold.
The delightful rush of wind. The searing pain of landing head first.
Light and leaf! What's a <<1>> like you doing out here?

These Orcs are doing more than just harassing travelers passing through Haven Trace.nnI can hear them mining in that cave. I've noticed tools in their camps.nnOrcs are lazy. They don't mine if they don't have to... so what are they doing in there?
Be wary. We don't know what we're up against.
So  cold. I can't imagine a worse fate than to be trapped here. Waiting  watching  feeling.nnThat's the worst. I can feel my flesh. It craves destruction. It craves blood.
Wishing he was not a coward.nnLonging for delicious fruits. nnAgonizing because he cannot reach them!
The signal fire... I couldn't light it in time... I wasn't strong enough....nnDid Crestshade even know what descended on them that fateful night?
You seem different, my love. Has our time apart worn at your heart?
Watching you from the trees above.nnTelling Elder Brump of your bravery.nnWill the <<1>> be honoring Cliffvoot as one of its sentries?nnThe status! The glory! The extremely light duties!
Acting as elder until Brump returns.nnImagining the dread of Brump's misfortune! nnContemplating Shoof's fear of the unknowable.
Knowing the reputation of the <<1>>. nnWatching you from tree tops, above Grahtwood.nnWelcome a brave <<1>> to Cliffvoot!
Missing Elder Brump. nnThe wisdom of his advice!nnThe grooming of his pelt!
Warning the <<1>> not to swim down the waterfall. nnNot wanting to fish for corpses.
I lost my livelihood after Ormax let me go.nnI hear things. Yes, I hear valuable things.nnPerhaps they're valuable to you, yes?

Things are in a bad way here in High Rock. I came from the North where things are even worse than here. I don't have much, but I do have information that might be useful to a person like you... for the right price.
Got no business with you, <<1>>. Let's keep it that way.

No doubt you have already crossed paths with one of my brothers. I joined the Lion Guard to get away from the family business, yet here I am bartering for goods. Ironic, isn't it? I don't have much to offer but feel free to look around if you like.

We were slaughtered by those Montclair dogs. I watched some of our men led away at swordspoint by the enemy.nnI couldn't do anything with my arm like this! It just ... hangs there. It's useless, like me.
Feeling the shame of foolish actions.nnRegretting the loss of precious things!
You! You're <<1>>, right? nnI've been looking all over for you. You have to help us!
My partner and I were on contract to the Mages Guild, before he vanished. Now I'm the only one left to play bodyguard.
The last thing I remember is a wave of darkness washing over me. When it ended, I was here, bound by the cultists.
As much as I'd like to track down who did this to me, I think I'll just call it even and get out of here.
Thank you for cleaning my grave.nnIt's a shame I couldn't be buried with the other knights in the great graveyards of Glenumbra. At least my spirit is blessed with a beautiful view of the ocean.
Good to see you alive, my intrepid friend.
By the Divines! Someone, please rescue me!nnThis place is haunted. Accursed phantasmagoria!

What is this? You're here to steal my fine crafts!nnI'll not give them up to the likes of you! Not when I'm so close to completing my collection. nnI'm missing only one item: a valuable painting of Sera Sofia, a lady knight standing on the cliffs.
The corruption is so strong. I won't last much longer!
Your spirit clings to the mortal plane, as if unable to leave. How is such a thing possible?
Buried in a shallow grave... for what? We were both betrayed by that daedra!
Strike hard, strike fast, and get out. That's how we do things, and you should too.
My wounds are painful, but superficial.nnLuckily, I wasn't bitten by a werewolf, so I won't turn into one of the beasts.
Get back! Get back, you damned vampire! Go find someone else to chew on!nnUnless ... have you come to help me?
So many voices speaking at once....

You've chosen a poor time to visit Lushwallow, stranger.nnThe Peatwalker tribe lives west of here. They've accused our tribe of stealing their totem. They've enacted the Rite of Quarrel, and now the spriggans are attacking us!
The Lion Guard must defeat Angof.
Find your own vein, stranger. This is my prospect.
Eagle's Brook is overrun. We were ambushed. I barely escaped.
<You see the spirit attempt to speak to you, but you hear no words. It points to the ruins to the north.>
The pain... it's too much to bear. nnCurse you, Ranser! Curse you for leading us to this grave!
Stay away from the ruins to the northeast. They're haunted. Ayleid ghosts, they say.
The Red Rook Dockmaster was burned to death in his failed attempt to save the Red Rook Crates.
Look at all the lights...they are so beautiful...
Welcome, stranger. You've come to burgle me away, haven't you?nnI will abide by the Laws of Lushwallow. They dictate that I must follow you peacefully.
The ruins to the north are cursed, traveler.nnStay clear of them.
Just let me find him. I'll kill him.  I'll kill the bastard who took my Leia.
Woe and misery! A spriggan killed our sage!nnThe Laws of Lushwallow allow us to abduct a sage from the Peatwalker tribe in return, but with the spriggans attacking, I'm afraid to leave the village.
No time for talk. One second of inattention, and I'll be a corpse, like the rest.
<Grim's kitten rubs against your hand and purrs.>
<Grim's kitten rubs against your hand and purrs.>
Are you here to help me? Thank the Divines! Faolchu terrifies me! What a horrid beast!
Thank for for saving me from that horrid beast! I hope never to see such a gruesome sight again.
She is impressed with your courage. nnShe might have torn your head off and dined on your entrails. nnNot today.
You took the fight to Faolchu. When they rebuild the inn, the first pint is on me!
You took the fight to Faolchu. When they rebuild the inn, the first pint is on me!
You took the fight to Faolchu. When they rebuild the inn, the first pint is on me.
You took the fight to Faolchu. When they rebuild the inn, the first pint is on me!
You may think it odd, but I knew you were coming. My mistress Raven told me to expect you - a visitor for parts unknown.
Wolves are furry, right?nnDarling? Where's my sword, Gaelle?nnI'll show them... I'll show them all.

We escaped the werewolves of Camlorn, but we lack the pelts and blankets we need to survive this weather. The cold nights might do what werewolves could not!nnTo make it worse, my drunken husband is going to get himself killed trying to get supplies.
You took it straight to Faolchu. When they rebuild the inn, the first pint is on me.
Don't know what we'd have done without your help, <<1>>.
Thanks to you, Ferdie and I will live to tell this tale for many, many years to come.
I don't care if you're lost. You're still not welcome here.
Thank you so much for saving my sister. I'll never let her out of my sight again.
Watch your step. I might have been ill there.nnThose damn mudcrabs took my ale! nnDon't look at me like that. It's the truth.
The creature is surrounded by some sort of magical field being fueled by the Fire Atronachs about it. Perhaps if they were destroyed, the field would dissipate.
I can't hold them off much longer! Help!
If you're not going to kill me, then go away. Let this old soldier die in peace.
Hello there, friend! It's so good to see others out and about. nnAre you're planning on hunting harpies? Perhaps you could do me a little favor.nnYou see, I'm a bit stuck out here....
The creature is surrounded by some sort of magical field being fueled by the Fire Atronachs about it. Perhaps if they were destroyed, the field would dissipate.
These cultists are planning something terrible!nnThey've been keeping us alive just to... feed us to the creatures they've summoned. Please, free me so I can escape!
Y-you c-c-caught up to me? That is n-n-nice.
If they find me, I'm a dead man.
You'll never get both parts of the Talisman!
You'll never get both parts of the Talisman!
What are you doing out here? Have you seen the size of those spiders! nnMe? I have some business to complete. I used to be a smuggler, but that's all behind me now.
We came here seeking a refuge from war. Then we were entangled in a nest of spiders!
My family has lived in Crosswych for many years. I'll do anything I can to help, including giving my life, if it comes to that. nnOf course, I'd rather not, if you know what I'm saying.
You answered the horse clan's prayers. You restored their hope.nnFriend of the Horsemen, it is my honor to speak with you.
The mine is filled with with much more danger than usual.nnI'll just catch my breath before heading back to town.
You saved me from certain death!nnThank you, friend. I'll make my way back to town shortly.
I've been hiding here for so long, my muscles are still cramped. It'll take me a few moments to stretch them out.nnThanks for helping me!
You're a long way from shore, aren't you?
I have been waiting for you, kind mortal.

The damned undead are everywhere. This is as close as I can get to the mine. nnI still need to check the supports. If the supports don't hold, the mine will never reopen, even after the undead are cleared out.
It's good to see a friendly face. I've seen too many angry ones.nn<<1>> dispatched Lion Guard scouts to Merovec's Folly. We need to find sources of magic we can use for enchanting our weapons.
These cultists are planning something terrible!nnThey've been keeping us alive just to... feed us to the creatures they've summoned. Please, free me so I can escape!
I see the fate of all those around me. nnYour fate confuses me. I see you dying a thousand times.nnThat's grim, but my pronouncements are infallible.
Help me! The bandits attacked us. My wife was kidnapped, and my birds... my birds are all lost!
You must help me!  The bandits attacked us and my wife was kidnapped. And my birds!  My birds are all lost... please help!
You must help me!  The bandits attacked us and my wife was kidnapped. And my birds!  My birds are all lost... please help!
You must help me!  The bandits attacked us and my wife was kidnapped. And my birds!  My birds are all lost... please help!
You must help me!  The bandits attacked us and my wife was kidnapped. And my birds!  My birds are all lost... please help!

One who looks upon me with such curious eyes, are you surprised to see a Redguard here? Not even our people are free from the reign of chaos that spreads through Rivenspire. Held here as the others, a special prize for Montclair.
The birds are everywhere, and my betrothed is gone. nnWhat are we to do?

I am the Magnanimous Maelle, the traveling trader. Perhaps you're familiar with my exploits? nnA terrible fate has befallen me. I was jumped by some highwaymen! Those uncouth brutes ran up the path to the right.
I found several baskets with most of their birds inside them.nnYou had good luck, I take it?
Oh, thank goodness you found me.  I didn't think I was ever getting free of these swine!  I can make it back to the caravan now, I think...
Here I am, and not a scratch on me thanks to you!
I'm just... resting here a little while.  Don't mind me.  I'm not a bandit.  Not at all.  Not even a little bit. nnYet.
I see the people who robbed these tombs have discovered the error of their ways. I only hope it's not too late.

I can't believe this madwoman still wants to visit the ruins.nnSure, I'll just slip us through the Imperial lines. That won't be a problem. Bosmer can completely disappear from view by putting a fern on their head, and we can summon tigers at will.
Please delete me if i am not supposed to be here.  Thanks!
You do realize this is a private room, don't you?
Please, don't move me. I'm in too much pain. nnI am not long for this world.
I'm dying, my love.nnGregoire, stay with me a little longer.
You'll want to check your path, friend. Selene's Web is a destination you'll want to avoid. Few have returned alive.
You... you're one of <<1>>'s assistants. Oh, thank goodness! I thought for a moment that he wasn't going to come.
You'll learn respect for your betters, cur!
Thank the Divines, you're back.nnWere you able to help <<1>>?
I barely made it out of Ebon Ro alive, but that won't be a problem much longer.
I lost everything... everything....nnPlease, can you help?
I hope the Razorvine hunters come back soon. I think I saw one of the Colovians eating his shoe.
Please, can you help me?nnI just need a few coppers, so I can get to Wayrest.
There is nothing more important to the Lion Guard than retaking Camlorn for the High King.nnWe will see it done.
Mortal creature, you trespass on the ancient grounds of my children. nnI do not know your intentions, but you should know that I am always vigilant.
Spare some coin for some news, stranger?
The water of this spring is corrupted.
This poor horse caught his leg in a rut running from the damned cats. I can only bandage it and hope it gets better. If worse comes to worse, though, I won't let him suffer.
We have little to trade and few horses to sell. We live off of the land in harmony with the herd.
A friendly face in our little village? That's a good omen!nnDon't mind the others. Many are distraught over the loss of our horses. I know the Herd Mother will look after us, as she always has.
The Dusklight is the finest inn in Hoarfrost Downs. It's also the only inn in Hoarfrost Downs! What can I get you?
I might be down on my luck now, but I hear things now and again.
There's trouble in Rivenspire, that's for certain. Still, for all that changes, much is the same. You can take heart in that.
I've had a long journey here, and I've heard many tales.
Even the main roads aren't safe near Crosswych.
I've had a long journey here, and I've heard many tales.
I've seen so much pain and suffering. I just want to find a safe place to live.
I might be down on my luck now, but I hear things on the street. Important things.
Please help me! I don't want to die like this!
My body's out there somewhere, raised from my tomb by that damned Reachmage, Angof.
<The spirit looks at you for a moment before letting loose with another ear-piercing wail.)
The spirit stares, unblinking. One hand slowly beckons.
One hears many stories, especially when one spends too much time on the streets.
Oh, my dear, sweet daughter. Oh no, oh no... I don't know what I can possibly do!
So... you must be the kind person my mother asked to go find me. Don't you worry - everything's just fine now.
Welcome to Maleron's Hoarvor Circus! Would you like a collectable stone?
You saved me from certain death in the mine, <<1>>. I can never thank you enough.
I never thought I'd be back in this old pub again after getting trapped in the mine.nnThank you, <<1>>, for rescuing us.
We've protected these lands and the Edrald family for years. Now the manorhouse is occupied by daedra and cursed, and here we are camped in our own fields.
It's humiliating, to be driven out of the manorhouse by vile familiars. The Baroness should have stopped her daughter from using daedric magic, before she drove us out and cursed the lands!
We've protected these lands and this family for years, but we didn't have a chance against the Daedra.
After the manor was overrun with Daedric minions, we had no choice but to retreat and set up camp.nnI'd rout those demons myself, but I don't trust the baroness's safety to anyone but myself.
You're runing everything! My mother sent you, didn't she? I suppose it was only a matter of time.
We thought this place was going to be our refuge. Instead, it might be our doom.
All hope is lost. We've fled from one terror right into the arms... I mean, the webs... of another.
The pain ....nnCursed spiders! We never should have come here!
How could we know these ruins were infested with spiders? What will we do now?
I'm still not feeling well, but you have my thanks!
I want to offer my thanks before you leave! nnWithout your help, I would have been dinner for those spiders.
Truly, I cannot thank you enough. You've saved my life.
<You've found a dead body. The remains have decomposed beyond recognition, and its clothes are ripped.>nn<A <<1>> must have made quick work of it.>

Keep your head down!nnMagharz asked us to scout the area and see what kind of trouble our brethren are stirring up. nnNo signs of any activity outside the ruins yet. I'm sure our brother had his reasons to send us here.
Help me!  Oh please help me!  I've been Brethus Tharn's play thing for so long I can't stand it anymore.nnDefeat him and then set me free. I'll make it worth your while!
The Guardians of Elden Grove -- enslaved! Such a thing is unthinkable! These Tharns and their abominations must be stopped!
Greetings <<1>>. I am the Protector of the Grove. There is little time...
Koeglin Village is not the only town to suffer from rampant paranoia. All Alcaire seems affected.
We've protected these lands and this family for years.  But we had no chance against those daedra.
I apologize for my deception.  I had to be sure you were up to the task of dealing with Attelus Tharn. You have passed my test of strength.
Should you need something, I would be happy to oblige.
Stranger, I'm bold to ask, but have you met a man named <<1>> in the neighborhood?
<This man appears to have been enchanted by the spellbook.>
What can I do for you, stranger?
Colovians have a lot of money, don't they? Or at least they did until the Imperials kicked them out of Haven.nnI'm trying hard to have sympathy for them. Really.
I am glad to see you're safe, my friend.nnThose cultists were preoccupied with their shattered anchors. nnThey paid little attention when I slipped away into the shadows.
Yeah, I've got armor. You want to buy some?
Will you be making a deposit today?
You'll find soft beds, a bottomless keg, and good company here.
Jo'dhen spies a discerning eye on this one. The <<1>> will approve of Jo'dhen's fine clothes.
I offer handcrafted weapons from the magical forges of Dusk.
The sly lift of a curious brow. The quiet nod of an agreed upon trade. The luminous glow of a satisfied patron marvelling at their purchase.
Why endanger yourself leaving Elden Root in search of junk? I haul the junk here from the many roads of Valenwood.
The Nevin family has held this land for centuries. I refuse to be the first to let it fall into the hands of those barbaric Nords. nnWe need the mammoth spirits back on our side.
Draw upon my wisdom to sharpen your skills in battle.
Quiet the mind. Bring peace to a battle. Ahnjada will teach you much.
The guards won't let us leave our home, unless they're making us do work for them.
Too much chat and the guards get ornery. Hold your tongue, stranger.
The Ravens fear not even death itself.
Draw upon my wisdom to sharpen your skills in battle.
Looking for a fight or training?nnI will teach you either way.
Never turn your back to a Nightblade, friend. nnHave you come to learn?
Hello. If you have come to learn, Arkay guides you well.
S'Virr watches this one. Have you come for a lesson?
What does this <<1>> want from Khazura?
Come to learn?nnTell me, <<1>>, how deep are your pockets?
Greetings. Are you looking to train?
First, a black cat shows up on my farm. Then the Nords land on our shore. Now I'm hearing rumors of necromancers and vampires.nnThe Nevins' say I'm being paranoid. I don't trust them.
My family has raised herds under the eyes of the Watchers for generations.nnThese days, approaching the shrines is too dangerous for herders.
May the Divines protect you, stranger. nnI feel a great change descending upon our people. I fear for our future.
<You've found the carcass of a mammoth. Someone has impaled it with a Nordic sword.>
The mortal creature wishes to speak. Speak, mortal.
Oh! I'm sorry. I must have been daydreaming.
Halt! Identify yourself! Everyone must tell me. Tell me who you are. Identify yourself.
We fight for Godrun and the Murtag Clan!
While negotiations drag on with the Nords, we should do what we do best.nnWe should go down to the beach and drive them back to Skyrim! We should send them back beaten and bloody.
I must be the luckiest girl in Valenwood! I've finally found my true love, and he's right here in Altmertown. Dear, sweet <<1>>. What an elf he is!
Yes, what is it? I am rather busy, if you don't mind. Conversing with a random stranger is surprisingly low on my priority list today.
Excuse me, but what are you doing in my home? You do know it is considered rude to intrude upon someone's privacy, without invitation? Please. Depart.
Please, browse my wares - they make excellent gifts!
Well! We don't often get visitors down here!
Good weather for fishing, don't you think? And look at those clouds!  You know the old saying: Clouds like mammoths, cast your lines. Clouds like dragons, run and hide.
Not all battles are won by strength alone. It's wiser to think about your options before deciding which road to take.nnThrough careful consideration, you will find that which you seek.
We fight for Godrun and the Murtag Clan!
We fight for Godrun and the Murtag Clan!

I have failed in my duties. Sworn to protect my liege, I set out to guard his family during the attack. When I returned... he was slain. I should have sent my guard with the queen and stood by his side! I should have been the one to fall!

My family starves while I try to gather food from the streets. Please, I beg of you. You must give me anything you can spare. Without it, my poor lil' boy will surely perish! He's starvin' as we speak! Starving!

What am I to do? My father has fallen ill and his health fades rapidly. My mother has already passed on. I've trained for this all my life. To rule in my father's place, but this is not what I want! I should flee, start anew!  A new life.
If we wanted to take Northpoint for our own, we could take it. nnIf the Bretons here are smart, they'll do what we want and avoid trouble.
Anyone too weak to keep what they have deserves to have it taken.
This is most peculiar... that chicken keeps staring at me. How did it even get here?nnWell, I imagine <<1>> will be able to explain it when she returns. I wonder where she has gone off to?
<<1>>, <<1>>, my wayward love. Truly you must care, to lock me away like so. One day you will come and rescue me, won't you my dear?

Those who join the Ravenwatch must have complete control of their bodies. nnThey must be swift and strong. They must be paragons of endurance. nnA fight is not always what it seems. Pay close attention to your surroundings and your enemies.

You can search and search but you'll never find my treasure!  I took it after I ran the ship aground and buried it where you'll never find it!  The cleverest spot, by the rocks near the northwestern Northpoint cliffs - nnoh.  Damn.
The forge is burning bright. Have you come to apprentice yourself to me?
Do you seek training in runecrafting?
Wesh is wanting to share a pattern with you.
I can't go on like this!
Hello, beautiful. nnWon't you dally with me for a while? nnI promise I won't bite.
The Dominion could use a skilled <<1>> on the field of battle.
Your sweat and blood wasn't in vain.
Come to claim a treasure from Jo'Halan? A reward you earned - Jo'Halan is proud to sell to a proven <<1>>.
Greetings little one. Looking to form a guild?
Don these vestiments and honor the Dominion.
Don't forget. Don't let them forget.
If you don't stop moving, I'll tie you to a chair, Murisa!nnHerd Mother grant me the patience to deal with you.
I'm not sure what I'm doing on top of this hill.nnThe weather is quite pleasant, so I suppose it can't be all bad.nnMy name? Well, I can't quite recall it! I'm sure it doesn't really matter.
Welcome to the Cat Box, the best tavern in Tamriel!nnWhat can Ra'Faril get you, eh?
This place has gone downhill since they started serving Altmer.
Hey. nHey. nYou gotta. You gotta whatsit? A drink? nI ordered a drink and never got it. nJust this glass. Got the glass. nWas empty when it got here. I swear.nHeh.
I barely made it out of Moira's Hope with my life. Whatever you do, don't go there!
Imagine that. Mor went all the way to Northpoint to save me! nnNormally, the giants never leave their mountain homes, not even when their lives depend on it.
Care to place a wager on the next fight? It's guaranteed to be a great show!
It hurts! The whole world is going dark. I'm not sure I'm going to make it.
Azura! Heed my prayers! Save Gavaudon from the evil that infects it.nnOnly Azura can save us!
I'm looking for an ogre with a stolen pack. One of the other scouts is wounded, and the bandages are in that pack.

Glad to have more help with our assault. Two houses of <<1>> are finally working together. Damn stubborn lot.nnMalhaven has been reasonably cooperative, but Sayda may become a problem. She seems more concerned with winning glory for House Tamrith
Ho! What are you doing here?nnThese bastards captured me when they attacked Southpoint. But listen - I think I can get out of here. I just need a distraction!
That was perfect! I bet the guards still haven't missed me.
I won't touch it! I won't go near it!nnYou... be careful there! This poor bastard grabbed that glyph... and the next thing he knew, some damn beast was chomping his head off!
By the Eight, where in the blazes am I?
Tired of hearing about the Nord negotiations, or lack of them? I've got more interesting tales to tell, and good wine to wash them down. Pull up a chair, my friend.
I can teach you everything you need to know about interrupting an attack. Only abilities with cast times can be interrupted.

There is no passive defense in ESO. Meaning your character will never randomly dodge, parry or block.nnActive defense, an ability that you activate, is a great way of avoiding damage. Defending can create openings on your target for exploits.
When your target is off-balance you can use an Exploit skill to deal extra damage or buff yourself. Waiting for the off-balance or creating the off-balance is the tricky part.
I might be down on my luck now, but things will surely look up soon.
The mountain pass contains Tier 2 monsters. The main thing to know is how to use your interrupt.nnWait for a long cast time spell or large wind up melee attack and then interrupt the monster.
We'd hoped to settle farther to the west, but it was not meant to be.
There may be vampires and other evils in the world, but we still have fish in the water and crabs on the sand.nnI'm not giving up.
Welcome to the Wayside Inn!nnWhat would you like? Something to sate hunger, slake thirst, or satisfy curiosity?
Something must be done about Godrun, and soon.
Something must be done about Godrun, and soon.
Something must be done about Godrun, and soon.
Something must be done about Godrun, and soon.
Something must be done about Godrun, and soon.
Something must be done about Godrun, and soon.
Welcome to the Wayside Inn. nnWhether it's cold beer or fine wine you prefer, we have it all.
Something must be done about Godrun, and soon.
I used to feel unclean all the time, but I feel much better now.nnSomehow, I feel that I owe you a debt of gratitude!
Why do I have a list of birds in the area? I hate birds!
I'm exhausted from all that walking I've done recently.
We can finally sleep at night without nightmares. nnThe next time I hear voices, I'll know it's just the neighbors fighting again.
So lonely in these halls. I do ever so wonder if I would find someone to keep me... company.
Years have passed since I've felt another's touch.  It's so lonely in these halls. I do ever so wonder if I would find someone to keep me... company.
Please! Please! You must help us!
I'm glad you caught the murderer before Wind Keep turned into a ghost town.
She meant the world to me, but now, we'll never see each other again.nnAt least we won't have other murders like this one. Thank you.
I will rend a hundred Imperials this day!
No matter what's going on in the rest of Rivenspire, we still have a job to do out here. And that's just what we're going to do!
My poor Daniel! My sweet son, eaten up by that monster, Ithguleoir!  nnWhat vengeful prince could have created such a monster?
Fishing without my Annine is not the same.nnLife without her will never be the same. I go day to day, now. nnSomeone should stop the damn beast that killed her!

Isn't that waterfall beautiful? I wish Mathias were alive, so he could see it.nnHe was a good husband. He always let me stop to admire the waterfalls.nnThat certainly is a beautiful waterfall, isn't it? I love waterfalls.
Now that Northpoint is open again, maybe things around here will get back to normal.nnI just wish I knew what was eating all the vegetables in my garden.
I still can't believe so many of our citizens were murdered. Thank the Divines, it's over now.
I didn't see anything. That's why I'm on patrol. I didn't hear anything, either.nnThey died, but I didn't see anything. I'm on patrol now, but I didn't hear anything. nnI'm on patrol now.

Stay down, and stay quiet.nnI'm investigating the Blacksap tribe in the village south of here. You're welcome to join me, if you want.nnI would certainly enjoy your company. If you don't mind me saying so, you look good enough to eat.
I hurt myself walking on that wall. Fortunately, Master Malarelie offered me a position as Wayside Inn's private guard.
My friend and I used to sit together under these trees all the time. She was one of the first ones slain.nnI will always miss her.
This one begs your pardon, but Mister Munier tells me when he is expecting guests.nnIf you would kindly leave the premises, this would be most appreciated.
Amidst the chaos, I have found respite. nnAny who come seeking knowledge and reflection are welcome by my campfire.
Friend, you have found me again. I cannot fully express my thanks with clumsy words.nnI know your path is not an easy one. I will pray each step you take will be surefooted.
Fishing without my Annine is not the same.nnLife without her will never be the same. I go day to day, now.
Oh, poor Ithguleoir! nnWe'll tell our children stories about that wonderful beast...
Ithguleoir is dead? nnHe was like a son to us... like a son to me!
There may be Nords to the east and demonic evil to the west, but we still have fish in the water and crabs on the sand.nnI'm not giving up.
'Tis a shame about Ithguleoir, for certain. nnWhat would Farmost Reach be without him?
This one has little time to talk.nnSomeone needs to make sure the chickens are watched and guarded!

I regret I have no better hospitality to offer you than this. My husband was taken by the sea, leaving me penniless and alone.nnIf you would but stay a while, I would be thankful. I've been so lonely.
Dra gru mmm go ram. Gra mum jarab! Mrrg.
I've been too busy healing the wounded and dying. I haven't had time to help on the battlefield.
You must be the attractive <<1>> my sisters saw wandering among the cypresses.

Well done <<1>>! Attelus has been stopped - Elden Grove is safe once again.nnAs a Protector of the Grove, I cannot thank you enough for all you have done.  Please, if there is anything I can do for you, let me know.
Arkay sent you! Gods bless you.nnPlease, please help! It's Marcel.
Oh, a tasty one!nnLean down. I'll only chew your face a bit.
Help me!  Oh please help me!  I've been Brethus Tharn's play thing for so long I can't stand it anymore.nnDefeat him and then set me free. I'll make it worth your while!
Don't waste your pity on me, <<1>>. nnI was the blind fool who fell in love with her, all unknowing. nnNow thanks to you, I have been avenged.
We can fish and harvest crabs in these waters, aye... while we wait for our untimely death.

Exploits can only be used on targets that are off balance. Only one  Exploit ability can be used on a monster per off balance.

There is no passive defense in ESO. Meaning your character will never randomly dodge, parry or block.nnActive defense, an ability that you activate, is a great way of avoiding damage. Defending can create openings on your target for exploits.
Harrenit's cultists have captured my sister! They won't listen to reason. I fear for her life!
I was sent here to hurt the Dominion, not aid them in gaining prisoners.
We will drive back the Aldmeri Dominion!
Don't come too close. I do not wish to spread my illness.
This one may have made a mistake in coming here. nnThe ruins are filled with artifacts and knowledge, but they're also filled with danger.
The door is sealed by some sort of magical barrier.nnI thought the shield would fall if the Soul Gems were destroyed. I know you must think I'm crazy, but we have to find a way in there. We have to!
Roop and Lug are eating fruit - not wanting to share it with crocs.
Be on your guard, <<1>>. It's a slaughterhouse in there.nnI had to fight my way out. I saw bloodfiends everywhere ... and Captain Gagnon's brother was leading them!
Please help, <<1>>, we must get through to Fairfax!
You've saved me. nnI shudder to think how many more lives I might have taken if you hadn't stopped me.
Copper at your service, friend. Don't ask where I got my nickname. It's a story I'd soon forget!
One of our scouts was eaten by a bear. This gave me an idea...
You can't make me go back down there. At least here I can see them coming!
I fear for my wife... I have not seen her in days.
I've been discarded here, to die.

The ogres stole my <<1>> and went up those stairs! I sent several conscripts to save her. Now they're trapped up there, too. I'm starting to run low on soldiers.n nI can't go into battle without her! Will you help rescue my <<1>>?
Look at this waterfall! I wish Mathias were here. He always let me stop to admire waterfalls.nnIt's a beautiful waterfall, isn't it? I love waterfalls. Even Mathias would have liked this one.
Always digging. It seems like there are always so many dead people. nnCouldn't someone at the mage's guild create some kind of magic shovel? I've seen magic brooms.
Too many deaths of late. I cannot dig enough graves for them. The stone mason takes too long to make markers.nnWhat can I do? Even my apprentice is slow. Everyone is slow; only death is swift.
Something must be done about Godrun, and soon.
Whatever dark purpose the Infernal Device was designed to serve, I only hope it can be halted.
I've come to warn you, <<1>>.nnI believe they know we're here. My hope is that they'll underestimate us and act recklessly in this fight. nnl'll aid you, nonetheless.
I'm not supposed to deal with Daedric priests.nnI'm not trained to handle the walking dead and crocodile-faced monsters! nnI'm just a simple, boring Bosmer. I can't believe they put me on guard duty!
My daughter and I thank you for saving Gavaudon. We can never repay you.
We will never forget what you've done for us, <<1>>. Indeed, all of Gavaudon is in your debt.
We must purge the foreigners! The impure will not interfere with the Covenant.nnAll of them are spies. All of them must die.nnWe must purify the Daggerfall Covenant, no matter what the cost.
Noticing a stone beneath a carpet of leaves. Taunting Foosh's curiosity.nnThe snarling and roaring of predators!nnHumbling Foosh, who is lacking bravery.
We must purify the Daggerfall Covenant, no matter what the cost  even if that means hiring mercenaries to do the work.
Who let you in? If you've come to kill me, turn around. Go back to the hole you crawled out of and tell your master Seagrave Titanborn is laughing. Go on!
What am I going to do? What am I going to do?
What are you doing up here?
We have much to do before we can bring prosperity back to Wind Keep. You helped us considerably, friend.nnMay the Eight walk with you!
Light and leaf! What's a <<1>> like you doing out here?
When my arms are finally free, I'll flail the hide from those Blackmaul thugs with my bare hands.
They want to grind my bones into flour. Please, untie me.nn<<1>> would like to assure you that any bread made from an Argonian would not taste very good.
Finally, the murders in Wind Keep are over. Now the town can return to normal.
Wind Keep is slowly returning to normal. Thank you for your part in our recovery, friend.
I'm still rather tired. For some reason, I haven't been getting enough sleep lately.
Meet me at the docks - southwest of town.
Greetings, comrade! My knave's senses tell me there is much potential for mischief in you.
Have you seen my wife? Have you seen Nadene?
I hope you aren't here looking for work. nnOur crops are failing. The alits and crocodiles are aggressively roaming our lands. nnIt's as if the Illsam Farmlands are cursed!
What did I do to get stuck with this lousy job?
What are you standing around for? Make yourself useful!
How does that song go? Have you heard it? It's called "The Orc and the Bear."nnI can't sing it until I remember it properly. Maybe it's called "The Bear and the Orc." Is that it?
We have saved this town from the Empire's tyranny, and brought the Aldmeri Dominion one step closer to winning this war.
This sickness has stripped me of all I have. nnI've lost my home, lost my wife, and driven away my son.nnNow its wearing away at the little sanity I have left.
Please leave me alone. I have nothing to say to you.
Sincere and not-at-all-condescending greetings to you, citizen. I represent the Aldmeri Dominion here in verdant Valenwood.nnShould you have any business with our alliance, I would gladly assist you.
My beautiful babies, slaughtered without a thought! nnWould you look at this? Who would kill a scuttle so close to spawning?

When the Vereansu stormed our gates, I fled the Tribunal Temple with the others. nnBy the grace of the Three, I survived! Yet here, the peasants see these trials as signs of abandonment. nnDon't they know these events are simply tests of our faith?

I was a fool. I can see that now, even as my lifeblood flows from me.nnWhat puppets we were to think the Tribunal cared a whit about our plight!nnI've been a disciple of the Tribunal my entire life. I would not dare make this pronouncement lightly.
Wyress Helene has brought me a tale I'd be loathe to believe under normal circumstances. nnI trust her, though. The wyresses once saved me from a great fever. They're as trustworthy as they are kind.
My lifeblood soaks the earth, even as we speak. nnWe were unprepared for such a vicious attack! nnThe Vereansu slaughtered us, even as we prayed for salvation.
For the time being, you'd best keep away from the temple. nnWe've yet to devise a strategy to wrest it from those crazed Vereansu.
You are brave to come here in this trying hour - braver still to approach me with this sickness! I pray that you will stay and hear my plea.
You are brave to come here in this trying hour.nnYou are braver still to approach me while I bear this sickness!nnI pray that you will stay. Hear my plea, wanderer.
I know not why the Vereansu gave me this vile disease, but I know where the answers may lie.
<You've found a sleeping body. The Dunmer tosses fitfully, mumbling incoherent words.>
I hesistate to attack the Matuul Ashlanders because I know their ways. nnObviously, they wouldn't consort with the warlike Vereansu unless they were under duress.
There's trouble brewing in the mines. I fear my brother has done something incongruous.
<The Farseer moans fitfully in her sleep.>
Another scout? I did not expect one such as you to come up this way.
Why hello! Welcome to this treetop!

No one dares enter the Ashkhan's yurt uninvited. Begone!nnIf you must insist on petitioning the Ashkhan, I must demand a task of you first. nnCome closer. I do not want prying ears to overhear my revelations.
I'm not sure what's worse in these times: being afflicted with this disease or being separated from family.
This disease has infected both myself and my daughter. Luckily, it has spared my wife and son.
I wish I could just go home. This disease just ruins everything.
Something must be done about Godrun, and soon.
Something must be done about Godrun, and soon.
Troubling times, very troubling. I see no good coming of these Vereansu infesting our camp.
Welcome to the Quarantine Serk. If you have some time, we could use some help.
Every day, more people are coming in from <<1>>. nnIt's too bad we have to turn so many of them away.

Guarding the southern gate is pretty easy. nnI don't need to worry about fights breaking out near the inspection tents. I don't have to see the emotional scenes that happen out there. nnI'd rather be here.

Spending all day watching the sick try to sneak through our checkpoints isn't the ideal job.nnIt's worse when they choose to deny it and claim it's something innocuous.nnLuckily, you appear to be in good health... for now.
It's rough being new here. nnI hoped I'd never see this contagion.nnNow I've seen enough sickness to last two lifetimes.
A new face? That's rare these days, especially with so many troops being sent to the front.
Clan Murtag defends the Daggerfall Covenant to the death. The honor of all Orcs, Bretons, and Redguards is at stake.nnSo says <<1>>, our illustrious leader.
I'm sorry, but I don't have time to speak to the citizens of Narsis. nnPlease take a seat outside. One of the servants will receive your request.
I'm sorry, I'm looking for someone. Please address another servant with your inquiry.
I don't know how the captain expects me to do my job. They're even rationing swords and shields now!
You've been meddling in my affairs, <<1>>. nnThis is a dangerous game you play. You should know who the players are... before you get hurt.
Sure feels good to be holding a quality weapon again.nnI'm itching to test it against a Vereansu or two!
A little fresh air is useful for balancing one's humours. nnThe council chambers can be absolutely... stifling!

I am not ashamed of my tears. nnA free man conscripted is naught but a slave, yet I honor demands I respond to the call to arms in Cyrodiil!nnTo know I will never see Falena again... it is a knife in my heart.
What are you doing in our house? nnMy father will be very cross if he sees I have visitors. He's forbidden me from leaving, ever since he found out about Savard and me.
<You've found a dead body, slain by several sword blows. The corpse has been searched and looted, but in its clenched fist, it still holds a gold ring.>
Once we get all these catapults set up, we'll give those filthy ogres something to remember.nnEver fire a catapult?

It's a pleasure to meet you! I'm Dirani. I manage imports and exports for House Hlaalu in Narsis.nnIf you're looking to do any major shipping, you'll have to understand our current situation with the Vereansu. It's not good.
Ah, yes. What can I do for you?
If we can't hold back the ogres in Shinji's Scarp, they'll overrun us.nnWe've got to kill Skull-Cracker.
Perhaps my wife had the right idea all along. Dancing does seem to make one feel better.nnI'm sure the Eight understand.
You've got to get me out of here!
Try to be quiet. There are hostile Ashlanders nearby. I can't afford to have you giving away our position.
This conscript won't lie still, and his wound is getting worse.nnI can't heal him if he won't listen to me.
Escaping without you was harder than I thought! nnNevertheless, I survived, thanks to you.
How could this have happened? I suppose I was too careless.
Please help me! I'm an innocent woman, and I'm with child! nnThese men will surely kill me if you don't stop them.
Do I know you? nnYou're interrupting my teatime. Quite rude, I should say.

I hope you're enjoying your stay in Narsis. nnIt's a charming town. House Hlaalu is proud to claim it as one of its own.nnIf you're here for official business, I'll direct you to one of my servants. So much work to do!
Sloppy, that's the word! Yes, the regulations in this town are laughable, and the enforcement is nonexistent!
The superiority of Hoom's skills over that of Wud. Hoom will be beating Wud in the Scavenger Hunt!
Wud is disliking Hoom intensely.nnThe frequency of his practical jokes! The vanity of the obviously inferior!
Something must be done about Godrun, and soon.
Nethryn is too foolish to know what happened. nnI know who did this to me. They'll pay for this.
We fought beside Princess Mira. We died with her. Now these invaders trample our graves.
I am bound to your will.
<You've found a dead body. It's bruised and beaten. There's a knife wound in its back.>
That worm won't get far without his fortune! nnMy family put Nethryn where is is today, and he thinks to repay us like this? nnI'll make sure his life is not a happy one.
My crown! nnI do not deserve it. Not when my sister and my people despise me.

Since the Obelus lost its power, we've been blocked off from the mines. nnDaedric abominations are swarming the pass, and we've yet to hear back from our scouts.nnWithout access to the mines, our noble house has lost its most precious resource.
Son of a... this really stings!nnSome damn scamp got a hold of me. He took a big bite right out of my flesh! I haven't been able to feel a thing below my waist since....nnOh, no. Kill me now.

What's this? Another fool wants to be a hero.nnUnless you're here to get killed, hero, I suggest you go back to the Obelus. Let the others know the scouting party was decimated. nnIf you're as foolish as the others, you should take my advice.

I'd keep my voice down if I were you, stranger.nnSee those Ogrim down there? They're pouring out of the Ebony Mines. nnOur squad didn't even realize that until it was too late. They were my friends. Now they're corpses.

My first visitors! I'm so glad you dropped by! nnDrop? By? Get it? nnHa! I amuse myself sometimes.nnEnough small talk. You want to make some coin? Of course! We all do! The potential for profit is everywhere.
Be careful. These may be ruins, but I've experienced firsthand that the Dwemer's handiwork isn't really dead.

This camp is full of idiots. They're sending a magical charge at the Obelus. nnThe Obelus is older than us! The magic it possesses is greater than anything we've ever seen. This plan is folly!nnThis will probably set everyone on fire or something.
