My children and my people suffer.nnThe Planemeld continues  but that's not why I'm restless.
<You've found a <<1>> that's been partially reconstructed with miscellaneous parts. A patina of rust and grime hints at the creature's true age.>
By the grace of the Three, I serve House Hlaalu. nnI attend to all matters of restoring and maintaining the public record of history. nnIt's quite a daunting task, I assure you.
Help me! My family is being held hostage.nnIf I don't report back to Clan Murtag soon, my family is going to get hurt.

I fled the Tribunal Temple with the others when the Vereansu stormed our gates. By the grace of the Three, I survived!nnYet here, the peasants see these trials as signs of abandonment. Do they not know these events are simply tests of our faith?

I was a fool. I can see that now, even as my lifeblood flows from me. nnWhat puppets we are to think the Tribunal cares a whit about our plight!nnI've been a disciple of the Tribunal my entire life. I wouldn't make this pronouncement lightly.
Do not interrupt our conversation. We're discussing some important business. The Blackmauls have a lucrative relationship with Clan Murtag.
We made it back, just barely.nnThat's good enough for me.
Wherever the  guards go, profit is sure to follow. I have an ample supply, if there's anything you happen to need.

This dream again....nn What are you doing in my dream? nnI remember now! Vaermina's Omen of Counting Stars has been destroying Gavaudon. It's poisoning our dreams.nnYou must kill it, deep in this dungeon. I cannot leave my sleeping self.
Only the pure will be allowed in the Daggerfall Covenant. He must be eliminated.
Is it safe? Can we go?
If Murlog keeps drinking like this, I'm going back to Orsinium. nnMy mother warned me about marrying a soldier.
You were in my dream. You  saved me.nnMalacath curse me, what have I done? What have I done?
Clan Murtag will defend the Daggerfall Covenant to the death!nnI see now that we were being influenced, but that's no excuse for our behavior. We'll help make things right in Stormhaven.
Clan Murtag no longer requires our services.nnWe'll be on our way soon, but I have no doubt our paths will cross again.

This nightmare is neverending. All my choices have ended in death and destruction. The Daedra are everywhere now, poisoning my mind with their lies.nnYou must save the Daggerfall Covenant. Kill the Omen of Counting Stars!
Once the Blackmaul showed up, we left so fast I didn't have time to grab my journal!
I know I should leave. Go south to the Razorvine village. Or west to Elden Root.nnIt's just that I feel safe here by the fire.
Thank goodness someone has found me. You don't look like you're from House Hlaalu though.... Be careful. There are Vereansu Ashlanders close by.
<<1>> is praying for those who were lost. The safe haven was not so safe, was it? <<1>> grieves, and remembers.
I'd never noticed how quiet and peaceful Wind Keep is before.

The crimes the Wood Orcs committed here are unforgivable. They've always been hostile, but never like this.nnI expect them to act like savages, but I've never seen them resort to such organized destruction.nnThis is new. It disturbs me.
Wood Orcs attacked us. They came from out of nowhere!nnWhy would they attack us? What could they possibly gain by raiding merchants?nnThey don't even use our wares!
Thank goodness someone has found me. You don't look like you're from House Hlaalu though.... Be careful. There are hostile Ashlanders close by.

I'd keep my voice down if I were you, stranger.nnSee those Ogrim down there? They're pouring out of the obsidian mines. nnOur squad didn't even realize that until it was too late. They were my friends. Now they're corpses.
I'm exhausted from crossing the forest.nnI really need a rest.
He's not coming out, is he?nnIs he?

I'd keep my voice down if I were you, stranger.nnSee those Ogrim down there? They're pouring out of the obsidian mines. nnOur squad didn't even realize that until it was too late. They were my friends. Now they're corpses.
What manner of creature are you?
I'm ill for two days and these Imperials move in and cut down my grove! The best mushrooms grew in that grove! All of them!nnThey, with their saws and their mushroom-trampling feet. How dare they?
We've got all the traditional brews and distillations, as well as our customers' more unusual creations! You look like you could handle them. nnHave a taste! It's for the advancement of knowledge!
Stay away from the Netch Floater Ale! nnAch! I fear I may perish....
Do you normally interrupt conversations so rudely?

Verandis put me in charge. I'm keeping this area safe from the creatures in the tunnels out there.nnCan't say it's been easy, but the Ravenwatch Keeper's magic is incredible. Some of the things he can do... let's just say he's made my life easier.
I have watched your journey here, <<1>>. The one who has cast my physical form into this unending sleep plots against my people, and yours. You must help us.
It's getting too dangerous to walk along the shore these days. nnI wish the duchess would do something to get rid of those damned Nords!
It's getting too dangerous to walk along the shore these days. nnI wish the duchess would do something to get rid of those damned Nords!
Lorkhan, curse those Nord monsters! I'm ruined!nnThe Daggerfall Covenant must avenge me!

Anyone who wants to fight in the Ravenwatch must have control of his body. nnBe swift. Be strong. Develop the endurance to withstand any blow. nnA fight isn't always what it seems. You must pay close attention to your surroundings and your enemies.

Anyone who wants to fight in the Ravenwatch must have control of his body.nnBe swift. Be strong. Have the endurance to withstand any blow. nnA fight isn't always what it seems. Pay close attention to your surroundings and your enemy.
Sorry, friend, but I'm closing up shop. Trading's shut down with those Nords at our gates!
My sister...my people...will they ever forgive me?
Isn't she wonderful? So elegant. So graceful. nnThis is what love feels like, isn't it? A million butterflies in my chest, ready to burst at any moment. nnMaybe it could have been something I ate....
Where are you going, apeneck? Nixad is as nixad does!
I'm trapped here with nothing. No food, no money. Only the clothes on my back and this blasted disease.
It is good to be in my body again, but I fear that enchantment has weakened me more than I first suspected.
<You've found a body. It's warm, but lifeless. This victim must have been killed recently.>
Mud and bark may have this dance. A poxy apeneck drinking wine and stars!
<<1>>! My child, these eyes may be blind, but I can sense your power. What brings you to Old Ulimu?
Bring glory to the Three with your actions, and you shall be justly rewarded!

Well done, <<1>>.nnFinally! I stand inside the Plane Merge. Such a strange feeling, as if it were so long ago, before this damned curse flowed through my veins.nnBeing so close to life and death inside this realm... it affects us all differently.
My time is devoted to my patients. Please state your business, and make it quick.
What are you standing around for? Make yourself useful!
Oh, it's you again. nnI'll have you know I hold no grudge. nnI miss my family, but I know I can do more good here than I ever could back at the Serk.
I feared this would end in bloodshed. How long will it be until the Vereansu attack us openly, now that we've shown our true allegiance?
You're back! What what happened? nnThe Plane Merge closed so suddenly. I heard Verandis's voice, and we all arrived back here.nnWhere is he, <<1>>? Where is Verandis?
Please leave me alone. I have nothing to say.

If you want to stake a claim in these mines, you're out of luck.nnThere's nothing but a morass of angry kwama and collapsed tunnels here. nnNot even our Great House has access to these mines anymore. Not with the cave-in!
Many of my sisters grew sick when corruption took our Wyrd Tree. I'm tending two of the most afflicted now, hoping to keep the fever from consuming them.
I'm glad you're not a cultist!nnThose thieving fiends are scuttling all over the place.
It's good to see you alive, my friend!nnWere you successful?
I have no time to chat. nnUntil there is peace, I will be busy making or mending equipment for the Dominion.
Have you got any ale to spare? Please?
By the end of a shift, I'm ready for a flagon of ale. nnOf course, sometimes I'm ready at the start of a shift, when you get right down to it.
Greetings. Are you here to craft some runes?
Would you learn the ways of a forester?
Psst! Keep your voice low!nnVery, very low.

You have woken us, loosed us from our own curse. Our leaders sealed the Archives, and we gave our spirits to power the spell. But now we are awake, and must leave this place.nnIf you were wise, you would leave too.
Yes? Did you have a question, traveller?
I need more ale. If you aren't going to give me any, then you'd best move along.
Yes? Did you have a question, traveller? Or perhaps an answer?
Have you got any ale to spare? Please?
Have you got any ale to spare? Please?
Have you got any ale to spare? Please?

Adyssa only came here because the little Bosmer asked so nicely.nnWhile this one set up camp, the whole forest filled with evil.nnAdyssa was only separated from her for a moment, but when Adyssa returned....
You come here to enjoy the city?

Afraid I don't have a lot to offer, friend.nnI lost a good bit of stock with the tunnels collapse. Not much I can do about it. Just been spending most of my time ironing out the ore we have left. What I'd give to work with something other than rock.

This statue stands unmoving with its arms out, hands upturned, as if expecting something.nnAt the base is a plaque with an inscription:nn"The book of Right Reaching informs the Selected of the Inflexible Axioms. Commit these doctrines to memory."
They expect me to make them a lush landscape, when all I have to work with is moss and lichen? Curse this swamp! What I wouldn't do for some rich Vvardenfell ashen soil!
I think I'm coming down with something. You'd best stay back, lest it's catching.
Off-duty - don't be bothering me, <<1>>! Another drink!
They'll kick me out of town soon. They always do! nnI just need to find a bit of bread to eat....

I knew I was right! I knew it!nnThe others didn't believe me. I told them from the start! nnI said to them, "These mines connect, you just wait and see!" And here I stand, proclaiming my genius in the very tunnel that proves it!
We fight for Godrun and the Murtag Clan!
Through your deeds, you honor the Tribunal and our Great Houses.nnGo with honor.
With a little bit of work, we could be back in those mines in a day or so! nnOf course, we'd also have to drive out the rest of the Daedra. nnI'm still trying to figure that part out.
I'm not ashamed of my tears. A free man conscripted is naught but a slave.nn'Tis a pity a poet must go to war, yet the skalds will sing of my triumphs!
Savard will mend in time. Thank you for doing this, friend.
You're a mad one, that's certain. Such lunacy! Such bravery!nnI thank you for saving my life... and my love.
I'm so glad to see you. This mine is filled with idiots.nnEverywhere I go, I'm plagued by idiots. I swear, Vivec must be testing me.
I can breathe again. Thank the Eight, I can breathe!
They'll come back. I know they will.
Curse that guard and all of his descendents! nnMay their bodies be scavenged by kwama!nnMay the guar tear them apart!
This camp was set up for the afflicted who can't enter Deshaan. They've been deemed too dangerous.nnIt's a safe place for them to stay before they move on. I just want them to hurry up and leave.
They just don't understand. I need to get through these gates! It's a matter of life and death!
This wasn't my first choice for a location, but I'll sell my wares where they're needed. nnSo... what can I do for you?
No live plants or animals through the gate. nnYou'd be surprised how many people ignore that simple rule.
How much longer is this going to take?
We waited so long to get past the palisades.nnNow this.
No one gets in or out of this place without an inspection. nnWe're here to make sure of that.
Hands off the keg, my friend. Step away from the keg.nnRations are only for off-duty guards.
These are my applies. I didn't steal them.
The Ayleids cursed this place. They cursed every place they touched!

The Master calls to us. He speaks to us through our dreams. nnWe've come together to awaken him once more.nnYou will bear witness to the summoning of our grand master. The power we've extracted from the Obelus will make it so.
What? Who are you? nnGuards! Seize him!

Just as I thought! Those cultists have stripped the Obelus from its source of power!nnNow they're using it in their insidious rituals. If they use up its magic, we'll never power the towers!nnDid you discover anything? Or did you just kill them all?
Unless it's urgent, please see Captain Yarborough.
Curse those bandits!  Another merchant robbed!  Please see one of the Sergeants downstairs while I deal with this.
Greetings <<1>>.  If you're looking to help, the patrol can always use some additional aid.  Please see either of the Sergeants in the rooms on this floor.
Greetings <<1>>.  I'm Sergeant Wallace, in charge of patrolling the road to Westgate.
Greetings <<1>>.  I'm Sergeant Ellsworth, in charge of patrolling the road to Eastgate.
I'm afraid Westgate is closed at the moment.  Is there anything I can help you with?
I'm afraid Eastgate is closed at the moment.  Is there anything I can help you with?
I don't understand why the Vereansu are so determined to defy the noble houses. nnI don't believe they're right to do what they do, but I have no personal quarrels with any of them.
I'm glad you stopped by. I didn't take the time to thank you properly before. nnSo thank you. Properly.
Why's it called blue wine? It's not actually blue.
Are you going to keep staring, or are you going to help me?
Is that it? Is that my wine?
Huh? Is that you, Relah? nnI thought you were... right behind me....

Pierre Donat and Claude Jerick roughed me up and threw me down here, just because I argued with them about the last job.nnWas it my fault? Did Andre really knock out Pierre because he smacked me? nnSometimes, I think there's no honor among thieves.
What do you want? Can't you see I'm busy?
They took my husband. He was only trying to defend our homes, but the dreugh took him. nnPlease, stranger, can you help?
Why the long face? One would think you were a horse!

Hold a moment, stranger. If you're heading into the plantation, let me give you some advice.nnDon't trust what people say within those walls. nnGovyn controls the minds of those in his employ as much as he controls their lives.
Want to place a bet? Here to pick up winnings?nnOr are you here to make ... other ... arrangements?
I'm sorry, I have no time for visitors. House Hlaalu is demanding an audit of the plantation's revenues within the week.
Do you see this? Even our crops are withering away around us! nnI've got little hope left for this place. We've been cursed!
I can't leave. Not while the others are away.nnI've also got good news. My new fishing poison's almost ready.
One of our own is missing. We can't leave until we find him.nnThis swamp reminds me of the marshes, but it's no substitute for my home tree.

This statue stands unmoving with its arms out, hands upturned, as if expecting something.nnAt the base is a plaque with an inscription:nn"Simple in summary, profound beyond measure, brief and yet all-encompassing: here you begin."

This statue stands unmoving with its arms out, hands upturned, as if expecting something.nnAt the base is a plaque with an inscription.nn"Read here how the Man-Ape Maruhk looked beyond the End and saw Eventuality."

This statue stands unmoving with its arms out, hands upturned, as if expecting something.nnAt the base is a plaque with an inscription:nn"Even the simplest minds can be consoled by truth, when that truth is presented in ritual song."

Welcome, stranger! As you can see, I've made myself a comfortable abode here.nnI still crave another soul for civilized discourse, but I doubt any Dunmer in his right mind live here with me.nnAssuage my loneliness, wanderer, if only briefly.
I wasn't expecting to see another sane soul on this damned mount. nnGetting past those crazed witches below was quite a trial!
Excuse me, but I'm waiting to speak to the elder. I've neither the time nor the patience for idle chatter.
There's nothing left for me! Nothing! What a fool I was!
I'm resting for a moment. I must return to my training soon.
I don't know if I can stand this anymore. Simply waiting for the inevitable to happen... watching yourself forget and decay.nnThis is too much for anyone to bear!
Come a bit closer, friend. I don't want to raise my voice. I fear of the wrong ears may hear us.nnThere's something very wrong with these mines. I'm determined to find out what that is.
Have you got any ale to spare? Please?
My mistress is going to kill me. Why did I have to buy the cheap wine?nnI can't pocket the difference in price, and I can't enjoy anything else until this problem is solved!
Have you got any ale to spare? Please?
I hope the war in Cyrodill concludes quickly. Then the council can finally focus on Aldsotha again.
I certainly hope you aren't here to stir up trouble. nnSeems like the ones who claim they're just "passing through" are usually the ones who make things more difficult.
I heard it won't be long before unspeakable creatures overrun this town.
I was told the council won't sparing any of their resources for the town's defense.nnWhen Aldsotha comes under attack, we'll be doomed.
This town is in danger, yet House Indoril's council does nothing.
Welcome to the arena adventurer!  You must purchase a ticket to see the games.
Welcome to the arena adventurer!  You must purchase a ticket to see the games.
Welcome to the arena adventurer!  You must purchase a ticket to see the games.
Have you come here for a challenge?.
Is that it? Is that my wine?
The Aldmeri Dominion thanks you for your aid. Welcome to Woodberth.

Being the only leatherworker in town has its ups and downs. nnOn the one hand, everyone comes to you for their needs. nnOn the other hand, you run out of wares all the time! Then you end up with unhappy customers.
Judging by the dress, you can easily discern this was a House Indoril scout. It looks as if he put up quite a struggle against his attacker.
Submit to the Three, the spirits, and thy Lords.

An outsider in our glen is a rare sight indeed. I know you've come to me for a reason.nnYour arrival must be more than mere coincidence. I see you walk the path of destiny.nnYou are the one for whom I have been waiting.

I, Zairrm-dar, greet you. Zairrm-dar and his men are here to help the Altmer unload their ships before all of us move into the Grahtwood.nnThis forest is not kind, however, and Zairm-dar has personally been attacked by the very plants themselves.
<You see the elder staring ahead, unblinking and unfocused.>
Watch your step there, you wouldn't want to step in anything smelly.
I have much work to do here.  If you need your horse looked after, see the stable master.
I have a confession, <<1>>. Fate and I conspire together, and many are the tasks set before you. To be the tool, the smith's hammer, the one who strikes the formative blow. This is known.
Looking for some food or drink before the games?
Thank goodness. You're not one of those crazed witch-women.nnFor pity's sake, listen to me! Hear a dying man's plea, friend. I don't know how much longer they'll let me live!
I got the finest weapons for sale.  What can I sell you?
Brelayne may never forgive me for my deeds.nnIn fact, I believe she was the one who asked me to endure this in the first place! nnStill, I must see her again, <<1>>. I must!
My Armor is the toughest around.  What can I do for you?
I've more pressing matters at hand than the wants and needs of a wayward stranger.
You've picked a poor time to visit, stranger. The Imperials haven't attacked us, but....nnWell, you don't dig trenches if you've come to talk.
By the Three, I enact my rites and perform my duties.
Welcome to Woodberth. We are glad to have the extra help. You might want to find a Bosmer by the name of Lilymoth near the log-bridge into the forest. She can direct you to the village of Razorvine.
Is that it? Is that my wine?
Difficult times for a town create difficult times for its merchants. nnSeems interest is rather low these days. Folks don't want to purchase anything they won't need for survival.

You must take the heart back to the camp. House Hlaalu will be most grateful for the restoration of the Obelus. I will send you back, do not worry about me. I'll clean up the mess here and make my way out.
I've rallied the warriors, but our most experienced archers went north to hunt in the Thrambles.nnOf course, warriors and archers won't help if the Imperials set up siege engines.
That man isn't part of the Daggerfall Covenant. He's half-Altmer!nnOnly the pure will be allowed in the Daggerfall Covenant. He must be eliminated.
I don't know if I feel better or worse, now that I've done it. nnWhat does it feel like to have your soul torn from your body?
I'm scared! My father shouldn't go out to investigate those murders.nnThat Orc has been saying such strange things since we passed him on the way into town....
I'm sure these murders are connected. I arrived in Wind Keep yesterday, but I am already feeling an affect I've never felt before. My dreams last night were haunted.
I'm in the middle of negotiations.
After all this time, I've finally done it! nnThe deed to the plantation is mine, and Govyn can't stop me!
After all this time, I've finally done it! The deed to the plantation is mine, and Govyn can't stop me!
What's this? Another guttersnipe here to whine about the dreugh?
Go away! Can't you see I'm hiding?
Friend or foe? Declare yourself! nnNo one will harm the Abbot, not while I draw breath.
I have no time to entertain the rubes of Valenwood.
This sickness has stripped me of all I have. I've lost my home, my wife, driven away my son, and now it chisels away at what humanity I have left.
Abbot Durak led us here for something he called "Azura's Guardian." He said it could stop the fires and protect the abbey.nnThe two of us were told to wait here outside. Then we got ambushed.
An atronach! Simply amazing. nnDurak, you were right, my friend. You were right.
You've got some nerve coming in here. Give me one good reason why we shouldn't just kill you.
You're interfering with my quality time with Serge. You'll have to excuse us, we're in love.
This is Pariah Abbey, home of the Spirit Wardens.
I have a great deal on my mind right now. Perhaps we could talk another time.
This sister has suffered a concussion, and the brother behind me has internal injuries. nnIt's an outrage. The Union must be stopped.
These spirit wardens are so pompous! The Fervor has set us free! Now is the time to rejoice!nnGorge on food. Dance into the night. Make wild love. We'll all be dead tomorrow!
Dance with us! Join us! When will you get another chance? nnTomorrow, we could be dead. Tonight, we are free!nnIt's going to be a wild night!
The fields! The fields are burning!
I don't understand how this could be happening  we have no feud with the Midnight Union!nnWhy would they suddenly come here and destroy the Abbey? It doesn't make any sense.

Suddenly, the light returns to my eyes. I was surrounded! Visions of the living! Revelations of rotting death!nnWhy am I here? How did this come to be?nnMortal One! You who stand before me! I want to taste life's breath once more.
We have to put out those fires before they destroy our crops!
The Midnight Union, pfah! And Sister Safia said we could trust them.
Azura take them! I planted that cornfield myself.
What are you doing in my house?

Being able to stand under the water and not long for the breath of the air is quite fascinating. Even better, the slaughterfish in the area pay me no attention without any flesh to tear at.nnNot that I'm really enjoying this, but it's... different.

Finally, I am whole again.nnI know not what I've done to deserve a second chance, but you have my thanks.  I shall return to Mournhold in hopes of reclaiming my memories. Perhaps there I will find out who I once was and reclaim my former life.
Hold for a moment, <<1>>. I would speak to you before you proceed. nnThings are never as simple as they appear, traveler.
Don't worry, Godrun, my friend. We'll take care of anyone you want killed: the Bosmer, the Altmers, and the Khajiit.nnWe'll get rid of whatever your funding desires.
I believe I see kindness in those eyes. Then again, I've been wrong before.
I never even had a child....
Who sent this Altmer to kill me? Skull-Cracker? Damn those half-breeds and filthy foreigners from outside the Covenant!nnWe must cleanse Stormhaven of all traitors to save the Daggerfall Covenant.
Die, Orc scum! If you won't be enslaved, you will die!
Without you, I'd still be trapped in that dream.nnNow we must work together to stop this threat to High Rock.

You have no business here, stranger.nnI'd recommend you head back to one of the nearby towns. Without the proper precautions, one could easily stumble upon a creature that would rip your flesh to pieces.
You startled me! My apologies, but I'm a bit jumpy, considering our chosen research site.nnYou look like a hale, strong individual. I think you'd be perfect for what we need!

Ah. We weren't expecting guests, so far out here. Come to admire these undead specimens? I've never seen anything so fascinating.nnThis may be our first trip out from the Guild Hall, but the dead, walking? That would thrill even the most jaded.
You're the one who helped save our fields.nnListenI may have discovered the source of Durak's affliction.
The greater part of our task still lies ahead.
You realize we cannot allow you to leave this place alive.
I am glad I wasn't wrong about you.
Do you want improve your smithing skills?
I can teach you how to make sturdy and comfortable clothes.
Would you like me to show you my forestry techniques?
Have you come to learn the ways of runecrafting?
Altis tosses in a feverish state. He doesn't seem to be aware of your presence.
You're new here, aren't you? What brings you to the Illsam Farmlands?
The Supernal Dreamers captured me and tied me up. You've got to help me!
I knew this job would be the death of me.
You have survived many conflicts, defeated many opponents, no? Your presence radiates this.

The body upon the altar is mine, the life claimed by my three compatriots. It seems they wish to claim another victim in the name of their experiments.nnIt's naught but a game to them. Us, the experiments, and they, the experimenters.
Shivina has much yet to learn.
I didn't want to kill him, I swear! The others forced me to do it. They told me to stab him! I've never killed a man before!

So, you know.nnYou spoke to the one who made this all possible. Our victim, as he would put it.nnDid he also tell you he was the one who led us here? The one who first suggested a sacrifice? I thought not.
I knew we should have left days ago! These fools want to stand about reveling in their work. I just want to forget all about this horrible place!nnIt's just not fair!
My accursed companions are gone. Show me the blade, so I may see what you have wrought!
The Altmer are high strung and dwell on the past -- ancestors this, ancestors that.nnWe need to properly welcome them to Grahtwood.
Welcome to the mines. Grab an pick and join in, if you want to earn some coin.
Most of the supplies we gather here are sent to Aldsotha, but lately, we've also been helping the Uplands.

If you're looking to earn some coin, you've found the right place.nnThese mines aren't held by any specific house of nobles. Lots of workers from Aldsotha come here to earn gold. Lately, we've been seeing lots of folks from the Sylvan Uplands.
You'd best step out of the arena before someone challenges you.
You will pay for this insult! All of you!nnHouse Dres does not take kindly to threats, peasants!
<You've found a body. It's frail and still warm to the touch.>nn<Its furrowed brow and grimacing countenance suggest its death was not a peaceful one.>
Why have you come back?nnThis is no mere chore to be done at your leisure! The Balac is the key to freeing this world from Molag Bal's grip. nnYou must find it with all haste.
I pray you got what you wanted.nnHe will spout his poisonous words no more.
We have been cast out as abominations.nnNow we live on as legends.
Perhaps the world beyond will simply wither and die. nnWe'll persevere, as we always have, as their wars tear the others apart.
Is there hope for my sisters? nnWhat must we do to stop this darkness from falling?
Mortal! I know not how you came here, but you must set the elder free! nnEven I am powerless within this dream.nnI do not like that.
Friend, we should leave this place. nnYou may be exhausting yourself more than you realize by staying here.

Times have been tough here lately. nnOur miners come from a wide range of backgrounds. Soldiers, farmers, medicine men... you name it.nnThey all want the same thing: a chance to earn some coin and feed their families, one way or another.
You! You look pretty dangerous. You're drafted. nnThere are goblins here that need killing.
I did all that I could but there was just too many of them to fight off.
This is a nightmare that will never end.
I don't have time for fools.  Please move a long.
Welcome to my inn.  How can I be of service?
What buisness do you have with me?
I'm retiring to Reywell. Those thieves made off with my precious jewels and gems. Now there's nothing left for me here.nnCan you help me take care of one last thing before I go?
Have you come to destroy me?
You there! Help! Please, help! nnThat double-crossing snake Sadir set me up!nnHe betrayed us. He locked us up the moment we got here!
I was supposed to meet my lady love here on the road to Koeglin,  but she never arrived. nnI fear for her safety!
Please, adventurer, you must help us!
I envy the living. Do not waste your life, as I did. nnYou never know when death might take you.
Well, at least now we know what brought the Stonechewer goblins down on us.
I'm sorry, but our usual tasks must be put on hold. Our biggest concern right now is defending these mines from the undead. nnThey want to drive us out. That's not going to happen.
Do you have business with the Mages Guild? If so, then I'm the one you want.

Don't worry about the blood. If anything, it will act as more evidence of my death.nnI was trained from a young age to ignore pain, but even now, I ache. The tip of my tail is a fitting goodbye to the only family I've ever known.
The local Bosmer test the patience of the Altmer. Our benevolent ruler, Queen Ayarynne, rises above the concern of such annoyances, but her image is tarnished.nnI will not have that.
<You stare into the face of a ferocious senche. It looks hungry....>
<You stare into the face of a ferocious senche. It looks hungry....>
Please, hero! You must help us!
Greetings, traveler. We welcome all who come seeking respite from their troubles.nnIf you are bringing a donation to our cause, I can accept it.
We are together. We are one.nnYou have restored us, <<1>>.
I feel the warmth of life radiating from you.
This is Sibellec, speaking through my familiar.nnWe have little time. Our bodies are dying as we speak.
Feel free to browse as long as you like. nnIf you see anything you'd like to purchase, I'd be happy to help you.

We've been sent here from Aldsotha to investigate musk screal plants. nnApparently, its scent attracts certain animals. Our guar was carrying all our belongings, and it was one of those poor creatures.
She stole us. She took us away.
Half-witted guar!nnAll our research equipment is strapped to the backs of those half-witted animals. nnNow we're sitting and watching helplessly with no hope of reaching them... or our gear.
You're speaking to me? You can see me! nnPlease, you have to help me.
Welcome to the Runecrafters Guild, traveler.nnWhat can I do for you?

This foolish girl just doesn't understand my logic!nnNix-hounds use their ability to warm their blood to match the temperature of a tar pit. The rest of their bodies react accordingly, giving them freedom of movement on the tar!

This man must fall asleep to the sound of his own voice every night. nnHe rambles on with no proof to back up his outlandish claims.nnSurely the Nix-Hounds are able to use the oil pits due to their skin and its ability to push off the oily toxins.

Ever since the Altmer arrived, the Camorans have been demanding I do something to end the crime in this city.nnHere's an idea; how about assigning me more reliable Bosmer, and fewer "I just love the Dominion" yes-men?
I don't know what you're doing in here, but you should leave.
Life is tedious, but bloodshed relieves the ennui. Don't you think?

I'm glad to see you made it. Turning and aiming is dependent on mouse look. Movement is dependent on the W,A,S,D keys.nnGo down this hill and talk to the man in the blue dress for some instructions on attacking and targeting.

You can target a monster by tabbing and selecting them. This will cause you to lock onto your target.nnYou can also rely on soft targeting. If you do not choose a target when you attack it will target the monsters closest and most in front of you.

You can defend frontal assaults with your right mouse button. Defending with your mouse button will not completely negate damage or effects but it can be the difference between life and death.nnTry your defending skills against the target dummies.
If you're heading for Cumberland's Watch, I've bad news. Goblins have overrun the fort.

Picking your fights is one of the most important factors leading to victory. You can practice on one monster before you are lead into an enemy encampment.nnWatch and learn their movements and strike when the time is right.
Excuse me. Do you have business with me? nnIf you don't, clear out. I'm busy.
I don't believe I've ever seen you at one of Hosni's parties..... Well, welcome to the party.
Did you hear the guards killed another guest? I'm sorry to have missed it! It's the only real form of entertainment here.

The musk screal fascinates me.nnFirst, its scent calls you, enticing your senses. Then you mindlessly trudge through the tar pits to get it. nIf you survive, you can taste a few sweet drops... before its poison kills you.nnSo deadly. So fascinating.

Welcome to the Uplands, stranger. Here, we stage our battle against the evil witches of the Mabrigash. nnWhen we accept petitioners, we harbor no prejudices of race or kind. nnWe all came for the same reason: witches wronged us, one way or another.
The longer I stayed in that cage, the more I felt like I was losing my mind!
We have to put out those fires before they destroy our crops!
This meeting is a farce. Do they think we have not realized their spies are trying to get into Elden Root even as we speak?nnThis is insulting.
I'm glad to see you again!
I wasn't even aware of the attack until one of the clannfear ambushed us.nnLuckily, Drevin saw it first. He saved me before it had a chance to finish me.

I saw their leader. 'Twas a Dremora Lord. When it looked at me, I stared back.nnBefore I knew it, several Daedra were upon me, but I just stood there, staring at their lord and master.nnWere it not for the other soldiers, I would be dead now.
I'm doing what I can. nnI can only hope the few supplies I salvaged before we fled will be enough.
Please. You have to help me. nnThe Midnight Union bandits. I don't know why. I was no threat to them. They attacked me anyways.
Thank goodness you're not one of them. You scared me half to death!
Welcome to the arena adventurer!  You must purchase a ticket to see the games.

You've come to this camp at a good time, stranger. The Sylvan Guard has grown, as of late. nnSoon, we'll have our chance to strike out at the foul, destructive Mabrigash.nnAny help would be much appreciated.
Welcome to the arena adventurer!  You must purchase a ticket to see the games.
The day of our attack on the Mabrigash cannot come soon enough. nnThose damned witches will pay for everything they've done to me... to all of us!

The Mabrigash should not be allowed to live.nnEven if we share the same blood, what they're doing to our people goes against everything we believe in.nnThey would use our magic for selfish reasons. Through defeat, they will learn humility.
I'm glad to see you again!
I'm glad to see you again!
The Mabrigash haven't moved from the glen in days, but I've noticed a spike in their activity lately. I wonder what's got them all stirred up down there.nnWhat can I do for you?

Always good to see a new face around here.nnPlease, have a seat and share a meal with us if you'd like. I'm just waiting for my husband Gharvin to come back from his watch before we eat. He's the nicest man I know. Most of the guard agrees.
Many chose to end to their lives.nnMy wife. My sister. Many others. Eventually, myself.nnI wept for them in life. I refuse to grieve in death.

We must put our differences aside if we wish to survive the battle against the Mabrigash. Both Ashlander and House Dunmer have felt the pain these witches inflict.nnStand together or fall one by one to their magic.
I can feel the myself slowly returning to normal. Thank you for freeing me.
It's hard to hold a meeting when the other side seems so distracted. They called this meeting, you'd think they could at least stay focused.
We're here to try and find some middle ground, so that all of us Bosmer can live in peace... without outsiders interfering.
I wish I knew why the Blacksap keep looking around. They seem nervous.

LookI have no interest in risking my money on this hand-held ballista contraption. Who would want a bow they have to load and fire with a trigger?nnI don't have any gold anyhow  oh  I'm sorry. Thought you were someone else.
Good, you're finally awake.nnWe were worried for you. You've been sleeping for hours.
Don't worry about Nevena. She's never wanted any part of Sadir's madness, and she's not interested in the Book of Circles. She won't stop me from returning home.
Treachery! I can't believe they attacked us!
I've arrived too late. I cannot help you... or save Christophe. nnWhen they left Pariah Abbey, I should have followed them immediately.nnWe should leave.

I'm glad to see you're awake.nnWe were all worried that we might have... lost you to whatever ailment that had stricken you.nnI've been delayed in creating the amulet because of your sickness. It'll be done soon though.
Did you kill her, <<1>>?nnIs she... dead?
Did you kill her, <<1>>?nnIs she... dead?
State your business, and make it quick.

Please, <<1>>. You must listen to me!nnNythis told me everything. You were their ally all this time, acting against your will. nnYou must free yourself from their curse! Free yourself from what they've done to you!
Travel with caution, stranger. The alit here are infected, making them far more formidable than usual.
<You've found a dead body. From the severity of the wounds inflicted, it's obvious the victim died quickly.>
There's some lovely filth down here.
I have a quest! Try it. You may like it!
It was a trap. They knew we were coming!
What do you want? Can't you see I'm grieving?
Excuse me. I was busy thinking deep thoughts.
I'm drinking. Leave me to my liquor.
If you want me to play something for you, you'll just have to wait your turn.
Who allowed you entrance, stranger? nnI think you need to leave.
I bet my last coins on Jazha.
Yeah! Did you see that tiger's head come off?
I hear the Altmer want to stop the tiger fights. That's why Shifty moved everything back into this cave.
I bet my last coins on Shanari.
I heard it won't be long before unspeakable creatures overrun this town.
I'm sorry. I have to keep a lookout for the severely infected.nnSometimes, they're attracted to the lights of the camp.
Spare anything for a humble stranger?
The scamps got me. I don't think I can fight anymore.
Sssh! You'll ruin my cover. nnIf the poachers find me, I'm as good as dead!
I haven't seen any boats from the Narsis temple in a while. nnI've even heard rumors that the Vereansu ransacked it... and killed Temple Master Nothsalea.
Help, please! These fiends must be stopped before they shatter any more of our souls!
Help me, please! They're doing unspeakable things to our souls!
Quickly! They're using our souls to create weapons... powerful weapons!
We were hunting for a tome called the Book of Circles when we fell prey to an ambush.
Help me, please! They're doing unspeakable things to our souls!
Help me, please! They're doing unspeakable things to our souls!
Help me, please! They're doing unspeakable things to our souls!
Help me, please! They're doing unspeakable things to our souls!
This is Pariah Abbey, home of the spirit wardens.
Quickly! They're using our souls to create weapons... powerful weapons!
You're not a Supernal Dreamer. Help me!
Be careful. These cultists attack anyone who draws near.
We can't leave until we've rescued the people these Supernal Dreamers captured.
Glad you made it. We found some injured, but don't have a way to free those locked in cages.
I must tend to the injured. Please excuse me.
My husband didn't come home last night. I'm worried sick.nnHe's a guard at Cumberland's Watch. Are you coming from there? I hope he's all right.
We were sent in here to place crystals in some foolish attempt to relight the Obelus at the canyon pass. Can't say we made it very far before we were split up from all the damn scamps swarming us.

If it weren't for Mhaltu and Danmus, most of us would be dead. They someone managed to someone find order in the chaos that happened.nnI wonder what became of the others. I fear the worst, but I can hope for the best.
Excuse me, but are you here on business? If you aren't, I'll have to ask you to leave.
You look better than most do.nnYou're probably the healthiest traveler the Quarantine Serk has ever seen. nnFor that, you should be thankful.

With Sarvyl gone, they've appointed me as the new Head Mender. nnDirdren's first orders required a full examination of everyone in the Serk. nnSince Sarvyl managed to linger so long while he was infected, concern and paranoia here has risen a bit.
<The silent warden stares back at you, glaring thorugh empty eye sockets.>
You! nnWell... it's strange to run into you again. Wouldn't you agree?
I know youyou're the meddler from Pariah Abbey.nnI don't care, so long as you amuse us more than the other guests. Quite frankly, they're gutless and feeble.
Why are you bothering me? I've done nothing wrong. nnI'm just watching the carts go in and out. Maybe if a spare scrap falls out, I'll get lucky.
Come closer. I must speak to you... quietly.
See these empty beds? We've been lucky. No outbreaks of the disease are plaguing Stonefalls yet. nnThe soldiers at the Serk are doing a splendid job.
My sister and I made it out of Razorvine just in time, it seems. I was watching for Imperial pursuers, but it seems like the forest took care of that.
This building is under quarantine. nnSpend no more time inside than necessary.
You! nnWill you fight me, little <<1>>? nnI dare you!
The plants around here are quite thorny today! Ha!nn...Just my little joke. Never mind.
How could you set her loose? What did I ever do to you?
Who let that horrid woman free?
I dare say next time you have a free moment, rescue me from this unreasonable woman.
Forlos won't take responsibility for trading our last good wagon wheel to those workers at the crossroads to the west. It will take forever to repair this one.
I'm sorry but the Count has ordered that no guests be allowed past this point.nnAnyone who violates that may be attacked.
The eyes of the Silent Warden are fixed upon Haventown to the south.
Begone, mortal!nnLeave me, lest I find an reason to separate your body from your soul.
Mortal, you tread on treacherous ground. nnMy sisters may take offense to your trespass.nnThat would bode ill for you.
Ah, it's you. nnThank Azura you're all right. I've heard terrible rumors about Count Hosni's revels here.
The satisfaction of seeing the Vereansu get cut down will be enough to assuage the pains of this sickness for some time now.
I didn't care much for House Hlaalu when I first arrived.nnAfter what I've been through, I can't thank the Three enough for their help.
With the shock of that rock slide, I don't think the Vereansu even knew what hit them.
Oh, praise the Eight you're not a slaver! Feels like I've been hiding up here forever.nnYou've got to help me. They put out the signal fire and I need help getting it relit.

Listen! <<1>> tried to steer our ship true, but I swear the first mate sabatoged us.nnWe were captured by pirates when we foundered. Once they're done beating our poor captain, they're going to sell us as slaves. You've got to untie me! Hurry!
Elvira Derre! I trusted her with my life and my ship. This is the thanks I got. Run aground and beaten, my crew . nnBlessed Mara, I hope they haven't killed my crew.
Our ship foundered in the dark, and now these filthy pirates plan to sell us as slaves.nnPlease help us! Our captain and half the crew are in chains!
You are not expected. nnIf you want your petition to be heard, you will wait with the others.nnIf that is not your task here, you may proceed.
Deliveries. Letters. Missives.nnWhatever. All I really want is a flagon of cool ale.
We're searching for a Nord woman named Lyris Titanborn. nnIf you see her, you will inform an Imperial representative immediately. Understood?
I'm a little busy now, if you can't tell. nnOthrina will have my hide if we miss this shipment.

First, they attacked my husband and left him to die. Then they separated me from my sister. They sent her to be sold as a slave.nnI've lost everything and everyone I ever cared about. Only my oath of vengance sustains me now.
Try to be quiet. There are hostile Ashlanders nearby, and I can't afford to have you giving away our position.
Please, talk to one of my clutchmates.nnI am in too much pain to offer you assistance.
You don't look like one of our guests. Maybe you can do me a favor....
Our rogue sisters may hold our attention, but remember: we're watching you.

This was... not what I was expecting.nnI'm unsure of how this is even possible. A cruel joke played upon me by the gods, surely. To live once more, yet be farther from life than ever before.nnYou put more than just bones in there, didn't you?

You are brave to enter our haven so brazenly. Few care to invite death as you have. I admire that.nnMy sisters may think little of you, but I know you are one willing to do what must be done. Time will tell if you are strong enough to succeed.
I will not speak to you. nnIf you need something from the guardians, speak to Kussi.
Stay away. I don't have time for your kind.
I'm very thankful that those dark times are past. I don't remember much of what happened, but what I do remember is unpleasant.
I'd prefer to work without distractions. nnThe last assistant who was distracted found himself stuck in the tar. He was eaten by a nix-hound.
Rarthis didn't deserve to be killed by those witches.nnWho will avenge him?
Don't worry about me. I'm testing out a new method of removing oneself from this viscous muck.nnI do wish my partner would return, though.
What does it matter? nnThere's no reason to guard Wayrest. It's gonna be gone by tomorrow! nnMay your end be pleasant, traveler!
By the Three! May the soul of my son Rarthis find peace...nn...and may the Mabrigash witches who did this to him find everlasting torment in Oblivion.
Rarthis and I were to be married!nnHow am I to tell my parents that I will bear a dead man's child?
He was too young! He died too soon.
Why have you come back?nnThis is no mere chore, <<1>>, to be done at your leisure! The Balac is the key to freeing this world from Molag Bal's grip. nnYou must find it with all haste.
This one has heard that only the dead walk in Haven.
I found this nice little spot on the road. nnI had to set up camp for the night, and thought, "Why not? Let's set up shop here for a little while!"
I'm on duty now. I gotta watch out for bandits. nnYou're not a bandit, right?
If you need something, talk to Rindras. nnHe won't let us handle the coins.

Being the only leatherworker in the area has its ups and downs. nnOn the one hand, everyone comes to you for their needs. nnOn the other hand, you run out of wares all the time. This job is always feast or famine.
What business do you have with me?
I certainly hope you aren't here to stir up trouble.nnSeems like those who claim they're just "passing through" are really here to make things more difficult.
What is it that you seek?
We've got to do something about the lighthouse before any more ships wreck. nnIf we can find enough mirrors, we can fix the damage and repair the lighthouse. nnThen we relight the lighthouse.
I don't know if I can stand this anymore! Simply wait for the inevitable to happen... watching yourself forget and decay.nnIt's simply too much for anyone to bear!
Welcome, intrepid adventurer!nnWelcome to the wonderful, the magical, the miraculous Crypt of Hearts!
Thank you for freeing me from that accursed stone!nnMaster Wizard Kellisa must pay for this insult.
You survived, my friend!nnNow you know the truth.
These filthy pirates want to sell us all into slavery. Please, find a way to save us!

It was the captain. I know it was! He sold us out. I can feel it in my bones!nnCrashing the ship was just a clever ruse, but I see through it. Getting tied up like the rest of us? Nice try, but I'm not fooled, captain!
Lately, brigands have been ambushing merchants on our roads.nnI suspect someone has been feeding them information.
I don't know if I can stand this anymore. To simply wait for the inevitable to happen, to watch yourself forget and decay, is too much for any one to bear.
Help me out of here! Hurry, before the slavers see you!
I'm tired of listening to Ra'ud's sellswords brag!nnMost of us have better things to do than swinging a sword all day.

The guards watch me like a hawk whenever I'm preparing their food.nnThe slavers think their wine is safe because they're keeping an eye on it. We should prove they're wrong.nnA little poison should do the trick, don't you think?
Why? Why does the Sleeper torment me? Why does the Sleeper's master haunt my dreams?
They say I'm crazy, but I know Danabi is alive! nnI did not feel his passing as I did my father's death.nnHe is still with me.
I must be dreaming... or is this the punishment I must endure?

I am bound by the will of Master Wizard Kallisa. nnKallisa is bound by the will of her master. nnTherefore, we are all bound by the will of Kallisa's master. nnI cannot break my bonds. When I break my bonds, Kallisa's Master will be my Master.
I can see them with my eyes shut!nnHow can you escape something that lives in your mind?
The sickness spreading through this village is a test of our faith. I'm quite certain of that!
Alas, my troops have arrived! Razorvine Refuge will be secured.
This area holds the first key: the <<1>>.
<The acolyte stares listlessly into the glowing artifact.>
Here, you will find <<1>>... if you stay alive.
Within the flames is the <<1>>, one of the keys you need.
The key you need, the <<1>>, is in this statuary.
Another challenger has come to taunt me?nnSave your breath.

So I finally have the chance to meet <<1>>, the hero who carved a path of blood and steel through Hammerdeath. This is indeed a momentous occasion.nnI am Hosni at-Tura. I think you and I have a few things in common, my friend.

They've gone mad! All of them! nnThe Master Wizard. The teachers. The apprentices. All mad!nnI came from Shad Astula, the wizard academy up the path. I barely escaped with my life, but others are still trapped inside!

Once the madness began, I felt it overwhelm me. nnI fled to my room and used a glass orb my mother gave me for protection against evil. nnIt warded off the madness long enough for me to barely escape! If you can find it, you can save my friends.
I could feel my mind slipping away. nnIt was like someone was pulling at each thought with a puppeteer's strings.
When I was slipping over the edge, I saw visions of the Red Mountain. I saw horrible creatures I cannot even begin to describe! nnIt was as if my terror gave them shape and form.
The others tormented me because I wasn't mad... not like they were. nnI did feel myself slipping away, but only slowly. nnPerhaps that's the only reason they didn't tear me apart.
What a noble heart yours must be, to have endured Nerien's trials. You give me hope for the world, even now.
If you require anything, please speak to Disciple Farathan.

A catastrophe in Shad Astula! A catastrophe caused by the taint of foreign magic! nnThat tree-licker was hired to teach "alternative" magic. Now she's disrupted the spirit of the Master Wizard!nnThat Argonian has destroyed our great school!
Shad Astula is poisoning minds. Its source lies in its roots.nnTo cleanse the great tree, we must remind it of its greatness.
Are you on their side? Can I trust you?nnMark my words. The Midnight Swell isn't all that it seems. They're up to no good on that ship. We can't have their kind coming ashore.
What do you want? I'm protecting our village from these foreign cretins. You'll move along if you know what's good for you.

The area behind me is known as the Sylvan Uplands.nnA gathering of men and women who have been wronged by the evil Mabrigash have come here to prepare for battle. We will slay each and every one of those witches to get our revenge.
I tried to stop them, but was too late. nnAncestors! Forgive me for my weakness!
We live in trying times. First, the House Dunmer forced themselves upon us. Now we must fight whatever plagues our village.
You shouldn't have come why did you come here?
The plants around here are quite thorny today! Ha!nn...Just my little joke. Never mind.
From the temple, blessings to you and yours  nnWhat can this humble servant do for you?
A blessing upon your house, traveler. nnMay the Tribunal grant you safe passage through our troubled lands.
I'm dead. nnI'm not intangible. I'm just a ghost.
I know you. <<1>>, right?nnDon't ask me how I know. I do this for a living. nnI run around, delivering messages to poor damned souls who don't want to be found.nnI found you. I have a message.

Beware! nnLosing his Heart, his Light has made him mad. Nerien has become Nerien'eth and he will doom you all.nnBeware what lies ahead - beware his tricks, beware the very ground beneath your feet lest it be a trap!
Alanwe means 'daughter of the moon.'  But now he sees only darkness.nWhere once there was love, now obsession. Where once there was joy, hopeless wrath. Where has his heart gone?

Nerien and I built Heartland, a city of great beauty, for those who sought our guidance.nnWhen I was killed, Nerien turned his intellect to cheating death.nnBeware his monsters that lie ahead.  You will need all your wits and strength to pass.
Nerien and Alanwe were so good to us, in those days. Heartland was a beautiful place, as they promised. Then the dream turned to a nightmare...
We all came to Heartland looking for something better. For a long time, we found that. Nerien and Alanwe created a paradise for us.
There's more work to be done here.
I couldn't ask for a greater gift than seeing dear Hairan's smiling face again.nnI have you to thank for that, friend.
By the Divines, do you come to help me?

I've collected beasts from all over Tamriel to fight in our arena. nnAdventurers travel vast distances to test themselves against these monsters. Spectators pay to watch their triumphs  and tragic deaths. There's nothing quite like it!
Make it quick! I have to feed the beasts soon.nnBut not too much. They're meaner when they're hungry.

I barely escaped with my life! Please, you've got to listen to me!nnI came here at the behest of the patriarch. I thought it was an honor to be summoned by him. nnI was wrong. He's gone completely mad!
Betting's the thing here at Hammerdeath. Winning isn't. nnWe're not here to lose money.
Betting's the thing here at Hammerdeath. Winning isn't. nnWe're not here to lose money.
I have no interest in what you have to say.
You win some, you lose some. nnI win a lot!

Somebody has to get rid of these scamps before they get me. They've kidnapped my boss, and I'm next! I can feel them all around me, sniffing at my thoughts...nnNo one else saw this coming but I knew! I knew! The chickens told me, you see.
What'll you have, then? This is a cash only establishment, mind you. No credit extended for anyone, not even family.nnCan't trust anyone to pay these days, other than up front. So what'll it be?
Have you seen a small guar around here? nnHe's dark brown and only about six months old.
The small, brown guar looks very frightened. He is uncertain of your presence.
Never a dull day in Alcaire. These are thirsty times, my friend.
The small guar looks happy to see you.
We're searching for a Nord woman named Lyris Titanborn. nnIf you see her, you will inform an Imperial representative immediately. Understood?
I was beginning to get worried!nnI overheard the Supernal Dreamers talking about using me in some sort of ritual. I guess you got here just in time.
I've never seen alits fight quite like these.
I'm trying to find a way into the lower level. Somewhere down there, we'll find a way to stop Kellisa.nnMy divinations have shown me she's siphoning dark magic from an unknown source.
We treated the roots, but the groundwater was fouled. The cleansing is not complete.
I know you must think I'm crazy, but I've seen this temple in my dreams.nnFor years, I tried to forget it, but I finally had to come and see it with my own eyes. nnImagine my surprise....

So you've finally arrived. That took you long enough, wanderer.nnI didn't call you here for pleasantries, <<1>>. No matter how much time I spent watching and waiting, knowing what I had to do... nn...I couldn't do it.

Two mages in my school are at odds over how to destroy this madness. nnOne proposes a traditional Argonian approach. The other would like to feed the magic back into itself, cutting it off from the source.nnBoth methods seem sound. What do you think?
<You've found a statue that looks very lifelike.>
Do you mind? I prefer to drink in peace.
At first, it was pretty quiet here. Then someone touched something they shouldn't have, and all of Oblivion broke loose. nnNow the ruins are a mess of goblins, Daedra, and Sep knows what else.
I'd stay clear of the ruins, if I were you. It's not a good place to be right now.nnSayma and I are returning to Alcaire Castle as soon as we can convince the foreman to leave.

So you've finally come. That took you long enough, wanderer!nnI didn't call you here for pleasantries, <<1>>. No matter how much time I spent watching and waiting, knowing what I must do... nn...I couldn't do it.

So you've finally come. That took you long enough, wanderer!nnI didn't call you here for pleasantries, <<1>>. No matter how much time I spent watching and waiting, knowing what I must do... nn...I couldn't do it.
You are no match for the patriarch. Leave this place, before you are enslaved! nnThe patriarch must not be allowed to bolster his ranks!

Do what you must. Do what I couldn't. Deliver the final blow!nnMy thoughts of you will not change. I understand you are merely guiding me along a path to the fate I deserve.nnYou are no more than an agency of my destiny.
There has been a distinct change in the mannerisms of the students, but those of power still seem far gone. We still have a lot to do, but at least no more will be afflicted.
The river has taken another course. Its flooding waters will no longer harm this land.

I was enslaved in a Dunmer mine years ago, but I escaped. Now, of all the villages in all of Tamriel, they attack here? nnI think maybe I'm cursed. I'm not going anywhere until I'm sure the slavers are long gone.
The Supernal Dreamers captured me and tied me up. You've got to help me!
I couldn't leave, not without knowing what's going on here.nnDid you free my men? nnThey didn't deserve this. None of us did.

I know you. <<1>>, right?nn<<2>> said you'd be arriving soon. "The Gray Carrier will come," she said. Damned woman is never wrong.nnI suspect you're eager to get this writ taken care of. Let's cut right to it.

A stranger? Here? Have you come to join us?nnWe always have room. There's always a dark alcove nearby, ready to hide another body.nnWhy the worried expression? Ah, yes. You must be Gray Carrier the master mentioned.

Keep your distance from these fetchers, Gray Carrier. nnThey would fill your ears with lies. They'll slice your neck, if chance favors them.nnEnough of my rants against the Brotherhood. You've come for the gray writ, yes?

What're you lookin' at, s'wit?nnYou're getting in my face like you got something to say. I don't remember saying you could speak to me.nnYou're disrespecting me, aren't you? You're lucky I don't smash your face in.
Thanks! I never though I would actually survive that. Let's get out of here... quickly!
They've tied me up here! They want to cut my heart out!

Wouuuld youu like to hear a shong? Huh? Let me shing a shong for you!nnI have sho many to choose from! What about the Morhagdongsh? I know pleeenty about them and their evilish ways. What'dya shay, eh?nnMy shongs are unique!
You! You look pretty dangerous. You're drafted. nnThere are goblins here that need killing.
Why do I bother trying to collect from people who have no money?
S'Rashi is grateful for the help you provided to Hilani at Hammerdeath Arena. This one thanks you.nnWhat business have you with S'Rashi today?
They let you in so you could help. nnI don't understand it, myself. In here, you're just another mouth to feed.
By the Lord, Mother, and Wizard, let us escape!
Nothing like a good drink to keep you going.
The alits here are truly fascinating.
Who allowed you entrance here? I think you need to leave.
The cloaked dunmer regards you coldly with no interest in speaking with you.
You're not a Supernal Dreamer. Help me!
Do you have business with me? I sincerely hope not. You seem like quite a bore!
Care to make a wager, friend?
They've tied me up! They want to cut my heart out!
If you think being nice will get you better service, don't waste your breath.
You look weary, traveler. I have talents to ease your tension.
I wouldn't try anything, if I were you.
I just need one good break to turn my luck around!
These fights keep getting better and better. I never knew those animals were so powerful!
What can I interest you in, friend?
May your journey through Mournhold be safe and profitable.
Blessings of the Three upon you. I fervently hope you fare better than we do.
Ho, stranger. Walk softly and trust no one.
What do you want? Do you make it a habit to accost strangers? nnThat's foolish, even in the best of times.
I have to admit, the man knows how to brew a good beer!
Would you look at this? It's just my luck.
I'm not doing business with you.
Stop bothering me or I'll call the guard.
Stay back! Spiders have taken over the basement!nnI think they're a Redguard plot to keep us from getting to our scrolls!
Tsajivi can see you are headed into town.nnPerhaps you are brave enough to help Tsajivi?
We came with Lady Brerama to see what happened to her brother.nnBe careful around here. Something's not right.
This is still House Indoril's property, regardless of what's happened here. nnState your business with the Lady Brerama, or be on your way.
I wish we were able to meet under better circumstances. nnI am Nelam Indoril, the father of Brerama and Beltis.nnTell me what you've discovered.
I don't envy you.nnI wouldn't go down there.
I don't envy you.nnI wouldn't go down there.
I don't know who you are, and I don't want to know. Leave me alone.
They're going to find me. Are you working for them? You are! Get away from me!
Get back, stranger. I don't know who you are.
You'll not get anything from me. Spy!
Keep your distance. I don't trust you.
They better stop talking about me, or I'm going to make them stop.
How would you like a sword in your gut? Mind your business!

This place was once a peaceful place, a refuge of repose... but the Supernal Dreamers have desecrated it with their bloody rites. nnEven as we speak, they enact their rites of sacrifice. My spirit cannot rest until you purify this land again.
I know we can't trust them, but how am I to run a boarding house when I haven't any boarders?nnMy son should let them sailors off the ship to spend their money at least.
I don't envy you.nnI wouldn't go down there.
I beg your pardon. Was there something you needed?
This is the worst port I've ever seen, with the most unfriendly people. What's wrong with them?
How bad was it?nnI'll bet you have some stories to tell.
I don't recognize you. What are you doing here? nnShow me your credentials!
What do you think? This is the finest Dwemer artifact I've seen in my four centuries as a scholar.

Being a dockworker has its benefits the ocean breeze on my face, eating fresh fish for lunch and meeting new people every day.nnOn the downside, it stinks like rotten fish and I've gotten more splinters than I can count.
I still don't trust them. I don't care what Oscent says. These sailors are bad news.
I wonder if these sailors are really what they claim to be? They could be spies. I'm sure they are!
Go away! No one asked you to be here.
Something's very wrong in the mine. nnI don't know the extent of the problem, but we have to investigate.nnI fear my brother may be involved!
One moment, we were unearthing an ancient obelisk. nnThe next thing I knew, my workers were dead, and Daedra were everywhere!
The Dominion owes you much.nnAnother regiment of troops are on their way. When they arrive, we'll take back the Cyro-Valen Trade Compound to the west.

You've got to help me! I won't survive another one of Jharad's interrogations.nnHe laughs when they beat us and smiles while he takes notes.nnI shudder to think what will become of us once he's collected enough information.
First, they kill my villagers and burn the village.nnNow they're looting the houses. They're torturing us for information about Bangkorai!nnThey can hurt me, but I still won't talk.
I killed her. She deserved it, didn't she?  nnI know she did, or I think I know  is this real?
You killed the Omen. May the Eight bless you.nnMy mind is free  but my sins remain.
Have a good- is it day or night?nnOh, now this is interesting....
They'll kill him. Don't you understand, they will kill my brother in there.
Be silent. Place your fingers on the stones. You can still feel reverberations. As if the Dwemer struck Nirn itself with a tuning fork.
The fishing has been good. Too good. Some sort of witchery. I don't think these fish look right. What, what do you want?
One day we'll understand Dwemer artifacts like this. After that, we'll be able to replicate them.
I came here to investigate the legend of the Band of Four.nnI almost became a legend myself!
They're coming for us all, you know. It's only a matter of time. That's why this lot had to be locked away. They're conspiring against us.
I didn't mean to do it. I didn't mean to do it. It was an accident!nnThey're out to get me. They locked me up, but it was an accident.
Go away! Go away! I'm not mad, I tell you! They are! The ones out there!
We set up camp on a main road close to Mournhold. You'd think we'd be safer here.
Please, let me out! They're going to kill us. We've done nothing!
I think I can pull these nails out. nnWe can escape before they hang us... or maybe they plan to cut off our hands... or burn us!nnAre you here to help us escape? You must be here to save us!
I want to die. Please, kill me. nnKill me before they do. They think we're mad, but we're not.nnIt's the nightmares. The nightmares are terrifying! Please, kill me before I sleep again!

Everything is going according to their plan. Everything!nnThey came in the night, right into our homes. They frightened everyone, didn't they? nnThey don't scare me! And soon, they'll come to set me free!
I was a smith, you know. In Heartland they taught me new ways to forge and better my craft. I was happy there.
You never saw such a beautiful place as that valley. And how we all lived together, worked together... it was every bit as good as they promised, until the end.
Nerien loved her to distraction. Everything he did in Heartland, he did for her. But then when she died, everything changed.  That was the beginning of the end. He was a changed man.
You should have seen our governors back then, Nerien and Alanwe.  So bright, so beautiful. He hung the moon on Alanwe, you know.  He called her his Bright One.
My wife and I grew such bountiful crops we had more than we knew what to do with. How things grew in that place was magic, I'm telling you.
We worked hard in those days, it's true. But we worked willingly, for the good of all. Not like later, when Nerien became so changed. And those under his hand toiled for such a dark purpose...
I'd have done anything for Nerien, before he lost Alanwe. He was a good man. But then she died and the things he asked of us many refused. Then we were punished. I will not speak of it more.
I was a tailor in Heartland. I made clothes for so many settlers who came, I scarcely remember their names anymore. I do remember we were happy, though. As happy as anyone gets in this life.
Alanwe was Nerien's light and reason. And when she was gone, light and reason went with her. Only darkness and insanity remained.
We were all so glad to find that gentle valley. We had no idea what nightmares would come later...
Nerien loved her too much. Without her, he transformed into something none of us recognized.
Oh, Alanwe was beautiful, I suppose. But what she was was smart. I was a good architect when I came to Heartland, but a better one after her tutelage.
We had a good life in Heartland. Almost as good as they promised us, before it all changed.

Don't try anything. Keep your voice low and don't hurt any of the villagers. They may be mad, but they're my friends and neighbors.nnBy Mara's heart, you don't think I'm in here because I'm next, do you? Do you?
Why are you here? Is Edros all right?
Do you see my power? Can you see all the atronachs I've summoned?nnTremble, mortal, for I am the Storm King!
There's nothing wrong with an honest day's work.
Nerien and Alanwe were so good to us, in those days. Heartland was a beautiful place, as they promised. Then the dream turned to a nightmare...
These devices would be quite fascinating if they weren't trying to kill us.
Welcome to Evermore Farms! Our fields are burnt, and our livestock is slaughtered, but hey - at least we're still alive.

The Reachmen killed our sentries. They attacked in the dead of the night. They slaughtered those who offered resistance and captured the rest.nnI can still hear screams from time to time, so I know at least some of our people are still alive.
Welcome to my realm.nnBe at ease and listen to my songs.
I beg your pardon. I'm trying to present the daily reports to Lord Saren.
You... you are the one who sealed the breach. I cannot thank you enough. nnYou freed me from that nightmare, though I may not have deserved such kindness.nnKindness is never forgotten.
I can't hear the stones anymore! nnWhy won't these contraptions be silent? I was so close to an answer!
There were vibrations everywhere. nnThere were sounds beyond hearing, just a ringing in the ears. nnI think I was close to understanding something.
Huh? Oh, you don't want to talk to me.nnI'm just a student assisting the <<1>>!nnNo one ever talks to me. It's so lonely here.

You! Yes, you! I remember you. Lord Saren said something about....nnOkay, I don't remember. I was busy extrapolating the past subjective tense of the rune representing the absence of decay.nnForgive me. Just some light reading.
I'm fairly sure one of those runes represented a rather nuanced concept. It symbolizes a lost soul vainly straining to reach apotheosis.nnDid I mention that?
Dwemer machines are impressive, but our efforts to reactivate them have been somewhat premature. nnWe need to study the instructions on how to operate them first.
My theory goes against all currently accepted scholarship, yet I must insist! It is the truth! nnOnly a fool would deny it!
Watch your step. We don't tolerate crime here.
I don't know what's going on around here, but if you're looking for a good Orcish novel, I can offer a few suggestions.
Hey, you! <<1>>! nnYou look like you're passing through town. Are you heading east?
Bring glory to the Three through your actions, and you shall be rewarded.
Careful, friend. Haven Trace is full of Wood Orcs.nnAs if we didn't have enough trouble with the Imperials....
You made it through! Fantastic! nnI was worried. I thought the Wood Orcs would tear you to pieces on your way here.
<This knight is too injured to speak.>
So many brave and injured knights. Some will not live to see tomorrow.
I sure hope Tidryn is all right. nnShe left to find a path. She's looking for people on the hill north of here.nnShe never returned.
These people have treated me well, despite the fact that I'm an outsider.
I sent a team out to research the swamps south of here days ago. nnI expected some kind of response by now.
I can't let anyone see what I've found. nnHow am I going to get away from here, so I can prove this was my discovery?
Whatever dark influence that dominated Sir Hughes, that was the enemy.nnThis man is innocent.
No matter how hard you try, you can't get this sticky mess off your hands.
Have you seen a guar with a scar on his rump?
I made it out. The fetchers up north won't let me through. Said I was sick. nnBut I found a way. Who says Ashlanders are good for nothing?

While the Dominion was focused on retaking Southpoint, the Imperials sacked the Khajiit town of Haven. nnSome of the Khajiit guards responded, but not many.nnI fear an Imperial advance on Razorvine is inevitable.
Keep an eye out! More Orcs means more trouble.

Have you come to help the Warrior Guard liberate Haven from the Imperials?nnThey've aligned themselves with Daedric forces, adding dark magic to their already formidable power.nnYour alliances should be quite clear.
We may be at war with the Empire, but that doesn't mean we should be rude to them!nnThey should meet some of our friends. In fact, I know some snakes who would love to greet them properly!
Spare a coin for the hurt and hungry? nnA good, strong <<1>> like you should always be flush with coins, right?
J'Hriss believes the Imperials hold secrets we should all know.nnWhy else would one guard a ship that's sunken and lost?nnThat makes no sense to J'Hriss.
You here for sleep, or are you here for talk?
Careful, friend! Haven Trace is full of Wood Orcs. nnAs if we didn't have enough trouble with the Imperials. Now the Orcs are preying on our weakness.
You here to spend coin? If not, get out.
You've made it through Haven Trace! nnWe've been worried that we wouldn't get aid from Southpoint. nnIt's fantastic to see you!
I have no money to live in the town, but I don't have the skills to live in the wilderness. Especially not after what I saw.
I sure wish I could help you with something.
The waters are muddy, and silt chokes. The surface is distant.

<<1>> took his scouts and moved through the Trace, headed east. nnIf you're looking for him, you should be able to find him on the other side of Haven Trace.nnHopefully, he's managed to clear the way, so we can get troops and supplies through.
My friends were slain, and their bodies were burned. nnThat stench... it was too much.

A Daedra's heart! I never thought I'd ever see one!nnTake it back to camp. House Hlaalu will be grateful for the restoration of the Obelus.nnI'll teleport you! Then I'll clean up. Then I'll outsmart these idiots and go back to camp.nnHmph. Idiots.
My soldiers fought ferociously to make it here.nnOnce they've rested, we'll press on and reclaim the town.
My arms are numb. I can't feel my fingers. I won't be able to fight.
Our Great House finally sent someone to get us out of here?nnThank the Three!
If I don't report by next morning, I'll surely be reprimanded. nnIf I leave, though, Marayn wil surely leave me!
I'm pleased to meet you, <<1>>. nnYou may not know me, but I'm well acquainted with your exploits. nnConsider me... an admirer.
The daedra are everywhere! I'd run, but where is safe?
I have a feeling you're here for the same reasons I am, <<1>>. nnIf you have a moment, I'd like to know more about what you've discovered.nnAbide with me a while.
I should be in fighting shape in a few weeks. Thank you again for rescuing me.
I had a few dark moments out there. Thank you for bringing me back to the light.
Thank you for saving me! I can't wait to see my mother's smiling face again.
Our attack was precise. Our victory was swift.
Halt! Identify yourself! Everyone must tell me. Tell me who you are. Identify yourself.
What are you doing out here? Did you see my parents on the road?
With the Warmaster leading the way, reclaiming this town will hardly be a challenge.
If you had business with the Morag Tong, I would have been notified. nnBest move along. Forget you ever saw this place.
We didn't think we'd make it past the Daedra. Thank you!

The war has even reached the southern shores of Grahtwood.nnImperial attacks on innocent villages are becoming all too common.nnWhy they felt this town was important enough to occupy still remains to be seen.
I've got to get back to Eagle's Gate. Can you help me?
You hold no claim to these goods. Unless you are another servant of House Dres? We've already dealt with the first one.
No one expected we would ever come back to Haven. nnIt is good to be home.
Villagers are trapped in their homes!
The fish are really biting! Ha ha.nnHa.nnOh gods.
What assistance do you require, traveler? nnIf you're looking for advice, I suggest you remain in Stormhaven  and stay well away from Rivenspire.
This is unexpected. Why are you here?

Honored guests! Please, excuse the mess. Things are just starting to calm down after the attack.nnWould you like something to eat? I'm waiting for Father to return. I've made more than enough.nnHe should be back soon... I hope.
Something must be done about Godrun, and soon.
Something must be done about Godrun, and soon.
Something must be done about Godrun, and soon.
Something must be done about Godrun, and soon.
Don't draw too much attention to me. nnI need to rescue my friends. I'm not sure if I can do it on my own.
I do not know from whence you came.nnNonetheless, I appreciate your timely arrival.
Will you look at the damage to this bucket? It's full of holes!
Greetings, traveler. What brings you to this remote locale?
You killed Blackroot? I won't lie. That's pretty impressive.nnHe's been a thorn in our side for a while, even before this Blacksap treachery.

The Imperials will pay for what they've done to my people.nnI will see them suffer, slowly twisting in agony! nnAnd I shall laugh and laugh at their torment. I shall savor their suffering! I shall have my revenge!
Nothing like a good drink to keep you going.
Tread lightly, for you are not one of our kind. My sisters may take offense to your trespassing, and that would not bode well for you.
I can send you to distant lands in the blink of an eye. Where do you wish to go?
I found Jillae, as you can see. nnWhat a fine adventure we all had!
Do you need assistence? If not, I'm afraid I'm busy at the moment.
