I'm not sure if I've ever felt like this before. This is the greatest contraption I've ever seen!nnSee how they've bound me? Not with rope... not with leather... but with these chainlink cuffs!nnThey're incredibly painful. In fact, they're brilliant!
It'll be good to be back home.nnWhat's left of it, anyway.
It's good to see you again, <<1>>!nnI'm glad you made it out of the palisade safely.nnI wasn't worried, of course. I'm just happy to see you.

Stormclouds gather over Rivenspire, just as they did in the days of Ranser's War. nnShornhelm's forces once filled this valley. They say his army was so vast that it spread beyond the horizon. Fortunately for us, that army is much smaller now.
There are so many dead. nnShe must be nearby. I can feel her presence.
It's good to see you again. nnI will confess, though, I wasn't certain you'd actually try to find us.
Why have you come back? nnThis is no mere chore to be done at your leisure! The Balac is the key to freeing this world from Molag Bal's grip. nnYou must find it with all haste.
Wisdom dictates one must retreat when outnumbered.nnJ'raka prefers to charge forth, butcher the enemy, and burn their corpses. nnThose who run carry fear into the ranks of the enemy.
I have a confession, <<1>>. Fate and I conspire together, and many are the tasks set before you. To be the tool, the smith's hammer, the one who strikes the formative blow. This is known.
From the shadows, <<1>> watches the Imperials' movements. nnThis one sees everything they do... every time they move... in every direction they travel.nn<<1>> will avenge Southpoint!
Thank you for ending my waking torment.

Qi, I want to help fight! I can fight, just like my brother!nnI think they made father run away. Qi, you have to let me help!nnI wa... oh, hello there, <<1>>. I didn't see you there!nnHave you come to join the fight?
They attacked while you were gone.nnThe Imperials knew we were here! Qi'Ravin tried to fight them off. nnThis one took many with him, but not enough to stop them from taking Farah. She's gone!

We've been asked to ensure these mages don't get into trouble while in Spritedancer Marsh. All of us Jaqspurs could watch over these Altmer and they would still manage to get themselves in trouble.nnIt wouldn't be so bad if they bothered to listen.

Why would anyone build warding obelisks in this Daedra-damned swamp?nnBosmer claim there was a road here once, but the forest reclaimed it.nnI remain skeptical. I have trouble separating their truths from their myths. Honestly, I think they do, too.
<This body has already started decomposing. It still vaguely looks like an Altmer.>
My Bosmer guide simply does not understand.nnI am an Altmer, and a mage at that!nnI am above this endless trudging through muck. This unnecessary physical exertion is beneath me!
Qi'Ravin has fallen silent. The life from his body now drained.

<<1>>? Is that you? How did you find me? It's so dangerous around here!nnThe Imperials treat me like a sack of fruit, tossing me about and what not. nnI didn't know how much longer they were going to keep me alive.
The warmaster believes Vonov awaits us beyond that foul-looking portal.
Look! When the magic disappated, that portal appeared!

My brother Loran and I were asked to guide these mages through the marsh. nnI expressly told the Altmer, "Don't look directly at the wisps!"nnOf course, one of them didn't listen. The wisps entranced him, and he wandered off with a ritual book

Thanks for meeting with me, <<1>>.nnI couldn't speak about this at Southpoint. Too many ears might overhear. I know what my father was trying to protect. nnI wasn't sure if I could tell you, but you've done more than enough to earn my trust!
Rahira is proud to know you, <<1>>.

<You see the body of Farah resting before you. A look of solemn peace adorns her face, even in death.>nn<The soil  rises up around her, embracing the body of the Treethane's daughter, as if the two were becoming one.>nn<Then she is gone.>
We don't have much to sell, but any coin we make here will help us.nnOnce those dirty Imperials leave our lands, I'm certain our lives will improve.
I would ask you to let these people rest, stranger. They need sleep, not company.

Our healers work day and night, attempting to heal the wounded.nnMost who fell during the invasion have already healed. The ones who still lay ill are suffering from something different.nnWe suspect poison.
Yes, father. I hear you. I'll do everything I can to protect our people.nnAre you hungry, father? Would you like something to eat?nnWhy, hello there, stranger! Have you met my father?

We must be missing something.nnWhile the Imperials are pushing from the eastern shores, they're maintaining a tight grip on Haven.nnThey won't relinquish their grip on the town. Why is that? Why focus so heavily on Haven?
The Imperials are sly. They keep slipping from our grasp.nnRi'osh thinks the guards attacking Haven aren't normal. He thinks they're accompanied by dark magic.
This guardian is now active. Cormeir is now protected.nnCaution is advised. The prison at Cormeir is no longer contained.

Cursed! Ever living. Never living. nnArlimahera demanded we hold the ruins. Padesh was our leader, but we followed.nnWe slaughtered the four mages and their retainers, but not before they cast their curse: no life and no release in death.
Why do we wait for the Ashlanders' mercy? We should force them to share their cure with us!
Could you ask someone to attend to us?nnWe've come so far.
The song! It stopped!nnMy hands feel so heavy. nnWhat just happened? Who are you? What do you want with me?

Do you see them? The Aldmeri Dominion is strong. It's powerful. It's honorable! nnIt's exactly like Ra'Vashi wants to be someday.nnTo live and die defending those he loves... that is Ra'Vashi's dream!
Welcome to Evermore, stranger.nnI fear our court is not suited for visitors at this time, but you are welcome to enjoy any of the services within our city.
Welcome to the Anchor's Pointa cozy home in weather fair or foul! How can I help you?
Are you interested in the arcane arts? nnMagic is an art, you know.
Come closer. I sense you carry a great burden.

Salutations, traveler. We are the magi of the Aldmeri Dominion.nnWhen we started scrying for magical weapons, the ruins at Cormeir blazed brightly.nnWe are endeavoring to unlock its secrets. However, the ruins exhibit ... strange behavior.

Ever since the Imperial attack, Spriggans have risen up on the cliff side over there. Crazy things tried eating me! If they're hungry, all they have to do is ask.nnYou might want to stay away. Not much up there anyways.
The animals here were docile, possibly even curious.nnAs soon as we killed the first one, they turned on us.
Aha! A fellow infiltrator. Ri'Zama is glad to see you.nnI have a plan to cause some trouble inside that Palisade. Perhaps this will help in your endeavors, no?
Cormeir Warden reporting: year one thousand, two hundred and sixty-three.nnPlease provide directives.

This one tries to focus on the positive. Fighting mad kwama now will make it easier to appreciate our lives later.nnThen we'll be ready to work long hours in the mines for poor food and no pay.nnSee? It is easy, yes?
All these giant bugs are making me hungry.
I hope another bug attacks soon.
Can you get us out of here?
Hunting here is strange. nnI can't remember anyone hunting in the Thrambles. That would be the easiest hunt in Grahtwood, I'd imagine. nnThe animals might even be friendly!
You probably don't realize how lucky you are. nnTell you what. You wanna play a game and find out?
Exciting, wasn't it?nnFighting your way through a dangerous maze of wilderness... racing to reach the cure....nnExcuse me. I lied. There is no cure.
Most people don't appreciate the importance of my craft. nnI provide comfort in times of woe. I create a final resting place for loved ones. nnWho else in this forsaken land can say the same?

You have done the impossible. Nerien's quest to bring me back from the grave has resulted in these atrocites you see around you. I must try and stop him now that you've freed me.  nnGo quickly, before you too are trapped here!  Thank you!
If you're lost, know that the paths in the Thrambles never change. You can always turn back.nnUnless the paths have changed, of course. That would probably explain why you're lost.

You must have eaten some of the moondrop mold. If it wasn't for that mold, you wouldn't be able to see me!nnDon't worry. I don't think the poison in the mold is deadly. nnUnless, of course, it is. Then you're gonna die.
Looking for the Grahtlord? I could lead you to him.nnWe might get lost, though... especially since I don't really know where he is.
The animals were docile, possibly even curious.nnAs soon as we killed the first one, they turned on us.

One moment we're hunting Thunderbugs, then I'm crushed under a stampede and carried away.nnI woke up in the dark. It smelled of rot and I think the floor was covered in bones...nnThen I'm knocked out, when I wake I'm on the path out of the Thrambles.

Thank you for searching for the Jaqspur. nnI made it out of the Thrambles safely, but I'll still be haunted by the memory of that attack.nnI'll be honest. It's gonna be a while before I aim another arrow at an animal.
Lob's men came and freed me from that prison. I can fight again. Moric is going to regret what he did... for about as long as it takes me to slice his head off.
It might seem strange to be a gravedigger's apprentice. But there's good coin in it, particularly these days.
What do we do now? We've lost everything...
I lost my children and my wares in that camp. What is left for me, now?
The Warguard slaughtered the scamps in town.nnThis one thinks there's still a few in the Bosmer burial site to the northeast.
Attacked in the night! Our fields burned, our livestock slaughtered! Now the trolls are here, feasting on the dead. I'm just a farmhand this is too much for me to deal with.
Have you seen them? The cutthroats downstairs? nnI really don't know how I'm going to get out of this place alive.

Excuse me! I wasn't expecting visitors today, not with all these unsavory characters loitering about the place.nnIf you're looking for the owner of the plantation, Lluthyne is in the house next to this one. nnWatch your step. After all, it's a farm.

You may want to turn around and leave Lushwallow, stranger. nnThe Peatwalker tribe set the spriggans against us because they believe we stole their totem.nnYou don't want to get caught in the middle of that.
Hey there. Come to buy some chickens? I'm afraid you're out of luck. Most of them were killed in the attack, and we can't afford to lose the ones we have left.

I'm a farmhand. At least... I used to work the farm. Now <<1>> always makes me work the kitchen. I don't mind the cooking, or the cleaning even. But the other farmhands - they don't respect my work! It's not my fault I have a nose for cooking.
Do you mind? I was about to take a nap. I haven't gotten much sleep since the attack happened.
How these small wood elves managed to capture a vicious senche fascinates me. nnNow they use them as gladiatorial combatants against each other?nnThat seems so wrong... and yet I cannot turn away.
Oh goodness! I didn't mean to push him over. But he was... and I just....nnPlease, don't kill me. It was an accident!
My injuries in battle left me useless as a conscript for their armies so I ended up here. They beat us and starve us. Most have lost all hope of rescue.
Those of us who aren't conscripted to fight will be sold as slaves or sacrificed.nnWe're losing hope.

For generations, animals have come to the Bone Fields to die.nnThey want to end their lives in a holy place.nnAfter Hallin's Stand fell, the Imperials started dumping bodies here. All those slain Redguards are defiling our sacred ground!
Greetings friend. It's nice to see a new face. The Mages Guild has its work cut out for it in Bangkorai and every member has to do their part.
What can I do for you?
Have you come to petition for healing, my friend?nnLet me take a look. I'll do what I can for you.
Wyress Reinette is the city's only healer now. I've come to get a curative before it's too late.
Something's gone terribly wrong in Evermore, hasn't it?nnAll the healers are dead except for Wyress Reinette.
Wyress Reinette is the city's only healer now. I need to get a curative before it's too late.
My father's dying, and I don't know what to do.nnI sent word to Wyress Reinette for help, but she hasn't returned.nnWhy won't she come here to save my father?

They told me that Wyress Reinette is Evermore's greatest healer.nnEven Queen Arzhela's consulted with her concerning the princess's illness.nnThat's why I... why I came to ask for Reinette's help, too.
Those barbarians they came back. Attacked us again. I knew it wasn't the trolls!
This situation is starting to vex me.
Careful there, friend. Rumor has it there's a nereid luring people to their doom.nnI guess it pays to invest in a magic charm or two!
You summon me to provide healing.nnI'm ready to help you.
I cannot leave here without my children. I won't!
Damned fiends got a hold of me before I could react. nnI won't let that happen again!
Stay back! I don't know if you're one of those fiends or a looter, but I know how to defend myself!
We're going to be in serious danger if the Nereid continues like this.nnWe need your help, stranger.
Lorelia sent you, didn't she? She always takes such good care of me.
What's going on here? Who are all you people? Who am I?
I was no match for him and his army.nnThank you for stopping him.

I welcome all who pass through the Viridian Woods... and I have seen many.nnThis young woman was brought here by her mother, Queen Arzhela of Evermore. I have promised to do everything in my power to save her from this sickness.
Whatever the sickness is in Evermore, it spread quickly through the town. Praise the Eight, I survived it!
I feel much better now, but still a bit weak. The sooner I can return to work, the better.
Our Queen's worried about King Eamond and Princess Elara, much to the detriment of the government. Her decisions are scattered and inconsistent.nnDo you have time to help me with a matter of state?
You've got to help me out of here! I'm Evermore's Minister of War. nnThis treatment is deplorable!
Please! Help me!nnThose Dunmer have left me for dead!
We don't care who enters the dungeon, just who comes out.nnJust beware the ghosts that roam below.

I can't believe someone would want gullygrubs so badly.nnImagine! Summoning creatures so he could claim the entire forest as his!nnWhat about the rest of us? We all enjoy them! That selfish nutwally is ruining it for everyone.
You heard me. You came.nnThank Azura.
Don't worry. I can keep up.
I've never been held prisoner by my own guards before.nnThis is an outrage!
This dungeon is older than Evermore's current castle.
I'll be fine here. You go on.

What happened to this place? nnTwo moons ago, I stood here without a creature in sight. Now they infest the entire forest, daring to attack any who come near!nnHow am I supposed to get my gullygrubs now?
<<1)>>, I offer you my sincerest thanks in getting me out of that dungeon.nnI'm going to have it closed down permanently once things are back to normal around here.
The Reachmen attacked in the the night.nnThey slaughtered anyone who resisted and captured the rest.
You are welcome to rest, friend. nnThe insane afflicted outside are beyond our help. nnBe careful. You must not fall prey to their madness.
<You've found the body of a slain Bosmer woman. She was clawed to death, most likely by the senches nearby.>nn<She's clutching a small book of forest rituals. One page is marked.>
I can't stop coughing. nnWhen will it end?

For a moment, that was rather frightening. Those blasted lurchers are everywhere! nnI figured they finally got smart enough to start looking in the trees for their food. nnBy "food," of course, I mean me.

What do you want?nnIf your family has suffered a recent loss, I offer my condolences.nnI'm doing what I can to keep the streets free of bodies.nnIf you have other concerns, please wait until this crisis is over before approaching me again.

All I want, and all I need, is to find out where my uncle's body was taken.nnHe's not the only one missing, but no one will tell me where they've taken the bodies.nnWhy won't the Minister of Health speak with me?

Do you see them? Did you?nnThey swarm like insects! They're just as mindless! The afflicted are everywhere!nnOnly the Three know when we can to return to our homes. We're heading to the temple until all of this calms down. Maybe then I can calm down!
I must not rest. nnIf my family shows up while I'm sleeping, how will they find me?
You must have been sent by the gods to save our family. nnNo words can express how grateful we are.
Too many. Clannfear. Could not fight them all.

Ah, greetings young <<1>>. I knew the foul reek of necromancy issuing from this place would eventually draw the attention of a worthy adventurer such as yourself.nnTell me, what do you know of Reach magic?
For every bird I pick off, another two fly out in its place.nn<<1>> needs to get back here, and soon. I can't keep this up forever.
Oh, mercy! I'm sick. Very sick. And when I die... I won't be dead. I'll come back as one of those things! What an awful way to go.

I know how to cure it!nnI've stayed up all night and concocted a potion that will cure Evermore's disease forever!nnYou must help me, before it's too late. My daughter won't let me use my cure. She won't let me out of her sight.
I must sincerely thank you for everything you've done.nnThey've poured so much emotion into me. They've infused me with such extremes of agony and ecstacy!nnI am exhausted.
<You see the spirit point to the southwest.>

<You stare at the coalescing energies of the spirit.>nn<Images of the forest flood your mind. Animals hidden in the trees and underbrush look in your direction>nn<As you commune with the spirit, the feeling of being watched is overwhelming.>
So many have fallen ill that I've taken it upon myself to supervise the tax collection from this ship.nnThey are being most uncooperative.
I don't know what exactly the Reachmen are doing, but I know this - where once there were peaceful folk, now there's walking dead.
I'm here to make sure these sailors pay their fair share of Evermore's taxes.
I hope you're not expecting any shipments from these people. They haven't paid the tariff yet and are refusing to do so.
We've never had to pay a tariff this high before, and we're not paying it now.
I don't understand why Evermore's taxes are suddenly so high.
I'm making sure Evermore's tax collector doesn't take more than his fair share of our profit.

House Redoran sent me here to ensure the Hortator's spirit finds rest, despite his violent death.nnI brought a talisman to honor his service, but the priestess does not share House Redoran's concern for the Hortator's well-being.

It all happened so suddenly! nnWe were getting ready to go hunting for our Gullygrubs and those... things rose up out of nowhere! They destroyed our camp!nnI'm scared for my brother. He ran into the forest, and he hasn't come back yet.
As soon as we can, we're getting out of this port.
So many have fallen ill that I've taken it upon myself to supervise the tax collection from this ship.nnThey're being most uncooperative.
We usually make a good profit in Evermore, seeing as they're so far inland.
Can't wait until we turn around and head back to Wayrest. Or Daggerfall.nnI've a lass in either city who'll be happy to see me.
I'm grateful for the chance to work aboard the Bjoulsae Queen! She's got a good reputation amongst the sailors.
Arkay help me, I don't feel well at all.

Think you have what it takes? Do you dare to challenge Bisni's runners?nnThe race is simple. Take three flags in order. The first to grab all three and get back here wins!nnI'll even give you a little something... extra.... to help. You up for it?
Running is fun! I could run all day!nnAnd I'm sure you could watch me run all day... from far, far behind me.
You would race against this one?nnThis one will tear you apart. Then you will eat this one's dust! nnWatch yourself!

Have you heard of Vonov Sarturus, the vile Daedric priest?nnWe defeated him in Haven, but after we secured the town, we couldn't find his body.nnRahira fears that even death could not end his treachery.
May I help you with something?
You are <<1>>, are you not?nnMy troops have spoken of you. Your reputation precedes you.nnCan you help our dying Bosmer king?
I'm not supposed to talk to you. I'm supposed to stand up straight and look menacing.
Don't disturb Her Royal Highness.nnShe's here to receive healing, not to mingle with the public.
Nothing is won in war, only lost.
Honored one, you grace me with your presence. nnWithout you, I fear our cries for help would have never been answered.
Blessings of the Eight upon you.
May the Tribunal bless and keep you in these dark times, friend. nnI've done my best to keep my family together. That will become much harder as the days pass.
Kynareth's good fortune upon you, friend.
What's happened to our friends, papa? I'm frightened!
What's happening in there? Father won't let us go back for our belongings.
I feel dizzy, father. It's too stuffy in here. nnMy throat's so dry....
I pray these people get better soon. nnI just want to go home.
Her Majesty, like the city of Evermore, is suffering. As Her Majesty's sister, I know how difficult things are for her at the moment.
This land dreugh is dead. The corpse is still fresh with no signs of decomposition.
I think I'm starting to see things. nnAre you real?
Bangkorai Garrison has fallen. nnThe others want to retreat. I say we fight!
I never thought I'd miss the days when our biggest problem was skooma smugglers. nnThis disease seems far worse.
Don't interrupt me. I must speak with the minister.
Wait... you're no Reachman. Maybe you can help me. Maybe you can help... all of us.
I certainly hope you're here to offer help instead of just asking for it.nnBetween the random lava flows and the Ashlander raids, rebuilding Senie has turned into an epic undertaking.

Aha! It's the meddling <<1>>!nnI knew it was only a matter of time before you discovered my true motives. The captain is too caught up in his own pride to notice.nnHow unfortunate. Because of your curiosity, you must die.
Heads will roll once I'm released!
We've been locked up unjustly! Release us, immediately!
They arrested us for no apparent reason.
I hope the Minister is all right. They locked her up elsewhere in this horrible place.
You should leave while you still can.nnDon't risk yourself on my behalf!
You shouldn't be here, child.nnGo back to the towns of House Dunmer. The Ashlands hold nothing for you.
Please be quick. I wish to continue my studies.
You are not Taros!nnWhy have you awakened me?
I loved Erena, but I was too afraid to let her know my true feelings. nnNow she's gone, and it's too late for us to be together.

The Karthdar Pilgrimage isn't just a place. It's a journeynnThose who partake are called wardens. We're trained to hold back Daedric corruption.nnSome stay to protect Gil-Var-Delle. Others become experts at holding off Daedric incursions.
The Imperials are losing their stranglehold.nnDespite that, they're ruthless. They're proving themselves quite capable of treachery. nnWe must be mindful. We must be cautious.
If you are a wayward apprentice seeking power from your master's collection, you should know that it's far too late for you. nnYou'll get flayed alive.nnThat being said, what do you want?
Please excuse me, child. nnWe're in the middle of our devotions.
I remember what happened. I remember when we died.
I would lament our fate, but I cannot be sad when Taros is near. nnEven after her death, her presence still warms my spirit.nnThank you for reuniting us, friend.
Kynareth save us! This temple is filled with ghosts!nnMust ... catch my breath.
Thank the Eight! I'm so glad you handled that mess.nnAll the same, I think I'll be worshipping safely in Evermore from now on.
I don't feel so good. My mother's medicine won't help me. Nothing can help me now.
I pray to Mara night and day for our princess, but she fares no better. I feel so helpless!
I'll stay here until the Ashlanders share their cure with us. nnWhat other choice do I have?
Thinking clearly is getting harder. nnI can hear my family crying in the night. Sometimes I think I hear them behind me, but when I turn around... I am alone.nnI don't think I have much time left.
You know, there are enough of us out here. We outnumber their guards.nnWe could break in and take their cure. Some of us would survive.

Why won't the Ashlanders give us their cure? I'm not going to die, but I'm not going to beg.nnIf I feel my mind going, I'll make sure it happens when I'm near some of these Kagesh. nnThere's no one left who would mourn over my corpse anyway.

Every pilgrim attempts to confront the corruption in Gil-Var-Delle. Few make it more than twenty steps up the hill before turning back.nnJust breathing feels like you're being choked, like your insides are being wrung out.nnI made it sixteen steps.
These villagers are under quarantine. Keep walking.

Soldiers brought many dead from a battle to the south. nnWe consecrated a few of their bodies, but the dead men rose up and walked again within a day of their arrival. nnNever have I seen a necromantic plaguge spread so quickly.
Keel-J'Rei hungers, but House Redoran's keeps this one trapped! nnThis one cannot hunt!
The sun crawls across the sky so slowly!nnKeeras-J'Rei can do nothing except dwell on this one's hunger.
I don't feel very well. It's the sickness. The plague's come to Evermore.nnPlease, help me!
If you try to enter, we will slay you where you stand.nnDon't even think about it.
If you try to enter, we will have to slay you where you stand.nnDon't test us.
I still have a few wares from Ebonheart, if you're interested. nnI've got some beautiful urns and exotic incense for your loved ones.nn I'm sure they'd appreciate it!
This land is my responsibility now. The things you've done here - I will not forget them. Thank you.
I'm off duty. What do you need?
My child is gone, dead to the sickness.nnThey let him die!
The world of the dead is reaching into our world more and more often these days. The undead that have overrun my graveyard are only the start of the problem.
You're a stranger to this place. I guess we have that much in common.nnI've lived under the watchful eyes of the Tribunal for years. nnThe ways of the Ashlanders are unknown to me.
This cabin belongs to <<1>>. nnHe's lived here as long as anyone can remember. Since I was a boy, I've done what I can to help the old man. nnI'm afraid this time, the task may be too great for me.

I have no idea how you made it this far, but if you need shelter, you're welcome here.nnI'm afraid I can't offer you much more than that, though. nnAfter all, I have to reserve our supplies for the few troops I have left.
I must not fail my comrades. I cannot leave them to rot here, no matter what the captain says!
Praise the Three! Someone came! Can you help me?nCliff racers and madmen have overrun the fort, but my brother was intent on delivering those supplies to the captain. nnI fear for his life!
What madness has taken hold of the creatures here? nnIs this the same affliction spreading through Davon's Watch?

We lost a battle with the Imperials at Bangkorai Garrison, south of here.nnThe bodies from that battle were brought here, but they rose from the dead before they could be consecrated!nnI think I have a way to stop them, but I need your help.
I'll carry out King Eamond's last command, no matter who stands against me.
Necromancy is blasphemy against the Divines. nnI will not allow it, not even in King Eamond's name.
These villagers are under quarantine. nnI'd stay back if I were you.
Did you see the bodies outside? Did you see the injured? nnWith no one to defend us, how long will it be before we're overrun? nnI can't sit here and wait for that.

The captain told me to abandon the barn, but I'm not leaving anytime soon. nnIf our men need horses, they'll have a place to stable them. nnUntil then, I'm not going to let those dirty cliff racers get their filth all over it.
The animals were docile, even curious, but when we drew blood, killing the first, they turned.
Who hangs laundry this high? How am I supposed to get it now? I bet it was one of those High Elves!
My son Eamond will not be raised as undead.
I respect the spirit of Queen Therese, but she no longer rules Evermore.nnI'm bound by honor to respect the final commands of my king.
Given the insistence of these knights, I saw no choice but to summon Queen Therese. nnI can see now I was right to do so.
You have no place here, outsider.
You are unclean. Go, or I will summon our warriors.
The Orlishkaarn are savages! nnI came here to reason with them, and what do they do? nnThey tie me up and leave me in this wretched hovel! I know they're trying to infect me.
It's good to see you've made it out of there in one piece.
I used to hate the days when taking inventory took a day and a night. nnWhat I wouldn't give to have them back now!nnWith our current supplies, I can count them in a glance.
Lost count again. nnI don't even know why I bother with precise measurements anymore, not in a patchwork house like this.
I despise not having the tools and materials to produce quality work.
You haven't got a spare leg on you by any chance? No?nnNo. Of course not. No one ever does.
I've prayed to Stendarr day and night, that he might see fit to bring my husband home to me.
What do you want? Did Rerynia send you to check up on me? nnI rough up a prisoner, and they act like I started a war. nnIt's nothing. He'll live.
I hope you're not here to harass me as well.
I will not welcome you at my fire, outsider.
Evermore can't force us to work after accusing us of spreading the plague.
You must leave our camp. Begone!
They attacked us without any warning, and now they sit there glaring at us. Well, I can glare at them, too!
I should've killed them all when I had a chance.
Have you come to murder us, or can you see past the prejudice that blinds so many others?
I didn't know that being a werewolf would bring such trouble to my life. Then again, I wouldn't live any other way.
I've got a moment to speak, but only if you make it brief.nnI have to continue my rounds before the captain catches me off-guard.

This grotto was once a great cave, and this shrine to Hircine is its hidden jewel. nnThe Daedric Princes are fickle masters. Legends are told of their fitful whims.nnSome legends yearn to be relived. Would you care to try one on for size?
What can I do for you?nnI'm afraid we're a little short-handed.nn I've started doing some of the less savory chores around here.
I don't remember asking you to report to me.nnAre you even in a regiment at the fort?nnI suggest you leave, outsider, before you find yourself in trouble.

You may be wondering why I don't order my men to take up arms. Why not drive these Ashlanders from our doorstep?nnIt's simple. I want to know what caused the Orlishkaarn to attack first.nnOthers are less eager to assess the situation, I fear.
My wares are not for such as you.
Evermore can't force us to work after accusing us of spreading the plague.
Evermore can't force us to work after accusing us of spreading the plague.
Evermore can't force us to work after accusing us of spreading the plague.
Evermore can't force us to work after accusing us of spreading the plague.
I don't understand why they don't just kill us. Isn't that why they're holding us captive?
Why don't they just get this over with?
I feel sick.nnThey did this to me. The werewolves brought the plague to Evermore.
The soldiers had no reason to attack Kerbol's Mill.nnThe werewolves here are peaceful!
You deign to speak to me, though I am a prisoner of your allies.nnI wonder if those you serve would be interested in a trade?nnTell them. I will bargain with them.

Those Imperials don't care who they cut through to get what they want.nnKill a dozen people here. Take a half-dozen hostages there. nnThey'll do anything their crazy leader tells them to do. nnAll we can do is try to get our people out to safety.
Don't get too close to the werewolves. They're spreading disease throughout the region.
I'd turn back, friend. The Imperials are holding Bangkorai Garrison now.nnYou can go in, but without allies, you might not make it very far.
You're the one!nnYou're the one who killed the centurion on the northern wall, aren't you?nnGood job!
Great job! The Imperials are already falling back to the courtyard.
They think I'm hiding a cure for the plague, but I'm not. I'm innocent!
This entire area has been quarantined.nnThe mill workers are werewolves. They're holding their cure for the plague hostage.
We've done nothing wrong. They attacked us without warning!
I used to trust these folks, but I heard they caused Evermore's sickness.nnCould it be true?

All who embrace Boethiah are welcome here. Those who have yet to embrace his truth may learn it.nnAll who worship of the pretender Tribunal will die. We will spill their blood in honor of the Prince of Plots.nnYou must choose. Which are you?
Thank you! I'm getting out of here!
Thank you! I'm getting out of here!
With all of these Ashlanders here, I don't see how anyone can expect to get Senie rebuilt.
Under your leadership, we'll retake Bangkorai's garrison.
Under your leadership, we'll retake Bangkorai's garrison.
<<1>> sends another in his stead. How disappointing.nnThe Viridian Sentinel's power wanes, yet he asks a boon? It is only due to his past service that the woods will respond.
I don't understand why they don't just kill us. Isn't that why they're holding us captive?
I don't understand why they don't just kill us. Isn't that why they're holding us captive?
The more I think about it, the happier I am that I chose this life for myself.
What was once a curiousity has grown into a coral monstrosity.nnWe were lax to allow it to spread so far.nnNow I wonder if we're too late to stop its spread.

This campaign is against a different foe than my men are used to fighting.nnIt's one that creeps and grows under our feet. It somehow conscripts other creatures to protect it.nnI don't know how coral growth does this. I just know we need to stop it.

You're one of the few friendly souls I've found here. nnPlease help. I have a task I can't accomplish alone.nnHopefully, saving the mercenaries will get them to reconsider their crusade or at least listen to us.
I don't understand why they don't just kill us. Isn't that why they're holding us captive?
Why don't they get this over with?
I heard that werewolves in Glenumbra overran Camlorn. Could the same thing happen here?
Some think the people of Kerbol's Mill made the plague. That's why they're immune. nnI guess we all know better now.
We've done it! We've won the day!
I would lament our fate, but I cannot be sad when Taros is near. Even in death her presence still warms my spirit.nnThank you for reuniting us, friend.
What business do you have here?
Every wretch with hands strong enough to carry a sword has beating down our doors these days to risk their miserable lives in exchange for a few coins.

The Mages Guild is accepting donations of any magical curiosities that you may have, as well as the results of any magical research. nnThese are desperate times, however, so we must be discerning about who and what we accept.
Hail, stranger. If I had to guess, you want to ally yourself with the Mages Guild.nnWe're not giving bread to the poor here. If you want to join us, you'll have to prove you've got the will to serve.

We lost a battle with the Imperials at Bangkorai Garrison to the south. nnThe bodies from that battle were brought here, but they rose from the dead before they could be consecrated!nnI think I have a way to stop them, but I need your help.
The world of the dead is reaching into our world more and more often these days. The undead that have overrun my graveyard are only the start of the problem.
Oh, look. Another seeking membership. You earned any scars yet?
The Argonians here see this overgrown fungus sprout as a creature to be communed with, not a weed to be rooted out.nnYou'd think the foul monsters it attracts would convince them otherwise.
Good to see you! How can I help?
Good to see you! How can I help?
They may not be from Evermore, but they still deserve a burial. It's only right.nnAs for our dead, they're going to Pelin Temple to be consecrated and buried with their ancestors.
This work may not be pretty, but no one deserves to rise as a monster.nnWouldn't be good to make us kill them twice, now would it?
There's many dead to consecrate and little time to do it. Please leave me to my work.
Lots of Imperials to put in the ground, thanks to you <<1>>.
If you would do ill to Serjo Ulden, you must face me first.
Have you come to praise Boethiah?
Have you come to praise Boethiah?
How could such a thing come to pass?
How could such a thing come to pass?
How could this come to pass?
How could this come to pass?
Take care, my friend.nnThe grotto below is full of danger. The Huntsmen of Hircine patrol it endlessly. nnThey're as merciful as a duneripper.

To think I'd be standing here again, ready to face the man who took my life!nnHe's caused so many troubles. He's taken so many lives. We must stop him once and for all.nnVonov must not channel the power of <<1>>.
Have you finished planting lifetimber seeds?
I apologize for our late arrival. You seem to have matters well in hand.nnThanks to you, we're gradually regaining control of Gil-Var-Delle.
The prince will lead us to victory again!
Daedra aren't much of a challenge for this one.
When we finally defeat Vonov, Grahtwood will be free.
Vonov is cowering. He knows his death is near!
These lands are the dominion of Hircine, the Huntsman of Princes. May his spear never dull! nnNone may trespass here without first making an offering to him. nnWhat will your sacrifice be?
Who are you? Tell me, stranger!nnHas the Dominion sent reinforcements?
I have shamed my people.nnI won't increase my shame by speaking with you, <<1>>.

There you are! I sure hope you've found something.nnThey're on to us. We nearly got our heads lopped off back there.nnWe need to finish our business here. Is that an Orc prisoner? Have those Orcs finally gone nutwally?
Are you mad, <<1>>?nnYou've set foot into the home of the Wood Orcs. Now you wander around like a lost child! nnKeep your head down if you want to keep it. This just went from bad to worse.
Those brutes almost got us, but I have to admit... that was rather exciting!
Blessings from the sea grace these shores.nnWe're here to bask in their glow, as they grow on these inhospitable lands.nnThe coral is quite like us in its resiliency. Wouldn't you agree?
You won't find better prices for my essential tinctures! Not anywhere!nnWhy take your chances with a virulent plague when you can prevent it right now?nnLive without fear, friend.
This disease is driving the good people of Ebonheart away... and allowing the dregs of <<1>> to filter in.
Another new face in Ebonheart? nnI should welcome you! nnI just wish you could have arrived under better circumstances.
Who are you?nnYou don't look like one of Irano's men.
<The Khajiit looks at the ground and remains silent.>
Yes? Please do not disturb the king. nnHis health wanes, and he needs rest.
<You smell herbal ointments and incense. The king is awake but unresponsive, his eyes staring into the distance.>

What a cruel mockery this life is!nnAfter days of hunting, Hircine's servants granted me safe passage through this grotto.nnThen with one careless step, I fell prey to the jaws of a waiting crocodile. What an embarassing demise.
We've had any number of supply problems, and now this.nnI swear that Imperial saboteurs are lurking nearby, destroying what little we have left.nnCan you help me find these spies?
My sons! Have you seen them?nnTheir names are Raiyeem and Raiyad. I haven't seen them since before the attack.nnThey went to Evermore to visit their grandmother.
Blessings from the sea grace these shores.nnWe're here to bask in their glow, as they grow on these inhospitable lands.nnThe coral is quite like us in its resiliency. Wouldn't you agree?

Fighting for freedom doesn't excuse being stupid. nnBack when we were slaves, those fools burned down our bunkhouses.nnDidn't they think we might need them later? It gets cold at night. Did they think the Dres would invite us inside?
That necklace...! The true son must have sent you here.
Friend, you've returned! nnI've told everyone of your brave deeds.nnYou're welcome to site by our fire or sun yourself on our shores.
You live! nnPrince Aeradran led us through the fires of the Rotting Tree. nnHe carried you out personally.
Skooma! Why are you so cruel to me?nnThis isn't your usual bliss! I may be an addict, but I know my limits.nnWait, is someone really there? I thought you were a figment of my mind. Curse this fever!

Cursed orcs and these Imperials are everywhere! No one spotted me on my way back here... I hope.n   nDamn it all! We're going to get ourselves killed creeping around here. <<1>>, I need your help again.nnTrust me, I don't like it either.
Another stranger to Ebonheart? Forgive me if I seem... unenthused. nnMost newcomers are only concerned with how they can profit from our plight.
Curse this disease!nnBoethiah protects the Kagesh! Why doesn't the Tribunal protect us?

It's unfortunate. <<1>> has fallen into disarray.nnThere was a time the Mages Guild could easily acquire assistance for research.nnNow every one is preoccupied with the Great War, rebuilding <<2>>, and this bothersome plague.
Surin has been obsessed lately.nnHe's always watching our neighbor's house. He makes me nervous.nnI'd hate to think what conclusions he's made about my lifestyle.
I only recently arrived here in Omaynia. Originally, I came to turn myself in.nnYou can imagine my surprise when I stumbled upon this!
Elvasia? Is that you?nnNo, you aren't my daughter.

We've never had this many people in the city. We need to send out more hunters to get food. nnIt's easy to forget about gathering food, but who's gonna get blamed when we all go hungry? Certainly not the Bosmer taking our bows to go fight.
Don't... don't look at me. nnDon't stand so close.
This one thinks you smell bad. nnOf course, this one is no rose himself, eh?
Slavery is better than disembowelment... or so they say.nnOf course, those who say that couldn't know what it's like to be disemboweled. nnMerely making an observation....
I'm a long way from Cyrodiil.
There has to be an end to this. There has to be.
You won't find better prices for these essential tinctures. nnWhy take your chances with this disease when you can prevent it right now?
Tall Papa left us with a few strong sword arms. We aren't heavily guarded, but we'll make do.nnThe Imperials won't take any more of us. We'll see to that.
I understand why Rushul fell asleep.nnMen are weak. It's in their nature.nnI will do better.
Are you lost? We are the leaders of this . rabble. And we are in conference.nnUnless you have urgent business with one of us, I suggest you find someplace else to be.

Not only was I captured again, but they also captured my son.nnNow they've poisoned us both as punishment. Without the antidote, we'll both die.nnI don't care about myself any more. Find the antidote and save my son!
Who's that, then? Come to laugh at the cripple, eh?nnHe was thrown away when too hurt to work! He was forgotten in the glorious slave revort!nnGo ahead, then. Drop your breeches and let fly.
If you've come to buy a cure from these apothecaries, save your coin. nnThey're charlatans!nnThey'll promise anything to get your money!
Pardon. Have you seen a young lady by the name of Zunaida?nnI fear I've done her an ill turn.
You're <<1>>, right? I've heard of your deeds.nnIs this important? I don't have time to gossip.
They've taken the Tribune captive. You have to save her!
Oh, hello! Sorry! Sorry I'm in the way here. Don't mind me, I'm just bleeding to death.nnI think I'll be speaking with Tu'whacca soon. Do you think he'll be tall?
They sacrifice us, beat us, and starve us.nnWhat hope do we have left?
Speak, <<1>>.nnTell me how you came into possession of my son's amulet.
Gone! My Farvyn is gone!nnWhat life will I have without her?
I know not who you are, <<1>>, but you carry the amulet of the true son of the Great Father.nnWe will let you pass. Make a wrong move, and we will smash you.
Have you have spoken to my Great Father, <<1>>?
Their cries echo through the cave. The sound comes from everywhere and nowhere.nnIt sounds like the cries of women we once knew, but they're no longer here.nnTheir wailing terrifies the refugees.
He was going to do bad things ... very bad things.
Where are my sisters?nnWhat has that mage done with them?
I'm so afraid!nnThat mage said such terrible things!
I'm sick. Caught a fever.nnStay away from me, unless you want it too!
The Reachmen may break my body, but they'll never break my spirit.
Your kind have no rights on our soil.nnBegone, before my men cut you down where you stand.
Zhavas does not care for cities in the trees.nnMetal is heavy. So are tools. Mere wood is poor support for such weighty things.
<This body is laid out in a sleeping pose.>nn<The boy looks young and strong, though death has robbed his face of its expression.>
If we're lucky, we'll be sold as slaves. nnIf we're unlucky, they'll sacrifice us on an altar.nnWe have no reason to live.
I worry about my mother, but at least I'm alive.nnThey're sacrificing the troublemakers. Then they plan to sell the rest of us as slaves.
Keep your voice down, or you'll give away our position.
This house is under investigation. Nothing to see here.
Speak, <<1>>.nnTell me how you came into possession of my son's amulet.
Why if it isn't <<1>>!nnI'll never forget that you came back for me.
You are strange, <<1>>.nnWhy risk your life for something that does not concern you?nnThese Imperials are blood enemies of the Orcs now. Why do you fight for us?

Skooma! Why are you so cruel to me?nnThis isn't your usual blissful oblivon! I may be an addict, but I know my limits.nnWait, is someone really there? I thought you were a figment of my mind. Curse this fever!
Speak, <<1>>.nnTell me how you came into possession of my son's amulet.

Our Great Father hasn't left his true son's body since it washed ashore.nnHe must have time to grieve. Then he must decide when to tell the others.nnMany will wish to know so that they may attempt to take control of our tribe.

That could have been a lot worse, I suppose.nnI can still hear the ringing of the Imperial and Orc blades from over here. nnIt's a shame we can't stir up more trouble, but I think we've done more than enough here.
I never thought I'd feel bad for an Orc, especially with them trying to eat us.nnHowever, this... this is just sad.

That cowering mage! I know he's far from his home in Alinor, but that doesn't mean he can get away with his crimes. nnHis monstrous growth potions are dangerous and unstable.nnHe thinks our laws are lax. He thinks he won't be caught. He's wrong!
Welcome to Heimlyn Keep, the safest location for your trading needs in Stonefalls! nnCan I interest you in some profitable caravan enterprises?
<You see the spirit point to the top of the stairs.>

The stench of fear pollutes the waters around our camp. It emanates from the coral-child.nnThe Dunmer mercenaries will not listen to reason. The coral calls for aid, and the Dreugh respond.nnThe mercenaries must withdraw if they want an end to this!
You cannot prove anything! I will not be assaulted by these brutes!
Greetings, comrade-in-arms!nnYes, I've seen your type. You've seenhorrors on the battlefield. A hero to many, a villain to few!nnPerhaps you could aid a kindred spirit....
Hello, sweetness. nnI'm not working right now, but I may have something for you... if I can steal a moment of your time.
Have you seen my Raijo?nnHe's a handsome Khajiit, very well-spoken and polite.nnI haven't seen him in a while, and I'm beginning to worry. This market is not safe.
The Imperials ruin everything.nnShavari cannot find peace, no matter where this one goes.

I escaped from captivity! I killed a slave boss and ran for it.nnWhen Hallin's Stand fell, the Imperials handed their captives over to the Reachmen.nnThe Reachmen sold them as slaves ... or worse. We've got to free them before it's too late!
They caught us as we were leaving the Cave of Many Tears.nnNow they'll use us as slaves ... or sacrifices.
We must do everything in our power to stop this slaughter.nnNeither the coral nor the Dunmer know what they are truly fighting.
Oh, hello. Don't mind me. I'm just quietly bleeding to death.nnHa. Talking to your hallucinations now, 'Aida? You'll be speaking with Tu'whacca soon enough ....
This one asks that the stranger be silent.nnI, Raijo, must hide from my mistress, lest she command me to return with her.
That Renoit has nerve. His men accused me of creating this plague.nnHe took me prisoner, and his guards attacked my sister.nnNow he wants our cure?
Thank you for protecting us when Virgil lost control.nnMy brother is still injured, but I think I can patch him up.nnWe're alive because of you, <<1>>.
I wasn't expecting a warm welcome, but at least they haven't turned into wolves and ripped out my throat.
The soldiers got out of hand.nnI'm just glad no one was killed.
I'm afraid I'm not interested in talking to strangers.
If you're looking for work, look elsewhere. Sugar's only got room for one stevedore, and I'm his man.
Those of us not conscripted to fight will either be sacrificed or sold as slaves. What hope is left?
If we're lucky, we'll be sold as slaves. Otherwise, they'll sacrifice us at the altar. We have nothing left to live for.
The Reachmen are barely better than animals.nnWithout your help, I would have died.
I owe you and <<1>> my life.nnTo be honest, I didn't expect you to come back here and help us escape.
The Reachmen are cruel masters. I wouldn't have survived for long.nnMany thanks, <<1>>.
Be careful. This entire area is quarantined.nnThe mill workers are werewolves, and they're holding a cure for the plague hostage.
These people saved Virgil from plague.nnI never imagined my brother and I would bring them so much grief. nnThey deserve so much better.
Those of us not conscripted to fight will either be sacrificed or sold as slaves. What hope is left?
If we're lucky, we'll be sold as slaves. Otherwise, they'll sacrifice us at the altar. We have nothing left to live for.
Those of us not conscripted to fight will either be sacrificed or sold as slaves. What hope is left?
If we're lucky, we'll be sold as slaves. Otherwise, they'll sacrifice us at the altar. We have nothing left to live for.

Do you recognize me, <<1>>? You saved my life back at the Nilata Ruins. nnMy children, my children's children ... all of them will know your name.nnThey'll tell the tale of how you fought so I could live.

I came down here to see what these numbbrained orcs were up to and they had the nerve to outnumber me! I'm all right; I'm strong as boughs. I just wish I could scout deeper in and see what the orcs are up to...
You can find good and evil in both man and beast. The same is true of the Daedric Princes.nnMany claim Hircine is a monster, but he's always treated us fairly.
I've never seen anything like this.nnWe sent a whole regiment into the heart. Then you two walked out unscathed. nnWhat of the swarming Dreugh? Why have they ceased their attack?
Rumors are the Reachmen sacked Dunkarn Haven.nnI hope my wife survived. I'm afraid to find out the truth, but I can't stand not knowing.
It was horrible! The Reachmen killed everyone!
I don't require anything at the moment, slave. nnRun along to the stables.

The slaves may be running amok now, but their day in the sun will be brief.nnWhen more of our troops arrive, we'll round them up and lock them in their cages.nnIn the meantime, I hope they won't become too malnourished.

House Dres has many demands on its attentions.nnSerjo Belaal's need for rest leaves them in my hands.nnI'm hardly her equal in intelligence and wisdom.nnI trust you appreciate the value of my time. Do not squander it.
And you are?nnAnd you bothering me because?
Life has been terribly dreary since our slaves ran away.nnI hope they come to their senses before our messengers reach Kragenmoor.nnIf they don't, I can't be held accountable for the consequences.
I don't have time for questions.
We're watching you, stranger. nnSugar Cove protects its own.
You won't find better prices for these essential tinctures. nnWhy take your chances with this disease when you can prevent it right now?
You won't find better prices for these essential tinctures.nnWhy take your chances with this disease when you can prevent it right now?
Where's my son? Why can I not see him? nnI'm his mother! You can't keep me from him!
You must know. You found out? nnFalonu will not answer me. He's hiding him from me!nnPlease, I beg you. Help me find my son.
Filthy, degenerate thieves and miscreants! The wharf is full of them.nnWatch your pockets, <<1>>. nnNo one can be trusted around here.
Fancy a scamp's foot? A harpy tooth? Lizard glands?nnWhether you want to ease your digestion, improve your love life, or remove unsightly warts, Heba's Emporium has the cure for you!
You made it. Good.nnI've found something.
Watch your step.nnThe patients here have trouble controlling themselves.
I knew you'd come back in one piece.
This is not a place you should be, <<1>>.
When the Ebonheart Pact was founded, the Dunmer agreed to end trade in Nord and Argonian slaves. nnNow the wind carries news. The Dres of Omaynia are still buying and selling my people.
The Imperials took Hallin's Stand. The people they didn't kill are now slaves.nnIt's safer here.
I came here to investigate rumors that the Imperials have been training gargoyles.nnI also heard you already handled the situation!nnWe should talk.
The Tribunes fight for the peoples of the sand.nnWe won't stand for Imperial aggression.
My strength... falters! How can this be?
You! You're not one of the guards.nnAre you a patient here? Perhaps we can help each other!
Must tell ... the commander ....nnMust tell her. Please, help me!

Several families in Mournhold have asked for updates on the condition of their kin entrusted to Sera Thovasi.nnI came to search the headstones for their names, but I am loathe to walk around this living graveyard anymore.
Keep your voice down. Imperials are everywhere.
Keep  your voice down. Imperials are everywhere.
Ah, it's you. I was about to give up hope. What have you found?
This is not a place you should be, <<1>>.

The Dres are only good for one thing: feeding a tree. nnThose Redorans are nice enough, but they're a little too eager to talk about their "gods."nnYou know, their gods are not a tenth as old as our Hist, and not half as wise.
Watch your pockets. The slaves outside are hungry.nnPoor n'wah. I feel bad for them, but with this affliction, we can barely feed ourselves.
These are difficult times, but the Dres have brought worse ills upon themselves through poor judgment.
Father is much vexed by the slave problem. I wish it would all just go away.
Trash surrounds our manor. nnI wish House Father Aryon would allow us to go out there and clean things up.
The slaves may be our inferiors, but the way the Dres treat them just isn't right.
The slaves don't seem to mean us any harm, but they still make me nervous.

Now that the Dres slaves have freed themselves, I wish they would all just go away. nnEvery time I walk by, I feel their eyes on me. nnWithout someone to keep them in line, who knows what they might do?
You've got to get us out of here!
You've got to get us out of here!
You've got to get us out of here!
You've got to get us out of here!
You've got to get us out of here!
You've got to get us out of here!
Are you here looking for wood?nnThere's not a lot left. The damned Dres took all the good pieces up to their manor!
You've got to get us out of here!
You've got to get us out of here!
You've got to get us out of here!
Come to finish me off, you accursed abomination? nnOh, it's you! Thank the Three! I mistook you for a wraith.
Mind your fingers in our manor. nnYou may have our pity, but nothing more.
They took my wife.nnThey took her, and they fed her to the lions.
I don't have many items yet, but soon, I expect to be back in business.
Fortunately those Imperial soldiers didn't find my cache of wineskins, or I wouldn't have anything to sell to you.
My master, <<1>>, asked me to pray over these fallen Redguards until we can sanctify their remains.
Be careful, adventurer. The wraiths within are ruthless.nnThe ritual to raise them must be powerful.nnThey're not just strong. They're Akaviri!
I've given too much of my merchandise away to the refugees.nnAny purchase you can afford is a welcome one!
Let me know if anything interests you.
Let me know if anything interests you.
The streets of <<1>> run red with the blood of Imperial dogs.nnThe town is ours again!
<You've found a dead body. Scamp claws have mangled and mutilated its flesh and bones.>
May the Eight watch over us.
What can I do for you?

I heard a rumor from the Mages Guild about a Daedric portaling open nearby.nnBefore I left to explore it, the merchants warned me of a flaming creature called the Magmer.nnI didn't see the truth until it burned me. Then I fled here to hide.
What can I do for you?

All of my workers ran off when those Magmer appeared.nnWith the workers gone, no one's keeping the shalk from breeding like Khajiit. nnThe prices of those yellow gems are higher than ever, but I have no one to gather them!
What can I do for you?
Did you find any of those unusual fire salts?
It's warmer here than anywhere else in Stonefalls. nnIs it the volcano, or is it perhaps the coral?nnI suspect the coral parts the very clouds so it can enjoy more sunshine!
The coral-child is primitive, but perhaps it will grow in time.nnWe've never seen anything like this, not since our time in the marsh-lands.nnThat was back when I still had my egg-tooth.
Have you ever eaten a fish plucked fresh from the sea?nnIt's the only way to truly appreciate the ocean's blessing.
Once I was a slave, working day and night on the docks of Ebonheart.nnI always wanted to see the coral. When I was free, I paid my debts and came here.nnI never want to leave.
Once those magmer appeared, I stayed by her side, but she refused to leave! I fled for my life in the night.nnI can't live with myself knowing that I left her there!

I'm sorry I rushed ahead, <<1>>. I just can't take it anymore!nnEver since I've been back, I've been haunted by the memories and what Vonov did to me... and my father.nnI've been given a second chance! Together, we can put an end to him!

Pardon me if I seem preoccupied. I haven't slept in days, and I've barely eaten. nnMy sons went with the others to look at the statues a few days ago. nnMy daughter went yesterday to find them. Now I fear I've lost them all to the curse.
Please, I have no quarrel with you. nnI just want to help my brothers. I mean you no harm!
Why don't you mind your own business? nnYou must be siding with Delvas! nnStay out of my way if you know what's good for you.
What do you want? nnCan't you see I'm busy?
Greetings, <<1>>. What brings you to Volenfell?

What do you want?nnIf your family has suffered a recent loss, I offer my condolences.nnI'm doing what I can to keep the streets free of bodies.nnIf you have other concerns, please wait until this crisis is over before approaching me again.

The Karthdar Pilgrimage isn't just a place. It's a journey.nnThose who partake are wardens. We're trained to hold back Daedric corruption.nnSome, like me, stay to protect Gil-Var-Delle. Others become experts at holding off Daedric incursions.
Our troubles never end. One threat immediately replaces the next. nnGrahtwood was never tranquil, but someday, I hope I'll only be worrying about insects.
You're brave to approach me, <<1>>. nnI'm not myself. By the Three, what have I done?nnMy own father, dead by my hand, and despoiled by those wretched scamps.
Have you seen my sister and her three children?nnShe's about my age. She has two sons and a daughter. nnThey should have been here days ago.
Quiet, traveler. You'll bring the Imperials down on our heads.
Walk softly. Don't let the Imperials hear you.
If you've come for trouble, you'll get more than you bargained for.
Hail to you, <<1>>!nnThe fires worked. The plan was a success. We caught the Imperials completely off-guard!
A word of caution, stranger. nnBeware the Brothers of Strife, lest their rage overtake you. nnOnce their hostility seizes you, death will be your only relief.

This is bad. Something's happened, and I can't handle it alone. nnWhile I was digging, I found an ancient sword encased in the rock.nnI'm certain the Imperials are looking for it. I hid it, but it won't be long before its discovered!

I'm so relieved to be out of that place, but I fear I'm not free of it yet.nnWhile I was digging, I found an ancient sword encased in the rock.nnI'm certain the Imperials are looking for it. I hid it, but I fear they'll discover it soon!
I don't like the look of those Orcs over there, not one bit. nnThis seems like a dangerous place to be detained. nnAt this rate, travelling to Deshaan will take forever.
I'm afraid you have me at a disadvantage, sera.
Take a look at what's on offer today. Some delightful items have just arrived!
I hope Julianos isn't holding your purse strings, friend. We have so many shinies to look at!
We built this bank to last. We built it like a fortress.
I can offer you some of the finest swords you've ever seen.
Some days, it seems there are more boats coming and going than drops of water in the sea.
Only the best for the brave men and women of the Daggerfall Covenant.
I'm here to see S'rashi. My business is my own.
Will the <<1>> be finding Elder Brump?
The forge keeps me  busy, but I've always got time for aspiring blacksmiths.nnNeed anything?
War's coming, friend. That's bad news for soldiers, but it's plenty of business for crafters like us who make weapons and armor.
Interested in buying? I can offer you a great deal.
In this, our chironasium, the enchanters and alchemists of Wayrest share their resources.nnAnd you benefit from our collaboration!
Only fools go into the wilds without the proper armor. How can I help you?
I have all that the journeyman Outfitter needs. The crafting table is out in the yard ... the smell don't you know.
Orcs and Redguards aren't subtle, but in battle, they're unmatched. We couldn't ask for better allies.
Redguard steel has protected Wayrest for many generations, just as it does today.
If you expect me to teleport you someplace, just go away. I'm out of that business.
Runecrafting is a delicate business, but you can learn with time.
I see an unfamiliar face!nnHeimlyn Keep is not a place for sightseeing, <<1>>.
Free at last from that wretched urn! nnOver the years, no one has overcome the curse of strife long enough to free me.nnBefore you, no one discovered this shrine.
Have you been to Omaynia? My brother lives there. nnWe haven't had any mail from him since the plague began.
Make no mistake. Kragenmoor is a hard place to live.nnThe Dres expect everyone to pull their own weight. If you can't swim with the slaughterfish, they won't throw you a rope.

Can I get you a drink? A Nightflower? A room? nnYou know, no one ever wants a room. They try to pass out in the corners, where they think I can't see them. nnWorthless freeloaders. I don't know why I even have the rooms.

House Dres has a cancer within, and I need your help to cut it out. Whatever foul necromancy they work, it is not to the benefit of any of us.nnPlease, you must help me. I will not leave this keep alive unless I have your aid.

As long as the soul gem remained intact, my rage was endless. nnMy anger and hatred for Thadan overwhelmed me.nnI believed he was responsible for our sister's death. nnThank you for releasing me and opening my mind to the truth.
Thank you, <<1>>. nnOnce you freed me from the soul gem, I was finally able to see the truth. nnI still can't believe it. Our own mother sacrificed our sister.
Welcome, stranger.nnWould one such as yourself like to partake in the many festivities of our little den here?nnMany have made a wondrous fortune by participating in our games.
With all of these Ashlanders about, I don't see how anyone can expect to get Senie rebuilt.
These fresh corpses have drawn scavengers in record numbers.nnThis is a prime opportunity for hunters like me to make a profit.
Keep your distance. By order of the Tribunal Temple, this ship is under quarantine.
This ship is under quarantine. nnNo one is allowed on or off until the designated time has expired. nnIf no signs of disease are found at that time, you can go aboard, but not a moment sooner.
That sailor has done nothing but stare at me for hours. nnDid he just wink at me? nnThat's... that's just not right.
I've been staring at that guard for hours now. I even winked once or twice, just to throw him off guard.nnHey, it's not like I have anything else to do around here.
They got him! I killed the scamps, but they got Master Muzgu.
Friend, have you considered that your soul has a real value?
Why do you trouble me? Do you seek training?
You're not a Supernal Dreamer. Who are you?
There's a good reason these people are down here. It's a matter of simple mathematics.

The captain fled when she heard you had breached their defenses. Soon after that, my allies released me.nnWe've retaken the fort for House Dres, not those crazed necromancers!nnTell me, what did you find within?
What's  where am I? Oh, gods, let me go!
Have you ever been to the coast? I'm told the breezes are refreshing.
I'll take care of Gerarde, and get us both back to Pariah Abbey. I hope to see you there one day.
Everyone's anxious to continue training, but there's been so many sick lately, we haven't had much opportunity.
I'm visiting from Vvardenfell. Sometimes I find the colors so bright here, I have to close my eyes.

The Dres are trying to keep a secret. The head of their Great House, Grandmagister Jaelyck, has gone missing in Deshaan.nnSo many people hate the Dres. The real question is who's above suspicion.nnFor all I know, my noble house is behind it.

Have you read the Sermons of Vivec? nnI find them more comprehensible after a glass or two of shein. nnI suspect he intended them to be that way. They're unintelligible to those of conventional intellect.
It is good to be back. I will not leave my brother again.

Have you been watching Mount Heimlyn, the mountain to the north? Every day, I see smoke rise from it.nnAfter the eruption of Mount Senie, it's an ill omen. I hope the mer at the keep are ready to leave.
You think you're better than me, don't you?nnThat's all right. I can use that. Please, continue.
Some are saying the Dres have lost their Grandmagister. nnI don't mean he's dead. I mean they really don't know where he is.nnHeh. Wouldn't that serve them right?
Smithing is not a craft for the weak-willed. Work through the pain of the heat requires determination. nnI've lost many students to attrition, but I'm still determined to find a true apprentice.
I know Master Dranolos means well, but he really should take things a little less seriously. nnHe can be a bit overbearing at times.
Forestry requires a steady hand and a keen eye, even in the face of danger. nnMany foresters risk their lives to find the perfect timber. Do you have that same dedication?
If I never see another splinter, it will be too soon. nnMaybe I'm just not cut out for forestry.
Can you see the striations in this stone? If concentrate, you can sense what it was really meant to be. nnWith a nudge here and a nudge there, you can created something... magical.
Master Tels speaks to the stones. nnHis whispers carve such beautiful patterns. You would think they were made by nature herself.

Clumsy, half-tight stitches in a suit of armor can kill a man as surely as a sword. nnWhere I come from, improper vestments mean you're nothing but food for the wolves.nnIf you wish to learn, you must take this to heart.
Does it matter if a few stitches are crooked? I'm sure she wouldn't even notice.
I have nothing to say to you. Begone!
Excuse us, this is a private matter.
I'll be with you in half a moment, sedura.

Many years ago, my great-grandfather Padesh slaughtered innocents here.nnHe was cursed to roam this place eternally.nnI want to find a way to redeem our family's honor, but the Redguard immortals attack me whenever I approach.
I hanged along with all of my men. Every one of them was condemned for my sins ... eternally cursed!nnI was unable to atone for a mistake made in a time of war. I will haunt this place forever.
This one does not care for scratching in the dust, but there are certainly worse punishments.
It's so hard to relax my mind these days. nnI'm not sure what worries me more: fear of the Orlishkaarn attacking, or fear of them infecting me with their illness.
It's so hard to relax my mind these days. nnI'm not sure what worries me more: fear of the Orlishkaarn attacking, or fear of them infecting me with their illness.
With all of these Ashlanders here, I don't see how anyone can expect to get Senie rebuilt.
With all of these Ashlanders here, I don't see how anyone can expect to get Senie rebuilt.
To think there was a time I used to complain about not having enough work to do. nnNow I don't even think four of me could get everything done for Senie.
I may be the only one around here who doesn't feel overworked. nnEveryone here seems to be more worried about the Orlishkaarn than the disease.
TBD - Tells the player about class training for Mages, Ritualists, and Sorcerers.
Little creatures ruined my experiment, scattering the pieces. I am unable to continue...
The Mages Guild takes pride in our knowledge of the world and its history. We gather lost tales and artifacts long forgotten... and now our collection is smaller because of those little thieves.
Have you ever stolen pollen from a bumblebee's mouth? My master once claimed he did!nnOf course, I doubted that was true... and while he was telling me the story, I stole his pouch.
Breathe easy. As long as your gaze falls upon me, you are safe this day. nnOnce you can no longer see me, however, I can no longer guarantee your safety.
Neither beast nor man can escape a true ranger. nnThe leaves tell of a ranger's passing, but the wind conceals a master ranger's trail.
I don't know if I'll ever be equal to the master. nnIt's as though she more than one lifetime of experience.
Put your ear to the ground, and you can hear the footsteps of your prey. nnThat is how you will find your next target.
Doesn't matter what happens in Stonefalls. My job is always the same. nnThat's comforting, isn't it?
Why do you interrupt me? nnCan you not see I am in pain?
Sorry. These are not for sale.
If you hadn't come along, I was as good as dead.nnI was next on Curio's list.
You've got to get us out of here!
The Tribunes sent me to investigate rumors that the Imperials are training gargoyle pets.nnI didn't believe the rumors until I saw them.
I feel my heart sinking into the ground. nnWhat use is it to me? It's broken. Adrusa loves me not.

Quit making a spectacle of yourself, Deval! You knew this couldn't last!nnPlease, stranger, do not tell anyone what you've seen here. nnIf this affair came to light, the consequences would be... unpleasant.
The water is sweet, but where are the fish?
I could sit here all day... though my master will probably scold me if I miss my lessons again.
Blessings of the Three upon you! nnThis temple is a testament to the power and glory of the Tribunal. nnI expect you to show appropriate displays of respect during your stay.
Submit to the Three, the spirits, and thy Lords.
Welcome to the Iliath Temple. Please be wary of the cliff racers that plague the path.nnSuch infernal beasts. I'd clip their wings and throw them from this mountain, if I could.

Beyond this gate lies the Gutter. Skooma addicts are everywhere.nnIf you must enter, I suggest you bring a weapon.nnOr a spell, I suppose. Personally, I don't put stock in magic. I like the feel of a weapon in my hand.
Your pardon, sedura. Your pardon. I didn't mean to be in your way.
Good day to you, serjo. Need a ride?
Take care if you must speak. River Walker gets nervous around loud noises.
Saint Nerevar, teach us valor, so that we may strike down our many foes.
The blasted dreugh are everywhere, and these citizens are brave, but they're no soldiers.nnCan you help, stranger? It's desperate.
You aren't an Imperial.nnMaybe you can help my brethren.

The Necropolis of Heroes lies ahead.nnIt's been a holy burial site for our people since the Ra Gada first landed on these shores.nnThe Imperials have completely taken it over, but we have no idea what they're doing there.
With the onset of this disease, many are seeking the comfort of the Tribunal Temple.nnWhile it's good to see them embrace the Three, it saddens me that we still have no cure.
I'm here to keep an eye on the Imperials.nnThey've taken a lot of our people prisoner and set them to digging in these caves.
Were we supposed to meet today? nnMy apologies. I've been distracted by the issue of the Grandmagister's disappearance.
<<1>>, right? I heard you'd be coming through here. nnI'm so glad I caught you before you headed into the city!nnCome closer. We don't know who else might be listening.
Now, now. Just a moment.nnWhere do you suppose you're going with those census records?
Could you ask someone to attend to us?nnWe've come so far.
We came to repair the works, but everything has gone wrong!
What can I do for you?
During the war, there was a shortage of ale. Could you imagine? Now we always have enough ale!
The Daggerfall Covenant means nothing to me. It's political jousting, as far as I'm concerned. nnSo long as no one takes away my ale, the king can ally with whoever he wants.
We need to gather up all able-bodied soldiers and return to the Garrison immediately. There should be no debates about our need for action.nnKing Eamond would have wanted it.
The soldiers cannot wait to return to the battle. Captain Ondre should let me lead them back now, before the Imperials press their advantage.
Greetings, friendly traveler!nnDon't mind me, I'm just your run-of-the-mill talking Ogrim.
My life wastes away at this temple. nnI feel emptiness in my heart when I pray to the Tribunal.nnWhat if they're nothing but a myth?
Keep clear of me, <<1>>.nnMy sister is dead, slain in cold-blood, and I suspect her murderer will pass this way soon.
I want no pity from heretics and outlanders. I will face my death as one of the true people.
You've removed the necromancer's hold on me.nnI am free.
You've removed the necromancer's hold on me.nnI am free.
I see that you've retieved the lost artifacts. Return them to the Grandmagister in a moment... but first I have a warning.
The Ayleids cursed this place. They cursed every place they touched!
Little creatures ruined my experiment, scattering the pieces. I am unable to continue...
Ensure that the message is heard. Take it to all the Guild Halls.
We shall depart knowing that our warning has been sounded.
The Reachmen nearly overcame us, but we fought them off.nnI was captured during the skirmish and dragged up here.nnDid you manage to free the rest of the prisoners?
Stay at an arm's length, if you care for your health. nnI've caught something that's burning inside me.nnI've no wish to spread it to anyone else.
You dare raise the Champion of Tu'whacca?

I would like to say they forced me to raise my hand against my own.nnI could claim I was simply surviving... yet we all have a choice. nnI chose to serve Dres until the revolt. I regret that decision with every breath.
Many have joined.nnMany more will join us soon.
Please don't startle me like that!nnI've endured so much already. My nerves are starting to fray.
The Imperials will not survive this.
No one enslaves our brethren. Verro will pay!
Tu'whacca's vengeance will take all who would defile our graves!
After I was free of the necromancer, I heard Mazira's call.nnI will gladly join you in destroying the Imperials.
I haven't seen my wife for months, but I know she's still alive.
Divad favors our calls. Verro and all his necromancers will crumble before us.
That swarm! I've never seen anything like it! nnThe Diviner told me to take comfort knowing so many have faith. nnI... could not.
Are you going to the sanatorium? nnThere's a lot of sick and wounded there. Be careful, or you might join them.
Did you see the Altmer running and yowling about the ruins? nnFine way to get yourself chewed on and killed... or worse.
Blessings of the Three upon you. nnThis temple is a testament to the power and glory of the Tribunal. nnIt's no wonder so many flock to its walls.
You are not permitted to leave until <<1>> is done with you.
What can I do for you?
Lost! Missing!nnWhere is it? It's gone!
I want no pity from heretics and outlanders. I face death a member of the true people.
I'm here to make sure these sailors pay their fair share of Evermore's taxes.
I'm here to make sure these sailors pay their fair share of Evermore's taxes.
Oh, aren't you just the sweetest, coming to visit me on my birthday!
Would that I had died young with a sword in my hand.nnPerhaps Ruptga will give me a chance in my next life.
If you're looking for a drink, go on inside. nnDon't bother anyone, and I'll give you a discount.
I've tasted better fluids from a mud puddle. I don't know why I even bother coming here.
I haven't seen a proper barfight break out for hours! nnThe barkeep must be watering the drinks.
Eating the weevils that nest in the bread here is better than eating the bread.nnThey're tastier, too.
Seems every customer asks me the same questions. nnNo, I'm not interested, and yes, I will stab you.
I'm ready to defend my goods and my life with sword and spell.nnCurse the winds that brought us to this decrepit port!
I must warn you. It's a madhouse on the docks. nnI barely beat back the villains that tried to take my possessions.
My brother and I fled to here not long ago.nnI could not dream of a better place to stay.nnI just wish he was around to see it.
Find me during the fight, and I'll use my energy to heal you!
Find me during the fight, and I'll use my energy to heal you!
At last, we face Legatus Verro.nnThe army is ready. Are you?
Tu'whacca's vengeance will seize all who would defile our graves!
Undead will feel the wrath of my blades!
We will crush all who stand in our way!
I hear the queen has asked for your council regarding who will be regent.nnI find this highly... unusual, but such has been our leadership since Princess Elara took ill.
Oh. It's you.nnPlease don't say anything about that little matter with the bodies. It's all handled, I assure you.
I handle disputes that cannot be resolved any other way.nnIf you've no business here, you'd best be on your way.

This inspection may be daunting, but I'd rather be here than the Iliath Temple.nnIn Iliath, the sick wail in the mountains and moan in the courtyards, every day and night.nnWe're trying to find the disease's source, but people here appear healthy.
If you're here to pick up goods, you're in for a wait. nnWe just started this inspection. If it's anything like the last one, this will be an all-day affair.
