This inspection may be daunting, but I'd rather be here than the Iliath Temple.nnIn Iliath, the sick wail in the mountains and moan in the courtyards, every day and night.nnWe're trying to find the disease's source, but people here appear healthy.
If you're here to inquire about goods, I'm not the person you want. nnThe ordinators won't allow any merchandise off this ship before it's ready, regardless of who wants it.
The captain's been talking to one of those ordinators for some time now. nnI wonder if he's trying to make a deal with her. nnCoin solves everything.
The captain's been talking to one of those ordinators for some time now. nnI wonder if he's trying to make a deal with her.
I don't see why we're even posted here. nnThe ordinators didn't find anything on the last ship, but quarantined it anyway! nnWhy not just quarantine it right now, so we can all get this over with?
Excuse me if I'm not in the most conversational mood. nnBeing trapped on my own ship after the nspectors found nothing has made me less than amicable.
Excuse me if I'm not in the most conversational mood. nnBeing trapped on my own ship after the inspectors found nothing has made me less than amicable.
This is insulting. nnI'm confined to my ship after those ordinators tore it apart with their so-called inspections.nnThey didn't find anything! Why am I still here?
I never thought I'd see my family together again. nnThank you, friend.
I never lost hope that we would survive. nnNow I know there is still kindness in this world.
Affliction! Nix-hounds! Mewling foreigners at our gate! Who knows what will darken our next dawn?nnSo you've made it here alive, and through all of that! No ordinary soul you are. That I swear.
Affliction! Nix-hounds! Mewling foreigners at our gate! Who knows what will darken our next dawn?nnSo you made it here alive, and through all of that! No ordinary soul you are. That I swear.
Affliction! Nix-hounds! Mewling foreigners at our gate! Who knows what will darken our next dawn?nnSo you made it here alive, and through all of that! No ordinary soul you are. That I swear.
My master, <<1>>, speaks the truth. The Imperials are destroying this sacred ground.

The Ashkhan wanted me to stay with the village. But our warriors are here, and the threat is here, not down at the foot of the volcano. nnAnd one of us must be here, to try and right what the Lost Farseer has done.

If it hadn't been for that fool of a Farseer, we wouldn't be in this mess. I don't have the warriors to keep up with what the daedra are throwing at us. Something must change, and soon. Meanwhile, our village stands all but undefended.
Be careful! This place is more dangerous than you can possibly know and it's all because of what I've done!
I don't see why we're even posted here. nnThey ordinators didn't find anything on the last ship, but quarantined it anyway. nnWhy not just quarantine this right away so we can all get this over with?
I managed to escape, thanks to <<1>>.
If you're heading further into Emberquay, stay alert.nnBetween this disease and Mt. Senie's eruption, resources are spread thin.nnLooters have moved in to get whatever they can.
The happiness of knowing <<1>> is Yoon's friend! nnThe joy of seeing <<1>> arrive safely in Cliffvoot!nnLearning my lesson. Staying in Cliffvoot. Not seeking adventure for the rest of the week!
Free... the prisoners.nnThe slave masters to the south. They hold the keys to the shackles. We... have to free them.
You must help us.nnA handful of scouts attempted earlier, but the Imperials quickly split them up. But you are here now.., you must be able to help!
You. It was you!nnYou'll go under the axe for this. nnWe've got friends in Nibenay. Powerful friends.
Skooma! Why are you so cruel to me?nnThis isn't your usual bliss! I may be an addict, but I know my limits.nnWait, is someone really there? I thought you were a figment of my mind. Curse this fever!

Halt. You do not want to enter this cave.nnThe air is thick with what they call the miasmata; the corruption left behind by Molag Bal when he was summoned here, centuries ago. nnIt is quite lethal. I advise you to turn back.
I am beset by greater ills than the troubles of a lost traveler.nnPray, take your problems to one of my mer.
I am beset by greater ills than the troubles of a lost traveler.nnPray, take your problems to one of my mer.

All who embrace Boethiah are welcome here. Those who have yet to embrace his truth may learn it.nnAll who worship of the pretender Tribunal will die. We will spill their blood in honor of the Prince of Plots.nnYou must choose. Which are you?

All who embrace Boethiah are welcome here. Those who have yet to embrace his truth may learn it.nnAll who worship of the pretender Tribunal will die. We will spill their blood in honor of the Prince of Plots.nnYou must choose. Which are you?

All who embrace Boethiah are welcome here. Those who've yet to embrace His truth may learn.nnThose who come to preach the worship of the pretender Tribunal will be slain, and their blood poured out in honor of the Prince of Plots.nnWhich are you?

Many years ago, my great-grandfather, Padesh, slaughtered innocents here.nnHe was cursed to roam this place eternally. nnI want to atone for this blight on my family's honor, but the Redguard immortals attack me whenever I approach.
I was hanged, along with all of my men.nnEvery one of them was condemned for my sins ... eternally cursed!nnNow I can never atone for a mistake made in a time of war. I will haunt this place forever.
I'll see myself out as soon as I've gathered my papers. Please free my retainer.
The Argonians here see this overgrown fungus sprout as a creature to commune with, rather than a weed to be rooted out. You would think the foul monsters it has attracted would be an indicator.
The Ordinators' false gods have abandoned them.
The Ordinators' false gods have abandoned them.
The farseer has gone to the oversee the battle outside the gates of the shrine.nnWe will prove our faith to Boethiah!
This is the NPC model swap tester.
We caught this Ashlander trying to spy on us.nnIf I were you, I wouldn't trust him.
Greetings. Do you seek runecrafting wares?
Are you a forester? If you are, I sell equipment you might need.
You have done well, <<1>>. Princess Elara is at last returned to health.
I have a few things for sale, but only if you're of the appropriate standing.

The Ashkhan wanted me to stay with the village. But our warriors are here, and the threat is here, not down at the foot of the volcano. nnAnd one of us must be here, to try and right what the Lost Farseer has done.

If it hadn't been for that fool of a Farseer, we wouldn't be in this mess. I don't have the warriors to keep up with what the daedra are throwing at us. Something must change, and soon. Meanwhile, our village stands all but undefended.
Watch your step. The patients here have trouble controlling themselves.
Mind your step inside. The patients here have trouble controlling themselves.
I have no wish to speak to an outsider.
May Tall Papa guide you, traveler.
May Tall Papa guide you, traveler.
May Tall Papa guide you, traveler.
May Tall Papa guide you, traveler.
May Tall Papa guide you, traveler.
May Tall Papa guide you, traveler.
May Tall Papa guide you, traveler.
May Tall Papa guide you, traveler.
May Tall Papa guide you, traveler.
Tava's blessings be upon you, wayfarer. You have come for silks and fine wools, yes? Our robes and tunics will ward off the desert heat and your foe's blade in equal measure.
The desert is an unforgiving place, wayfarer. Are you sure you are prepared? nnTake a look at my goods. You may find something needful.
In defense, speed is best. Is it not so? In this armor, you will be swift as a scorpion.
How do I know you? Who in the Lion Guard doesn't know you?nnYou're becoming something of a legend in our circles.
Be careful. The villains of the Withered Hand have been committing crimes again.
Welcome to my humble inn, traveler!nnMay you find rest, comfort, and peace within these walls.
Welcome to the Desert StarSentinel's most aromatic blossom of culture and refinement. Please, sit and be welcome.
What's the matter? Never seen an Orc who likes forestry before?
Welcome to Sentinel's forge, my friend.nnWhat can I do for you?
What can I help you with?
Greetings to the Sisters of the Sands. Sit, and abide a while. Our inn is your oasis in the desert.
Take your time and browse, my friend! nnI'm sure you'll find I have what you've always wanted.
My countrymen prefer the simple elegance of the swordbut there is glory to be found in the bow and staff as well. If you have an eye for fine woodcraft, you'll want to see my stock.
Hail, O wayfarer. The swords of Alik'r are the finest in all of Tamriel.  But mind your fingers! They are as sharp as jackal fangs.
Everyone who talks about heavy armor mentions the heat. It's not that bad. Getting killed is much worse!
Spells or swords? I am skilled with both. nnCome. Let me teach you how to survive.
My specialty is the art of healing.nnIf you'd like to learn more, I can teach you.
Iif you'd like to learn more about being a mage, then come closer, my friend!
Do you need training in the skills of a knight, my friend?
Few who can track me in the wilds or best me at archery. nnI'm willing to share my knowledge. You have but to ask.
I've made a lifelong study of the magical arts. nnIf you wish to learn more, don't hesitate to ask.
Some of what I know is best taught quickly and quietly. nnStand a little closer, my friend, and we'll talk.
Welcome, wayfarer. You have traveled far, is it not so? You may sit and take rest in our hall, but do not tarry long. I have training to offer.
My brothers live in Alten Corimont. The Nagas will not pass.

When you can learn to be be still - truly still - the wind will tell you all the enemy's secrets. By the rustle of leaves, the stirring of water, or the scent of musk, they cannot move without your knowing.
My brothers live in Alten Corimont. The Nagas will not pass.
I trust you're not here to disrupt my negotiations?
The Imperials have overrun the Fallen Wastes.nnPlease. Help us.
What makes you think you can board my ship, stranger?nnYour tongue had best be quick... or I'll use it for a fishing lure.
Won't these workers listen to reason? nnIt's as if their very lives were at stake!

Oh, ho! Another intrepid researcher has come to swell the ranks of Telenger's team. Splendid!nnWe've made excellent progress with our excavations.nnUnfortunately, it appears the indigenous goblinoids are working contrary to our efforts.
If history is what you seek, you have certainly come to the right place.nnTry not to step on anything.
Have you come to assist our little expedition? How amusing!

One cannot simply stroll into an enterprise such as ours and expect to make a valuable contribution. nnTelenger and I have dedicated centuries to our craft.nnIt pains me to say it, but I doubt the ability of others to discover anything of true worth.
Ho, there! For a moment, I thought you were one of those damned Altmer.nnThey dig in the dirt, even as the dead rise to ravage our lands.nnSuch folly!
Stay your weapon if you wish to enter our home. Do you seek the blessings of Sithis, or are you but a chance wanderer?nnEither way, you must speak to the Nest-Mother.
It is not my will to speak to you.
Filth! Traitors! Sithis take your soul, unbeliever!

Can you see the spirits? They're fascinating! nnI do not know their purpose, but I am intent on discerning it.nnAre you one of the locals? I have a task that wants doing right now: three deliveries, one for each of my assistants.
The Sand-born sabotaged Redguard ships. I must get back to the docks and stop any ships from leaving.
Welcome to Samaruik, palace of the all-beneficent King Fahara'jad. I serve His Majesty, and through him I serve our people. nnWhat seek you here?
Now is not a good time. Please go.
We can't even go to market.nnI fear some thug will put a knife in my wife's ribs.

By the Three! I've never seen your face before!nnListen. The villagers here have hidden in this canyon since the Knahaten Flu broke out. That was twenty years ago! You have to help me convince them to leave.
Run along, <<1>>. You're not welcome here.
I long for the days of peace within Stormhold. These constant protests and arguments weigh heavily on my heart.
Stay out of trouble, and be on your guard. This place offers no safe haven to travelers.
I thought it would be so glamorous to be married to the king's favored general. nnI was wrong though. It is not glamorous; it is just lonely.
I'd steer clear of this area if I were you.
I'd steer clear of this area if I were you.
I'd steer clear of this area if I were you.
Eldros was a good commander, but that life just isn't for me.
Eldros was a good commander, but that life just isn't for me.
What are you doing here? Shouldn't you be investigating <<1>>'s murder?
You are from the outside as well?nnTell me, are all the men as handsome and charming as my dear Devad?
My weakness cost lives. If only I could have fought off those thugs last night.nnRedguard ships "mysteriously" sunk off shore moments ago. I fear all the ships which leave port now may sink as well.
Who are you? I don't know you!
Who are you? I don't know you!
Who are you? I don't know you!
Who are you? I don't know you!
Who are you? I don't know you!
Who are you? I don't know you!
I wish I could go kill those dogs with you, but I can't leave mother.nnMake them bleed, <<1>>.

The Knahaten Flu has run its course and trade flourishes once again.... But the trade brings travelers, and the travelers have brought a new parasite that threatens our Hist. A threat to the Hist is a threat to us all.
What can I get you today? We've wares from all over the world!
All eyes are upon you, outsider. We feel your clumsy footsteps upon our soil.nnBe sure your words do not offend the Nest-Mother, or they will be the last you utter.
An outsider wishes for the poison of our Nest-Mother? Strange that a victim would seek death so earnestly.

These assassinations are getting out of hand. We've never seen crimes like this in Stormhold before. <<1>> blames the Shadowscales, but I think the real minds behind it belong to those much closer to us.
To think those Wardens have the audacity to keep me trapped down here. An Archein noble! nnI suppose it's better than a cell, at least.
I've heard some shalk have made a home among the roots of our Hist Tree. It's a pity the Wardens don't take better care of Stormhold.
The Wardens are handling the assassination investigation poorly. Stormhold is in turmoil due to their incompetence.
No one wants any part of the war in Cyrodiil. I'd be protesting and deserting, too, if they forced me to join up.
You must believe me. I've done nothing wrong!nnThe investigator who arrested me is the real criminal. He's working for the Pellingare gang!
With the state of turmoil that Stormhold is in, I almost don't blame the soldiers for deserting. But how can you turn your back on your own people?
Would you have us believe lands beyond the fields we know are safe?nnYou will come to know the truth. You will learn who yokes the dead to drag their people to an unseemly future.
Are you here for the Telenger expedition? We could certainly use another pair of hands.
What do we have here? A new research assistant? How droll.nnTelenger will be pleased.
What are you, an errand runner? nnI grow weary of Telenger's open invitations. nnWe can't let just anyone into these sites. Our research could be compromised!
Welcome to the Mages Guild. Please let me know if I can be of service.
The body is horribly mutilated from the neck up. At a glance, the only thing recognizable about this corpse is that it's a Dunmer.
This is great! I'm having the time of my life!
Stormhold is under too much strain. We've attempted to settle things peacefully for far too long. Now is the time to use force.
Welcome to Neeneban's Emporium of strange and wonderful things!nnCan I interest you in a lizard-catching net  or perhaps a trained lizard?
I've never enjoyed such fine food and drink!  I don't want to stop!  Why would I?
What?  Oh welcome to the party!
I've never knew such joy existed.  Nothing else seems important!
Let us leave this place, and quickly!
If the danger is so pressing, why do we dawdle here?
Do you always run so slow? This rapid escape is taking an embarassingly long time.
Be wary should you intend to venture deeper into the caves.  Your mind may become stuck like an insect in sap.
Where am I?  It's all a blur.
I came in to explore.... After that, it's all blank!
I'm full to bursting.  What have I been drinking?
You're in danger! If the Pellingare smugglers find you here, they'll kill you for sure.
Can it be true? Have the Gods abandoned us?
Can it be true? Have the Gods abandoned us?
Whatever it is you want, don't bother me with it.
Helene said she'd sent you after Anelle.nnI thought it was too dangerous, but you seem to have made short work of her.
We wait for the Nest-Mother to allow us to end his worthless life. Do not dawdle.
Can it be true? Have the Gods abandoned us?
Can it be true? Have the Gods abandoned us?
The Shadowscales have no hand in these murders.
Who are you? I don't know you!
Who are you? I don't know you!
There you are! Say, about that drink I'm afraid I spent my last gold on this one.nnMaybe next time!
I'd steer clear of this area if I were you.
I'd steer clear of this area if I were you.
I'd steer clear of this area if I were you.
Stormhold has gone to ruin! We demand to be treated with respect! They can't force us to go to war, and hiring these mercenaries is the last straw!
Stormhold has gone to ruin! We demand to be treated with respect! They can't force us to go to war, and hiring these mercenaries is the last straw!
I'm sorry, but only Spirit Wardens may enter our abbey.
It's been a long time since I've seen the horizon.
I'm sorry, but only Spirit Wardens may enter our abbey.
I'm sorry, but only Spirit Wardens may enter our abbey.
I'm sorry, but only Spirit Wardens may enter our abbey.
Ruined! Sunk as surely as my lost cargo!nnThe Black Marsh expeditions of the illustrious Vivendus are over. Curse these treacherous swamps, and the lizards wallowing in them!
Alten Corimont is going to be a problem.
Walk softly, <<1>>.  You wouldn't want to find a rope around that neck of yours.
Who approaches? Scar-Eye may be blind, but he can smell you well enough.
Unless we can halt the beetle infestation, Sentinel will be without water very soon.
This is not a safe place, stranger. A band of Nagas have taken Ten-Maur-Wolk.nnWe are trying to keep them from spilling south into Alten Corimont. It is... not going well.
These assassinations and protestors are getting out of hand. I think I may know the cause of all these problems.
I long for the days of peace within Stormhold. These constant protests and arguments weigh heavily on my heart.
I knew it was just a matter of time before one of us Wardens fell victim to these assassinations. We should have locked down all of Stormhold in order to find the murderer.
Dock workers are rioting, and a cabal of mercenaries called the Withered Hand have kidnapped Dock Master Bahir. nnI fear I'm not capable of freeing him alone.
People are dying under suspicious circumstances... without our consent!
Halt! What business have you in this place?nnWe can't tolerate any more disturbances to the site.
If you're looking for trouble, turn back now. nnThere won't be any more disturbances here. Not on my watch.
If this one doesn't meet his quota, he will not eat tonight.
Welcome to Sentinel, crown jewel of the Iliac Bay.
Please, I must focus on finishing this antidote. I've no time to talk.
You'll forgive me if I do not welcome you, stranger. The last traveler who came through our camp sought to destroy us.nnIf his poison doesn't kill us, the dead he summoned probably will.
I don't suppose you've seen a well-dressed Argonian around here?nnMaybe a well-dressed Argonian corpse?
Walk softly. This territory belongs to the Cult of the Fang.
A return to tradition is the only true path for the Argonian people.
Why am I still being held? Let me go, I'm no threat to your group.
What do you want?  I've no time to waste on the likes of you.
I need more recruits if we're going to make a go of this.
You should speak with <<1>>. I can't speak with an outsider without his approval.
Knowing the Withered Hand hasn't defiled the honored dead puts my mind at ease.

The lamia would rather eat me than my goats!nnI fear they may soon forget this preference. Then my goats will become part of their diet again.nnI would venture to the oasis to retrieve them... but I don't want to get eaten.
I know my lack of confidence in battle played a part in my desertion. I hope further training will make a formidable soldier out of me.
I know my lack of confidence in battle played a part in my desertion. I hope further training will make a formidable soldier out of me.
I know my lack of confidence in battle played a part in my desertion. I hope further training will make a formidable soldier out of me.
I know my lack of confidence in battle played a part in my desertion. I hope further training will make a formidable soldier out of me.
The risen dead! They're everywhere!nnIf I die from these wounds, I pray I don't join them.
Welcome back, my fellow researcher.nnHow did you fare in your search?
The Cult of the Sangiin has taken over Bloodgutter. Most of this one's shipmates were killed. nnDar'Thid, barely escaped with his life, no?

Oh, hello, and welcome! We rarely get visitors in our humble village, at least friendly ones. nnWe thought our troubles were over once we drove the Worm Cult out, but now mercenaries hunt us outside of our village. Can we not just coexist in peace?

Welcome to Velyn Harbor.nnI hope your journey was a good one as I am afraid you will not find much in the way of pleasantries here. Our army is holed up within the city walls and all ports for trade have been shut down.nnEveryone is restless.

Come to drown your sorrows in a glass of wine?nnThe port is closed. Our army stands around eager and anxious waiting for word from our scouts in the forest. It's been days now. We may as well drink until then, yes?
Why do you disturb me?nnI would recommend you keep your distance. This business of mine does not concern you, stranger.

Thanks for that, but you should have stayed back. That man  he's stir crazy. He's been harassing people for days trying to cause trouble. I just happened to get caught in his sights this time.nnWatch your back out there, all right?

Ahmuzi welcomes you to the trade district, friend.nnWith the closing of the shipping ports, you'll find most of the merchants now reside here. Take care not to get caught up in their mess.nnThe mob they gather makes even Ahmuzi nervous.

We cannot just simply stand by and lose out on our profits! The Dominion would have us starve and lose all that we care for. For what? For our safety?nnTheir incompetence and inability to keep the seas safe only results in us being their prisoners!
He's got a point you know! We're losing out the longer we sit around here!
The very ground rises against us. Even the dead dare not strike against it!nnScar-Eye does not know what has caused this, but soon Master Lorkus will arrive and put this to rights.
State your business, stranger. nnI have no time for idle chatter.
<This Redguard goatherd was recently slain. The discoloration of his skin indicates he may have been poisoned.>
<The body is hardly recognizable. Small sprouts and vines are already growing from the corpse.>
You are exceedingly eager in these pursuits, <<1>>.nnSuch a quality is far less admirable than you might believe.
You've returned. I hope you have not done so empty-handed!
You don't look like one of my mer. What do you want?
Though we may be dead, the ties to our past still remain. Perhaps it's our state of death that amplifies the pain of our restless brothers and sisters. My concerns grow daily for them.
Anything I can help you with?

Blood Cat Cultists dragged me into an alley in Velyn Harbor and brought me to Bloodgutter. I don't know what they have planned for me but I'm sure it's not good.n nWho sells knives in an alley at three in the morning? I should pay more attention.

Blood Cat Cultists dragged me into an alley in Velyn Harbor and brought me to Bloodgutter. I don't know what they have planned for me but I'm sure it's not good.n nWho sells knives in an alley at three in the morning? I should pay more attention.

Blood Cat Cultists dragged me into an alley in Velyn Harbor and brought me to Bloodgutter. I don't know what they have planned for me but I'm sure it's not good.n nWho sells knives in an alley at three in the morning? I should pay more attention.
Brave <<1>>! Why do you hesitate?nnOnly a fool would leave a lovely creature like me to the whims of these murderous spirits!
Alten Corimont does not allow casual visitors at this time. So says the Archein nobles, forever shaded be their steps.nnIf you wish to do business here, you must be recorded by the guard captain.

When we docked, Dar'Virr didn't know Bloodgutter was controlled by the Cult of Sangiin. Half this one's crew had wandered into town when the cultists struck.nnDar'Virr repelled the attackers, but they stole Dar'Virr's pet raven during the fight!
Unless you have business with the guard, I suggest you ask questions elsewhere.nnAnd you don't want to have business with us, I assure you.

Inerri, the leader of the Bloodgutter sect of the Cult of Sangiin had my crew murdered because I refused to smuggle moon sugar.n nI was the lucky one. She turned her scurvy minions on me after I spit on her fine blouse.
Stendarr, sweet merciful god! Deliver me from this trap.nnI'm too young to die!
Listen to me very carefully, <<1>>.nnYou must not, under any circumstances, leave me here with these idiotic spirits.nnDo you understand? Free me!
Boats trickle in slower by the day. I know not what the Archeins will do when the Pact finally cuts off this town from our commerce.

We didn't know Bloodgutter is  under control of the Cult of Sangiin. It's always been neutral. The crew had already wandered into town to drink when the cultists struck.nnWe repelled them, but they stole my bird. I want it back!
Come closer and I'll bleed you like I did your friends. I am slave to no one, mer or lizard!

A pleasure, <<1>>. You look to be most capable. Perhaps I can engage your... expertise?nnWe've had trouble keeping our allies out of sight from the Archeins of late. I worry what befell Shadowscale Teeus may strike twice.

I was wealthy a month ago. And then the spiders came. Who knows what brought them, but it didn't stop our production.nnNow the spiders are everywhere! I've closed the mines, but the last prospectors haven't come out.
My cousin was supposed to meet me here in Bloodgutter, but he never showed. That's not like him at all.nnIf he'd been at my side I might not have taken that blade to the stomach.
We drove out the Worm Cult, and we can do the same to these mercenaries. They don't realize who they are dealing with.

Since we forced out the Worm Cult members in an uprising, they left many of their possessions behind. I've been going through them to see if they've anything to learn about how we were created. So far it's proven quite interesting.
Damned elves!nnSince they set up camp in Ancestor's Landing, the ruins have been crawling with angry spirits. nnI used to harvest mudcrabs down by the water. Now I can't get anywhere near the place!
This one smells an ill odor wafting across the land, and it is not just the stink of old fish.
<<1>> recommends you stay away from the slums of the city. People have been going missing. More and more every night.nnIs not a good place to be, no. This one suggests you stay here. Drink instead!
News for me, friend? Or just here to dirty my floors?
<The raven stares at you with one beady eye, in the manner of suspicious avians everywhere.>
I don't know your face. So I doubt we have any business to deal. Off with you.
Tall Papa is testing me. He is watching how I deal with this crisis.nnHe did not pour those spiders into my mine. No. Tall Papa wants to see how I prevent the spiders from eating all of my workers.
Mauloch's sword! I thought I'd met my end! nnGet me out of here. We don't have much time!
Thank you, friend. Though my wounds will take me to the Tree soon, I had no wish to endure their interrogations with my last moments.nnTell Shade-Tail I died honorably.
You are Lei-Kai's friend. Keep your ear to the ground, for his friends do not lead the safest of lives.
It's so peaceful here. I hope it stays this way forever.
Those flesh flies were just what we needed to launch our attack.
<The lumbering creature seems to be looking at you, but does not make a sound.>
<<1>>, it is dangerous for you to be seen talking to me. I would not have you captured by these fiends as well.
Freedom is within reach, but my clumsy hands cannot grasp it. I never thought living within the law would hurt me so.nnWould you know any thieves or swindlers about these parts, friend?
This old one has no time for you, stranger. Too many new branches, far too many. They will drive me into the ground before my time.

Our egg-brother returns to the Hist this day. We celebrate his life and what is to come for him.nnThe rite will go on, despite our difficulties. What we lack in our preparation, we will make up for in words.
I wish I could give you a warmer welcome, <<1>>, but what you see is what you get.
It all happened so fast. We've lost everything... and everyone.
What is going on? What is happening?
How dare you come near me! I'll tear your eyes out!

I've been appointed the new captain to look after the Mirewalk Expedition. We were lucky the Chief of Stillrise was willing to accept our surrender. Compassion isn't something I'd think a skeleton would have.

Please, leave us be.nnOur valuables have already been taken. There is nothing left here for the scavengers.nnI simply wish to give comfort to my dying son and lessen his pain. Having my home filled with strangers is not what we need right now.
Don't give Elandra a hard time. My friend's already gone through too much pain.nnI won't let anyone else hurt her. Not while I'm around.
What is going on? What is happening?
Walk softly, you're scaring off my catch.
Soradenor is a skilled mage, but his magic is not powerful enough to feed all of us.
Hello <<1>>. I hadn't thought I'd see you again.
I don't know whether to hug you or punch you, <<1>>.
Hello <<1>>. I was just wondering what ever became of you.
Come and join us. There's plenty of free space, as you can see.
If you're looking for work, look elsewhere. I have my hands full paying these mer as it is.
Tall Papa is testing me. He is watching how I deal with this crisis.nnHe did not pour those spiders into my mine. No. Tall Papa wants to see how I prevent the spiders from eating all of my workers.

One cannot simply swing a blade and expect success. Each novice here must forge a blade before learning to wield it.nnBy understanding what goes into making the blade, a novice can understand how it must be used.
Please, kill them! Kill them all!
You may have caught me, <<1>>, but my sister is far beyond your grasp!

Look at them all. Delectable. Exquisite.nnAnd no, I speak not of the food.nnAn adventurer of my kind tends to grow bored with being shut out of the forest and such. He needs more... common things to keep his mind off the troubles of the world.
I hope joining the Cult was the right decision.
I hope you didn't encounter any of our mindless bretheren out there. Poor souls.
If you'd like to purchase more space at the bank of Wayrest, you can buy it from me.
We drove out the Worm Cult, and we can do the same to these mercenaries. They don't realize who they are dealing with.
Care to trade in your old bag for a larger one? I'll make you a great deal.

Terrifying beasts attacked us in the night and many of our neighbors went mad turning into horrid creatures! We tried to reach the safety of trees, but we're trapped here. If it wasn't for the scouts outside, they'd have eaten us already!
We have to keep the werewolves at bay. There are townsfolk counting on us.

If one waits for the right time, they can see the stars rise and fall on the setting of the ocean.nnIt's as if the sea is freeing its children, allowing them to fly, gliding into the heavens above.nnZihija wishes she too could be free like them.

If you have no business here, I would ask you leave.nnThe Aldmeri Dominion is hard at work with our attempts to open up the port once more. We have nothing new to inform anyone who may be looking for information.

Have you seen those Altmer walking around in their shiny armor? They are so adorable!nnMother was right when she told me to come here. "Start a family. Get to it now! You'll need to catch up to your seventeen brothers and sisters!"nnI can't wait!

All manner of beastly creatures arrived in the night and attacked the village of Gallowroot. Most never stood a chance, but a few villagers managed to avoid getting eaten and made it to the protection of the trees.

Oh gods, it's awful. Awful! I came back to check on Hadima, to see if you had found her. But that's not Hadima up there. It's not!nnWhat about my other friends? I know they are out there... walking around, even though they're dead. It's unbearable!
We have to keep the werewolves at bay. There are townsfolk counting on us.
It's my job to keep the beetles in check, but something has gotten them riled up. I'm a farmer, not a warrior. I don't have the weapons or skills to deal with this.
We have to keep the werewolves at bay. There are townsfolk counting on us.
We have to keep the werewolves at bay. There are townsfolk counting on us.
The stink of death will hang over Gallowroot for many months.

A shame this building sits here abandoned like this.nnI've been thinking. The traders are restless because they make no coin. I... might be able to remedy that, but I'd need some help.nnMaybe, just maybe, we could start turning things around here.

Ahh, I can smell it from here. Fresh crab!nnI've managed to convince some of the traders to provide the necessities we need. It'll need to be blended just right.nnWe mess it up even a little and we'll need to start from scratch.
We drove out the Worm Cult, and we can do the same to these mercenaries. They don't realize who they are dealing with.
Did you see what those flies did to those mer? I feel like they're crawling all over me!
<<1>>, do you have business here? I am usually not this cautious of outsiders, but we are plagued with many troubles and I cannot be certain of every warmblood.

You're back! You won't believe what's happened.nnI passed the dish around to a couple of traders in the area and people were ready to start eating right away. So, I went ahead and set up shop.nnThis is amazing.
I shouldn't have left her behind!
<<1>> thinks he's got worries? I brought most of the miners here. Now I have their deaths on my conscience.
You are welcome to pay homage to the Elder Hist. May her branches rain on you one day.
I am without flesh, and still I feel the flames.
There was great beauty and power here, once. Now, there is but ash.

The Withered Hand has mustered an army!nnMy partner, <<1>>, and I were sent here to sabotage the camp. <<1>> killed a cultist and used his robes as a disguise. He slipped inside the caves unnoticed, but he's been gone for some time now.
Why have you called me forth?
Why do you draw out my torment?
It's dangerous to go further. The Nagas kill anyone who enters Ten-Maur-Wolk.

Look at them all.nnDelectable. Exquisite.nnAnd no, I speak not of the food.nnAn adventurer of my kind tends to grow bored with being shut out of the forest and such. He needs more... common things to keep his mind off the troubles of the world.
This one is glad you brought her out of her slump.nnThis Larland. He is funny, even for an Elf! Perhaps I shall buy him a drink?

Really? This is your friend?nnYou should have told me. This... acquaintance of yours almost had himself thrown in the cells with the way he approached me earlier!nnWhy, maybe I shall still throw him in one before the night is over.
Oh, this is so exciting!nnLook at this man. He is so adorable! I think we shall name our first child after him. We'll call him Larls. A great name if I do say so.nnI wonder how tall he'll be?
Why? Why did she leave us?
A viper needs only one precise blow to defeat an opponent. nnThe style of Viper's Strike follows this principle, focusing on speed and control over brute strength.

The scorpion overwhelms its opponent by attacking from all sides.nnThe style of Scorpion's Claw provides multiple avenues of attack, overwhelming an opponent's defense with lighting fast strikes from multiple angles.

When a duneripper is threatened, it burrows into the earth to shield itself, then strikes again when its opponent is weak.nnThe style of Duneripper's Guard emphasizes defense as well as aggression. A proper balance of the two will lead to victory.

A lion attacks without fear, overwhelming an opponent with strength and power.nnThe style of Lion's Roar follows this principle. Put enough force behind a two-handed blade, and your opponent can only flee or fall.
Oh a visitor? And look at the state of my home!  I simply don't see why it's such a mess. Doesn't anything know how to put itself away these days?

This is as far as I can take you - from here, you'll have to find my scout.  nnBe careful. We have not had the best of luck here, and despite your reputation, I worry that you underestimate the Maormer.
Come, come.nnWon't you stay a while?
You know you want to buy it... you just know it.
Careful. It's not safe out there in the Mire. Not safe. But you seem to have made it here all right. Maybe you're not safe, eh?nnDon't mind me. Chopping to do. Go ahead and talk.
Who are you? Why are you talking to me?

Look at that mess down there. Used to be a caravan, on its way to Bergama, but it was attacked. We suspected bandits were using this basin as a hideout, and so we came here to search. What we found was worse. Far worse.
I can't talk. I must deliver this message.

My husband has lost his wits and become something beastly. We saw it happen to others in Gallowroot.  A madness overcame them and our friends became vile creatures and attacked us on sight. They've destroyed the town and killed most of the townsfolk.

My husband has lost his wits and become something beastly. We saw it happen to others in Gallowroot.  A madness overcame them and our friends became vile creatures and attacked us on sight. They've destroyed the town and killed most of the townsfolk.
What do you want? I'm quite busy.

Have you seen our new neighbors to the east? Pirates.nnSo far they've only attacked trade barges going up and down the river, but many people come for our rocks. They bring money to exchange for goods and services.nnPirates are attracted by money!
You're not familiar to me.... Are you really there? I can never tell these days. My mind plays endless tricks on me, but I suppose it's what I deserve.
You don't belong here. Shove off.
I was only here to observe! I had no real hand in this!

I was out on patrol when I caught this boar sniffing around. Then <<1>> told me it's an Archein spy and I need to guard him, make sure he doesn't escape. I didn't realize boars could be spies.nnI'm just waiting until we can eat him!
<<1>> said this Argonian is an Archein spy.

Why are you here, mortal? Why do you not heed my warnings?nnThere is only death in this forest. Death in these ruins.nnHave your eyes not already shown you enough? Why do you press deeper into this cursed place?

We once came across a Bosmer, ridden with disease. Filled with a mad rage. We could've left him to die. It would have not mattered to us. He was no one.nnBut we did not. We nursed him back to health, saving his life.nnCould you do the same?

I once met a great beast's gaze with my own. Four heads taller than I and as wide as a Valenwood oak. He could have crushed me... if he could catch me.nnBut he did not. With a single blow, his head was dismembered by my blade.nnCould you do the same?

When we first set foot upon this soil, we had no knowledge of the lands or its people. We were lost. Confused even. But through the years, we learned.nnWe taught ourselves what we needed to survive. What we needed to live.nnCould you do the same?

This was a nice vacation. Good to get some sun on the old bones. Too bad about the pirate slaughter, eh? Too bad they only had one toothless old lizard with a dull sword to protect them.nnWell, their mistake, I suppose.

Please, no! Get away! You'll not put your tendrilly spirit bits near me!nnWait... you have flesh. Like me! You're not one of them, are you? One of the spirit people?nnBy the Treethane's flowing hair, I'm glad to see you.
My illusions were without peer, visions and phantasms of such detail that they would be the envy of all other mages!
In death, I can still heal the land.
They want to see fire? I'll show them fire.
Pleasant rays warm your back, traveler.
What are you doing here? If you're with these necromancers, draw your weapon now.

I noticed you're no friend to the Withered Hand. Please, hear me out.nnI may wear their robes, but I'm not one of them. This is merely a disguise, although it's not as effective as I would have hoped.
Running the mines is Kasal's job. I'm just his assistant.nnIf you want something, talk to him.
Please help, if you can. It's too late for me, but my mission must be accomplished.
Freedom is within reach, but my clumsy hands cannot grasp it. I never thought living within the law would hurt me so.nnWould you know any thieves or swindlers about these parts, friend?
Strangers are both rare and rarely welcomed. What brings you here?
Please help, if you can. It's too late for me, but my mission must be accomplished.

Mongrels, all of them, those Withered Hand necromancers!nnThe dead left here recieved no proper burial and so the Withered Hand are able to raise any corpse they find as a slave. If we had only sanctified the corpses, none of this could happen.
Give me a moment.nnIt's harder to swim with one arm than it was in my youth. I had to walk along the riverbed. I was afraid you'd get here before I did.

I am pleased that you stand before me.nnWith the chaos of the forest erupting across all of <<1>>, these lands need more that know of the true virtues. More that can stand up and fight against the coming shadows.nnPerhaps there is still hope.
The best part about being a guard is finding out where the best parties are!
Well, that was satisfying. Everyone likes a bonfire, wouldn't you say? And good work with Nedir!
The Cult of the Fang holds the only true answer to the problems of our people.
How am I supposed to get any work done with those little men climbing all over this tree? Don't they know it's not allowed?
I hope joining the Cult was the right decision.
<<1>> - this is no place for civilians. Are you trying to get yourself killed?

Excuse me. The smell of the corpses. I think I'm going to - hurp!nnUgh. Those waste-of-skin pirates took everything. I can just imagine them over there, sitting around their fires, drinking our wine and eating our food. Infuriating.
No one gets through this door without my permission.
<<1>>, whatever your motivations, you deserve our thanks.
You saved my life, <<1>>. May you never lose your way in the woods.
Don't worry, this time I won't leave my cousin behind if he stumbles.
My wife and I will go with Soradenor back to Velyn Harbor. It will be hard, but we will do our best to start over.
Time will heal both Venosir's wound and the ache caused by our fallen kin. Thank you, <<1>>.
Shhh. If you're very, very quiet, you can hear them breathing.
What are you doing here? If you're with these necromancers, draw your weapon now.
Welcome to Mirewalk Village in the heart of the Percolating Mire. I'm sure your stay here will be interesting to say the least.

Caravans are being attacked on the way to Bergama. You can see the remnants of one from here. We suspected bandits were using this basin as a hideout, and so went down to search. What we found was worse. Far worse.
You don't look familiar to me, so I highly doubt you're real. Now leave at once!
Long swim.nnPirates everywhere.nnOnly thrown up twice.nnI think my Khajiit friends would call this a good day.nnHow was your trip?
Please, cut me free! I must get back to my family.
I'm glad to see you made it here safely, friend.
<This corpse bears many cuts and bruises. The victim was tortured before being killed.>
Greetings and welcome! I get few visitors, and my father will not let me leave with the strife that has taken hold of Bergama.
Your arrival to Whiskerleaf is fortuitous. I need the aid of an outsider.
I sent for the leaders of this rabble. Not a messenger.nnYou are dismissed.
An outsider? We don't get many visitors here at Whiskerleaf.

You have met us at an unfortunate time, stranger. The elder held us above the Pact's squabbles, away from the Archein's desperate preening. With him gone....nnAh, but our troubles are not yours. What do you wish of me?
Fire and iron! Did you escape too? That was the most awful thing I've ever seen. Ever!
I think I pulled a muscle running up the hill.
You think there'll be any more? If I have to start casting again, I might- urp!
I just can't believe this could happen. Where did they all come from? The dead! The dead are walking! Why did the Withered Hand need to attack this place?
Your arrival to Whiskerleaf is fortuitous. I need the aid of an outsider.
How did Eiam become a fisherman of notoriety?nnThat is a secret, known only by Eiam.

Damned elves! Ever since they set up camp in Ancestor's Landing, the ruins have been crawling with angry spirits. I used to harvest mudcrabs down by the water there. Now, I can't get anywhere near the place!
Damned elves!nnSince they set up camp in Ancestor's Landing, the ruins have been crawling with angry spirits. nnI used to harvest mudcrabs down by the water. Now I can't get anywhere near the place!
Damned elves!nnSince they set up camp in Ancestor's Landing, the ruins have been crawling with angry spirits.nnI used to harvest mudcrabs down by the water. Now I can't get anywhere near the place!
Damned elves!nnSince they set up camp in Ancestor's Landing, the ruins have been crawling with angry spirits.nnI used to harvest mudcrabs down by the water. Now I can't get anywhere near the place!
You are the first to venture here in so long. I regret the trouble my kind brought to the stone-builders. Do you know of Gatheron?

The body of a woman has started to bloat. Her skin shows signs of painted symbols, and feathers adorn her hair.nnJudging by her position, she died before being able to reach the door before her. Her right hand looks like it still clings to something.
I don't like your face, outsider.
Your arrival to Whiskerleaf is fortuitous. I need the aid of an outsider.

No good! No good at all!nnWhat is Da'Nishi to do with all of my wares? Who wants sugar at a time like this? No one!nnThis is why Da'Nishi shouldn't have come here. This one will rot away before the ports open back up.
Do you believe this will actually work?nnDa'Nishi is not so sure. If the girl is wasting this one's time, she will find herself in much pain. Of course... Da'Nishi has nothing better to do either.
I do not taste the touch of Brinereed upon you, stranger. What has made you drink of my waters so lightly? What do you seek?
I've lived here for many years, you know. My father came here during the Imperial attempts to - ah - settle the area.

I know the Dominion is just trying to protect us, but... well there's a lot of commotion being stirred up around town. It's amazing how much of a mob a bunch of traders can become if they get restless.nnHopefully the ports will open soon.
We now work for ourselves and not a master.

It's so boring here!nnI'd almost say it'd be worth going out to sea and facing the Imperials, or even venturing into the woods and confronting whatever manner of beast is out there.nnAnything but this.

Dried pieces of sinew still cling to the bones of this skeleton. A closer examination of the bones shows evidence of gnawing. This person must have died recently and became food for the scavenging creatures of the hamlet.
You might want to step back. I don't know if you'll catch what I have.
You might want to step back. I don't know if you'll catch what I have.
Are you new?nnPlease, buy something! Please!
Take a look around, and let me know if you need anything! Regrettably, this is not the fine market of Velyn Harbor, but I do what I can with the lot I am given.
I'm putting my faith in Andri. She's a smart girl and the idea's a good one.nnIf it doesn't work out, well, I lose some goods that might otherwise go bad regardless. No risk, no reward!
Now this, this is exciting!nnIf Andri can make use of my grains, I'll be known all through Velyn Harbor.nnThat is once everything opens up and what not. Sure hope that's soon.
Yes, yes, of course this was all Da'Nishi's idea.nnThis one may not know how to prepare a meal, but a business man I am. If not for Da'Nishi, all of these people would have not come together.

You have to give her credit, Andri knew what she was doing.nnJust look at it in there. Busy as can be and for once everyone seems to be enjoying themselves. Hopefully we can keep this up for a while. At least until the ports open again.
Can you taste that? Comes all the way from the heart of Valenwood.nnYou might not want to ask what's in that exactly. It might be better that way.
First sandstorms plague us. Then there's talk of necromancy.nnAnd now the Crowns won't leave us in peace!
People are disappearing from the streets, and no one's doing anything!nnAll the Crowns care about is keeping their people in power.
I suppose you want me to talk in Imperial? Always gives me a headache.nnAs if I didn't already have one.
Do you think it looks like rain? That would be a pity. The weather's been pleasant all week.nnWe get a lot of rain here. You probably guessed that.

You're in luck, my friend. I have here some of the finest treasures this cursed place holds... and all for a reasonable price! Something for every taste.nnWait, are you that <<1>> everyone's been talking about? <<2>>, is that right?
I'm going to kill them! I'm going to kill all the ogres, everywhere!
They came from the sands. They came from every direction!nnWe didn't know who she was. How could we have known?
It's <<1>>, isn't it? Your reputation precedes you. Will you help those less fortunate than yourself?
You have saved my people. I was unable to finish the ritual of protection before succumbing to sickness. It was trapping our spirits. Now we are finally able to move on. Thank you.
I won't let you harm her. No fighting, understand?
What will I do without my wife? I'm lost without her, lost! Alakad's Curse lies heavily upon these shoulders! She is gone! Gone!

I believed this day would never come, but here you stand before me.nnThe Hunt has begun and few will have the will to stand before it. Cities will fall and many will lose their lives, but there will be hope.nnThat hope will be you.
A lot of my goods have been stolen by those cultists, but I still have a little coin left.
No one knows what you need better than I do.nnYou won't find better deals!
So very busy, but not enough business!nnYou'd think with all the danger in this world, more people would want to wear light, inexpensive armor. I know you want some? Right? I smell a sale.
The best way for us to survive is for the Archeins and Wardens to destroy eachother.
He deserves what he gets, the cowardly fool!

You walk into death's maw, stranger. Yet that is not what you should fear, for there are worse fates than the peace of the void.nnMy egg-brothers have turned away from the Shadowscale. I must discover the cause, before we are all destroyed by it.
No one gets through this door without my permission.

Why is this happening? We had no warning! When we woke up this morning the ogres were here, screaming and killing! I've never been so scared in my life!nnThey killed so many, even my father! Oh, father! Why?
For too long we waited. Waited for what was not to come until now.nnWas our life wasted? Andrial seemed not to think so.nnThe rest is in your hands now. Do what we cannot. Protect this forest.
Andrial has sacrificed so much. So very much.nnThe Tear's powers are strong. They will keep the darkness of the forest away.nnThe time for it to be used once again has come. You must not fail.
The forest is falling.nnHave we failed?nnNo, I still sense the power of the Tear. The city of Silvenar... it is in danger.nnAndrial will know what to do. She always did.
I just got to open this... all this skin on my arm is so frustrating!
Kneel and bow your head! The Blood Cat will tear out your throat unless you show submission!
This one cannot stop crying! Why? Why! Tell me!
You... where? This one does not... so confused.
I have not overslept. Why are you not resting like the others? I shall take five more minutes, now be off.
Is not life grand? Sangiin has opened my eyes! Everything is so beautiful, so many colors!
The scent of blood clings to you easily, stranger. Our Nest-Mother would approve.nnThey have not molested the shrine proper. Disturbing. Perhaps... they are not as malevolent as I first thought.
You are not... numbed by their magic. That you have survived is a blessing from Sithis himself.nnBut you must not tarry here, lest you find yourself lost with my brothers.

The Shadowscale seek to petition me, after their betrayal? I would think it fitting to grind them into dust for their hubris.nnBut you are not one of them, and neither are you tainted by their necromantic blood. Why are you here, mortal?
An outsider? We don't get many visitors here at Whiskerleaf.
The Silvenar Prime has been trapped within the bramble walls. All of our power is not enough to break him free!
You're going to break my concentration. Ask Zanthir to help you.
I am trying to concentrate, knave! Go bother Zanthir!
Blessings find you, stranger.nnHave you come to seeking Caretaker Thahala?
Greetings! We are happy indeed to see you, stranger. As you can clearly tell we are in dire need of assistance.
Please don't bother me. I'm currently deep in thought about my research.
Forgive me, but I must remain alert. There are many dangers in this desert and I must be watchful.
I have seen this type of heat sickness before. It is a terrible way to die.
Come! Come and enjoy the festivities and games of the bazaar!nnYou there! Why don't you join us?nnSurely you don't have anything better to do!
Come, come!nnBet on the right rat and you can maybe win shiny token. How special you will feel. M'adric promises this.nnBeginner's luck will maybe give you an advantage, yes?
What in Sep's name are you doing down here? There are dangerous creatures in these caves! nnHead back to the surface at once.
I don't know who you are, but now's not the time to come visiting.
What is it, <<1>>? I am on duty and cannot linger to entertain your insipid curiosities.

Outside, the creatures of the forest roam about in a craze, ripping apart any who would wander into their path. In here, a rousing affair goes on where people cheer, dance, drink, and eat cheese.nnThese people are either daft or suspicious.
What? What are you staring at? Can't a mer think in peace?
The wind told me of your arrival, <<1>>. "This is the champion of Alik'r," it said, "the one who will end the threat of undeath."nnIf this is to be, <<1>>, you'll need my aid. I have a gift for you.

The snakes have gone Wrong. Very, very Wrong. These sacred waters are befouled, and the get of Sep now grow in strange forms. nnThese aberrations, these insults to the World Eater  they must be destroyed.
My brother is missing! The High Priest gave us a sacred task, but the lamiae nearly killed us. nnYou must help me!
Gah! What ... wait ... who are you?
Is there something I can do for you?
No one gets through this door without my permission.

I was once a Judge in Sentinel. I served with honor in life. My peace in death, however, was disturbed by these infidels, these Withered Hand necromnacers!nnI have returned to see justice done! Four above all must die. Four I sentenced to die, here.
I have little time for idle talk. Unless you have business with me, be on your way.
I used to live near here. A little town to northeast called The Mire. But I have no time to go visiting.nnNothing ever changes there. I'm sure they're all right.
I smell old blood on you. Many races. Many lives.nnI wonder, have you come to see them as mere numbers? Momentary sparks in the depths of time, there and gone again?
You're heading the wrong way, wayfarer. Just so you know.
You look lost there, <<1>>.nnPerhaps I could help you find what it is you're looking for?nnFor a price, of course. Everything has a price.

Turn back now, if you value your life. Bergama is full of kidnappers! Forebears are being taken from the streets.nnThe Forebears blame the Crowns. Now both sides are crossing swords! I'm leaving the city before I get taken  or killed!
You again? Haven't I told you to go away? I don't care for your company.
We weren't thinking. We were fools!nnDaneem and I wanted to show we weren't afraid of the harpies.
Come, take a look. You'll find no finer wares this side of Bergama.
You think you can outdrink one of the Nord?nnHah, you are nothing but a puny <<1>>.nnCome! We welcome a challenge!
Greetings, O traveler. What can I interest you in today?
You are welcome to pay homage to the Elder Hist. May her branches rain on you one day.
I'm going to kill them! I'm going to kill all the ogres, everywhere!
The Ogres! There were just too many of them! My Captain is surrounded and has injured men! You must help him!
<This horse looks injured and frightened. Perhaps he can lead me back to where he came from and I can learn more about this area.>

Why look who graces us with their presence.nnWere you lucky enough to receive this little broacher from Silvenar as well? I must admit, I can never truly say no to a pretty woman giving away free handouts.nnI am sure glad I came though.
A new life... a new beginning. It's exactly what I need. My past weighs on me like a boulder. I can't bear it another day.
Did you see that? They race rats here. Rats!nn<<1>> thinks this is quite amazing.nnThis one has seen many races before, but not like this. The cheese they have here must be delicious.
People usually only come to White Rose Village if they are trying to escape their past. You don't look the sort.

You gave me a scare. I thought you were a Maormer pirate. Keep your head down or they'll see us.nnI think they're looking for something. Captain Ravenil and his men must be after the Treasure of Bleaker Rock.

You have been chosen by Sithis himself, mortal. Your life is his. Your will is his. Listen well, for he speaks through us.nnGo now, and submit to his shrine. The blood we have created for you will cleanse away your fears.

I am the messenger of the will of Sithis. He has decreed the treacherous Shadowscale are to die for their hubris.nnFrom the blood we bestow, you will grow strong. Drink deep from the pools we provide in his shrine, and all shall be revealed to you.
You are without your mark, servant. Be bathed in the glory of your master! Join your brothers in his shrine!
At last you arrive, <<1>>.nnI hoped you would arrive before grass sprouted across the Alik'r, there is much you must learn before you become our savior.nnShould I teach, will you listen?
At last you arrive, <<1>>.nnI hoped you would arrive before grass sprouted across the Alik'r, there is much you must learn before you become our savior.nnShould I teach, will you listen?
At last you arrive, <<1>>.nnI hoped you would arrive before grass sprouted across the Alik'r, there is much you must learn before you become our savior.nnShould I teach, will you listen?
What is this bag?nnThe smell is very strong.
My brother is missing! The High Priest gave us a sacred task, but the lamiae nearly killed us. nnYou must help me!
These outcasts need to be dealt with. They are thieves and a blight upon our peaceful existence.

I wondered when you would arrive.nnWhy would one such as you feel the need to investigate my camps? Can you not see the people of my bazaar are simply enjoying themselves?nnNo, of course not. There must be some sinister plot involved!
You don't look like one of my mer. What do you want?
Oh, hello there? Are you new? I'd introduce myself, but I can't seem to remember my name.
Well done, <<1>>. The Silvenar Prime is now free, and we can turn our efforts to others who need them.
Thank Y'ffre, that is over. I don't know how much more I could have channeled.
Please, no more. I... I have no more.nnJust kill me. I want to... <<1>>, is that you?nnHow... how did you find me?
Thank you  thank you for saving me! I'll make a run for the cave entrance. nnSpeak with my sister and I before you leave the caves. We must repay you for the kindness you have shown us.
I boasted to the sergeants that I was going to kill all the Gray Sail pirates and rid Malabal Tor of their menace
I heard a rumor that the Gray Sail pirates have all but been eradicated, today.
Though we may be dead, the ties to our past still remain. Perhaps it's our state of death that amplifies the pain of our restless brothers and sisters. My concerns grow daily for them.
I hope the Mayor will help us. I need to know what where my friend is. It feels important.

You gave me a scare. I thought you were a Maormer pirate. Keep your head down or they'll see us.nnI think they're looking for something. Captain Ravenil and his men must be after the Treasure of Bleaker Rock.
We heard the screams from the road and we came to investigate. This place was hit hard, <<1>>.
Where could he be? I wish I could remember his name....
This guard won't listen to me, will you?
Go on, do not worry about me. Ma'Zarman will stand watch here.
Everything you see, R'Dashun can sell to you.
I am ready to drink!nnAre you ready? Are you?
<<1>>, I would speak to you.nnI come on behalf of the king. He has a matter that requires great discretion.
The Shadowscale seek to petition me, after their betrayal? I would think it fitting to see them all ground into dust for their hubris.nnBut you are not one of them. What brings you into this, mortal?
May the spirits of the Ansei watch over you, child.
You saved me! One day, I will walk in peace on the distant shores of Tu'whacca's realm.nnYou have my thanks, traveler.
Your pardon, citizen, but I do not have time to speak with you.
Another rescue from Lei-Kai? You're a lucky one, my friend. We usually don't get to the newcomers fast enough.

Ah, there you are.nnMa'Zarman was wondering if you had gone all sneaky sneaky on me. When this one realized that the rat that ran by me was you, my curiosity took the best of me.nnGood thing too. Bad things happening out there. Very bad things.

Valaydia is dead, I assume?nnI must thank you for what you have done. Her tyranny will not be missed.nnMy apologies for deceiving you through all of this. I worried if you knew the truth, my words would fall on deaf ears.
I owe you my life. I never thought I would escape from this place.
Being trapped by the serpent's poison for days on end - it was a nightmare. One you ended. You have my thanks.
I used to live near here. A little town to northeast called The Mire. But I have no time to go visiting.nnNothing ever changes there. I'm sure they're all right.
Dar'Thid is angry at cultists for killing his friends. Blood Cat is a bad influence, he says.nnKeeba-sho misses his friends, but misses his lost profits more, yes?
Don't even talk to Idrasin... he's dishonest and a cheat! Speak to Mala!
It is dangerous for the living to enter Loriasel. I have only been within once, but that was an age ago.
Speak softly. Relazar's followers don't yet know what we've done.
I've never seen the forest as dangerous as it is these days. Y'ffre is displeased or there is something worse afoot, and I don't like being stuck here in either case.
Shh! Stop making so much noise!
Don't stare, <<1>>. I'm not so different from yourself.
You there, <<1>>! Surely you wish to test your skills and earn magnificent prizes and fame?
I can't believe I lost him! Y'ffre's sap, what if a troll eats him?
<The wolf growls and raises its hackles as it glares off down the path.>
<The wolf looks up at you expectantly.>
Be silent.nnWe are waiting for the right moment to strike.
Be silent.nnWe are waiting for the right moment to strike.
<The wolf lets out a vicious snarl at the garbage heap.>
They say we're going to attack Hissmir. For what, I wonder? They're not Archein, but they're not against us, either.

There you are - just as the Prophet predicted! He was here waiting for you, with the Nord woman Titanborn. They said you would show up, and to send you on to Wayrest to meet them.nnBut you can't go yet - there's been a theft from our Moth Chapel!
The Hissmir are obstructionists. They're too busy with their own little issues to think about the rest of us.nnI don't see why we should worry about attacking them.
A new life... a new beginning. It's exactly what I need. My past weighs on me like a boulder. I can't bear it another day.
Don't even talk to Mala! She and the other beggars are disloyal!
Forgive me for following you. I wanted to help, but... I was afraid. I am no fighter.nnJudging by the commotion I heard, you found the thief. Did you find our book as well?
Zud-Reen, one of our old ones, has gone on a fool's errand to reason with ghosts and whispers.nnI do not expect him to return alive from this tomb, but we cannot leave without knowing.
Welcome to our chapel. How may the Ancestor Moths aid you?
Do you have anything amusing to share? A joke, a story? Perhaps a song?nnWe've been here for weeks. There's nothing to do. Well, there's one thing we do. But I don't think you'd like it.

If we don't find some way of protecting ourselves the Imperial Army will sweep us away like chaff on the wind when the barrier falls, as it surely will!nnI am the only one with a plan that can possibly save us!

You're in luck, my friend. I have here some of the finest treasures this cursed place holds... and all for a reasonable price! Something for every taste.nnWait, are you that <<1>> everyone's been talking about? <<2>>, is that right?
It's <<1>>, isn't it? Your reputation precedes you. Will you help those less fortunate than yourself?
<You can smell burnt flesh and blood. This scout was tortured before being slain.>
A visitor? To see me? How fortuitous.nnPerhaps you are the one who will solve this mystery.

We really don't have much time left before the Imperial Army is upon us. The Thane keeps telling us that the barrier will keep us safe but I know better.nnI've seen the Imperial Scout camp near here. They are searching for us. They will find us soon.
I wish someone would bring me news of a dead goblin shaman.
There isn't a <<1>> standing in front of me.nnThere isn't a <<1>> standing in front of me.nnI'll just close my eyes... and... damn it, still there!
So you are the one who bypassed the barrier?
Don't worry about me, traveler.nnI have my own problems to deal with.
I have need of someone to look through some of the boxes.
I wonder what games my mistress has in store for today.
Y'ffre's blessings, <<1>>. I am Yendirwen. Are you interested in earning a bit of silver?
What do you want? I don't have anything to hide!
I don't know what all the fuss is about with the brambles. It's just some rampant overgrowth.

Where is she? She should've been back by now.nnYou haven't seen a little, fierce Bosmer girl named Exani have you? She's my daughter; sent off to scout the area with another.nnShe's never been out this long though.
We meet again, <<1>>. I am glad. Molag Bal and his servant Mannimarco tighten their net. Yet together, we persevere.nnNow. The book - "<<2>>." Have you brought it?
Speak, dog! Speak or I will slice you apart one piece at at time.nnI don't care if the Imperials catch me, but you'll wish you were dead if you even dare think of screaming.
You look different than when we last met. nnSpilled some blood since then, have you?
The fish aren't biting today. Who can blame them, eh? Trouble upstream, trouble downstream. If I were a fish, I'd hide under this bridge too.
Y'ffre's blessings, <<1>>. I am Yendirwen. Are you interested in earning a bit of silver?
You expect to get anything from me?nnHmph, you'll not get out of this alive. Dumb-witted and ignorant? Hah, if not for a moment of foolishness I wouldn't even be in this situation.
This isn't good. It isn't going to work.
It is dangerous for the living to enter Loriasel. I have only been within once, but that was an age ago.

The Huntress has gone too far and we have no choice but to take arms against her. She has captured innocent Bosmer and plans to sacrifice their lives to create an army of Risen loyal to her. With this force she will be able to sweep all foes aside.
Go away, I will only speak to a <<1>> or greater.
I've got a job. It's members only.
No one gets through this door without my permission.

This Dunmer's throat was slit. The flesh around the wound has turned black and started to decay at a far more rapid pace than the rest of his body. It looks like only a matter of time before the decay separates the head entirely.
Move along. We're waiting to see S'rashi, not you.
Do you seek enlightenment? I offer training in Mages Guild techniques and a few goods to members who qualify.
Praise Azura! We're desperate. I beg you. The Abbey's under attack! They're trying to burn the place down!

This Dunmer was stabbed in the heart. The fatal wound has decayed rapidly, leaving behind a crater of blackened, dead flesh where his chest once was. The discoloration is spreading outward toward the arms, neck, and torso.

This Argonian suffered several blows that appear magical in nature. She has large circular wounds on her left shoulder and abdomen. It's hard to tell if the affected flesh was melted and charred, or has just severely decayed.
It is dangerous for the living to enter Loriasel. I have only been within once, but that was an age ago.

The Huntress is unmasked. We all believed in her, even worshiped her. She brought us back to this life and promised a new dawn for all Bosmer.nnNow, we see her true nature. That she would kill innocent Bosmer to create more Risen is unforgiveable.
The force of the shield is quickly fading. We need more focus crystals to put into the charge if we're to have any hopes of keeping this up.
The Huntress has gone too far this time! I can't let her continue down this path.nnThe altars must be destroyed!

I am one of The Huntress' Risen warriors, brought back from beyond death to serve her.nnSome of the Risen, like me, have decided we can no longer follow her. She plans to kill nearly everyone in Malabal Tor in her quest for power. We must stop her!

You're new to this area, aren't you?nnMaybe you'll hold no prejudice against what I have no control over and offer me aid? Something of mine has been... lost. And I'm not going to find it by myself.nnI don't have much time. Please help.
If you haven't found out yet where they're holding Miranda, please keep searching. nnI'm working up my courage to go confront the kidnappers.
The Midnight Union has taken over Farangel's Landing.nnThey're holding my wife for ransom, but I can't pay it!
You have but one more step to take, mortal. You must take your charge into the inner sanctum and put it upon its final resting place. Only then will its power be sealed.
A new life... a new beginning. It's exactly what I need. My past weighs on me like a boulder. I can't bear it another day.
I hope the Mayor will help us. I need to know what where my friend is. It feels important.
Our chapterhouse has been ravaged, and my fellow priests are all missing. I don't know what to do!nnI wish the abbot were here ....
You look competent, and I could use another competent soldier. nnWe need to show these goblins that Cumberland's Watch will never belong to them.
More visitors?nnThe cloaking shield must be fading faster than the Thane let on. This isn't good. Just another headache I have to deal with.

It's nice to finely meet you, <<1>>.nnFarah has told me about your many adventures. Surprising how even one who was raised from the dead can be so cheerful, isn't it?nnI shouldn't complain. She's been the best friend I've had since my former life.

<<1>>, I've missed you!nnIt's so nice to see you here. Of course I wish it were under better circumstances and all, but you know, a friendly conversation here and now is better than a boar mauling your face. Or... something like that.
Time is of the essence, <<1>>. What do you need?
You aren't an Imperial! What are you doing in here?
What a grave insult is this to the trees, and so to all of us.
The Midnight Union? Cowards and traitors. Snuck up on us and attacked, and a few got by into the cave.
I shouldn't have had that fish last night. That woman couldn't cook a decent meal if her life depended on it.
The crow soars upon the wind, free to go wherever he chooses. I do not.
Bah da da, Bah da da. Bubble, bubble. No more trouble!nnSwimming little fishes. Tasty little dishes.

Layliana is up there.nnShe must know how I feel. I don't care what she is. This love is true, isn't it? nnI can't think on it too long, or I'll miss my chance. I'm meant to be with her. No matter what.
I stand with Enerist against The Huntress. She cannot be allowed to slaughter her way through Malabal Tor.
I stand with Enerist against The Huntress.nnI couldn't stand it if I was responsible for helping her to kill so many innocents. She can't do it. We have to stop her!

This ring... did Thorne show you this ring?nnHe carved it himself. Did you read the inscription? "Even in death, our bonds shall grow stronger". I... I can't say no.nnNo matter what happens, we're together now. Until the end.

I'm going to travel with the Risen when they leave.nnLayliana has accepted my hand. No matter what happens, I'll be with her until the very end and I will fight anything that would do harm to my love.nnMy eyes are open. I'll not regret this.

So the rumors of the cloak failing must be true, otherwise you'd not be standing before me.nnThe Imperials must not know of this yet, or they'd already be burning through our homes.nnIt'd seem we still had some time.
My grief is too great to face alone!
The hatching will be soon. New life is such a joy to behold! I wish <<1>> could be here, but he is still traveling with the elder of our tribe.
What should I do? They are coming for me. I know it. My dreams tell me it all of the time. You... did they send you? Are you going to hurt me? Torture me? Kill me?
I have an urgent message for you!
You've ruined me! You blasted fool, you've ruined me!
You there! What is your name?
I swear, if they do not open this port soon, I'll drink every ounce of mead and wine they have.nnIf only they actually had some decent food around here, maybe I wouldn't be so damn grumpy.
If you ever want to go back to Tenmar, just let me know.nnThis boat will be leaving shortly.
I'm Lady Miranda's steward. nnWho are you, and what do you want here?
Why am I still here? Scybalum is the place to be!
Look at all of this junk! We can make a fortune here!
Whoever you are, please help me.
Greetings, noble soldier. The Maruhkati Selective welcomes you in this time of trial.

Welcome to the finest carnage you'll ever see. Welcome to Hammerdeath Arena!nnWhat thrills do you seek? Gladiatorial combat? A Grand Melee? Fighting a slavering beast alongside your friends? You'll find it all here!
I had heard that Alten Corimont was the best place to trade with the Argonians, but my stock isn't moving as fast as I thought it would. I wish I had something truly unique to offer shoppers here.
<<1>> doesn't like strangers talking to us.nnI don't much like it either. You just stay back.
<<1>> doesn't like strangers talking to us.nnI don't much like it either. You just stay back.
You must help me end this.nnHelp me end what I began, so long ago. I never meant for it to come to this.
I do not know you. Why would one not of our village repair this totem?
Have you come to see the skull?nnYou can't touch it.
Yes? Hello?nnThis garbage is ours. Get your own.
You do not belong here, Unbeliever.
We keep our own ways, stranger. Keep to yours as well, and the wind will blow gently.
You are strange to my eyes. They will not see you.
You have no business with us.nnGo. We have much planning to do before our next negotiation.
The Worm Cult has trapped Kothringi spirits. They are torturing them!
These peasants are trash. Trash! nnThe judge will believe me. He has to believe me.
I don't believe I've ever seen you at any of Hosni's parties.nnI'm sorry this one had to be your first.
Don't make eye contact with Lady Adima. nnIf she thinks you don't like her, she has the guards take you away.
A new face? Welcome, stranger!nnIsn't this the most wonderful party? Wonderful, wonderful!
What can I do for you?
Do you have any wine? We ran out of wine, and now we're all trying to find more!
<<1>> is going to get you killed.
You are living, but you are not one of the Imperials. What do you want in this cursed place?

Welcome to the best carnage you'll ever see. Welcome to Hammerdeath Arena!nnWhat thrill do you seek? Gladiatorial combat? A grand melee? Facing a massive beast alongside your friends? You'll find it all here!
A mortal walks among us. I cannot imagine what force of will has driven you this far, creature. So enlighten us. Why do you tread the dead halls of the Maruhkites?
We're the Midnight Union! The Supernals should fear us.nnInstead, they've turned our shore into their campground. The dogs.

<<1>> and <<2>> play in the filth of the Imperials. They see the garbage as a source of money.nnI have lived here a hundred years. I remember when the waters were green and the air smelled of flowers.
We will complete our mission. The Dominion reigns!
The scent of blood clings to you easily, stranger. Our Nest-Mother would approve.nnThey have not molested the shrine proper. Disturbing. Perhaps... they are not as malevolent as I first thought.
Let your eyes feast upon the wonders of the world. From the vast deserts of Alki'r, to the planes of Oblivion itself, my wares have traveled far and wide.nnAll are available. For a price, of course.
Thank you for returning the Welkynd Stone to its proper resting place.

I can't believe Larland brought me with him!nnWe're going to travel the world together. He even mentioned something about going to the most dangerous places in the woods to see if we could get lost.nnHow romantic is he?

Your friend has a certain charm about him, you know that?nnI would not have guessed I would leave my post to go on some wild adventure with an Elf such as him. Either I have lowered my standards greatly, or perhaps I am finally finding enjoyment.

Zihija must thank you for introducing me to this elf, <<1>>. Without your help, we would have never met.nnIt turns out, Larland doesn't mind fur so much. He says I am very snuggly! Very odd thing to say, yes?
Leave me alone.nnI have more pressing matters at hand.
It's my duty to guard, Count Hosni, but I'm too frightened.
How can I guard Count Hosni, when my vision is fading? I can't see.
It is dangerous for the living to enter Loriasel. I have only been within once, but that was an age ago.
Count Hosni is not present.nnAll closed up here, so move along.
