I think you must be in the wrong place.
I never thought it'd come to this. I hope the others have made it here safetly or I fear we'll have no hope of winning.

We're a bunch of fools. The whole lot of us. With the battle of Shattered Circle turning in our favor, we decided to strike while the Huntress' eyes were averted.nnClearly her gaze wasn't as blind as we hoped.
We captured a couple of those Dreamers.nnThe captain and I are taking turns interrogating them. They might not survive the process.nnYou know, that would be a damn shame.
Xuth! Luring fish out of these waters is never easy when the lines are a mess like tangled vines.
May the waters be calm for you, <<1>>.
May the waters be calm for you, <<1>>.

I... I never thought the one who valued the lives of Valenwood and brought so much hope to its people would be the one that would ultimately destroy it.nnI used to believe in her. I used to trust her. And now... now I don't know what to think.
I never thought it'd come to this. I hope the others have made it here safetly or I fear we'll have no hope of winning.
You aren't an Imperial! What are you doing in here?
There are fortunes to be found here.
There are fortunes to be found here.

You've returned safely! I... I was worried. Just for a moment of course. I mean I knew you'd be fine! It's not like we haven't been in worse, you know? You're rather powerful, you know that? And I just....nnOh my, I'm rambling again.
There's nothing better than a night of drinking  except a day of even more drinking.
My wife, Franara, wanted to move out to the country. So here we are, I guess.
I don't miss Koeglin Village one bit.
Eboth-mok has things to do. You come back another time, walker.
No one gets through this door.

<<1>>! Thank Azura you're all right. S'Rashi said you were coming here. There have been ominous rumors about Count abd-Tura's "party".nnI also didn't expect the Supernal Dreamers, so I was forced to hide here. Who is the Midnight Phantom?
The spirits are angry here. I fear for the safety of <<1>>.
New business is hard to come by with all of these protestors around town. Protestors don't buy many shoes.
What should I do? They are coming for me.
Hissmir is the best town for a tanner like me.
Have you come to see the skull?nnYou can't touch it.
A series of murders plagues Wayrest, and I have no reliable leads. nnHigh King Emeric is extremely troubled by these crimes. He expects results, and I have none to give him.
The nobles tear at the scraps like rabid dogs. There's nothing left for me here.nnI almost wish Montclair would descend upon us and finish the lot of us off.
Your name is not known to us.
Are you to be a stone dropped in the still waters of Hissmir?

Our days are coming to an end. The Huntress attempts to summon her master, the Daedric Prince Hircine, into our realm to begin the true hunt.nnAll who live in this forest would fall prey to it. Even you. We can't allow that to happen.

One of the living... how strange your presence makes me feel. I wish I could welcome you.nnInstead, I give warning. This is no place for your kind. My brothers and sisters are taken to arms. They defend this place beyond the veil of death.
Greetings, traveler. We welcome all who come seeking respite from their troubles.nnIf you are bringing a donation to our cause, I will gladly accept it.
Did my son send you, or are you just one of his feckless, doomed guests?
Keep out, you Supernal brutes! Remember what happened the last time you tried to sneak in?nnI may be old, but my stiletto is still sharp.
It's over, isn't it <<1>>? I never thought this would happen... not again. I... I can't feel her in this world anymore.nnThis is for the better... it has to be.

Our days are coming to an end. The Huntress attempts to summon her master, the Daedric Prince Hircine, into our realm to begin the true hunt.nnAll who live in this forest would fall prey to it. Even you. We can't allow that to happen.
It's... it's over?nnI didn't get enough time. There was never enough time. Why... why is this happening?
Value every second. Take in every breath. Hold the hand of a loved one, squeeze tightly, and never let go.nnBe sure you are remember to live for every moment.
Why does Layliana hold back? She's hiding something, but she refuses to tell me.nnSomething's wrong, my friend. What it is... I don't know. I just have a bad feeling.
No... this can't be happening. I can't lose her. Not like this.nn<<1>>, you have to do something! There has to be a way.nnPlease... there has to be.
<Count Hosni sleeps deeply, but looks troubled.>
My betrothed lies dead before me, but all I can feel is  relief.
Something must be done about Godrun, and soon.
I tried to protect my crew, but once the first mate sold us out, we were finished before we started fighting.nnIf I ever get my hands on that scoundrel Elvira Derre, I'll make her pay!
The Blackmaul have yet to squash you. Hah!nnDon't you think it might be better to hide somewhere safe?

Oh, no! The captain is going to keelhaul <<1>>, beat <<1>>, and make <<1>> walk the plank. And once that's done, he'll skin <<1>> alive!nnThe captain was not always this way. There's only one thing <<1>> can do.
I don't understand what's happened. Part of me feels relieved, and the rest? I can't describe it suffice to say I am overwhelmed with guilt and horror at what I must have done.
Lady Adimashe was the Omen of Blood all along. A spirit. Not real .
Is the Captain dead? Is <<1>> safe?nnThe thought of becoming a rug for the Captain's cabin has left <<1>> unable to eat or sleep.
There was great beauty and power here, once. Now, there is but ash.
You don't look like one of those necromancers. What are you doing in Hissmir?
My illusions were without peer, visions and phantasms of such detail that they would be the envy of all other mages!
They want to see fire? I'll show them fire.
In death, I can still heal the land.
I can't believe his premonition proved true!nnMy father was Gavaudon's chief constable. He was close to solving the recent murders, but he was killed before he could reveal the murderer's identity.

Welcome to the Dusklight. I'm the cook.nnThings have been so nerve-wracking lately that I've started to lose my hair. If you find a stray strand or two, it's probably mine. But I wash it quite often, so don't let it concern you.
Eggs are such delicate, precious things. Such a thin shell!
A fine weapon is an important accessory in times such as these. Feel free to examine my stock.
You'll want to talk to my husband. He handles the customers, I just keep the fire going.
If you're looking to protect yourself, I've got just what you need.
Four pigs. Four chickens. Nice, even numbers.nnEven numbers are good. Not like odd numbers.nnWouldn't you agree?
For a modest fee, the Mages Guild would be happy to teleport you across Tamriel.

Too many deaths of late. Can't dig fast enough to prepare graves for all of 'em, but it doesn't matter! The Blackmaul will kill me if I bury even a single one! So I figure, may as well get reacquainted with an old friend. The Eight know I need it.
I don't care how much loot <<1>> says we can plunder from the tombs.nnI'm not going near those holes in the ground.
Your Majesty. I humbly beg your forgiveness. My mind was poisoned, and I was not myself.nnI vow to make this up to you.
Welcome. I've been waiting for you.
I've been watching the Veiled Grotto for days. There's definitely something strange going on inside.
It's a beauty, isn't it? Been working on this sword for months. nnI think I might send it to King Emeric as a gift.
Knarstygg left the farm, but what happened to Murk-Watcher?
Thank you for helping us get revenge. I will travel along the river singing the song of the crocodile.nnI hope that will give my Xanajol some peace.
I'll try to find work.nnThere's a stonemason nearby. Maybe I can help him while I'm keeping an eye on the levee.
You're not from around here, <<1>>. What do you want?
<The body in the water appears to be a Supernal Dreamer. It seems someone was using this dock as a dropoff to supply weapons to the Supernal Dreamers.>
Flesh is so soft, so easily shredded. I can still feel the rake of their claws.nnWhy did my brother ignore my warnings? Does he feel the same pain I do?
You will pay for your interference, dog! My master will avenge me.
You've got to help me! The Murtag Clan is holding my family hostage to force me fight. If I don't report back, they'll hurt them!
It is about time we stopped running from these Imperials, yes?
It is about time we stopped running from these Imperials, yes?
It is about time we stopped running from these Imperials, yes?
Wait! Don't kill me, I won't sound any alarms! I can help you!
Y'ffre's blessings, <<1>>. No one wants to admit it, but we surely need it.
Y'ffre's blessings, <<1>>. No one wants to admit it, but we surely need it.
Ah, are you part of the emissary's retinue? King Ranser is quite busy presently, but I assure you, all will be seen as promptly as possible.
I'm just checking the lock to make sure it's still safe. You can never be too sure.nnDid you lock your door? I think it's time for you to check it. If it's not locked, you aren't safe.
I'll do what I can to help you against the Omen.
Please, release my bindings.nnWe've got to liberate my plantation from these Blackmaul fiends!
I wouldn't take another step, friend. Evermore is a city filled with plague.

As you examine the body, burn marks are scorched upon the skin from head to toe. Only magic or a creature of flame would be capable of dealing wounds of this magnitude.nnNear the corpses' hand rests a slightly burnt note and a tarnished silver ring.
You're not here for food, are you? Our rations are running out.
We need to get these defenses repaired before the ogres attack them  again.
We've got to hold this position! If we lose it, we'll never push the ogres out.
I apologize for not getting up. I've been  ill for some time now. If you need anything, please talk to my husband, Karnosis.nnWait. Something is not right.
It is here. I know it is.nnI must find it. Give me a moment.
What are you looking at? It's not like they're using this stuff anymore.
You've done what I thought no mortal could accomplish.
You've done what I thought no mortal could accomplish.
<This cat's body has been mutilated and completed drained of blood.>nn<There's no sign of <<1>>.>

Can you help me? Someone has to drive these Daedra away from the lighthouse. They doused the signal fire at the top. They want the passing ships to crash!nnOnce they get tired of looting ships, they're going to attack Koeglin Village!

All I hear outside is Montclair this and Montclair that! The Baron has been a true friend to the people of Rivenspire, and I'm sure he has a perfectly good reason for raising arms against the other nobles.

My aunt has an opinion about everything. She's especially passionate about politics.nnBut she makes a mighty fine pie, though. So I sit here and listen, letting the wonderful aromas coming from her cooking fire fill me with happy thoughts.
Hungry? I've got the freshest goods this side of the Darguard Ridge. That's not saying much, but you get the idea.
<<1>> suspected that I was behind his recent problems. When he saw the crew making a break for it, he grabbed me and dragged me down here.nnMake sure they get away. That's all I ask.
O intrepid traveler! Heed my words before you climb this hill.
That scheming fetcher that backstabbing f'lah! I'll skin him with my bare hands. No one backs out of a deal with me.
What are you doing here? How'd you get this far into the cave?
If you wish to kill me, do so now.nnDo not make me suffer like an animal waiting for slaughter.
No one's been in here since the Daedra appeared. Will you help me, stranger? Will you help this restless spirit find peace?
<Most of the bones have been torn from the corpse, leaving it a bloody mess of flesh.>
It's good to be free at last. Thank you, Empty One.
I'm in no mood to suffer strangers, y'see?nnWhatever you want, say it quick before I think to run you off this dock.
Sweet release! I am unbound!nnThank you, stranger. You have my eternal gratitude.
If you're the inspector <<1>> sent, <<2>> would like to speak with you.

This one not so tasty! Giddy likes them fresh. This one old. Not so fresh.nnSkin like soggy branches, too. Not crispy! Not like scamp skin ... delicious, crispy scamp skin. Ooh .... Better than bacon, it is!
After all the gold I've spent here, you'd think these backwater merchants would be more grateful. No patience whatsoever. I miss city life. I miss Wayrest.nnBy the way, have you seen Sir Higgins?
Sometimes, a true knight must undertake a mission that requires reading books rather than slaying monsters. Such is what I asked of you. nnDid you learn anything in the library?
The forge is closed, especially to strangers.nnThe door is over there.
Outsider - what are you doing here? Come to serve your Daedric overlords?
Welcome to the Sleepy Sailor. As long as you behave yourself, you're welcome to drink yourself into a stupor.
<This man looks like he put up quite a fight before the slavers killed him. He's gripping a letter in his lifeless hand.>

Darima told me you spoke to Sir Hughes about Dame Falhut. Thank you.nnYou don't know what a relief it is to have her here. I am an outsider in Alcaire Castle, with no one I can fully trust. Sometimes, I even wonder if I can trust the duke.
What we became, what we did ... I couldn't stand it. I ran. I tried to stop them, but they were too strong. nnHelp me end this nightmare.
Have you seen my son? He's been missing four days now.nnThere are bad people everywhere right now. Even people in Koeglin can't be trusted.
Shh! Just keep moving. I'm spying on the slavers.
Who are you? What do you want?nnI don't like strangers in my home  especially in times like these!
Help me! My family is being held hostage.nnIf I don't report back to Clan Murtag soon, my family is going to get hurt.
I have no business with you. Come back when you're proven yourself.
I got away; others, not so lucky.
We could hear your fight from here, <<1>>.nnI take it Dame Falhut is dead. What happened?
You shouldn't be here. Sir Hughes sent you here to die!
<This body is still warm to the touch. The blade in its back bears the sigil of the Knights of the Flame. This weapon obviously belonged to Sir Hughes.>
Why would someone do this? Where were the Knights of the Flame? Why weren't they protecting my wife?nnThere must be something  anything  that will explain this. Search the castle!
We don't like strangers around here. There's too many of you, if you ask me.
What do you want? Do I need to call the constable? Get away from me!
Our ship foundered in the dark, and now these filthy pirates plan to sell us as slaves.nnPlease help us! Half the crew and our captain are in chains!

Good morrow to you, fair person! Please, allow me to introduce myself. My name is <<1>>, wandering knight and hero extraordinaire.nnCan I just say what a pleasure it is to have a bit of genial company once again? Praise the Eight!

Survivors of the Hinault Farm massacre have been wandering in, but there are still more of our soldiers out there.nnLieutenant Fairfax and his unit have yet to return. I hope they found a defensible position to hold up in.
Help me! You've got to help me!
When the slavers show up for another attack, they'll be in for a nasty surprise.
This ship is nothing but trouble.
Did you find the medicine? One of the wounded is fading fast!
This ship is nothing but trouble.
Halt! Identify yourself! Everyone must tell me. Tell me who you are. Identify yourself.
The constable has lost his mind.

The items you hold could only mean you've read the ritual book. You are foolish to follow this path, just as I was. Do not give in to curiosity.nnMake no mistake. The ritual worked, but not in the way I expected.
Welcome to my new establishment!nnWait a minute. I know you.
You walk among the living, yet you speak to the dead. I've heard only the winds of these caves for so long.nnCould you be here to help?
Inside those walls, my duchess continues to attempt diplomacy. Outside? They're burning and pillaging their way along our coasts.nnI've had enough. The time to talk is over.
Honor and faith. These hold the Covenant together. Keep them always in your heart, warrior.
Too busy, soldier. See Jeggord or Dar-Liurz.
Have you come to authorize release of our cargo? The Captain wants to talk to you. She's waiting in her cabin.
Go away! No one asked you to be here.
I didn't see anything! Don't let anyone tell you anything different!
Koeglin Village has been a lot more helpful since you proved our intent. Since we've already had a run-in with the slavers, I've agreed to do what I can to help the village.
You don't have any skooma to spare, do you? No? nnThat's all right. I've never tried it before. I was just  curious.
If you were planning on visiting Dorrell Manor, you should rethink your plans, friend.
Work hard. Do not stop for idle chatter.
Don't know why you're here, but I know you'll leave soon.
All I ask is rain and sun for my crops. nnIf any blight should come, it should fall on those Nords.
You can barely get from the town to the farms without risking your life. nnI'm sure the duchess has her reasons for negotiating with those wretches, but I'd rather see them struck down.
Welcome to Northpoint, <<1>>. Be cautious as we deal with our little  Ebonheart problem.
You'll need quite a lot of bag space to carry all this beautiful equipment. As for the fee, well, it's contractually (and programmatically) obligated of me.
Another day in the forge. Another set of armor smashed in the arena. Blood and guts and bone.nnThe life of a smith is glorious!

Chatter, clatter goes their teeth. Slither, slather goes their tail.nnThey watch us through the cracks in things.
Who are you? What business do you have in the warehouse?
Get me out. Get me out of here!
Until our business with Clan Murtag is finished, I'm Godrun's shadow.nnWe've got to protect our interests.

Tell me you don't come bringing more bad tidings. I've already heard about the slavers on the shore and the cultists in the hills.nnI don't mean to be rude, but I have enough concerns. It's probably better if you speak to Sir Hughes.

Our Duchess, Lady Lakana, knows that you speak with the Knights of the Flame. She also knows that you are an outsider. A traveler who is unaware of the true nature of what goes on behind these walls.nnYou should know, not all is as it seems.
Another day in the forge. Another set of armor smashed in the arena. Blood and guts and bone.nnThe life of a smith is glorious!

Another day in the forge. Another set of armor smashed in the arena. Blood and guts and bone.nnThe life of a smith is glorious!

I hope you will forgive us for not offering a more friendly welcome. The affairs of the region weigh heavily on my husband's shoulders.nnThere are also concerns about security here in the castle. You really should speak with Sir Hughes.

Welcome to Alcaire Castle, visitor.nnI apologize beforehand if I'm a little blunt this morning. The duke and I have had a recent  disagreement, and I'm still attempting to clear my mind of distractions.
Something must be done about Godrun, and soon.
Step right up and see the spectacle. Don't know if she's innocent or guilty, but it's good for business.nnSee anything you like?
For a modest fee, the Mages Guild would be happy to teleport you across Tamriel.
Shela ... oh, Shela ....nnWhy did you leave me? Why did you break my heart?
I didn't know that being a Northpoint Guard would be so much work. I miss my little home in Fell's Run.
All day long, I strike metal for scales and strapping.
Yes? Tell me, what do you want? I'm a busy man, you know.
I glad to not be in cave now.
I didn't see anything! Don't let anyone tell you anything different!
Didn't I see you talking to those traitors?
You! You're an agent of the duchess, are you not?nnThe Nords are marching. You have to warn her!
Those who seek wisdom and observe the law will find peace in Julianos.
Always be open and true to love and the beauty it brings.
Honor the spirits, both living and dead.
May Zenithar grant you prosperity in all your honest ventures.
May Stendarr grant you clarity in your most trying of times.
Gods! You scared me - I thought you were one of them.nnBut no, I can see it in your eyes. You're normal. You're not like they are. You're not gone.
Thank you for helping me. I only wish my sisters were as fortunate.
I'm always willing to hear from the citizens of Northpoint. It's gotten harder to hold court as of late, but I haven't forgotten my duties to the people.nnWhat can I do for you, my friend?
I can't believe it - you came back. I feared you would lose your mind in there like the rest. But you didn't. You freed them from that madness, didn't you?
I keep hoping all of this is one long nightmare.
I'm not afraid of dying. But I am afraid of vampires!
Everyone's dead.nnBy the Divines, what has Montclair done?
Everyone's dead.nnBy the Divines, what has Montclair done?
Be wary. We don't know what we're up against.

I don't trust Verandis as far as I could accurately spit a rat. And despite what you might have heard, that's not actually very far.
Apprentice crafting components are my stock and trade.
Shhh! If you make too much noise, the cats will hear you.
Shhhh! I didn't know there were so many sabre cats about.
I fear my brothers will be trapped like this forever. Herd Mother protect them!
My armor is the best protection money can buy.nnIf this isn't enough for you, I suggest buying a castle instead.
If you wish, you may purchase surplus runecrafting supplies from the Mages Guild.
The trick to sturdy gear is tight stitching. As I always say: stitch the sleeve, not the arm!

I knew the days of the Daggerfall Covenant were numbered.
Cruel death ... Kin of my kin not rest easy. Help him.
If this bloodfiend plague isn't controlled, it could mean the end of Rivenspire.
It takes much more than simple fabric to make a tailored masterpiece. A true clothier needs what I provide.
I have all that the Adept Outfitter needs.
I love the mix and mingle of alchemical concoctions. That's why I got into the business!
Yes, I am Shornhelm's most prominent enchanter. If you have enchanting needs, I can probably fulfill them. Feel free to examine my stock.

Hold, stranger  this is Hammerdeath Arena. It's run by a gang called the Midnight Union, and they've taken to capturing travelers and forcing them to fight to the death. nnYou might want to go another way.
What's this? Another Midnignt Union lout come to torment us?nnWhy can't you just leave us alone?
Please help me! They've taken my husband. They'll kill him! I know they will!
For a modest fee, the Mages Guild would be happy to teleport you across Tamriel.
Something must be done about Godrun, and soon.
Thank the ancestors you found us! Are you the one the abbot sent? The newfound friend of the order?
You! Did Sir Hughes send you to kill me?
Curse the Midnight Union! They're nothing but murderous thieves!nnThey killed my brothers and left me here to suffer.
Most of my provisions are needed for the soldiers. But I do have some things I can trade, if you've the coin.
Heavens above, you found us! How did you find your way here, <<1>>?
Welcome to Gudrun's Retreat, <<1>>.nnNow, I'm curious - why in Shor's name did you bring a Dremora Kynval here?
This camp is all that remains of my regiment.
This regiment was hit hard by Montclair's forces. I'm holding them together as best I can.
Who's this? Another Midnight Union thug? nnTell you what: leave us alone, and maybe we'll put on a good show for you.
More than three quarters of our regiment is lost, dead or injured.nnI hope <<1>> doesn't lose his command over this. There's no way he could have known what would happen.
Welcome to the bank of Wayrest. In times of trouble, you should take comfort knowing that we'll keep your money safe.
I have a war to direct, soldier. Speak with the others if you need orders.
Every day my future becomes more and more bleak. My sister ran off to Cyrodiil so long ago, I can barely remember her  and my brother? He's dead set on being a bandit. A bandit! My own brother!

You've collected two of the Ansei Wards, but <<1>> wields the remaining blade. Even now, she is preparing her ceremony in a magically sealed vault within the necropolis. nnWe must stop <<1>> before the undead overrun Alik'r!
<This Breton hasn't been dead very long. His body is still warm.>
Welcome, friend. You can't get better fruits or vegetables anywhere in Daggerfall. I guarantee it!
Flowers for sale!  A posy to gain a sweetheart's favor, perhaps?
Interested in a set of new clothes? Something in silk, perhaps? No one ever leaves my shop empty handed.
I'm busy. Can't you see I'm drinking here?
Unless this is about cargo, I can't talk right now. I'm extremely busy.
Welcome to my court. What brings you into our presence this day?
Ugh. Who are you? What happened?
My wound itches, but they told me not to scratch.
What're you doing back here? Come to give me some coin?

While the duchess attempts diplomacy, the Gripdjur Nords burn and pillage their way along our coasts. War is inevitable, but until it starts, our hands are tied.nnI fear the people will have lost faith by then.
Retrieve the Ansei Ward from the body of <<1>>.
For a modest fee, the Mages Guild is willing to teleport you across Tamriel.
<<1>> has already started her ritual. You'll have to hurry.
You'll find <<1>> in the next chamber. She's already begun raising the consecrated dead of the Motalion Necropolis.nnWe must recover the Ansei Ward from her before it's too late!
Good news! Strong fermented drinks are acceptable within the Green Pact's rules! nnBring on the ale!
Hail, citizen. Will you lend your aid to the war effort?
I am at your mercy, mortal. Before you turn away, listen for a spell. Perhaps we can come to a mutually beneficial arrangement.
Chatter, clatter goes their teeth. Slither, slather goes their tail.nnThey watch us through the cracks in things.
I'm glad the guards showed up when they did! Those bandits would've killed me!
I'm a little busy. Red Rook bandits are holding hostages at a house down the lane.
We almost had him. Catch him before he reaches the King!
The spirit of the Wyrd weeps, for something drives her children mad. nnI fear for the innocents in this village.
A caution, my friend. If you're following this road, know that Deleyn's Mill is lost!
My executioner? You couldn't lift the axe, let alone deal with all the blood.
Thanks again for your help with the Bloodthorn. It was careless of me to get captured. nnNow, shall we straighten out this gloomy town of Aldcroft?
<The pig devours a huge chunk of the strange, thorny vine.>
<The pig pauses eating long enough to look up at you with tender affection before going back to its meal.>
Thieves! Daggerfall is full of them! They steal anything that's not nailed down!nnThey even stole my livestock.
Welcome to the Rosy Lion, friend. Have a seat and I'll pour you a mug of something strong.

I've no time to answer questions. Whether the noble houses will be patient is the least of my worries.nnWe only have a brief opportunity, so we must attack. Our enemies grow stronger with each passing moment.
Bandits are always trouble in the woods. Watch yourself if you leave Daggerfall from this gate.
Ha! Stupid monsters! Nothing gets past Mighty Marie! Best saw in all the land!nnAs long as she spins, the mill will be safe.
Did you hear? Such terrible news from the Mill.
My husband says we're safe in here. I hope he's right, but I think he gives this stupid saw blade too much credit.

She ... she was just picking flowers. Kailey, my beautiful, beautiful wife. She wouldn't harm a thing. She cared for the forest! Why would those creatures harm her?nnI'll not leave her side. I'll not let those creatures desecrate her body.
<This is the corpse of the man from upstairs at the inn. Apparently, his employers weren't happy with his loose talk.>
Right, so here's how we capture a werewolf. You fight the beast and keep it busy. Meanwhile I cast the spell that entraps it. nnJust do your part and leave the magic to me. I'm an expert.
I'm tired of defending this backwater. There's work to be done in Camlorn and  oh, sorry. I thought you were one of my soldiers.
Why does the forest attack us? It makes no sense.
Soon there'll be nothing left in Deleyn's Mill worth saving. If not for Bernard's quick thinking and the arrival of the Wyrd Sisters, we would have all died back there!
Angof the Gravesinger has imprisoned us and we are cut off from the Wyrd. You must set the Guardians free.
Excuse me! <<1>> has asked to see you. He's inside the inn.

Who are you to nonchalantly walk through flames and forest? You smell of the city of stone.nnHave you come to cleave our forest? Rip up our soil? Haven't the spirits already been enraged enough by your kind?
Why are you in my house? You're not here to take advantage of a beautiful woman during this mess? I have stabbed others before, I'll have no problem stabbing you as well!
<<1>>, <<2>>, and <<3>> wield the Ansei Wards. Even now, <<1>> prepares her ceremony in a magically sealed vault within the necropolis. nnWe must stop her before the undead overrun Alik'r!

You've collected one of the Ansei Wards, but <<1>> and <<2>> wield the remaining two. Even now, <<1>> prepares her ceremony in a magically sealed crypt within the necropolis. nnWe must stop her before Alik'r is overrun by the dead!

You've collected one of the Ansei Wards, but <<1>> and <<2>> wield the remaining two. Even now, <<1>> prepares her ceremony in a magically sealed crypt within the necropolis. nnWe must stop her before the dead overrun Alik'r!
Hurry! He's trapped in the south tower.
You captured one. Good work. nnNow for the ritual.
Could you help me? I'm next. I know I'm going to be next.
There must be something in the air. I've never seen the watch so busy.
<This beggar was savagely mauled. Deep slashes appear to have been made by large, sharp claws.>
Please, you must help me. I don't want to die. I'm not ready to leave this world!nnThose creatures out there ... they tore those poor people apart. There's ... there's nothing left of them.
It was huge! Went right into the river after it struck down poor Guillaume.
<This man's spine was twisted several times before he died. The attacker must have been incredibly strong.>
Get out of here! It'll kill you, too!
All I saw was fur and fangs! It killed that one in the alley, too!
It seems like the poor were made to suffer. I wish I had been born into a family of wealth and means.
The fire! Put out the fire! It's so hot!
The fire! Put out the fire! It's so hot!
We supply the Lion Guard with whatever arcane gear they may need.nnBut we don't have an exclusive arrangement, so if you need something, just ask.
Trust me, you don't want to sound like a child's rattle when you're trying to sneak around. nnYou want my leathersstrong enough to turn a blade yet silent as a whisper.
What a rousing speech! Makes you want to run out and join the Lion Guard!
You don't look like you belong on the docks, friend. It can get kind of rough down here.
Welcome, friend. I don't care what you may have heard, but I sell nothing but the best light armor that your gold can buy.
I'm telling you, what with werewolves and cultists on every corner, you can't trust an inferior weapon to do the job.
You want it sharp? You want it strong? You want it pointy? Well, you've come to the right place!nnSwords and daggers. Two handers and single-hand grips. I've got just what you need.
If you want state of the art protection, then you want to encase yourself in heavy metal armor.nnNothing gets through my armor. Arrows, axes, blades, my armor laughs at it all. Laughs, I tell you!

Times are tough, but people have to eat, right? There's barely enough for the residents, what with the influx of refugees and all.nnStill, if you have the gold, you're welcome to purchase whatever I have left.
Yes I know  I am a Bosmer. I am also a Smith.  So stop staring and tell me what you want.
I have settngs, inks and everything needful to craft items most arcane.
I stock the finest tools and supplies for runecrafters.
Welcome to my shop. What can I help you with?
Forget those idiots selling their rusty swords and shaft rotted axes. Make your own.
You want something? Well I got something. If what I got and want you want are the same, we can trade.
I command the Lion Guard forces in southern Glenumbra.nnYou must be curious about the proud history of the Lion Guard.
I apologizeto all of you. I thought I could fight this off. I was wrong.

I did not lose hope that someone would come to our rescue. These fiends would not listen to reason. They are mindless in their dedication to their mad lord.nnLet us flee from this place while there is still time!
You know, it's difficult to take notes, fight, and tell you about the Lion Guard all at once.
You seek the inner mysteries of alchemy?nnAllow me to lead the way.
Enchantment!nnMy favorite scholarly pursuit. I have many rivals, but none can compete with the master enchanter!

The Wards are restored and so are we. We can again maintain vigil over the living and the dead, and ensure that both adhere to the divine laws of Tu'whacca.nnYour role in this has not gone unnoticed, young one.
The Nords have been blocking shipments for weeks, but there's a barrel of ale or two left for my best customers.
Looks like we're in time. The Duke hasn't transformed yet, but he's very close. nnIf you're sure about this, you'd better act now.
Don't hassle the dock workers. They have plenty of work to do and no time for chit-chat.
If you've got a problem, you can wait, or you can talk to my associate.nnI suggest you wait  or leave.
I should never have suggested fleeing to Aldcroft. Brilliant idea, LeBlanc. nnNow they're gone. All the women in our group. Kidnapped by cultists and dragged off into the fen.
You startled me. I thought you were one of those awful Bloodthorn people!
I'm no warrior. I'm a chandler. Candles don't make very good weapons, you know.
I guess we lucked out when you came by. Thank you, <<1>>.
Help! Free us before the hags come! nnWe were traded like so many beads and glass trinkets. How degrading!
Break the stone! Just hit it with your weapon and smash it to bits!nnQuickly, before that horrible hag returns.
Please, please! You must set me free.nnSwing your weapon and break the stone!
Swing your weapon at the floating stone and set us loose. Then go kill all the bastards that did this.
Please, you must help me. I don't want to die. I'm not ready to leave this world!nnThose creatures out there ... they tore those poor people apart. There's ... there's nothing left of them.
We lost a lot of good people today, and for what?nnWhy would Montclair do this? Revenge? Lust for power?
By Stendarr, I thought we'd have this figured out by now. We're supposed to be the Daggers' gadgeteers, after all.nnI never knew harpies could be so tricky.

Did Lord Diel send you? Well, there's nothing new to report, except that my brother is an idiot.nnArmel placed dozens of traps and he just realized something. Harpies don't walk! Now we're trying to figure out how to salvage the situation.

You're going to help me find the rest of the Daggers? Hmm. I'm not sure you're Dagger material.nnYour hands look kind of soft and delicate. Like you've never beaten anything into submission with your own two fists before.
Thank Mara! Rescue!nnOne of these crazy birds thinks I'm a hatchling. It keeps trying to feed me dead bodies!
I can't do this! I haven't found a single harpy egg, and all around me, enraged harpies are mauling people.nnI'm going back to camp before I'm next!
What are you doing back here?
Tu'whacca says this is good. He says all is as it should be, and you have done well .nnI agree with Tu'whacca. I have enjoyed walking the sands with you.
Balance is restored. The dead can rest. The living can thrive. And we can return to our vigil.
Ah, another one. Here to work with the great Lord Diel, no doubt.nnI'm renowned throughout Glenumbra, you know.
Stendarr's Mercy! If you won't save us, at least put us out of our misery!
Don't worry, no one will get past us, not as long as we draw breath!
No matter how much I study, I still have more to learn.
Arcane knowledge is secret knowledge, but my bargains are clear and forthright! Take a look at what I'm offering today.
I think all this talk of war will affect trade. I must shore up my investments accordingly.
Sorry. I was just thinking. I need to walk through the alleys, but I'm afraid of the back-alley murderer.
My family has lived in this city for many generations. This statue depicts my great-great-great-grandfather, Ducal.
The ghosts of the Alessian army still haunt this place. nnIt's been an age since the Battle of Glenumbra Moors raged here, yet the spirits linger.
Can't you see I'm miserable? Leave me to my pain.
When food is this good, life is great!
Thank the Divines you've come! I thought I was to die in that cage!nnWe must leave quickly. I've no wish to tarry in this cursed place!
It might be unseemly for a woman of noble birth to be drawn to the forge, but I can't help myself.nnI find all the muscles and sweating to be  so interesting.
<<1>> has asked me to clean the southern rain catcher.nnCan you protect me while I work?
Pay no attention to my little friend here. He has a weakness for tall tales. The taller, the better, I'm afraid. nnIt's all rubbish, of course.
Bhagrun here claimed that the threat that Faolchu poses has been greatly exaggerated. nnPoor fool wouldn't know a moth from a mammoth.
You made it here at last, <<1>>, as was foreseen. I'm glad I was here to meet you.nnYou are the key to defeating the Withered Hand, but to do so completely, you must defeat them in Satakalaam.
There's no problem a few mugs of ale can't fix. And this sweet roll is delicious!
Have you ever met a Wyrd sister? I think it might be fun to run around in the forest with the nature witches. At least for a little while.
I'm writing a letter to my family back in Hammerfell. I have so much to tell them about!
Pay no attention to my little friend here. He has a weakness for tall tales. The taller, the better, I'm afraid. nnIt's all rubbish, of course.
Bhagrun here claimed that the threat that Faolchu poses has been greatly exaggerated. nnPoor fool wouldn't know a moth from a mammoth.
Is there something I can help you with?nnHis lordship keeps me very busy, you know.
This is a good place to make a quick profit.
I'm cold, I'm hungry, and I don't have any gold to my name.nnBut at least I'm in Daggerfall.
A tidy shop is a profitable shop, my mother always told me.nnIf you've got anything to trade, I'll give you a fair price.
My horses are beauties! Look how they hold their heads up high.nnI treat my horses well, whether they belong to me or if they just happen to rent a stall in my stables.
Someday, my husband's ship will return. Until then, I'll come here every day to watch the harbor.
I won't complain. I've got too much work to do.
No matter how bad things get, as long as I can keep the flowers growing, I have hope for the future.
I can never decide. The market has so many choices.
It seems like I'm always working.
We just had major repairs done on the house and I'm checking the work.
Keep an eye on your gold. I was robbed and now I'm sleeping in the street.
I assume you have my eggs? I really want to  er  get on with my studies. Yes, that's what I told you. Studies, right?
I've had it! No disgusting old swamp woman is going to steal my youth!

You helped me before. I'm hoping you can help me with one more thing  revenge!nnAsk <<1>> why the harpies are in such a state and attacking everyone. He'll claim ignorance. That's a lie. Lord Diel is responsible for all this!
I can't believe we ever agreed to this. What were we thinking? Can we really be that stupid?
Greetings, <<1>>. I can send you through the roots of the world to our nearby enclave within the northern bog if you wish.
Well met, <<1>>. How can I be of assistance?
<<1>> was furious at me for returning without any harpy eggs.
What a disaster. Why did we try to be heroes?
Stranger, beware! My captor is a jealous and suspicious man. He'll kill anyone who comes to this island.nnHe musn't see you speaking to me!
Oh, Sonia! This life is nothing without you. All I have left is sitting and waiting for death to reunite us.
I foresaw this meeting. nnYour arrival was written in the stones and the sky.

Hail, stranger! Welcome to Daggerfall. Have you come to aid in defense of this great Alliance against the unwashed hordes that seek to see us dead? Will you do your part to keep the Ebonheart Pack and the Aldmeri Dominion from killing us all?
<This Orc hasn't been dead for very long.>
Eh? What do you want with this old Huntmaster?
Oh, my sweet wife, my sweet Sonia! This life is nothing without you.nnAll I have left is sitting and waiting for death to reunite us.
Don't worry, <<1>>. I'll take care of him. I always have, and I always will.nnThank you for freeing me ... for freeing us both.
My poor Poppa, what will I do without you? Why would they kill a defenseless old man?
Angof's corruption defeated us. But never again, thanks to you.
The stench of Angof's magic endures. It fouls the air with its wretched odor.
Angof's foul influence pollutes the rivers and streams. We must end this corruption now.

Zeht's Tears! I am at my wit's end. We woke early this morning to the sound of screaming horses and roaring Daedra!nnMy father has a plan to retake the stables, but I fear I'm not up to the task. Can you help me, O benevolent stranger?
Welcome to Gudrun's Retreat, <<1>>.nnNow, I'm curious - why in Shor's name did you bring a Dremora Kynval here?
We all thought we were going to die when the Daedra attacked <<1>>! Thank Zeht for Master  <<2>>. He saved us all! nnNow we're trying to save his family's legacy. Will you help us?
We expected to find fresh mounts here. Instead, we found Daedra rampaging all over the stables.nnI sent a patrol inside already, but I need the rest to protect the horses and stablehands.
<This corpse has been cut multiple times by a blade and mangled beyond recognition.>
I had a terrible dream. It was very  bloody.
I felt so  furry. And mean. Why was I so mean?
The shard won't be yours. It can't be. Angof won't get it. Faolchu won't get it. No one will get it.nnWho are you? You'll not take my shard!
This shard has to be protected. It has to be. They'll have to take it from my dead hands. Not letting go. Never letting go!
We've got to get the Daedra under control!nnYou look like you can handle yourself. Can you lend us a hand?
You saved my husband. I can't thank you enough for that. nnI'm truly in your debt.
I was so worried about Father! How brave you were to rush in there and save him.

The earth cries. The wind's lullaby is silenced. The soil in which we stand upon suffers. This is just the first of what will happen when nature rebels against us.nnThe innocents who call this place home are caught in that very rebellion.
I'm sorry. I should have told you. I thought I could fight it off.nnI was wrong.

The Withered Hand summoned a Dremora Kynreeve to negotiate a pact for the destruction of Aswala Stables. The Dremora betrayed them and bound them with dark magic.nnNow the Daedric portal draws its power from the life force of the trapped occultists.
I can't thank you enough. You have saved my husband and you're well on the way to becoming Camlorn's savior.nnWe are truly in your debt.
I was so worried about Father. How brave and courageous you were to save him.
<The portal appears to be feeding off of the lifeforce of the trapped men.>
<<1>> does not like this desert where the dead crawl out of the ground.nnThey buy nothing, scare her customers, and want to bite her tail. <<1>> dislikes all of these things!
I've come to pay the debt I owe to my ancestors. Lead on. I'll give what aid I can.
He's in agony! Do something! Help him!
What's happening to Father? This is so horrible.
I should never have suggested fleeing to Aldcroft. Brilliant idea, LeBlanc. nnGone. All the women in our group. Kidnapped by cultists and dragged off into the Fens.
We're very lucky you came along. Thank you.
This was a disaster. Why did we try to be heroes?
Greetings, traveler. I am <<1>> of the Order of the Ancestor Moth.nnIs there something I can help you with?
Shove off. Can't you see I'm busy here?
<This corpse still has bits of shell still on its hands. Obadal must have tried to steal harpy eggs.>
The Daedra attacked in the night. The horses' screams were deafening.nnWithout the Lion Guard, we would never have survived.
I thought Poppa was nearby, but nownothing. nnDo you have his pipe? I just want to hold on to him, just a little longer.

Husayn doesn't want anyone to get killed, but you're right. If this doorway to the past is the answer to defeating Faolchu... then we must open it!nnUse the sword as a focus in the battlesite. We'll see if we can open up that doorway again.
That's it. I've had it. I'm done with this bog. It's like looking for a needle in a muddy haystack!
We should never have left Camlorn. This bog is worse than the werewolves.
Shouldn't have left Camlorn. There were werewolves, but at least we were all in one piece!
I'm wet, I'm muddy, and I'm totally miserable. This was the worst idea ever!
We should never have left Camlorn. This bog is worse than the werewolves.
<<1>>! It is great to see you again! I'm a guard now, how about that?
Stranger, a word. You look like the courageous type. I have an opportunity. nnYou're sober, aren't you? Good. Are you interested in taking on a contract?
Shhh! Don't move. There are harpies all around!

The Daedra struck from the heart of Oblivion, aided by the cowardly Withered Hand. They rushed us in the dead of night. Only my father's leadership kept us alive. nnNow we must enact his plan to drive those beasts away, or <<1>> will be no more!
Ah, someone has finally arrived. My father sent me to this godsforsaken beach to round up some layabouts. I think he hates me. nnInterested in taking on a contract?

I'm sorry. I need something new to keep me occupied, but I can't decide between the martial arts or the culinary arts.nnMayhem or marinades? Fencing or fricasee? Bloodshed or blood pudding? It's a tough choice.
I remember this place. It all started here, on the day of the final battle. nnWe gave up everything to kill Faolchu. I'll be damned if I just let him come back to life and curse the world again.
I miss Orsinium something awful. I'm going to go back there one of these days. Take a ride on one of those ships and sail back home.nnOne of these days.
Captain! We were worried you might have not made it. We've been looking all over for you.nnWe're about to make the final push against Faolchu's forces. We'll need every sword we can get.
Why do you linger while Parmion rallies the troops for the final assault? You're his best officer and our noblest knight.
It's been so long since I've seen Leon. It's good just to spend some time with him.nnThank you for all you've done for us.

I can feel the anger of the wraiths emanating from my sword. You've made the town safe for the living, but damned the innocents of Westtry.nnBut Leon is to blame for this, not you. I can't bear to speak to him yet. You tell him of his fate.
The lamentations of Westtry's dead have been silenced. Now I can finally tell Rosalind how sorry I am.nnThank you, traveler.
It's good to have Rosalind back, but she won't speak to me. What happened out there?
There you are, my knight. Did you recover the orders?
Quiet. I have a long-winded speech to give.
There were too many of them. They tore us apart . nnCaptain, I have bad news. Commander Parmion is dead.
Do you need my assistance, sir?
What a disaster! I should have suspected a trap. And now Commander Parmion's dead. nnWhat about Faolchu?
What can I do for you?
Come, step forward. Let me get the measure of you, friend. It allows me to serve you better. Plus, I like to get to know as many of our members as I can.
Welcome back. Are you all right? Were you successful? nnWhy  why are you staring at me?
We can't resist much longer. Soon we'll be forced to answer their call.
Welcome back. Are you all right? Were you successful? nnWhy  why are you staring at me like that?
It's good to have you back. nnSaravith was just starting to babble about time travel magic. But here you are, gender unchanged. As usual, her theories prove to be wildly inaccurate.
The Withered Hand attacked us in the night. I fear they have slain all my brothers and sisters.nnWe have failed in our sacred duty to protect this foul ground from the dark arts.
You're back. And just in time. But the celebration must wait, I'm afraid.nnFaolchu's forces have taken all of Camlorn and the Lion Guard's counterattack falters.
The ghosts of the Alessian army still haunt this moor. nnIt's been an age since the Battle of Glenumbra Moors, yet the spirits still linger.
Shove off. Can't you see I'm busy here?
<This unfortunate soul appears to be the victim of a necromantic ritual.>nn<The corpse is crawling with worms.>
I was too weak to protect the tomb of my lord, the Iron Son of High Rock.
I failed to protect the regalia of my exalted lord, the Golden Prince.
I have failed in my duty. I could not defend the trophies of the supreme hunter, the Ivory Lord.
I suffer eternal dishonor for failing my lady, the Emerald Princess. I am no longer worthy of the post I hold.

In life, I doled out justice with an even hand. Many of my sentences were executed here at the Tears of the Dishonored. My spirit rested peacefully knowing I made the land a safer place.nnNow I can no longer rest. Someone has overturned my rulings!
Say the word, and I'll follow you into battle, captain.
Sheathe your weapon. I may be dead, but I am not your enemy.
His lordship has a plan, but that's nothing new. He has plans coming out his ears. But this one might actually work out this time.
Daggerfall's as good as saved. Now all we need is something to save it from.nnEr  don't tell his lordship I said that, all right?
We weren't sure if you'd be coming back to us.
You have no idea what a relief it is to see a friendly face.nnBut who are you? Where did you come from?
Asheeni is watching you. You do not steal from Asheeni.
You have no idea what a relief it is to see a friendly face.nnBut who are you? Where did you come from?
We've got to get these Daedra under control!nnYou look like you can handle yourself. Could you lend us a hand?
Please, we're dealing with serious matters here. The guardians are in desperate need of our aid and any interruption can have dire consequences.
Not everyone can successfully walk the path of both steel and magic. If you have a moment, I'd be happy to show you a few things I've mastered.
Honor guide you. In times like these, it's a rare commodity.
If your weapon isn't of the finest quality, you may as well call your life forfeit. A finely crafted weapon can shatter a crude one.
Sheathe your weapons. I am no wraith sent to drain your soul.
You returned the sky-iron sword to my crypt. You are a true knight and I thank you for your efforts on my behalf.
You have an entrepreneurial nature. Continue on this path and one day you'll be as wealthy as I was.
You have the cunning and skills of a true hunter. May you always catch whatever prey you stalk.
Our duty to High Rock did not end with our deaths. We shall always defend this land. Thank you for assisting us.
The wayshrine is a powerfully spiritual place. The ancestors are strong here.nnThat's fortunate. Their presence may yet give us insight into the troubles of this town.

Come, let me gauge your strengths. I offer training to Fighters Guild members in some of our special techniques.nnI also have a few things for sale, but only if you're a member of the appropriate standing.
What can I do for you?
What can I do for you?

Come, let me gauge your strengths. I offer training to Fighters Guild members in some of our special techniques.nnI also have a few things for sale, but only if you're a member of the appropriate standing.
The Mages Guild asks that all members do their part to destroy the Cold Harbor anchors, dispatch the creatures that have come through, and return any artifacts to learn more about that realm.
The Mages Guild asks that all members do their part to destroy the Cold Harbor anchors, dispatch the creatures that have come through, and return any artifacts to learn more about that realm.
I offer Mages Guild goods to members who qualify.
Do you seek enlightenment? I offer training in Mages Guild techniques and a few goods to members who qualify.
Do you seek enlightenment? I offer training in Mages Guild techniques and a few goods to members who qualify.
Thank you. These ancient stones are precious to us.
The Mages Guild battles alongside the Lion Guard this day. If we fail to reclaim Camlorn, this entire region will fall into darkness. nnWe're making final preparations now.
First we lost Camlorn. Then they turned back our offensive. nnIf we can't retake this camp, Faolchu's beaten us. Nothing else matters until this is resolved.
Another day in the forge. Another set of armor smashed in the arena. Blood and guts and bone.nnThe life of a smith is glorious!
Another day in the forge. Another set of armor smashed in the arena. Blood and guts and bone.nnThe life of a smith is glorious!
Another day in the forge. Another set of armor smashed in the arena. Blood and guts and bone.nnThe life of a smith is glorious!
This ship is off limits. Step away.
