May the spirits of the Ansei watch over you, child.
The corruption. It's gone! nnWe did a good thing here this day.
The old magic returns. That gives me hope. We may yet restore the Wyrd Tree!
What Angof's doing here sickens me. It's a relief to finally be able to do something about it.
I won't just stand here and watch our people die.nnGet General Gautier to give the order. My axe thirsts to taste werewolf blood!
Hold on, traveler. You don't want to go that way. nnFaolchu and his werewolf legion have taken Camlorn.
How in Oblivion did you get in here?
Oh, thank goodness you've come! The bandits tossed us down here. They threatened to kill us!
I'll be all right. I stepped in front of Lord Noellaume to protect him. The Red Rooks didn't appreciate my loyalty.
I can't believe we made it! I'm so glad to be out from under those bandits. Thank you!
Arm's not broken. Just sprained. I'll be all right. I can't thank you enough for helping us get out of there.
This place is great! I love this place!nnI  so  wait a moment. This doesn't look like Aldcroft!
Who's drunk? I'm not drunk. You're drunk!
Hold your horses, I'll get to you in a moment.nnIf you're in a hurry, head over to the bar and talk to Phelain. He'd be happy to help you.
Can you think of a better place to recruit guards? It's the best place to hear people boasting of great deeds.
Your gold won't do anyone any good at the bottom of the well.nnInstead of throwing it in there, give it to me. That would certainly make my dream come true.
Please help me. Please. A bit of gold for a poor, old woman.
The forest aches. Angof's bane is upon it. We must end this.
The guardians should have prevented this. Perhaps they aren't as powerful as we imagined.
The guardians have provided us with so much through the ages. We must help them in return.
I hate to see the trees that shelter us tortured and twisted by these  cultists! It's time to end this.
Ah, a new recruit! We could certainly use the help out here.
Thank Kynareth I found someone. Just let me catch my breath.
My own court conspires against me. Whispers of "that Redguard witch" fly through the servants' quarters. nnMy own Knights of the Flame treat me with suspicion. Dark times indeed.
We're ready to start the charge! Camlorn will be ours once more!
Everything you see, R'Dashun will sell to you.
I don't know what to do. It's all my fault. If the Duke dies, his blood will be on my hands.
I hate meeting new people when I'm not at my best. Is my hair all right? Are my robes on straight?
You survived. Are you still all in one piece?

I noticed you're no friend to the Withered Hand. Please, hear me out.nnI may wear their robes, but I'm not one of them. This is merely a disguise, although it's not as effective as I would have hoped.
A stranger who isn't dressed as a Bloodthorn? I don't know what you're doing out here, but you're a sight for sore eyes!nnNow hurry up and cut me loose.
I don't understand it. Instead of using their resources to help people, the Bloodthorn cultists insist on causing all kinds of trouble.nnIt's such a shame.

I can't decide what I want to read next. Should I go with something scholarly such as Glenumbra's People? Or am I in the mood for something a little lighter? Perhaps Lady Veronica's Best Friend?nnDecisions, decisions .

I'm writing the ultimate guide to the factions of the Daggerfall Covenant. It's going to be so much better than any of those previously published guides.nnYou don't look like much of a reader, though.
The book I need used to be on this shelf, but now it's gone!nnVaruhl probably placed it on one of the higher shelves again. Just to annoy me.
<This woman was in a struggle. She paid with her life.>
<This woman was involved in a struggle. She paid with her life.>
<The crow stares at you intently, then looks off to the south, almost as if directing you.>
You have the look of a bowman, I think. Or do you wield the staff? Onsi shines on you this day, for I sell both!
This is for you, hero! Thanks again for that timely rescue.
The poison ... it's like a yellow fog smothering my lungs and heart.
I'm in the middle of something right now.
What brings you to our pleasant little city? The war? The blood? The thrice-damned werewolves?
This poison will kill Marimah if we do not stop it. Malooc's spit!
I don't know you. Shove off!
The Wyrd Tree screams. The corrupting vines choke it from within.nnCan you hear its pain?
Draw upon my wisdom to sharpen your skills in battle.

Must ... get this potion to ... to the mages. Can't ... can't let it go to waste. Alinon would be so ... so very angry, heh.nnYou who stand before me. Are ... are you my mind playing tricks ... or are you real?
I have many fine wares for sale, O wayfarer.
You've seen action, eh? Scars are like mugs of ale, friend. Having a few is great, but having too many is  well, no, that's good too. Bad metaphor. nnLook, just buy some armor, all right?
The earth weakens. Angof's poison corrupts it. Together we will crush this vile manifestation.
Retribution must be swift. Angof will pay for his insolence!
This pollution is almost too much for me to bear. Help us restore balance to the Wyrd Tree.
I've come on behalf of <<1>> to deliver an invitation to the palace.nnThe king has need of your unique abilities, traveler.
You're placing the sacred candles instead of my worthless descendant? Has he no shame at all?
What did great-grandfather tell you? Am I back in good graces?

There are still many souls in jeopardy at Motalion Necropolis. <<1>> has begun amassing an army by raising the consecrated dead.nnShe's using soul energy as fuel to incite their rage. The spirits are in agony!
My little boy's all grown up! I never thought this day would come!
I can't believe it! My baby brother is getting married before me!
I never thought I'd see the day that <<1>> got married. nnSeeing how happy he is, I've changed my mind. This is a good thing.
I always get so emotional at weddings.
May Tava's winds guide you, traveler.
Welcome to the Runecrafters Hall, traveler.nnWhat can I do for you?
Greetings!  I am the QA Quest NPC.
Greetings!  I am the QA Quest NPC.
Greetings!  I am the QA Quest NPC.
Greetings!  I am the QA Quest NPC.
How is it I'm still alive?
Was that a dream or did I really ?nnThank you for changing me back.
There's nothing better than a night of drinking  except a day of even more drinking.

<<1>> just killed my partner and stole her horse. <<2>> and I tried to stop him, but we were too late.nnIf it weren't for <<2>>, I might not have survived. And I would never have believed it had I not seen it with my own eyes.
I was chasing a criminal from Bergama, but I lost him in the desert.nnIf he shows up here, I'll be waiting for him.
Greetings!  I am the QA Quest NPC.
I was hoping I'd see you again. I'm so much happier in Crosswych.nnMy family here has helped me move past my loss and start a new life.
Outfitters are hunters, attuned to the ways of the animals of the field and forest.nnWe take raw hides, and bones and turn them into armors, weapons and salves.
Are you injured? No? Then stop bothering me.
You should grovel before me for my help, weakling.
The Ash'abah is my family.nnI've heard all the tales of the undead, but seeing them crawl from the sand  nothing can prepare you for something like that!
The guardians do not answer our call. Without their guidance, we are lost.nnThis whole region will fall to the unnatural corruption you see before you.
The magic of this forest sheltered us and cared for us. It has never failed us. In return, we must do everything we can to preserve it from Angof's corruption.
The wounds inflicted by Angof's minions fester rapidly. They're difficult to heal.
<<1>> - I've found you at last. The ancestors whisper of your successes against Mannimarco's Worm Cult, and so I seek your help in fighting them once again.
I don't care how tough you think you are. No one should go into battle without a good set of proper armor.
A good weapon is better than food, better than drink. I sell very good weapons.
The armor I sell didn't just fall off the back of a caravan wagon. It's the finest medium-weight armor that your gold can buy.nnI guarantee it!
My relief was supposed to be here hours ago! I'm supposed to be enjoying a nice hot bath right about now.nnDo you need a suit of light armor? It's cool and it doesn't chafe!
Oh! A customer!  Can I help you choose something from our selection of fine woodcraft? Please? nnSorry I'm so excited. It's my first day.
Spellcaster? I've got what you need.
<<1>> - I've found you at last. The ancestors whisper of your successes against Mannimarco's Worm Cult, and so I seek your help in fighting them once again.
See someone else if you need orders, soldier.
The harsh winds of war sweep the lands of Cyrodiil. The Pact must ride those winds to victory!
Excuse me for being so forward, but I know who you are and I need your help.
It is a fine day for war, yes?
Sorry, soldier. Very busy here right now.
Back off, stranger. I've no time or patience to spare.
Just look at those lost souls. What drives them? Why do they fight on?
Please help me. I'm supposed to find Wyress Ileana, but I'm afraid to go on. It's too dangerous out here.
Stranger, if it is in your heart pray to Tu'whacca to guide the souls of our fallen to their final rest.

Are you an agent of <<1>>? You do not look to be from <<2>>, yet your face is familiar.nnThis city is filled with vipers waiting, watching, and spreading dissent. I am surprised the Imperials have not taken over completely.
<<1>> was apparently slain by one of the undead. From the look of her hands, she must have fought back fiercely, but to no avail.
Never a quiet moment 'round here.nnFirst, Renchant suddenly cancels all court activities, and then .
Why do you linger, my love? Commander Parmion rallies the troops for the final assault. You're his best officer and our noblest knight. You should be at his side for this moment.
Be kind to each other. That is our way.

Mongrels from the Reach flood into Bangkorai, yet what does their "High King" do for them? I have yet to see a response from Wayrest.nnI do hope the people of Evermore realize we can work together for our mutual benefit.
It is a surprise to see you standing here, <<1>>.nnUnless <<2>> sent you, I am quite sure we have nothing to discuss.
My debt to you is great, <<1>>. Without you, I would still be in prison.nnDid you have any trouble getting me released?
The Imperials walked all over us at <<1>>. <<2>> is dying, but he continues to fight.nnAs for what he's contemplating  well, you'll have to talk to him if you want to know more.
<This knight has been slain with three precise slashes between the plates of his armor.>nn<The assassin who killed him must have been skilled.>
Forgive me. I have many things to consider and precious little time to decide.nnThe funeral waits for me, but I cannot go. Not now, after everthing that's happened.
I have nothing left for me here.nnMy son, my breath, is gone.
Ishan died well. I am only here out of respect for his family's traditions.nnMourning his death would lessen his deed.
Ishan was always a braggart. When he was assigned to Bangkorai's garrison, all he would do was crow about how he was going to be a hero.nnHeroes die just as easily as any of us.
You have to buy a ticket before you play games in the gray market.nnNo exceptions. Everyone pays.
The dead walk again in Pelin Temple.
I once asked the gods for more work. I guess they have a sense of humor.nnAnd if you want to bury <<a:1>> someday soon, I've got coffins already made in that size.
I'm afraid you've caught me at a bad time. Master Virian's just returned from his expedition, and he's been in a foul mood ever since.nnWhatever it is, make it quick.
Ah, well. I was not expecting visitors.

There's not much we can do except hold our position. I would not think to question my lady, but unless we find reinforcements, we cannot think to stand against the numbers of Lord Montclair's soldiers.

There's not much we can do except hold our position. I would not think to question my lord, but unless we find reinforcements, we cannot think to stand against the numbers of Lord Montclair's soldiers.
Gods! First Her Majesty, and now our own guards turn against us!nnEvermore is sure to fall to ruin if somebody doesn't do  something!
So much work, so little time.
Can you help me? You've come from the woods. Did you meet one of our sisters, Wyress Ileana?nnWe haven't heard from her and we're very worried.
May Tall Papa guide you, traveler.
What? Are you another pawn of Hermaeus Mora come to torment me? Away! I have suffered enough.
Pelin Temple is no longer safe for virtuous people.
You're not one of them! Quickly, untie me before they return!
I'm glad you came along when you did. I wasn't expecting an ambush on a routine inspection.nnI'll have to ply this one a bit more to get the answers I need. What did you find in the hold?
We have nothing more to discuss. You've abandoned Prince Adrien and our only chance to beat the Imperials.
I saw them! They went north, toward the cliffs. A guard chased them!
Are you after the prince? They took him toward the cliffs! nnHurry!
I saw them running! They went west.
I saw them. They dragged someone into that home.nnGo get them!
Everything you see, R'Dashun will sell to you.
All of these unconsecrated corpses. It's no wonder the dead are walking.
Something is strange here. But I just can't figure out what. Do you have any thoughts?
How could my father have done this? How could he be responsible for all this sorrow?
Shhh. Please don't interrupt my prayer.
I hope the Eight have answered my prayers.

The Eight have seen fit to answer my prayers. The curse will soon be broken!nnThey've sent help to rid my family of our undying shame. Our regret has haunted us since the time of Arlimahera the Blood Queen.
Why did Padesh's curse draw me here? Wasn't a life of poverty bad enough? Must I suffer an eternity repeatedly watching his failure as well?
By the Eight, look what they've done to my city. nnAnd now the Lion Guard is being driven from its own siege camp.
Camlorn was a great city before Faolchu dug his claws into it. Just look what he's done.
Seeking our help? If so, you're destined to be disappointed.nnThis is a dark time for the Beldama Wyrd. We have little aid to offer.
Greetings. I am chamberlain to the king. How may I assist?

One cannot simply swing a blade and expect success. Every novice here must first forge a blade before they can wield it.nnOnly by understanding what goes into making the blade can they understand how it must be used.
May Tu'whacca, God of Souls, help me restore my family's honor.
I haven't had to handle these kinds of problems since I left the Lion Guard. This is beyond what the Wyrd Sisters usually deal with.
The wayshrine is a powerfully spiritual place. The ancestors are strong here.

Alik'r's predators all use different strategies to kill their prey, just like the foes you will face on the road. At <<1>>, we have bred particularly venemous predators to test our students.nnIn a long battle, strategy is as important as strength.
It is here that the best blades of our generation train and hone their skills. Do you think to count yourself among them?
Do not fear me. The curse that caused my madness has no hold on me  for the moment.
This is so much sorrow here, but at least I am at peace for now.
Out for a stroll? No? nnWhatever you're doing here, it's impressive you've made it this far.
Don't pester me. I'm working on a cure. Go bother someone else for a while.
No forgiveness! Vengeance for the murdered!
Blessed Mara, why is this happening? What did we do to deserve this trouble? nnYou better go. They'll be back at any moment to demand more gold from me.
We've been ordered to search for people snatched from Daggerfall.nnIf you're going to continue saving people, I'm sure <<1>> can make it worth your while. I wouldn't fight these creatures for free.
I should never have lowered my guard! Thinking that the werewolves would remain in the city was a foolish mistake. I only hope we didn't lose too many lives because of it.

The Mages Guild shall be helping the Lion Guard in the battle this day. If they fail to win and reclaim Camlorn, this entire region is at risk of falling to the darkness of the area. nnWe're making final preperations now.

This might be the last thing these soldiers do in life. Unlike the others, I'll let my troops rest and enjoy each others company for now.nnOnce the battle starts, they'll be no more time for such pleasantries.
Hi! I will give you the Interact with IO and Quest Items quest!
Many lives are at stake here, as is the future of Crosswych.

We had no warning! When we woke up, the Daedra were pouring out of the portal, screaming and killing! Now they've overrun the stables.nnMy father has a plan, but I fear I'm not up to the task. Can you help me?
Tough times ahead. <<1>> is dying, and <<2>> is lost.nnThe prince has a plan, but you'll have to talk to him about it if you wish to hear it.

Greetings, young one. You've come to ask about the Daedra. Know that the Withered Hand summoned a foul Dremora into this world. nnThe creature betrayed the acolytes. It has them bound with dark magics. The portal is now drawing their life energy!
The dead walk again, in Pelin Temple.
To choose for oneself is simple. To choose for a nation is hard. The heaviest blade is as a feather compared to the trust of one's people.nnAbide with me and listen carefully.
A goat will run if you strike it. A jackal may bite if you give chase. Only man can choose to do nothing. The path of restraint is often the hardest. I pose to you a questionone that still haunts me.

All choices exact a toll, wayfarer. Some are trivial, but some  some linger for generations. I was forced to drink from a bitter cup in my time and all Redguards have paid the price. I wonder if you would have made the same choice.
Great heroes often carry the greatest regrets. They lie buried in the sand with the bones and broken blades. Hidden. Forgotten. I had many stories to pass on, but only one is known. Hearken to me .
Are you ready to free Padesh from his madness?
The dead walk again, in Pelin Temple.
I was careless. I never thought they'd leave Camlorn to attack us. nnI only hope we didn't lose too many lives because of my mistake.
The wind told me you're the savior of the Alik'r. We'll see about that.nnYou've come for the artifact I protect, yes?
It is good to see persons of renown traveling to <<1>> to train with our masters.nnI wish you well, traveler.
I was careless. I never thought they'd leave Camlorn to attack us. nnI only hope we didn't lose too many lives because of my mistake.
I'm glad to be alive and away from those beetles.
Hold there, friend. I suggest you turn back. Crosswych is under siege both without and within.
Know that the Eight themselves look down upon the masters and their students in <<1>>.nnOur actions can mean honor or dishonor for generations to come.
Not a month goes by without a dozen new mouths to feed.nnStill, I've never felt safer than I do at <<1>>.
O Noble One, I am a hard worker. Please, I just need a few coins to get back on my feet.
The dead walk again, in Pelin Temple.
What <<1>> wants .... It's an insult to the Divines!
Why have you interrupted my rest?
Blood of the Forebears! Angof's minions are relentless.
Blood of the forebears! Angof's minions are relentless.
Return to your time. You learned that Faolchu's weakness is fire. Use that knowledge well.nnNow enter the nearby portal. It will take you home.
Knowing the Withered Hand hasn't defiled the honored dead puts my mind at ease.
You're interrupting my business with Master Luvian!
Have you seen the children? It's my turn to watch them, but they've seem to run off. I hope they aren't hiding in Virgil's supplies again. He gets so mad when they do that.
What can I do for you?
You are the first to come here in many long centuries, since this place was sealed.nnI despaired of anyone ever finding their way here.
I have nothing more to say to any of you!nnKill me if you want. It'll be better than what I'll get if I say any more!
You there! You can see me?
It's about time you arrived. You have the missing details, I hope?
<<1>> is going to get herself killed! She went into the aeries to find out what the Imperials are doing to the gargoyles.nnI knew her love of monsters was going to get her into trouble eventually.
Hearken, wayfarer! An opportunity for honor presents itself. Are you open to this challenge?
That lunatic woman  Sep himself wouldn't step in her shadow!nnI'd stay off this path, lest she demand some humiliating task from you.
And what do you come seeking?
Looking to crack some Daedric skulls? I've got what you need.
Daedra don't go down easy. You need the right weapon for the job.
What can the Fighters Guild do for you?
What're you gawking at? Do I look like I'm here to entertain you?
I can't believe what's happened here. It doesn't make any sense.
Knowing the Withered Hand hasn't defiled the Ash'abah's honored dead puts my mind at ease.
Knowing the Withered Hand hasn't defiled the Ash'abah's honored dead puts my mind at ease.
Knowing the Withered Hand haven't defiled the Ash'abah honored dead puts my mind at ease.
You are not marked with the corruption of undeath, nor those that foster it. You are not aligned with them, are you?
I'm not much good with a sword, but I'll do whatever Captain Darien asks of me.

Before you speak, stranger, I would have words with you. For centuries, this cell has held me. You are not the first. Others tried to free me and failed.nnNo key will open this lock. No weapon will break these bonds.
I should never have lowered my guard! nnWe're trying to take our camp back, but we're not having much luck.
My enchantments are superior to anything you'll find anywhere else in the city. Of course, quality will cost you more. But trust me. It's worth it.

I should never have lowered my guard! Thinking we would be the only one to take the offensive was a foolish mistake. I only hope we didn't lose too many lives because of it.nnWe're trying to take our camp back, but we're not having much luck.

I thought I could save my ancestors from the Withered Hand, but I wasn't strong enough. Now their eternal rest has been broken. Someone has raised them from the dead!nnI can't leave this world knowing I've failed to protect my ancestors.
You make this hero business look almost as easy as I do.nnSomeday we'll return to that inn and I'll buy you a drink.
I tried  but they got me with their evil magic!nnThey took the prince  down there. I think it leads out of the city! Please, go stop them!
We meet again, Sentinel-friend. Gurles has left us, and a new <<1>> has come to take his place.nnBut can she wield the forces of nature? That is the question we must ask.
You found him. I knew you would. The Withered Hand will not harm this family again. We'll see to that. nnSafe travels, friend.
May Tall Papa guide you, traveler.

Zeht's spade, I can't believe it's come to this. First, the Imperials chased us from our home. Now, I must sell the few things I have left in order to feed my children.nnWhere did our ration tokens go? What will we do?
Don't worry about the wars outside. The Shining Scarabs will take care of you while you are here.
Oh, my leg  a stupid beetle bit me! Does this wound look poisoned to you? It doesn't to me, but it sure hurts.
Maybe I should have stayed in Hallin's Stand.
How will I ever keep all of my children fed?
I don't think that we'll stay here much longer. The caves have become too dangerous of late.
When you don't have anything, you want everything.
I know the Shining Scarabs are trying to help all of us survive, but did they have to recruit both my husband and my only son? What will I do if anything ever happens to them?
There's more work here than there was in Hallin's Stand.
There's more work here than there was in Hallin's Stand.
They say that recruits are fighting the beetles in the lower cave. A few days ago, I was there and barely escaped with my life. Those raw recruits must be either dead or injured.
Want to test out getting an achievement via completing a quest?
There you are. I've been looking for you.
Prince Adrien is gravely injured. He is unlikely to survive the day.

Are you lost, friend? Make sure to watch your step. These woods are not as friendly as they used to be.nnI know a few folks have gone missing, even by the outskirts, but with Stendarr's grace, I'm sure they'll make it.
I have a test of skill for you to try I'll give you an achievement if you complete it. Care to try?
Welcome to Leki's Blade. Enter with an open heart and a steeled soul.
I'm in the middle of something. Go talk to someone else.
The Prince's instructions are clear. His death does not change the content of his orders, no matter how we feel about them.
What these knights are doing is sacriledge!
You need to get out of here right now. These mists are poisonous and  wait, are you immune too? Mara's bosom, what's going on?
Saving the day again, eh? Can't say I'm surprised. nnBut I'm not about to let you have all the glory. There ought to be enough here for both of us.
My uniform must be in here somewhere.
The great King Casimir sent us to stop Angof.nnWith the combined might of the Dragons, the Lion Guard, and you, Angof will surely fall.
We'll beat this Angof, claim glory for the king, and return home victorious.
Against the knights of the Covenant, the Lion Guard, and you, Angof doesn't stand a chance.
Who are you and why have you taken my amulet?
Please! No! Go away! They're going to find me! nnI don't want to die!
This is no time to dither about with maps and reports!nnWe're here. The enemy is to the south. The longer we dawdle, the more likely we lose the initiative!
<This body is perforated with innumerable tiny thorns.>nn<Perhaps the forest did not welcome this person's presence.>
Arkay help me, I've never actually had to fight before.

Thank you, my friend, for giving an old man his vengeance. These folk think I'll live, thanks to you and Theodore.nnHe's a good lad, but he hasn't lived to see the day when all his greatest battles are behind him.
We're almost to the family crypt. I'll be able to take my last mortal breath under the watch of my ancestors.

The hunters watch and wait, Sentinel-friend. We wait for a weakness to show, when our prey takes a single faltering step. Only then do we strike.nnThe <<1>> must possess the will to find our weakness and best us.
<<1>> too tough to bite. Small one not able to keep us now. Small one too weak, too frail. nnThis one enjoys eating the weak and frail. Crunch bones. Sweet and red, like berries. Easy to chew!
That Reachman got lucky. Just wait until my head stops spinning, and I'll give him what for!
Great Ruptga, if this be not your will, send me a sign .nnWait  who are you? What are you doing here?
They killed Heseph. They gave Gelves everything he demanded to keep the townsfolk safe. Even surrendered his own house. nnThey killed Heseph anyway. Our beloved mayor. They killed him in cold blood!
So much anger. So much suffering. I don't know where I am or why I'm here!
No more! No more! I just came to look at the gardenias!
I can feel myself slipping away. All the confusion  the fear  I'm losing myself in it.
I hope we find the Queen soon. All these other spirits are so full of anger. It's not safe here.
Thank you for helping me. I don't know what I would have done. I couldn't find my way.
I'm feeling better already. Just having the hope of getting someplace safe....
What a terrible idea this turned out to be. What was I thinking?
I don't suppose you've seen a frightened tailor wandering about. nnHis name is Odei Philippe. I'm his wife and I very much want to find him.
Who are you? Another Red Rook dog barking for its masters? nnI've got bad news for you, hound. I'm fed up. Whatever you want, the answer is no.
I won't rest until I see the Red Rooks answer for their crimes. They've taken enough from me. nnThey've taken enough from everyone.
You must witness the past to help those who are cursed. Padesh's memories can be revived if he is confronted with his past.nnYou must witness the past and take up the relics you find.
Morwha's mercy! What have I done?nnI was just trying to defend myself, and now I have committed the greatest dishonor and brought a curse down upon my family!
I've made it to the family crypt.nnI'll be able to take my last mortal breath under the watchful gaze of my ancestors.
If you're a smith by trade, I can give you a fair price on our raw materials.
I offer materials and recipes best suited for expert smiths.
Stay back. We don't know what kind of magic this Reachman may wield.
I only teach the best of the best.nnTheir weapons are legendary, just like the crafters who make them.

I'm going to have to sell more if I'm going to meet my quota for the month.nnOh, I'm sorry! Where are my manners? I'd like to offer you the finest armor money can buy. Not too heavy, but always strong enough to save your life!
Oh, hello! Just taking a break from working outside. I think I know exactly what you need!nnMy armor is so light, you'll forget it's even there.

I love having an isolated, quiet place for our studies, but I must admit, some of the alchemists and enchanters working here tend to be a bit  melodramatic.nnThat's often the result of seclusion and scholarly pursuits.
Yes I have a Nord name ... is that a problem? If not ... buy somehting.
What can I get for you today?
What can I get for you today?

Have you ever seen such madness? Every farmer and family have fled to Evermore because of the Reachmen.nnIt'll only be a matter of time before the guards start turning them away. And then where will they go?
We are in the midst of blessing these soldiers for the service. Though King Eamond has passed on, his soldiers will continue to serve his kingdom.
Learning is not the means to an end. It is both the beginning and the end.
You blink, you're dead. Just like that. Always make sure your opponent blinks first.
Have a care around those banekin, friend. They're small but viciousI saw a man lose his foot to one just the other day.
Come to hear my challenge, have you? Listen up. I'll tell you about a decision I had to make.
From now on, I do not think I will allow my children to swim in the sea here.
After what happened here, I cannot see myself setting foot in the sea ever again.
You are truly a gift from the gods, seafarer  from Ruptga himself, in fact.
I am afraid to go home and face my family  how do I tell them that I have caused us all to be cursed?nnThis is all so unfair.
I thought I would escape the curse. But no, no one can ever escape their fate.
Pardon me. I must attend to important matters.
I won't rest until I make the Red Rooks answer for their crimes.
Everything you see, R'Dashun will sell to you.
Everything you see, R'Dashun will sell to you.
<<1>> does not like this desert where the dead crawl out of the ground. They buy nothing, scare her customers, and want to bite her tail. <<1>> dislikes all of these things.
Asheeni is watching you. You do not steal from Asheeni.
What can I get for you?
I wasn't always a merchant, you know. Believe me, it's not like I want to be one. Do I look like a salesman to you? nnDon't answer that.
Greetings! I can see you have an eye for fashion. You'd look quite fetching in blue, I think .
Stout woodwork requires a strong arm, friend. Think you're tough enough?
Knowing the Withered Hand haven't defiled the Ash'abah honored dead puts my mind at ease.

Crosswych isn't the best place to visit right now. If you do enter the town, try not to get noticed by the Red Rooks.nnIf you're good in a fight, though, you could join our resistance. We could really use the help.
Shh Get down! Can't you see that the barracks have been overrun by Imperials? Do you want to get us all killed?
I pity these foolish Bretons, with their hot iron casques and rusty metal plates. You and I know that in battle swiftness is best.
Blessings be upon you. nnI apologize for my sparse stock, but we must take heart. In times like these even trifles feel like treasures.
Brave meeting! Come to look over my gems? They can be yours  for the right price. nnPoint one out and let's make a deal.
A fellow clothier, is it? Well, you've got your work cut out for you in Evermore. Some folk are wearing nothing but rags and bandages.nnGot a few things that might help. Take a look.
If it's provisions you want, look elswhere, stranger. Too many hungry mouths in Evermore nowadays.
Looking for a weapon, eh? Well, If your enemy's got a head, I've got a blade that'll cut it off. nnHave a look for yourself.
I won't do it. I won't pay any more hard-earned gold to those Red Rook dogs. nnIt's time for action, I say!
I'm trained as a snake charmer, but I've lost my snake. I'm going to starve without my livelihood to sustain me.nnMy poor <<1>>! Where could she have gone?
May Tall Papa guide you, traveler.
Can't stop the storm. You can only build a stronger roof. That's what keeps us goingthat, and our children.nnPity about the queen's young ones. She's held up admirably, considering.
Ah. Another one. Must I explain myself again?nnKnow that my business is my own. The queen invited me here. And no, I won't make a potion or poultice for you.
For my entire life, I prayed that Tall Papa would keep me from suffering Padesh's curse, but here I am. Now, I pray that someone will free me from having to watch this endless slaughter.

These soldiers won't last much longer and I don't have enough magic to extend my ward to protect them.nnDarien told me about the amulets. Did you get them? With any luck, they'll work like the talisman you're carrying.
Oh, gods! Why is this happening? Ever since the Red Rooks showed up, everything has been in shambles!nnIt's almost time. They'll be here any minute to collect their protection money from me!
Tamien sent word to the Lion Guard. They'll help us get the town back to normal.
Thanks for reminding me of my duty. nnI'll make certain this never happens again.
A few Red Rooks have taken refuge in the mine. Ha! They won't last long.
It's good to see you again.nnThese soldiers won't last much longer. Did you get the amulets Darien wanted?

If you value your hide, keep away from Hircine's shrine. It's been overrun by Reachmen, and the shrine's guardians have turned against us.nnOnly the matriarch would know why our Lord Hircine allowed this.
The scent has left. The blood taste does not plague me any longer.
What are you doing here? You're not working with the smugglers, are you?

Creature! You are not of the Wyrd, nor of the northmen. The scent of fear is upon you, but it does not overwhelm  neither a true hunter, nor simple prey.nnYet you have made your way into this blighted place. Why do you travel this path?
Curse those smugglers. To rot and ruin with them!
May Tall Papa guide you, traveler.
I will help you complete the Combat Quest section of the smoke test!
You're <<1>>? You've made quite a name for yourself. I'd shake your hand, but I'm pretty sure something would snap.nnTo what do I owe the pleasure?
I mean you no harm. I only wish to complete my task here so I may leave this realm.
I'm glad to be away from those beetles.
Those beetles will give me nightmares.
I'm glad to be away from those beetles.
Traveling with mages always makes me queasy.nnI'll stay here and guard Gabrielle. Be careful out there.
You must be Magician Benele's friend. nnWhat went wrong with that spell? That's the last time I volunteer to be teleported.
When I heard the King was sending troops up here to go after Faolchu's master, I wasn't about to be left out of the action. nnBy the way, is this your dog?
King Casimir finally decided to take the war to Angof. nnIf his Daggerfall knights and the Lion Guard can work together, we have a chance to stop this madness.

Always saving the day, aren't you? Heh. I can't say I'm surprised to see you here. In fact, I'm glad to see you! nnIn any case, I wasn't going to let you have all the fun. I'm happy to take on anything that won't lie down and die like it should.
By the Eight, never creep up on a person. You're likely to get beheaded. nnYou must be Wizard Benele's friend.
Stay backthis area's trapped. Don't get caught like I did. nnI've been watching to see how it works. The trap has guardians. They're the key to disarming it, I believe.
How does this sound?nn"The Imperials are murderous fiends who burn our towns and starve our children. Join the Shining Scarabs to fight them!"nnIt's very inspirational!
The Imperials are murderous fiends who burn our towns and starve our children. Join the Shining Scarabs and .nnWell, you don't look like a refugee from Hallin's Stand. How can I help you, friend?
I  almost got through.nnWe can't waste any more time out here! Ugh!
I will help you with the Escort/Waypoint section of the smoke test!
I will help you with the Conversation section of the smoke test!
I will help you with the modification section of the smoke test!
I will help you with the quest creation section of the smoke test!
Are you the answer to my fevered prayers? Surely, Stendarr hears our cries!nnThere's so little time left! Soon, the hagraven's curse will sweep away our will to fight the Reachmen.
Reachmen are strong people, but they've never been this aggressive before.
The Reachmen killed so many of our people when they attacked.nnOnly a few of us managed to gather here. The guards are keeping the attackers at bay for now, but what about everyone we left behind?
Corruption surrounds you, yet it does not touch you. I will not question this blessing.nnOffer what you found to Hircine. He will destroy it, if that is his will,
It's good to see <<1>> again. We've been so worried about her, especially after what happened to His Majesty and their children.
That spirit. His gaze, so hard and cold. nnHe won't stop looking at me. He looks right through me. Why? Why am I so cold?

Greetings. You may believe fate brought you this way, led you to speak to me. I say: give the credit to your legs and your heart. They are what have brought you to me.nnI am working to prove that fate's bite has no sting.

If you value your hide, stay far away from Hircine's shrine. It has been overrun, and his guardians have turned against his worshippers.nnThe matriarch would know why Hircine's guardians have turned on us. Tiria thought she could get to her, but .
How goes your hunt?nnIf there's anything I can do to aid you, I will not hesitate.
Did you know you were meant to talk to me? It was your fate. You cannot escape your fate, you know.nnI can prove this truth.
Did you know you were meant to talk to me? It was your fate. You cannot escape your fate, you know.nnI can prove this truth.
Did you know you were meant to talk to me? It was your fate. You cannot escape your fate, you know.nnI can prove this truth.
Did you know you were meant to talk to me? It was your fate. You cannot escape your fate, you know.nnI can prove this truth.
Grrr  greetings, tall one. Will you save <<1>>?
You're the Covenant scum who knocked me out and tied me up.nnI'm going to carve your heart out with a spoon.
Look at all of the folks we're helping. All of them have lost their homes. With any luck, we'll be able to return home once the war with the Imperials ends.
Never a dull moment. I just want to get back to cooking.nnAh, the sweet smells of garlic and leeks! How I missed you.

Supervising the newest Shining Scarabs may look easy, but it's not. Some of these fools take on beetles without planning a strategy first. Fighting is more than using one's body; it's also using one's mind.
These ruins  this was once a place for prayer and contemplation.nnNow these fools have awakened the sleeping beasts, and I bear the shame of helping them do so.
Thank Stendarr you're here, <<1>>. The necromancers who fell at the <<2>> are giving me no end of trouble. Their cursed bones are still a danger.
<<1>> ! I knew that was you.nnListen, Zeli needs your help!
You look troubled. How can I aid you?
Alik'r has its own pantheons, but I serve Arkay.
Welcome to <<1>>, traveler. May Tall Papa guide your steps.
I love to talk! Talk to me about anything!
You are the one who wishes to destroy my master. nnI know what you seek. I would tell you if I could, but instead, I must thwart you.
Someday, the Red Rooks will pay for what they've done here.
Has it finally happened? Is this nightmare over?
Maybe the Red Rooks think they can break me. nnHeh. And maybe the sun will rise in the west.
<Sir Etienne was stabbed through his armor, and his skin is still slightly warm. Sir Etienne's leg is splinted, leaving one of his greaves slightly askew atop the bandages.>
Get me out of here! Please!
Please! Get me out of here!
The pain . I can barely stand it!
And the mortal has returned.nnHave you considered Hircine's offer? My lord doesn't invite every stranger to hunt in his hunting grounds.
It ... hurts! What did that werewolf do to me?
Did I escape the reach just to die here?
Can you believe that reachwoman bit me? Marthe said I was infected with lycanthropy. That just can't be possible.
Captured by a werewolf and now we're in a village full of them? You're the only person left I trust, aside from my friends here. That Marthe even tried to give me some potion. Said it'd cure me.
Virgil left me access to his cache of goods to sell. Have a look, if you like.
We should hurry back to the rally point.
We must recover the Ansei Ward from <<1>> before it's too late!
Another mortal ready for a test of skill!nnI eagerly await to see how you fare in my hunting grounds, young one.

You're here! My savior returns. Thank you for all your help.nn<<1>> told me you freed her from the Pellingare gang. She released me before heading back into the sewers. Praise the divines! I can finally return to my life.
Thank you for the kindness you showed my husband. It's a rare soul who would risk their own life to save another's.
Greetings!  I am the QA Quest NPC.
Want to test out getting an achievement via completing a quest?
Are you ready to put an end to all this?
If the Knights of the Dragon and the Lion Guard can work together, we have a chance to stop this disaster.
When I heard the king was sending troops up here to fight that Reach-born bastard, I was ready to go within minutes.nnSay, this isn't your dog, is it?
Come to admire my lizards?nnAll my little babies are highly trained. You should see Hiram do a trick!
I grieve to see any destruction done to Hallin's Stand, whether by pestilence or by invaders.
You are bold to enter a collapsing mine, stranger! nnBeware, lest you share my fate!
Hurry upstairs! Grab Bonerender before the Reach do!
I endured their lashes. I endured the burns and the beatings. I will endure the humiliation.
I'm not paying any more gold to these blasted Red Rook. Not doing it. Not one bit more.
<The dog whines and paws at the mound of sand at her feet.>
I know I left some rum arond here somewhere.
These weapons all look so nice. I don't know which one to take.
I endured their lashes. I endured the burns and the beatings.nnI will visit my suffering back upon them a thousandfold!
Just give me a few minutes and a splint.nnI'll be back in the fight as soon as I catch my breath.
What? Are you another pawn of Hermaeus Mora come to torment me? Away! I have suffered enough.
It's not safe for your kind here. Best leave these woods before you end up as a troll's meal.
Welcome to <<1>>. Should you require information about <<2>>, please talk to <<3>>. I must see to city's defense.
I'm hurt, but I think I'll bet better soon.
Those reachmen were roughing me up, but I wouldn't tell them a thing.
Marge says that I need time to heal. I hope it doesn't take long. I want to get the Reachmen back for what they've done.
I'm very sore, but Marge thinks I'll bet better soon.
What? Are you another pawn of Hermaeus Mora come to torment me? Away! I have suffered enough.
What? Are you another pawn of Hermaeus Mora come to torment me? Away! I have suffered enough.
We survived, as we always do in Crosswych. nnMountain winters, Red Rookswe're strong folk. We endure.
Things have gone from bad to worse in Crosswych. I'll just stay here, where it's safe.
We were complacent. The Red Rooks took us like wolves take sheep. nnIt won't happen again.
Welcome to Balfiera recruit! I have orders from the Commander to give out hit and run tasks!
Welcome to Balfiera soldier! I'm here to make sure you and your allies have proper orders!
The water is so calming  you can almost see into the lands beyond
Oh, my sweet wife, my sweet Sonia! This life is nothing without you.nnAll I have left is sitting and waiting for death to reunite us.
What? Are you another pawn of Hermaeus Mora come to torment me? Away! I have suffered enough.
You'll find <<1>> in the next chamber. She's already begun raising the consecrated dead!nnWe must recover the Ansei Ward before it's too late.

Stenwick served the woods well, both in life and as the Sentinel. The Wyrd will etch his name upon our stones, and his memory will last as long as the mountains.nnHe has left his last wishes with you, it seems. Honor his memory.
And so the Sentinel passes. Fair journey, Old Stenwick. We will remember you fondly.nnWe will take care of the body. He would want it to be left in the woods he loved so dearly.
Something is not right about this village.
Oh, my sweet wife, my sweet Sonia! This life is nothing without you.nnAll I have left is sitting and waiting for death to reunite us.
What? Are you another pawn of Hermaeus Mora come to torment me? Away! I have suffered enough.
They took him. A pack of madmen abducted Captain Jerick. nnI've got to get up.
<The captain lies writhing on the ground. Nightmare fire streams from braziers to his struggling form.>
<The troll looks at you, but does not move to attack.>
You shouldn't be down here. Only residents of Kerbol's Hollow are allowed here!
Nothing like finding out that the family estate you inherited is nothing but a pile of ruins.nnAnd here I thought my life was finally taking a turn for the better.
The Guardians do not answer our call. Without their guidance, we are lost.nnThis whole region will fall to the unnatural corruption you see before you.
Another visitor? Suddenly this village isn't feeling so isolated.
Not a bad scrap. Thanks for getting me back into the fight.
<Istahn appears to be in silent prayer.>
Do not distract me from the races  I am on a winning streak.
Welcome to Balfiera recruit! I have orders from the Commander to give out hit and run tasks!
Welcome to Balfiera soldier! I'm here to make sure you and your allies have proper orders!
Welcome to Balfiera recruit! I have orders from the Commander to give out hit and run tasks!
Welcome to Balfiera soldier! I'm here to make sure you and your allies have proper orders!
Welcome to the fight soldier! I'm here to give you any information about the battle going on here in Balfiera!
Welcome to the fight soldier! I'm here to give you any information about the battle going on here in Balfiera!
Welcome to the fight soldier! I'm here to give you any information about the battle going on here in Balfiera!
We heal much more quickly in our werewolf form. I'll be better in no time.
We felt the passing of the Viridian Sentinel, and we came to see who would claim his place.nnSo far, I am not impressed.
You look strong and capable. I could use your help, if you're willing.nnAnd if you're brave enough.
Gods! They killed them all! Those Daedric filth killed my entire patrol. Then they dragged me off and threw me into a nightmare. nn"Vaermina." They kept saying "Vaermina."

The Divines smiled on us when they brought you here today, my friend.nnMy thanks for saving my lord from himself. The man's worth more than just a sword arm, and its weakening pains him so. Hopefully, wisdom will find him soon.
The Reach can just stay in that tunnel for as long as they want, as far as I'm concerned.
We don't see many outsiders here.nnMost folks wouldn't understand that we just want to be left alone. We don't want to hurt anyone.
<<1>> has asked me to repair the broken rain catchers.nnCan you protect me while I work?
You're the Covenant scum who knocked me out and tied me up.nnI'm going to carve your heart out with a spoon.
You're the Covenant scum who knocked me out and tied me up.nnI'm going to carve your heart out with a spoon.

Once again, our sacrifice has proven worthy. Alik'r belongs to the living, and the dead can return to the rest they have earned.nnThe vile arts will return to these sands again someday, and again, we will be ready.
Before I died in this tower, I prayed for my child. Akatosh, Daedra  it didn't matter. I wanted my baby to live. Just not as a Baelborne.nnImagine my surprise when someone answered.

I know it is only a matter of time before we are called to the fight in Cyrodiil. nnWhen that day comes, and we fight that final, desperate battle, I hope I find myself fighting at your side once again. May the gods keep you until then.
We met only briefly, but I will remember you forever, <<1>>.
Tu'whacca's Throne is under siege by the Withered Hand. All of the Keepers have been slain or have fled, except my master, <<1>>.nnMy advice is to escape before you're trapped here, like I am.
Ambushed! Of all the stupid luck. I barely got out of there alive.
Didn't think I'd make it. I barely made it into hiding before more of those bastards showed up. nnBut by the Eight, it's good to see a friendly face!
I thought I was done for. Thanks for finding me.
The Imperials are more devious than I thought.
History presses down on us like a weight. Pay heed, or it will crush you into the sands.
Another creature entering the fray? Lord Hircine will be pleased!nnAnd what part will you play, little mortal?
I knew you would succeed in your quest, <<1>>. As I foresaw on the Rain Catcher Fields, the Ansei Wards have been returned.nnYou are a truly a gift to Alik'r.

The winds spoke of your return, and with the Ansei Wards no less! You are a blessing upon every grain of sand.nnThank you, <<1>>. And thank you for the chance to leave Leki's Blade for a time. It has been a pleasure to speak with a fellow tribune.

<<1>>! It is good to see you again. I've spent the time since last we met layering spell after spell onto the vault.nnYou can imagine my expression when the king said we'd be admitting this many people into the area. A mage's job is never done!

They're already telling quite the tale of our time at Salas En, friend! The Aldmeri are in retreat from Alik'r. The ritual we cast has left them no choice.nnMany of my kinsmen look down on my magecraft, but I look on our adventures as validation!

I've visited <<1>> many a time with horses for the king's army, but I have never entered the Impervious Vault. It is wondrous!nnWe have you to thank. Always know, as I vowed, that you are family. You are most welcome at Aswala's stables!
What's going on? I was able to get this far, but I still feel the approaching dread and building terror. Did you talk to the spirit?

The Impervious Vault! The Ansei Wards! Never in my lifetime did I think to see such wonders.nnIt's all thanks to you, <<1>>. You saved our stables, our family, and our livelihood. We can't ever repay you, but know that we will never forget!

My arm has recovered since we last spoke at Aswala Stables. Soon, I'll be able to fulfill my vow. I'll never let evil threaten my family again!nnYou are a true champion, <<1>>. I may never see another hero like you.
<This corpse appears to be powering the Daedric gate through some sort of necromantic ritual.>

<<1>>! You helped the Ash'abah greatly at Morwha's Bounty. Now you have slain the spawn of Suturah and returned the Ansei Wards.nnWhat we started, you have finished. Know that we will always consider you part of our tribe.

<<1>> honors us for our part in saving Alik'r, both then and now. Admitting the Ash'abah to the Impervious Vault borders on sacrilege. It is not lost on us.nn<<1>> is a good man. He sees right beyond tradition. We are proud to serve such a ruler.

<<1>>! It warms my heart to see you've done so well. You will always be part of the Ash'abah. I have stepped in to lead the tribe, now that Marimah  I miss him dearly.nn<<2>> does us great honor by admitting us to the vault. Hail to the king!
Thanks for finding the missing scouts. I wasn't sure I'd see them alive again.
All safe and sound, thanks to you.
I was in quite a bind. Thanks for getting me out of it.
Good to see you again. I hate to think what would have happened to me if you hadn't come along.

Consecrating the corpses at Sep's Spine was just the start. Once you slew Parisa, the Withered Hand fell into chaos. Rashdi and I saw to that. nnIt is good to see you alive and well. Then again, I never had any doubt you would succeed!
I bring our respects from Kozunset.
<This corpse is powering the Daedric gate through some sort of necromantic ritual.>
I endured their lashes. I endured the burns and the beatings. I will endure the humiliation.
Another traveler in the <<1>>?nnSee that you keep a good distance from the trolls. They're even more bloodthirsty than legend would lead you to believe.
The water is so calming  you can almost see into the lands beyond
The Imperials will never defeat us.
Word of the conflict here reached me at Pellin Graveyard. If you have need of a strong shield, I would fight the Imperials with you.
I could not rest in Pelin Graveyard while this conflict torments my people.nnI'm honored to fight the Imperials at your side.
I do not often leave Kerbol's Hollow, but I couldn't stay away while so much innocent blood was being shed.nnIf you need someone to seriously reduce the Imperials' forces, I will help you kill them.
I will not rest until the dogs who captured the garrison and defiled my soldiers are rotting in the ground.
There is no safe haven while the Imperial threat exists.nnI'll help you defeat them, so my sacred grove will remain secure.
I wasn't sure if I'd run into anyone else on these forsaken roads.nnWell, except for the werewolves and the maniacal cultists, that is.
My wife is wounded and my son, <<1>>, is missing!nnWhy do you test me so, Stendarr?
Without your help, I would have been a meal for the jackals.
I'm trapped up here! Do you know a way down?
I sell humble bags and backpacks. They're not extravagant or lavish, but they're very roomy and they get the job done.
Welcome to the Bank of Daggerfall.
Thank you, thank you, Wayfarer. My family is in your debt. Thank you for returning my son to me safetly.
You come to Morwha's for fresh water? Better stock up on other supplies while you're at it.
Please take a look at what I have to offer, but know I have an eye on you.
On your way out into the desert, adventurer? It's dangerous to go alone, you should probably buy a few things?

Ah, but you must be wondering what we're doing on your shores. That's a fair question.nnThis was to be our last destination on this side of Tamriel. It was the last ruin we needed to seal away, but as you can see, we were less than successful.
The Primeval Seekers aren't all bad.nnIf we can't make peace, however, we won't hesitate to do whatever we can to protect our Lady.
Hey there, you've got to help me. My buddy's missing, and I think he met a bad end!
Be wary. We don't know what we're up against.
Be wary. We don't know what we're up against.
Be wary. We don't know what we're up against.
My brother - I can't find him anywhere. The High Priest sent us down here to kill the lamia, but those beasts nearly killed us instead. You must help me!
Please, choose the type of wave event you'd like to participate in.
She's not going to make it, is she?nnTu'whacca, what have I done?
I thought I'd make my name as a feared bandit, but it didn't work out. nnNow I'm going to live out my life as a fisherman of notoriety!
Be wary. We don't know what we're up against.
Be wary. We don't know what we're up against.
Be wary. We don't know what we're up against.
Be wary. We don't know what we're up against.
I have a long walkabout ahead of me, wayfarer. Make your purchases quickly so I may be on my way.

Be careful. The villains of the Withered Hand have been committing crimes again.

This might be the last thing these soldiers remember in life. Unlike the others, I'll let my troops rest and enjoy each others company for now.nnOnce the battle starts, they'll be no time for pleasentries.

The curse has lifted. Thank you!
Please help us! We escaped Camlorn only to fall straight into the dangers of the bognnMy people are out there!
I provide a service. I supplement what the soldiers receive, for a price. If you're interested, I'd be happy to show you my wares.
You! Are you one of the survivors from the fight at <<1>>?
Bound and weaponless ... If I only had a weapon and a free hand, I would cut my way through these Imperials.
Bound and weaponless ... If I only had a weapon and a free hand, I would cut my way through these Imperials.
Please help me! The Imperials have kidnapped my father. I have to save him!
Learning to control the ebb and flow of magicka requires patience and expert training. And I, my friend, am just the expert you need.
Honestlywhy fight a foe up close when you can roast them from afar? Some people call it cowardice. Me? I call it good sense.
If you're looking for trouble, you must be looking for me. Let me show you how to walk in the shadows.

Hi! Would you like to adopt this darling child and/or follower?

Is that Antoine's ring? You have my husband's ring? Then you freed him from his bonds to this dark magic?nnNo  he would be here again at my side if that was the case. His spirit still wanders. Cursed by this evil.

Hello, <<1>>! I am your follower that cleans up when you die or logout. Can I have your autograph?

More and more people are arriving at our camp. That must mean the fighting outside isn't over yet.
Ugh! This blood will never come out of my shirt! How can I protect these refugees if I can't even get bloodstaind out of clothing?
Please help us! The Imperials captured us to use as blackmail against my husband. He's stationed at the old tower.
We don't take well to outsiders, even on our best days, and I've already lost several friends to a Reachmen's raid today.
We're with you. Our people are engaging the Reachmen where we can.nnWe'll leave the Hagraven to you. She would just turn us against ourselves. Good luck!
Hello, <<1>>! I am your follower and I will defend you in combat, but only until you are victorious.

<<1>> has many fine items for sale.
The Hollow Wastes are unsettled right now.  We're safe enough here.

Welcome to our little oasis in the wilderness. Out there? Vampires, giant bats, bloodfiends . In here? Frightened villagers, bad food, and poor company.nnAll the comforts of home, all things considered.
The Hollow Wastes are unsettled right now. Difficult times for any traveler.
The fangs! The blood! Everywhere, crimson in the dirt.nnWhat? Who?
I can't sleep. Those fiends are going to descend upon us, just as they did in Crestshade!nnWhen will my wife finally join us? What happened to our village?
In my day, I might have been able to help defend <<1>>, but it's getting harder to lift a pick, let alone a sword.
Greetings. It is good to see the garrison back in the hands of the Daggerfall Covanent.
Greetings. It is good to see the garrison back in the hands of the Daggerfall Covanent.

Hail, stranger! Welcome to Daggerfall. Have you come to aid in defense of this great Alliance against the unwashed hordes that seek to see us dead? Will you do your part to keep the Ebonheart Pack and the Aldmeri Dominion from killing us all?

Thank you for destroying what I had become.nnI was trapped in my reanimated body. I heard voices speaking deep within my mind as we fought, controlling me  and taunting you.

I'm sure I don't know you, stranger.nnThese are dangerous times. Perhaps you should find another table to sit at.
I'm sure I don't know you, stranger.nnThese are dangerous times. Perhaps you should find another table to sit at.

Governor Seius' days are measured in hours!nnThat sounded better in my head. Ah, well.

Have you seen the children? It's my turn to watch them, but they've seem to run off. I hope they aren't hiding in Virgil's supplies again. He gets so mad when they do that.

Dangers are all around us. Beetles scavenge our food. Imperials murder our neighbors and starve our children. Join the Shining Scarabs and .nnWell, you don't look like a refugee from Hallin's Stand. How can I help you, friend?

Stendarr, help me! It hurts so much

What you did in the barracks will change this battle. Our forces are streaming through the hole you punched in their defenses.nnI took advantage of the confusion to escape. We actually have a chance to dislodge those dogs from our garrison!
What can I get for you?
Curse those pale bastards! They've ruined me!
The Nords of the Ebonheart Pact have all but invaded us, but Chirane would have us stand defenseless while they camp on our shores and burn our farms. This is an outrage!
I'm sorry, friend, but we're in mourning and we've no heart for visitors. Those young men sleeping, they're my sons, unconscious for days. Their spirits are far away.
Anyone too weak to keep what they have deserves to have it taken.
Anyone too weak to keep what they have deserves to have it taken.
Anyone too weak to keep what they have deserves to have it taken.
Memories that beg to be forgotten haunt me. The knowledge of what my corpse has become torments me. You must save the others, so that we made destroy the abomination and eventually find peace.

Flesh is so soft, so easily ripped.nnI can feel each rake of their claws.
I stand with you, friend. Let's put an end to this, once and for all.
We must find peace, <<1>>, and you're our only hope.

Watch your step. Every manner of foul magic is being used in this place.nnI trust the Wyrd only a little more than I trust the Reachmen.
A bit of bruising and a few broken ribs won't stop me from getting my report to Shornhelm. I've got to let my superiors in House Tamrith know what happened at Crestshade.
My daughter's still out there. I know she's alive. Those Nord dogs couldn't lay a finger on her.

<The mammoth looks down at you with an ancient and weary gaze.>

You did it! I can't believe the size of the hole you punched through the Imperial lines!

What you did in the barracks will change this battle. Our forces are streaming through the hole you punched in their defenses.nnI took advantage of the confusion to make my escape. We actually have a chance to dislodge those dogs from our garrison!
If you have urgent business, take it to <<1>> or <<2>>.nnIf you don't have urgent business, move along.
You hold all of our fates in your hands. If you return to Evermore, you will surely have a hero's welcome waiting for you.
You! You're the one I detected when the fracture closed. I came here because I felt a connection between that closure and this place.nnThis man was already dead, killed by Imperial hands.
Welcome to the Mages Guild. Please do not touch, gesture at, or talk to any strange objects. The Guild cannot be held responsible for accidental teleportation, death, or dismemberment.
Your army will be right behind you, <<1>>.nnMay the Divines watch your path!
The resonance between our world and Oblivion increases with each new fracture.nnWhat do the Imperials have planned? Do they even realize what they've done?
House Tamrith employs mages like myself to give them an edge against their rivals.nnI'm just happy for an opportunity to practice my skills and continue my research.
Oh, the pain! I can feel his will burning into my soul!nnNo! I will never serve Molag Bal!
I don't know how much longer I can resist the call.nnNo! I will never call Molag Bal my master!

Steel and stone! I've many fine sacks, pouches, satchels, bags, backpacks, knapsacks, bandoliers and purses to suit the storage needs of well, anyone, really.
Tall Papa guide your steps, my friend.nnI have little honey left, but it is of excellent quality, as always.

Your friend is dead, and I'm trapped in Cold Harbor.
Not many still take to the waters. To me, it seems like a fine place to stay.

You did it! I heard you were headed here, so I rushed over to help, but you had already finished before I arrived.nnI never thought, when we were scouting the Imperials near here, that you would be the one to kick them out of the garrison. Amazing!

For the last time, stay out of .nnOh, apologies. You are not another one of those Evermore soldiers. We have been trying to keep them out of the Reachmen's camp, for their safety and ours. But, like most, their skulls are too thick to understand.
We're fighting with the Imperials on too many fronts.nnThe troops we sent across the bridge and toward the stables were overwhelmed, but we can't spare enough men to rescue them!
We're fighting with the Imperials on too many fronts.nnThe troops we sent across the bridge and toward the stables were overwhelmed, but we can't spare enough men to rescue them!
We have to save them! We have hurt soldiers behind enemy lines!

Come closer, my friend, and look upon my armor! Do you see the fine metal rings? The shining buckles? True craftsmanship is in the details!
Little busy here, so make it quick.
Preparation is half the battle. Good armor, good weapons, and a good head on your shoulders.
The greatest lessons you'll learn are the ones you experience for yourself.
Welcome to the Fighters Guild outpost. Interested in training today?
There's much to be done here. What can I help you with today?
There's experience behind your eyes. That's just what we like to see here.
What brings you out here today? Let me guess . Your endless quest for knowledge, right? Well, you've definitely come to the right person!
Hmm . Oh, interrupted again! That's only the tenth time today, and Jollivet seems to think I can still get my work done.nnRegardless, I always have time for someone willing to learn.

Welcome to the Mages Guild! I hope we may be of service today. Please let us know if you need anything, anything at all! nnReally, it's so dull out here. I don't see why I can't go help at the Garrison!
Ah, an experienced traveler. What can I do for you today?
What can an old man do you for today?
I could hear you coming a mile away. You definitely need my help.
The sharper the blade, the better the kill.
You look like you could handle yourself. We'll have to put that to the test.

The refugees coming from Hallin's Stand are complaining about their difficult trip through Nilata Ruins, just outside our southern entrance.nnSeems the whole place was first overrun by Imperials, then overrun by Dremora. I hope we'll be safe here.

Refugees keep trying to make their way through the ruins to the northern road. First, it was Imperials waylaying them. Then it was Dremora.nn<<1>> sent someone to investigate the ruins and find the source of the Dremora, but she hasn't come back.
For a modest fee, the Mages Guild would be happy to teleport you across Tamriel.
I'm not here to cause trouble. I've earned a living in the desert for the past twenty years. I know what you'll need. Would you like to see my wares?
Only the best prices for the people of Bangkorai!
Adventure? Interested in gore and glory, hm? Well, hard to keep at it when you're hungry! Step up and buy your fill.
Everyone deserves variety in their diet. I provide that.
Oh! Popped in for a bit of a respite as well, I see.nnIf you'd like some provisions, I might be able to help you out while we're both resting in here.
Begone, accursed thing! I  hmm  you're not a bloodfiend. nnPlease, whoever you are, help us. Help the spirits of Crestshade. They tore our spirits from our living flesh.
Stranger, I'm surprised to see any friendly faces out here.nnDid you meet any Covenant soldiers on the road?
If you're looking for pleasant conversation, find a bard.nnI'm looking for soldiers, not friends.
Flesh is so soft, so easily shredded. I can still feel the rake of their claws.nnWhy did my brother ignore my warnings? Does he feel the same pain I do?
These items are meant for the experienced handler. Otherwise, I can't guarantee you'd reap the full benefits.
Welcome to the war.nnWe're losing ground to Covenant raiders. If we don't hold the line here, they'll push us back to Ebonheart and take all of Zabamat.
Whatever happens, we can't let the Covenant retrieve the Coral Heart.
You've been in the belly of Daggerfall's beast. Did you find <<1>>?
<This soldier was stabbed in the back.>
I'm Holgunn, the Nord commander here in Davon's Watch. My men are the spine and strong arm of the Ebonheart Pact. nnI've heard good things about you. Let's see if they're true.

I'm the Nord commander here in Davon's Watch. We are the spine and strong arm of the Ebonheart Pact.
Welcome to what used to be the front lines, soldier. Something very strange is happening out here.nnI'm just a grunt. And not a very smart grunt, at that. Maybe you can sort things out for me.

Ahknara ambushed us. She used a flask of blinding light to stun us, then ran back through the door behind me.nnWere you able to activate the plates?

Are you here to help? There's much to do, but the Dunmer and Argonians aren't even talking to each other!
Stranger, you've picked a bad time to visit Senie. nnThe volcano's burning up the town! You'd think these thick-headed louts would accept some help.
Look at the devastation! And in the face of all this, they still argue.nnYou can't believe it either, can you?
Stranger, you have come at a bad time. The ground bleeds, and many are hurt.nnIf you wish my time, first you must help.

<This soldier has several stab wounds on her back and neck. The assassins must have ambushed her.>nn<Someone ran across the floor and used the trapdoor in the corner. Strikes-from-Shadows may be down there.>
I don't want to look at my wounds. You do it.
<The nix hound stares at you with unblinking, multifaceted eyes.>
Thanks for helping us on the Starved Plain.nnWith the spirits guarding us, we need not fear on this front.
I gladly gave  my life for victory.
Captain Hjolm will be forever honored, along with the others slain here. Their deaths will fuel our conviction to slaughter the Covenant.

The brazier, did you light it? Did you do anything to it?

Those tents  they seem so far away.nnWhat? So what if I'm lazy?
Someone came! Did Father send you?nnI fell and twisted something. Damn my ankle!
These warmer climes warp our fine northern wood terribly. I feel like I'm constantly making repairs.
Did you hear? There's been another murder!
Hello fellow Pact person. We should do something about all these angry Daggerfall spirits.
What can I do for you?
You're standing a little close, don't you think?
I have heard of your deeds. Finally, we meet!
Why do you insist on interfering, dryskin?
You don't look to be Daggerfall Covenant, and you're not one of ours. Who are you?
You have to get the Heart.

A traveler. This is a strange time to visit Senie.
A traveler! This is a strange time to visit Senie.
Ready to wring some Orc necks?
Well, you're a warm hut in a blizzard.nnWhat news? Could you keep that <<1>> out of the Covenant's hands?
You Morag Tong scum. Let us go right now!
You Morag Tong scum. Let us go right now!

Praise Vivec, child. Tell me you're here to pray instead of fight.nnIt pains me to see this holy site bathed in impure blood.
Um, your pardon. Have you seen any kwama around? Maybe west of the town?nnIf you do, I don't suppose you could lead them to my mine, could you?
I, uh  your pardon. Have you seen any kwama around? Maybe west of the town?nnI don't suppose you could lead them to my mine, could you?
I have phat loots... buy them!

Something must be done about Godrun, and soon.

It's fortunate that you were able to recover the Sacred Thumb. With it, we can continue our work and worship in the area.
Troll's blood! Why have you come for training today? Fort Arand is under threat.nnThe Covenant stands poised to gut us as easily as a horker lazing in the sun.
Thank you for your efforts, friend.
I can't wait to get back to helping the afflicted.
Orcs to the south, mercenaries camped outside by the lake, and now people are missing.nnI'm not sure how much more we can take.
