How do you fight something you can't see? It isn't fair!nnI can't cut the throat of the plague. I can't smash its bones. I can only wait until it fills me with its blackness and takes my life bit by bit.
It's about time you showed up! I was beginning to get a bit charred around the edges.
I told you, we're leaving this forsaken place. I'd rather .nnWait. You're not my husband! What do you want? Narsis isn't safe, stranger. Not that House Hlaalu cares.
I don't suppose you're here to buy a weapon?nnNo, you probably just want me to fix another wagon wheel or something. Everyone just wants to get out of here.
Yes? Is there something you need?
You! What are you doing here? Why do you disturb me?
I'm sure that witch is around here somewhere.
We've won a great victory! I'm eager to hunt down the survivors.
I don't know why I put up with him.
Why has our village suffered so?
Who are you, stranger? Were you sent by the Tribunal?nnNo, of course not. What would they care for the problems of five little people grubbing in the dirt for a living?
I know this place. We made our last stand here, many years ago.nnGone! Why am I here? Why have I been summoned?
Wait. This is where the final battle took place. Why am I here?
Run, friend! Get out of here before the Covenant soldiers come back!nnI'm staying put, so I can direct other survivors to safety. But if I see another Dagger uniform, I'm leaving!
"Just read some old runes," he said. He didn't mention how  active the dead are here.
What are you doing? Hide, fool!
These filthy pirates want to sell us all into slavery. Please, find a way to save us!
A Brother of Strife walks near Ash Mountain, so the Ordinators sent me to learn how bind it. "Read some old runes," they said. "No danger," they said.nnThe dead are very active. I need help.
I know we are few, but we must not fail in what we've come here to do.
I have much to do. The fate of Narsis hangs in the balance!
So you're the guar who raised me.nnThis had better be astonishingly important, or I'll do unspeakable things to your fleshy mortal form.
These cursed shalk are after my blood. They've got me pinned here. Please, help me!
Why? Why did they do this?
You've done us a great service, friend.
There are wolves all around and I have no more house.
You judge us from another era, but you should know: we could have chosen power or chosen death. nnIf power destroyed the enemy, then nothing else matters.
The Chimer were powerful. We thought we could face any challenge. Even at the end, we were arrogant and proud. nnBut I will not believe our sacrifice was in vain.
Have you come to learn more in the ways of healing? I'll be more than happy to show you.
Did you need something? I don't have as many things to sell as I did before the war, but you might see something useful.
I know it seems strange that I'm in this dark place, but the pain of losing him once was unbearable. nnI can't lose him again.
Common filth! You dare to disturb my slumber?
What is this thing, Eanen? Why is it looking at us?
The roads aren't safe, but I haven't a choice if I want to sell my goods, do I? Why don't you buy something from me and make my journey worth the while?
My brothers have awakened! Thank you!
I couldn't find him. Did you?
I had to change my breeches before I came home. Don't tell my father.

I hope this war with the Covenant ends soon, preferably with us slaying their men, selling their women and children into slavery, burning their towns, and salting their fields.nnThose ruthless barbarians deserve no better.
You cannot put the yolk back in its shell.
Why do you meddle in our affairs?
These once-fertile lands have been reduced to ash and dust.nnMy fair <<1>> must be ashamed of me. I am a poor protector.
Have a care, traveler. My lord Hrogar's fields are overrun with hideous Goblins and spiders. Whatever business you have here, best come back another day.
These Goblins are merciless, stranger. They don't feel pity or remorse or fear, and they won't stop until they're killed.
I wish I could make them pay for what they've done!
This once-grand hall has been reduced to ruins.
Watch out, traveler. Troll's bones, the Goblins could be upon us any moment!nnI won't go down easy.

We've been members of the Fighters Guild forever. In fact, that's how my wife and I met! When we retired from all the fighting, it just made sense to go into business selling what we know. And we do know our weapons!
My stock isn't what it used to be, what with the war and all. But I still have a decent selection, if you want to have a look.
These are hard times, my friend. I hope you find something to your liking. I could certainly use the gold.
Some armor can be too light, and some armor can be much too bulky and heavy. But the armor I carry is just right. Take a look and see for yourself.
If you're going to be dabbling in the arcane, I can tell you that quality ingredients are essential. Unless you don't mind singeing your eyebrows, that is.
Ooooh my head. where am I?
No matter the troubles assaulting our fair city, my vault stands strong. You may bank with me in complete confidence. Your personal items will be perfectly safe within our secure facility.
Oh, good! Someone new! I was worried that business would be slow, what with the rumors of war and vampires and all.nnFeel free to look around and don't hesitate to let me know if you need any help!
A fine day for an exhilarating battle! A fine day!
Soon, I'll get the cure they promised!
I saw the Goblins capture Gar. They took him into a cave near the beach.nnPlease, you've got to save my brother!
Nice to see someone who's not walking around looking like their pig just died. Let me know if there's anything you need.
Fell's Run may seem like a strange place for the Fighters Guild, but we try to hold a presence in the major locations.
Need something? I'm a bit busy at the moment, but . What am I saying? No blade is ever sharp enough to suit my tastes.
Greetings, greetings. Let me know if there's anything I can do for you.
Welcome to the Mages Guild in Fell's Run. It's not much to look at, but hopefully someday. We have to start somewhere, right?
Well met! The Vale of the Ghost Snake doesn't get many visitors.
Halt! This quarantine is under the authority of the Maulborn.
The dreugh attacks have killed most of my kinsmen. I thirst for revenge but <<1>>, has stayed my hand.
And what do you think of that  man?
Strangers aren't welcome here. Be on your way.
We don't get many visitors in the vale.
House Redoran has things well in hand.
I hate relying on others, but I owe you my life. I will not forget that. If it wasn't for you and Drathyra, I'd be ashes in our ancestral hearth.
My father is a strong man. Not as much as my mother, but strong enough. He will survive.nnAs for me, I'm going to Cyrodiil. I'm going to kill Daggerfalls.
Thank you for helping me save my mother. I'm sorry I panicked. It won't happen again. nnThere's more steel in me than even my father suspects.
I'm sure the Covenant troops have eaten them all.nnUncivilized savages.
I've never seen Hrogar so drawn down by sorrow. It pains me.
Well, look who's back! Good to see you again.
Siege weapons win wars, no matter what the generals tell you.
Don't go into a Siege battle without the proper gear!
If you question the value of siege weapons, try to take an enemy keep without them!
Hail! <<1>> wants all able bodied fighters to report to him immediately.
So many people have left or simply disappeared. My profits are falling faster than the level of mead in a Nord fest hall. Please tell me you're here to buy something!
By the Three! Good to see you again, my friend.
Rest assured, the Maulborn pose no threat to House Hlaalu. My husband guarantees it.
While you wait for the cure, my fine wares will keep you strong and healthy.
Please don't kill me. I had nothing to do with the ritual.
Welcome, landstrider. Good to see you again.
Ah, the landstrider! Welcome to the war.
I've got a message for you!
How could he be so stupid? I told him where to deliver the shipment. But he thinks he knows everything! That's why things get messed up.nnMy apologies. Just talking to myself. Don't mind me.
Please, you have to get this crazy woman away from me! I've done nothing, but she keeps insisting I'm a smuggler or something.nnI'm innocent!
I have no intention of letting an amateur screw up my investigation.nnTurn around and walk away. Now.
How curious to see a creature like you.
Didn't my messenger reach you?nnNo matter. You're here now. Speak.
Have you seen it? I don't know where it went. I must be cursed!
It's true. I was cowering here when Mavos cast his spell . Don't worry,  I was hoping you'd survive the entire time. nnAhem. Do you know how to bind Balreth?
Father was sure Balreth was the only way to defeat the Covenant army. But it seems he may have been a bit hasty in his actions.
Thank Vivec you're here. We desperately need your help.
Please, help me. My son died before my very eyes. What do I do?
Here to kill me? I wouldn't blame you. But save this mage, at least. nnYou can leave me to die.
I have no quarrel with you. We shall speak.nnBut know that if you would help those trying to murder our Hist, I will speak with my teeth instead of my tongue.
Writhing worm. You have no idea what you've done.
Wretched meatsack. Let me return to the dream of death.
He killed them all. They're all dead.
Say something. Speak now, before I hack you apart!
We were going to expand the plantation. We wanted to trade the useless cat-men for some strong Bretons and Redguards.
He hasn't said anything. Hasn't moved. He's just watching.
You bring Ra-shadda the Idol of the Hollow Moon, yes? Moons guide you, stranger.
Beware, soldier. There's a curse on the keep.
Have you seen my husband? We got separated when those Khajiiti animals started rioting.
Ha ha! It's all green. Can't you see it?
Soldier! There is a curse on the keep!
They say curiosity killed the Khajiit, but that never stopped me before.
My family and I thank you. May the Tribunal bless you for what you have done here. Perhaps we shall meet again.
Thank you for your efforts, friend.
I look forward to our next meeting, friend.
Thank you for your efforts. We shall rebuild our village in another area.
Why do you bother me, outsider?
Watch your step among the Mabrigash, outsider.
I'm a respected House Hlaalu merchant. How dare they treat me this way!
I hope they suffered at your hands!
The undead fascinate me. Their energies are so potent.
Keep your voice down and act like you're helping me.nnI can't go into details. Not here. But I know you've been trying to find the missing people for House Hlaalu.
<Star is a cat. Upon closer examination, you notice a small silver key hanging around the cat's neck. She seems well-trained for a city cat.>
I hate all this waiting around.
At least the plague doesn't hurt the plants. That would be a shame.
I've done nothing wrong, I promise. Please don't take me away.nnI'll find a way to pay for the bread. I swear it!
Living trash. You have no idea what you've done.
Begone! Your living breath pollutes our bone-dry air.
You found us. I apologize for my earlier abruptness. nnWe heard you confirmed that our people were taken.
You must be the one Slips told us about. She said an outsider was hired to find our people.nnThat's a strange thing for an outsider to do, even for Hlaalu gold. What are you really up to?
Madras has a plan. And with your help, it's sure to succeed.
House Hlaalu can lock the gates, but they can't lock up the truth.nnIf the guards won't help, we'll do it ourselves. Damn Hlaalu! Damn the plague! I just want my family back.

How did you get in there? Madras doesn't let just anyone attend his secret meetings.nnWait! You're the outsider working for Councilor Ralden. Please tell me you haven't bought into Madras's foolishness.
Knowing the Withered Hand haven't defiled the Ash'abah honored dead puts my mind at ease.
Knowing the Withered Hand haven't defiled the Ash'abah honored dead puts my mind at ease.
Knowing the Withered Hand haven't defiled the Ash'abah honored dead puts my mind at ease.
Sick workers, poison fumes, enraged kwama  could anything else go wrong?
Glad to see you made it out.
Sorry, I haven't time for pleasantries. We're having a bit of a crisis, here.
Were you successful in the mines?
Come and join us. This spot is safe, above the smelly fumes. Safe for the little scribbles.
Don't judge us too harshly. We do things our own way here.
Everyone screaming, everyone dying. Why do you taunt me, filth?
The wind is alive with butterscotch! Can't you feel it?

Before you ask, yes, I've been following you. No, I have nothing to do with the missing people or the plague. And no, I'm not here to fight you.nnThere, that's out of the way. Feel better? Now let's talk about why Giron wants you dead.
Ralden isn't here. He and Giron left some time ago.nnAnd Giron's connection to the Maulborn makes me a little concerned.
There you are, outsider. I came as quickly as I could.nnMadras and the others left for the ruins. They want to save our people but they're going to get themselves killed.
Curious how some people want to escape the plague, while others continue to arrive.nnI wonder why that is?
I'm such a fool! Why did I think a gang of untrained villagers could handle this? I led them to their deaths, and it's my fault.
Giron betrayed me. He killed our people. Put Llodos plague in the corpses. Said it made it more potent. He bled them into the lake.

What brings you to this gods-forsaken Dark Elf dung hole? The beer in this land is fit only for pigs. Good thing we brought our own.nnHave the Elves asked you to help beat back the Covenant yet? Bah! To Sovngarde with them.
Still alive, I see. I suppose that justifies Naryu's confidence in you.nnDid you find them? How's Ralden? Are they inside?
I've got the key and the location you seek, as promised.nnOur plan might have worked a little too well. You can still hear screams coming out of Madras's house.
Please, you must listen to me!
Giron betrayed me. He killed our people and put Llodos plague into their bodies. Said it made it more potent.nnHe needed a large supply of potential corpses. That's why he wanted Narsis locked down.
Soldier, be warned. There's a curse on the keep.
Things have been strange around the fort lately.
An army travels on its stomach, and this one won't get anywhere without me.
Serving the needs of a fort isn't the same as setting up a shop in a city.
Welcome, traveler. We don't have much yet, but I can show you what's in stock if you like.
The snakes are agitated. They sense something is happening in the Vale.
The pain of losing him once was unbearable. I can't lose him again.
I can't find him. nnSo hard to go on without him.
Soldier! There's a curse on the keep.
Soldier! There's a curse on the keep.
This pain is so hard to bear.

If you're looking for honest work, look elsewhere. There's little enough of that to go around.nnAnything dishonest goes through One-Eye, unless you want to find out how she got that name. Catch my meaning?
Don't trust the mead here, friend. If you're lucky, they'nt done nothin' more than piss in it.
Rich times for some, not for all. Chee-Dooka and I have been  less than fortunate.nnBut, the sea brings new breeze each day. That is the saying, is it not?
No, these breads are Eilara's! No stealing!
Hard enough making a living with the tariffs from Skyrim. Now the elf Houses want their cut! Not to mention the thieves right before me!nnWhen I next head north, perhaps I'll stay there.
I thought coming home would mean the end of hardship. Turns out, It's no easy feat to feed a family in the swamps.
I take my creature comforts as they come. You don't know when you'll next have a warm meal or a dry spot to nap.
I have no reassurance to offer. Do what you think best in the time remaining.
I have nothing to say to you or to the House Redoran tyrants.
<This corpse has stretched, bruised flesh. Its clothes are soaked with blood. Judging from the exit wound in the soldier's back, something tore its way out of her from within.>
Come not to the keep.nnIt is cursed.
No one keeps their forge as hot as an Avani. You'd have to journey to the heart of Ash Mountain to find a fire this strong. nnYou're welcome to work  if you think you can handle it.
My Lady Almalexia bids you carry a message to Disciple Sildras.
Beware the curse of Heimlyn Keep.
Fool. Flee the curse of Heimlyn Keep while you can.
The Llodos plague is a curse upon us! A curse, I say!
I appear at my lord's behest.nnOr perhaps I was always here, and you merely lacked the ability to see me.

Step up, step up. Ahhh you look like a fine player, yes. No silly games for you. No. Not for you. You are a true adventurous spirit, a gambler. Perhaps I can convince you to try a -real- game. What do you say?
We'll all be reunited in Sovngarde, won't we? That's what I tell myself.
If you're planning to use the pass to Mournhold, find another route. It's not safe.
Gods, why did I ever set foot in this stinking pit? Was it duty or stupidity?nnCome to mock me like the rest, have you? Well, fear not. I've no dignity left.
I speak to <<1>>, and only her.
This place has seen better days.
If you're here to complain about that Dominion soldier, I've heard everything already.
Need to report back. Maulborn. They're trying to make the plague stronger.
<<1>>'s the name. I was working as a guard in the trading camp before the Maulborn attacked. nnThis Elven scout was lucky I came along when I did. She was getting her arse handed to her.
He he killed them. They're all dead.

I fear I've done terrible harm to the morale of my people in Ebonheart.nnI will do all I can to convince them to work with House Dres. They, at least, have been constant in their defense against the Daggerfall invaders.
Well, hello there. What can I do for you today?
Well, hello there. What can I do for you today?
Oh boy, oh boy! A Consumer, customer, maybe even a friend. Do you like parfait? Ain't nobody don't like parfait!
I'm eager to prove my worth.
I've heard the stories about Ahknara, but she's a Redguard, not a Daedra.
I've heard the stories about Ahknara, but she's a Redguard not a Daedra. This
Take a look at my goods. Nothing but the best for the brave members of the Ebonheart Pact!
I purchase what I need from our allies.nnFor the Ebonheart Pact! Blood and glory!
What an amazing thing, this Ebonheart Pact. Safety, strength in numbers, and increased profits.nnWhat can I get for you today?
I love our new alliance! Now I can sell to three times as many people!
Are you ready for some action, comrade?
Master Samtri always talks about walking the narrow path, but I just want to learn how to cast spells and such.
Anchors fall from the sky! Daedra spill from the shadows!nnSometimes it feels like we're the only thing keeping this world together. Pray we don't fail.
We learn to anticipate the ebb and flow of Magicka.nnThat's the difference between an acolyte and a mage.
Fear not. I intend no mayhem.
The Eight provide all the protection I need, but I do look good in heavy armor.
I've all manner of potables for the discerning palate. Care to look over my stock?
The path to enlightenment is exceedingly narrow and must be tread carefully. Are you prepared to walk this path?
A chicken in every cooking pot! It's more than a house councilor's promise. It's a way of life when you strive to create the perfect bite!
Anyone can pick up a sword. Learning not to cut yourself with it requires dedication and constant practice.
I love this place! Kemirik knows how to show his customers a good time.
This place is great! I can't wait for my turn to dance in the fire pit.
I get ten percent of whatever I sell, so buy often and buy a lot.
Not all members of House Hlaalu are simple merchants. I deal in alchemy. But I only work with the most advanced practitioners of the craft.
You need something. I know you need something. Something alchemical, perhaps? What do you need?
Welcome to the Flaming Nix. Our fire pit adds a level of entertainment not seen in the other, so-called, finer establishments.
Runecrafting isn't for everyone. You look like someone who's mastered the techniques.
My enchantments are the finest in the land. But quality has a cost my friend, quality has a cost.
Yes, I sell runecrafting supplies. What can I get for you?
If you're looking for enchantments, you've come to the right place. Best in the city. Costs a bit more, but it's worth it.
Welcome, friend. You won't find a better stable in all of Morrowind!
Yes, I'm a Nord. Is that a problem? Are you going to buy something or not?
We always seem to be taking inventory.
My weapons are without equal. They are oiled, sharpened, and polished to perfection. Leave lesser weapons to farmers and footpads. Heroes deserve the best.
I like to write poetry when the forge isn't too busy. Someday, I'll be as famous as Fjokki!
These elites smiths think the sun shines only for them.nnIf they weren't so good, I'd take my business elsewhere.
If you're a smith by trade, I can give you a fair price on our raw materials.
Benus believes that his weapons are without equal. That's only because they've never been tested against my armor.
I really can't talk right now. Master Benus would rather we didn't mingle during business hours.
I erect the spine of welcome. Welcome to the bank of Mournhold.
Don't leave town without the proper equipment! Let me get you outfitted right.
What do you need today? I just received a new shipment, so take a look at what's in stock.
Welcome, friend. What bit of arcane wonder can I sell you today?
My armor can withstand a charging ogrim. Can your armor do that? I don't think so.
You look like someone who appreciates a good weapon.
I know exactly what you need. You won't find better deals anywhere else in the city!
Be welcome and wallow. Gaze upon this wonderful armor and prepare to open your gold pouch very wide.
If you're looking for the Bank of Mournhold, you've come to the right place. Your valuables will be safe with us.
Care to trade in your old bag for a larger one? I'll give you a great deal.
Our curse is misunderstood by outsiders. We wish to remain here in peace, as we always have.
Those nix-hounds won't take me! Won't make me into a husk.nnBled myself with my own blade. No use to them now. That'll show them.
Looking to craft some sturdy lightweight armor? War's at our doorstep, so now's the time.
You look like you can handle yourself in a fight. The Pact needs your help here.
I knew someone would come to free me. Vivec wouldn't allow his priestess to suffer like this.nnHe sent you, didn't he?
Pardon my tears. I recently lost my wife, and .nnI'm sorry. Can I help you?
Who are you? What do you want with me?
I get 10% of whatever I sell, so buy often and buy lots.
Didn't my messenger find you? nnNo matter. You're here now. Talk to me.
You approach the Vale of the Ghost Snake. Tread carefully, outsider.
Visitors to Stillrise Village are rare.nnHave you spoken to our chief? You should pay your respects.
A stranger to Stillrise? You have some surprises in store for you here.nnIf you haven't spoken to <<1>>, you should.
Good day. What are you drinking?
We perform an important service, you know. If not for us, the Dark Elves would never see a massive log or a long, smooth piece of wood  especially the lady Elves, if you know what I mean.
I signed up to guard these wagons for the money. And guarding's the only thing I take money for. You got that?
I tried the drink at the inn, but I think I'll stick with our own mead.nnI can't take this local stuff. It's made out of mold or something.
Some of the boys like to flirt with the Elf girls. I don't know why. They're so little. There's nothing to them!
About time you showed up. nnThose Wood Elves're creeping forward, step by step. I don't like it.
I tried to visit the Maulborn camp. Figured they'd need some work done on their boots. But they sent me away.nnHow rude is that?
The grandmaster is very busy today. Move along.
Shornhelm's in dire straights, but I'll never be sorry we moved here. It was the only way my daughter would get over the loss of her worthless husband.
This Khajiit is not here to challenge. You have won your right to lead. All here will follow you, if you spare them!
Living in Shornhelm's been hard on our family, but we've still prospered more than most people in this poor city.
The Trials are not for the faint of heart.
My father sees my grief as weakness. But I will not forget my husband. Embracing the sadness I feel at his death only makes me stronger.
They came out of nowhere. Attacked the caravan. I'm fine, I just hope my brother's all right.
Don't tell my sister, but I'm not really injured. I'm just terrified.
Yes, yes. Finally, a discerning customer.
We were going to expand the plantation Sell these useless slaves for Breton and Redguard slaves
We were going to expand the plantation. We wanted to trade the useless cat-men for some strong Orcs and Nords.
Hold a moment, friend. You look like a fine specimen of  well, nevermind.nnAnyway, perhaps you'd be interested in helping me with a little  experiment?
This plantation was built on suffering. It's only right that it should end in suffering.

As soon as we finish repairs and fill the cart, we're heading back to Eastmarch.
You're still alive. Good! After I found poor Kanat, I wasn't sure. nnWe've got some help from Narsis. Things are looking up.
I can't believe someone would steal from the Root Stewards. It's unthinkable.

Kaoc! Do you make a habit of barging into houses?

Come closer if you want to work on your technique .

<<1>> is waiting for you on the docks. She has some important news for you.nnI'll get this back to <<2>> and <<1>>, after setting aside a cut for you and your crew. Don't worry. I excel at counting coins.

All these sods puttering about with their nose in dusty books. Frighteningly boring, don't you think?nnI'm tempted to summon up a skeleton or three. It'd liven the place up. Ha!
Can I help you find something to sate your appetite? We have many delicacies here, from all over Skyrim and Morrowind.

Victory requires strength, courage, a good weapon, and a great teacher. Hope you are prepared!

Yes, I am new to  swordplay. But I have known the fine edge of blades since I was hatched. Shall I show you my wares?

Truly talented. And in more than the arts, let me tell you. But quite out of your league.nnI see you making anything but friendly conversation with Attiri, it'll be the last words your tongue says.
Dung-for-brains over here hardly knows the business end of a weapon. If he's going to watch our stock, he needs to learn to use it as well.nnNow, what can I help you with?

No time for talk. One second of inattention, and I'll be a corpse, like the rest.
No time for talk. One second of inattention, and I'll be a corpse, like the rest.

Right up the walk! Step inside! <<1>> has items to dazzle and delight the most jaded traveler!
Zeht's tears, traveler. She weeps for Hallin's Stand.

Welcome to Evermore. Can I interest you in a fine riding beast?
These filthy pirates want to sell us all into slavery. Please, find a way to save us!
I'm lost. Horribly, horribly lost.nnThen again, if you're here, I'm sure you're lost, too.
Welcome to Evermore, home of the best ale in Tamriel!

These soldiers seem nervous. They want to end this fight and move on, but for some reason, the general has them waiting for reinforcements.nnOf course, I don't mind staying for a few more days. I hate packing.
I thought we would be moving on by now, but the general wants us to put up more walls.nnMaybe he's planning something more elaborate. I wouldn't know.
It has been a long time since I've made a sale.
Don't know why I even bother fishing. These damn crows snatch the blasted thing right off the line before you can pull it ashore.
At last! Someone who can appreciate my wares!
What? You just walk up and start talking to everyone you see? Maybe I want to be left alone.nnPox! There's a patrol. Just pretend like you're talking to yourself.
I hope you're not headed for Deepcrag Den.
Quiet! I think I hear something!
Greetings! Have you heard of the once-great Volek family? I'm the last of my line.
Over here! You have the look of someone who deals in gold and blood.
I pray that you will help us, land-strider.
Enjoy the gratitude of Sen Dres.

I've been in port a week. If you can even call this a port.
When you've sailed for as far and as long as I have, the swamps don't bother you much. It's the people that get to me.
Don't mind me. I'm traveling with these folks because they're paying for my drinks.
I don't trust the Shadowscales. Sure, they're on our side. But they're secretive, unaccountable, and all they know how to do is kill.

<<1>> was a kind woman. She tended eggs, you understand? She was a midwife to Argonian hatchlings.nnAnd they butchered her. The Dominion cut her down and left her to rot.
You don't look like much. I could take you.
My scales are dry with disappointment.
Before the Three, as is my right and my duty, I greet you as the eldest of the Brothers Randoro.
Own no weakness or fault. I greet you as one of the performing Brothers Randoro.
Justice does not know sleep, and the honor of your house is yours alone. I greet you as the youngest of the Brothers Randoro.
Welcome to Lukiul Uxith. If you're here to slaughter Covenant soldiers, you should hurry before they're all dead.
Not so loud. You'll betray our position.
Please. Our swamp is being corrupted. I need help to prepare, so I can stave off our destruction.
What is it you wish, child?
If we had an army of heroes like you, we'd never lose a battle.
I owe you a drink, partly for saving us, but mostly for proving that Aanthis was wrong.
Thank you for saving usespecially my friend, Meejapa.nnI'm glad he's alive. I just wish he'd shut up.
You there! What is your name?
<This body has been stabbed multiple times and appears not to have died that long ago.>
Thanks for meeting me here. I'm glad I don't have to face this alone.
If you're another Dominion retainer come to mock our hatching ritual, we won't stop you. Not that we have a choice.
I'm sorry. I don't believe I know you.
This is a disaster! Some scavengers are lost in the mire and I can't spare anyone to go look for them.nnAny chance you can help me?
Tear this room apart if you have to.nnThere has to be something here that can help us against the plague.
Thanks for meeting me. I am glad I don't have to face this alone.
<Belronen Telvanni's corpse remains where it fell in the duel. The only wound he bears is a tiny cut on his arm.>nn<There is a crumpled note tucked into his belt.>

Lord Vivec, I was here when Belronen issued his challenge. He would still live if not for Fenila! She stoked the Telvanni's rage, urging him not to back away from an insult to his honor.nnShe called herself his friend. Curious way to show it.
Thanks for meeting me. I am glad I don't have to face this alone.
Get ready. The lizards should arrive at any moment.

Ah, it's you! Good. We need someone here who can get things done.
With the death of the alchemist Merdyndril, our contract is fulfilled. nnI'm not sure we could have accomplished it without you.
You're full of surprises. Not that I doubted you.nnThanks for your help.
Well. Looks like both of us survived.
So much to be done, and too many strangers nearby.
My turn is coming and I have to get ready.nnIs there something you want?
<This Argonian was stabbed in the back. Her closed hand is still tightly clutching something.>nn<This must Dreams-in-Daylight's body, it matches the description within Lotash's diary.>

The mire provides to me, and I provide to you.

You've found the Mournhold crafters' circle. What're you looking for?
Welcome to the crafters' circle. Feel free to look around.
I can't believe so much of my stock survived that ordeal. My wares're in fine condition. See for yourself.
Hello Traveler! *woof*nnCould you please offer me some of your time? *woof*

Father! Oh, Father! Why did this happen to you?
I was so not ready for this. Tribunal save us!
I hope you drank one of Edrasa's potions. Otherwise, this is going to be a short visit.
These bindings are an indignity. Uncomfortable, too.nnYou, there. Untie me.
Please, I can't get out. I don't want to die.
My wife escaped, but I'll never see her again.
You have to help me. My son died before my eyes. What do I do?
My whole family. Dead. I'll never leave here alive.
Hail! I am Rigurt the Brash. I lead our Glorious Expedition for Nord Cultural Exchange to the Dark Elves.nnExcuse please, Dunmer. The proper term for puny ones is Dunmer. Small, I mean. Not puny.
The imps attacked as I was passing through Deleyn's Mill. Now my wagon is damaged and I'm stuck out here. Perhaps the kind stranger would care to buy something before everything spoils?
I have some items you may find useful, many gifts from nature.
Welcome to Shad Astula. I maintain the school's collection of manuscripts and books.
Who are you that shatters Vox's wards and defies her will? Why hasn't she consumed your soul, as she has with all the others? How very interesting.
Without your help, I would have been food for baby spiders.
Please get me out of here! Do whatever she says.nnYou can't imagine the indignities she's promised me if you fail.
You dare trespass in the Kingdom of Zuuk? Begone!
The prisoner's in the tower. Up the path and enter the tower on your left.
Why do you intrude in the Kingdom of Zuuk? Be on your way!
I still feel the Fang of Sithis clacking at me.nnGet it away from me, quickly!
This is a nightmare. You must do something.
Well met. I'm studying the ruins throughout Shadowfen.nnShould you find anything significant, please bring it to me.
We're all doomed. Almalexia save us!

Clothing, fine raiment here, the finest in Mournhold.

Make haste or soon I will be no more.
I heard Ruvali scream. When it came from below, I took a few swings at it, but we can't kill this thing unless it's in a body.

The son listened when cunning Boethiah whispered in his ear. He tried to steal an artifact from the Tribunal Templethe hammer known as the Judgment of Veloth.nnMany of the Tribunal's faithful died gloriously that day!
I don't see this thing. Ruvali said you chased it down here.
He hasn't said anything. He hasn't moved. He's just watching.

Please, you must help the woman! I beg you!
I'm sorry. I don't believe I know you.

Welcome back to the fight, my friend.nnThis mountain's been rumbling for hours, and we're stuck out here, blades in our hands and no one to stab.

My friend. I see you've come to stop me. Thank Vivec you're here.

Thank you for rescuing Elynisi. I hope you can help us.
Can't keep fighting. We need help. Our village  is under attack.
I never thought I'd be so happy to get back in this inn.
Need help. Our village is under attack. Defend it.
Impressive! Her memory detected your presence! Look how her power grows!nnYour time is running out. This is so exciting! I think you'll have only one chance to stop her.
There's nothing here but withered roots and dead earth, but it's too soon for Tanval to join the dust. He still has a part to play.
Look at him, my friend. Garyn's death has ruined him.nnHistory won't remember him as a great general. They'll just remember him as this.
You shattered my wards. You entered my Hollow in service to a false god.nnI'm impressed you made it this far. But your interference ends here!
We've already dispatched messengers to Kragenmoor. Shor's bones, I hope we don't need to evacuate Ebonheart.
My gods have forsaken me, but you radiate divine favor.nnI sense power in you. Have you come to set us free?
The power in your hands is familiar, yet I cannot place it. It almost feels .nnOh, what I would give to be able to feel anything. To feel the touch of wind on my face, my hand on another's.
A visitor? Strange. Your hands. Your body. Solid. Whole. nnWhere did you come from?
Please  I must have peace if I am to complete this ritual.
<<1>> goes through difficult times. Few friends, many foes.nnSo? Are you friend, or foe? Best to learn now, when turning you away is a simpler affair.
Our leader, dead by an unknown hand. Now a stranger arrives, unannounced.nnCurious.
Please  I must have peace if I am to complete this ritual.
No time to wait around while some other House grabs this spot. House Hlaalu has coin to make!nnWe'll honor the fallen by doing what we know best. Filling our pockets with gold.

You bring chaos and destruction to our ordered afterlife. Why are you here?
Return with the stone, or we have nothing more to discuss. Follow the magical steps we used to bind Sadal.
Mortal! Come closer. I cannot harm you in my current state.
My gods have forsaken me, but your gods favor you. nnI sense great strength in you.
You've done it! At last! The power in your hands. It's Veloth's blessing, isn't it? nnI remember now. I was a priest at the shrine before the woman came. Vox. I will have my revenge!
You've done it! By the Three, you've done it!
I've never met anyone like you. I doubt I ever will again. You've saved us.
It's as though the storm still blows, but I can see the sun on the horizon.
We must reforge the links in Sadal's chains, or we'll all be ashes in his inferno.
You saved the woman. You have my thanks.
I spent three days haggling over treacle-sap and fermented fish sauce. And look how well that's worked out for me!nnThree curses on their house, those lizards.
Yes, I'm waiting to speak to the Shadowscales. My business is my own, and no one else's.
The Shadowscales are a necessary evil for governing so many provinces, yet we cannot stand by as they continue their senseless killings.nnWe will have answers, or they will pay the price in blood.
The Daedra. They drove me mad. And now they've done the same thing to Mother. nnIt can't go on. She must be stopped. Go. The Reservoir of Souls stands open. We'll join you on the other side.
I don't plan to sit here and wait to be seen.nnThese lizards saw fit to murder without asking questions. Why should I not do the same?
Thank you for rescuing Elynisi. I hope you can help us.
I never thought I'd be so happy to be back in this inn.
I'll answer no questions, tail-lifter. I spit on your snout! Do what you will with me, for I welcome death.
Come to fight, have you? All right, let's do this.
I was sure I was going to die. Thank you!
Please, I did nothing wrong! I'm a simple merchant. This is all a misunderstanding!
You walked in our skin and wrought our judgment. You exposed the lie at the core of all truth.nnThis may be lost on you. It does not matter.
How did you make it through the Daedra, stranger? nnWe're having a damned hard time just holding back the tide.
<The arbiter stands dormant. A loose panel slides open to reveal five empty sockets and five large pegs within its chest cavity.>nn<The panel bears a small but legible inscription.>
<This construct stands dormant, obviously missing some crucial gears and pistons. An inscription reads, "Fix me.">
<This  construct stands dormant, obviously missing some crucial gears and pistons. An inscription reads, "Fix me.">
<A dead Imperial lies in the sand, his skin blistered as if struck by lightning.>
Have we met before? There's a familiar air about you.
You are doing well, valiant one.
You gained the decanter. There was an echo here, but now it is silent. The defilement begins to lift from Selfora.
I have shown you everything I can remember.
We have to stop Vox here and now. This power is not hers to control.
Dominion troops have been spotted in this area. Steer clear, if you've a mind to keep your head.
The Tribunal will not stand for this. Even in death, life, whatever this isI can't allow Vox to continue.
Another visitor to <<1>>? This isn't exactly the main route.
We won't last much longer. Every day, the cannibals get more desperate.

Excuse me for not rising. I'm not as spry as the hatchling I once was.nnLook out there, outsider. What do you see? Sadness? What of the ones who can never find their way to this place of rest? What of the ones lost to us forever?
Hold the tower, he said. Keep the ferals in check, he said. If we ever get out of this awful place, I'm going to demand hazard pay.
Am I cursed to watch the world go on without me?nnWere my crimes that great?
We're pushing them back! We'll keep them hammered. You get that next ward down!
Balreth is too powerful. Portals everywhere. We're doomed.nnWho are you? Where did you come from?
You're not my acolyte. Where did you come from?
<The construct tilts left and right, like it's considering which way to go.>
Who are you? How did you get past the flames?
I knew someone would come. I never gave up hope.
Your reason surpassed the arbiter's trap. In doing so, you revealed yourself to us.nnYou do not fully comprehend. Such is your imperfection.
I knew I wasn't abandoned. The Three watch over you!
It's good to see you alive.
I'd heard that the roads outside Cyrodiil weren't safe for travel, but I had to see for myself. Perhaps I should have stayed home.
Balreth is too powerful. Portals everywhere. We're doomednnWait, where did you come from?
I am returned to my customary ethereal vigor.nnThanks to you, my child.
It is good to have our city back. My steel has been sullied by the touch of Imperial dogs. Soon, we strike back!
The Imperials fled with their tails between their legs. They headed southeast, to some dig site. A Dwarven ruin. Dogs are probably going to make a fortune from their finds.
News Imperial defeat is never bad news, my friend.
I worry for the other settlements in Bangkorai. The Imperials won't just lie down in a ditch.
Tidyn's gone, I'm afraid. I'm all that remains of his too short life.

My Lady has not forgotten us.nnI should never have doubted her. She has released us and given us our freedom.
I need more material. I hope you got the joke.
Have you spoken to my wife? Me, either.
Where would our Khajiiti friends find work, if not with us?

Justice knows no sleep. Neither does profit. Where there's trouble, prices go up. That's why I'm here.
My ambitious apprentice seems to be in some trouble.
It would have been perfect! I had such plans for the goblinization spell matrix.
Please, kind serjo. Would you help me find my cat?nnI swear, it's like he slips out the door every single day.

You know what would make me very, very happy? Being left alone.
I'm not sure what this is all about. Politics, no doubt.
This is official Fighters Guild business. If you want to join, find our hall over there in Daggerfall.
This is where our end began.
Beware! This is a place of angry death.
Stranger, are you interested in earning a few coins?
Well, I see that my considerable investment in you wasn't a total waste.
Tomorrow will be better! Is it tomorrow yet?
I've been working the Deepcrag Den for years and I've never heard of a single instance of a kwama attacking a handler. Something very strange is going on.
Honor to you, traveler. Name's Naril. I'm guessing you're new in town and need some work?nnIt's a bit of luck we met, because I need some help in a business deal.
Welcome to the Fish Stink. What can I get you?
You did it. The Echo of Vox is defeated and the fires and spirits have dissipated.
Up on the hill looking over the town there is an old temple. We are hoping that others have fled there from the destruction.
Hi, I'm a test NPC for verifying various quest bugs.
What brings you to this stinkhole?
Poor Valen! All that drinking has really taken its toll.
I have plenty to do without constant interruptions.
Honor to you and your house, traveler. nnSay, you look like a smart one. Any interest in a business arrangement?
About time you got here! I've been dodging spiders for what seems like forever.nnWait, you're not Raynor.
Stranger! Stranger! Stranger! I require your immediate assistance.
You've done well, for a mortal.
We want no trouble, outlander. My injury doesn't keep me from stringing a bow.

Divines bless you, friend! I am a good man who's fallen on hard times. I have eleven starving children who will surely die without a morsel to eat today.nnWon't you spare a gold for an honest man and his adoring children?
I wouldn't want to be stuck here forever myself.
It's a shame that some of the kwama have to be put down.
<This guar's body was ripped open, and it's partly devoured. The beast that killed it might be nearby.>
You there! Come over here  quietly. Don't let them spot you.
Even in death, I feel trapped here. Part of my soul is tied to this prison.
We were told to expect you, citizen.
Prepare yourself, muthsera. What happened here was terrible.
I can't spare a moment for another tryst. Oh! Excuse me, I thought you were someone else.
I find this village refreshing in its innocence, don't you?
<This skeleton is covered with a thin layer of dust. A journal lies just beneath its rib cage.>
My brewing skills are unmatched, for one who must work with dregs.
You'll have to wait with the rest if you're seeking passage, f'lah. I don't care if King Emeric himself is banging on the gates. These manifests need to be checked and filed before we embark.
By the skull of the saint! Sacrilege, blasphemy, and heresy!
Dithisi pays me well to make sure there's no trouble. So do me a favor and don't start any.
The Tanval Blades have pushed us out of the city. I don't know how we'll get them out of there. The grandmaster seems to bend to their every whim.
I won't let this mockery continue.
If you value your life, go no further. The <<1>> does not welcome outsiders, even moreso with our current woes.nnEven wardens have been turned away. Don't let it concern you.
<This mudcrab's shell is discolored, as if from poison. The beast that killed it might be nearby.>
<This vanguard is dead. His armor is deeply dented, and the disjointed look of his limbs suggests crushed bones. The creature that killed him might be nearby.>
<This vanguard is dead. Her armor is deeply dented, and the disjointed look of her limbs suggests crushed bones. The creature that killed her might be nearby.>
Hello, traveler! I am but a humble merchant searching for new markets for my fine goods.
If you want to join the Fighters Guild, you should visit our Guild Hall in Daggerfall city.
Bakkhara, one of our Khajiit guild members, traveled to the Elden Tree in Grahtwood to look for rare alchemy components. Everyone's worried about her.
This is no place for wanderers.
This is no place for wanderers.
You have far outstayed your welcome in our home.nnThis farce must come to an end.
I don't know what convinced Bakkhara to think going into Dominion territory was a good idea. Sure, she's a Khajiit, but that jungle is dangerous!
We can't survive much longer here. Every year, the cannibals are more desperate.
They're going to turn me into one of the unliving. You've got to save me!
I don't want to die. Please!
I don't want to be a zombie! Save me!
They're going to turn us into zombies. You've got to help me!
Word is that Bakkhara found something big going on under the Elden Tree.nnThat Khajiit always lucks out!
Bakkhara has a good nose for trouble, by which I mean she seems to actively find it all the time. Who would have thought that the Worm Cult had a foothold beneath the Elden Tree?
All my bags are genuine Skyrim auroch hide.nnThere isn't one stitch from any of those weird critters around here.
Forgive my wheezing. The road from Dhalmora is long and my stock is ample. I could have loaded my burden onto a Guar, but I can't bring myself to do it. They look too much like family.
It's a bad time to visit Davon's Watch. The Daggers could come over the walls at any moment.nnYou should buy some of my father's armor. You won't find better in all of Stonefalls.
As far as you know, the leather in my boots isn't from anyone in my family.nnExcuse me. That's a joke.

Welcome to Narvyn's Arcane Emporium. Glad you found us. And by us, I mean me. Because a mage needs no one. Just his mind and good equipment. And every mage knows the best equipment can be found at Narvyn's.nnAm I going too fast for you?
I do not like the Khajiit, but Bakkhara was at least one of us. Why she crept off to Valenwood's Elden Tree, I will never know.
Why don't you grab a drink and join us?
Hello, stranger. Just talking about the giant rats around here. nnHectur, the owner, goes after them like he's a great hero. He thinks it makes him look brave.
Pardon me, I'm showing this scale sister around town before we take up blades for the Pact.
Stupid Khajiit! It's no wonder we made slaves of them. Bakkhara is going to waste her gifts creeping around Valenwood.
That Bakkhara has more luck than any Khajiit has a right to possess.
Leave it to a Khajiit to stir up a pot with the Worm Cult and some crazy Bosmer.
I've been beaten lower than a dock rat. What's it to you?
What took you so long? And who's your sparky new friend?
Don't know who you are, but you should get out if you can!
In all my years, I've never seen anything like this.
If you value your life, go no further. The <<1>> does not welcome outsiders, even moreso with our current woes.nnEven Vicecanons have been turned away. Do not let it not be a concern to you.
What can I do for you?
Are you here to help me out, recruit?
Good timing. I think I almost have this contraption figured out. Did you get the parts?
Looking to shape some metal? I've got what you need.
Were you successful in the mines?

They say their spirits are here, you know. The lost souls who can't return to the soil. They say that this Vox  she enslaves them to do as she pleases.nnDo you think that's true? Are they not truly free from life's burden?
We're safe. I would prefer not to do that again.
My shield brother is gone. He died as well as anyone could.nnLet's return to Kragenmoor and drink to his memory.
Now that you have gathered the necessary components, we must begin to combine them and place them accordingly.nnWe'll need to find an area where the lost spirits emanate from a central area.
Give me some room. I'm trying to relax down while we're in port.
You spare some gold? I'd do anything for a bottle of - urp! For a bottle of, uh, whatever.
Meht, my mouse, is not feeling well. His last meal sits ill with him. I will stay with him until he gets better.
It is good to see another friendly face. Most let our current troubles weigh heavily, but I prefer to see them as challenges.nnAre we not to take challenges as a sign of Sithis' love for us?

We have few supplies left, but no merchants are allowed on our grounds for the foreseeable future. Maybe I should send out our agents with a shopping list to get the sundries we need.nnBy the Sap, I tire of this task.
Your pardon. I know you have urgent business, but I must entreat your aid.
You have to help me. I watched my son die before my eyes. What do I do?
My whole family. Dead. I'll never leave here alive.
Did you harvest the kwama cuttle?
<The corpse of an Argonian female lies in the dirt. Even though her body is slashed and burned, she appears to be dressed in the accoutrements of a tree-minder.>
Hello, traveler! I am but a humble merchant searching for new markets for my fine goods. Can I interest you in a morsel of food? Perhaps you would prefer a cool drink?
Raynor showed up right after you went inside. nnWe heard scary noises from behind the door. What was in there?
I appreciate the help you gave my sister, even if she is rash and impetuous. Was the control rod useful?
<This skeleton's bones show signs of abuse. Hidden beneath its bones, a small journal has survived the years.>
<This skeleton's bones show signs of abuse. Hidden beneath its bones, a small journal has survived the years.>
<This skeleton's dry bones barely conceal an old journal.>
<A skeleton lies here. Whatever armaments it may have worn at one time are gone, but a journal remains behind.>
Beware! This is a place of angry death.
I should do my best to comfort this man. He's dying.
I like the ambiance out here.nnThere's a quiet in the air. So pleasant compared to that screaming from below.
Stretch your tail here in peace.
Be welcome and wallow, soldier. We aid Mistress Reesa in her humble works.
What are you doing here?nnNo matter. I have goods to trade. They're just trifles, except for that odd statue.
Haven't seen you before, are you new here?
I hate them rats! If I see any more of em in my kitchen, I'll stomp em myself!
What? What are you doing out here?
Three bless you! We're grateful for your help.
For speed on the battlefield, light armor is the best choice!
I've been expecting you. I'm the Nord commander here in Davon's Watch. We are the spine and strong arm of the Ebonheart Pact. nnI've heard good things about you. Now you work for me.
Protection and speedthat's what my armor offers!
This one offers weapons to fit every hand!
My wares are small but powerful. Don't risk battle without their protection!
Light armor is for cowards who plan to run. Invest in heavy armor and you will never regret it.
I'm glad you got back safe.nnSince the merchants have returned, I decided to stick around for a while.
What a pleasant surprise! I didn't think you'd get out of that gorge alive, but I'm happy to have been wrong.
Those pirates are digging  and drinking. We can take advantage of that.
You look like someone who appreciates armor that doesn't slow you down!
Why wear armor that won't stop a dagger or that will rust if it rains? Try my armor on for size!
My weapons will keep you alive out there, warrior!
Small items pack great power. My wares will make a believer out of you!
I sell the best protection available. Anything less will leave you dead on the battlefield!
You go into battle unprepared, expect to die. Equip yourself well, warrior.
While heavy armor suits clods who plod around the battlefield, light armor is best for the nimble of foot and mind!
The wise choose both protection and speed, qualities in which my armor excels!
It's the little things that make the difference in battle, friend. See for yourself!
When some Elf is poking at you with his little sword, you'll be glad you bought good armor from me!
I suppose I must now see to the farm. nnIt won't ever be the same, you know.
Three gods. One faith.nnI trust you have practiced your devotions for the day.
I'm going to die and rot in this swampy grave. No hope.nnI can't even get a dry pair of socks! Can't a soul die in a dry pair of socks?
Don't touch me. You stink of life.
I'd never give up my invitation!
No way! Get your own invitation!
I've waited all my life to go to the Academy.
What? Give up my invitation? Never!
I'm glad you're with us on this.
You want me to give you what now? Nope. Not gonna happen.
Those pirates aren't just digging. They're drinking, too. Good.
What do you want? Do you have an invitation?nnNo invitation, no passage.
I can't wait to get to the Academy! I want to become an officer and help lead the Pact.
The instructors think they'll be able to contain my innate power. Ha!
This is official Fighters Guild business. If you want to join, find our hall over there in Daggerfall.
I may not look it, but I'm glad to see you.
I'm new to the Guild, but I'm ready and eager to help out.
My squad's heading to Aldcroft. We'll show these Daedra what it means to face the guild's steel!
Tell me, how did your invitation arrive?nnIn the claws of a bird of prey? In the fist of a charmed giant? I got mine from a terrifying ghost!
I've never been this far from home. I can't believe I'm doing this.

Everyone here's given up. They're just waiting to die. They all make me sick.

Cold  cold  since the accident, always so cold.nnOh! I didn't see you there.

Up in the morning, down at night. Morning comes, they're up again!nnThe trees are ready for a fight. Watch where you step! They do

Thanks for helping me back there. I don't want to think about what those rieklings were going to do to me.

The body is bound and gagged. Bloody gaps where scales were forcibly removed appear on his body. There is no poisonous blackening around the wounds.nnBesides the plucking of scales, there is no evidence of physical violence.

Shandi has much to do, much to do. Rhymes don't find their own way into words, no.
<A skeleton lies here. Whatever armaments it may have worn at one time are gone, but a journal remains behind.>
Stop staring and close your mouth or I'll call a guard.
Nice to see a friendly face around here.
Who knew that war mostly consists of sitting around and waiting for something to happen? I was promised action!
Just because I'm not a soldier doesn't mean I can't defend myself. I am a Nord, after all.
Oh, hello. Are you here to see my grandfather?
What business do you have with me, stranger?

I hate all this sitting around and waiting.
Pinooh is always happy to meet new people.

I'm worried about my twin brother, Thalm. nnHe's down there with those stinking Stormfists. Not a true Nord in the bunch. Not a one!

Go away. I don't want them to hurt my husband, Ogmann. If they see us talking, they're liable to kill him.

I need to keep busy or I'll worry so. I don't like these Stormfist thugs. Don't like them a bit.

My younger brother, Holguss, is in the mine. I promised our parents that I'd look after him, but I never should have let him follow me from Windhelm.
Can't talk. Very busy. Leave me alone.
Stupid Fildgor. He thought he could just force us to help him.nnHa! We showed him.

I feel so helpless. I wish there was something I could do that wouldn't just make the Stormfists angry.
It feels good to have those rotten Stormfist thugs out of our hair. Thanks!
My wife toils away in the mine while I stand here and wait for my stew to boil. What a life!
Hjolard sad. All my friends are gone.

Greetings, Master Drenduf. As always, your memories are alive in me. How may I serve?
I need help. Things haven't been normal for a long time.
The cultists. They came out of nowhere. Aera. She was leading them!  She demanded I join the cult. nnSurprised  surprised her.
It felt good to hold a sword again.
Resilient. Determined. I like you. I take it you've dealt with my would-be assassin?
Told you something bad was going to happen.nnI wasn't going to let you walk into this trap alone. So I followed you.
We've been overwhelmed by Reachmen led by a Ghost Giant!
Told you something bad was going to happen.nnI wasn't going to let you walk into this trap alone. So I followed you.
Work is so much better without Fildgor's ruffians standing over us.
I'm going to kill that old Dunmer. He's probably laughing, enjoying a drink, thinking me dead.

Thank you for all your hard work here in Fort Amol.nnI can't say that Vurlop was as useful as I'd hoped, but he served his purpose, right? I mean, just look at me! Stunning, am I not? A Breton leading the Nords. Who would have thought it?
My sturdy little assistant! Where have you been?
The trick is to look busy and not draw attention to yourself.
Isn't <<1>> just charming? He's seen so much, yet he told me he's never seen anything so beautiful as. As. nnOur fort. Er. Excuse me.
King Jorunn's breathing is shallow. The poison Dhalen used. It's tainted. Daedric.nnI'm not sure what it's doing to this poor man, but I don't think he will survive.
I can't believe the Stormfists had the audacity to disrupt this proceeding and attack the Nord king. Their actions are so  undignified.
Where's my father? What did our so-called allies do to him?nnI'll kill every single Argonian and Dark Elf myself if my father's been harmed!
This is not the best time to visit Lost Knife Cave.
My twin brother, Thalm, is safe and sound. Thanks for helping him.
I hope the trolls stay in the west dig. We have enough problems as it is.
I've hidden weapons around the mine, just in case Fildgor's goons come back. We won't get caught with our pants down again!
I'm glad that's over. I don't think Fildgor's fools ever realized how little we actually produced for them.
Can you distract Ganthis Fancypants so my brother and I can sneak off to get a drink? There's not much mead in Shadowfen, and what the Argonians drink  well, I'd rather taste rotmeth.nnNo? Oh, well.
My brother <<1>> and I haven't broken anyone's bones in days.nnHe gets twitchy. Don't bother him.
We'd best be on our way. If they turn on each other so easily, who knows what they'll do to us!

Be careful if you're going through to Treehenge. The spriggans have been on guard ever since the Worm Cult's invaded. nnI haven't been able to convince them to let anyone pass. If I don't get to the grove soon, it'll be too late.

Yes, I'm Haraldar's sister. Mother demanded at least one female to help even things up a bit back home.nnI'm happy to see the meadery up and running again. We'll do our best to live up to the Voljar family's standards.
The last sunset stained the land like a great battle. It seemed a portent.nnWho knows what the next eve will bring?
Don't sit here and chat. Our enemies are everywhere!
You did great work today. Thank you.
Know what I like to do? Fish!
Feels good to remove my helm for awhile. I can't stand helm hair.
Have you seen all the Pact soldiers? Fort Amol is crawling with them!nnAnd do you know what that means? My till is full!
So many new people to meet. So little time.
Fort Amol sure is busy. The inn needs lots of mead and wine.
What  what do they put in that meat? Meal? Mead? Mead! It's so yummy!
This mead's going to give me a headache. It'll be massive. I'm sure of it. But first, I'm going to get very, very drunk. nnYou should join me.
Nothing like a crowded inn full of good food, good drink, and good company to bind the Pact together.
These Stormfists and their Orc allies are starting to get on my nerves. They better give us the order to attack soon or I might have to deal with this situation in my own way.
I really only know four chords, but no one seems to mind.
You've done well. Now that the sphere is safe, we can mop up what remains of these dungy Sea Vipers.nnThe Thalmor thank you for your assistance.
The Nords are an interesting people. Always drinking. Always fighting. Always happy.nnIt makes me wonder what's wrong with Fildgor Orcthane.
These soldiers don't appreciate my music. They'd rather sing along to bawdy drinking songs. I wish I knew some.
Even officers need to relax every now and then. And an inn! The last place my troops camped was cold, hostile, and barren. And we ran out of mead.
Glad you're back. We've got a little problem.
There's got to be a clue here somewhere.
I find that quiet contemplation helps me prepare for battle.
<Her body appears to have been mauled by an animal.>
<This Nord male appears to have been stabbed to death.>
You'll not get a word out of me.
Your courage and compassion are welcome, but I fear it's far too late for anything to be done.
I need to keep my skills sharp, but that tree isn't a very challenging target. It doesn't move or shoot back or anything.
A newcomer, eh? I hope you'll stay for dinner.
Welcome to Windhelm and to the finest stable in the city! We also run the best inn, if that's what you're looking for. It's right over there.
Sure, we have the best stable, but you're better off at the Sober Nord. It's much nicer than our place.
What can you tell me about Nord mating rituals? I'm not sure how to respond to some of the things Innbild has been suggesting.
That Nurara sure is great! Did you see how I impressed her?
Welcome to the Cold Moon Inn. We only attract the lowest class of customers. No offense.

I continue to work on my masterpiece. The one song that will win the heart of the woman I can't live without.nnShe'll surely swoon and accept my hand in marriage the moment she hears it. I  just need to finish it first.
Were you able to catch Thorulf?
A grim day. Who could have seen this coming?
Stay back. I know what I have to do.
Stay back. I know what I have to do.
Grandfather is himself again. I can hear it in his voice. We owe you a great deal.
What happened? I heard a terrible commotion from below.nnDid heis my brother dead?
Hi there! I'm Undead Green Flavor Clippy!
Furu's been leading us around for weeks now. She keeps promising she'll find us a new home and some work so we can settle down.nnIf promises were gold, we'd be wealthy misers by now!
I greet you in the traditional manner of my people.
I'm learning how to use my brains!
Well met! Let me buy you a drink, my newfound friend.
If you need something, please talk to Master Benus. I have a lot of work to do today.
You're not one of them! nnPlease, get out before it's too late!
I do not want more trouble. It's bad for business. And business is often trouble enough, yes?
Please, stay and browse. If something catches your fancy, Jainda will put it aside for you.
Brother says I'm too small to fight. I'll show him. I'll wet my claws on his blood!
This one feels a storm brewing. My fur's standing on end. Hurts my old joints to be up and about.nnBest stay inside until it passes, kitten.
You'd think my kitten brother had learned after a few cuffings. Stubborn takes a lot of licks to beat out of the young ones.
Hrr, what'sit want from Fazaddu? No more room, no more. Bring more sugar next time.
Greetings, honored one. I trust your travels have been pleasant?
You talk to the girls, that's fine. You want more, you talk to me.
When I asked for a room, I wasn't expecting a mat and some linens. Ah, well. My time of riches is far behind me.
No caravans, no kids. Protection is extra. Want me to kill an Orc'll cost you more, but I'll kill Elves for free.
I work all day, then they yell at me for napping. Jainda's tongue is too quick to lash.nnShe probably needs a nap too.
Fighting only hurts those that cannot defend themselves. And with the troubles the Houndsmen have brought about, I thought it was wise to prepare.nnI see now that I may have been  mistaken.
Get out of here, I'm busy.
Spare a coin for a stranded traveler, friend?
If <<1>> asks for gold, don't give him any. nnHe's got this crazy idea that he's a stranded traveler. He's lived here all his life! Too much sugar for that one.
Is it time for feasting yet? I'm starving!
This place is a mess! Maybe you've time to wander about, but we've work to do!
Silvenar, Green Lady  who cares? Our city's in shambles because of them.
I'm not usually a gossip, but when you hear about Dunmer in Malabal Tor, it's hard not to talk.
Never trust a Dark Elf. My mother said their skin is a reflection of their soul.
Praise the Silvenar! Praise the Green Lady! Pass the rotmeth!
Nothing like a feast after a hard-fought battle.
All that fighting works up my appetite. I could eat a whole roast mammoth leg, bone and all!
Hope you're not here to buy eggs. This celebration's all but cleaned me out!
I've brought everything to the celebration! Well, what little the Hound didn't devour.
Fortunately, the Houndsmen didn't destroy all my stock!
I know all the best songs. And if I don't, I make them up.
Welcome to the Fighters Guild outpost in Silvenar! Have a look around, and don't be shy!
Bright blessings! Are you here for training?
There's nothing like fresh meat washed down with aged rotmeth! This is the best posting I've ever had with the Guild!
You have business with the Guild, hrr?
Not right now. I'm much too busy to talk.

I've visited every known Ayleid well in Cyrodiil, yet I still have no clue as to how they work or why they exist. The Ayleid culture was so interesting  aside from the slavery, torture, and cruelty, of course.
I won't tell you what he has planned for you.nnI can keep a secret  unlike someone else I know.
My prince said that if you don't put on a good show, I'll get to show you how it's done.
He told me you'd be back!nnI can't wait for you to entertain me. It sounds so exciting!
There was a scream and the sound of fighting. When we arrived, Golun was dead. It happened so fast.
You're safe! I thought Boethiah meant to destroy you too. Glad I was wrong.
You stopped the ritual, praise Y'ffre!nnThe Worm Cult failed to summon Mauloch! One less Daedric Prince for Malabal Tor to worry about now.
Never seen a guar spook that easily. What a mess!nnSomething I can help you with?
If we don't get underway again soon, I'm ruined. Ruined!
Father needs to calm down. Silla just gets skittish around mages. All those loud booms. It's not her fault!
My prayers are answered!nnPlease, lend me your talents for a time. My comrades have been captured.
Please, I require assistance. Maormer attacked our ship, and captured some of the crew.
Hail, friend. This is a sad day for the guild, but I'm glad we'll perform this terrible duty together. I still can't believe Sees-All-Colors betrayed us.
Well met, friend. Aelif has sworn to pursue the traitor <<1>> into Oblivion itself so that justice may be served. Aelif knows that you will execute the sentence.
There's something wrong across the river. Trolls! They don't usually get this close to major settlements.nnI hope they don't decide to come over here.
Darkwater, across the river, is crawling with trolls. The poor Argonians that were living there probably ended up as troll food.nnI can't think of a worse way to go than that.
Nice weather, eh? For the season, I mean.
You handled yourself pretty well in the caves. Impressive work.nnWe'll be fine, now that the captain's safe again.
The Stormfists have been dealt with and the duplicates rounded up.nnBut whatever poison attacks the King grows worse with each passing hour. We can't help him without more information.
Those who give the orders, whether intended or not, can alter any outcome.
Shor's blood! You're a serious one, aren't you? Why not stop and enjoy the springs with us?
<The sabre cat-mauled corpse of the Worm Cultist is settling into the mud. It will be devoured by scavengers before long.>
Velyn Harbor's being overrun. We have to do something!
The Ra Gada came out of nowhere! Velyn Harbor is under attack!
Velyn Harbor's usually safe. Why'd they attack now?
We did what had to be done.
Molag Bal lost a powerful servant today, thanks to you. And, because of your wisdom, I can continue Meridia's sacred work to resist the God of Schemes.
target: Molag Bal ha perso un potente servitore oggi, grazie a te. E, grazie alla tua saggezza, posso proseguire il sacro lavoro di Meridia per resistere al Dio degli Intrighi.

source: Please  help me! I don't want to die!
I don't know what to do! Tell me what to do!
We fled Darkwater Crossing when the trolls attacked. If not for Stormy-Eyes, we wouldn't have found this place.
We were sleeping. There was a rumble and some shouting.nnNext thing I know, Pulls there grabs my arm and yells that we have to go. Those trolls. They almost got us.
All my supplies, my stock of goods. All smashed by some oaf of a troll! I'm ruined!
I don't have a lot left, but I split my supplies with the rest of the camp.
The Skald-King. Bah! He gave us Darkwater Crossing and what good did it do us?nnHe probably knew the trolls were coming. Probably sent them our way!
Stormy-Eyes, he's special. We owe our lives to him a dozen times over.
This one is ready now. As mud is my mother, no trolls shall pass.

The King has been good to us, and we're grateful. We came here after the Aldmeri attacks on our land and the King gave us Darkwater Crossing. Even helped us rebuild it.nnI just wish he had provided soldiers to protect us, though.
<The body of a dead Worm Cultist.>
Sister-of-Wind was injured when the trolls attacked. She's still unconscious and I'm worried about her.nnStormy thinks he can save her, but he needs supplies that were left behind when we fled.
Too much to do and too little time.
Laughs has what you need to slick your crest or spin your tail.
The Lieutenant died for Velyn Harbor. We should remember his sacrifice.nnIn his name, I think I can help out a little more, too.
I never thought we'd have to take up arms ourselves to protect Velyn Harbor, but the city's worth it!
It's been a long time since I've handled a weapon.
Nice to see you again, friend. Have you tried the mead? I didn't think Roruld could do it, but I'm happy to say I was wrong.
That was well done. I'm sure the Wood Orcs will be back, but we now have a foothold on this side of the bridge.nnWe'll need to keep fighting, though, if we want to hold it.
Dralof found this amazing hot spring. It really opens the pores.
Isn't it nice out here? The water's so warm and bubbly!nnTake off your armor and soak with us.
You're back! Did you get the bath salts?
Did you bring the bath salts? They say they make the water tingle!
You're still dressed? The hot water can't do its thing if you don't jump in!
No more! I can't work anymore! You can't make me!
Poor Sister! I've never seen such terrible injuries!nnStormy said that everything would be all right. Told me to sit and rest. I hope he can really save her!
Did you bring the items I requested?
The spirits told me you were close.nnI spoke to the Ternion monks. They admitted the King and the Prince, but not me. I left the fold. They remember that. But they will help the King.
I'm glad to see a friendly face.nnYou are friendly, right?
I'm searching for ingredients for a potion. It will make me grow a full, flowing beard. Just like my father's.
If you follow this road, you'll cross into the Rift.
Did you hear that Bleakrock was hit hard by the Daggerfall Covenant? I have family out that way. I hope they're safe.
<The Pact scout died of exposure to the elements.>
You made it back. And you're not bleeding, frozen, or gibbering! Damn sight better than those Cultists, eh? nnAndrin's people will help me back to Riften. And then, mead, lots of it.

People claim many things. Some claim to be the best gamblers. Others the best lovers.nnMe? I'm the best hunter you'll ever meet. No question about it. I've never lost a hunting competition. Not a one.
The lizard mocks me. I'm the best hunter in Eastmarch, but he shows up and out hunts me. Twelve rabbits! I need to figure out his secret.

Steady-Hand swears he's the best hunter in Eastmarch. Says he can nab more rabbits in a minute than anyone else.nnI've got an idea, if you don't mind bending the rules a bit. Come back and talk to me after you equip the hunting bow.
I'm staying, no matter how bad things get. Mark my words, 500 years from now, there'll still be Dorans in Chorrol.
Every tremor brings another piece of my house down around my ears. I hear there's a portal to Oblivion at the bottom of the fissure!
I don't care if the fissure and earthquakes are punishments from the gods. Not even they can chase the Motierres from Chorrol!
A customer! Welcome, how can I help you?
Thank you for getting me out of there.
Just when things were going so well, all this had to happen.
The balance of the world tilts precariously and the gates of the dead shiver in anticipation.nnThe Daedric Prince succeeds at his unholy task. This pocket proves that.
No one expects an Altmer to enjoy fighting, but I can change their minds.
Though the ground shakes and fumes taint the air, Harzad is here to help.
I don't want to die! What can I do? What?
Welcome to Weynon Priory, friend. In these troubled times, helping hands are welcome.
If you've come to join the Quickstep Bandits, you're too late. The Black Daggers killed my whole gang. But they'll pay, if it's the last thing I do!
I don't see that bard fellow with you. Did those creatures kill him?
Thank you for convincing me to fight. Velyn Harbor's my home.
I may not be a citizen of Velyn Harbor, but I'll be damned if I let the Ra Gada take it!
Who are you? Z'en! What've we done?
Gods, let it not be my time yet!
"Don't trust the Orcs," I said. But did they listen?nnNow they're dead, all dead.
It isn't enough to drive the Drublog back to the forest. We have to kill them all!
The Drublog have taken too much from us! We have to start taking from them.
What's the purpose of all this, if Z'en won't protect us in our time of need?
I told them not to forsake Y'ffre for Z'en! I told them!nnThat's why I'm still alive. I put my trust and faith in Y'ffre.
Don't believe a soldier's life is all fame and glory. Taking a life isn't heroic.nnYour enemy has a family, just like you and  like I did. No one deserves to die. No one.
If I have to comb through the Worm Cult's filth to find her, I'll strangle her with my bare hands.
The Worm Cult! Y'ffre help us. What are they doing here?
I'm currently well employed, friend, and not taking requests.
Fair day, traveler. Best steer clear of here. Vernim wood is not safe.
You'll want to steer clear. Danger on the road ahead.
A shame. He may be a killer, but this is no way to die.
He slipped and fell! What kind of imbecile assassin does that?
Oh ho, did the poor assassin take a spill? Saves me the trouble of putting an arrow in your backside as you run away, coward!
Don't worry, I'm not going anywhere. Keep your mind on the task at hand.
We all walk the river's edge. What do you see on your journey?
I traveled many days to commune with the Hist. I cannot wait to begin the trials.
Looking to taste what's come down the river? Or brew your own?
You're clearly a person with a refined palate. Interest you in some swamp cuisine?
I failed. I failed the Trial of the Heart. To have come so far to fail. Why?
Which trial do you look forward to? I cannot wait to partake, and have my mind judged by the Hist.
I was to partake in the Trials. And then that Dominion soldier showed up. The Hist speaks with a High Elf! Pah!
Don't let the river knock you around, friend. Toughen up those scales.
Looking to hit something? Trust me, I understand.
Just trying to keep folks happy, you know? Have any requests?
I can't go back to the lines. So much blood and death. I can't do it.
Hard to keep warm here. Even harder when your man is on the front lines.
Sinmur is alive again   how can this be? How can we fight this monster?
Now we know what the Reach were here forreviving that monster Sinmur. The bastards.
Please, let the poor girl be. She just lost her father.
It's rude to interrupt someone while they're eating! Hmm, or is it the other way around?
Ever wrestle a mammoth? It ain't pretty.
A dull blade will betray you. Care for your weapons as you'd care for a lover, and they will both stay true.
People think that manipulating magical energy is easy. You and I know nothing could be farther from the truth.
I'm working on an alchemical recipe for a self-silencing spell.nnFirst test subject will be my fool brother. I'm so tired of his bellyaching!
I heard tell of honest work in these parts. I've no want to turn to brigandry as long as there's work to be had.
Another local. How lucky I must be today.
The ground yields to one's step here, not like those parched lands up north. It reminds me of my home, far from here. Good memories and bad.
Blessings of the Eight upon you. You  do know of the Eight in this land. Don't you?nnAh, Stendarr, how you send me almost too many burdens to bear.
This is humilating. I was hoping for a little decency, but these Hlaalu savages have trussed me up like a spit roast.nnI suppose it's better than being impaled on a Dwemer sphere's blade.
You'll need more than claws to get through well-forged armor. A small sword in between the cracks does the job in half the time!
What's done once will be done again.
There is strength in you, to do what must be done.
I don't care how thick your skull iseverybody needs a strong helm. Gotta protect our pretty faces, eh?

Many years I have traveled, in search of the finest luxuries!nnHave you ever lain on a rug that once graced the steps of the White-Gold Tower? Or drank from a cup forged in the bowels of Ash Mountain?
I saw her head toward the water.
This will be a celebration to remember!
So. You're the one who's working with this beast?nnFunny. You look familiar somehow.
Did you hear my singing? I'm certain all of Silvenar heard me!
We did it! We played at the handfasting! I hope this makes Dadazi happy.
This is just one small step. First the handfast, then  well, I don't know what comes next, but it'll be great!
