Again, I must thank you! We got to perform at the handfast because of you!
My da's starving, and I'm too weak to hunt. I just need a few coins to buy some food. Something to get me back on my feet.
Kind stranger will bless Halarel with a favor, no? Some scraps, or a sweetroll? My belly needs medicine, before it goes into knots again.
Which do you like better - the drummer, or the flautist? I'm partial to the dancer, myself. Very provocative.
That is my sister dancing. She hopes to perform in Elden Root one day.nnI think maybe they are not ready for our kind of dancing.
Don't waste my time, if you know what's good for you.
A fair day to you, friend. Care to try your strength against mine?nnI may not look like much, but in Morrowind, I arm-wrestled many a Nord warrior to his knees!
Ah, a fellow traveler. If you wish, I can relate some of my adventures to you. I've been told they are quite exciting.nnI'm a storyteller by trade, you see. Words are my instrument.
Some say Khajiit cannot retract their claws. It is not so.nnI am skilled in massaging away the hardest knots. My warm pads will melt your cares away, friend.
Are you the mercenary we've heard so much about?nnI am skilled in the ways of the harp. Shall I strum a tune to relax your sore muscles?
This dress is ridiculous! How can I cook a decent meal in this?nnWell, if you're interested in Bosmer cuisine, let me know. I'll change into something more practical.
Finally. I thought I'd be paid for nothing. I warmed up my steps just in case, worry not.nnWhat kind of dancing do you need? I'm versed in the rotes of many cultures.

Well. This is quite a pickle I've gotten myself into.nnI've been hoodwinked into this. The cat outside said I couldn't leave until everyone else left. Whatever indignity you're here to inflict, let's make it quick.
I don't have all day to be waitin' around.
I was told there'd be entertainment. This place's as dead as a hanged cat.
My sword arm's getting stiff with all this waiting. Maybe I'll get some practice in before I leave.
The best horses aren't just strongthey're smart. Now I'll be honest; these ladies aren't guild scholars, but they're sharper than most. nnSo what do you say? Need a ride?
The last of the Heritance have been driven out. Silsailen is safe once again, thanks to you.
I feel  I'll never leave that cavern, no matter how far away I travel.
Welcome to my home, friend. Get you some mead?
Hey there, traveler. Come to watch the trials? Or join perhaps?
I can't believe we got this far, only to have this happen.
Hello! I'm just a simple merchant searching for new markets for my fine goods. Can I interest you in a morsel of food? Perhaps you would prefer a cool drink?
I hear you adventurers go around murdering potential threats. Ever think of reasoning with them?
The giant left us little more than our lives. We have no wares and no coin to rebuild. My mother is too proud to admit it, but this may be the end for us.
I don't really stand on ceremony, so out with it. I'm very busy today.
Why my father continues to cater to these  foreigners  baffles me.
You really shouldn't be in here. The Skald-King is extremely busy right now.
Celebration is fine, but we must stay vigilant. Especially with so many visiting dignitaries in the city.
What a humble chamber for such an important king. We could all learn a lesson from this impressive dry-skin.
Ten years and they throw a party. Only the Nords.
With all the work the ambassador has given me, I won't get to attend any of the celebration.
I remember when we didn't have to put up with all this Pact nonsense. That was when I was young and I ran the forge. Now my daughter's daughter stokes the fires. And I sit in here. Alone.
This one is not worthy to talk to such an accomplished traveler.nnThis one expresses astonishment and admiration!
Soon as my brother is well, I'm out of here. I'm brokering a deal to buy blades in Mathiisen.
Feel free to browse, friend. Best prices in all the Rift.
And that was the last time Geirmund was ever seen.nnOh. Yes?
Riften welcomes those who mind their own business.
<This Dark Elf appears to have died beside a nest of kwama eggs.>
The view from up here is amazing.
A thousand pardons, but please do not stray too far from the walls while in our village. It is for your own safety, and ours.nnOur shops are still open, for your convenience.
I'd heard rumors you were here, stirring up trouble. Fortunately, you're easier to find than I expected.
You've done it! Now, we name you to the crowd.
When you sit, you exercise muscles that can atrophy if you stand or walk around too much.
Oh thank Kyne! Can you see to Jakaral? nnHe lured the giants away from us so we could escape.
I have news from Vernim Wood!
My wife and her cousins run the shops on Merchants Row. Me? I take care of the house. nnI assume you don't have a problem with that.
Between the fumes and the berserk kwama, I didn't think I'd make it out of there.
Please don't make me go back in the mine yet. The kwama went crazy!
I like working as a librarian, but this isn't much of a library.
Trade's picking up in the harbor, isn't it?
The Ra Gada won't get their hands on our gold so easily!
I hope things get back to normal soon. My business is suffering!
Not sure what was worse, the smell of the fumes in the cave or the taste of the potion Edrasa just gave me.
I sell armor. I don't normally use it myself.
I got a whiff of those fumes and my head's still pounding. Small wonder the kwama went crazy.
Work piles up faster than dead bodies, doesn't it?
Fighting leaves one with a powerful appetite, no?
Remarkably, we lost very little from the marketplace, but the residential district was nearly burned to the ground.
They say there are fumes in the mine, but I don't see how that's possible. We're raising kwama, not digging for minerals.
I love listening to the roar of drunken Nords, but it's far too dangerous for me to go inside that drinking hall.nnMost Nords don't care much for Altmer.
Another round of drinks! Another song! nnAha! And I see I have another ardent admirer.
Apologies. Betting is closed. Come back later.
Get down! Don't let them find me!
I've never seen anything like it. The attackers used Dwarven spheres and spiders!
If you plan to fight in the arena, I suggest you use your own weapon. These tend to snap on impact.
Ahh. I saw you around at Geirmund's. Here to save me. How nice! nnHow nice.
Unless you've got business with me, leave me be.nnEven if you do have business with me, I don't give a fig. Piss off.
Hmm. You look like you could win a bar fight. But what about a drinking contest? That's a real challenge.
Why we feed and house that stupid dog, I'll never understand. The damn flea bag bit me again!
Just look at them over there! Win one battle and think they've won the war.
The Maulborn know we're here, but they don't care. I guess they're not frightened by a handful of house guards.
First Narsis and now here! All we can do is watch. There aren't enough of us to challenge them.
We're lucky. My wife Taderi and I made it out alive.
This poor one didn't make it. What a shame.
If not for Viros, I wouldn't have survived.
You nearly scared me to death when you and Elynisi came through that door.
There was an explosion  then the wall collapsed on top of me  by the Three, it hurts!
Whenever I get nervous, I pace. Unless something changes, I'm going to wear a hole in this floor.
I'm hoping to find something for my nix hound, Anther, to eat.
I can hear the ghosts wailing outside. What do they want with us?
That woman came into town. That's when all this terrible trouble started.
I hid in the chamber below the temple when the explosion occurred. I'm lucky to be alive.
I hope that Aamela can help my brother Nilus.
We're lucky the inn had so many books. We've been able to keep the fire going, but we'll run out of books soon. Then we'll have to burn the holy texts.
I'm so nervous. I just can't seem to get any sleep.
People often say I look just like my sister, but I don't see the resemblance.
We were lucky enough to survive the explosion, but now we're surrounded by hostile spirits!
My husband, Dural. We were separated on our way to the inn. He never made it, and they won't even let me go out to look for him.
Thank you, stranger. nnEven a soul-shriven can stand only so much torment.
Ahem. This one was not cowering. No.
Thank you. Our fate would have been dire.
The Maulborn really made a mess of things.nnWe've got a lot to clean up before we're ready to open.
Ani and I brought Lluther and Adol from Narsis. I'm trying to find the blankets we packed. Even though it's warm, the sickness makes them shiver.
The Maulborn really care about the little people. We received more help from them than we have from the Houses or the Tribunal.
Ani? Is that you? I hope they let me in soon. And I hope it's warm in there. I'm so cold.
They call it the Llodos plague, and we're here to get help for my brothers. It's taking so long, though. So many people are sick.
Why have the Three abandoned us? A mother shouldn't watch her daughters wither. That's not  not how it's supposed to be.
Father thinks we don't see him pray to the Tribunal. I know it's hopeless, but he wants to help.
My daughters deserve better than this, but there's nothing more I can do. We must keep up appearances, however. For their sakes.
I'm not sure about all this. The Maulborn seem too good to be true, if you ask me.
I've been helping my sister, but now I'm starting to get the shivers. I hope I don't have the plague, too.
This is unacceptable! People are dying, actually dying! There are dead bodies piled in carts! I won't let them cart off my wife like some  dead peasant!
Please, go away. I don't want to spread the plague.
My son, my daughter. Both sick, just like me. We wait here for our tokens, but time is running out.
We need a token to get inside? Really? I have plenty of money and influence, and yet I still have to wait here with all the common people. What a disgrace!
I have a bad feeling about this place. The Maulborn are friendly enough, but something isn't right .
My son's talking to the gate guard, but he isn't having much success.
I feel  wrong. Not just sick. Something's very wrong.
I'm waiting for my brother. We got separated at the gate. I can't leave, so I hope he gets in soon.
My children are sick, and there's so much suffering. I wanted to do something to help, so I'm making soup. Hot soup always makes you feel better.
This damn plague! I need help, but I don't trust these Maulborn cultists. Who are they? Where did they come from? Why haven't we heard about them before?
I'm writing to my cousin to let him know about this plague. I want him to leave Mournhold before the plague spreads there.
My brother's a scholar. A master of divination and illusion. It hurts so much to see him like this.
I'm sorry, do I know you? Dalyn says I'm hallucinating, but I don't know if he's real.
The Maulborn have special healers called nostrums. That's why they were able to develop a cure so quickly.nnFeel my head. Do I feel warm to you?
My husband's still out there, while the Maulborn take their sweet time. When are they going to let him in?
When will they finish administering the cure? My daughter has gone to the wards, yet nothing seems to be happening. What are they waiting for?
For a group of healers and care-givers, the Maulborn sure carry around a lot of weapons.
I gave my wife my token. I wanted her to get inside as soon as possible.
I was just telling handsome Belos here about a quiet place I know. But my, look at you! I think you might be more fun.

Wherever we are, wherever we go, my sister finds someone to flirt with. We came here to help, but she's more interested in aiding the not-quite-sick among the crowd. And those with a bit of muscle tone. Typical.
Even sick people have to eat, so we set up these cooking fires. And the Maulborn were kind enough to provide some much needed supplies. Don't you just love those guys?
I miss my brother and my father. I even miss my brother's silly little nix-hound. Does that mean I'm dying?
Ginger! No! My poor, poor nixie. My brother and my nix-hound, both victims of this damn plague!
Please go away. It hurts to talk.
There's a breeze up here. It's cold, but it keeps the stink of the Serk away.
The Maulborn keep atrocious records. I hope their elixirs are better than their bookkeeping.
Please, can you spare some gold? I want to hire a cart to bring my sick cousin to the Serk.
Who are these Maulborn and where did they get this miraculous cure?
People out there cry to get in. People in here scream for the cure.nnI'm so tired of all the yelling.
I'm here for the cure, that's all. Please tell this woman that I'm not interested.
You know, I never appreciated the hired help before I got sick. When I'm well again, I'm giving gifts to all my servants.
I feel terrible, but I'm not worried. Vunden will take care of me.
The nostrum gave me the cure, but I don't feel much better. I wonder how long before it takes effect?
Alaru means everything to me. I'm not leaving her side.
I came here so my dear Urynnar could be cured, but I've been inspired. If they'll have me, I'm going to join the Maulborn and make sure others get the help they need.
The guards, the locked gates, the rules and regulations. It's like these Maulborn were some kind of cult or something.
As soon as I get well I'm going to join the Maulborn. I want to help others, just as they helped me.
My wife's been helping out since she arrived. She's sick, but she still goes out of her way to lend a hand.
Pardon? We're not open for business yet. Be a while.
The Hlaalu allowed me to set up shop here in the Gorge if I promised to help clean up.
Look at all this trash! It's hard to decide what to keep and what to burn.
Velyn Harbor nearly boiled over. Glad you put a lid on it.
Wish I'd been here for the excitement. Might've made a profit. Still, plenty of good weapons ready for sale.
Mastering a weapon can take a lifetime. Of course, it helps when the weapon's a masterpiece. nnLucky for you, that's all I sell.
Hurry up. I got me some hot metal to work.
Magic always comes with a price, but my prices are eminently reasonable.
A good suit of armor is all that stands between you and your enemy.
I don't know about bringing my wares to Velyn Harbor. This place is dangerous.
Fermented meat, spoiled milk, and honey! Those make a good Bosmer brew.nnIf you want something else, I can help you, too.
What can I help you with? Something mystical, I hope.
I'm trying to stay on the down-low. Just keep walking.
This Vox is evil. Word of her plague has spread to the north. We came from Eastmarch to help our Pact allies.
Looking for a little excitement? The Fighters Guild can provide it.
Ready to fight for the Dominion? I sure am! Defending Velyn Harbor gave me a taste of battle, and I hunger for more.
She scares their gods and the Dark Elves send only a handful of soldiers to confront her?nnIf this was Eastmarch, Vox's head would already be on a pike.
Hey there, friend! Just looking for an ale? Or a chance at the trials?
Well met. You look a little lost. Are you looking for the kegs? Or the competition?
Velyn Harbor survived, but many of our homes burned.
It's amazing the Drublog didn't run off with all this stuff!
Please, don't bother me! I'm trying to write the Ballad of Velyn Harbor! It was much simpler to free the harbor than to sing about it!
I'm here to help with the reconstruction. There's money to be made here!
Relax! We're just cleaning up the beach. Invasions make such a mess.
What do you want? We're not doing anything wrong!
All the fighting scared away the fish. The mudcrabs are feasting, though.
Have you seen my cat? She's gone. Did one of those Drublog eat her?
You! You're the one that helped the Fists and formed the militia! Wish you'd stick around to help with clean-up.
My oxen got loose when the Drublog attacked. I'm lucky they didn't end up roasted or slaughtered, I guess.
Damn Drublogs' blood must've poisoned the worms! Fish ain't biting!
I have no idea how we're going to rebuild.
I don't know who lived here before, but I don't think they're coming back.
We cornered a few of the Ra Gada and their pet wood orcs on the ship. They can't leave the harbor, but no one wants to go in and clear them out, yet.
The mayor of Velyn Harbor died during the attack. We need to find a new leader.
We have a lot of work to do. The Drublog destroyed almost everything.
They say our mayor was poisoned. Those Drublog Wood Orcs wouldn't do something like that.nnAt least, I don't think so.
You look familiar . Oh! You fought the Drublog!
Velyn Harbor's been exciting lately. I could do with a little less excitement.
I'd like to get the worst of this cleared away by nightfall.
Looks like someone started a fire in here.
Just like always. My partners'll talk while I work.
I should be grateful, I know, but rebuilding will be hard work.
I appreciate what the Fists of Thalmor and the new militia did, but we need to rebuild! I need to find some help.
It's a good thing some of the townsfolk fought back. I would never have had the courage to do that!
The Ra Gada won't mess with us again!
I weep for my gentle guar! I wish we could have saved them all.
Don't know you. Don't care to, either.nnBack off while your face is still in one piece.
Eh, what's that? Barely understand you people from around here. I'm no scholar myself, but at least I know normal speech!
Not bad, not bad. Certainly not my usual tastes, but I won't turn down the local  delicacies.nnOh, you're not one of Rejmina's? A thousand pardons.
I think they've watered down my drink again! I should kick'n that door and show 'em what we do to drink-robbers 'round here!
I wish the Silvenar would visit here. I hear his beauty brings awe to man and mer alike.
You can make so many meals out of meat!nnI can't imagine what it might be like to  grow something and eat it. That's against the Green Pact!
I can't sleep at night with all the wolves howling.
They say you should wrestle wolves when you're feeling lonely. I tried it once, but it didn't make me feel any better.
Why would I ever leave Deepwoods? I mean, aside from the fear of getting eaten by wolves?
This town's all right. People stick by each other.
These blades aren't bad. Doubt they could hold up to our Colovian armor, but for a backwater hovel like this, it's good quality.
Found a curious waterlogged book in the river a few days back. It's a fascinating read!
This ale's not bad. Least, they told me it was ale. It's sweet, like Ma used to make.
Mmm mmm. I could get used to this view.
I've got half a mind to up and leave this swamp-hole. Never seen an insect dwarf a dog! And I certainly don't want to find out if they can bite like one.
Grateful just to have a dry place to set my old bones. This'll be my last tour with the captain, methinks.
Got no business with you, unless you want to meet one of my arrows close up.
Never again. I'm done with games for good. I've got to find a way to get that ring back!
Those evil cats need to be punished for this.
My songs are silent now, for my heart mourns.
Be quiet. Those cat bastards didn't see me sneak in here. I'm safe, for now.
Welcome to Sanguine's Dem  Deme  Sanguine's  Sanguine's party! nnLeave the Divines at the door and come have a good time!
This is ridiculous. I've been waiting in line for  what day is it?
I love this place! We don't have anything like it in Skyrim.
This temple has survived three purges, four wars, and an attempted crusade. And you know why? Because it's Sanguine! He's not that evil!
Sanguine was here once. I saw him! He waved at me. Well, he told me to move along. What an honor!
I don't understand why everyone hates Daedra. I mean, Mehrunes Dagon, Molag Bal, sure. But Sanguine seems harmless. He's certainly more fun than the Divines.
Stay away from those ogrim. Very unfriendly creatures! And they smell bad, too.
I left my family for this place. And you know what? I don't miss a single one of them.
Those Dremora don't scare me. Give me a sword and I'll take them down a peg or two.
Why would anyone ever want to leave this place?
Nice to see you! I just stopped by for one drink, but they taste so good!
I enjoy the arena games. The blood, the stabbing! It's all so exciting!
You missed the best fight last night. I caught an arm!
Welcome to Sanguine's Demesne! Put down your weapons, grab a drink, and join the celebration!nnActually, hang on to your weapons. The Daedra can get a little fiesty.
Let me guess. You're here for the party, right? It's through the door at the end of the tunnel.
Seen any Drublog nearby? I'm afraid they're going to come back and finish off what they started.
I am very drunk, and standing is surprisingly difficult.

We've seen more than our fair share of sorrow. It's my job to comfort everyone who lost sons and daughters to this madness, even when my own daughter is gone as well.nnI trust you're not here to add to our troubles?
Praise Sanguine! That temple makes this swamp almost tolerable.
Thane Mera isn't home right now. She has so much to do what with the Konunleikar and all the visiting dignitaries.
What do you think? I so want a suit of Nord armor, but I'm not sure this works for me. Perhaps I should go for the light armor instead.
Lots of people in Windhelm right now. It's rather exciting.
I suppose I am getting used to drinking mead. But I'd pay good gold to have a jug of flin.
Ten cheers for the Skald-King! One for every year of his reign!
Cheer? I say ten drinks for King Jorunn. And then ten more!
Ooh. This Nord beverage makes my head all fuzzy. What was I singing again?
Saint Veloth taught us to respect the Daedra, not fear them.
We'll get through this. Vox just caught us off guard.
Healer says I'll be fine, but by Veloth, how it hurts. nnWatch out for the tails on those clannfear.
I'm appealing to the saints to heal my injury. I think it's starting to work.
Cursed Daedra smashed the holy reliquary. Will I ever polish it again?
Holy Veloth was a warrior as well as a philosopher. We're not afraid of Daedra.
When the shrine is restored, we'll add a memorial to the faithful who died today.
I'm trying not to be angry at Magistrix Vox. She's misguided and lost.nnI'll redouble my prayers for her.
I heard there was another stranger visiting the Vale. How tedious.
This is the Vale of the Ghost Snake, outsider. What do you want here?
Treat the snakes with respect, and they will respect you.
Sometimes I feel like I'm the only one who actually does any work around here.
The Coiled Path requires a light tread.
What? Never seen a Nord who could use magic?
What? Never seen a Nord use magic before?
May Kyne guide my way and light my path. nnAnd may Kyne forgive my parents for raising a daughter cursed with magic.
Just wait till the instructors see true Argonian magic in action. I'll be in the advanced class in no time.
I can't believe I'm drinking with these Dark Elves. They enslaved my people, and now they're teaching me magic.nnThis is going to take some getting used to.
I'm one of the first Argonians admitted to the Academy since slavery was outlawed and the institution decided to open its doors to all members of the Pact. nnI hope I can handle the pressure.
You must be new. Did they tell you how hard this place is?nnI'm in my second session and I'm still struggling with illusions, alterations, and military strategy.
The Academy better not disappoint me. I waited my whole life for this honor.
I think that instructor over there just offered to sell an Academy invitation. For gold!nnI must be mistaken. Why would an instructor do such a thing?
No! My report was almost finished when a shadow cluck ate it! I can't believe I have to start over!
My friends and I trained all our lives for this.nnA shame I was the only one who got selected. Maybe next season for them.
I'm so nervous. I'd kill for some flin right about now.
Maybe now that his report's gone, Belvo'll pay some attention to me.nnWhat? Belvo just needs some help with his priorities.
I was looking for Sergeant Aera, but the Thane tells me she was slain valiantly defending her from the Worm Cult.
I wonder if something happened to the water? Too much blood, maybe?
It's great the Redguard Ra Gada are gone, but we need to bring back the fish!
The fish aren't biting. I think all the excitement has them worried. Guess I'll need some new bait .
If you're looking for my sister, get in line. She's out at the stables today.nnIf you want something to drink, grab a table and wait your turn.
Well met, traveler. Good to have another strong arm in the field.
Nothing like a Dark Elf covered in mud to brighten my day.
This isn't the most humiliating thing One-Eye's done to a nosy fellow. She's got a leather collar for the ones that really scrape her scales.
So much decoration, so little useful coverage. It's a wonder the Pact hasn't fallen to bandits, if this is what they suit their soldiers in.
He's a handsome one, Neeta-Li. At least, I think it's a "he." nnEither way, handsome. I'd take 'em home, no question.
This spot has the best rays in the afternoon. If I don't stake my claim, some other mud-scale gets here first.
You must got something better to do than bother me, now don'tcha?
Your smell pleases me. Many nights spent in the swamps, I gather?
Can't you see we're having a conversation, here?
Warm welcome, kitten. S'jash sits at the bow, if you wish to speak with him.
I've no quarrel with you, stranger. Leave me to my drink. It's the only rest I get all day.
My patience for these whining merchants wears thin. Perhaps I should bite one of their noses off to get them back in line.
Don't get much shore leave nowadays. Think you could leave a body to enjoy herself, won'tcha?
I'm collecting letters. We give them to the guards, to pass to family in quarantine. Deliver any for you?
I know this scaly rat took my ledger. He thinks he can fool me, but I know!nnFilthy beasts, the whole lot of them!
Why isn't High Kinlord Rilis or our new Queen doing anything about this plague? Never would have happened in the old days.
I've heard stories of the Maormer sniffing around Auridon lately. nnWouldn't be surprised if those Sea Elves started this plague business. Their ships are full of sea rats!
I've got my eye on you, stranger.
Soon as this is all sorted, I'm going to Shattered Grove. Friend told me the critters there are so friendly, they come right up and let you pet them.nnIn the meantime, got work to do.
I am so glad my daughter Elenya went off with that Telenger fellow. She's part of an important Mage Guild project now!nnDon't know what I'd do if she got this nasty plague.
Shh. Quiet. I'm just pretending to be sick so I can be with my husband. They put him in quarantine last week, I'm so worried about him.nnDon't tell anyone.
Someone has to keep an eye on goings-on. That someone is me.
Dimarra hopes the Dominion goes home soon. Too many eyes have seen this one.nnSomeone from Tenmar will find this one. No, let it not be so!
Monkeys. The worst thing those Khajiit brought with them. That and the fleas, but at least those don't screech when you take their bananas.nnGreedy monkeys.
Mmm, what have we here? What a fragrant vision of beauty!nnCome a little closer. Feel that rumbling, kitten? You would like to  have more of a taste. Is that not so?
I seem to inspire nothing but snickers from the others on the decks.nnI don't mind. I prefer to stay down here.
There's no use worrying so. Turan will make himself sick. Nothing to do about it, it is.nnAs soon as I'm well again, I'll show him there's no reason to worry.

My egg-brother was once in the Shadowscales. A few hours earlier, and it would have been me.nnCertainly would have been a better fit. He got himself killed on his first contract. 'Course, didn't help that his first contract was me.
The jungle rat Bosmer think they can keep our docks from us. I saw 'em laughing.nnWell, I'll spit and roast the next one I get my hands on. We'll see how much they laugh then.
What? You need directions or somethin'? There's the door.
Nothing like the smell of fresh fish at sunrise! Well, except old fish at sundown. That's a smell to remember, I tell you.
All this shore leave's making me crazy in the head. If the captain doesn't get back soon, I  I don't know what I'll do.
This ship's not free, friend. You buy your way, or you work your way. Or you swim. Ha!
Nope, not on my list. Can't take any shipments unless you're on my list. No exceptions.
We ain't got room for wanderers. All bunks're taken.nnYou're welcome to sleep in the barn, if'n you don't mind the rat droppings.
I don't know what's turned my stomach so horribly. True, this place is less than gourmet, but I thought a mug of mead would be safe!
Hrr, stop that infernal drum-beating! You shake the ground with that noise!
Are you from the swamps, traveler? Seem comfortable enough in the muck, from the looks of it.
Shabol wouldn't know a good deal from a hole in the ground. He don't got what you want, I bet I can find it for you.
Aye, and who might you be? Don't look like you're from this stinkmire.nnTake my advice - you don't want to die in a place like this. So keep your nose clean.
You don't find a lot of moments for peace and quiet in a place like this. Got to carve them out for yourself, or you'll go mad like the rest of 'em.
I have One-Eye's trust to keep her accounts. And that trust is not for sale.
You want better stock? Come back in, oh, let's say a month. If I'm still here, I may have something worth your time.
We're missing a few barrels, but that's understandable. This must be the seediest place I've ever brought trade to, but I keep coming back.nnWhen the coin's this good, it's hard to turn down.
By the looks of things, I should start importing weapons and armors. Conflict is always good for business.
We're out of rotmeth. And honey mead. House ale's on tap, though.
Rotmeth's not for the faint of heart. Or of stomach!nnAslohild knows how to brew it, though. Just like home.
See them in the cages there? Yeah. You don't want to be them.
Watch out! Some invaders made it inside!
We've cornered some of the invaders inside. But there are too many for us to handle alone.
There aren't enough of us to rush inside. We'd just get killed.
I'm not going in there without back-up! Where's the Captain?
If the Lieutenant wants us to go in there, he's going to have to tell me himself. There's at least a half-dozen invaders inside!
If you want to go in there, that's your problem. We're just here to keep anyone from getting out.
We can't go in there! We're the last line of defense Velyn Harbor has! It's a fool's errand!
If they come out, we'll try to hold them off. But we can't just go inside and die.
The bugs never stop, you know! Blasted creatures must be a curse sent down by Shor himself!
Four hundred seventeen thousand, six hundred and  thrice curse you! Now I've lost count!nnUgh. I'll be here until the next moon at this rate.

Do you see them? The eyes in the leaves? They are always watching, you know. Their lids fell off, long ago.nnThey think I don't hear them. Know they follow me. But I do. And I'll catch one, soon enough!
We need more actors in Skyrim. We have an annoying bard or two in every inn, but no real actors.
Theater makes me feel so cultured. I usually don't understand what's going on, but that's hardly the point.
I hear there's a war going on out there. If it's all the same to you, I think I'll stay in here.
The architecture reminds me of my summers in Vvardenfell. I find it to be very peaceful.
Something you need? Anything for a discreet friend.
A place in the center market. What a stroke of luck for us!
We have been lucky, some might say. I say that willpower overrides luck.
The Rothalen family has overcome many hardships. We are Dunmer - we will rise from the ashes once again!
Unless you have food and drink, get out.
I found my husband Dural! He was hiding in the temple.
Thank you so much for your help.
Anther and I wanted to say thanks!
My sister and I can't bear to be separated. Thank you for saving us.
Selfora will recover and prosper. Salima and I will see to it.
Please respect the peaceful nature of the Tribunal Temple.
Welcome to the Tribunal Temple. May your worship bring you solace.
Things are stressful with only one of the Three in residence. Even Almalexia can't be in multiple places at the same time.
Please keep your voice down. We whisper to maintain the serenity of this holy place.
We help those who come to the Temple seeking aid. Often, we can deal with problems before they ever reach the Tribunal.
I'm training to become a priest. Today I'm practicing my Temple voice.
My wife has been studying to become a Tribunal Priest. I'm very proud of her.
My sister came to ask the Tribunal to reprimand Shad Astula's irresponsible mages. She's seeking a compromise when she should be demanding recompense!
The Academy continues to use my farm for their training exercises, and it's starting to interfere with my ability to make a living. I don't want to complain, but the Tribunal has to do something!
I represent my people to the Dunmer in an effort to maintain good relations. Things are going well. Only a few Dark Elves have mistaken me for a servant.

Diplomacy with the Dark Elves is like holding a dinner party with a netch in the room. Everyone eats and talks and ignores the creature even as it stings them all over and over. Our netch? Slavery. And oh how it stings!

I come from a long line of diplomats. The Dark Elves have often spoken with us Nords, in peacetime and in war. They are not fools and do not shy away from dealing with people bigger than they are. I can respect that.
My husband and I visit Mournhold often, but lately many more diplomats from Skyrim make the journey. Have you met Rigurt? He's one of our newest envoys.
The Treethane says we just have to set our roots and recover. Easy thing to say when you haven't lost everything.nnWhat am I saying? We've all lost something here. There's just too much to take in.
I'm the apothecary of the village. Or at least I was until those brutes came in and ransacked my supplies.nnAh, there's nothing for it but to salvage and move on. We've got our lives, at least.
Come to try your hand against old <<1>>? I may be blind, but I can smell you from here, goblin-spawn.
We're all trying to do our best to help each other. I hesitate to call this tragedy a good thing, but  it has brought us together.nnI just wish it didn't come at such a cost.

I don't care what the others say. The Drublog aren't going to stop with one raid, and we need to be ready.nnI may just be one Bosmer, but any Drublog shows its face, I'll show it the business side of my blade.
I'm luckier than some. I got out of the way just in time.nnNever thought I'd find myself hiding in a stew pot, but whatever works, right?
Sorry, I'm a bit busy looking for reagents. Old remedies for wounds and such.nnThe beetles I need are getting harder and harder to find.
My boy took the fight to those Drublog. He said, "Mamma, we've got to chase them as far away as possible."nnI wish I'd stopped him. I wish I could have.
Be sure to purchase any books you need before heading up to the Academy! You can never have too many books!
Students concentrate best on a full stomach. If you're hungry when you cast a spell, you might turn someone into a tasty pie by accident. And we wouldn't want that to happen, would we?
The start of the season is always exciting. New faces at the Academy mean new customers. And new customers mean more sales. nnAnd that means more gold in my coffers. Life is good.
When the Drublog burned the town, so many people lost everything.
This used to be my home. I never thought I'd outlive it.
An unprecendented opportunity for research! And perhaps a way to stop this from happening again.nnAuri-El protect those that gave their lives here today.
Stars. Almost too tired to stand. But we need to examine these pylons before they cool. They could help us prevent this kind of assault on Firsthold in days to come.
Velyn Harbor's under attack, and the townsfolk are fleeing to Greenshade! I don't know what the lieutenant's thinking, but we've got to get everyone out of here!
Thank you. You have served your queen and nation today.
I am not sure I feel completely safe here.
You have done well, but we cannot rest till the Veiled Heritance has been eradicated!
The lieutenant's trying to rally the civilians, but I just want them to get to safety!
Oh  who would do this, and why? Am I being punished? Why take my family and leave me to suffer?
Stop right there. I've got three murders and a heartbroken girl to deal with here. I don't need any more complications.
<This woman's throat was slashed and the skin of her ring finger appears torn.>
Er, hello. I thought you were someone else. Share my fire if you must, but don't stay long. I'm expecting someone, any minute now.
The rain falls sweet upon these roots. This will be a rich hatching.
Nasty biting creatures come for the young ones, and I must find them. I am lucky they are tasty.

I came when I heard the Shadowscales were killing Dunmer in Shadowfen. I'd rather see my killers face to face, you get?nnNow they tell me it weren't them who did the killings. Guess this'll be the safest place for me, for the time being.
We don't see many visitors here. At least, ones that come and go of their own free will.nnYou must be someone important.
I'm busy taking inventory. I can't talk now.
We've waited for Falinesti's return for so long.
The chill at nightfall can catch one unawares. I like to stay close to a warm fire.
I love Am-Rana's cooking, she knows how to handle a dagger too. If you know what I mean.
Without a leader some of these Shadowscales have been slacking. It's my duty to whip them into shape.
I haven't had a contract in three weeks. Usually times of war are busy. This is unsettling.
Do I feel remorse for those I've killed? No. But I feel like I should.nnIt is a strange thought, to want to feel a certain way. It is unnatural.
Keep to the shadows. You never know when someone may be following you.
"A blade is only as good as its bearer." Pah! Let the expert come at me with a dull blade, and I will prove him wrong.
I thought I was a candidate for leader. Turns out, they were all making fun of me.
I don't know what's in this, but it tastes divine.
I like the porridge here. Thick and fishy.
Adzi is still sore about that one time. She should know better than to make me angry.
I once split an arrow in half with a following shot. My training partner broke my hand for that.
Jarakh came here to find new trading opportunities, but all he found was danger.
I was hoping you'd come back. Thank you again for all you've done.nnJorald will stay with me as long as I need. He's so very kind. Don't worry for me.
Good to see you again. Raerana is resting inside. Go ahead and talk to her, if you want. Just don't get her upset.nnShe said it would help her sleep if I watched over her. So here I am.
Well met. If hunger afflicts you, I've got the cure! What can I get you?
Honor and blood. May His hand guide your blade.
They broke my husband's arm and tied him up! Lady Noellaume even lost her family heirloom! This is awful.
You must be here for the secret meeting. Sign in and head downstairs. Madras has already started.
In the name of the Aldmeri Dominion, I bid you welcome!nnHmm, was that formal enough? I'm still working on my royal-ese.
Everyone just has to wait. I'm cooking as fast as I can.
Hmm  what? Go away  I'm trying to sleep.
Goblin troubles? Rabble-rousing Argonians? What do I care? It isn't like I'm getting paid much anyway.
If I can't work, I might as well rest.
This trouble will be resolved soon enough. We have to make sure the gear's ready when the mine is!
Damn goblins! They take our jobs and now they've taken the mine!
Stay down! They're shooting arrows!nnI hope the Guard does something about them soon.
That was so exciting! A real rescue, with adventure and disguises and everything! You're my hero!
Narsis has been cursed. Plague take us all!
Do what you can to assist our comrades. The skin-stealers are ruthless combatants.
The Dominion will pay for this treachery.
Strangers seldom find peace in Stillrise. I suggest you leave while you can.
Why don't you leave me alone?
Please  there must be some way to end this.
We have it better here in Stillrise than most. If it weren't for the necromancers and the whiny villagers, this village would be a paradise.
Stillrise is cursed, and now we've got outsiders making trouble. I hope you aren't going to add to our sorrows.
Your presence merely reminds me of what I cannot have. Begone!
Those fools playing soldier  can't they just let it all end?
Some people don't know a blessing when they see one.
Go away! If they spot me, there's no telling what they'll do!
Now that you see our true shape, are you horrified?
Don't look at me, damn you!
Now you see our horror, first hand. You must end this torment! I don't care what happens to us, just so long as this curse ends!nnPlease, when the time comes, make the right choice!
You want to die? Of course not. But if you did, would you want to take everyone else with you?
I'm sorry for the soldiers, but the rest of us have endured too much. It's time for this to end!
This isn't what I agreed to. It needs to end.
Your time will come, too, stranger, if you stay in Stillrise much longer.
The Shaman did his best, but we need this to end, now!
Bet you didn't expect this! Welcome to Stillrise!
What are you trying to do? Get me caught?
Watch it. You're likely to get hit standing there.
The ruins crawl with Dominion. Watch yourself out there.
Go on and sit down. Enjoy a meal. At least the food is still good in Riften.
Please, help us.nnJust break the floating stone. That should free us!
I was afraid that no one would come to help us.
Are you enjoying yourself at this fine celebration?
I can't thank you enough for freeing me and the others. nnI shudder to think what might have happened to us if not for your timely intervention.
Without your help, who knows what would have happened to us.nnBut what about next time? You can't just follow us around and keep us safe, you know.
I feel like I'll never be safe again. nnFleeing the horrors of Camlorn, then taken in the night by cultist thugs. When will it all end?
What I wouldn't give to be in a nice warm inn, drinking a pint of ale. Or three.
I just need to rest for a bit. I'm sure I'll be all right soon.
I'm sure we'll find someplace safe in a few days.
To know your weakness is to know your enemy's strength.
I'm not arrogant, just better than you.
I know, I know. I'm amazing.
<This bandit was executed with a single slash to the neck.>
I'm doing what I can, but my family's falling apart.
You're the first interesting thing to walk into Narsis in a long time.
Unless I killed a friend of yours and yer here to get even, back off. nnI'm lookin' for someone and it's not you. It's yer lucky day.
The Cultists came out of nowhere. It was chaos. Netapatuu fought back. We all would have died if not for him.
We're just researchers. We don't stand a chance. The others are dead, or worse.
Not much to do in Ivarstead except drink, fish, hunt, and, well, drink. nnI like it here.
Welcome to the Horker's Tusk Tavern. Fancy a drink?
Step right up, they have pretty good drink here. You won't find much rat hair in it at least.
Haven't seen you here before. Or I don't remember it at least. But welcome to our little tavern. Well, it's not mine, but I kinda feel I belong here, you know what I mean? Well, anyway, hello!
This one will be staying down.
Maybe I should go talk to her instead of sending illusions.nnNah, that's a horrible idea. I'd probably throw up or something.
Isn't this conjuration simply adorable? But when is Drifts going to come over and talk to me?
He insists on sending her small illusions. What a coward.nnHe should just go and talk to her!
I'm glad he's going to hurt.
I hope our soldiers take the fight all the way to Auridon. I want blood for blood.
Look at these magnificent projections. I wonder what they do?nnAre they wards? A test of some sort? Maybe mood lighting? I just don't know.
It's so hard to say goodbye to a friend.
I can't believe I lost that fight! I was cheated out of my invitation!nnAh, it doesn't matter. My family's gold secured me a new one, and here I am.
I need to cast a spell. Conjure a familiar, levitate a groundskeeper, blow something up.nnIf instruction doesn't start soon, there's no telling what I might do.
I just arrived and I'm already overloaded with work.nnConjurations, illusions, healing salves, Pact diplomacy, leadership training. What's next?
My first assignment. Study the flame. Determine what fuels it.nnI'm pretty sure the wax and wick fuel it. But it can't be that simple, can it?
My invitation? I don't have it with me. Someone took it, all right?nnMy family is dealing with it. Now go bother a Nord, why don't you.
House Hlaalu. That's where I'm going after the Academy certifies me. Merchants need magic, and they pay well.nnHey, got any flin?
By Kyne, don't these chattering Dark Elves ever shut up? They're driving me crazy.
The Mages Guild will never give up. No werewolf, undead or not, will harm the people of Glenumbra.nnWe'll find out how Faolchu fell and we'll put him right back in the grave.
We've been at this for weeks.nnThe Mages Guild is comprised of the wisest scholars, but even I'm starting to doubt if we can really learn anything here.
Is he a friend of yours? This one is doing what she can for him but it is difficult.nnAt least he's alive. That makes him lucky compared to the other pilgrims we found in the storm.
Never would have thought that I, a mere farmer's son, would one day explore the ruins of the Glenumbra Moors. nnI'll never forget this experience.
The Mages Guild has never been known as a militaristic force. You tend to find us in ruins, searching for lost knowledge.nnBut sometimes even scholars need to take up arms.
These lost spirits refuse to rest. They just wander about, lost in the dream of battle.nnThe Alessian Order had the wrong intentions, but I wouldn't wish this on my worst enemy.
The Alessian army was driven by faith to put a quick end to anyone who didn't share their beliefs.nnIf only we'd learn these lessons from the past.
The remnants of the last battle of Glenumbra Moors still linger.nnThat means there's a connection, something that holds them here. But what?
My brother was almost killed by one of Faolchu's werewolves.nnI couldn't bear losing him, and I don't want anyone else to suffer such pain. That's why I'm here. We'll find a way to stop Faolchu.
We've been out here digging around for hours, and we haven't found one clue. It's hopeless!

This site was the breaking point of the Battle of Glenumbra Moors.nnThe Alessian army made one of their last stands here. The Direnni army was able to defeat Faolchu and prevail. We need to figure out how.
Burns. My chest is like fire.nnSovngarde take me.
I begged him not to go on this pilgrimage, but he wouldn't listen. nnIf I lose him, my heart will break.
I can't stand to watch him suffer any more. I know he'll soon be lost to me.
Y'ffre's bones! A brave adventurer! Please, won't you help me?
Welcome to Ivarstead. Stay out of trouble and we'll both be happier.
<This body has been stripped of all possessions.>
Just get me some food in my belly and I'll be back at those stairs.nnDamned avalanche didn't kill me. I'm not going to give up now.
To save a life is the greatest of pleasures. It is why I choose to heal. nnThis one would not have lived without your help. Take pride in that. May you always help the innocent in times of need.
If you hadn't shown up, I would have been burying my husband now instead of watching him stuff his face. Thank you!
<This corpse is badly burned. His death was recent, no more than a day ago. A note on the body may explain what happened.>
I've been by the Prince's side since he could hold a sword. And I'll be with him until he puts it down again.
You need somethin', friend? Got more than enough to do for two of me, so let me be unless you're looking for work.
Somethin' you need, stranger? Go talk to Pa.
I don't know you. State your business and don't make me angry.
<Malsia holds a broken soul gem in her hand.>
<<<1>> lies dead near the shrine to Mauloch. Blood still oozes from a stab wound in his chest.>
I almost had the bugger, but that right tusk came from nowhere! I'm going to have bruises in the morning, I tell you!
I don't know how the mammoths got out, but they certainly aren't coming back in on their own!
Ugh, my head  it's the only thing that doesn't hurt.
I saw what you did up there! You took on the Green Hunters! Are you crazy?
<This man was killed by a massive club. He was stripped of all valuables, including his shirt.>
<This woman was stomped by a massive boot. All valuables have already been looted.>
J'Eeja's wares are yours, friend, for a mere pittance.
<The senche died horribly, torn and bloody from many wounds.>
I think that so-called Witch of the Moors puts on airs.
My little Firwin  is that you? I can't see you clearly.nnI'm so tired, dear.
Arfanel must have sent you. The Queen's Eyes see all, eh?
Oh  another guest. Splendid. Vesta will be so pleased. Have you told her you're here? If not, just run into the house and let her know.
Welcome to Narsis, where people vanish in the night and a flesh-rotting plague ravages those unfortunate enough to still be here.nnThis must be your lucky day.
We can rebuild, with time. I don't think many others share that feeling.
If we were better stewards of the forest, the forest would have protected us. Don't you see?
I knew this day would come. We should have taken the fight to the Drublog when we were strong. When we were ready.
Things are much more peaceful up here. Simpler.nnIf I could, I'd live in the treetops. Think of how wonderful that would be!
Me? I'm not hiding. What makes you think that?
Welcome to the Serk. Head up to the crypts and wait for a nostrum. You'll be cured of the plague before you can recite Saint Veloth's prayer.
Step back, peasant. Why aren't you in the nostrum's care?
Even in this place of war, knowledge can still be found  by those interested in such things.
What do you want? Can't you see I'm preparing the ritual?

Divines bless you, friend! I am a good man who's fallen on hard times. I have eleven starving children that will surely die without a morsel to eat today. Won't you spare a silver for an honest man and his adoring children?
Hello, traveler! I am but a humble merchant searching for new markets for my fine goods. Can I interest you in a morsel of food? Perhaps you would prefer a cool drink?
Greetings, traveler! Welcome to the Pilgrim's Rest, the best inn in Ivarstead.
I often wonder if you could get a rock to grow if you cared for it enough.
Though it is rare, there are members of the Wyrd that are not Bretons.
I never thought much of the Wyrd, but the way they've taken us in shows they have good hearts.
I never thought of living in a tree, but I could get used to this.
Thank you for your help, stranger.
When can we get back to our lives?
Where I am from, the trees are not so green.
Simple toil is good for the heart, or so the Wyresses say.
I'm glad to be back at camp rather than at that mill.
This camp may not be what the survivors from the mill are used to, but it will have to do.
What are we to do when the earth itself rises to harm us?
Apples, apples, where are those apples?
Many of the Wyrd dislike fire, but I find I have an affinity for it.
Be careful if you're going to Crosswych. Red Rooks have taken over the town. nnWe're getting ready to fight back though. If you want to lend a hand, you can join the resistance.
You want to watch your step in Crosswych. The place is crawling with Red Rook thugs.nnOf course, we'll take any help we can get. If you feel like getting involved, talk to Tamien at the inn.
A pact was forged here many years ago. No Baelborne may walk this land. Any of that bloodline who ignore this decree shall be dealt with.nnHarshly.
Every Baelborne who dares to return to this land shall fall.
I have more important things to do than give you directions to the inn.
Excuse me, I am much too busy to deal with you right now.
You did a great thing this day. If you need anything, you can always find me here.
You saved my life. You're a hero.
No refunds, no returns. No exceptions.
Belarata is closed. All you'll find is a shady Khajiit selling rubble and old spoons.
The Redguard like bloodsport almost as much as we do. I like their style.nnYou one of the new champions? Make sure to show 'em up, will ya?
Always happy to serve. Get you something?
Running orders to Mathiisen, but I can stop for a moment. What do you need?
You lead, and we will follow, friend. We all want our pound of flesh from the Wood Orcs.
They took us captive in the middle of the day. Brazen disregard for generations of peace!nnI always knew they were animals.
I do not know this land like the others. But my time here has taught me much about its inhabitants.
Get me near one of those Orcs, and I'll rip their ears from their skulls!
You'd be surprised what bounties the sea provides. Share in the bounty?
From the Skywatch docks to your pack. What can I get you?
Weary steps? I have something for that.
My deals are the best deals! Taste the value!
Why wait for the high prices in Firsthold? Enjoy bargains for a weary traveler.
Great prices for a weary traveler, here. Test my claim?
How did you manage to get here? You must have had quite a swim.nnSadly, that skill doesn't qualify you to attend the Academy.
Serving the needs of a fort isn't the same as setting up a shop in a city.
I've got a quest for you.
What? Where am I? Where have they nnAh. I'm in the archives. Fitting, I suppose.
Is it my time? You're going to turn me into one of those deathless?
Terrible dryness. My scales feel cracked even though they are long since gone.nnOh? Is it my turn? Very well. I'm not afraid.
It's too late. He's lost to us.nnKill me now. I don't want to live if the Silvenar is no more.
I saw a big light over the tree and came this way. Do you need anything?
Before you have any of my brother's drinks, I'd recommend getting some solid food in your stomach.
I'll never understand why we didn't build one large stable instead of these two smaller ones. It makes no sense!
Don't tell the stablemaster, but I can't stand the smell of guar.
Another murder? Why doesn't that surprise me?
Have you come to hear my daughter Ophalia's music? She's performed in some of the Pact's largest cities.
Move aside. I have house business to attend to.
Hello! I'm just a simple merchant searching for new markets for my fine goods. Can I interest you in a morsel of food? Perhaps you would prefer a cool drink?
Hello, traveler! I'm just a simple merchant searching for new markets for my fine goods. Can I interest you in a morsel of food? Perhaps you would prefer a cool drink?
I've never seen Mournhold this crowded before.
I'm waiting for word from Narsis. I hope things have returned to normal.
Thanks to your efforts, order and peace are restored. Crosswych will be back to normal in no time.
I'm rather busy right now. Come back later.
Shoveling guar droppings has one thing going for it. Job security.
The Academy turns out the best leaders and mages in the world. And now I'll be a part of it all.
You really ought to visit Crosswych when we're not quite so overrun with  pests.
This would never happen in Summerset! Where is a justiciar when you need one?
He sold me a Welkynd stone! Do Welkynd stones dissolve in the rain? I think not!
Don't believe anything that swindler says. Look what his garbage did to my brother. It's not safe!
Ugh  feels like I've been trampled by a mammoth.
Who are you? I won't let you torment Indaenir. I won't allow it!
Another fine night. Or is it day? Doesn't matter. The drinks are still coming.
You'd think trained warriors wouldn't make quite such a mess, but I guess it keeps me employed.
Between the armies tearing up the countryside and the demons terrorizing the island, the dust never stops flying. And it all seems to settle on my doorstep.
I have to speak to the King, but they won't let me into the castle.
Here to taunt the blind man too? The captain doesn't deserve this mockery!
Will that woman ever stop sweeping? It makes me exhausted just watching her. Not that I mind watching her, you understand.
I'm on a business visit from Vvardenfell. With the Argonians emancipated and Shadowfen open to the free market, there's plenty of money to be made.
Much hotter and more humid down here than in Solstheim. Have to say that I like it.
Monsters, soldiers, and demons. As long as they leave me to my work, I don't care what they do to each other.
I have a great many staves to choose from. Summon powerful magicks with a flick of the wrist!
You will always be welcome in Crosswych.
Well done. Well done indeed. nnWe'll make sure that something like this does not happen again.
I've paid my debt to society. Unfortunately, I haven't paid my tab to Six-Coins.
Ever been to the ruins at Bogmother? That's where we returned my mentor, Bran-Na, to the swamp.
The Dunmer no longer take us as slaves. But that doesn't mean they take us seriously.nnI'm fine with that. The less they know about us, the better.
Stormhold's a great city. You give us ten years and it'll be the crown jewel of the Pact.
I understand why we need Argonian and Dunmer vicecanons. But what do we need a Nord for? Drunken tie-breaker?
I've got a lot on my mind, and all this noise isn't helping me think. Do I need to get lost in the swamp to get a moment of peace?
If you see that bastard Five-Coins, tell him  don't tell him anything. He doesn't deserve it.
They say you can actually go talk to the Dunmer gods. Given the way the Dunmer treated us  do you think that also means you could punch them?
I'm a test model used for doing appearances.
Something has occurred within the Mages Guild, and now I'm being terribly inconvenienced.
Wagers only interest me if the stakes are high.
I tried to find one of the magisters to assist my lady, but no one's available.

My miners will take care of any Red Rooks hiding out in dark corners of the mine. It'll restore their confidence, to send these shiftless rogues running. nnMuch obliged to you, for all your help here in Crosswych.
A banekin delivered my invitation! Walked right into the house and dropped it in my porridge.nnNow I want to see who else got one!
I've been studying at Shad Astula for two seasons now. I can't wait until I get my certificate and take my place as a Pact officer.
Don't think this affront will go unanswered!
Thanks for your help on the trail. I might've not made it home without your help.
Fishing's pretty good here. The screams and flashes from the Imperial City don't seem to bother the fish any.
Hello! Welcome to Admand Brothers Lumber Works. Please don't bother my workers, we have orders to fill.
There's plenty of good fishing on Lake Rumare. This is our spot; go find your own.
I rue the day I agreed to work here. We have been paid in thin stew for a week. I shall not work without pay.
You don't want to talk to me. Yves is the smart one, apparently. I do the work, he drinks the ale. Yes, don't waste your time talking to the dumb Admand brother.
Who?nnYou about scared me out of my pelt. At least there's flesh on your face. Where did you come from?
I can't believe what I just heard. Magistrix Vox was a paragon of virtue!
I haven't heard news from Narsis lately. I hope for the best, but I fear the worst.
I thought they were all dead. Glad to find it isn't so.
Never got to repay those Sea Drakes. I'll kill them some other time.
I may have only five working fingers, but that's enough to hold a mug.
I told you to get out. Glad you ignored me.
Nightcaller Molacar inspires me. His interpretation of Vaermina's sendings in our dreams has shown us our true path!
I hope there's a sacrifice this time. It's been too long since we made an offering to Vaermina.
I worry that we misread Vaermina's intent. A nightmare may be inspired by a spoiled serving of swamp eel pie. Then would it be Vaermina's will we follow, or the swamp eel's?
Nords boast that they can hold their liquor. What they mean is that they don't care what they do when they're drunk.
I don't want your help or your pity. I have willingly offered myself to Vaermina. Only she can save Cyrodiil. If my sacrifice brings peace to others, I go gladly.
Don't get on Vori's bad side. She may look pleasant, but I heard she flayed a failing student. For botching their spell! Can't count how many times I've done the same.
A pilgrim, I see. Vaermina's shrine lies just down the path. Worship will continue for some time.
I'm glad we have two smaller stables instead of one big one. Working near my sister all day would drive me crazy!
A new face! That's a rare occurrence. Welcome to the Everfull Flagon!
You're not one of the Flagon regulars.

Therich and I grew up in Daggerfall, but people there weren't very tolerant of our relationship. We moved here five years ago and instantly felt accepted.nnFunny how the smallest minds are found in the biggest cities, isn't it?
Talmo has been whining about his stupid flag for days. I'm glad it's gone!
So many refugees here, it's not an Imperial town anymore. I'll be glad when this war is over and the newcomers can go home.

Why have you wandered into the Cliffs of Failure, mortal? Are you curious as to what you must face here? Do you wonder why we haven't destroyed you? Or why these mages are bound before us?nnI have answers, of courseif you are willing to listen.
The land's plenty fertile. The main problem with farming here is armies tromping throughruining fields, stealing livestock, and burning homes. All we can do is build and hope for the best.
Has Therich talked to you about his dumb wall idea yet? Stick around long enough and he will. What a nut!
I don't see what's so ridiculous about building a wall around Vlastarus. We'd all be a lot safer!
I can't believe these chickens eat so much. Where do they put it all?
You have no idea what you just walked into. You should never have come here.
Yes, yes. I see, I see. You would make a fine addition to my forces.
Ah, a new recruit! Splendid! I have a good feeling about you. Yes, I really do.nnTogether, I'm sure we can win this contest. Good fortune follows me, or so I've been told.
Cursed, Daedra take it! Cursed! A curse on all curses!
I don't know what I'm going to do about Darvell.
Everyone thinks I'm crazy, even my wife.

If it weren't for Vastae, I'd have left town a long time ago. Everyone here is so concerned about the fissure and earthquakes and such, they don't take the time to appreciate music. It'd do them some good to relax a little.
I try to keep what's left of Chorrol as neat as I can. I hope to eventually plant a small spice garden. The food here is so bland!
You want to help? Walk along the fissure and watch for monsters.
Halion is an unappreciated genius. Chorrol doesn't deserve him. Isn't he great?
The waters of life flow strongly through this village. Despite the dangers from the fissure, the people remain. I admire them, though I will not stay.
Hello!  I'm another Breton Male!nnI am <<(c:1>>, the spiritual advisor to ? why, it's you! Wonderful.
What? My friend's looking for an heirloom that was put in the wrong coffin. Keep moving.
Hello, I'm the third Breton Male at this little party of yours.  Updated text.
Ha, well I am Five!  Suck on that Four.  Updated text.
Well I used to be a Breton Six I think it was Updated text.
There's never anything new here. The danger scared away the best merchants. Not that we have the money to buy anything, with Asvorn just hanging around the tavern all day and night.

Join the army they said see the world they saidnnNow look at me half decomposed and last in line of a stupid test group.nnI've editted this too on Tuesday 2nd Oct at 9:58am to see if splunk catches it.
This is a cursed place, wayfarer. Satakal's flames will consume all who dwell here. I await the end. What sense to flee when all Cyrodiil burns?
Hard to believe there aren't any beds available in town. I think it's anti-Orc racism!
If you're looking for a bed, check at the Oak and Crosier. I'm full up.
Times are hard here, stranger. If not for the help we get from Weynon Priory, this would be a ghost town.
<You can see a resemblence between this young man and Nelulin. This must be Iwelien, Velatosse's younger son.>
We have such lovely flowers here. I can think of a thousand places to plant them around the city.
Why are you here? Why have you come searching for this damned fleet of the lost?
You'll be in my songs, friend.nnThank you.
I could hear the giants howling from here. How many did you kill? A hundred? A thousand?
You  you came with us to stop Molag Bal, didn't you?nnI'm sorry you got caught up in this stupid game, too. Well, take my life. Finish me. I refuse to participate in this travesty.
Stay away from Mim!nnDon't  don't make this one hurt you. Mim will win this game. Mim will beat everyone and get us out of here. All of us!
I can end this nightmare  one step and it would all be over. No more worries. No more unpleasant options. I wouldn't have to hurt anyone .nnJust one single step.
You came back. I was afraid I'd imagined our earlier discussion.nnMy mind plays tricks on me. Especially when the craving gets really bad.
I see your skin is still on your bones. I searched the rest of the ship, but there's no sign of the journal. nnDid you have better luck?
What do you want? Can't a Nord drink in peace?
Well met, stranger. I suppose you demand a song.
Maybe you can convince Ravila. She's actually talking about breaking the rules.nnBy the Tribunal, that's just not done!
Why does anyone care what I do? It's not like any of you are the boss of me.
I think Ravila should be allowed to do what she wants. We're all free now, after all.
What a creepy place! It feels like something's tugging at my mind.nnFind my brother and the scholars. And hurry! I don't know how long we can resist the binding spell.
I'm a test model used for appearances.
I'm a test model used for appearances.
I'm a test model used for appearances.

Did you see? The villagers. They're starting to remember.nnThe Thane threatened my daughter and I actually stood up to him. Of course, he knocked me down, but still. We're returning to our old selves!
My mind is clearing, I remember more and more. I was studying to be a healer once.
Your interference will be tolerated. To a point.
Welcome to the Everfull Flagon, friend. Have a mead. The first one is always on the house!
I used to be a House Hlaalu slave. Now I'm a paid assistant. Honestly, I'm not exactly sure what the difference is.nnAnd I still have to stand in line.
All the way from Narsis and we have to wait out here like common  commoners! I blame it on all this Pact nonsense.
We avoid getting the plague, escape the Maulborn, and dodge falling anchors. So what happens? We get waylaid by Dunmer bureaucracy. Oh, the irony of it all!
The wheels of Mournhold turn exceedingly slow, but they do turn. I, for one, support their efforts. With these procedures in place, we remain safe and secure.
Good to see you again, friend!
Lunk likes the pretty sky. And the rocks. Lunk likes rocks.
I'm sticking with the Captain. If anyone can get us out of here, she can.
This is a bad place. A very bad place. It chills my scales.
Damn these crowds! We're going to lose our entire shipment!
The registrar still won't see us. And now our guar steaks are beginning to spoil in their carts.
The Maulborn turned out to be evil. I never would have believed it!
Rats in the supplies. Lord Vivec sent them, I know it. Just as in the scriptures  a living parable!
You hold a knife one way, it cuts through an onion. Hold it another way, and it cuts through three Orcs in no time flat. Screams, carnage. Sorry, what can I get you?
Mother Almalexia teaches us that work is good for the soul. I believe her. But I wish that sleeping was good for the soul too.
Avani's fires must be tended. Always. Dries my scales!

Look what I found: some long-lost relatives. The shock of seeing me has knocked them out from under the crown's control, but it won't last. nnThat be the crown right there. What're you going to do with it, mate?
I don't know what you did, but something changed! Everyone can feel it.
Are you waiting to see the registrar, too? You're not the only one.
Behold me in my glory. The fleet it now mine to command. nnSeek me out if you have need of us.
I just returned from business outside the city. Now I can't even go back to my own home!
Why do we have to wait for the registrar? It's taking so long!
I'm tired of waiting for these silly little Elves to get their act together. I'll sell my rabbit meatballs right here.
And another weary visitor washes up on Mournhold's crowded shores.
I can't believe it. I haven't had good rabbit meatballs since I left Skyrim!
I don't know. Tillrani did keep us all safe for years. But Rana is captain now. We should listen to her, right?
A new contestant arrives, peering out from cold, cold eyes. But what does this mean? Only the Shadow Court can glean!nnChoose wisely or we shall see your demise!
Where do you think you're going? We're in line here.
It feels like I've been waiting here forever.
I don't think this line is ever going to move.
No one may enter Daggerfall Castle without special permission at this time.
We can't allow you to enter right now. My apologies.
We can't wait any longer. As soon as the roads are clear, we need to get our caravans moving again.
Belosi's orders are very, very precise. She wants to get her caravan back on the road as soon as possible.
We must be cautious. I believe the Maulborn still pose a serious threat.

We make many decisions in life that we truly believe are correct when we make them.nnThis body, for example. It was a gift from the lord of this realm. He said it would grant me the power to topple the corruption of Glenumbra. He lied.
It seems as though the purifying potion is working. People are coming to their senses.
Ebonheart this. Pact that. Bah! This alliance hasn't made any of you any cleaner.nnNow watch where you step. I just swept that spot.
The damn registrars had me running all over the place. No more.
Not now! I have to find it!
Travel in the Ashlands can be slow. I can sell you some strong legs to get you going.
Oh, are you here to clean? I think the fire pit needs sweeping, and my daughter always leaves spell components in the corners. Be quick about it, please.

This book is fascinating. It attempts to disprove the fourteenth law of arcane pyrodynamics by applying Magnus' theorem of non-conjoined thaumaturgic vectors to Geirmund's system of harmonic resonance. nnWhat do you think?
There is nothing you could possibly say that would interest me. Begone, netch fart.
Such treatment! I shouldn't have to wait for the registrars. I'm not some  commoner!
Compared to the inside of a noble's home, I don't mind tending to a nice damp well. Smells ever so much better.
I'm not a Dark Elf. Apparently she thinks she could get preferential treatment.nnGuess what? We're both waiting.
Got to get the old planks ready. The Perch are biting off the coast!
Have you ever just stood and gazed into the water? The river flows through us all. Truly.
By the Three, your gear looks worn. What can I get you?
My father's the best armorsmith in all the Ashlands. Just ask him.
Things were easier for me before the Telvanni decided to abscond with all of their knowledge and goods.nnBut, no matter. Can I be of assistance?
I love this place! Kemirik knows how to show his customers a good time.
How positively exciting! You have won the game that could not be won. You defied the laws of this realm.nnOh, well done! Well done!
Leave me! You must take the others and go. That is your only option.

When you make your final decision, remember the reason we all came to this dreadful realm. You must select whoever you feel will best serve you in the battles ahead.nnWhatever you decide, I know it will be the correct choice.
I had allies and friends once. I understand this was not an easy choice for you.nnHelp me restore my mortal self and you will have my support. On this, you have my word.

Yes, yes. You decided to serve me because I have the best chance to win. I understand that. You want to survive.nnListen to what I say and do not question my orders. Do this and we shall escape this game.
How good to see you again! And on the winning side! Wonderful!nnMy dear friend Relmus told me so much about you. As I told Relmus, if you help me, I shall help you. It's as simple as that.

Molag Bal plays such cruel games with the people of his realm.nnTo put those who have failed in their life in a never ending battle, it's just, I don't want to think about it.nnI'm thankful that you saved me. What now?
You have come to Haj Uxith in its most desperate hour.
I grieve to see Khajiit like those on the streets below.
Not an ideal post, but I'm sure this is temporary.
By the end of each day, Jul-dar is exhausted.
Welcome to my wife's inn! Please, make yourself at home.
The dust makes cleaning impossible, so why try too hard, yes?
Why must we work so hard for so little?
I sharpen my claws against the stones. It feels good.
There's no reason we can't all get along, provided the ale flows.
They say all cats are grey at night, but I don't believe it.
The winds singe my fur! I can't wait to leave this place.
House Hlaalu maintains a very strong presence in Mournhold. We support free trade throughout the Ebonheart Pact.
Do you make a habit of entering homes that clearly don't belong to you? Please leave at once!
If you're here for the auction, you're early.nnWe only show the merchandise on Middas and Fredas.
Cause no trouble, and I'll cause no pain.
The dead may not speak, but they have so much to say.
The other houses are jealous of House Dres.
We disagree about many things, outsider, but it all comes down to this: our Hist tree is dying.nnBah! I will say no more until you have passed the Trials of Body and Spirit.
We're still getting set up, fair traveler. Offer you something to tide you over?
Perhaps Venthin will listen to you. An alliance is Morrowind's best hope.
Best stay back, citizen. Those people are from the cursed town of Phaer. They might be carriers of a deadly plague.
You look fit and able. Ready to get back into the action?
Did you hear about the magister? The Ordinators are keeping it quiet, but I heard it was murder.nnWhat a pity. He was a favorite of Almalexia.
I don't know who you are, but I know you shouldn't be here.
Have you been to Cyrodiil recently? Tell me we're winning the battle!
A well-balanced blade that holds its edge and cuts without effort? Priceless.nnHow many can I get you?
Would you like to see some of my latest designs? They should really add a boost to your next stint in Cyrodil.
The right tool for the right job, I always say. If you've got the gold, I'm sure I can provide you with the right tool.nnThe rest is up to you.
Why deal with the outrageous prices at the Mages Guild? We have everything you need right here!
My secret to a great sauce? Pork fat and a barrel of butter!
Free samples? If you want charity, go bother someone in the Tribunal Temple.
One good thing about war: business is booming. And that means profits continue to rise.
Our techniques may not be as fancy as the master smiths on the other side of the city, but our metal is just as strong.
Ma crafts all our armor. If it doesn't fit, she'll be happy to resize it for you.
Mournhold has become a dangerous place, friend. All of Deshaan, really.nnYou don't want to be caught without a sturdy weapon when an enemy appears.
Step right up! No need to wait! I can put you in a fine suit of armor before the grass waves in the afternoon breeze.
I make leather look good. And my armor will do wonders for you, too. Ready to buy something?
Hold on, hold on.nnWhere do you think you're going? Are you mad?
To have come so far, and be turned away at the gate. Damn the Skywatch guard!
Don't, don't come closer. I can feel the fluid in my throat now.
I can't believe they won't let us in. We pay coin into the Queen's purse like everybody else!
You'll want to keep back. Who knows if the damned of Phaer are catching?
I grow weary of conversation. House Dres requires no help from lesser creatures.
Don't feel bad for this one. He got what was coming to him.
Thou wouldst speak to me? Thousands of years, the highest arcana, and I must speak to you? Ahem. nnWhat may I get you, valued customer?
Yeah, you're fine. Go on through. These folks still need to pass inspection.
Welcome to the city of Skywatch, and the Festival of Defiance. Can I answer any questions for you?
This one was told Perch are running today. Best get out there while you can.
In town for the celebration, are you? You'll find all manner of debauchery here, if you're one to debauch, that is.
I may have something special for you. Let me check my stores.
Buy a sword, get a mug of mead! You won't get a better deal than that, and I can tell you from experience, this batch isn't half bad.
I can't wait until closing time. I don't want to miss the drinking contest! Thane Jeggi is sure to win. And his victory belch is a wonder to behold!

This woman will live. I have made sure of that. She is too valuable to lose so early in the contest.nnYou may have accomplished her task, but I know she will help me in the end. For this reason, her life is not forfeit.

So you ended up with my rune? Interesting. You're either working with the cat or you killed him. I'd prefer the latter, of course, but perhaps that's just me.nnStill, there's a way for everyone to win today.

Do you see my court jester? Isn't he handsome? In life, I knew him and other members of the Shadow Court. We worked together on more than one occasion. Doesn't he dance like a Daedra?nnOh, but you must be wondering why I'm here to greet you.
Honor and faith. Please keep your distance from the door. This ruin is off limits to those such as you.
No time to talk, I'm getting out of here!
This one never expected this development.
<The researcher shows signs of being savagely mauled.>
<The claw marks on her back suggest this researcher was trying to escape the ruins when she was attacked by a mist tiger.>
<The researcher's body has stab wounds and claw marks, consistent with a Spriggan attack.>
Please help methese women are crazy, they're going to kill me for no reason!
Turn around and leave. This pitiful excuse for a man has wronged all three of us. It's none of your business.
Don't interrupt me while I'm working!
Never enough provisions, but we do what we can.
This will be Erning's last picnic. I hope he enjoys it.
Erning is a three-timing bastard. He gets whatever Adrienne gives him. I think she's looking for an excuse not to kill him though. Maybe just maim him a little.
Got gold? Spend it here. Don't waste your money on the trash for sale by other merchants!
Best deals in townquality goods, no watered-down ale or stale beer here!
I heard the Maulborn have spies in the city. Maybe that's what all this fuss is about.
Seems silly, doesn't it? Sweeping the front porch when our house is in ruins. I just don't know what else to do.nnAt least no one's tried to stab me in the last few days.
That was an impressive bit of work. I was right to doubt <<1>>'s claims about the amulet. Thank you for sparing my hide that bit of unpleasantness.
You should get out of here. Imperial troops assume everyone new is here to support the rebellion.
