Did you really just leap down into this slime pit?nnYou're either remarkably brave or really stupid. My guess? A little of both.
I can do this. I really can. All I have to do is  oh, who am I kidding? I can't do this! There's no way!nnWhy did I ever think I could make it in the Fighters Guild?
Some of those Dunmer travelers invited me for a drink. They probably want to see what a drunk Argonian looks like.
Can't talk. I'm on duty. Last time I did, I got latrine cleaning for a month. Not going to make that mistake again.nnBloody Sovngarde, I'm doing it again!
The dead outnumber the living in Cheydinhal. Sometimes I wonder which group is better off.
This isn't a safe place for anyone not in the Imperial army. Get across the river!
My family has lived here for three generations. Now our home is gone, all gone.
Just let me rest. Hilio is doing all he can, for me and the others. Nothing you can do.
Get away! This is my hiding placego find your own!
So many dead and wounded. No cause is worth this!
If I can just fix this old cart, Junia and I can load up our few remaining possessions and get out of here.
<You recognize this figure's familiar face from the images projected by the Speaking Stones. It is none other than Eboric Direfrost, his features frozen in abject horror.>
Ah, a new guest has joined our little party! And will you provide amusement and interesting diversion? I think you just might, at that!
You aren't one of our soldiers.
<Borgath obviously hasn't been dead very long.>
Have no fear. I shall be free in a moment.nnBut why wait when you're standing right there. A little help, please.
Welcome. Are you here to help in our time of troubles?
You helped us get out of that terrible place. I won't forget that.
I was almost out of those ropes, but I still appreciate your help. Thanks.
This is no place to dally, friend. I'm waiting for the Vicecanons to arrive as soon as they've stabilized Stormhold.nnUntil then, travel on this road is not advised.
You'll want to find a different route. Travel on this road is not advised.nnI'm waiting for the Vicecanons' arrival. They have their hands full stabilizing Stormhold, or so I hear.
Who are you. What do you want? You've been spying on me, haven't you? Watching me!
You so much as smirk and I'll gut you.
Talk fast, stranger. You look like a spy to me.
This poor soldier. He didn't have to die. At least the Khajiit got away. How long can he manage to survive, though, I don't know. My clan can be very persistent.
You've made some progress, I see. You fleshly types, so energetic.
Welcome to the Hissing Guar! How can I help you?

This one doesn't understand the game the little Elf and the snake thing are playing, but we have something important to do! We need to get into this tower. The key to our victory, it's in there! I know this to be true!

We shall help you enter the tower. But first, you must help us against these foul Wood Elves. Do not listen to their lies!nnThey murder our children! For no reason! Please, you must help me save the little ones!
By the First Forge! Welcome, bloodkin.
I may be sleeping in this tent by myself. Jena refuses to leave our house, battered as it is. If you heard that thing groan with every breeze, you'd be sleeping out here too.
Have you seen Brielus? Is he still setting up that stupid tent? He thinks our house is about to fall down, but I'll chance it. I'm not sleeping in a tent.
Look at these. Water damage. Loose ropes. It's amazing they survived at all.nnDid you need something?
Who are you and why are you here? Stop staring at me!
Where is everyone? No more drinkers in town?
Are you the new bartender? More mead!
Sit and listen awhile, friend. If you hear something you like, coin is appreciated!
By Malacath's bloody mace, I feel so much better! That unbearable cloud of fear and confusion has finally lifted. I assume that this is your doing?
You should not be here. This place is dangerous.

I know, I know. The signal fire is out. There's nothing I can do though. I had just stepped outside to relieve myself and all these slavers came out of nowhere. nnHow was I to stop them? I'm a lighthouse keepernot a soldier.
Do you have a comb? These damn slavers messed up my hair.
I'm in your debt. I will pray for Rupta to guide you in all your journeys.
Knowing that Captain Angarthal is dead will keep me warm for many nights to come. You fight well, friend.

Anyone who wants to join the Fighters Guild in Mournhold has to talk to me. Are you good in a fight? Ready to serve and protect? While the army is off to war, it falls to us to deal with the Daedra.nnLet me know if you want to sign up.
You enter the Mages Guild at a most difficult time, friend. Please bear with us.
Even in our time of grief, the work of the Mages Guild must go on.
The Mages Guild always has numerous irons in the fire. We could always use some help.
Why are you still here?nnThe one person in this entire place that has free reign to come and go as you please, and you come back? I'll never understand some people.
What's going to happen to us? Why won't they let us leave the city?
Since you're working for Councilor Ralden, you've been granted access to come and go as you please.nnDon't abuse the privilege. And don't disappoint these people. They're counting on you.
I'm sure you must find my predicament endlessly amusing.
The plague is coming and they lock down the city!nnThey're going to get us all killed.
They have no right to do this.nnI have family in Mournhold. We know it's safe there. The Tribunal would never let harm come to their city.
Do I look feverish to you? We should never have left Eastmarch.
I'll recover. Don't let them send me home, please! I want to make my father proud and return as a Thalmor guard.
Don't look at this one with pity in your eyes! This one is tougher than she looks, I promise you. I will finish this cursed school and join the Thalmor to protect the Dominion.
This one just has to stay strong, a while longer. This one is sure they'll send us to the Thalmor soon. Right?
I won't let them beat me. I won't! This is all just part of the training, to make us strong, right?
Ha ha! Look at the poor fool, Adima. Does he think he can defeat your mistress in her own realm?
It would be amusing, Count Hosni, if his insolence weren't so insulting. But he'll get his comeuppance. I just hope we're there to see it.
What are you doing here? Get away from our prisoner!
I've got weapons if you've got coin. Let's keep this brief, eh?
If our queen could see us, she'd send help immediately!
This is madness. Why wasn't <<1>> around to stop these pirates?
Have we met? Got knocked on the head by one of the pirates. I think it was a pirate.nnI don't feel so good.
Pirates or not, I have wares to move. Schedules don't keep themselves.
No matter what happens, we must honor our commitment to the Fighters Guild.
Bloody black-hearts! I sailed out as the pirates sailed in. Their mages blasted my boat!nnBarely made it to shore. If I can't fish, how do I find the gold to fix this thing.
Sharp. Pointed. Makes a clear statement to your enemies.nnNobody will make swords for you but Zhosh, so get them right here.
I don't know why everyone's standing around. We don't fish? We won't eat!
Look, I just want to do what's right. Anyone who wants to grab a pole can fish, but I won't turn over our catch for free.
We're all tired, we're all frightened, and we're all hungry! I just want to make sure I get my fair share!
You look like you could use a drink. Listen well, friend. Ale makes everything better.
My food isn't anything to write home about, but it is hot and filling. Let me get you something.
I drink, therefore I brew. Heehee. Just a little brewer humor.nnCan I get you something wet and wondrous to drink?
Bless you for what you've done! I never thought we'd see our homes again.
<<1>> really acquitted himself.nnHe's no <<2>>, you understand, but few people are.
Enough with <<1>>, I say. <<2>> has room for one hero, and I say it's <<3>>!
I fed one of the pirates to a strangler. He kept screaming, even when he was inside it. Not sure how to feel about that.
Welcome to Daggerfall, stranger. Enjoy your stay.
Go away. Leave me be. There's nothing for you here.
Seems like the war in Cyrodiil never ends. We need more soldiers willing to do their part. That's the only way we'll win this damn war.
<This Veiled Heritance officer looks like he was killed recently.>

Our Lady Almalexia has asked us to keep an eye on Vox's forces until her champion arrives.nnWe'll make our stand here if her troops attempt to leave this place. Though we may fall in battle, we do so in the name of our Lady.
You're favored by the Ghost Snake, outsider. Did you find the eggs?
Who are you? And why are you dragging that frost witch behind you?nnOut with it.
Outrageous! What kind of protection can the vicecanons offer if they can't protect a Dunmer in his own home!
The dryskins do not welcome our prayers. But they are confused.nnI don't pray for their dead. I pray for those who live in these dark times.
I thought it'd be safe for us here in Riften after we escaped Northwind. But just look at this place
Finally, we're away from those Reach bastards.
I saw horrible things at the mine. Is anyone trying to save the ones who didn't escape?
You know the deceased? I do hope so. Too many people have come, as if this is a spectacle for entertainment.nnBow your head as you leave. The Hist watches us all.
All must return to the swamps, eventually. We are but borrowing a spark of life from the world. It must be passed on for life to continue.nnTake comfort in that, if nothing else.
Please don't tell the guards we're here. We need a place to stay, just for a little while.
We've been watching this place. No one lives here anymore. Just leave us be. I'm only trying to keep my family safe.
Lookin' for armor? I'm your man. What'll it be?
Greetings. Please excuse the mess. Sinmur has disrupted everything.
Welcome, friend. How may I help you?
Welcome to Menoit's Emporium. If I don't have what you need, then you don't really need it.
Be quiet! Those thugs haven't found me yet. I can stay down here for days.
The Midnight Union's retreatedand I never got a chance to clout one of them!
I guess I'll be replanting half the field. But thanks for saving what you did.
This horse is not for sale. So don't ask.
Well, what'll it be? Don't waste my time.
Once we defeat the Imperials, we can start rebuilding Cheydinhal. We must re-take this town!
My family  My friends  Please, you must help them!
Sorry, little busy here. Speak to Hadriss if you need something.
Keep walking, hero. If I had business with you, you'd never see me coming.
Armor is like tree barka tough outer coating protecting the tender insides.
We meet again, little fleshling. Surely this must be fate!nnOr perhaps I could not get enough of that sour look on your face. You're quite cute when you're annoyed, sweetling.
Are they gone yet? Damned cats nearly ate me!
Well, what is it? I've got a lot to do today.
As soon as I can, I'm leaving this cursed town. I've been indentured to these Nords far too long.
Is Thane Fjora still alive? I couldn't stay in Nimalten anymore. Who knew that Riften was even worse?
May your sword always strike true!
I pray for the souls of those we have lost. You should do the same.
Don't mind Akarn. He's surly until he's drunk.
Sorry, just enough mead for us two. Go find your own!
Dark clouds gather over Aldcroft. You don't need magicka to see that.
Never extend your claws unless you intend to use them. The same is true of magic. If you're going to cast a spell, you may as well unleash a monsoon of magicka.
Welcome to Shadehome. Need a bed for the night?
Yes, I sample my own wares. What of it? With all that's been going on out there, we all deserve a few drinks.
First time Mari's been able to sleep since Sinmur's attack. Please don't wake her.
The secret to my wonderful physique? Why, I cook my own food, of course.
We're hanging by a thread here. One more setback and we've lost this war.
Bed and brew. We've got the best of both! Just go on in and see my wife, Bolfrosti. She'll get you set up.
Hey there! Skills getting rusty or looking for new ones?
What sort of gear are you missing?
Hey, I saw you earlier! Next to the injured elf girl.nnGlad you could help her and, well, everyone here. Don't suppose you'd be willing to help me with something as well?
When the guild calls, all must answer.
You want to poke someone with something sharp? Come talk to me!
Do Guar look  tasty to you?
Greetings, traveler. Not even Sinmur can shut us down!
Sorry, can't help you. Too much paperwork. Go talk to someone else.
I've found that my workers perform better when I watch them closely.nnTakes a lot of effort on my part, but productivity has never been better.
Did you take my favorite pole? Someone did.
I have the finest woven cloth in the north. What is it you're looking for?
Ignore Eager. His shadow frightens him and it's dark in here. Nimalten's a nice place, full of friendly folk!
I was told Eastmarch was a nice place. It wasn't. So I came here. And what did I find? Bandits, Reachmen, giants. nnI should dig a hole to live in.
First it was bandits attacking on the roads, now Fjora is attacked right here in town. I'm sick of it.
This store was my life. What now, retire?
Don't worry about us, stranger. The giant made a mess of things, but we'll rebuild.nnI hope someone kills that thing, and soon.
We were thinking of starting a family. But now? Everything we'd worked for, gone in an instant.
The fish aren't biting anymore. Something's scaring them off.
The Covenant sends troops here to watch over us. Are we children?
These are joyless times in Riften.
I appreciate Sifvid taking me in and giving me work here. But it's been five years. Any longer and I'll grow scales and gills. I want to see the world. You know what I mean?
I can hardly wait to strike the bandits. Until then, we train.
I love listening to songbirds. So does Dimi!
I may not have everything you want, I'm afraid. Those Red Rook thugs help themselves to my stock and leave me precious little to sell.
Take care. The shrine downstream was once a site of great evil. Perhaps it still is, as the fishing is poor here.
Greetings, adventurer. Come, check out the finest that Nimalten has to offer!
Welcome to my inn. A room for the night, a meal, or both?
If you find a hair in your drink, blame the dog. Mutt sheds like a dead pine.
Hungry? I got anything you'd want right here.
Bandits ambushed my companions and me while we escorted these merchants here. Poor bandits.
I've got a stalwart band of mercenaries at my back. What more could I ask for?
The last person that made a joke about my cooking ended up wearing a pot of stew. Just saying.
Good to see you, my friend. nnMuch to do in Crosswych, but things are improving daily.
Well, I must say, I was quite annoyed with those Red Rook ruffians. They took anything that wasn't nailed down.
We are grateful for your help.nnNow we just have to make sure to keep our town safe in the future.
Much obliged to you for all your help.
Prepared to learn the intricacies of our craft?
In these times, the talents of all mages are welcome.
How can I help outfit you?
Don't fool with alchemy unless you know what you're doing!
The Rift may be falling apart, but at least the guild library is still here.
The rare and unusual are my specialty. Care to look?
Organizing these books is a losing cause. Mages are such slobs.
Enter our hall, friend. Unlike some guilds, all are welcome here.
Feast yer eyes, pilgrim! The great Vithon Battlewolf and his, er, battle wolf. We won't see his likes again, as Mother always said, curse her tongue.
I don't know why they didn't just kill us all.
I wish those two would shut up. I can't hear myself think.
Nothing on those pirates' belts but empty pockets.nnI suppose that makes sense. They came here hoping to fill them.
Bloody pirates, swimming up from below!nnI should get down to the hold, help finish them off. But, oh, it hurts .
Pirate mages blasted the deck. If I don't put out the cinders, the Prowler will go up like a torch!
Don't get a blade from those other guys. They're rubbish! Buy from me!
Have you ever seen anything like this? It is High Elf make, but what it's for, I've no idea.
We were destined to meet. Why are you saving so much from my low, low prices? It is your destiny.
Ten days in the cage for two underweight fish. Seems a little extreme, doesn't it?
Shoulda chopped off that bum's hands, insteadda throwin' him in the cage. Gives us all a bad name.
Welcome. How can I help you today?
We offer a rare selection of ingredients here. A true specialty shop. There's a solution for any problem you might have.
I have plenty to sell. And I've saved you a trip to the market!
If you can find these goods cheaper  well, you'll have to walk pretty far to find bargains like this.
I was up all night reading this book. But I'm so close to being done. Just a few more chapters, I promise.
I always prefer a walk in the country to a crowded marketplace.
We meet across a crowded table of goods. We lock eyes. nnAnd I ask you what you want to buy.
Oh, hello. I saw you coming. Last week, I believe it was.

I'm good  It's a wonderful thing, traveling.nnSo much interes-intra  new. Like-like Breton wine. So interes-  it's great stuff.

Crosswych needs a stronger Mages Guild presence.

I could stay here like this all day.
What a beautiful day! I just wish I knew why it smells like wet fur over by the river.

Don't talk to me. Talk to your gods.

Another one of my shipments has been delayed. They say that there's some kind of trouble at Camlorn and Aldcroft. It's really quite vexing.

Get out, before I beat you senseless.

Have you seen the guillitone in the marketplace? I think they're going to do something about that Dreamer cult.nnI'll be glad when this is all over.

Working in a garden is almost as nice as living in the forest.nnAt least, that's what I keep telling myself.
My father named me after a flower. My mother taught me to tend her garden.nnI got sick of it, so I moved out here to be a carpenter. I made the right choice.
I told <<1>> someone would come to stop this madness.nnAnd here you are, but you're too late.
Welcome to the house of the Eight. Enter and may you find whatever it is you seek.
Look what the sea spat out, Lambur. Might be just what we need. You interested in some easy money?

<This farmer was mauled to death by sabre cats. A tattered note is clutched in her hand.>

I'm tired of chasing that damned Breton.
I can't believe it. Trelan and Iriana were finally on their way off this rock!

This one regrets ever coming to Stros.
I miss Ebonheart. I wish I was home.
I'm a master trader from House Hlaalu! I'm welcome everywhere. But these people want to sacrifice me to some snake!

Don't you be causing any trouble, understand?nnBertrand might be friendly and forgiving, but I like to break things.

This is the part where I trust you.

Thank you, for Rilyn and for my family. nnRilyn will keep me safe, forever. For now, I just need to rest.
Velyn Harbor is a beautiful city. We'll restore it to its glory, I'm certain of it.
I'm not sure if I should welcome you or curse you.

Pirates? Who said anything about pirates? I certainly didn't. I'm just an honest business woman waiting for her ship to come in.nnSo to speak.
What you did here was impressive. I hope the rest of Velyn Harbor realizes that.nnI also hope they'll welcome an Argonian trader. Not all of us are warriors or fanatics.
Why would she want to go in alone? I swear, if the Silvenar finds out about this, I'll never hear the end of it!nnSorry, I'm trying to keep an eye on <<c:1>>. Not having much luck, though.

Let me catch my breath before the next round, small one.
Let me catch my breath before the next round, small one.

I don't care about the Covenant's wars. I just need some food and a safe place to sleep.
I've spoken to some of the Mabrigash Wisewomen. They've been perfectly polite.

Don't get me wrong. This is a nice place, but it can't compare with Orsinium.

Greetings, I have every thing a young Alchemist can want.

I thought we were all dead. You and the captain got us out, but it was damn close.

Sit down, warm your bones.nnSee the two dead pirates? They killed Lazy Gwael. I liked him. Only pirate I ever knew who liked rats.nnNow, the pirates who killed him are rat food. Seems fitting, doesn't it?
Fair warningdon't drink the rum in the desk below. I'd guess someone poisoned it.nnThis is a nice bed.
If you're looking for that bastard Jakarn, he's at the tavern with a Redguard girl.
Hey there, glad to see you made it out.

Just leave me alone, would you?
Tedras must be strong if he hopes to get through his teachings. Let us hope they do not send him on many boats.

How much longer must I wait? I need this loan!

I can almost see Bangkorai from here.nnI knew I would have to leave home when I married into a Breton family, but now, I don't think I can ever go back.
I have a job. I don't live in a swamp. People here don't try to kill me.nnThe way I figure it, I'm better off than most Argonians.
I miss the ocean.nnI left home so I could go on an epic journey, but I don't think I've reached my destination yet.
You've inspired a number of Velyn Harbor's citizens to join the militia. You rescued them, now they'll protect the town when you're gone.nnThank you!

The Dwemer were wonderful machinists. We could learn much from studying their works.
If the others were unharmed, maybe there is hope for my sweet <<1>>!
I don't know why we're still here. <<1>>'s the boss, so we wait on her orders.nnI could use a strong drink right about now.
That was amazing! I'll need to get myself some of that oil now.nnUh, but don't mention that to <<1>>.
I trust you are here to help. Dark rituals are being performed around the island. nnI first smelled the corruption on the wind. Then my shaman found evidence at an Ayleid ruin nearby.

Summoning spirits can be dangerous work. I heard about you. About how you entered the ruins of Baelborne tower.nnYou must not undo the sacrifices that have already been made. My master sent me to give you advice and guide you to the right decision.
Nyah, go away! Supper's not for another hour, at least!
It's such an honor to work here! <<1>>'s rotmeth is legendary. His family's made it for generations. I wonder if I'll ever be trusted with their secrets!
I'd still be in <<1>> if those blasted Houndsmen hadn't stirred up trouble.nnMaybe <<2>> will come to his senses soon.
Isn't <<1>> a marvel? He's from Summerset! The songs he plays are from all over!

What is this place? What happened to the tower? What  what have you done?nnThe Baelbornes hired you, didn't they? But you don't understand. You don't know what I gave up to stop them. I lost everything! I lost my  my baby.
Please hurry! If nobody stops them they'll eat everything, even the trees!
There's something not right here. The forest, the beasts  everything's wary. Watching.
What  what's going on? Where am I?nnWait, I know you. I feel like we just talked but  I can't remember anything.
I walked in here and this young man nearly fell on my head!nnAnd you? Were you successful?
Have you ever been in lovemadly, desperately, stupidly in love? If so, you know how I feel. Madria and I were meant to be together.nnIf only I weren't so hateful in her father's eyes.
You'd better not be here to talk about Remius. I hear enough of him from my daughter, who needs to learn obedience. Remius - bah! He'll never have Madria.
You you look familar. Have we met? My memory is hazy, I took ill on a recent trip to Deshaan.
Father doesn't understand. Remius and I love each other. We must be together!
The work around here never ends. I'm just resting for a bit.
Shoveling mud! I suppose it's better than getting my skull bashed in by a Goblin or being eaten alive by a zombie. And I'm getting paid for it, so it could be worse.
I hope Amadour comes up with new pumpkin recipes soon. I'm sick of eating fried pumpkin every day.
No time for idle chatter. I'm testing a new way of growing corn. I flood the field, keeping the plants wet all the time. I just have to figure out why half my crop keeps dying.
If I catch that pervert Shagol staring at my backside one more time, he'll get this shovel between the eyes. That should teach him.
The time has come to leave Coldharbour.
Joy to you. Have you ever seen a pleasanter place? Dirt upon one's hands, life growing, the smell of manure on the breeze. No more the soldier's fate for me.
Quickly  you've defeated the guardian, but it will return soon. You need to get inside the city and locate the three spinners.

Every night, I pray to Arkay to kill me in my sleep. Every morning, I wake up, still here. I hate this place. There's nothing to do, everything's always dirty, and I'm dressed in rags. Someday I'm going to beat Octavimus to death with this broom.
Hi,nGo talk to the Second bot, on my left, Thanks!
Don't cross the headman here, stranger. You'll end up in the Grave.
Hello.nI'm kinda busy at the moment, please talk to my sister over there, to my left.
Cropsford's not much, but it's good enough for me. Start a family, grow crops, grow old, and pass it along to your children. Who needs anything more?
C'mon, in or out. Stop blocking the gate.
At times it is a hard decision: grow crops or wallow in the waters.
I've been praying to Z'en for the Drublog to stand down. None of us would survive against their mad rage.
We haven't had a good night's sleep ever since the Drublog arrived.nnWhat I wouldn't give for them to up and leave.
The Drublog should be ashamed of what they're doing to this valley. They destroy the Green without a care.
I've heard rumors that <<1>> has been seeing the Drublog chief's son.nnA fool's folly. She's too good for that lout.
I hope my lackwit twin isn't bothering you. Ever since the accident Well, just look at him.
Do you know why we're building more walls? I sure don't.nnNo one tells me anything, but I think there's something odd going on.
I have a question for you!
I thought we would be pulling up stakes by now, but the general wants more walls.nnI don't ask. I just do.
I thought we would be moving on by now, but the general wants us to put up more walls.nnThat means I don't have much time to talk to wanderers. Excuse me.
Everyone around here is on edge. I mean, it's a dangerous place, but I think they're ready to move on.
I don't have any food to spare, but I can certainly sell you some brew.
Hey there. Interested in one of my girls? They're the finest mares on the Isle.
Did my sisters send you to aid us?
My darling daughter. No. She  she can't be dead. No, no, no.
Have my sister's sent you to aid us?
New to <<1>>? Walk softly around the Bloody Fists.
Don't know why I bother. The fools sink these boats as fast as I fix 'em.
Kaleen's never getting off this island. No one's gonna sail with her ever again.
The Spearhead's no Maiden's Breath, but at least she doesn't have a giant hole in her side.nnI'd be happy if we never saw land again.
Stros M'Kai is a depressing place. Too many Redguards waving their damn swords around. At least on the Spearhead, no one wants to kill me except Irien.nnShe'll come around. She's crazy about me.
I'm looking forward to seeing Jakarn in action. I hear he's an incredible sailor. Lots of  stamina.
Blade's edge, we're setting sail with the famous Jakarn!nnElethian and I have a bet on who's going to bed him first.
I'd give my sword arm for him!
I can't wait to see Jakarn's battle scars. I'm sure he's got them everywhere.
Wherever Captain Lerisa goes, I go. Even on this tub. Can't wait until we get our own ship again.
Ah! Don't sneak up on me.
<This body has multiple stab wounds and several blunt impact wounds. It's been stripped of anything valuable.>
I can't hold a sword yet, but I can hold a book. Perhaps I should find a book that will teach me to fight with my left hand!
Really, how do they eat this stuff? I'm going to teach Fenlil a thing or two about cooking.
<This body had its head bashed in. There are no valuables.>

The Spearhead's a good ship but she's no Maiden's Breath. At least she'll get us away from Stros M'Kai.nnLooking forward to getting to know Lambur better. I like an Orc with a quick blade and a quicker tongue.
When active, Dwemer spiders have an extraordinary capacity for learning.nnNow I have to stop Andrilion from teaching Clanker to bring him drinks.
Wonderful. Now I've been ordered to follow Neramo on another fool's errand. At least the drinks are free.
To be on the seas once again. This is paradise.nnHeadman Bhosek is a cruel master. If Kaleen will have me, I will join the Spearhead's crew.
This should be an interesting voyage. Quite a crew Kaleen has thrown together!
Captain Kaleen took her time getting off this damned island. Doesn't surprise me. Orc problems aren't her problems.nnBut we'd be stuck here if not for your help. I won't forget that.
I think I'm on the verge of a breakthrough. Stand back! This could be messy.
I don't want to die out here! You've got to help me!
The bounty of the sea nourishes my family. Early word of approaching ships brings coin from Headman Bhosek as well.
I thought I was the last one left out here. Well, get up here and fight beside me. Today is a glorious day to die!

<<1>> iwrites as fast as possible, but still these spinners come up with more to say! After uncountable generations, they still change the story.nnDo you know the story of the Silvenar and the Green Lady? Or I should say, one of the stories?
The witches use magic the likes of which I've never seen before. I don't entirely trust it, but it does seem to be working.

She needs time. Her daughter died right in front of us. The imps just kept tossing bolts of fire. They wouldn't stop. It took everything I had just to keep the flames at bay.nnSomething evil corrupts the forest spirits. It must be stopped!
In <<1>>, the wise look for protection against the blades of the Bloody Fists.
I still can't believe this is happening. The forest has never turned on us before.nnAnd there are so few of us now. I hate to say it, but this might really be the end of Deleyn's Mill.
Peace to you, wayfarer, but I have naught to sell. Speak with my mother below.
Some gather firewood only when they see snow fall. The spring sun will thaw their corpses.
I don't have time for idle chatter. This wheel won't fix itself.
Larus is stubborn as an ox. Maybe it comes from hauling this cart around all day.
Need a weapon? These Redguards love swords, but I sell all varieties.
My poor Jakarn! I don't want to think about what they're doing to him down there. He's a Prince! He doesn't belong in the Grave.
<<<1>> died recently, blood still oozing from his wounds.>
Shhh. Don't tell Ufgra you saw me here. She's always finding something for me to do.
A fortunate tide brings you to my stall, traveler.
Khajiit make me nervous. We must be desperate to be hiring all these conscripts.
My darling son's gone off on some fool errand. I hope he returns in one piece.
We weren't supposed to be here so long. The general's waiting for something, but I don't know what it is. Reinforcements, maybe?nnI don't care about his reasons. I care for the wounded.

Selling supplies to these grunts is child's play! I don't think the moron commanding them was ready for this mess.nnOf course, it is also my distinct pleasure to sell to discriminating travelers such as yourself.
You'll have to come back later I'm afraid. My master is out on a grand adventure at the moment.
The melodies ease my mind. I like being around all these musicians.
Excuse, please. This one must entertain the guests.
Shove off. Can't get into their coinpurses with you standing around.
Excuse me. A hundred guests to feed before evening. Lots to do and only ten fingers to do it with.
Yeah, yeah, welcome to Skywatch. I've got work to do.
The quarry faces the hunter at last. You won't stop me from claiming my prize!
What can this one get you?
Zally admits, she likes to keep the upstairs clean. Warmer up here, and fewer drunken hands to squeeze her tail.
Nice to get some warmth into these old bones. The mistress is kind to give us time to rest.
Come, sit by the fire. Nice and warm.
They keep asking me if I have trouble getting things off the top shelf. Geniuses.
No, we don't know any of the "Lusty Argonian Ballads." Sit.
Don't worry. The beer's better than the music. What can Mic get you?
Don't worry. The beer's better than the music. What can Mic get you?

My father met my mother in a tomb not far from here. He said when their eyes first met, he was struck dumb. She cut him down from the spider nest, and they're together ever since.nnPerhaps I'll meet a lass the same way. Keep up the family tradition!
You look tired. The best beds in all of <<1>> are right upstairs!
Kaleen's still hiding behind Lambur, eh? If I catch her alone, I'll suck her eyeballs out.
Hmm? Don't want any. Stop bothering me.
Don't bother Grubulash. She's obsessed when researching.
<A slit throat marks the end of this Breton's adventures in the exciting city of <<1>>. The backpack next to the body has been emptied.>
Nothing like a good book, is there? And this is nothing like one, I'm afraid.
So far, Cropsford hasn't been ravaged by this war. Some say we've been lucky. I say we've been blessed by Zenithar.
No man can resist my charms. It's good to know I've still got it!
The only good Goblin is a dead Goblin. With its head cut off.
<The monkey seems agitated and keeps looking eagerly toward the coastline.>
Leave me to my drink, stranger. If I can't remember what matters, might as well forget it all.
Cropsford may seem peaceful, but trouble is everywhere.
Who's there? <<1>>? nnNo, you're someone else. Please, don't kill me. I've nothing of value to steal.
No matter where I travel, my bargains are all the same!
I'm in the mood for skewered Goblin. You with me?
You'd have to walk awfully far to find bargains like mine  farther than I do!
By the thousand scales of Satakal! What savings!
The prisoner must pay for his crimes. It is the only way to restore order to the kingdom.
My customers all say the same thing: Mahbub knows quality. Mahbub knows bargains.
If you've got extra junk you want to get rid of, I'll give a decent price for it.nnIf you're looking to buy, my prices won't break you. I'm not that kind of merchant.
We weren't prepared for the Aldmeri Dominion to assault Farwatch Tower. Now we're scrambling to keep them contained.
Blasted elves! How dare they attack Farwatch!nnWe're not prepared for this. If they launch a full assault, we're doomed.
Death is but another moment in time. Quickly, continue your mission or my sacrifice will be worthless.
Death came before all but life. It will come again to us all. I shall linger, though, to see your mission conclude.
The future is always uncertain. You did what was necessary. Continue, and you may yet save Silvenar.
Hey. Get you something? A room, maybe a drink?
Glad to see you made it out.
Glad to see you made it out.
Glad to see you made it out.
I'm standing here trying to figure out how much this stop is going to cost us. The Queen's time is valuable, you know. nnKeeping up with noble fashions alone sets us back several gold a day.
Just jotting this stop down for posterity. Ahem. "The Queen was a stickler for tradition, and would not eschew the dead."nnNo, that doesn't sound good at all.
Damn this delay. Her majesty is too good for this pomp and circumstance.nnWe should be out with the people, not wasting our time with the dead.
The countryside is beautiful, is it not? Just wish my lovely wife were here to enjoy it with me.
<Qawi squeaks happily. He seems very fond of you.>
Are you with the Thalmor? Thank Y'ffre, I knew they'd send help!nnThey wiped our camp out. When the patrol disappeared, I thought  wait, where are the rest of you?
Stay wary, traveler. Unnatural creatures stalk these woods.nnWe paid the price for our ignorance. Learn from our mistakes.
Your scent is familiar, but I do not know you. Why do you interrupt my courtship of the Hound?
My wife will never know what happened to me.
Just being back on a ship brings more memories. I'm looking forward to the voyage.
Run while you still can! There's no telling when they'll strike again!
Damn that Kaleen. Won't sail with her again, no money in it.

A Breton fighting for the Direnni? Somewhat surprising though not unheard of considering the current circumstances.nnWait a moment. That armor . I've heard stories about you. They say you fight as if Auri-El himself blessed you.
Please get some water and help me, my tree is on fire!
I pray that blessed Tava sends a ship soon. Never again shall I sail on the Spearhead.
Ask anyone. If you want the best, you need to make it yourself.
How can I help you, friend?
<The captain doesn't seem to notice you. He's staring intently at something behind you.>
I bring fine powders, tinctures, and concoctions from far away lands.
Favorable winds no longer fill Captain Kaleen's sails. I fear she is landbound forever.
Wanna drink? Better than the stuff the tavern serves!
Know, O wayfarer, that Bloody Bhosek will soon be no more. Await the sign and strike with us!
Soon, the fates shall descend on Headman Bhosek and he shall be no more!
Shh! Don't give me away. Soon as I get a chance, I'm climbing those vines and robbing this place.
Hoping to see Bhosek? So am I, for three days now!
I'm sorry, but I don't really feel like talking. I've been trying to find a quiet minute all day. nnI need to pray for my son. He's missing, you see.
The gods have abandoned Stros M'Kai. All live only at the whim of Headman Bhosek.
Don't irritate him, please. He can be quite cruel.
My daughters! They spend all day working in that inn.nnI'm so proud of their success, but now they're all grown up! This house is so big and empty when they're away.
I don't see "Meet Disreputable Stranger" on the headman's agenda, so you'll need to wait for another day.
Don't touch anything! Everything's in its proper place; I don't want anything moved.
The waters of justice flow around this cursed town, avoiding all in it.
Isn't he done talking yet? I've been waiting forever!
I hate this place, don't you? But I can't drag Gurilda away from her books until she's read every last cursed one.
This place would be nice, if Bhosek weren't around.
Surprised to see me? So were the Sea Elves. I didn't even have time to say "Mages Guild!" before they killed me. nnAnd now, here sits poor old Beddi. Stuck because of that stupid bet.
I'm waiting for someone  someone who isn't you.nnI think it would be best for you to leave now.
Stars above, more interruptions. Is this important? I'm monitoring a very delicate experiment right now.
You haven't seen a sneaky little Goblin around here, have you? I'm gonna kill that thing, no matter what Amadour says.

On behalf of the Knights of the Flame, I came here to pay my respects.nnYou saved my order and now my king, friend. I have a feeling I will hear about many more of your accomplishments in the future. I'm honored to know you.
You remind me of my old self. Proud, and full of hope.
In all the years I've known him, I've never seen Godrun so emotional. nnI'm sure the king will forgive him, but I worry that he will not be able to forgive himself.
<This man was killed by wild beasts.>
<This man is dead. Beetles have been gnawing on the corpse.>
<This woman was killed by wild beasts.>
The souls of the dead are restless. Ancient warriors who died in battle against the Bretons now rise. Who calls to them, and why?
The hills and valleys of this land are so beautiful. Even the light is different here than in my homeland.
Ho, there! You're who I think you are, aren't you?
<This scamp is not obviously aggressive. Around its neck is a choker bearing an inscription.>
The souls of the dead are restless. Ancient warriors who died in battle against the Bretons now rise. Who calls to them, and why?
Hello there! Are you enjoying the festival?
You return, new scent? To free the one who is trapped?
I'm drafting a report for command. I hope you don't mind accolades.nnIf it was up to me, you'd get the biggest damned medal they'd make!
Where am I? The attack  the lieutenant was injured. I pulled him into a bush to hide. nnAfter that  voices, dead ones! I struck at them  the lieutenant! He isn't ?
Who are you? Why does Lyris walk with you?
I've supplies for the seasoned traveler, and those who're just starting out. Please take a look.
You bring sunlight in your wake. Welcome and be blessed.
Ah! The savior of Silvenar. How can I help you?
Who's there? I thought I said I wasn't to be disturbed!
Shandi is a funny one! I hope she stays for the next feast.
Time I spend talking to you is time away from my patients.
Trouble follows like hyenas after the wounded. I wish they were dealt with as easily.
Just when things were settling down, the Khajiit make a mess.
So many tomes. So little time.
Did you hear what happened to the Mane? Disaster comes for us all eventually, but a Daedra? Unthinkable!
Welcome to my home. Do you like it?nnGreat. Thanks for stopping by. Now leave, before I throw you out.

And so we meet again. Tabakah and I were actually just on our way back to the Abbey.nnWe heard Abbot Durak was here so we came to tell him that the shrine was cleansed. I guess you beat us to it, though.
Ah! <<1>> did not hear you approach!  Too busy  helping the shopkeeper, ah  organize her wares! So organized now!nnAnd, um  <<2>> is nice this time of year, yes?
Oh! It's you. I can't believe it! nnI was just praying for Azura to watch over the king, and you show up at that very moment? This can't be a coincidence.
Queen Ayrenn decided a warrior would be her best ambassador to Silvenar. I agree.
You know, I was thinking. If Vaermina's Omens were really driving people mad, does that mean they weren't responsible for their decisions?nnNever minddon't answer that.
Ah  good to see you again, my friend. Your fame is growing fast. nnI hear your name all the time now. Better you take the spotlight, and I can stick to the shadows, eh?
It's you! You  you are amazing!
The Silvenar is saved, thanks to you! Our city will sing your name for years to come!
You set those Houndsmen running with their tails between their legs! Get it? Tails? You know, because they're  Houndsmen!nnHave a drink  it'll sound funnier then!
The spirits of the tree told me to follow you. They spoke of great suffering in Aldcroft.nnI'm here to aid in any way that I can.
Hello again. We decided that a few of us should come to help the refugees here.
Hail, friend! I was ordered to bring news of our victory at Camlorn to the main camp here in Aldcroft.
No, I'm not gonna do your laundry too. Bug off.
Thank goodness for the Sea Drakes. They may be bad people but the wrecks they cause are great!
You  you are not one of them. You have not the taint. Help us. Free us from this torment!
Piss off. Find your own junk pile.
There you are, Vestige. We must speak at once.
Hark at Kaleen, acting like she owns the town. I wish her a bitter fate!
The pain is bad enough. The surprise and betrayal, worse.
One definitely tires of seeing one's own blood.
Don't tell the others, but maybe going back to Kaleen would be better than sitting around here.
Things are settling down, now the town is free of the Red Rooks. nnI confess, it was a bit exciting, being part of the resistance.
I was thinking I might join the Fighters Guild.  See the world, have some adventures.
Thank you for what you have done.
I wanted to say thank you again.
Congratulations. You are a true hero.
Is this not peaceful? I seek refuge here when the cruelty of Bhosek and his minions overwhelms me.
Um, hello. That was a bit of a predicament. The Remly brothers do set a good trap, I must say. That one trussed me up tight.nnBut now that you're here  wait a moment. Who are you?

Divines bless you, friend! I am a good man who's fallen on hard times. I have eleven starving children that will surely die without a morsel to eat today. Won't you spare a silver for an honest man and his adoring children?
Hello, traveler! I am but a humble merchant searching for new markets for my fine goods. Can I interest you in a morsel of food? Perhaps you'd prefer a cool drink?
Raw seaweed. That's the secret. I could eat it for hours on end.
Just keeping my fingers warm, friend. I'll be playing in the tavern later tonight.
Careful. Bhosek's Fists watch strangers closely. Step out of line and you'll get beaten.
You have freed me! But my warriors still cry out for an end to their torment.
You're not a Supernal Dreamer. Who are you?
Have you seen the guillotine in the marketplace? I think they're going to do something about that Dreamer cult.nnI'll be glad when this is all over.
This waiting's killing me. I gotta get to sea again soon.
I didn't realize the harpies would be in so much agony. They hate being trapped like that.nnI'm starting to get a bad feeling about all this.

Something's not right. Gelvin hasn't returned yet and Lord Diel's getting more and more impatient.nnBy Azura, he doesn't look like he intends to do much research, either. I think he likes to watch those creatures suffer.

Ah, you're back. Much more reliable than those damn Daggers. I don't see their leader, Gelvin. He didn't come back with you? More gold for the rest of you, I suppose.nnNow, hand over the eggs, please.
Greedy, ignorant, ugly, son of a mammoth's ass! That Diel can go leap in the river.
Enjoying <<1>>? It's a fine place, until you get your throat slit.
Something fishy's going on here. I think Lord Diel hasn't been entirely truthful with us.nnBut how did you find me? Granette sent you, didn't she?
Ready to fight for the Dominion?
Hope I can help you find something magical.
How can this one serve you?
Knowledge is power. Power is power. Learn to wield both.
<<1>> will need your help dealing with these muskarse invaders. You're up to the task, yes?
I didn't want to do it, but it had to be done. nnI just hope he forgets all this when he gets back to his right mind if he gets back to his right mind, I suppose.
We'll work through the night if we have to. We're putting out to sea as soon as possible. This will be my last visit to Koeglin Village.
Have you ever noticed you just can't find a specific book when you really need it?nnGuess I'll just have to keep looking.
Get back, monster! I won't give in!
I'm glad Gelvin came to his senses.nnHe doesn't realize it yet, but sometimes you have to make wrong decisions for the right reasons. This was one of those times.
I'm glad my brother came to his senses.nnI don't care if Diel is a bastard. As long as he pays Gelvin for his work and no one gets hurt, that's all that matters to me.
I do hope you have both the thief and the egg with you. For everyone's sake.
I need to think about all this, but I think I'm all right with how it turned out.nnThank you for helping us. Without you, the Daggers would have disbanded and we'd all go hungry again.
Why did Zeht make this place such a desert? The horses' troughs never remain filled.
Bhosek's horses live better than we do, curse him.
Step back and wait your turn!
You're not staying for dinner too, are you?
This town's history is fascinating. Did you know that many of the Dwarven relics still function?
The quality of Orcish arms and armor are excellent, but their other goods
He's going to survive. He has to!
No one is going to help us. We're all going to die here!
These northern lands are not to my liking. The mud is frozen, the trees do not speak to me, and the winds are bitter. I long for Black Marsh.
Laganakh sent me to look for you. She was concerned for you and eager to know what you've learned.
It is gone. Everything. Torn away by the winds of death.
Huh. More driftwood washed up from the sea. I'm Tazgol's forge-wife, so watch your tongue or I'll pull it out.
Gelvin's sister gave up his location so easily. Now where is that damn thief?nnAnd where in the Eight is my damn egg?
Ah, see, another outlander. May you prosper in Sentinel more than I have. Stay moist.
My sister the mercenary needs to get out of the house and find a job. If I bought her a new dagger, do you think she'd get the hint?
In Orsinium we would have settled this zombie nonsense before breakfast. If these Redguards are afraid of the dead, what good will they be against the living?
The dry side of the city is best, yes?  Less salt on the whiskers  and fewer guards.
This one is happy he is a groundskeeper and not a dockworker. Eilam does not enjoy being eaten by zombies.
The risen dead, almost within the city walls! This is what happens when a Forebear is king.
Thank the Eight for imported mead. Little taste of home overseas, yeah? Ha!
You'll need a stout back to bear the weight of this armorbut you look like you're up to it. Have a look.
You look dry! Wash the sand down with a pint, eh?
Quite a place, the Sentinel market. And the prices are acceptableeven for foreigners.

I'm afraid these aren't for sale at present. I'm cataloguing inventory for the Mages Guild. They're obsessed with acquiring books like these.  nnYou should speak to them if you haven't already. Membership certainly has its benefits.
I only swim here when the Redguards are not looking. The water is cool, and clean. nnToo clean.
Those crates behind the target are brand new. A noble catches an arrow in the calf and suddenly it's safety first. What a joke.
Why is it so hot here? It smells like  goats. Why does it smell like goats?
How do these Redguards stay cool while wearing so much fabric?
Glag works us hard, but he pays well. I guess he misses Wrothgar.
I don't know what they do in there, but I see people come and go at all hours. I don't mind. I just want to know what's going on!
This cat follows me all over town. And when he begs for food, he gets it.nnI should have been born a cat.
Leki's Sparring Ring is closed to outsiders, but you may observe if you wish.
By Tava's red feathers, I'm sick to death of these monkeys! I buy a brand new fez from the bazaar, and they make off with it.
I'm going to go home, lock the doors, draw the windows shut, and sit quietly until this all blows over.  nnMay Onsi's justice come swiftly!
Have you been to the palace yet? It is a nest of asps and jackals. nnIf you are looking for the truth, you would be better served by speaking to the people.
The Frozen Palms has become quite raucous since the Nord took over. If you prefer to drink in peace as I do, you should stay here or seek out the tea house.
I stopped sparring here a long time ago.  Still enjoy watching, though.
You have need of these goods, is it not so?
I hope he still has a few bottles of the seventy-four in here. This year's batch was shamefully harsh. Quite undrinkable.
I have not seen much movement across the bridge since the docks came under attack. It is probably a good idea to stay indoors, wayfarer.
Look at that statue. I wonder who that was? nnI bet he was some Forebear's ancestor. Think they're better than us, you know.
We used to get more caravans from the south, but trade has been light recently.nnWith all this trouble at the docks, the well of prosperity may go dry before we know it.
I meet you at last. I saw you defeat the scheming Redguard who rules Stros M'Kai. I see great events swirling about you.
That's the package to be delivered to Magula, right?
I have a package for you.
I can't wait to tell Haraldar that this bastard is dead. It won't bring Inga back, but I know I'll sleep better now.
So Gelvin killed the bastard? I didn't think he had it in him.nnIt still doesn't change the fact that he botched our entire deal. I told you to talk him out of it.
Diel's gone, but I don't feel any better. These people depended on me and I failed them.nnI can't even do one job correctly.
Thank you for helping my brother. I was worried there for a bit, but it looks like everything worked out in the end.
Wait. Does this mean I get to build more traps and gadgets now?nnThis is most excellent news.
I knew Gelvin would come through!nnWe chose a good leader for the Daggers.
What can I tell you about the magical arts?
Good to meet you here, where the river runs to the sea.nnCan I get you something from guild stores?
You have much to learn, adept! What can Master Uftbat teach you?
And what do you want? You're just here to gawk at the weaponry, aren't you? Make a purchase or shove off.
Stand up straight, soldier! And tell me why I should train you.

The Daggers, the new champions of Daggerfall, have been victorious this day!nnHah, I always wanted to say that. Well, actually, I wanted to say that since about five days ago. When we formed. But still.
Gelvin actually went through with it. I'm surprised, to say the least.nnA little disappointed. A little happy. I'm so confused!
This is Abnur Tharn. The Master and I are very busy. This had better be important.nnWait a moment. I don't know your face. Identify yourself, immediately!
Oh, my head. No more drinking, I swear.
I'm a little busy here. These guar don't skin themselves.
<The body is warm to the touch. The odor of charred flesh suggests he was burned inside his armor.>
You're new to Daggerfall, aren't you? I know everyone in town.
Thank Kynareth I found you! You don't know how many people I met who had been torn apart by these cultists and their creatures.
Who's this, now? I bet you've got a wild tale or two to share.
I hope you're not expecting a performance. I had to sell off my equipment and instruments just to make ends meet.nnTimes are tough, my friend.
It's a fine day, isn't it? The fish are biting, and the water is soothing.
Since the war began, the market has never been busier.
I wasn't going to ask you for coin. I'm no begger. I prefer to sleep out here, where it's warm.
<<<1>>'s breathing is labored. She is not aware of her surroundings.>
Bloodthirsty savages! If they won't join the Covenant, they should be wiped out!
You don't look wounded. What do you need?
Greetings! Blessings of Arkay upon you.
I'm dying, aren't I? Hjorik keeps telling me I'm not, but I know I am.
When the Empire was strong, the madness that has overcome Bruma would not have been possible.
I couldn't take it down there anymore. I tried to help, but all that pain . I just need a rest, just for a little while.
Every day, the piles of dead and wounded grow and our supplies dwindle.
<Sud-Hareem keeps his focus on the center of the room. He pays you little mind.>
Greetings, traveler! Blessings of Arkay upon you.
No one said anything about haunted ruins and necromancers! I didn't sign up for this.
Superbly done, as expected. I'll just take a look around now that you've cleared the way.
Nothing but dusty tomes and rusty weapons. I expected tagging along with Neramo to be more lucrative.
Foul cultists, defiling the souls of the dead. I hope we find more of them so I can cut down a few myself.
Redguard architecture is so elegant, don't you think?nnFor human structures, that is.
Did you see the way that one looked at me? They all look at me like that.nnDo you think it's the tusks?
My husband and I came here all the way from Wrothgar.nnNow he just spends his time drinking and sleeping. And he leaves making the money for it to me. Lazy brute.
My husband was supposed to meet me here for a drink after work. A few glasses of wine, some Redguard poetry .nnI suspect I chose the wrong tavern. Or the wrong husband.
I don't trust that Khajiit as far I can throw him, but then again, I don't have to pay him much.
Too hot for me today. A person blessed with wisdom knows when to stay in the shade.
The king, Ruptga's blessings be upon him, invites all his kinsmen to enjoy this garden.  nnWe need such tranquility in troubled times, is it not so?
There are far too many foreigners in the palace for my liking.  Present company excepted, of course. nnDo mind the carpets, though. Blessings!
Have you come to speak to the Forebear king? I have waited long and long and he does not even lift his eyes. nnSuch is the way of things for Crowns in Sentinel.
Water is life. Without johad wells, our cities couldn't prosper.nnI dare not leave it while that Argonian lingers. I've heard distressing rumors.
When I heard the commotion from the docks, I came here. There is no safer place than the house of the king. Is it not so?
The palace has been like a tomb since the news of trouble at the docks. I am sorry, wayfarer, but I fear you may not receive much hospitality today.
I've no idea what most of this is, but I'm fairly certain you can't find it in Alinor. Smells like profit.
I've not seen the dead wandering the streets yet, thank Tu'whacca!
There are foul doings at the docks. May Onsi's justice be visited upon those responsible.
Is there a reason you're in the chief's chambers? nnIf not, be on your way!
Greetings, friend of Lambur. How can an old Orc help you?
Fair breezes unto you! I have all manner of needful things if you've a mind to buy. Please, feel free to browse.
I don't have much left, but I'm still in business. For now, at least.
You were among the crew that arrived with Lambur, yes? I envy you, free to see the world and make of your life whatever you wish.
Rajhin's shadow! <<1>> thought you another monster, coming up to . nnDo not surprise Zahra again!
Wait! Stop! Please don't hurt me.
Beer! It brings us together. Can I interest you in some liquid courage?
This one does not sail the seas for riches. Instead, the riches sail to him.
These bodies stink worse than High Elf perfume. Makes you wonder if these cultists were dead before they attacked.
So many dead. You'd think even Bretons would know better than to attack an Orc fortress.
Watch where you step. Still plenty of fresh corpses fouling up the place.nnCan't burn them soon enough, if you ask me.
You stand on Orc soil, outlander. Tread carefully. This is not a good time to visit our island.
Who're you? This is a dangerous place for the unwary.

Ah, my friend! <<1>>'s compatriots had the <<2>> appraised! Its enchantments are much diminished, but still worthy of study. They even found a buyer in Morrowind!nnSuch songs they will sing of us! May Khenarthi's breath carry them far and wide!
Eyes of Akatosh! You just scared the oblivion out of me!nnI guess that's what I get for reading these scary books.
Who  who are you? What are you doing in here? Everyone was supposed to be gone.
I don't care what they say, I wasn't drunk! I saw something!
You have entered my son's dream. Some uncorrupted part of him has sent me to tell you what you need to know.
I am sure that among Your Excellency's many virtues, generosity is paramount!
I hate taking things without asking, but a man's got to eat. If you saw anything, just keep it to yourself, all right?
Outlander. Have you met Lokra, the chief's daughter? She has a fascination with the lives of adventurers like you. It's unfortunate.
This desert sun has dried my scales. Would that I could buy some fresh water!
Wanna kill something? I got what you need.
How can it be so hot? How is this even possible?nnGods! I need enough coin to sail back to Skyrim. Have pity on a poor traveler!
We should just eat all the horses and be done with it.
Curse this leg. I hate sitting here while Bruma burns!
The guards won't let me drink from the fountains. They won't let me climb the trees to eat figs.nnI must depend upon the generosity of strangers  like you.
In the name of Morwha the compassionate, have mercy on a child of poverty.
Don't mind me. A little dust-up with the town guard. Nothing serious. Just keep walking, all right?
You are a stranger to me. What do you want?
Is it too much to ask, that I have a few moments of peace?
I keep telling him to lie still and be quiet, but like all Nords, he's too thick-headed to listen to reason.
Tall Papa aid me. Have you been to the docks, wayfarer? Half my inventory is missing. Probably ruined or looted. nnFahara'jad better settle this or he'll have a riot on his hands.
My husband was supposed to meet me here. He was due to arrive at port today  oh, Ruptga help me.
Just keep moving. Around here, folks are as likely to knife you as talk to you.
Don't mind Dommy, she just likes to fuss over me. I'll be up on my feet and hacking cultists to bits in no time.
Auri-el knows, I'm here to serve. What can I help you with?
Fivefold venerations, my friend. You've come to make a deposit, yes?
Thank you, again. Our injuries will heal, but I'll never forgive those Sea Drakes!
Thank you for your help in Vinedusk. It was a glorious battle.
You're a true hero of Reaper's March. Your efforts will not be forgotten.
Fine work, my friend. Vinedusk salutes you.
Don't bother me, traveler. I must be ready to aid the Prince at a moment's notice.
Such a waste of the Prince's time. That such a great man should be made to follow along after Ayrenn. Like a tamed hound!nnNaemon is no hound. He is a wolf.
My husband died in the invasion  but I never liked him anyway. nn<<1>>, now that's a lizard I could wrap my fingers around!
<<1>> lives to drink and sell another day!
Thank you for saving me.nnThere has been so much death, so much destruction. I don't know if I can stay in Murkwater any longer.
<This hunter hasn't been dead for very long. A notice of some kind lies on the ground nearby.>
Let the alliances fight over the castles. As long as they leave Cropsford alone, I don't care what they do to each other.
Hey there. Want to know how to think like a Bramblebreach Bosmer?
Don't think I've seen you in the Rosy Lion before.
These old cliffs and valleys  there are too many places to hide.
Azartah exists to serve. How may I help?
Do you think the town walls are strong and solid? I think so. I think we're well and truly safe here.

How do I look? Had to stretch the leather straps a little to make the armor fit, but I think I still make quite the impression. nnI'm ready for adventure again. Perhaps we'll cross paths in the bottom of some dungeon, eh?
Wind, water, and sunshine. Everything that adds spice to life is also needed to clean clothes.nnIt is good that I enjoy my work, as there is always so much of it.
This is not good. This is not good at all. These trees are unfamiliar. And there are spriggans and lurchers everywhere.
A fine day here in Daggerfall.
Don't look so shocked. I'm a member of the Mages Guild, not an Ebonheart spy.
This one welcomes you to this humble Fighters Guild hall.
Just between you and me, my husband Beaubel and I are making a killing off these grunts.
You look like someone who can appreciate the finer wares I have to offer.
I was sent here to find <<1>>. Have you seen him or perhaps his son, <<2>>?
What? Not all of Clan Murtag are warriors. Who do you think they get their armor from?
TEST Text for bug reproduction purposes.

You want to sign up? You ready to fight for your king?nnThe Covenant needs strong arms fighting for Cyrodiil. You sign up now and I'll make sure you get out there to fight those poxy Ebonheart and Aldmeri bastards right away. So, what say you?
And so your journey brings us together again. I was wondering if I might encounter you during my trip back to Wayrest.
My Savior! My greetings and blessings upon you.
Stay low! The Stormfists don't know we're here yet and I want to keep it that way.
What can I fill you with today?
If I don't have it, you don't need it.
Poor Mingor. He's not very bright. He'll never catch a fish that way.
I know I could shoot these fish, if only they'd stop moving!
Trouble in the woods? Send the Wood Elf. He can deal with it. Bah!nnWhy do people think all Bosmer have an affinity for nature? That's like saying all Nords love mead. Oh. Wait a moment .
Something is wrong here, very wrong.
I can't believe a spriggan got the drop on me. I'm going to turn that thing into kindling!
Hail, friend. We do meet each other in the most interesting places, don't we?
Well if it isn't the hero of Camlorn.
Well I'll be. What are you doing here?
You think you can handle Orcish brew?
The river of plenty flows through my stall, adventurer.
I cannot wait until my next assignment. Orcs abhor "outsider magic."
The dreugh have become unsettled since the Dominion arrived.
<The corpse of <<1>> looks different than the others you've seen at <<2>>.>
I agreed to guard this fool of a forester, but I never signed on to fight an army of trolls.nnI think we should head back to Windhelm and consider this camp to be a lost cause.

Thulvald was right to bring me along. He never would have survived that troll attack without me.nnBut I've never heard of trolls roaming around in such large numbers. This is all very strange, if you ask me.
Hmm? Can I help you with something? nnThe Fort Amol Guard barracks are off limits, so I hope you don't plan on trying to get inside.
I really needed this drink. These Dark Elves have the right swill for when you're trying your best to forget.
The others can hide in the manor and church. I'm staying here. This is the most fun I've had in a long time.
There's no end to these creatures!
Don't stop, now. Keep moving! More guards are on the way!
We are ready to attack. We await only your success with the door.
Get this door open, and we'll fight our way to the relic!
We're with you. Captain Kaleen's going to lead us in as soon as you open the door.
Orcs are dying, worse than dying. Get us in there!
<<1>> lives to drink and sell another day!
I have never seen anyone activate the welkynd stones before!
Same old crap, every day. If Tazgol would let us join the Covenant, we'd have stuff worth buying.
The others have gone on ahead. I delayed here to discourage pursuit.
Worry not, life still flows strongly through me. The others are waiting for you. I will be safe here.
Stubborn Orcs. I told Master Peverel this was a mistake. They're not even part of the Covenant!
She was the beauty of the sea, the Silverfish. But her captain drank and she fetched aground. Such was the will of the Divines.
This island's too small for a man of my ambition.
Hard to make a living hunting around here. Between the Orcs, the Ayleid ghosts, and the cultists, game's scarce.
Beds? Ha! There's some mulch piles if you're not tough enough to sleep on the ground.
Lesser being  there is a void within you. I find it intriguing.
Do not cross the Shadowscales. We have a long reach and even longer memories.
Can you believe this? I thought I'd be in the tavern, three sheets to the wind by now.
You want a drink? Go see the other girl. I'm all out.
This place isn't safe for strangers. What are you doing here?
<This gentleman is quite dead OR IS HE?>
Be gone from this temple, there is nothing for you here.
This is an interesting visage you've made for us.
I shall remain aboard until we reach Daggerfall, my friend.nnAn island full of Orcs would try my patience.

I see now. You were only thinking of the clan when you fled with my horn. You knew how great a threat my descendents faced, and that we would be needed to defend our land one final time.nnLet them come, then! None will break our line!
First time visitor to the Harvest Festival? Enjoy yourself. We love visitors!
This whole festival seems like a lot of nonsense, but it's all in good fun. What's the harm?
An outsider, are you? You're in for a few surprises before the day is out, I'll wager.
It's a lovely day for a festival, isn't it? It's all so exciting!
Wayfarer, what interest have you in a goat herder with no goats?
I don't think I can eat another bite.
Enter and be welcome, friend! Make yourself at home!
More food! Keep it coming! I'm starving over here!
Where does Airia put it? She eats like twelve Orcs, that's for sure. She must have a hollow leg or something.
After my thirteenth victory, they made me the judge. But I really want to get back in there are show them how to eat!
We're so busy because of the King's festival! It's almost enough to make me forget how terribly I miss Betra. Almost!
One cask of mead? Is that all they expect us to get through? What kind of contest is this?nnI'm sure I'll need another dozen.
Tell Old Man Jeggi that he's going down! This year the trophy belongs to me!
Sorry, boys! If anyone's winning this contest, it's going to be me. Let's have another round!
They asked me to judge this contest, but I honestly have no idea what I'm doing. I've never had a drop of mead in my life.
You're standing too close. I'm trying to watch the bard perform. She's very easy on the eyes, if you know what I mean.
Please, friend, I need to concentrate. I am the judge of this competition, after all.
Her voice is as soothing as the healing mud of Black Marsh.
Since Arani started performing here, the number of male customers has increased dramatically.
I just joined the Royal Work Crew! I'll be repairing the roads of Eastmarch in no time.
The Cold-Moon Stables might be larger, but we provide a much better level of service.
Another busy day at Windhelm Bank. It's the safest spot in town.
As soon as I finish my chores, Papa says I can go watch the eating contest!
I can't believe my partner and I have to travel all the way out here from Wayrest. What do you want?
Watch yourself. This is a frisky one.

You really know how to make an entrance! But forcing your way into the Prince of Murder's realm  that takes exceptional bravery. Or is it unprecedented stupidity? No matter.nnClearly, you came here for a purpose.
You've come to put hammer to anvil, yes? I have some goods you might be interested in. nnRemember that Onsi's eyes are upon you. Mind the angle and strike true.
Welcome, friend! Has the sun gone to rest yet? My scales dry and crack in this heat. Fortunately I have potions and ointments of all kindsfar better than those found in the marketplace.
So you're an enchanter? Or just getting out of the heat? nnI sell enchantmentstop quality only. Poor enchantments can cause  complications.

I am Oromin, head of Thalmor affairs here in the fair city of Woodhearth.nnYou may speak if you have business with me, otherwise I would ask that you leave me to my work. Fariel may be more suited to help you.
Wayfarer! Would you be wise in the ways of the desert? Hearken to what I have to tell you.
<The corpse of an Altmer female lies cold upon the stone floor. She has clearly been dead for a considerable length of time.>
Didakah is a wise man. Didakah purchases very shiny object for what he told is a great price. This one is wise indeed, and now owner of a new shiny.
Who  who wants a drink? Oh, that's right. I did! Now  make your  make your own, with my high quality merchandise.
Eyes open, my friend. We are not out of this yet.
To learn is to live! To live is to eat! To eat, you must cook! To cook  you must have the right supplies.
Hmm hmm hmm  by Stars, Moons, and Green! Sorry, sorry. The whole pub broke into song last night in Skywatch. What can I get you?
And what, my good adept, can I do for you today?
Do you smell that? The magicka on the air, fragrant as the wind off of a sand dune. Ahh.nnWhat can this one help you with?
You the one with the delivery for Dariah?nnShe's right back there. Tell her no more excuses. I'm ready to eat my biscuits!
I see you have a Lycanthropy infection. I know that feel bro.
Why does the Dominion send Hazazi to places like this?
My eggsister's mind is dry with madness. Do not buy from her. Purchase what you need from me.
Scales can only protect you so much, adept. I recommend heavier plates to keep you safe.
You have to believe me when I tell you this. The Lord, the Mother, and the Wizard all three want you to buy from me.
Spices, sauces, sausages, more! You name it, I've got it galore!
The Mages Guild is fortunate indeed! This Eyevea  the perfect place to practice spellwork and sell my leatherwork!
Welcome, welcome, welcome! To the best selection of heavy plate armor on this island full of wizards! I don't regret coming here at all!
Rigurt is glorious master of ceremonies of glorious Corn-loon-licker! I am so proud!nnBut don't tell him where I am. I want to enjoy the party, not work it.
Tell me honestly  how do my eyebrows look? No, never mind. What can I get you?
Strong wood and taught bow strings, newly made by the finest crafters in Daggerfall. And now, awaiting your light touch.
Joyful day! Know, wayfarer, that the waters of magicka flow freely from these robes.
Peace be upon you, wayfarer. If I can give you some friendly advice? Don't bother with robes. They are for scholars and old women.
I know you're looking for me. I'm showing myself to tell you to leave. Tell Thorinor you found me dead. It'll be true enough soon.nnI'm going to end my life before I turn.
A blade in the hand is worth two in the back, if you catch my meaning. What can I get you?
Bright steel and hot coals! What can I get you?
Heavy bags weigh down even the greatest Arch-Mage. Allow me to lighten your load?
Welcome to my beautiful patch of Eyevea. What do you want?
Sorry, sorry. Much to catalog, less time to talk. What do you need?
I'll have to make another trip to Woodhearth soon to replenish my ingredients. If you have your own, you're welcome to use my tools.
Fine woodwork from Cyrodiil and beyond!
A sharp blade is a Mage's best friend. And you look lonely.
There's so much to learn on Eyevea! Like, who knew there were this many kinds of brew in the world?
Hey there adept! Be one of the first to get new goods just off the boat from Auridon!
Welcome to Longhaven! Used to be a busier place, before the trouble with the mist started. But we won't let that be an excuse for poor hospitality.
Turn back. That way's bad omens. Even the air's turned against them in Longhaven.
Begone. I must finish my prayers and purify my spirit before I meet my foes in battle.

You kept your head and did very well, my friend. The Fighters Guild owes you a debt.  nnBefore you go, you should take the crystal over there. I'm no scholar, but I bet it's a Light of Meridia. That's probably why Ifriz kept it behind the barrier.
Enough idle talk. Let us hunt.
The slaves are armed and the uprising has begun. We may yet escape this place!
Interact with me to make me say an SAT.
The kagouti walk amongst the guar, but do not hunt unless the guar strays from her herd. Then wooden wasps would fly, bringing the guar down to the mud.
Brothers, do not despair! The fleshed ones do not know their wrongs. The unborn do not deserve to carry this burden,nnWe must not be rash. Patience!

Brothers, did you not feel our life leaving this husk? They took our lifeblood, set it ablaze! Our roots shriveled, and the earth held no solace.nnWe are too weak. They will overcome us as summer brings drought. We shall wither away!
These thoughts are not ours. Who has planted these seeds here? Brothers, I hear you, but I do not understand.nnWe are one, but fractured! Do we not all share the same taproot? Speak!
Enak is a valued assistant. I am disappointed at his failure to outwit this door, however.
Brelynd pays well. Good thing for her or I'd be using her head for a battering ram.
You there! Have you seen my squad?
Who are you? Were you part of the fleet?
Bless Y'ffre, I'm glad you came by! Have you seen any other marines along the beach?
I lost a lot of friends in that storm. Give me some good news.
I have an important matter which must be addressed quickly, before things escalate.
These sea rats came without warning!
<You can reach your hand through the opening in the head to deposit your choice of reagents.>
<Tied to a blood-stained post is the body of a Wood Elf marine. He appears to have died recently.>
Rum. Nothing but rum.nnWho do I have to gut for a flagon of wine around here?
"Let's open an inn!" he says. "We'll be rich and have the time of our lives!" he says. We're in the middle of nowhere and get hardly any customers!nnWe'd have been happier farming.
Cabbage, salted pork, rum  dear gods, the Prowler will smell like a flux-riddled mammoth if we can't improve her stores.

Rasala thinks we made a mistake opening an inn here. Sure, we're off the beaten track, have trouble getting supplies, and our only customers are bandits who never pay. nnWe just need more time to work things out!
In Alik'r I played for royalty. Here  nobody.nnI agreed to play for a portion of the inn's profits. That Leono, he really pulled one over on me.
I'll handle this, Zur. You can come out and see in a moment.nnSo, someone has come to help us at last!
<A strange aura surrounds <<c:1>>'s corpse. His body is warm to the touch. A faint smell of sulfur permeates the room.>
The Horns of the Deep! They must be destroyed!
I suppose I'm getting used to the taste of mead. Still, I'd pay good gold for a jug of flin.
Are you lost? Ambassador <<1>>'s quarters aren't open for visitors.
Floors that don't sway. Sand that creeps into boots. Bugs the size of anchors!nnMay the gods see me posted to a proper ship.
I make the finest ales throughout the Frostwater Tundra.
If you're not here to help, get off my ship.
One soup. As long as it's delicious, that's all anyone ever needs!
This Elf is mad! I deal in reagents, not instruments of death!
I am honored to represent the Fighter's Guild in General Godrun's presence.
There's no situation so bad that a dead horse can't make it worse.
This company needs a good minstrel, then perhaps there would be someone worth conversing with.
Bonjour, je m'appelle Eric.nRavi de vous rencontrer!
Aidez moi, je vous en supplie !nMa femme et mon fils sont partis il y a deux heures, et ils ne sont toujours pas revenus.nJe commence a etre vraiment inquiet.
Can you fight? We have a serious situation here and we need all the sword and spell-arms we can get.
Maormer, eh? This could be fun.
Repairs go faster with a drink in hand!
Have the sigil-trees been reactivated yet?
Well, there. You look like someone who could use some coin. How about running a simple errand for me? It'll pay well.
The situation developing across Eastmarch has the Mages Guild quite concerned.
The Fighters Guild is watching the situation here in Skyrim very closely.
My oh my, these soldiers sure are a thirsty lot! I can hardly keep up with the demand!
I've got this! You keep moving.
You look like a person of great intelligence. Allow me, wayfarer, to let you in on a secret.
All of these wars and rumors of war make it very difficult for scholars to advance their studies.
Fortune favors you! Keep it up. I'll take over here.
If you wish to raid Sercen, wait your turn. Our claim takes precedence.nnIf you wish some coin, I offer a task.
You don't look like much. This one hopes <<1>> knows of what he speaks.
A good drink cures whatever ails you. And I know how to make very good drinks.
Soup is for dryskins! Now a stew. A stew is a meal!

I have to commend the Nords. They certainly know how to throw a grand party. Almost makes me sorry that I'm stuck inside catching up on Mages Guild paperwork. There's always paperwork. It never seems to end.
A strong plan wins a battle, and a perfect plan wins the war.
Oh, perfect. My favorite people. The very faces of my failure  and now you've tracked me down just to watch me die?nnYou're just like my sister and the rest of the Thalmor. No sympathy whatsoever.
The time has come to destroy the Mortuum Vivicus.
I'm a distant cousin, but brewing is in my blood!
Sauce. That's the secret to great cooking. A good sauce. And spice.nnA good sauce and a little heat can hide any other imperfections in your cooking techniques.
The best armor in all of Skyrim! Get it here and get it now! No waiting!
Ugh. My stock is probably ruined.
Oh! Hey there! Welcome to my eatery! Are you feeling hungry? Me, I'm always hungry.
Greetings, wayfarer. I'm sorry, but I have nothing to sell. I'm just packing up my sister's things.
These Redguards are slow to reopen their shops. Halinad is not slow, and has much to sell. Please look.
I'm leaving. I can never fish here again. This has ruined it.
Fish aren't biting. I'm afraid they might never bite again.
