I always hated this boat. Now I'm going to have to pay some Argonians to yank the damn thing out. To Sovngarde with the Alik'r!
Fair winds and blessings, my friend!
This one promises to bring money next month! No, next week!
I wasn't stealing, I just slipped and put my hand in his coin pouch!
Shor's bones! Look what the jackals dragged in! Ha! I'm just yanking your helmet-horns. What'll you have?
I'm trying to write a ballad about the Harvest Festival. You'd be amazed how hard it is to find words that rhyme with "festival."
This is my first Harvest Festival, but I'm having a wonderful time!
They can sacrifice all the apples and grain they want, just tell them to keep their hands off the wine!
If you're not careful, this desert air will turn your tongue to jerky. How about a drink?
I foresaw your coming, strange one. In my vision, you bought many of my finest items.  nnYou don't want to buck the forces of prophesy do you?
You'll need to bear more than water across the dunes. Why not make sure you have room for all that is needful?
Your belly growls like a duneripper! You should sit and abide for a while. Even the mightiest heroes have to eat.
Cast your eyes over my wares. I swear by Tava's bright feathers, we've got anything you might need.
You  did I overhear you correctly? Vampires were the source of the creatures and the corrupted mist? Tell me it isn't so.
You look light on your feet. Have a look at my stock of armor. You might find something you fancy.
Greetings! I sell the finest garments from Alik'r and beyond. You'll need a fresh tunic if you're heading off into the dunes.
You address the seneschal of King Fahara'jad's court. Spare me your foreign preambles and tell me your business here.
Swords aloft, warriors! With the blessings of Onsi's bright blade, the Covenant banner marches forward. Are you ready to make war upon the enemies of the Alik'r?
By Onsi's bright blade, I welcome you, wayfarer. You are in the Sentinel branch of the House of Leki, patron of swordswomen and swordsmen. In this place, we honor her through meditation and combat.
I'm afraid I can't tarry. I'm on an errand for the Mages Guild. They don't like to be kept waitingespecially Master Eteldil.
Cordial greetings, and welcome to the tower: an isle of knowledge amidst a vast sea of ignorance.  nnHave you come for training?
Well met! I'm the resident librarian. We don't have much, but what we have I care for. Have you found anything to add to our collection?
Here at the priory, I have found the peace I never knew as an adventurer. Perhaps someday you will find this as well.nnIf you're looking for work, Mael is in need of assistance.
Akatosh's blessings upon you. All are welcome to worship at the eternal flame of Akatosh.

<<1>> asks how I find you so swiftly. I tell him I look for the one trudging as if their feet were stuck in the soft mud-sucks of Black Marsh.nnUp, up. Lift your feet up. Surely you've seen Zaeri run enough by now that you recognize good form, yes?
Ah, a visitor! Do you have a moment to talk about Akatosh, the Dragon God of Time?
The horses are restless. I think they sense the taint of necromancy better than we do.
Y'ffre knows what would have happened to me if you hadn't come along.
This one owes you her life.
Did you kill it? Is the Hollow Lord dead?
Welcome to <<1:)>>! Though  normally, everyone isn't stranded by a storm this way.
My friends are going to murder you for this, just you wait!
You are the outsider who has done so much for my people. I am grateful.nnPerhaps when this is over, my people can live without fear or worry.
Who knew that being a stablehand was such hard work? If I had some money, I'd leave this place and never look back.
Curse those Arbordawn idiots! I'll be bald for life!
Why am I stuck in this forsaken mud pit near all these tree lovers?
Please excuse me, but I need to finish packing the Great Mage's tent. I want to be done when <<1>> returns!
Can you believe where we are? A Falinesti site! I've dreamed of visiting a site like this since I was a little boy in Aldcroft. I can't believe I'm actually here!
It's peaceful here, isn't it? As long as the cold doesn't bother you. The fish here taste much better than those caught in warmer lakes.

Now what were we talking about? Oh, I remember!nnBefore my people will even listen to you, you need to perform an honor deed. It has to be an act that benefits my clan. Something they would expect one of us to be able to accomplish.
The sun and salt are bad for injuries. If you are wounded, get to the encampment in the shadow of those towers. <<1>> will have you up in no time.
Unless you're in serious pain, I can't help you right now. I have too many patients to attend.
This one can't believe you crossed this chamber without so much as an illusion to mask your presence. You are so brave! This one? Zur's whiskers were twitching inside the Dark Elf's head!
Trying to do everything myself is killing me.
The ship was too close to shore, even before the storm hit. I said as much before she sank.
Can you heal my wounds? Better yet, heal the others. If they stop moaning and groaning, I can finally get some rest.
An Altmer ship would have survived the tempest intact.
I'll wait until there's more room amongst the injured. My wound isn't as bad as some of the others I've seen.
I'm not used to seeing so much open space. This is my first sea voyage.
It's a wonder anyone survived! Did you see the wreck?
A lot of folks were injured in the storm. Good thing there's a town nearby, even if it is full of Khajiit.
Everyone's ready to pass the blame, even folks who know nothing about ships and sailing.
Strange winds blow lately. The air's full of salt and sorrow!
Nasimar prepared for such an event, but there are more injuries than expected. Sleep is best for them now.
Many new faces, many new clients, yes? Business will be good for Duharr soon!

You don't look tough enough to have beaten the lamia champion, but even a mighty storm starts with a light breeze.nnStill, an honor deed is an honor deed. Maybe the council of elders will actually agree to meet with you.
You're lucky, outsider. The only thing keeping me from sticking my knife in you right now is our code.nnBut if you think I'm going to help you, think again.

I don't remember the last time I talked to an outsider. Killed one? Sure, I do that all the time. But talk? That's a new one for me.nnI was born and bred in these woods. Never ventured outside its borders. Always wondered what was out there.

Faraniel is like a sister to me. I almost convinced her to give up her foolish plan, and then you showed up!nnWell, since you made it this far, we might as well try it her way. I guess any chanceno matter how remoteis worth the trouble.

Use the portal behind me to reach the council.nnThey didn't want to meet with you at first. They can be extremely stubborn when they want to be. But when I dropped the lamia champion's head at their feet, they quickly changed their minds.
I see the delight in your eyes. You want something special, yes?
Did you come in with the storm? I'm sure you've worked up a thirst out there.
He may be a drunk, but <<1>> is one sleek walker. Wait and see.

This is a great privilege, allowing you to stand here. Never before has an outsider been permitted to set foot on this platform. My daughter, however, was insistent that we speak with you.nnWe shall hear what you have to say.
Spew forth your lies and be quick about it. I have a great many things to contemplate today.

You poor child! Dealing with those disgusting lamias as you navigated the Moonless Walk must have been so unnerving. Such horrible creatures!nnNow, sad little Faraniel mentioned that you bring us news from Nirn. What is it?

You've accomplished much, outsider. Survived the Moonless Walk, performed an honor deed. Well done!nnI shall listen to your words and consider them with great respect. I promise you this much, at least. Now tell me. Why are you here?
Everything this one sells is fresh. Except for what's clearly marked old.
There's nothing like a good fire to warm one's weaponry, my friend.
Hey, look. A hero came to save the day.
You don't look like you belong in this awful place.
I have work to complete before the Taskmaster returns.
This one has an escape plan. So simple. So elegant. This one just needs the machines to stop working and away we go.
Alexis? Is that you Alexis? I've missed you so!
Don't know why I bother. I no sooner patch one hole then another quake hits and more of the walls fall apart.
Welcome to the Oak and Crosier. Don't worry about that fissure. It's been rumbling and shaking for years, and we're still here.nnHow can I help you?
What is it? I need to record my latest observation of the fissure's activity before foolish chatter wipes it from my mind.nnPlease go away.

I'm sitting on a pier, ready to end it all, and <<Ac:1>> appears. "Don't give up," he says. "The Green provides for all its saplings, you just need a patch of sun."nn<<2>> comes to me the next day, looking for sailors! To think I nearly gave up.
And the Mane spoke, "Look to Riddle'Thar! Did he surrender ja-Kha'jay to Skooma Cat and the others? No! He kept it close for all of us, under his belly for all to follow!"nnIt is true, you know?
When I don't catch enough to feed my family, I sleep beneath the docks. It's safer that way.
Welcome to my humble abode! A place with a roof costs much more than an open area like this.
What do you think goes on inside these buildings? Why live inside at all, when Mistral is so beautiful?
What are you looking at? Haven't you ever seen a Nord wait for a magic tree to return from  wherever?
I don't care what Mother says. I'm not going home until I see Falinesti with my own eyes! In the meantime, can I get you something?
I hope those fool Arbordawn cultists don't come back here. They have this look in their eyes that chills my bones. Crazy fools!
The ale's weak, the bread's stale, and the weather's too warm. I hope this whole village slides into the fissure soon.
Farisel's going to crack one joke too many and end up eating Blodrat's sword. I'd pay to see that!
Don't know why I come in here. Can't be the ale or the company.

Another traveler, by the looks of you. If you're heading north, you may want to explore the Sancre Tor ruins. It's a major historical site; many former emperors are buried there.nnI couldn't get closetoo many undead. But you might.
Too many foreigners in Chorrol nowadays. I hope that fissure swallows every non-Imperial here!
Sit down and rest a while, friend. Don't try to move any of the furniture though. We had to nail it to the floor because of all the quakes.
Between the vapors from the fissure and the dust from the earthquakes, cleaning this place is a never-ending task.nnExcuse me, please.
I have the finest in armor available. Well, some of it's not all that fine, but it's still decent quality.
The view is quite entrancing. If only smells didn't waft upward.
I've never had such a difficult time deciding. Especially in a shop with such few goods.
I love <<1>>, but it is good to see Altmeri faces again.
I do hope <<1>> comes to his senses. Since grandmother died, he isn't himself.nnHe's never been a heavy sleeper. Lately he's taken to wandering <<2>> at night! He's even changed the way he dresses!
<<1>> was built on an ancient Khajiiti temple. Without proper maintenance the ruins could collapse, taking the city with them!
I don't have anything to steal, or sell. No sugar, nothing.
I am unused to begging, but with so many mouths to feed, what choice do I have?
We'll be cleaning up after that storm for some time to come. And I don't just mean the docks.

Some dislike the way <<1>> runs <<2>>, but this is such a tiny island. Storms, pirates, even the Maormer threaten us, yet we are still here!nnOur leader, she is clever, yes? She sees what must be done and does it! How many others can say the same?
I'll not leave my cousin behind. You're on your own from here.
Maormer just walking around like they own the place. Mark my words, this entire island will regret dealing with those sea rats.
What good is a wall if the sand blows over it? I'll have words with the Magistrate about this.
We simply let their ship dock right here in town? <<1>> has lost her mind.
So. I bet, then I roll the dice? Or is it the other way round? nnTall Papa help me.
Oh, hello. You caught me off guard. My pretense is that I am doing research, but I really come to watch Bailiff Trayard. nnBy Tall Papa's starry breeches, he is handsome beyond measure.
Before you ask, no, you can't have my bed. Now go find some other place to stay.
Unless you're offering to pay my debts to Uncle Thakh, I'd appreciate it if you let me be.
A thousand pardons, wayfarer, but I am still taking inventory. nnI believe Nabeenim across the street is offering general goods. Visit her and convey my regards.

In her tale, Aranias was volatile and she swung between anger, shame, and hope. Feared by her own parents because of her abilities, she faced the bandits alone.nnThis made her bitter and hardened against others. Vulnerable to outside influences.
I don't actually need new armor or anything. I just like coming here to get warm.
I hate to admit it, but there is a certain charm to this place. If only it were cleaner.
Heaven's sun shines brightest on Redguard steel. Gaze upon my wares. You'll not find better blades in all Tamriel.
If you cleave to Fahara'jad and the Covenant, do not expect a warm welcome here in Bergama. There are many Crowns here, and they disapprove of such new-fangled ideas.
Only in Bergama would the honored warriors of the Covenant be forced to train in a goat sty such as this. Accursed Crowns. I hope my writ of transfer comes soon.
The wine selection here isn't all that impressive. But at least they have some bottles from the Hegathe vineyards. All you get in the inn is cactus pear cordialsat twice the price, to boot.
This music is fine if you've an ear for the traditional. The performance is predictable, thoughjust like everything else Crowns produce.
I must ask you to find another table, wayfarer. I have this man drunk enough to bet, but not so drunk that he falls asleep. It is a delicate dance that requires my careful attention.
Someone tell this doddering old coot to place his bet.
Our honored dead may be rising to plague us, but someone has to keep the spirits flowing. I don't know about you, but dread makes me thirsty.
I am certain I can win my money back. Certain as sunrise. Just a few more games, then I walk away for good.
Malooc take all this disappearance nonsenseI just want my writ of ownership! Those goats will starve before I get them back to Kozanset.
Greetings, my friend! You have a fair amount of equipment there. I'd wager you need something to hold it all.
I've watched this Forebear and Crown staring each other down for hours. Even a stump-brained Orc like me knows to stay out of that mess.
Magicked goods are hard to come by in Redguard country, but I think you'll find this assortment of soul gems impressive nonetheless.
Being an Orc in Bergama is miserable. Getting charity out of a Crown is like squeezing ale out of a skeever's arse.
Hrm. Quiet today. I don't like it.
These Crowns don't pay us Orcs much, but it's better than living on the street. nnI guess.
Do you mind? I get so little time to write in this cursed place.
Many tasty bugs hide in the crevices of old stone like this. And I am hungry.
My father catches fish with his bare hands. Soon as I find one, I'm gonna do the same.
Desolation overwhelms this one. The horse is missing, gone in the night. Without a horse, the wagon does not move. Where the wagon stays, this one stays. Purchase some goods?
How can this humble servant aid you?
What are you doing? Don't stop now! You're almost there!
You haven't seen my sister Thiirril, have you?
Curse those decadent Nibenese, trying to spread their foul Daedra worship across Cyrodiil. A few came to Chorrol, but we chased them out. I hope wild animals tear them to pieces on the road!
I haven't the heart to tell him there aren't any fish in there.
Tava's blessings to you. You are new to Sentinel, I think. You wonder how I know? The sun has barely kissed your cheeks yet.
Keep some distance from the beast. It is only my long exposure to it that allows me to tolerate the smell.
Ah, I think it's working. I can feel the soul-meld unraveling.
It feels like my very essence is being shredded.

The city returns to life, thanks to you. The Mages Guild and the Fighters Guild have joined forces and believe the time to strike is fast approaching.nnWar is coming, champion. May the light guide us.
<<1>> asks for patience. Easy for her to say when my men are still out there! The longer we wait, the fewer will come back.
This is my favorite spot in the priory. Nature's beauty is spread before me, yet I can feel the warmth of Akatosh's presence at my back.
I've been told this staff casts an opacity spell over the windows, and it needs to be renewed constantly.nnI suspect the older acolytes are playing a trick on me.
Please speak to an acolyte. I am preparing for our next service to Akatosh.
Urp, land  have we reached land?
Tu'whacca's breath, how could we have left so many bodies beneath the waves for this long? Had we cared for our honored dead properly and buried them, none of this would have happened.
I heard a stranger helped save the Great Tree. Thank you!
Just got to clear away this brush before auntie gets mad. Thank Y'ffre that foul green stuff is gone!
I'm sorry, but I can't talk long. I'm preparing for the trip back to the shipyards at Tava's Blessing. Some of our finest warships are berthed there, and they always need fresh provisions.
I thought the most dangerous things in the shallows were mudcrabs. May Mauloch yank out my tusks if I ever swim again.
As soon as I finish taking inventory, I'm off to Wayrest. If you see a weasel-faced diplomat, tell him he'll have to book passage with a different captain.
The dryskins' boats sink and suddenly I am everyone's friend.
Hello. I think you must have the wrong person.nnI only speak to two kinds of people, and you seem to be neither of them.
Ya? Need something to wash that salt out of your throat, am I right?
How did someone like you get an invite to the party?
You are the one who struck the Ra-Netu? You will forgive me for not taking your hand in friendship.
Oh! Hello, wayfarer. I am sorry, my mind wanders.
I am ashamed to be working with what's going on downstairs. This old warehouse may well become sacred ground.
Welcome to Cyrodiil, soldier. Here to help out in the war?
War is certainly good for business. We're having trouble keeping up with demand. What do you need?
Very flammable materials here. Watch your tail.
Kill any ogrim lately? Wouldn't mind bashing a few of their thick skulls myself.
Please stand away. This area is for the royal family and their consorts alone.
My brother was suppposed to meet me here well over an hour ago. I don't doubt he's still squandering his money in that damned gambling hall.
We've got a good view of the island here, but our situation's less than ideal.
Brilliant works from Breton masters left to crack and peel here in the desert sun. It's a travesty! I should have known these Crowns would fail to recognize their value.
I'm drinking mead! Well, I'm pretending to drink mead. But it tastes pretty good.nnNow I'm eating fried guar. Yum!
I like having firm ground under my feet, but treebranches over my head would make things even better.
The temple of the Crescent Moons has such a beautiful view of the island. If only this one came here under better circumstances.
You're in a sorry state, friend. Head up the beach and rest.
I never want to see another ship. I'll stay on this island for the rest of my life, if I have to! They can't force me to go back, can they?
What is it? Rasha finally figured out a way in? If not, let me rest.
I hope you're here to help us get into that ruin. Rasha sure doesn't know the way in. I've sharpened my sword into a toothpick waiting.
That Crown priest over there has been muttering to himself for hours. The only thing worse than a muttering Crown is a loud Crown.
You want to talk to someone, talk to my sister, Rasha. She likes to talk.
Crown priests are intolerable. Couldn't we have a moment's peace to bury our sacred dead before the hectoring begins?
The sword is the soul  without the sword I am lost.
Fair winds, O wayfarer. You stand at the foot of Leki's Blade: swordsmen's most holy site. All who place their trust in the blade are welcome here.
It's a relief to be here in the Hollow City, but I wonder if I'll ever see my home again.
I went days without a sip of mead when we were in the Tower of Lies.
I wouldn't go up there. The dead roam freely in Juras Fall.
Weapons! Freshly imported from the mainland!
Exotic foods from the mainland! So fresh it's still damp!
I've entirely too many manifests to go over. I almost wish more boats had sunk. It would save me the paperwork.
I've been here for hours. If I'd known that alit were on the contraband goods list, I'd never have brought them here.
Getting out of the heat? You won't find a better place to duck work.
These dune-dwellers are suspicious in the extreme. In the Alik'r sharp ears and noble bearings stand out, so we are watched constantly. That's just the price of doing business here.
I hope you've got this zombie nonsense well in hand. Some of this inventory is perishable!
I can't wait to get back to Woodhearth. I've had enough goat meat, thank you very much.
This lot stinks of Aldmeri treachery. When they make their move, I'll be ready.
My wife  she didn't even like fishing, but I bullied her into it. I thought it would make for a fine afternoon. I'll never forgive myself.
I was guarding this tree when the others were seeds in the wind.
Hello again. I guess by now you've figured out that I'm not just a researcher.
We've come upon a great deal of fresh meat and have decided to have a feast. You are welcome to stay.
What do you want? Good way to die, bothering me now.
Do you come to worship? The temple is open to all who revere the moons, whether they be khajiit or not.
Please, leave us to our training.
Do not disturb the ritual, cub. Our harvest depends upon it.
There's something strange going on here!
Let me guessanother new recruit. And you're here to fight for the Pact?
I long for quieter times, but I fear they will never come to Cyrodiil.
Carefulthis is a live firing range. Are you supposed to be here?
Another soldier to join the fight?
Repairs will take a while, but the Quay will recover in time.
Pardon, wayfarer, but there is much work to be done and few hands to do it. Speak with Roshan, please.
Nothing like the smell of a freshly oiled trebuchet, is there? Well, how can I help you?
This one is glad the Dominion was here. <<1>> could have died without your help.
Escaping death at the hands of those savages gives me a thirst. Fortune favor you!
Y'ffre bless you, my friend! We're lucky you came along when you did.nnI broke open my personal reserve for this occasion. Nothing settles the nerves like a tankard from back home.
Something strike your fancy? The sea bears strange fruit of late.
Please, join the festivities! My sister, she dances! <<1>> plays music from distant lands! Even <<2>> plays a wonderful fool!nnWhen he stops drinking, anyway. Which is never.
Bold bandits are not long for this world. Mark my wordsthey'll think twice before reaving along these shores again.
Alik'ri forges are hotter than any in Tamriel - and the hottest steel births the keenest blades.
Magics are not welcome here, wayfarer. The forge must be kept pure. If you practice the dark arts, have a care and do it outside.
Tell no one, wayfarer, but I have always favored the bow. I only train here to please my father. Hopefully the Disciples will take note of my weakness and send me home.
Maybe <<1>> is right, we have been lucky. Still, this one will rest more easily when word arrives from <<2>>.
We were very lucky to survive this storm. Khenarthi smiles upon us, or perhaps we are just lucky. Either way, <<1>> is grateful.
<The wooden ring Darius mentioned is not on this body.>
The storm, it brings strange fish, yes?

<<1>> fishes up an Elf! "Throw it back!" this one says, "You cannot eat it. You cannot use it as bait. What good is an Elf?"nnWhat does he do? He keeps it! If it dies, <<2>> will never hear the end of it!
You are here to trade? Not to cause trouble? This one is sorry he must ask, but it pays to be careful, no?
Thank you, my friend. You let me see that preserving life is not worth abandoning it.
<The wooden ring Darius mentioned is not on this body.>
<The wooden ring Darius mentioned is not on this body.>
Today you saved <<1>> from destruction. Khenarthi herself must watch over you.
These totems seem to harness a combination of wind and spirit! I wonder if I can nnExcuse me. Do you mind?
You're slow, but you turned the tide of battle. <<1>> admits that counts for something.
Think of the power the Maormer must command to control a creature like that. But the cost? It's simply too great.
What the Maormer planned with that storm atronach was madness. Did they realize their own lives would end if they succeeded? If so, did they care?
You saved many of our brothers and sisters. Thank you for so bravely charging into battle.
I ran out of Maormer to kill. If you find any more, let me know.
The Prowler is headed to Auridon, and we're happy to ferry you there. When you're ready, hop in the launch. We'll set you up with your own bunk.
<<1>> seems happy to join the Dominion now, but it won't last. I give it less than a year til they forget what happened here.
<<1>> is gone, and I wasn't there to stop it. We may have won today, but why does it feel like I lost?
Don't mourn for <<1>>. You made sure her sacrifice had meaning.nnGods favor you, friend.
We swept the shoreline. <<1>> captured some Maormer. <<A:2>> slaughtered the rest.nnYou fought well.

A few more serpents came rose from the sea before you silenced the horns. With the Green Lady leading our forces, we quickly slew the beasts and put down the remaining Maormers.nnIt was a true honor to serve alongside her. Rictus will be glorious.
The time has come. The Great Shackle must be destroyed.
Your pardon, please. This one is too worried to speak with you at this time.
No teeth marks on you, huh? Well, just wait!
I thought I would rot in that cage forever.
Someone needs to pay for locking me away in this dung heap!
How did someone like you get an invite to the party?
I'll have a glass of wine.
Do you know how many Breton, Redguard, and Orcs Ayrenn has taken to bed?
These days I have time to talk. What would you ask of this old warrior?
Come up for some fresh air? I've been sparring all day. The breeze up here is always so refreshing.
Your purse looks heavy, wayfarer. Can we help safeguard your valuables?
I was beginning to think you wouldn't make it. I've already begun Aranias' story.
You were a fine character. Most enjoyable. And it looks like you made quite an impression on Aranias.
Dogs and  sons of dogs! Jackals and fiends! Swords aloft ! Come, brothers! Come and .
I am all right  just tired. Go and tend to the others.
These green recruits need to be shown how a real soldier fights.
This one'll be doing repairs 'til the big cat catches the little one!
Hope for no more bad weather, but this one's shoulder is acting up. There's another storm on its way!
Have you seen my ribcage? That milk drinking wizard scattered me across three of these piles.
Do you hear the call of Sithis? It was drowned out by the wailing spirits, but now they're at rest.
Where's the lieutenant? She was supposed to rendezvous with the landing party hours ago.
Hey, you saved us from <<1>>! My brother and I didn't want to fight you earlier, but that wizard controlled our bodies. Or what's left of them! Ha!nnCome, dance with me in the fountain!
Pelidil. What a fascinating character.nnHe doesn't die here, you know.
How do you fight the weather? I'd like to kill more of these Maormer, but I'll follow the sergeant's lead.
The gods are certainly playing games with us today.
Luck's been bad ever since we hit this damned beach.
This appears to be the body of Zakavit. He appears to have been poisoned.
I was beginning to think you wouldn't make it. I've already begun Aranias' story.
Little Elf thought he could get away from Oblan. He was wrong.
I'm afraid this one is about to die. I didn't realize how frail Bosmer were.
Step away from me, filth! This changes nothing! It's too late for you!
You you cut my bindings?nnYou're not one of them, are you? I can tell. Please, get me out of here!
I told the last of your cretins that I was more than adequate for the time being, thank you. I would appreciate some privacy.
This residence is meant as a retreat for acolytes of Akatosh. Please don't disturb anything.
Everyone here, from the newest acolyte to the abbess, partakes of the chores necessary to run the priory. It keeps us humble in Akatosh's sight.
I'm looking for the rest of my squad. Have you seen them around the beaches?
We must be vigilant. Daedra can be as devious as dark clouds on a sunny day.
Would you do a mate a favor? I'd wager a meat-walker like you would like to put your hands on some treasure that ain't cursed. I could arrange that.
I hope Nelhilda and the others are safe in that Hollow City. nnA few people stayed here. If anyone finds there way here, at least they will find a friendly face.

If you have come to search my remains for the gems I was accused of stealing, then you are both a coward and a fool.nnYou will not find the gems here, only the corpse of a good woman who did not deserve this dishonor.
And thus, Longhaven is cleansed of the rank pollution of the undead.nnCherish victory, but do not let vigilance falter. We cannot fathom what evils lie undiscovered in this wild land.
The jaws of the Dominion close upon Pelidil now. He will not escape this time.
You are changing much in this story. Salalin and his wife are both supposed to die. Andur is not.
I don't believe we've met. I'd prefer to keep it that way.
I remember you. You helped free us from the Everfull Flagon. Thanks for that.
This place is great! They have the most delicious mead!
I still enjoy mead. Just not the enchanted kind. And not all the time.
All this traveling has really taken it out of me. I'm so tired!
I like to come out here and just look at the trees. nnIt doesn't look anything like my memories of our lost home, but it is rather beautiful here.
The hero of the Everfull Flagon! Nice to see you again, my friend.
Well met, my friend. nnWe have met, haven't we? I confess, my memory isn't what it used to be.
Should have listened to father. Should have gone to work for Hadran at the Caravan.
Don't eat me! This one will taste terrible! Wait. You're not a troll! Thank Jode!
Feels good to be somewhere safe again. I don't know how much longer we would have survived out there.nnI'm just going to enjoy this quiet time for as long as it lasts.
All this bickering becomes tiresome. While I agree we can't just leave our brothers and sisters out there, Darien's right. We need a plan.
Everything we saw out there  it was maddening.nnThere's no way we can win this. There's just no way.
I refuse to leave our guildmates to rot in the wilds of this wicked place! I don't care about the dangers.nnHow would you feel if it was you still out there? Wouldn't you want us to come find you?
My apologies for that display. The whole rash commentjust a figure of speech, of course.nnSo! I suppose you know more about this place than any of us? Like, where I can get a decent drink?
I do not expect this group to blindly trust me. That would be foolish.nnI plan to instill them with confidence so that when the others arrive they will follow me without question.
Greetings, soldier. You stand in a holy place. The Elder Scrolls are a sacred charge of the Aldmeri Dominion. We must keep the scrolls from those who would defile or misuse them.
The pieces begin to fall into place. With the King's aid, we shall assemble a force worthy of Meridia's blessing.
It's just the wind. No one's there.
I heard something. I know I did.
I'm glad Vanus made it. I was afraid we lost the old braggart.nnVanus and I go way back. I'm not sure we could continue this mission without him.
We all knew we'd be fighting for our lives and the lives of the people of Nirn when we agreed to undertake this mission.nnI never expected anything different.
I will take it from here, my friend. We have many things to do before we can assault the planar vortex.nnContinue to build our forces. I promise we won't march against Molag Bal without you.
The air is heavy, like velvet in my throat. It is a wonder these blades do not rust before my eyes!
Welcome, friend. We need to discuss the preparations for the coming assault, but I wanted to wait until you arrived.nnDo you have any questions before we begin?

With the slightest amount of assistance from the Mages Guild, I have figured out how to cross the Chasm and reach the planar vortex. The effort, however, will require the work of our combined forces.nnKing Dynar will explain everything shortly.

Look at this place! All fancy and formal. Everyone gathered, putting aside their differences to overcome a greater evil. How heroic! I expect this means that we're all going to die.nnHeroically, of course.
Vanus has assured me that his plan will work. We just have to put aside our differences and work together.
The Mages Guild and Fighters Guild, working together! I never thought I'd see the day!nnBut with you helping us, I'm sure that everything with turn out fine.
It is time to have our revenge!
Let's make this quick. There're monsters out there that need killing.
This is so exciting! My first council meeting! At least, my first that didn't involve Wood Elves and a dark forest.
All that work and worry, and here we are, helping the Mages Guild! It's like a dream come true.nnI can't wait to delve into a few more of these Coldharbour dungeons!
The probability that any of us will survive this adventure, based on every calculation I could reference, is exceedingly infinitesimal.nnCould be worse, I suppose.
I represent the people of Haj Uxith. My soldiers are your soldiers, as promised.
Molag Bal will shiver in fear at our approach! He will feel the might of me and my sisters!
I'm curious to examine this plan that Vanus has come up with.
If this one wasn't shaking in his fur at the thought of facing Molag Bal, I would find this gathering to be extremely fascinating!
Remember our deal. I help you, then you help me.nnEverything else is just so much sound and fury.
I'm not strong enough. nnHe's going to kill the Wilderking.
I didn't escape the fields with much, but you're welcome to take a look.
Don't bring the war in here with you. I don't want to hear it. I served my time in the Covenant army, and I want nothing more to do with it.

As soon as the cart is fixed, I shall return to my mother in Bergama. Crowns I can suffer, but never again do I want to see another beetle! Jahi offered a fat purse if I would stay here as cook, but I would rather sell everything and go.
I don't feel safe leaving the house anymore. The war seems to be right outside our doors.
Peace be upon you, wayfarer. Do you have a thirst that I can satisfy?
Welcome. Whatever Vlastarus has to offer is yours, for the right price.
I'm rather busy right now. Come back later.
This ram doesn't want to move. The training grounds always get the worst equipment.
I'm still a Shadowscale, sight or no sight. I protected <<1>> from the lamias, yes?
Everything is so beautiful here. I never thought I'd see anything like it.nnI think my people are starting to understand how important this decision really was. For all of us.
Please, take care where you step. Whoever killed this man may have left something behind.
Faraniel seems so at peace here in this city.nnMaybe she was right all along.
We'd just put out for Haven when the storm hit. Our ship foundered on some rocks and we had to swim back to land.nnNow we wait for another vessel to hire us on.
Fighting an opponent you know nothing about is like going into battle unarmed.nnStudy him firstwhat he wants, how he moves. If you can discover this, he is defeated before blades are drawn, yes?
Hush! This one is busy! Can you not feel the skooma flowing through the streets? If you cannot, listen! It is all around us!
I hope we made the right choice by coming here.nnBeing surrounded by all this though - it's so overwhelming.
Well, I'll be. Who knew what we were missing out on all this time?
I have not seen this type of greenery before. It's fascinating.
If Aranias does not receive help, she will die.
I'm scared. Is it okay to be scared?nnLook at all of this! I've moved the land on my island but. Tell me I can do this.
There is an island. There is an island out there. I can feel it reaching. I can almost touch it.

We receive strange looks from your people. I expected nothing less. They still think we are monsters.nnWe will prove otherwise. We will show them the power of the lamias and how our aid will help win this battle.
It isn't every day a bard comes to <<1>>! What better way to set aside our cares than by listening to songs of far off lands?
Isn't <<1>> wonderful? He's been to every port between here and <<2>>!
Anyone can sing. This one is here for news from afar!
<<1>> has come to <<2>>! We'll be drinking rotmeth to a spinner's yarns before the month is out!
Can I help you, or are you just going to stand there and stare?
It is my task to show the Imperial the sights of Alik'r.
This used to be a place of repose, of learning. Now  I don't know.nnIf my heart weighs this heavily, it is probably best if I leave this place.
Your skill with siege weapons will make a difference in many battles. Learn to use them here.
This one saved what one could from the wreckage of our ill-fated caravan, and wrestled the vultures for the rest! nnYou wish to see these things?
If you remember that gates are a keep's weak points, you know what tool to use to break in.
Our caravan was set upon nearby while <<1>> and I were  occupied elsewhere. I suppose we are stuck here until another travels through here.
You don't plan to patronize this place, do you?nnNever mind. Forget I said anything.
Walk softly, warrior. You are in the presence of great power.
Some of those creatures are still out there, but we'll deal with them now that you've cut off the source.
I heard you were the one that came to Longhaven's aid. I thank you, friend.
I hope those filthy elves didn't raid my shop.
If the beetles rush us, I will give my life to buy a few moments for the others to escape. nnMy son died in the fields, and I hold no fear in my heart at the thought that I might join him.
Look, Barbas! A surprise mortal.nnI hope you aren't here to cause trouble for me.
Welcome to Willowgrove! Thanks for visiting!nnI'm sorry we don't have enough spare honeymead to offer you a sample. We're running a bit low at the moment.
Oh! Come to sample our honey-mead?nnMy apologies, but we're running a little low at the moment. Hopefully things will be resolved soon and we should be overflowing again.
Must a man watch his livelihood slip through his fingers like sand, and his friends take Tu'whacca's guidance to the Far Shores? It is almost more than I can bear.
Careful, soldier. Siege weapons are dangerous to the unwary.
I have played in these fields since I was a child! I will not simply walk away!
How can I help you, soldier?
Hail, warrior. Have you come to gaze upon the Elder Scroll of Alma Ruma?
I must needs ready these supplies. A thousand apologies.
It is beyond my importance to speak with you. Best to seek out Jahi, at the house near the center of the field.
I wonder what <<1>> intends for these Dominion fools. If he has any honor it will be nothing pleasant, mark my words!
It will be good to leave this forsaken rock! How do the cat men stand being so still all the time?
Comings and goings, records of supplies, dialogues between the Helmsreeve and the Aldmeri envoys, the paperwork never ends!nnA moment's rest! Is that so much to ask?
Had the Dominion simply sailed on by, it wouldn't have come to this. Whatever happens next is on their heads, not ours.
This place is like the northern wastes of my homeland. The sky dominates the landscape.nnI could sit here and look at it for days.
Brewing fermented liquids in this dry climate is much more difficult than working in my beloved swamp. But foul ale is better than no ale at all, I always say.
Magic and magical tomes abound in this strange land!
The Fighters Guild is watching the situation here is Deshaan very closely.
Even strangers are welcome at our table, though we have little to share.
In the days of the Empire, rabble like the Black Daggers were hunted down and left to dangle from trees along the roadside.
With the Empire gone, who protects people like us? No one, that's who!
The Dark Lord's vile scheme fails today.
Though I live in squalor like the rest, I will not die here with them. Somewhere in Cyrodiil, there is a place unsullied by chaos and war. I will find it!
This one cannot find anything since fleeing the chaos in Hackdirt!
I cannot lose him too. Elethlin is all I have left, but I fear he will leave me soon.
Perhaps this place is worthless enough that no one will bother us here. Who knew Hackdirt was of value to any but us?
Let Iirenir rest, please. She hasn't had a good sleep in weeks, not since those damned Black Daggers kicked us out of our home.nnI could use some sleep too, but I can't seem to relax.
Now that I've got me sea-legs for this deck, so to speak, I think I'll navigate these waters just fine. nnMe and my new old friends.
The war has been our undoing. You see us at the end of our days, treasures stolen and safety gone.
Bird-people, unsavory sellswords, and dung in the streets. This Kozanset is a shaveskin paradise, yes? nnHa! Lucky for you, I sell many blades. Have a look.
You look like a wise walker to Khunzumnot like these unclawed Redguards. They spit on this Baandari's goods and wares. nnBut you know better. You know quality. Only the best from Khunzum.
Do you tire of wares that do not meet your impeccable standards? I see the woe on your faceyou need not try to hide it. Look, then, at my sweet goods! I have spotless items from all across Tamriel!
I am thinking you need more bags. Easier to hide things, yes?
This one's wagon would not break if we did not stea-  if we did not buy so many heavy things!

Ah. Come in, come in, walker! You have traveled far to see this one, yes? nnI know; you seek something lost. Hanubina-ko may help you find it. This one sees through mist and stone to speak with the moons and stars.
I don't know who sent you, but the answer is "no." I just want to be left alone. Please leave.
Soreheels tried to cook the bird people, but their meat tastes dry and sour. The shaveskins do not want to buy it. They make strange faces and run away. Now what is this one to do with it?

Good ale loosens the tongue and also the purse strings, is it not so? nnI have some things you might likeold Khajiiti spices. Nothing illegal, mind you. At least it was not illegal when last I was in the khaj. You will take a look, yes?

Between Soreheel's lead bottom and Wheelbreaker's clumsy carpentry, we will never get the wagon out of this stinking village. nnI do not wish to stay here. I'm far too young and sleek for such a place.
The only way to reach Molag Bal's planar vortex is to take control of the Chasm.
Andrathel does a much better job at coating these bowls. I don't know who coated these, but the honey is caramelizing.nnWe don't have the spare honey to waste on bad batches of mead.
Even the best chef can only do so much with inferior ingredients. But I am grateful for what Desh-Wazei and the other farmers provide. And I do make a delicious casserole surprise!
In my experience, a community's success depends in large part upon the quality of its brewmaster. And make no mistake. I am the best brewmaster you'll find in this Hist-forsaken realm.
Visitors to our ancient city are a rare commodity. Almost as rare as some of the wares I sell. Let me show you what I have available this fine day.
Icy water is the key to long life. First I work up a sweat, then I jump in the lake.
Oljorn is crazy, but it's all I have for entertainment out here.
It was truly unwise to let things get so out of hand.

May those bastards' evil souls languish here for all eternity!nnNow we must only nullify the wrong they did to me in life. If you will take the gemstones back to Darius, he can present them to the authorities and prove my innocence.
Never had I thought to hear an apology from such as she. Truly, I too am to blame for being too quick to fight.
With you here, maybe I don't need to worry so much about getting my ship back from these cursed Sea Elves.
Pelidil will pay for what they did to Asteril. They will all pay.
I never thanked you for helping us back in Woodhearth. Asteril was my friend, and because of you we can catch the ones that did this to her.
Well met, Queenseye. Grim work to be done here, and we're glad to have you with us.
Those bastards. If they hadn't outnumbered me .
<The harpy doesn't seem to be afraid or aggressive.>
Fancy a drink? All the finest libations in Tamriel, here. All the worst, as well.
Those Maormer pirates came from the water. They're all over <<1>>!
We can't let those Maormer pirates reach <<1>>. They'll butcher our families!
What are you doing here?nnDoesn't matter. If you're in the mood to cave in some Sea Viper skulls, I don't really care.
Why, it's you. We do seem to meet in the strangest places.
Not one Sea Viper will make it through this door.
<This Wood Orc's neck was snapped with incredible force. A blood trail leads off the edge of the cliff, and huge claw marks are gouged in the rock. It appears something tumbled off.>
Let me work on this barrier, you help stop the daedra coming through the portals!
I think our friends have the Chasm well in hand. What say we pop in for a chat with Molag Grunda?
These mages are crazy. Fearless, but crazy. The little wood elf says she can get this barrier down. I'll just make sure no one attacks her in the meantime.
Hey.nnSquad got separated. <<1>> and I found <<2>>. They hurt him bad.
A ringing head is bad.nnBut when it remains somewhat head-shaped  that is good, yes?
At last, a messenger! Welcome, oh winged deliverer. What does my prince have to say to me, after all these years?
What are you doing here? Get away, this is my place!

Greetings! This magical projection presents my current plan to my allies. Separated and alone, I decided to complete our mission. Personally.nnI entered the Black Forge through a side door with the intention of destroying the Great Shackle beyond.
Oh, it's just you. What a relief! I hate guard duty. Especially portal guard duty. You never know what's going to pop out and kill you where you stand.
My friend! To escape death so triumphantly is constant thrill, yes?nnNot so thrilling for the Maormer, of course.
You must be here to work with that matchmaker lug. If so, the boss says I can't touch you. nnWhich is a shame, because some of that stuff you're wearing looks pricey.
"No robbery, extortion, or drunken revelry until after the wedding."nnBloody Wildur and his blasted daughter. What are we supposed to do, eh? Are we the Ungodly, or ain't we? Pooey.
Let me be clear: I don't like you, and I don't like your smarmy friend inside the tent. nnStay out of my way, lest you want me to show you the color of your guts.
Vanus is amazing with his portal placement. Conjuration has never been a strength of mine.
My name is Halelah, and I have a gift for you.
It's finished. My masterpiece. What do you think? Be honest now.
I greet you, walker. Study my wares; there is sure to be something to your liking.
Please buy from Airal. He refuses to move until all his wares are sold. This one tires of the cold and his sullen company.
Do you honestly believe that this collection of misguided mistfits can actually challenge the Lord of Brutality?nnI take it back. You are as stupid as you are brave!

Ah, darling! Perhaps you could say something to your companions? They refuse to let me participate in their little council.nnThe Ayleid actually told me to shut up and be quiet! How terribly droll of the man.
I wish that Zur were here. He would have been shaking in his fur at the thought of going up against Molag Bal, but he also appreciated a good council meeting.
Lord Sanguine has decreed a revel! Talk to Skeewul and join us!
Lord Sanguine provides needed relief in dire times like this. Do you wish to participate? I have a special drink, brewed just for this occasion!
The world is going to Oblivion, so we might as well enjoy life while we can. Talk to Skeewul if you want to join in!
There are no unhappy folk at Lord Sanguine's revels. The war, those alliances, the Empirenone of that matters anymore.nnJoin us, talk to Skeewul!
Feel free to look, but don't touch the prisoners. Sylvian wants them alive, for now.
My father would be very proud of us, I think. nnYou have ensured that the honor of the Ash'abah will abide. I am grateful that I can count you as one of our tribe.
To know that young girl masquerading as a scholar's apprentice was actually one of the most dangerous necromancers in the Alik'r desert ?nnI still cannot understand it.

I still feel like such a fool. To have shared my knowledge with that evil girl, and the whole time .nnI am very grateful that she is no longer a threat. If things had not turned out this way, I don't know if I could've forgiven myself.
Look at you. First you drive the risen dead from the Sentinel Docks, and then you drive them from all of Alik'r.nnI must confess. I am impressed.

When I think back to when this all started, when the Withered Hand had captured me and was holding me beneath the city  I can't believe how far we've come.nnIt wasn't easy, but we defeated the Withered Hand. We're heroes now!
This is our spot. You're welcome to sit by the fire for a time, but you'll need to make your own camp, if you're staying.
I hope the fish keep biting. We'll be here a while.
This camp is primitive, but at least we're alive and out of harm's way, for the time being.
I can't believe they dragged me out into the middle of nowhere. It's cold and wet and all my books are ruined!
She killed them all. Froze them solid. How am I supposed to defeat that? I had to run, right? I had to hide or I'd be killed too!
Watch it, stranger. <<1>> put me here to keep an eye on his daughter's dowry.
Hold. In the name of the Dominion.
The city has been empty for so long. It's good to finally see a new customer in here.
Welcome to the Shining Star, my friend! You won't find a more warm and inviting place in all of Coldharbour!
Welcome, friend. I come from a long line of master brewers, and I guarantee that my beverages are the best you'll ever drink in this horrid land.
If you're looking for something to eat, just give me a moment. I'm not used to these crowds.
I represent the Fighters Guild here in the Hollow City.
My job is to establish the Mages Guild hall here in the Hollow City.
I'm almost sorry to be stuck inside these walls. I'd love to get out there and get into the thick of the battle!
A secure vault makes for a confident heart.
To see everything so alive and full of energy pleases me greatly. It is a stark contrast to the world outside these walls.nnIt reminds me of my time in Glenumbra, when things were  better.
This city is dreadful. All the bright colors. The blooming flowers and trees. The  life!nnMaybe I should go back outside again. I think I prefer Coldharbour's stark landscape to this  wonderland.

Finally, I can just relax in a nice, warm room. A glass of fine wine in my hand.nnI think I'll draw a nice hot bath to soothe my weary body. I just wish I had a servant or two to deal with these mundane tasks.
Hungry? Of course you are. C'mon over and let Firuin take care of you.
The wonders of war never cease. Every ram that shatters against a keep door, every trebuchet set afire, it's all coin in my pocket. Hurray for war, I say!
Aetis drives us like he fears the war will end tomorrow. Can't come soon enough for me.
Last load of logs broke our wagon wheels. Now Aetis says we have to cut them all in half.
Sorry, no time to talk. Vanus is running me ragged.
You'll want to talk to Vanus. I'm just his assistant.
Valenwood just keeps getting stranger and stranger. I might have to change my route entirely.
People call this one a coward for not fighting. Ziss on them. Getting drunk when things turn dangerous takes real courage!
Just policing up the last of these damned Imperials. Most scattered like bloodflies when we threw down our sheathes. Cowards all.
These claws are only good for one thing: slashing prices!
My head feels as if a dozen Orcs are pounding on war drums inside my skull.
I am proud to lend my magic to such great personages as you and Vanus Galerion.
Just give the word and my hammer will be by your side!
Hello, wayfarer! I am but a humble merchant searching for new markets for my fine goods. Can I interest you in a morsel of food? Perhaps you would prefer a cool drink?
Greetings. I guard this Transitus Shrine for the Dominion. Do you have questions for me?
<This Bosmer was tortured to death. There is nothing left to be done.>
I hate this place. I miss the warmth and golden glow of Alik'r.
I came along with the original force. I wanted to show my support for this important effort.
What a dismal land this is! Why don't they ever send me somewhere nice?
It's like stepping into the past. We're walking around in a piece of history! Look at the architecture!
I find it rather inspiring to see the Fighters Guild and the Mages Guild working together. It gives me hope for the future.
I fear for the mages still lost in the wilds of Coldharbour. I do hope we find them all before too much time has passed.
We need to gather our forces and end this! If we stand back and do nothing, the Planemeld will destroy our world.
If you're thinking of venturing outside the city, you'll need the toughest armor you can afford. Lucky for you, I have exactly what you need.
It's hard maintaining stock in a place like this. Especially with such a high demand. But I'll show you what I've got.
I wasn't sure what it would be like when I got here, but it isn't too bad. I might even be able to turn a profit!
As soon as I can take a break, there's so much I want to search and explore!
Irrki's heart beats with a thousand sorrows! But if you wish to purchase a sword, this one will show you what she has.
What a spectacular day! I almost feel like singing!
Despite the lack of ingredients I'm used to dealing with, this desolate place isn't half bad.
Enchanting requires concentration and precision, but I'm just not feeling like myself today.
My forge is your forge, friend.
If you need something, step right up! My work is in high demand right now. High demand.
I left my family back in Windhelm to come here. I hope I don't live to regret it.
This ancient city is pretty impressive.
You You're the one from the mine. Leave me alone! nnIsn't it bad enough to see me this way?
Hmm. This one smells wood smoke. You should wet your throat before you go. Easier to breathe with some sugar on the tongue, yes?
Greetings, walker. As events have turned from foul to fragrant, it falls upon Manabi to see to the blessings of this temple. She must see to this thing, but may the moons ever light your path.

This one's task is to render our temples sleek and fragrant once more, as should be any Temple of the Two-Moons Dance.  It would be too much to ask for the invaders of Dune to have been tidy about it, yes? This one thought as much.
Valenwood is a trove of rare ingredients.
The forest is rich with spiritual energy, so be careful. It makes the gems  anxious.
The Elf Queen demands garments, demands leathersdemands, demands, demands! But isn't that just the way of the world?
Welcome to Marbruk. Jewel of Valenwood. A good place to spend some coin!
Most Altmer wouldn't trust a Wood Elf with their money. Fair enough, but trust is the Dominion's foundation, is it not? We have to start somewhere.
This one could tell such stories of war over Valenwood. Yet none so strange as an Altmer city in Greenshade.
The best woodcraft is both strong and flexible. Just like me, yes? Ha!
Mead from meat, wine from grapes  by the end of the night it all tastes the same.
What? You think an Orc doesn't know his spices? That he can't please the delicate Altmer palate? Pah. Then you haven't tried my cooking.
If one more Bosmer tells me that he's "enchanted to meet me" I'm moving back to Summerset.
Equipment is at a premium in Valenwood, but I've orders to see guild members supplied.
At your service. One can never know enough.
A fine day for fine goods, no?
War brings high demand for armor, but it makes metal costly, especially in Valenwood. The Bosmer rely on imports.
The finest silks, the finest thread, the beauty of Nirn woven into a robe.
This is a good place to have one's mind opened. The magic runs deep here, and there is much more quiet.
Keep an eye peeled; this wood is full of the remnants of the Ayleid civilization.
The law of meat, hide, and bone obligates us to use every fleshy thing in the air, on the earth, and beneath the sea. Hence the superiority of Bosmer leathercraft.
Normally, I'd say these woods are no place for riding, but these are no ordinary woods. Seems like the beasts know their way better than I do, sometimes.
It is not the horse that makes the mount, but the master. Take care of your animal and your animal will take care of you.
Lay aside ancient enmities, or take up arms and make me rich. I'm not particular.
Sometimes claws do not suffice. Sometimes only the skill of the able craftsman will do.

You strike an imposing figure, friend. And you look like you might not be shy about using it to make a little coin, yes? I've got a little problem, and I think the answer just stepped onto this balcony.

Careful. Sure, you look like you can handle yourself, but this place is full of unscrupulous rats. nnEspecially Angore. Bastard thinks he can get away with ripping me off. Say, you interested in helping me settle accounts? For pay, of course.
I'm quite busy at the moment, sorry. I'll be lucky if this haul allows me to keep myself fed, much less pay off my debts. Please leave me to my work.
Do you know how to read?
What captains are going to come out here to trade when there are magical hurricanes destroying entire fleets?
We meet again, fellow knight! Wonderful day to sally forth, wouldn't you say?

You can go in, if you want. This one knows you drove the muskarse mage out of our inn, after all!nnBut this one must have you know the inn is closed for now. It is unsleek and foul-smelling, unfit for visitors.
What luck that someone came along. Don't worry about me. My companions need help!
Don't mind <<1>>. We're together again, and it's all thanks to you.
I've been waiting forever to spend time with my darling. A little privacy?

Red-Ears hears you, walker. Though his mate and he are very grateful for your assistance, the inn remains closed for now.nnUntil I wash, and I wash, and the filth and soot alll scrub away. Then and only then may Dune's inns accept visitors.
Not going to make the same mistake this time. I've got a system.
What is this? Who are you?
You're not with them, are you? Help me!
You fight well. I don't suppose you're here for us?

Daedra apparently don't have a big interest in looting. My goods are completely fine, even after all the chaos! And a good thing, too! With all of the destruction in the Merchant's District, people are going to need me.nnDo you need anything?
You get what you deserve. Nothing more, nothing less.nnStrength. Strength and steel, these are the only things that matter.
Leave me be, sera. I am considering the homilies of blessed Almalexia as I hone my body.nnThe next s'wit to cross blades with me will surely be passed under the axe, mark my words.
Zur hates standing in the green goo. No amount of licking gets it out of one's fur.
Whatever it is you want from me, make it quick.nnWith Dune having so recently been subject to a daedric incursion, I don't exactly have much time to deal with you.

Hmm? Oh, excuse me. I lost a bit of time for my studies with the Daedra and all.nnIt's imperative I show my family I deserve to leave this dump and return to Auridon. So, I hone my magics constantly. I'm sure you'll understand, I am, thus, busy.
Many of us will be remaining here, to fill in for those guards of Dune who died in its defense. Just between you and me, I'd rather be on the front, but orders are orders.
It's pretty from here, isn't it, Aleswell? Majestic even. Up close, inside, it's very different. I prefer the view from here.
Banking is an unfamiliar art, deep in Valenwood. But I am an eager student.
Fortunately, we didn't get hit as hard as most. We won't be able to take another storm like that though.
I have roamed this land since before many of these trees were seeds. In that time I have wanted to know how I came to be. nnYet here you stand with the answer and I hestitate, uncertain.
This one has many fine goods for sale. Care to look?
This one has traveled far and wide to assemble these wares. Special discount, just for you!
The water flows once more! Our souls are no longer bound by <<1>>'s magic.
Spare a coin for a veteran's meal?
Now that the storm's over, everyone here is really just trying to pick up the pieces. If you are looking for work or trade, I'd recommend Mistral. They didn't get hit as hard as the rest of us.
Do you see how strong these ants are? They can carry a dead bug three times their size!
Kamu crossed the Chasm, with most-fragrant companions by his side! nnThis one grieves for the friends we lost today, however, and for the losses yet to come.
Animal husbandry; one of the few jobs here that doesn't violate the Green Pact. But Marbruk's where the money is.
Just the person I was looking for. King Dynar is rallying our forces near the Reaver Citadel.
I shouldn't be able to see you. It looks like the Mourning Stone brought the spirits out in the temple courtyard. Can you hear me?
Cadwell takes some getting used to, I must admit, but he really is an amazing fellow. He .nnWait a moment! What happened? Where's the rest of your team?
Greetings Soldier! How may I aid you?
Many outsiders who visit Bramblebreach are weary. They carry weapons and have seen much violence.nnIf you are one of them, please stay a while. Relax. Daydream a little.
The spirits told me another outsider has come to visit Bramblebreach.
Don't mind Uunril. Welcome to our home.
Does everyone break into each other's houses where you come from?
Shh. Don't tell Galesse my hiding place.
I can't tell if it's laughing  but I think it is.
See the tower in the distance. That's where the Wilderking lives.nnI hope to travel there one day. Maybe I'll meet the Wilderking himself!
You look like a confident person. I wish I was confident.
You scared them away! I almost had one.
My poor brother Thragaer. He's really looking for them.
I thought the battle behind us was dreadful, but this place  it boggles the mind!nnStill, we've made it this far. Victory is within our grasp, especially now that the Radiant Lady stands with us.
Meridia and Molag Bal have always hated each other with a fiery passion, but that hatred has cost so many of our lives.nnI have a notion to show them both why Vanus Galerion's power should be feared!

Most people dream of lusty Argonians or delectable dishes. But not old Darien.Oh, noI dream about planar vortexes and blinding lights of Meridia! How is that possible?nnAnd why do I keep asking questions that no one can answer?

I've seen so many things in my life. This though, I could've never imagined something as big as this.nnThere have been far too many people who have given up their lives so we could stand here. We have to ensure they did not die in vain.
If only we could have known about  all of this. If we'd have known about this before everything happened. Maybe my people could have stopped it.nnOr maybe it's just wishful thinking.
Quickly, untie me! They could be back at any moment!
Greetings, soldier. How may I aid you?
You're welcome to share my fire. Or is there something else you need?

They say the war will affect us all. That we should all care about what is happening. Well, I do! Nord mead is so much easier to come by when Dominion soldiers are raiding supply caravans in Cyrodiil. I like the softer stuff.
I like these little guys, but I can't help wondering how they might taste.

I came here after hearing rumors of vampires and some kind of magical cursed skull. It all sounded quite interesting. That is, until I heard some hero went and destroyed it for the sake of the village.
Come and have a look! Any traveler can benefit from Shajamah-ja's finely-stitched goods.
These are dangerous times. Don't leave unprepared.
Fada thought merchant life wouldn't be so bad. Certainly safer than picking pockets. But, you know, this one sometimes misses the thrill of the hunt.

We heard a lot of the merchants left Longhaven, so we decided to try our luck here. Even if the claims that the place is cursed turn out to be true, it can't be any worse than dealing with Bashshi-ra in Woodhearth.
Nirnroot wine. This one sings its praises!
Need a warrior you can count on? For the right coin, I can supply you with one.
When you're on the battlefield, you want comrades you can count on, soldiers you've paid to be at your side. My mercs are the best in all of Cyrodiil.
I'm just passing through to resupply before I head out to hunt for more Dark Anchors. Everyone has their share of problems, but none of it will matter either way if we don't destroy those Anchors.
We are always willing to wield swords in the Dominion cause, for the right pay, of course.
Oh, it's you again! I heard a rumor that you ended up saving Longhaven. Maybe I'll return there one of these days and take up hunting again.
I'd planned this painting as a gift to Queen Ayrenn, if only people would stop getting in the way.
The Dominion is looking for more able-bodied fighters. I think I'll answer the call.
I can't believe the Thane tricked us like that. And he hurt Bernt! If the Thane shows his face in here again, I'm going to give him a piece of my mind!
That so-called Thane threatened me for tampering with the casks. nnMy father pushed him away from me and that dreadful  creature  he knocked my father down. I was afraid he might kill him.
Damned bloodfiend took a piece out of my arm.
When you hunt lizards on the sands, you must know their favorite basking spots.nnI make sure the softest and warmest pits are clear of debris. Then, the lizards come to me.
Crime is the brother of civilization, I suppose.
It's almost like that girl doesn't realize how ridiculous she looks flouncing about like that.
You look bored. C'mon over and have a drink!

This passage leads to an old sanctuary built by the first Altmer to travel to Valenwood. It is now in the hands of the Maormer, but the rightful rulers will soon reclaim it. I suggest avoiding the place until then. The Maormer protect it fiercely.
This is my favorite fishing hole. I'm glad the Altmer left it alone, even though the guards give me grief when I try to visit.
You've a strong heart. Don't let the troubles of this world change that.
Have you seen my husband, Cassirion? If he's ogling that Bosmer dancer again  and on top of that the Green Artisan stole my wedding gift!
I have to travel to Marbruk every day for work. It is a long walk, but Shalirr has many mouths to feed.
Come to use this Transitus Shrine? A wise choice. Do you have questions?
O, I beseech you! Let none of them remain safe from your blade, let your righteous wrath flow through them and leave not a scrap behind  and let my family be yet alive.
It is all gone  everything and everyone  just gone, in the blink of an eye!
Every able-bodied soul is needed to oppose our enemies. We will either bury old divisions, or bury our families.
Stand back, vile beast, lest I slay you in no uncertain terms!nnOh, it's you. Taking a stroll, then? Enjoying the beautiful countryside?
Welcome to our humble guildhouse.nThe presence of the Thalmor in Woodhearth has been a mixed blessing for us.nI fear you'll find the bureaucracy as vast as our collection of rare knowledge.
Arkay preserve me, I thought you were one of them for a moment!
The horses were screaming and something hit me  I feared I would die here.
My husband Calastil hasn't left his bed since his favorite dog Pluck was stolen by the Green Artisan. I'm worried for his health.
You are always welcome here, warrior.
My heraldic cane was stolen by the Green Artisan! I can't show my face in court without it. How humiliating!
Don't bother Lowindor, he's pretending to be asleep.

An Altmer researcher from Summerset told me the Bosmer here worship a god they call the Wilderking. She is determined to search for this Wilderking in that treacherous forest, discover if he is real, and if he is in fact a god.nnSuch a brave girl.
Truly it is a beautiful place now that the stains are washing away and the rightful owners have reclaimed this place. Oh, I wish Asteril could see it. Perhaps she is looking down on me now.
Not a bad haul. Good condition, too. We can use these to resupply our soldiers.
I've kept the forge running hot if you need to use it. Retaking this place isn't without its benefits for the Dominion.
The battle made this one a bit hungry. Let's cook up something nice, yes?
Hard-fought and well won. You're making quite a name for yourself you know.
It's surprising how many of our own supplies and armaments the Maormer managed to take from us on their raids. But you've seen to it that they're back in our hands. Well done.
It feels good just to be able to sit by a warm fire and read again. It's been too long, really.nnIf anything, it's a nice distraction. Takes my mind off everything that went on back at the cliffs.
Thank you for not giving up on me back at the cliffs even though I had already given up on myself.nnI was so close to just stepping off that edge .

This one apologized for stabbing Juline. She  didn't seem to accept it, though. This one thinks she's going to need time to forgive Mim.nnMim hope she knows that what Mim did was for her own good. To save her. Sounds strange, even to Mim, yes?

Fariel wants me to remain here for a time as her representative. Holding the sanctuary could greatly strengthen the military might of Woodhearth. We've driven the Maormer out, but they won't stop the raids. They never do.
Marbruk gardens are beautiful, yes?nnAzurdat planted these. Of course they are beautiful.
Best get back to Shrouded Vale before it's too late.
Make your selection quickly. This potion requires my utmost concentration.
You want my services? Fine. It seems any fool is allowed to meddle in the arcane these days.
An outsider! Don't tell me anything about the world. I want to see it for myself.
Hello, I hope you are enjoying our village.
Compared to other Bosmer settlements, Woodhearth is downright civilized. At least, they don't constantly try to steal your tools here.
I traveled Tamriel studying the art of weaponsmithing. And then war brought me back to Woodhearth.
Treethane Fariel herself commissioned one of my blades. I was humbled, truly humbled.
Greetings, warrior. I guard this Transitus Shrine for the Covenant. Do you have questions for me?
So much soil to till for the planting, so little time.
Bosmer brew is poison. Mead from the guts of insects. Blech.
This one sells a wide variety of meats and also plants for those of delicate digestion.
You are always welcome here, warrior.
A hunter's weapon is no mere tool. It's an extension of himself.
It's imperative I be left to catalog our supplies. Leave me to it, if you don't mind.
We're going to scare our friend Khalima. She loves it when we scare her. Once she stops chasing us she laughs. nnI haven't seen her laugh  but I'm sure she does. She loves us!
Aha. A guest! How wonderful!nn I wonder, would you help my friend and I with a little experiment?
See? <<1>> has more sense in him than half the Albatross crew.nnHe never did like <<2>>. Next time, I'll trust the monkey.
Found the old Everfull Flagon, eh? Interesting place, the Flagon. Glad someone's finally got it sorted out. Good show!
If the fight reaches these walls, I plan to be ready.
I'm a merchant by trade, but a warrior at heart.
Even for a well-traveled denizen of the planes such as myself, this place is way beyond my comfort level. I fear it won't get any easier from here on in.
There's no time to rest. We have to keep moving. I'll make sure our flank is protected while you clear the way ahead.
Every strategy has a dozen flaws. The trick is making sure the enemy doesn't take advantage of them.
I prefer to fight from a distance. The longer the better. So I'm quite content to hold up in this city for the duration of this engagement.

Look at this! I'm actually sweating! I can't remember the last time I performed this much physical exertion.nnThis better be worth it. Usually Kireth deals with these things while I deal with the research and planning.
Come to buy some of my astonishing Nirnroot wine? Well, I hate to break your heart but I'm all out.
I greet you, wayfarer. Doubtless you have come for my renowned Nirnroot wine. I grieve to say that I have no more at present.
Zur does not like this place. It has everything this one despisesgreat heights, impenetrable darkness, deadly opponents . But it also has things that fascinate this one.nnZur is so conflicted!
I don't care for this job, I'm just here for the free food.
Ignore my brother, we're professionals. Laurosse isn't paying us enough to fight Orc warbands. Much less haul this cooking bowl around.
Laurosse is so cute when he's fumbling with life skills.
That was a close call. Thanks for helping me in there.nnI don't know about you, but I'm really starting to dislike Daedric death traps.
The planar vortex is destroyed. Molag Bal's Planemeld is at an end.
My time has finally come it seems. I have  I have lived far longer than any of my people.nnFinally  I will  I will be able to join them once more.
I fear the King's wounds are too extensive for us to heal.nnHe  he doesn't have much time left.
Do not fear. This one won't jump.nnBut the thought has occurred.
Talk to Maelen. He makes the deals around here.
When I'm not terrified of dying, this job's pretty boring.
If you have need of swords, speak with Maelen. His word guides us.
Have to keep practicing. There's a war on, you know.
A swift stream yields the tastiest fish. Few know this, but Minal shares with you.
Welcome! Siege weapons win the wars, you know, no matter what the generals say.
It is good that Mangeth likes to talk. He could not repair a siege engine to save his life.
Slowly, now. You've been through an ordeal. Take a few moments to collect yourself.
Run here, check on this, note down thatsomeday I'm going to stab Sorcalin with this quill.
No time to talk, soldier. Grand Warlord Sorcalin keeps me running all day.
I finished training yesterday. Had too much to drink. Need time to recover. Just go away.
We'd better win this war, with all the crap I've had to haul for you soldiers.
This one honors you for your service to the Dominion, walker. Nezashun will soon join you on the battlefields.
What a dismal location for a battle! I can't wait until this whole thing is over and I can return to Auridon and put all this nonsense behind me.
What destruction! What death! Oh, this entire situation brings a smile to my face.
I can't believe you came here. And killed that monster of a man. Thank you.
Used to be known as Fangs-Like-Steel. I changed my name when posted here.

Greetings, wanderer. If you have come to speak with an augur, there are none present at this time. Augur Volso was the last to have blessed this refuge, and he passed to his reward several months ago.

Smashing. So glad you could join us. Welcome to the Fighters Guild, which is rather a mundane name, isn't it? nnThough it is precise. They fight things and they're in a guild. Works rather well, actually, come to think of it.
These Argonians don't know what cold is really like. Where I grew up, even our fires froze solid.
Moth Priest Crassius is practically an augur. The ancestor moths sing to him, when outsiders are not about. His wisdom guides us in this refuge.
Though the Elder Scrolls we studied have been taken from us, this is still a holy place. Walk reverentially here.
I'm just an acolyte here, as you can tell from the vital tasks I've been given. Speak with Moth Priest Crassius in the temple, if you seek answers to questions.
The cold here torments my body, but the serenity of this refuge soothes my spirit.
While the Way of the Peaceful Fist cannot prevail against the hordes that stole our Elder Scrolls, it is sufficient to defend ourselves against wayfarers who come to despoil this refuge.
Greetings, wayfarer. If you seek knowledge, speak with Moth Priest Crassius in the temple. My advice extends only to cooking.
Onto the backs of a few fall the duties of many.
Going crazy around this place. I need some live targets.
Welcome to the Mages Guild enclave.
Welcome. Is there anything the Mages Guild can do for you?
Greetings. You've stumbled across the Mages Guild enclave here in Nimalten.
Welcome. Are you here on Mages Guild business?
I don't understand what you people see in this city. I mean, compared to the rest of Coldharbour, it's a bloody rathole.
Welcome to the Mages Guild. Make yourself at home.
This one is having some difficulty translating these pages. Your distraction is welcome.
Gindur and I have a bet. Whoever collects the most Altmer ears in the first month of battle wins a dozen bottles of sujamma.nnI'm going to enjoy drinking that.
You think generals are demanding? Try keeping a bunch of whiny merchants fed and supplied. Then you'll know what work really is.
Oh, thank Y'ffre you're not one of the Wood Orcs, and you're not one of the strange people in that cave.
I hope you've got a job for us. I'm sick of eating gritty bread at every meal.
There's always another sword to sharpen, another piece of armor to clean. The work never ends around here.
It is an honor to assist Grand Warlord Dortene. On the battlefield, I would be but one sword amongst thousands. Here, with Dortene, I help guide the course of the war.
Going into battle without a siege weapon is like eating mountain bear hash without any teeth. You might live through it, but it won't be pleasant.
Grand Warlord Zimmeron is demanding, but at least the constant movement keeps me warm.
I do all the work and Ulg gets all the credit. I'll have my own shop one day and run her out of business.
Organizing this camp is a never-ending task. No sooner do I get one pile straightened out and someone else makes another mess somewhere else.
Get out of here, before they spot you. They'll kill us all!
When you're tired of being regular army, come join us. The food's good, the pay's good, and we take the jobs we want, not those some general forces on us. No suicide missions for us!
Another one who likes to stand around and watch work being done, eh? Well, this statue's not going to carve itself.
There's nothing like a little ale after being on duty. Unfortunately, I never seem to stop at just a little.
I hate always having to cook, but I'm the only one in camp who doesn't burn the food.
I will bring honor and glory to my clan and the Covenant!
