Greetings. When I sight on the target, I picture an Elven face there. My aim is true every time.
Growing up, I longed to be a warrior. Now that I am, I long for home. I wonder if I'll ever be happy.
Asheeus likes to talk. Why don't you go bother him and let me do my work?
Welcome to Gottlesfont Priory. You come at a sorry time, as we will soon close our doors, perhaps forever.
Greetings, warrior. I pray that the Eight watch over you as you head to battle. Remain here as long as you like.
I don't know why Dortene hasn't had all those trees chopped down. Hard to see if enemies are coming.

These creatures show up in the night, try to take everything from Mura. This one has worked hard to make friends, find people who would accept her.nnMura will not allow these beasts to kill her friends.
Even the fish here are foolish. No southern fish would bite at hooks in this cold. They would be sensibly buried in the mud, waiting for the weather to become liveable.
The sisters are in the cathedral. They're in charge of the priory now, what's left of it.
Only vigilance keeps the enemy from our gates.
I love the feel of a skull splitting under my sword. But I hate all this waiting.
Deliveries of supplies never stop around here. If the weather weren't so nice, it'd be pretty miserable.
Do not stare so, warrior. Though Redguard mages are rare, we do exist.
I keep thinking I see movement by the rocks. Must be shadows playing tricks on my eyes.
Soldiers step out of line, they answer to me. A couple hundred laps around the camp usually straightens them out.
Keep a sharp eye, soldier. We've spotted enemy spies out there. An army might not be far behind.
How lucky am I? Apprentice to some of the best crafters in the Covenant!
It's, uh, good you got here when you did. You were much more, eh, merciful than I was about to be to those creatures.
This one knew Ronyssa's daughter. She was a good girl. Full of life.nnWhat evil could have done this to us?
I still don't know what happened out there. I've never felt fear like that before. nnI just froze. Sorry about any trouble I gave you back there.
We can use all the help we can get here. We've already lost a few brave scouts.
Looks like the previous owner took a fall off the rocks in back. Bad luck for him, good luck for me. This place is mine now; go find your own.

This cave is quite lovely, but have you seen the nightmarish landscape outside? How do you people keep your sanity? nnI believe I'll just remain indoors. Do let me know if I'm needed for anything heroic, won't you?
Tu'whacca's breath! Are all my efforts doomed to failure? Is there nowhere I cannot be found?
Would ya look at that thing? It's huge!nnYou're going up there, aren't you? I'd say you were an idiot, but what use would that be? I'll just wish you luck and hope for the best.
<Maujad appears to have been struck down by unholy magic.>
Are you with those loggers? Damn Admands. I never should have trusted them. Now they're chopping down all my trees.

Dibella's legs! But you are a bold one! Even the bards of Wayrest sing of your exploits. nnI must confessI had hoped to meet you one day. We sharpen our blades on the same whetstone, if you take my meaning.
I've served the Thalmor for almost twenty years now, as an advisor in the matter of healing arts.
You don't happen to be my relief, do you? No, I suppose not.nnI hate standing guard on my own. Not that I'm afraid or anything. It's just a little eerie out here, so close to poor, cursed Crestshade.
The Light of Arkay guides our way. It protects us and gives us strength. It shines forth through this unfortunate darkness and shall lead our troops to victory.nnThe Light protects us all.
I will stay your execution since you came all this way. But choose your words carefully. I'm not a patient king.
Ah - thank the Eight. Hurry up and cut me loose!
We sat around Shornhelm for way too long. I'm tired of twiddling my thumbs and watching my nails grow.nnIt's time to get out there and hit something.
House Dorell is ready. More than ready!nnWhy we have to wait for that vampire to order the assault, though, I'll never understand.
The lightest and finest armor, that's all I sell!
If you trust your life to inferior armor, you deserve the death you'll receive. I sell only the best.
My armor protects and conceals. Neither heavy nor light armor does both!
Light armor gives you stealth and speed, both vital on the battlefield!
No armor defeats my weapons. No arrow straighter, no blade sharper!
Some think of my wares as trinkets. Think that if you will, but one of my trinkets could very well save your life!
Heavy armor repels heavy blows. What foe delivers the lovetaps that lighter armor can turn away?
Wisdom lies in being prepared for all eventualities. My weapons will ensure that.
Here for mercenaries? I have only the best.
There's nothing like the feel of a good, skull-splitting weapon in your hand, is there? Go ahead, take a look.
<It appears to be the corpse of an unfortunate mage. Possibly a low-ranking member of the Mages Guild based on his garb.>
Like a pebble rolling down from a mountaintop, sometimes the smallest of things can have great effects.
It's well known that everyone attacks the least-armored foe on the battlefield. Don't make yourself a targetwear heavy armor.
Please! Please! I can't breathe! I can't  breathe! Let me out!
To make an impact on the battlefield and impress the generals, you need siege weapons. Check out my stock!
Ahh  it's the Mane's pet. Are you here to let me out? I can't wait to dig my fingers into your very soul.
Fire  pain! Faolchu  repent. Please  release me.
This one is greatful for your help.
Sorry, stranger. I'm here on important business with the Mages Guild seeking some rogue members of our organization. I don't have time for idle conversation.
Vanus is a dear man. In many ways, he is family to me. Since he has given you his trust, I'm willing to set aside our differences. But under different circumstances, you and I would be sworn enemies.
This one's eye is on you. Make one move against the Queen and this one will cut you down.
Mind the skies. There are harpies about.
<This man is wearing the uniform of a Mages Guild acolyte. His face is contorted in fear and pain. However he died, it was sudden and unpleasant.>
For soldiers, this is a waystation, one place among many they will see in Cyrodiil. For myself, it is home and I would be nowhere else.
I hate to say it, but this place is starting to get a bit overwhelming.nnNah, I'm just kidding. This has been exciting so far! I'm having a great time!
We need to ensure that whatever is behind us does not get ahead of us.nnI think this is where we make our stand while you go ahead. Hopefully the others catch up eventually.
And how can I help you, warrior?
Let them attack. I'm eager to prove myself in battle.
It took a bit of work, but I was able to track you down. Just one of my many gifts, if you must know.
You soldiers better use these furnaces. I'm not hauling all this wood for nothing, you know.
Shimmy tries to be patient, but he never holds out for long.
Huh. Another soldier. You here to break things or buy something?
This one is clever, always taunting her foe to strike first. I will not fall to her wiles this time.
If you want to see them in action, hire us. Talk to Milva inside and make a deal, get us out of this damned place.
There's nothing like a good meal after a hard day. Sadly, this is nothing like a good meal.
I'd rather clean up after pigs than soldiers. At least pigs don't crap where they sleep.
Don't mind me. I'll be fine. It takes more than a few Daedra to finish me off.
In Hammerfell, it is said that any food is preferable to starvation. Those who speak so have never tasted army food.
Everyone complains about my cooking, but no one offers to do it themselves. Typical.
Speak with Roshan. I just work here.
The enchanting facilities upstairs are open to all who wish to use them.
An army that attacks here, gets crushed. I look forward to that.
Excellent fighters, these orcs. I once saw Thoga slice an Elf's head clean off his shoulders. We laughed for days about that one.
This post will not be taken while I can wield my sword.
Take care of your mount, and he'll take care of you.
Yeah, I'm wearing human armor, so what? Mine was stolen at Fort Ash. How do Bretons fit their heads into these tiny things?
Bad food, poor pay, and deadly work. If the ale weren't good, I'd quit.
This place has changed.nnThe Wilderking he's leaving us.
Only constant vigilance keeps the enemy from our door. I am honored to do my part for the Covenant.
Dydier spends too much time atop the tower. War looks glamorous when you're high above the bloody fields.
One can never be too careful with alchemy. The slightest mistake by the unskilled can have disastrous results.
Want armor that doesn't clank loudly with every step, slowing you down and alerting your enemies? Look no farther!
Moderation in all things, including armor. I have what you need, warrior!
Want to cut through armor to get to the delicious meat inside? The tools you need are right here!
Without the right accessories, you're not ready for war.
Fear no blade or arrow in my armor!
Fur in your food is just an added bonus, friend.
Ah! Another sharp-minded citizen!nnDo you also prefer not to be ravaged by Reachmen?
When the troops cram in here before deployment, you could die of thirst in this place. Take me days to find your body too.
Ah! Did you hear the voice of reason and come to listen more closely?nnThe Reachmen are at the city's doorstep. Something must be done, must it not?
Drink up, soldier. No ale out in the field.
You can never have too many friends around you on the battlefield. Want to rent a few?
Sharul fights for coin, not politics. Coin purchases more two-moon cordial.
Not all mercenaries are motivated by greed. Some choose this life for reasons no less honorable than yours.
Anyone who wants to eat vegetables needs to find another cook!
Hail, friend! Have a look around. Take your time, admire the goods. nnYou don't see much work of this quality south of Orsinium.
Cyrodiil will belong to the Dominion. Soldiers like you will make it happen.

You've a mind to weave enchantments, I take it? Do be careful with the equipment. Like everything in my shop it's spotless  and expensive. nnI've a few enchantments of my own if you're interested. Have a look.
This staging area requires constant supervision. I serve as General Marenil's eyes and ears throughout the camp.
If it were up to me, I'd toss those mercenaries out of camp. They're nothing but spies who'll sell out to the highest bidder.
AhNabina-ko is glad to finally see someone with jah in their purse. You've come to look over my potions, yes? Each is a fragrant gem, walker. Potent as skooma and sweet as sugar! Behold!
You, there! The Covenant is threatened by more than filthy Reachmen and Imperial conscripts! The Pact and the Dominion are poised to pounce. We must take up the sword to defend our homeland!
Blessings of St. Pelin be upon you. What brings you to the house of the Divines? Do you need aid or shelter?
Few come here. The tavern seems more popular with soldiers.
By Zenithar, it's good to see someone with a heavy purse againwe haven't had a deposit in days. How can I help you?
Greetings, my friend. You've come to make a deposit, yes?
Comrade  Aelif never thought to see you again. What are you doing here?
Perhaps the gods do not intercede on mortals' behalf. But I'm unwilling to take that chance before battle.
Want some helping hands for battle? Talk to me.
You puny mortal whelp! Father is so very angry with me, all because of you! Come here! I'm so very, very hungry!

I heard there was an important meeting going on. I'm sure they meant to invite me. After all, important meetings lead to quests, and quests are my speciality!nnI'm always ready to smite evil and preserve the natural beauty of Coldharbour.
Enough. Enough! I'm ending this story now.
I find the wisdom of my ancestors soothes me on the eve of battle.
I cannot wait to return to Hammerfell. This city stinks of dog and bird droppings.

I am a long way from Ash Mountain and the warm climate of Stonefalls.nnBut I have committed my time and talent to helping the Mages Guild here in Coldharbour. Hopefully, this will soon be over and we can return to our homes.
Nice Fighters Guild hall! It's got all the comforts of home. But I'm ready to get out there and fight. nnYou can only plan so much. Sometimes you need to swing your damned axe and move forward.
Until we take back the Imperial City, no one crosses this bridge!
General Braning is a harsh taskmistress. My work never seems to end. Get out into the field as soon as you can, before she finds something for you to do.
You can't get through here. Even if you survive the monsters, the bridge is in ruins.
Fancy yourself a clothier? Well, I'm the best in town. You'll need some of my goods if you want to keep up.
Soldiers cut down trees to make siege engines, which in turn cut down soldiers. I sense a lesson in this, but it escapes me.
The captain of the Bjoulsae Queen still hasn't furnished me with her manifest! I suspected smuggling, but the guard won't even help me enforce the laws.
Talk to Golvy if you wish to purchase. Rest assured, machines made by me fulfill their duties.
We are ready. We await only General Marenil's orders to attack. Until then, we try not to go crazy with boredom.
The general likes his home tidy. If the books aren't lined up like soldiers on review, he makes me run laps around the house.
I've been following Angranel around for years now, keeping her house and making her meals. This is the nicest place we've ever stayed. It's usually a leaky tent with mud floors.
Quiet in here right now. No stabbings, no bodies to toss out the door, no broken furniture. I could get used to this.
Yeah, what is it? If the sarge sent you, tell him I'm not coming. I'm going to sit here and drink until I pass out or piss myself. Or both.
<The torn and bitten flesh of this recently murdered victim displays remarkably little blood for such a violent death.>
Siege weapons win wars, no matter what the generals tell you.
The other soldiers laugh at me, but my soul yearns for sweet, gentle music. If only my father had let me become a bard, instead of forcing me into the army!
These louts better be ready for the battle of their miserable lives, because they haven't seen anything yet!

I am proud of the Guilds and what we have accomplished thus far, but it isn't over yet. I hope we can continue this unprecedented cooperation a while longer, for I fear our greatest challenge is yet to come.

So you have fought your way to Molag Bal's gates, outsider. Saying I am impressed would be an understatement.nnAs promised, I have come to give you a gift from my people. It will aid you in your coming battles.
These poor bastards. They're just trying to find some place safe, but disaster seems to follow after them.
Here's someone who's seen a battle or two. You've read the writing on the wall, haven't you, my friend?
I think I'm going to be ill.  Sorry.

Vanus wants me to round up this interesting bunch and lead them into the battle. This should be  challenging? Yes, that's a word.nnI understand you're going in ahead of us. Be careful in there. And leave a few Daedra for us to deal with!
We've come from Senalana to help secure the Mane's ascension.
Thank you for your help in Greenhill.
Thank you for your help in Greenhill.
Thank you for your help in Greenhill.
Thank you for your help in Greenhill.
Thank you for your help in Greenhill.
Thank you for your help in Greenhill.
Your work here and in Falinesti should be a beacon for others.
Your work here and in Falinesti should be a beacon for others.
Your work here and in Falinesti should be a beacon for others.
Your work here and in Falinesti should be a beacon for others.
Dune and Willowgrove wouldn't be the same without your help, my friend.
Dune and Willowgrove wouldn't be the same without your help, my friend.
Dune and Willowgrove wouldn't be the same without your help, my friend.
The vessel is ours and the shards are in place. But we must be careful. If the vessel is destroyed before it reaches the barrier, our chance to to get inside will be lost.
That's a big, uh, bone thing you got there.nnSo Verandis was able to get that thing under control, eh? I need to remember not to cross that guy.
Leave this business with the Reachmen to the militia. A pack of howling hill-dwellers dressed in skins is not a matter worthy of your skills.
When times are tough, there's always beer!  I hope.
Welcome to the Bay-Tar's Mess, mate! nnBe careful not to step on any toes here; everyone's a little on edge, and I only allow one bar-fight per day.
Ah-ha! Another would-be brewer. I can always tell.
Greetings, customer! Or so I hope. nnMy other customers say I sample these delectable morsels far too often. But how else can I be sure of their quality? Eh?
Those Reachmenby St. Pelin's sacrifice, they're inhuman. I saw their faces beneath the rotten leathers. Black eyes  like a troll's eyes. Gods help us.
This one thinks you could be looking to make a purchase, yes?
I trust you plan to purchase something?
What can I get you today?nnEverything's made right here in town by my father, Merail Avani.
It is time, Vestige. Sai Sahan's strength has returned. You must accompany him to his ancestral home in the Valley of Blades.
Hail, friend. I apologize for the mess. The chapel is usually a bit more  tidy.

Are you headed to the Mages Guildhall? I've been waiting on a shipment of nirnroot for days! Magister Sernays will not be best pleased. If he says anything about turning Jernald into a goat, you'll let me know, right?
We set out for Skyrim in a few days. I hope the drovers Dalmi sends with us smell better than the last bunch.
Honor to you, traveler. You don't look like one of those poor devils out on the street. But if you've come for work, I'm afraid there's none to be had.
I'd rather drink alone if it's all the same to you, f'lah.
I ask Master Larhoth for guidance. He says "poke sharp end" into the fighting doll. Fine advice, no?
One of those creatures bit me. It bit me!nnOh, I don't  I don't feel so good.
I  I can't feel my legs.
They get you to join up, too? nnFrankly, I'm just here for the chow.
Greetings, warrior. I have mounts for sale, if you need one. Do not travel Cyrodiil on foot!
Looking for a mount? I have the fastest ones in all Cyrodiil!
If it's a mount you want, a mount you shall have. None finer in all of Cyrodiil!
The gods protect us in our time of need. We will  we will get through this.
I was a damn fool to charge in here. Caught in the heat of the moment.  I could smell the chance of victory. And we ran into this. I  I'm at fault for these troops. They died because of me.
May St. Pelin watch over you, traveler. I'm afraid I can't tarry. There are many here who require my attention.
Ah, hello there, my lovely! You look thirsty. See anything you like? Of course you do. Haby Dibella, I'm such a tease! Can I get you something?
You a sailor? I don't suppose you're setting out anytime soon? I'm a fair carpenterI just need a way out of this town.
If you're thirsty, you'll want to talk to Mortine. Dibella knows she'll want to talk to you. nnIf it's grub you're after, you're talking to the right person. What can I get you?
This inn has quite an impressive library. I'm surprised the Mages Guild hasn't ransacked the place.
Have you any news from Northglen? My aunt lives there, but I've not seen her among the refugees.
I left Sentinel shortly after the dead started rising. I've got a real talent for migrating to doomed cities.

Divines bless you, friend! Rivenspire has become a hard place to earn a living. My eleven children will surely starve today without a morsel to eat.nnWon't you spare some gold for an honest man and his poor children?
Divines give me strengthin my time I've helped both the poor and the wounded, but never both at once.
He told me he wished he could stay, but he couldn't be in two places at once. I think I proved him wrong.
Once again, you succeeded at the task set before you. Well done, my friend.
I didn't fight my way up here just to wiggle my toes in front of a fire. There's killing to do!nnIf Verandis tells me to wait here one more time, I may just have to stab him.

I'm trying to talk some sense into the Countess. She needs to abandon all this Light nonsense and start trusting in herself and her own abilities.nnBesides, she's much too pretty to hide her head inside a prayer book all the time.
This one was honored to fight alongside you. Adusa knows there will be more battles ahead of us. The Doomcrag, for example. That will be one to tell our descendants about!
The Light shines upon you, champion.nnLet us give thanks for the power and guidance the Light provides us. May it illuminate us in the coming battle.
If I hear one more word about the Light, I'm going to throw this woman off the cliffs.nnLet's see how this Light of hers guides her on the way down.
Sebazi greets you, walker. Return when you have risen higher in the Fighters Guild.
Greetings, comrade. You must rise higher in the Fighters Guild to hear of the contracts I offer.
My contracts are for high-ranking members of the Fighters Guild. I cannot offer them to you yet.
Solid ground, beautiful surroundings, and a customer! What more could an Elf want?
I thought I heard the jingle of coins approaching. Care to make a purchase?
Soldiers  soldiers everywhere! They've turned our holy site into a slave camp.nnGet out of here while you still can!
Your sharp claws played no small part in the rise of the new Mane, walker. Be proud of your achievement and know you have the eternal thanks of the Khajiiti people.
My friend, you definitely bring the party. A new Mane, dead Daedra in the streets  I can't wait to draw steel with you again.
Blood and toil! The new Mane will do just fine  thanks to you.
Impressive work. Very impressive work indeed!
Many pray for the return of the Walking City. I seek to honor Falinesti's memory.

Your soul is restored. I can see its light within you. And you have saved your world from a great calamity. nnBut know this, mortal. The forces of Oblivion are legion, and the God of Schemes is but a single player in a complex battle for supremacy.
target:
La tua anima  ripristinata. Posso vederne la luce in te. E hai salvato il tuo mondo da una grande calamit.

Ma ascoltami bene mortale. Le forze di Oblivion sono una legione, e il Dio degli Intrighi non  che un semplice giocatore nella complessa battaglia per la supremazia.

source: You have done much for Shornhelm and Rivenspire. I hesitate to ask more of you, but I am concerned about Tainted-Heart. nnI sent one of my best Captains, Janeve, to track him and hopefully eliminate him.
I would simply like to escape this prison.
I have some beverages for sale, but do exercise caution. The penalties for spell-weaving while inebriated are  severe.
If you're hungry, I've got plenty of food here. All of my drinks have been paid for already, unfortunately.nnAll of them. But not the food, I've still got plenty of food.
Quite a battle! I suspect you'll need a few things before you set out again. nnMy stock's a bit sparse, but I still have a few items for sale.
You were leading the charge, eh? I can tell from the state of your armor  no offense. Why not buy a shiny new breastplate? Mara knows you've earned it!
It is difficult to find a blade worthy of Onsi's blessing outside the Alik'rbut I do have a few fine swords worth inspecting. Take a look.
Are you bound for southern Bangkorai? It's an unforgiving place, my friend. Why not have a bite before you leave?nnMight be your last good meal for a while.
I don't know about you, but laying siege to a fortress and killing a half-dozen Imperial soldiers makes me thirsty!
I would like to put him with the rest of the wounded, but it is too dangerous to move him. nnI fear it will not be long before Tu'whacca comes to claim him.
I thought the Garrison would be a little  I don't know  grander. What a dump. nnGlad I'm not one of the poor bastards who died for this place.
The battle for the Garrison has left us all weary, friend. These tents are sparsely furnished, but might afford you some rest and comfort. Shall I prepare one for you?
Just have to  walk it off.
Bah! Imperial cowards . Dogs and sons of dogs! They were right to pierce me with an arrow. Attacking me with a sword is  is an errand for fools.
Say what you want about the Imperials, but they make damn decent armor. It's a real shame we beat it all to pieces.
Well, I took down six or seven before I fell. nnIf I don't make it  and you see the priest speaking my eulogytell him I took fifteen. Mauloch loves a good tale.
Don't suppose you saw a loose squirrel foot around here ?
If you've come to mock or assault these soldiers, I suggest you move on.
The healers tell me they might be able to save my arm, but it'll never be the same.nnI say cut it off. By Leki's first lunge, I will not be weighed down by a useless limb.
I've not been north of the Garrison since I was a child. It is good to see a little green in the world.
Hmph. I guess this is Yagramak's last brawl. Damn shame. nnIf I see Mauloch, I'll put in a good word for you.
"Uuth! The stables need tending to!" "Uuth, the horses need feeding!" Mauloch's left tusk, I'm tempted to just eat the cursed beasts. nnWell, you here for a horse or what?
We lost too many Lion Guards taking back this pile of rocks. Far too many. nnIf Queen Arzhela's commitment to the Covenant falters after this, I'll march on Evermore myself.
Ah, the flame. It can bring comfort on a cold night, or reduce one's enemies to embers on the wind. nnForgive an old Elf his ramblings. You are welcome here among the Mages Guild.
Treat your mount well and it will never betray you.

These Wood Elves have a way with animalswhen they aren't trying to eat them, that is. I've had much success raising strong horses here. If it's a trustworthy steed you seek, you'll find no better than these.
We must arm ourselves, body and soul, for the obstacles ahead.nnTo do any less is an insult to those who have gone before us.
Peer review and cooperative research is the root of all arcane development.nnThe Psijics formed for just such a purpose, did you know that? And from them came we, the Mages Guild.
Come to do some Blacksmithing, eh? Well take up the tongs and get to it! nnI've got some goods here you might like. Fair prices too. Interested?
Traveling to Onsi's Breath? Do you wish to be enslaved?nnImperial soldiers will drag you into the mines if you're not careful. That's how they caught us.
Delectable sweets from the heart of Elsweyr, brought here at great expense!nnYou seem quite the discerning walker. Care to browse?
Delicious fruits from the Summerset arbors! Our grapes are the freshest this side of the Abecean!
This one makes soup. Tasty, fills your belly, keeps the plague away.
So many people have gone. Damn the plague! Who am I going to sell my delicious beverages to?nnBah, maybe it's time for me to move on.
He's always just, and always right. We'll scrub the town until it's bright.nnHe leads us down a golden path, away from filth and free from wrath.
The Order of St. Pelin thanks you for your aid here at the Garrison, traveler. We owe you a great debt.
Why are we even bothering to heal these flyblown Imperials? They're bound for the dungeon or the gallows. nnNothing but a waste of effort and supplies, if you ask me.
I'm terribly sorry, but the inn is closed for business.
I only listen to the fire.
A poultice to bind your wounds? Restorative elixirs to sooth your skin? <<1>> has it all!
My father is an influential tribune, you Covenant cur! He won't stand for his son being treated like  like chattel.
I lost my head back there. <<1>> says it's not cowardice if you're transformed into a bear by a town full of crazy people. I guess that's true.
You know, my time as a bear was somewhat liberating.nnDon't get me wrong, I'm glad you saved me, but it was fun while it lasted.
Not only did they kidnap us from our own homes, they tried to turn us into bloodfiends!
Any enemy of Montclair is a friend in my book. Thanks for releasing me.
My mother sent you, didn't she? I suppose it was only a matter of time.
What's Rivenspire coming to? Tales of vampires roaming the countryside. Bandits camped outside our town. The noble houses at war.nnAnd people want to know why I spend my days drinking in this inn!
What's the rush, my friend? I have a message for you.
Please, get me out of here. I saw what they did to the others. It is a fate worse than death.
I'm tired of trying to convince people to buy my wares. I'm just going to lay it out here and you can tell me if you see anything you want.nnYou should definitely buy something, though. I mean it.
The power we seek is close! I can feel it!
My father told me how you kept Mother's condition a secret. I  I thought you were better than that.nnI think you need to leave me alone until this is done, Verandis.
I'm sorry, I don't have room for more passengers.
And the thorn in my side returns. Your prince has accepted the gift I offered. He is a visionary. He sees beyond convention.nnBut what about you? Do you still question the value of my blessing?
I worry about Verandis. I know I shouldn't. He's brilliant and strong. But this whole thing with Montclair and the death of Lleraya. It has him all torn up inside.
Please, I just want to be alone right now. A dear friend didn't survive the occupation and  and I don't feel like talking about it.

She'll be fine. A little bruised up, but I pulled her away from those bloodfiends just in time. She hit her head pretty hard when she fell, though.nnBut that's nothing compared to what I'm going to do to Zeli when I get my hands on her!
I should probably be more frightened, what with fighting vampires and dodging blood curses and all. But damn if I'm not having fun!
These fiends can't withstand the might of House Dorell!nnThe vampire holds us back and wastes time! We're going to lose our advantage if we don't strike now.

The Ravenwatch. I do not trust them, and neither should you.nnThe Light speaks to the good in our hearts, to the life within us all. These vampires have neither good nor life within themonly hatred and evil.
The gate around the bend is unlocked now. I was surprised we didn't need one of those damn stones, but my lockpicks did the work.

For centuries I languished, trapped in the husk of that cold machine.nnMy dear Klathzgar; he only wanted us to be together. But once I was in the machine, I could no longer express my feelings. He may never have even realized I was conscious.
No need to worry, Adusa shall fight beside you. Almost as if you were one of the Ravenwatch. Almost.
Fifteen apologies, but my stock is khaj-dry. Dungy Imperials stole nearly everything I did not sell to the Knights. nnLuckily for you, Sanua-la is good at hiding things. Take a look.
Oh, just leave me alone!nnThe horses are all dead or carried off. I don't have anything left for you.nnI'm sorry, just go.
Usually, where there are soldiers there is drink and song. But these Knights of St. Pelin, they pray, and complain, and drink only water. nnYou are more fun, yes?
You have seen battle this day, yes? You must eat! What will you have? Greedy-Gut will put on the pot. It is not healthy to go to bed with an empty belly.
Hrmph. Not much left in stock, but if you see something you want, just let me know.
Mind your eyes, you knave. Do I look like some mangy Baandari hustler to you? In the guild we have rules about fraternization and lewd advances.
Hey there, friend. You're blocking my view of the fire. And the heat, too. Mind shifting a bit?

Before all this trouble, dinner conversation consisted of all manner of interesting subjects. Now all that anyone wants to talk about is Montclair and vampires.nnI just want life to get back to normal around here.
I'm going to write down what happened here. Tell all about the vampires and what not.nnI've never done anything like that, but how hard can it be? My book will make me wealthy, mark my words!
So many dead. So many wounded. nnThose Imperials may not wear animal skins, but at heart they're as bad as the Reachmen.
When I shipped out with these knights, I thought I'd be using my needle and thread to mend their tunics, not their wounds. Maybe you can use these goods for something a bit less  gory.

I never really thought this day would come. But it is what Verandis has been training me for.nnI guess we're really going in there. Into the Doomcrag. It's a bit scary, but I'm with Verandis to the end.
Welcome to the Sloshing Tankard! Please don't take the name literallyI'm sick to death of cleaning these floors.
I'm looking for someone, and she is not you. Leave me be.
I prefer the woods of <<1>>, but sometimes you go where the work takes you.
Dominion troops are stingy with coin, but you're an adventurer of refined tastes. Yes, one who appreciates quality wares.
Gravedigging doesn't pay too well, but there's never a shortage of work.
My player go stuck as a Guar. Help!
<There's a dead knight on the floor of this cell.>
Turn back now. And take the other mortals with you.nnYour flesh and blood is too fragile to withstand the power of the cursed relic.
I trust you have spoken to Tamrith and Dorell. Are the soldiers standing guard at the second portal?
This one enjoys the great tree, but truly appreciates those who gather in its shade.
The roads are dangerous. Be sure you're well stocked, friend.
I don't make many sales here. Come, take advantage of my misfortune. I need to move stock!
The Imperials' tricks are undone, but your stone city will still fall.nnThrough crows' eyes I spy your weak defenses. These lands belong to the Reach, and we will soon sweep through!
You can buy in Redfur. Or you can buy from me, to save some coin.
I'm glad you made it out of there. I wanted to ask you something before you leave, and I wanted to thank you once more for trusting me.
It is better for Verandis to tell you what will become of this place if the Remnant is destroyed. It is not for me to say.
Very funny I find it that you have come so far from your stone city.nnAre you a little lamb lost in the forest? I could have this crow shepherd you back home.

Look at this! We leave you alone for a bit and look what happens. The Countess, the Baron, even the little vampiredown and out for the count!nnWell, we're here now. So what are you waiting for? Go and kick Montclair's arse!
I'm not going to be a refugee forever. Life's too short to always be on the run.
Things are just so wretched these days. So much misery and filth  how are we supposed to live like this?
I never thought I'd get away from them! I've never run so fast in my life.
I'm not sure why, but it seemed like the Baron expected me to turn into some kind of vampire or something.
What  what have we done? I don't remember  ugh, what is that feeling? The Remnant's power must be reaching out to us.
Thank you for helping Verandis. For helping me.nnIf it hadn't been for you, well, I  I don't want to think about it.
Eselde is still breathing. That's a good sign, right? Of course it is!

Karnosis tries to tempt me with the Remnant's power. He knows just a taste of it would be enough to drive me over the edge.nnI can't face him like this  and he knows that. This is why I found you in Shornhelm.
House Ravenwatch is in your debt, Five-Claw.nnThank you.
<The multiple cuts on this Wood Elf's body appear to have come from an axe. His hands are calloused, and he wears the simple clothing of a tradesman.>
We need <<1>> alive. But if she runs, I'm putting an arrow through her ankle.
I don't guess you've run into a big, lumbering, brute of an Orc in your travels? Name's Storgh. Was a friend of mine, emphasis on the "was."nnI'm in a pile of trouble because of him.
It's never snowed this far south. I don't like this. I don't like this at all.
It's finally over, isn't it?nnWhat a terrible price we had to pay for this victory, though. A lot of good men and woman diedincluding Verandis. For a vampire, he turned out to be an honorable man.
Put a blade through the fanatic girl Zeli, then you go and blast two vampires straight into Oblivion.nnI'm impressed.
I heard what you did. Zeli  the vampires. You saved me.nnZeli was my most devout general, but even she wa ready to leave me in the name of the gods. I still can't hold that against her, even now.
The Countess continues to impress me. Even after all she went through, she's still holding firm to her faith.nnSomething to be said for that.
Please, they might come into the tent at any moment! The only chance I have is to get away while they aren't looking!
Being the only Orc in the order has its benefits, I suppose. Like  well . nnUhm. I'm sure I can come up with something. Eventually.
Divines forgive us. To be bested by a flock of leather-clad draftees  I almost hope this wound proves fatal. Better to die than to live with this choking shame.
Greetings. I have a wide selection of rare delicacies, if you are buying. Eggs from the legendary Wamasu, perhaps?
Do you see something you like?

You know the best thing about being a cook? You are never out of work. Sand storms, invasions,  occupations  but still, everyone needs to eat!nnSpeaking of which, you look famished. What can I get you?
Each new piece I unpack is bought immediately. Take a look, before everything is sold from under your very nose!
Look at your posture! Why do you hunch over so? nnWeighed down by your burdens, I'll wager. Luckily for you, I have many backpacks and satchels to sell.
Is a gold drake too much to ask from one as noble-looking as you?
The Grandeya is outside? I hope she finds the palace to her liking.
I can understand killing people, but trampling plants? It's inhuman!
Please tell my dear sister that I'm still waiting for that apology.
Please. Release me. I have to get back to Lorelia. I have to.
Please get me out of here! These Daedric cultists have been torturing me!
Even in the south, I can't seem to keep these old bones warm. Heh! Share my fire if you like, as long as you bring no trouble with you. This war is for younger men than I.
May the Light bathe and bless these people. May it guide their way and grant peace to those they have lost.
You shouldn't be talking to me like this out in the open. You're going to ruin my cover.
They dragged him into an alley, dragged him like a sack of horse feed! Then  oh, Tu'whacca help me.nnPray for my son, O wayfarer. And for me.
A city can be repaired. A heart will mend. But memories can never be erased.
I can no longer hold a weapon properly in these hands. Too many broken bones over the years.
My beautiful abomination! How you shine in the dark. nnBut heed a mother's warning.
Be wary, my friend. There are worse things than Imperials in the deep deserts of Hammerfell.
Some drink to forget. I drink to honor the fallen. Is that a crime?
This used to be a quiet place. And then we built walls. Suddenly our town became a city, ripe for plunder.
We had hoped you would come. We have watched you ever since you first emerged from Coldharbour. nnIf you were like other mortals you would soon turn. But you are unique.
I sent my husband to the market to see if  any vegetables are left.nnMeanwhile he's busy looking for produce at the bottom of every bottle at the inn.
Disturb me not. I pray for the dead.
I don't recall an appointment for this hour. Come back another time.

Tread carefully. An army is massing under our feet. I don't know how this happened.nnSomehow the Covenant has managed to fill this ruin with troops, and more seem to be arriving as if out of thin air.
I used to own a goat farm, but the smell got to me after a while.
My scales bake in this sun. I welcome the heat, but not the arid air.
Please tell my beloved brother that he has a better chance of squeezing fire salts out of an ice cube than he does of recieving an apology from me.
<This Khajiit mercenary was recently slain. There are no visible wounds on the front of his body.>
I tend to their child's education, but not much longer. She's already quite the lady.
If you're not here on Dominion business, I'll need you to move along. My time is precious.

Sorry, friend. If you're here for goods I'm afraid my supply has run dry. nnI was researching the kwama in Burroot mine, but I had to abandon everything. Even my research was left behind in that mine.
You have come seeking a steed, is it not so? I have given the Imperials naught but wheezing mares and half-dead nags. I have saved my best stock for you!

Hail, friend! I heard shouting about Imperials invading or somesuch. Is that true.? I  well  I don't really get out much.nnI've been busy, you see? Take a look at the fruits of my laborthe best enchantments in all of Bangkorai.
Just because I can't chop wood doesn't mean I can't hawk it! What do you need?
You want supplies? I have supplies. Fresh down the river today.

Let me guess  another sticky-fingered Mages Guild docent, yes? nnWell, we have labored long and long to assemble this collection. Tell your heretical masters if they want to plunder our cultural heritage, they'll have to look elsewhere.
According to this ledger, the Imperials ate more than half of our emergency food stores. Zehts tears. Looks like we'll be eating nothing but salted lamb until the next harvest.
So much to do to prepare for the Grandeya!  I have tried to keep the palace tidy in her absense, but those Imperials lived like wild animals.
Tell me you found something good, hero. It's not like the fate of Rivenspire is hanging in the balance or anything.
What're you looking at? Just 'cause I'm an Orc I can't enjoy the finer things? Go swallow sand!
I like the sound of the water. It's soothing. Plus, I get burned a lot. You know how it is. Get you something?
My blades are as good as any a fancy-dress High Elf would make. Try one, and see!
Who says High Elves are fragile? C'mon! Hit me! Or  just browse my wares. That's fine too.
Leather has so many uses, don't you think? Armor, especially useful. Try some on today!
I can tell you're smarter than most of the unwashed masses that pass by our stall. Try my armor  special, just for you!
I'm not sure how Montclair and his troops stand this armor. It's itchy and it smells like rotten mudcrab meat.

I find it hard to believe that Baron Dorell allowed a smuggler to dig a tunnel into his cityand right under his very nose!nnStill, it is our good fortune that this tunnel exists. The Light truly shines on those who need it.
Participating in this ceremony means you accept a dark fate. Will you proceed?
You're lucky my trap didn't work. We'd be sweeping your body parts up right now if it did.nnMy traps never fail  wonder what went wrong.
I thought my son might be hiding here, in his office. But all I found was his journal. You might as well have a look.
Letting a noble woman wander alone through a city full of vampires and bloodfiends. What was Skordo thinking?
<The soldier's throat is slit, and there are numerous bruises on her exposed skin.>

Verandis sent me to help. He said he needed to do some more research. I swear, the man's got his head buried in that old book you found in Lorkrata. But if it wasn't that, it'd be something else. He loves his research, that's for sure.
I still don't know why my trap didn't go off earlier. That's so strange.
Never heard a man cry so much in my entire life. Good thing my drink is almost empty. Would of hated to spill this wine. It's got quality. Rich people stuff.
Can't talk now. The pretty lady said it's sleepy time. Ssshhh!
Sit awhile if you wish. Speak your prayers. The wood will hear them. Y'ffre is there.
Are those two still arguing like kittens?nnMinshur finds it quite difficult to enjoy his book with them prattling on in this way.
Who are you? Where is my mother? She always brings the water to these falls!
I had hoped to save Lleraya from this fate. Or else, I should have been the one to end her campaign. I'm sorry this unfortunate task fell to you.
I've heard a lot about you. Finally, we meet in person.
Are you looking for the Captain? You will find her at the city's docks.nnShe said something about a 'great beauty' that she needed to see.
This ship  she's impressive. Maybe someone will give her to me.nn"Commodore Jimila." Ha! What do you think of that?
I'm surprised there's only one vessel. They must have been absolutely packed in here.
This is a dark elf vessel? It's so large!nnAnd very open. I think having this chance to study one will be good for us.
It smells like boiled cabbage and feet in here.nnPirates.
Ah, that look. So familiar. Your mouth is dry, your blood boils in your veins, while your skin turns cold as ice. nnYour body does not accept the blessing for what it is. It resists.
The itching  it just won't stop!

I upheld the promise I made on the boat out there.nnBumnog and the others are resting up, but they arrived a short time ago with your companions. My friend here has already sent one boat out to give them passage.
Wood Elves  hmph. I serve my potions in the finest glass, and what do they do? They pour the tonics into their filthy deer bladders then cast the bottles aside! nnSavages!
These Wood Elves have scads of leather, but bolts of fabric are few and far between. Makes a career in clothing quite an ordeal, let me tell you.
I pity these High Elves tramping about in their metal pants. Leather and cloth are so much finer, don't you think? Of course you do.nnIs there anything I can help you with?
I get a lot of strange looks for my choice in armor. It requires some talent to imbue ebony with Daedric essence, you know.nnI consider it a point of pride. A mark of my trade, if you will.
The raw destructive power imbued in a staff of quality is enough to make a difference on any battlefield.nnImagine: An entire army hurling bolts and blankets of fire, frost, or lightning. Majestic.
Nobody makes bows like the Bosmer!nnNo, really. Nobody does. Everyone else cuts down trees, it's insane.
Sorry, friend. I have no time to chat. One of my subordinates recently came across something very interesting. Something that could make our time in this dreadful land worthwhile.
If you've come to work wood, I'd keep your wits about you. The locals stage protests now and again.nnIt's bizarre, but you get used to it.
Please, get me out of here! I've changed! Please!
You! You did this to me! nnSai Sahan, my love  let me out, would you? I promise you an eternity of delights
Since we've had more high elves and khajiit around, the food has gotten much more varied in Elden Root.
The spirits of the dead require as much soothing as wounded soldiers on a battlefield.
What do you want with this old woman?
My heart goes out to Arzhela. I admire her strength in shouldering so much responsibility in the wake of so much tragedy.nnI look forward to seeing King Eamond and the children avenged.
I'll tell ya, these Khajiit are tough on fabric. Mending claw-marks is a full-time job, but I still sell some goods on the side. Have a look.
This one has many accounts to settle before the Moons rise and fall. What do you need?
You can trust this one implicitly. Or, if you do not trust her, trust the guards and their blades. What can I do for you?
We may be far from the front, soldier, but there's still much to do. Now, report!
I can tell, you've got brains and smarts both. Smarts enough to buy from me! So what do you need?
I've been in more fights than most, comrade. What can I teach you about the fine art of fisticuffs?
Tell me what you're here to learn! My northern magic may be too much for you, but if you fail to learn it shall not me on me!
Greetings, walker! Rabamak has many spotless goods. You will come and look, yes?
If you want a horse, then we have something to talk about. If you want gossip, find the tavern.
I've got all manner of guild goods here, readily available. Especially to one such as you.
I have a delicate spell matrix in progress here. So please, speak quickly. I don't want to lose all this work.
Many and many are the inner mysteries of Alchemy. If you seek to learn more, you are speaking with the right woman.
Do not be fooled by my eggbrother's words. My goods are just as moist as his.
Don't mind my friend. She's always looking for an excuse to tear down <<1>>.
<<1>> wasn't garrisoned at <<2>> to protect it. The Dominion put her there to keep a boot beside our necks.
<<1>> means well, this one is certain.nnPerhaps "certain" is too a strong word.
I try to share my love of culture with friends. Some take to it better than others.
I have no idea where the funds for these projects are going to come from, but it's my responsibility to find that funding.nnPerhaps I should reopen my family's salt mine.
I ensure the reception and distribution of all Thalmor-requisitioned goods here in Elden Root.nnIf you don't mind, I must be about the day's inspections.

I am doing my very best to reconcile the diverse culinary preferences of the Dominion.nnThe Khajiit prefer their food with moon-sugar, which doesn't respond well to the aging in Wood Elf meats. High Elves, of course, prefer neither. Impossible!
Oh, hello. I was just napping.nnIt's just the thing after a stout meal and a pitcher of warm jagga  a good nap.
You want to know what happened to Falinesti? The real truth is, nobody has a clue!
Every Wood Elf thinks they have some special claim on the walking city of Falinesti. They don't, or they'd know where it went!
Such a shame, how the Argonians were treated. My friend has lived in <<1>> for decades. Will the Dominion think her a spy, too?
One grows used to the mistrust and suspicion, outside of the Black Marsh. I've learned to smile with my mouth closed. That usually helps.
Long as you haven't come to take my things, you're welcome to loiter in my home for a bit.nnI'm a touch busy, I'm afraid. Probably won't make the best company.
This one moves things into and out of the vault for Ahmussa. Speak to her for any banking business you have.nnShe keeps the records and logs. This one  he mostly forgets.

My favorite thing about the Elden Tree is the gardens. They're cultivated, but also wild. The same plants you see elsewhere in <<1>>, but here kept safe from harm and disease.nnJust like pets. Except  plants. Plant pets?

I used to live down in the Middens. It's a hard place to stop living once you startonce you're down it's hard to get back up, right?nnSo, once I came into some money I got out of there. I can't go back. I just wish I could have brought my friends.
The Thalmor asked me to do something with this plaza space. Ideally, I would use it for something that would appeal to the entire Dominion. Perhaps a monument?nnOr a tea house! I would prefer that.
I've never experienced a carnival before. I think I need a moment to just appreciate it all. With all of the darkness in the world, it's nice to have something like this.
Freedom. Freedom at last! And Uela dead. Dead!

Zeht's tears, what a mess. It's a miracle that these laborers were even able to lift a pick, let alone meet Imperial Legionnaires in battle. nnWithout your help the losses would have been  catastrophic. You have our thanks.

Well these Imperial louts weren't paid much, I can tell ya that. I've been rooting through their pockets for hours and all I've found is a wad of lint, a handful of drakes, and a half-eaten wedge of cheese.

That runt on the left was called Fibias  the one on the right was named Marano. I always favored a sword in my old dog-fighting daysbut I gotta tell ya, thumping those slavers to death with a mining pick was pretty damned satisfying.
Honor to you, stranger. You have my thanks for helping us escape, but I urge you to step away from these prisoners.
Greetings, warrior of the Dominion. Bask in the presence of this revered artifact.
You are welcome here, soldier. Even more so if you've come to defend our Elder Scroll.
Gaze upon the Elder Scroll if you must, but do not linger unless you are here to defend it.
I was worried for a moment there. I gave you the antidote but then you passed out. I thought I mixed it wrong!
My brother Brendar went into the barrow last night and still hasn't returned. Do you think he's okay?
Thank Kyne someone came. I thought I'd die down here. I was surprised I even woke up at all. Did my sister send you to find me?
That mine was like a prison  worse than a prison. If I had my way, we'd throw those Imperials' bodies down the main shaft with a heap of firesalts and blow the whole damned thing to Oblivion.
A small bottle of wine, a pair of boots, and some pickled hoarvor for the road  not so much to fret over, yes? So why the stockade? This one is just going to steal them back tomorrow, no?
The Wood Elves  aheh  they do not eat plants, yes? So where do they get their ale? Fermented milk!nnThey call it "jagga," yes? Hearty, sweet, and it goes down smoothly! <<1>> could drink forever!
If the prices of moon-sugar were not so high, there is so much more this one could make. As it is, we must make do with what the Bosmer provide.
Yes? Are you here for supplies?
You. You must reach my brother.
You  you're not one of these cultists. Get me out of here.
My friend, I'm so glad to see you!
Thank you again. I made sure to put myself in harm's way to protect my little brother. Unfortunately, he learned nothing and thinks I caused us to get caught. nnAh, youth.
My  my friend. I never thought to see you again. Please, end me. Put me out of my misery one more time.
Ah  my brother's keeper. Here to taunt me in death as you did in life?
Count Verandis is a kind and caring master. I am grateful for everything he's done for me.
This business about the Covenant invasion makes you want to crawl in a hole and drink, don't it?
Arms for the war effort? I give you a special price. I wouldn't want you to think I profit from misfortune.
Some put faith in the Divines, some put faith in the Tribunal. Me? I put faith in my armor is stronger than your sword.
Yes, I make armor. It's nothing glamorous. Lots of sweat, lots of hard work. If you need supplies, I sell them.
A little bit of this, a little bit of that. And maybe some of  no that's perfect.nnAlchemy is a delicate but rewarding art.

You spend a lot of time thinking about weapons? About armor? Plenty do. They spend good coin on what they take into battle. But then they don't give a second look to the enchanter.nnMight as well charge into battle naked, I say.
The way I see it, the world has a certain hierarchy. You've got your kings, your generals, and your blacksmiths. After all, what's a king or a general without a good weapon?
Have something you need to keep safe? This is the place. Best service in Tamriel, too.
I won't pretend it's the best stock in Tamriel, but I'd trust my life to it, and you'll get no better guarantee anywhere.
Crafting warm, sturdy clothing is the most important job on the island. Think you're up to it? I've got a few goods you might like. nnTake a look.
Times like these, it pays to know the art of alchemy. Reagents are more dangerous to acquire, sure, but everyone wants potions. Very profitable.
Pains me to think of leaving this place behind. But maybe it's time I did. The danger is too great.
Take a load off. Our banks are the most secure places in all Tamriel. We pride ourselves on our services.
<The horse eyes you nervously as if he's expecting to be beaten.>
We're about to run a shipment back to Wayrest if you'd like to come aboard.
I wanted to show the guard that I appreciate all they do for us. After giving it some thought, I decided to shore up their defenses instead.
Why have we been visited with these disasters? Sometimes it feels like all of Rivenspire has been cursed.
I'm writing a letter to my sister. Let her know what's been happening here in Rivenspire. Sometimes the town criers blow everything out of proportion.
Now is not a good time, friend. I have a lot of thinking I need to do.
My Lord  my Count  Your Highness? Oh, who cares? We don't need to stand on ceremony. Not us!nnMe and good old Verandis, showing the world how vampires are supposed to behave .
The people in this town aren't very welcoming.
How may I be of assistance?
I keep hoping to see my wife or a few others from Crestshade coming this way.  I promised my wife I would not go back to town. I wish I hadn't made such a promise.

Holding down the fort while you have all the fun? Remind me again why I volunteered for this mission.nnWell, don't get your robes in a bunch. I'll keep the way out clear of skeletons until you get back.
Frost trolls, in <<1>>? The world has gone mad.
The following conversation will start an actionlist, when complete.
I am praying for strength and courage. I should not be hiding from those foul creatures. Arkay watches over me, surely.
In the springtime so fair, nthe ladies sow the seed.nWhen harvest rolls around,nI'm still drinking mead .
My father was working here during Ranser's War. He disappeared and we never heard from him again.nnI've been looking forward to meeting this man Althen for a long time.
Another one, eh? Come to gawk at Titus the Mad?nnWell, I'm not insane, no matter what you may have heard. And I might be your only hope to defeat the Anka-Ra.
By the Eight  who did this? What happened to my people?
"Alchemist," they call me. My dear traveler, I am no mere alchemistI'm a miracle worker!nnWhat do you need?
I'm positively enchanted to make your acquaintance. Ha! Get it? I  oh, never mind.nnWhat do you need today?
It's dangerous out there. Goblins, pirates, and beasts! What I've got here will keep you safe.
Protect yourself! The armor I sell will keep your pretty skin intact.
Don't let these meat-heads get to you. A good set of lightweight armor is worth every bit of effort you put into it.
There's no steel better than Orc steel. What more do you need to know?
Come to try your hand at some alchemy? I started out as a brewer. Worked great for a while. But when my beer started turning people into mudcrabs, I figured it was time for a change.
Think you're strong now? Give enchanting a try. A few soul gems and a bit of elbow grease is all it takes. You'll be arm-wrestling trolls in no time!
Without a well-crafted, carefully maintained weapon, you can end up as a meal for some wild animal. Or worse. All sorts of dangerous things out there, my friend.
You can always buy armor, of course. But wearing pieces you made yourself will give you more confidence.

Pointed metal pieces, or iron casings are all well and good, I suppose, for your common adventurer. But understanding the mysteries of enchantments? That is for the refined, well-traveled and intelligent adventurer.
I love mixing different reagents, trying different things. Mind you, I've singed my fur a time or two with some unexpected results, but alchemy is for the adventurous, I always say.
Perhaps I deserve this. The death, the suffering. I am to blame for this disaster.nnLock me up and throw away the key. I must pay for these crimes.

Awake! The long eons of silence have finally come to an end.nnI speak in the coarse tongue of our servants so that you may understand. Knowledge is the key that opens this door, and none may pass who have not gained knowledge.
The shrines are under attack. They maintain the temple barrier. If they fall, so too will the temple.nnThe attacking gargoyles contain star shards. Use those star shards to empower the shrines.
Shor's bones, look at those sunken cheeks! You need a good meal and fast. What can I get you?

Kyne curse those Daggers! They burned everything. Ten years ago I would have killed the lot of them before they stepped off the boat. Old agebah! If you run into Holgunn, tell him to split an Orc at the shoulder for old Vestalgar.
Bah! Off with you, troll bait! You're ruining the show!
Honor to you, sera. Welcome to the Watch House Inn. Those netch-brained Daggers won't trouble you hereI hope. How can I help you?
I'm just going to ignore our farmyard neighbors at present and simply go on about guild business. The business of selling magical paraphernalia.
As with all creatures, time brings change, and with change, wisdom.nnThe Mages Guild grew from the Psijjics, often held as the wisest of mages. Lord Sotha would grant them room to grow.
I'd be happy to help with anything you may need.nnAs long as it's mystical, and you're paying.
Not every Orc wants to wield a heavy mace or hammer. Some of us prefer the use of staves and other magic implements.
Is there anything this humble perquisitor can get for you? Everything is ours, I swear. We would never knowingly distribute the temple's relics.
Bah! I can't take this waiting any longer! If our regiment doesn't march on Cyrodiil soon, I'm going to rent a mule and ride there myself.
Out traveling and exploring, are you? Let any evil-doer or riled up creature know you mean business with a finely-crafted and sharp blade!
We've been waiting on a troop of reservists for days now. At this rate the war for Cyrodiil will be over before we even get there.
You look dry, my friend. Fancy a drink?
I thought for sure that dropping a mountain on top of you would turn you into a fine paste. Not sure how you got out of there, but I'm glad I was wrong.
I'm glad the Light saw fit to guide you back to us, my friend. If not for you and Verandis, we all would have died in there.nnThe Count's name will be remembered. I promise you that.
Got sturdy shields and long-range weapons. Safety first right?
YOU WANT EVENT?! YEAH! EVENT GO TIME! HOTDOGS!
Have you come looking for a steed, friend? Fallen knights mean riderless horses! Misfortune for them means savings for you! Have a look at my stock.
My mounts are bred strong to cross mountainous terrain. The Gold Coast Trading Company is one of my best customers. I'm also happy to take care of your animal, for a fair price.
Welcome, friend! Don't believe my sister, over at Skywatch. I breed the best mares on the island. Just you see.
I left my family back in Windhelm to come here. I hope I don't live to regret it.
My horses are beauties! Look how they hold their heads up high.nnI treat my horses well, whether they belong to me or if they just happen to rent a stall in my stables.
Hello. How may I be of service?
These are troubled times. Let me know how I can help.
What? Haven't you ever seen a Wood Elf before? I know I'm still learning my trade, but the armor I craft isn't half bad.nnFor a Wood Elf.
If you're heading into the White, you'll need some strong armorheavier the better! nnJust shout if you see anything you like.
It's good you've arrived. You should talk to Hara, if you haven't already.
It's strange. The Star-Gazers have been around in some form or another for a very long time. But no one really knows how they started.
I've spent so much time on the water, it is dry land that seems to pitch beneath my feet.nnAll a matter of perspective anyway, is it not?
These beasts belong to the embassy staff. They are not for sale. So don't ask.nnOne of those little Bosmer creatures sells horses outside of the big tree. Assuming you can even afford one.
These docks aren't all they once were.
I'm pretty good with knives. I know how to fillet fish, butcher livestock. I can gut an enemy on the battlefield too, if I need to. But honestly, I prefer to cook.
You came through the valley and you still have your wits about you? I'll drink to that.nnDrinking's about all there's left.
By my sword, I will end this. Divines give me strength. Warrior give me strength. Ysmir give me strength!
Divines help us, this isn't how it was supposed to end. We were supposed to die gloriously, not trapped in a Mead Hall, drowning in our cups.
The false Ysmir has been overthrown! The true Ysmir has returned! Nothing can protect you! The Age of Order has ended. The Age of Chaos has begun!
I'd be careful if you go in there to talk to poor Nuhran. He's  twisted.nnWhatever's happened to him, I  I just don't know.
How many friends do you have?
Oh, I'm afraid you'll have to wait your turn, my lovely.
Please, let me repair your broken gear!
They built that fort for a reason, friend. Why not buy some protection of your own?

I regret I can offer you no hospitality today. I lost my husband to the sea, and now I am alone and without so much as a half-gold piece to my name.nnBut if you care to stay and talk awhile, I would be grateful. My days and nights are so lonely now.
<This soldier appears to have been killed recently, but his limbs are stiff and cold to the touch,  and the blood is frozen in his veins.>
You look a little dry, stranger. What can I get you?
Hands to yourself or I chopI mean, please refrain from touching anything. Please.

Well met! Welcome to the Dead Wolf Inn! Not the most flattering name, I know. But at least you needn't worry about being mauled, right? Because the wolf is dead, you see . Oh dear, that sounds awful. Let's just start over. nnHow can I help you?
This adventure is over, but another one awaits. Would you like to return to Raid Heaven and claim your rewards?

The Anka-Ra seem to be coming from burial sites like this one around Craglorn. nnThere is a ritual that can consecrate this ground for a time and keep the Anka-Ra from rising, but you must protect me while I perform it.

The Anka-Ra seem to be coming from burial sites like this one around Craglorn. nnThere is a ritual that can consecrate this ground for a time and keep the Anka-Ra from rising, but you must protect me while I perform it.
You are a friend of the queen, yes? Hazazi recognizes you from the sketch. Though this one thinks it may not do you much justice.

Sometimes I can't even hear myself think, what with all the hustle and bustle at the temple. I can't expect the Three to hear us through all that noise and bother, so I came out here to pray for an end to all of Deshaan's troubles.
Plenty of dangerous folk out there on the moors. The trick is to be the most dangerous one. I've got the tools if you've got the talent. Take a look.
Come to look at my knives? Well, be careful. These aren't for buttering your bread.
The squalls haven't been kind so my stock's a little thin. But what I've got is fresh as milk and roses!
Welcome to the Redfur Fighters Guild. Such as it is.nnI suppose you'd like to take a look at my stock?
Ah, you come to see what is on offer in Redfur. Even here, this one can procure useful things for mages. Have a look.
My eyes are his eyes. My blood is his ink.nnMy eyes are his eyes. My blood is his ink.
We boast a unique Mages Guild hall, nestled here in the great tree.
Hey! Hey you . Don't tell my boss I'm here. I'm supposed to  I don't remember what I'm supposed to do. Damn. I hope it wasn't important.
Poor, poor Monster. You didn't deserve this. It should have been me. I've had more than enough time, and you were always so strong and healthy.

There's a rumor going around that the most recent grand melee was won by an unarmed and unarmored Imperial! nnHard to believe. Especially when others add that he also appeared seemingly out of nowhere. Sounds like magical trickery to me.

Welcome to the arena of Rahni'Za, initiate. This is a trial of stamina, strength, and teamwork. nnWhen you are ready to put your discipline to the test, give the command. Then I will commence the trial.

I did not think any beating heart would ever undertake these trials again. And you say you have come to avenge us? Hmm.nnI would help you, if I could. If these arms were more flesh than spirit. If I could grip steel and strike at the betrayer.
I never dreamed that our avenger would arrive so soon. Thank you for defeating the betrayer. There's no saving the Sword-Disciples, but at least their spirits may find rest.
The path to the final trial lies below. You will need to find the True Path through the darkness. It will lead you to Abelazar the betrayer. nnIf you would avenge us, this is the path you must take.
Abelazar bested the Trial of Air like it was nothing. Like he had been born a bird and had spent his whole life flying.nnWe should have seen through him then.

The story of the Wilderking has come to an end, and the story of the Wilderqueen has begun. nnFew Bosmer realize how fragile their relationship with the Valenwood really is, but you and I know. We've seen the sacrifice required to preserve it.
Glad to see a friendly face. I've a few goods and extra cots prepared if you're in need of some rest. Just have a care walking around the injured.
I'm in this for the profit!
I truly enjoy my work. Creating graceful armor that protects you completely? It's very satisfying.
I suppose you wish to see my fine gems? I don't stint on the quality of my stock. Prepare to be impressed.
You carry many things. Small things, bigger things? You need to put them in something, yes?nnPunirai's Put-ins. Bags, to put things in!
Listen closely. You were right to help Titus. Had Tarish-Zi been able to gather his forces, there would have been nothing you could do to stop them.
Have a look at my woven creations. There is no reason one can't look good while protected by light armor.
Sure, sure. steel and iron are fine for armor  if you want to make sure your enemies know you're nearby.nnBut leathers, tanned and treated  that's for those of us who prefer a more subtle approach.
I've been doing decent amount of business out here. Warriors and soldiers like to take care of their armor, that's a fact.
The intense heat of the forge, the power in shaping metals for weapons It's a craft that makes you feel strong and alive. nnNot an easy mistress, though.
The alchemist's suppressant works wonders. I may not be cured, but I certainly feel much, much better.
Sometimes soup really is the best medicine. Hot, tasty, and made with your own two hands! Well, not your hands. That would be disgusting.
You look a little parched, friend. Perhaps I can assist you with that.
I do not live here, nor do I intend to remain here.nnYour purchases will help ensure my future relocation to somewhere more magical.
Looking to wet your whiskers? This one thinks you've come to the right place.
It's been difficult getting everything I usually stock, but so far I've managed. What I lack in selection, I make up for in bulk. So what can I get you?
No, I'm not worried. This will pass. Trouble comes and trouble goes. It's the way of the world.
Well met, traveler. Looking to resupply?
We're trying to clear as much room as we can for the refugees from Elinhir. I hear the destruction out that way is pretty bad.
You look like you could use a strong drink. I know I could.
My food was voted "least likely to cause a stomach ache" in a region-wide cooking competition. Lucky for you!
There's a lot of uncertainty in Belkarth these days, but you can rest assured we'll take good care of your valuables here.
The Orcs of the Dragontail Mountains were powerful allies in the fight against the Daedra, but now something's driving them from their lands and into ours.
The Fighters Guild only recently arrived in Belkarth. We're here to help with the Celestial threat.

The Mages Guild isn't very popular here in Craglorn. The last time we were here, our representative was tied to the back of a horse and run out of Elinhir. And that was merciful compared to what happened to the others.
I first came here because of my brother, Oscar. I had to make sure he stayed out of trouble.
We didn't ask the Pact to come to our sacred refuge.
Few remember the old ways or the Three Old Gods. But we try. We try.
It  won't be long now. Even without the flowers, I'm glad we came. Being in this place  with Hartmin  this is how I want my final moments to be.
They  they handed me over to the Nereids. My own people!nnA sacrifice to Shada they called it. My life  I could feel it slipping away. I don't know how much longer I could have lasted.
You are not Yokudan. You are their enemy. nnWhy are you here? How are you here?
My horn  have you seen my horn? The Yokudan army is coming, and I don't have my horn. How am I supposed to signal the others?nnIt must be around here somewhere.
Stars above, is that thunder, or the Yokudan army I hear? Where's my lucky mug? It figures we'd come under attack, and I'd lose my mug.
How am I supposed to use this book of schematics Alexam gave me without my hammer?nnI bet I left it in the tavern again. I swear, it's the last time. By the heavens, I'm never drinking again.
What's taking that blacksmith so long with that book? I need those schematics back so I can finish the fortifications before I meet Juliana.nnOh, I hope she hasn't been waiting too long.
It's about time! We sent a runner to Belkarth days ago!nnWaityou're not the reinforcements we requested, are you? Damn it.

He never came for me. I waited here for him when the Yokudans attacked. I killed them until they overpowered me and still I kept fighting, kept hoping.nnWhy did he not come for me? We should have died together.
I sell armor crafted by the finest smiths in High Rock, Skyrim, and Hammerfell. Only the strongest plate and mail in my shop, that's for sure.
Leather from Valenwood, metalwork from Skyrim, produced by the best crafters in Hammerfell.
Yahiri's wares are sleek-fit and stitched to perfection. And do not worryall my fabrics are troll-tested, so you can count on both style and safety, yes?
With all the mages here in Craglorn, you'd think business would be better.
I have traveled to many places, seen many strange things. The discerning shopper appreciates my wares.
Don't bother haggling. I can't control the prices. Supply and demand, you see.

My wife told me that I need to move more product, so I took the shields out of a crate and put them in a barrel. I don't know how that's supposed to help our business, but she's always been the brains in the family.
They say the caves of Craglorn contain plants that don't grow anywhere else. I wouldn't recommend looking for them, though. Much too dangerous.
Come for enchantments? By Tava's red feathers, you'll not find better.

Working a huge stone forge on the second floor of a broken-down warehouse is dangerous, sure, but the gold's too good to pass up.nnCan I helpwait. Did you hear a creak? Please tell me you didn't hear a creak.
Less fashion, more functionthat's my motto. Don't get me wrong. I clean up all right. But a pretty shirt isn't worth a damn on a dead man.
Sometimes I wonder what I'm doing with my life. My father wanted me to become a banker in Daggerfall. Instead, I'm in the middle of nowhere, selling backpacks to people with more armor than sense.
The Mages Guild must guide the people of Craglorn through this difficult time. We will accept any aid offered.
You've picked a fine day to visit! Take your time, browse around.
That's the third caravan this week. Besides what's happening at Elinhir and the giant crater outside, we'll be out of business by the end of the year.
It may just be my imagination, but it feels cold and dark now that the stars have fallen from the sky.
I worry about Hara. She's been working so hard since the Celestials appeared. I tell her she'll wear herself out, but she doesn't listen.
This one roams, for this one knows: Those who themselves roam often have needs.nnAnd Mulabez, he satisfies these needs, yes?
What can I do for you? It pays to store your items in a bank vault, no matter what's happening in town.
Shausa meets many travelers upon the road, and of all of them she asks one question.nnDo you need anything?
It's a hard life, traveling with your wares. I imagine that is why few do it.
I love traveling this part of Valenwood. It's very different from the forests of Summerset, which I find both refreshing and pleasant.nnI often run across individuals in need of supplies, as well.
Don't mind me! Just your average traveling peddler of sundries, I swear.nnI can prove it, too! Have a look at my wares, you'll see.

This one believes that each piece of wood can have only one ideal use. As a woodworker, Splinter-Paws must find this ideal use. Only then can he create a useful object, and if it is the will of Jone and Jode, an object of lasting beauty.
I stock only the freshest herbs and the finest spices. Let me know if you see anything you like.
Quality leather goods here, at honest prices!
I have many quality items crafted of the finest woods in all of Tamriel. Would you like to peruse my inventory?
Mine is an honest profession. I'll take your measurements anew every time I see you. The rest of the world will size you up once and expect you to fit those measurements forever.
This one thinks you have come to make a deposit, yes?
Well met, friend. Are you interested in the study of Alchemy?
Pulemu welcomes you, honored guest, and hopes she can be of service to you.
Trading runs in my family, though I wish I had chosen a warmer climate to ply my trade. nnStill, business is good when there are soldiers camped nearby.
I'm rather enjoying my stay in Fort Amol. Not every town I bring my wares to is so accommodating.  Deldwine's Inn is very nice and there are lots of friendly soldiers.
I know this is a bit of a rustic set-up, but I promise you, my armor is as good as any you will find in Windhelm.
Will you say a prayer for those who have fallen behind the walls of Rahni'Za, the great school of blades?nnFor the great Sword-Disciples, who have been reduced to mindless thralls?
Someone around here needs to make sure work gets donegoods get sold. And it's usually me. Did you want to see my stock?
A camp full of soldiers. Mostly Nord soldiers too. Pretty much the ideal situation for a brewer.
Please leave me be. I'm lost in thought.
I only sell the finest of wares.
This drink really hits the spot.
You mean there's not going to be a hostage exchange? nnDirt-eating liars! We'll kill you all and feed your remains to the seagulls!
Gods' mercy  what's going on? Why don't you just kill me ? To let me linger like this  it's wrong!nnWait. You're not one of them, are you? Where in Oblivion am I? Who  who are you?
This timber does not speak as the Hist does, but it does have a voice. Each branch begs for purposefor meaning. You need only listen.
Don't have many ingredients to work with here in Coldharbour. Ones that won't kill you I mean. But you're welcome to look over what I've got.
Even with the alchemists camped here in the mill, I can still get plenty done.nnSpeaking of, need anything?
I handle the woodworking for the village heremost of it anyway. Anything I can help you with?
Bokeeus whispers secrets to the wood. Our craft requires trust as much as a steady hand, yes?
There's been a shift. Since the forming of the Pact. Dunmer are using more and more wood, less and less bone. I molded bone once. Things change.
Getting your hands on proper woodworking materials in this swamp can be a nightmare.nnThat's why I'm here.
You need something? If not, I've got wood to cut.
Strange to see Nereids in here. It's like they're taunting me, but as soon as I get near, they dive beneath the water.nnThey must have played a role in the curse that's on this place. But what?

I can't tell you how relieved I am to find you. I'm Ibrulaa friend of the Star-Gazers.nnI'm trying to gain entry to this temple, but the Celestial Warrior's army of Anka-Ra have sealed the door. I need help to get past them and disable the seals.
Have you seen an old Redguard woman around here? A Star-Gazer, dressed in the garb of our order?nnWe've been searching for days. Please tell me you've seen her.

That's the second time I've seen a spirit like that. It's like they're all locked in time, on the day that the Yokudans invaded the city.nnIf theses priestesses were trying to protect the goblets from the Yokudans, that confirms their importance.
