Wanna know a secret? I'm a terrible woodworker. Can't plane a board to save my life. But you know what they say. Those who can, do; those who can't, sell!
This one assures younone of the wood here violates the Green Pact.nnIf it did, we would not hear the end of it.
Every port needs a gifted woodworkerespecially if it's a proper naval yard. There's always work to be done, so let's make this quick, eh?
We have less trees here in the Reaper's March than many other places, so a fine carpenter is a rare and cherished thing. This one, he is a fine carpenter. nnWhat do you need?
Of course I am distressed over the recent incursion of daedra here in Dune. But looking on the bright side, it is certainly going to increase demand for my services.
Yeah, I work with this lot of rowdy nords. It's a struggle, but an artist can't always pick where their materials come from, y'know? nnAnyway, what can I get you?
If I'm understanding this right, this chamber is where most of the healing took place. The Nedes considered this area their holy place, their temple.
You almost feel bad for the Guardians, knowing that they were once alive. Before they try and kill you that is. nnIt looks like we found one of the goblets, at least.
Sanabi's stock is not the finest, but you cannot expect quality in a place such as this. We work with what we have.
Move along. I've got some serious guarding to do.

The crypts. There's a lot of ugly rumors about the Nedes and their dead. Most of it written by their conquerers after the fact, of course.nnStill, I'd be ready to face the restless dead. It wouldn't be the strangest thing I've seen in this place.

I know the Yokudans were powerful, but for these people to call this curse on themselves to stop them?nnIt's either the bravest thing I've ever heard of or the dumbest. Was sacrificing an entire city worth it?
A well-made and carefully maintained weapon made from treated wood can last a lifetime. Or two!
I left the Grahtwood, because I have the gift of working with wood. Not a skill prized by many of my people.
It looks like the goblins tried to break into the city and  couldn't.nnIn fact, it looks like the Yokudans tried the same thing hundreds of years ago.
The city may fall, but the goblets must be saved. So says Shada.nnThe Yokudans will destroy everything if they gain this power.

When I first saw this room, warded by spouts of water, I thought it would be important. nnNow, I'm certain. The Water of Life is through here. We're so close. My son will have his cure soon. Do you have the goblets?
Please, do come in. Here at the Parchment and Horn, we do our best to ensure a relaxing stay for any journey to Marbruk. Even yours.
I love the feel of smooth planks and the smell of sawdust. Making beautiful, durable wooden weapons is a useful skill to have.
I never expected to end up in a place like this, let alone selling foodstuffs to any wanderer who passes by. Still, I like to be useful.
Bah. The teeth on these saws are flatter than mine!nnAh, carpentry  It's a labor of love. Unrequited I'm afraid. What can I get you?
Fresh flavors! Exotic spices! A queen's bounty of flavor for the discerning cook! Come, have a look!
Woodworking takes patience, discipline, and absolutely everything I have for sale! Buy now because supplies are limited.
I wasn't sure if I would be able to ply my trade in Grahtwood, given how touchy some Wood Elves are about their trees. So far so good.
I hate it here. I'd rather do my tailoring somewhere warmer and safer. Less remote.
Can I interest you in anything?

Only the most skilled warriors earn the right to study under the Sword-Disciples of Rahni'Za.nnThe Trial of Fire is the test that separates the worthy from the unworthy . With its completion, you begin your first step into our school.
Wooden wonders for sale. This is what I sell.nnYou will buy them, of course.
Trust me when I tell you that none but an Argonian truly knows quality leather or hide. We live it, you know?
I weave fabrics while I meditate.nnI seem to do a great deal of meditationafter all, I have so many garments to sell!
Bark-Scraper does not understand this hate for fine woodcraft here in Elden Root. But then, the little walkers do many things that make no sense.

Initiates often tested their might against the most ferocious beasts of the pits. It was a means of improving strength and teamwork before facing the more arduous trials.nnThe betrayer skipped this trial in his hurry to destroy us.
The forests and fields of Greenshade are a treasure trove ingredients and foodstuffs. I forage and explore and always find something interesting.
Care to lighten my load? It's a long way to where I'm going.
I shouldn't have bought so much stock. Care to trade? I could use a lighter pack, and I'll give you a fair price!
The road is long. Best stock up while you can, eh? Never know when you'll have another chance!
I'd shake your hand but, y'know  wood sap. nnWhat can I get you?
Most Nords don't really appreciate the gift of magic or what I do.nnIncluding me. I'd rather be a lumberjack.
You've come seeking power. I can see it in your eyes. Look on my wares. I'm sure you'll find what you're looking for.
Channeling arcane power is an art. You'll need soul gems if you wish to perfect it.
Interested in creating your own plane meld?nn Sorry. Bad joke.
Do you see something you like?
Some of the other mages do not care for such rustic quarters, but I rather like it here. Stone buildings are too confining.
Hail, O wayfarer. I must admit, I am uneasy around so many Orcs. But a carpenter must go where the wood is, yes?nnWhat can I help you with?
Sturdy, eye-catching clothes are a must for any true privateer. nnYou could buy some from the scoundrels here in town, but isn't it more satisfying to make your own?
It sure is a fine time to be a worker of wood. Plenty of good, strong wood to go aroundand plenty of demand for it.
I am quite sure my posting to this backwater was a mistake. I am sure the situation will be rectified soon.
You're in luck, I've recently re-stocked. Have a look.
I must've upset someone high up in the guild to end up posted here. Ah well, things will change eventually. In the meantime, I still have some interesting items to show you.
I don't remember why I came here, but I have every regret for doing so.nnIf I could move backwards through time, I would slap myself.
Wood's hard to come by out in the Alik'r. You should stock up while you can.
The wise cook knows that the secret to cooking is patience. And the right ingredients, of course.nnAs it happens, I have such ingredients, all for sale at fair prices.
We have to import a fair amount of wood, but the warm sun and dry wind here cure it wonderfully.
Well, well, well, look what the Khajiit dragged in.  What do you need?
With the power of the Earth Forge, we can arm the Guild. Deal with any number of enemies!nnLucky for us we have Guildmaster Merric to lead us, eh?
The quality of the lumber here is wonderful!nnIt's been quite an asset for the Guild, I can tell you.
If I may be of assistance, do let me know. Otherwise, I shall be occupying myself with my own duties here.
Since Guildmaster Merric took over, our stores have been top quality!. If you should need anything, just ask comrade!
I hear you've come to help, and let me tell you, we're all grateful.
Shada will destroy you  she'll destroy you all!nnShe's going to save us. She'll do anything to save us.
My dear friend, what did you get into? This is worse than moon-sugar withdraws.
You must be from outside. I'm glad to see someone's noticed us.nnA word of advice, though. Don't drink the water in here. Don't even touch it.
All the new faces in the Forge since Merric was made Guildmaster! nnIt's a boon for us grunts on the ground to have a seasoned veteran at the top. Can't wait to see what changes he makes!

Another day, another new Guildmaster. First the lizard, now the Redguard. I remember when there was a real Council, and the Guild was a force to be reckoned with.nnHmph. Hope we return to that, someday.
It's good to see a strong man of Alik'r leading the Guild! May Tall Papa guide his judgement, and the guild prosper forevermore!
You should know, not all of my people were like that snake Aelif. We of Elsweyr are the proud claws of the guild. We would never betray our comrades!
This Dwemer machinery is maddening. I'd love to repair some of it but  well. They didn't leave a lot of instructions behind.
I wonder what Merric is up to. What he's thinking about  If he's thinking of me.nnHe's an impressive fellow, you know? But then, so are you.
You're in luck, warrior. Whatever you need, I have it right here!
The Grandmaster is very busy today. Move along.

Please, help. I was with the research team that was sent to investigate this wing of the temple.nnThe others drank the water, but Nahlia and I refused to drink it. They attacked me, and then they captured Nahlia and took her deeper into the wing.

Where do these undead keep coming from? Have you seen how they gather around the Nereids? It's as if they're worshipping them.nnI wonder if that's what happens, eventually, when you drink the water. You start worshipping Nereids and turn undead.
What did we do? Nahliashe's going to be used in the sacrifice. The waters turned us against our own people.
The water. Don't drink the water.nnIt turns your mind. The Nereids will control you. Shada will control you. She made us take Nahlia.
It's over. Thank you. nnWe took Nahlia. You have to save her. I hope it's not too late.
I can't believe Klause and the others would have done this. This is all because of the water?

I don't know how I can repay you or Ralai for saving me. It was horrible. They captured me and handed me over to the Nereids. My life was being drained away.nnI don't know how much longer I could have lasted.
I miss the soft-hearted cypress trees back home. These Craglorn maples are too rigid and creakylike an old man's knees. But I ramble. How can I help you?
Have you tried the local food? Bah! Bland as my auntie's ash tea. A true cuisinier needs what my wagon carries. Exotic flavors at rock-bottom prices!
Friend of the Star-Gazers. Look at this place. Here, the mages of Craglorn fended off the Prince of Schemes and his Dark Anchors.nnBut the sweet taste of victory quickly turned bitter.
You there! You must set me free!

I thought I heard the tell-tale sounds of the living outside these doors.nnBe warned: the once-refreshing waters of this place run rancid with an unholy magica curse that grants great strength and unnatural long life, but for a price.
How this fool ever possessed the power to control such mighty atronachs, I'll never understand.
I don't know why the Serpent has bound the monarch atronachs like this. I'm not sure I want to know. He must have some purpose.
The atronachs are bound to the gem of command. Use the gem on each focus stone to summon the atronachs. Then we may speak with them.

I suppose I should thank you. I couldn't have bound the atronachs or defeated the air monarch on my own.nnI'm sure this isn't the end of the Serpent's mad plans, but I'd wager this sets him back for a while.
Kelmen believes there is a fourth Atronach roaming Craglorn. Could this one have been created by the Serpent?
Between cities, it's usually just me on the road. Well, me, and the other idiots looking for a profit.nnSpeaking of profit  anything I can do for you?
Enjoy the fruits of the robust Stormhaven agricultural community!nnBuy your produce here!
The freshest produce and food stock of the fertile Deshaan plains, grown locally by only the finest of Dres plantations!

That flesh abomination killed thousands of Yokudans as they assaulted this place. That you took it down so easilycould Zal'ik's magic be weakening?nnIn any case, the cloud of poison has begun to move.
Buy Dungeon Items from me. Also, I'm a Mammoth.
Folks said I was mad to build a huge stone forge on the second floor of a rickety warehouse. I did it, anyway! Sure, you might get crushed in a fiery collapse, but you can't beat the view!

Such terrible times these are. At least we are safe here in Belkarth.nnI heard that Elinhir did not fare so well. In fact, I hear that the entire Eastern portion of Craglorn is overrun with atronachs.

This one thinks the Star-Gazers should spend less time looking at stars and more time gazing down here. Walkers starve while they shuffle around in their silly robes, comfortable in their observatory. Ziss on them!
Quite an impressive library for some paltry inn, eh? I haven't seen many Dragonstar thugs or traders up here for story time, though. Damn odd, that.
Keep it nice and orderly. And if you see anything suspicious, let me know.
Can't you see I'm eating? Off with you, troll-bait.
This can't be happening! The mages haven't turned against us. They wouldn't! This is  just a silly nightmare isn't it? I'm going to wake up and my Itinia will still be alive .
What do you want? This one has gold! Jewels! Slaves! Riches beyond your wildest fantasies! Release me and this one will make you wealthier than anyone in Tamriel!
I demand that you release me at once! Do you have any idea who I am? You'll regret this injustice for the rest of your short life!
Well, my situation can't get any worse  so now it can only get better! Onwards and upwards!
All my friends have gone mad. The town is in ruins. What's going to happen to me?
<This scamp is not obviously aggressive. Around its neck is a choker bearing an inscription.>
Things like this aren't supposed to happen in Elinhir. They just aren't.
How did I fail to see this coming? It was my responsibility to protect them. The city was my responsibility.
Behave yourself. These people have suffered enough. I won't let any more harm come to them.
Did you hear that? Spellfiends, howling in the tunnels. Terrible sound.
No mage is going to get the better of me.
I've been waiting days for a reputable escort to Evermore. Nothing but low-born hooligans and toothless drovers in this Eight-forsaken place. I'll not have my things handled by such people.
Ugh. No time for chatter. Too many wounded!
Of all the  oh, I'm sorry. I didn't see you there.
I studied at the mage school for a little while. In the healing arts. I did not think they would turn against us.
There's nothing left. It's all gone.
If it weren't for Minerva, we'd all be dead.
How long do we have to hide in this sewer? We should arm ourselves and kill them all!
What if Minerva isn't really on our side? What if she's just gathered us here to kill us?
My father always said it was a mistake, handing control of Elinhir over to the mages.
Hara wanted me to stay with these Mage women to keep an eye on things. But I might have had a little too much wine .
I trust that you've come to harrass us like the others. Let me save you the effort. Until such time as we're physically removed, we will remain here to conduct our research. Now begone.
This one has many accounts to settle before the Moons rise and fall. What do you need?
Your riches will be well looked after. I swear on my mother's egg-tooth.
Now how did I know it was you who was helping the aspects?nnThey convinced me that they are what they say they are. The time has come to restore what was shattered and lost.
May prosperity find you. You are here to make a depositis it not so?
Do I look right to you?
You. I remember you, though we have not met. nnI am glad you arrived before the Scaled One. I believe this place is no longer safe.
Fascinating creatures. Such uncomplicated lives. Kill or be killed. Consume or be consumed.
Halt. This mile gate is a restricted area. Only members of the Covenant will be granted passage. Now be about your business.
You want something? Go talk to the lieutenant. I got a lot on my mind. Strategy, you see? So take off.

The ruse is dropped, and the thief emerges from the shadows. You see the truth.nnForgive me. I wore the guise of Hara because I didn't know who to trust, but neither could I rest while the Serpent preyed on the other Guardians.
Here to join up? We're offering decent pay for a hard day's work. And with this much rock to move  well  there's plenty of job security.
The Scaled One craves magic. But you have stopped him from gathering it. For now.
Antonia Gratas. Sixth Legion ahorse. nnI have some items you might find useful. Purchase something or be on your way.
Greetings, walker! You mean to enter the Seeker's Archive, yes? This one thinks you have the brains of a ja'khajiit. That is good! Crazy people need my goods most of all!
Careful. There are dangerous doings in Elinhir. I'd prefer to run for the hills, but we can't very well move the farm, can we? Zenithar preserve us.nnBut enough blather. Do you need supplies?
Headed up to Rahni'Za? Hope you enjoy boring lectures. Me? I prefer a merchant's life. The open road. Exotic locales. And happy customers!
Yeah? Did the Dremora send you to finish me off?
While we have a moment, we should try to fortify our position. Find supplies throughout the district and bring them back here. If we get enough, we can upgrade our defenses.

It's strange. The longer I spend here, the more clouded my mind becomes. Memories that to me are only days gone are becoming as fleeting as a dream. I suppose at least there is comfort that you aided me in stopping Tarish-Zi before it was too late.
It's strange, all these people pouring into Belkarth. We used to be such a quiet town. nnWell, maybe not quiet. Just anonymous.
Mauloch gnash it! Of all the damned tuskless, ogre-brained . Argh!nnWhat do you want?

I knew settling near the city would eventually lead to trouble, but Alarice just had to live close to her mother. Now we've got giant monsters running wild in our garden. nnI guess it puts a visit from the in-laws into perspective.
If those mages want this farm, they're going to have to come and take it.
Keep your head down. It is not safe here.
Have you come to slay Iron Orcs? If so, give this one a wide berth. What I do will be  messy.
Get out of here. No telling when they'll come back.
Those aren't Orcs, they're monsters! Mauloch help us!
They call it liquid courage. I'm not sure that's the right name. More like liquid forgetfulness.nnA toastto our dear, lost friends. And to the Thief, whatever she may be.
Those Dremora aren't going to kill themselves, you know. Talk to the captain and help us take back the City!
If you're looking for the dumbest man in all of Cyrodiil, your search is over.
Many pursue the arcane arts, but few truly master them.
My deals will make you howl!
Welcome! Get all of your siege weapons here, free of charge! I have siege for every alliance!
Wha  who are you? Flee, foolbefore they come for you too!
Who are you? You've got to get away! It's not safe. Run  run while you can.
What is it? You're one of them, aren't you? Traitor! Leave me to die in peace!
You fool! Flee this dungeonget out! Leave now or you'll never see sunlight again.
Another Daedra lover. So, it's my turn now?
Well, I'm glad to see you, no mistake. I'd rather have been rescued by Imperials, but you'll do.

You and I have a common enemy; the Serpent and his Scaled Court. If you will stay your hand and hear what I have to say, I can offer you a unique opportunity to see this enemy slain.nnWill you listen to my offer?
You're not one of Master Relvi's guards.nnDoesn't bother me. I don't get paid enough to care.
I don't know who you are, but I don't want any trouble.
I'll be honest, I'd given up hope and was looking up and down the path for another group of adventurers to send in after you.nnWere you successful? I'll not blame you for running away.
It's excellent to see you came out alive. We were worried we wouldn't see you.
Captain Brocchus told us to hold here, so that's what we're going to do. At least until those monsters spot us, anyway.
Keep your head down! There's Dremora all over the place.
Why are you here? This is my spot. Hurry, go away before they see you!
Get your head down or the Daedra'll take it off for you.
Good to see a face that's not horrible to look at. Not too horrible anyway.
Hello, I am an Inn Keeper. I offer bounties.
Don't go in there. You don't know what they've done to us! It's horrible!
What are you looking at, skeever?
You're not a Stone-Fish. State your business or move along, if you please.
Every life is a battle waiting to unfold.
Come to spit on us like the rest of these thugs? I'll tell you what I told the others. We're here to compete in the Arena, nothing more.
Hello there! Are you enjoying the festival?
This one has much to offer. From as far away as the Summerset Islesenchanting and mystical!
My enchantments are the finest in the land. But quality has a cost my friend, quality has a cost.
Anything can be made better through enchantment. Anything. Don't believe me? Give it a try.
Please, leave Holstagg be. He's had a trying day.
A secure vault makes for a confident heart.
Something catch your eye? Something hard to find? Something exotic?
Yes, yes. Finally, a discerning customer.
Something I can help you with today? Feel free to browse and just holler if you need help.
Welcome, outlander. Have you come to prove yourself worthy of the hist?
Welcome child of Nirn. You have come to prove yourself?
Well, look at the little wasp. What brings you here little wasp? Wanting to prove your sting?
<The scamp doesn't appear to be able to speak, but it does offer some basic services.>
You're on a layer, and when you turn in this quest, should remain on this layer with me.
Have you seen my dogs? A horrible noise spooked one of them and all three ran off in different directions. They're my babies and I can't go on without them!
You're not part of my expedition. Interesting. nnThis is no random chance. I believe you're the answer to our problem.
You did a great thing this day. If you need anything, you can always find me here.
Interact and let someone else do the pummeling to douse yourself in the blood fountain!

Countess Tamrith returns here for her father's funeral, and what does House Montclair do? They attack the upper city!nnThe bastards killed more Shornhelm Guards and civilians than I care to think about. It's like Ranser's War all over again!
A fool and his gold are soon parted, but you don't look foolish. We will keep your valuables safe and sound.
You can rest assured we'll take good care of your valuables here.
You may bank with me in complete confidence.
You can trust our security and discretion.
Time is gold, and today I have a short supply of both. Do you need something?
This one has many accounts to settle before the Moons rise and fall. What do you need?
Your riches will be well looked after. I swear on my mother's egg-tooth.
Auri-el knows, I'm here to serve. What can I help you with?
Take it from me: Your goods are safe here.
Once you ask us to store an item of yours, our guarantee is that nobody will ever touch it again.nnExcept for you. Usually.
Welcome. Shall I attend to your account?
Greetings, my friend. You've come to make a deposit, yes?
A secure vault makes for a confident heart.
This one thinks you have come to make a deposit, yes?
Your purse looks heavy, wayfarer. Can we help safeguard your valuables?
I erect the spine of welcome.
If you use an ability while sprinting, you will automatically slow down to normal run speed.
I've helped the contingent out of Crosswych fight back the Werewolves on the Moors.  It may not be enough to turn the tide, but it's something.
I've provided Father Arod with enough hops to continue quenching Crosswych's insatiable thirst.
I returned the blades I collected from the zombies to Gaspar. Though he was dismayed at the condition of them, he believes they can still help equip his soldiers.
I have aided the Magis Order by clearing out a number of bandits in Ykalon Forest.
I was able to ensure the safety of Orator Simine, but Orator Dalomar was murdered. Lady Kallath is determined to send her people out with better protection in future.
I've completed a patrol of Camlorn, and helped the shortmanned Magis Order keep peace in the city.
The acolytes in northern Ykalon have fled to the north, but Jha Gra-Muzgob still lives.
I returned the werewolf ears to High Inquisitor Averos. He assured me that despite their human origins, the creatures are subhuman and thus worthy only of death.
I've informed Marcus's wife of his death.

I returned the soul gems to Captain Danfor. He asked me not to think of the soldiers I slew, but rather of those I saved by helping bring the conflict between Northmoor and Shornhelm closer to an end.
By slaying Jha gra-Muzgob, I prevented her from raising an army of dead to attack Eagle's Watch from the rear. King's Guard is much safer with this orc necromancer in the ground.
At the request of Battlereeve Tariella I managed to infiltrate Sunhold Isle and lay waste to the Maormer Siege Engines stationed there, destroying both machines and the engineers who maintained them.
I brought a supply of Hag Scales to the hospital in Crosswych. Doctor Sevarain was quite pleased.

Faya is fine, though she was a bit shaken up by the discovery that her friend was a ghost. She promised me she would never have an imaginary friend again. Given the many ghosts wandering Aldcroft, that may be for the best.
I used Thetis' unction to purify the foul lake water by the goblin camp.nnNathaniel Varle hopes this will also purify the water in Grayborne's well.
I've successfully defended the Oyinaam from the Zombie Incendiaries. I should speak to Battlereeve Tariella at the Harmonium Fortress.
Tactician Veraul believes the reports I collected may help him devise a better defense against Shornhelm forces. After he reviews the reports, he promised to call on me again.
Brennoc was glad to see me.  He needs my help with a problem the Magis Order have created.
High Inquisitor Averos asked me to speak with Captain Arin Blayne about a graverobbing epidemic. Averos is worried the graverobbing may have something to do with Shornhelm's next attack.
I put an end to the feud between Al'kari and Guillie, freeing up Watchman Derran for more important duties.
Odette, the nominal leader of the camp, is a girl of perhaps 17. She claims that her small camp has had trouble with bandits and requested my help in stopping them from harming the camp.
I've agreed to help Tactician Veraul with matters pertaining to the Shornhelm invasion.
King Fahara'jad, ruler of the Nine Crowns, sent Oron to defuse a potential war between Shornhelm and Northmoor.
I managed to help Pierric break free from being corrupted at the hands of the Ulorion Cultists.  Guendeline is elated at his return.
Summary of what happened on the quest. Appears in the Completed Quests tab.
Warden Rielle assured me that everyone affected by Mother Murk's machinations will find good homes at the caravan. She credits my efforts with saving both the children and their families.
I've given Veraul the documents I stole from Marshal Gerard's desk. He promised to inform me the moment he found anything of use contained in them.
I've returned Henri's pendant to Denise, his twin sister. Though Denise grieved for Henri's death, she feels he found peace when I slew his possessed body.
With my victory over Namira's spawn, I wrested the Mines of Khuras from the Ulorion Cultists and stopped their plot to resurrect Ulorion.
I gave the heart of the Spider Daedra to Bruno Dabney, who thanked and paid me for it. He thinks it may help the Magis Order learn the Daedra's weaknesses.
I collected a kelpie spirit in Alain's soul gem and gave it to him for use in his studies. He thanked and rewarded me.
I chose to do as Constable Barre asked and killed Morgan Frey.nnShe died knowing justice was done and the muder of her family answered.
With my actions, one threat, at least, will no longer trouble Odette and the murklings.
Jes was grateful to have his missing weapons back, and my efforts have made the roads to and from Camlorn safer. He said the Red Rook bandits were led by a lunatic who is not to be trusted.

The lumberjack camp was attacked by wolves, in force. It's an odd behavior, even for pack hunters, and the camp was ravaged. Many of the lumberjacks need help, and they're willing to get it from anywhere.
Baron Avon is confident that Magister Averos is responsible for the murder of Lord Ranser.
The courier was seen south of Grayborne, near the forest edge.  Roche mentioned that there are Spriggans within the forest who could have harmed the courier.
I met Nathaniel Vorne.  While I wait for Brennoc to locate the courier, I may help about town.
I fulfilled Pane Oges' desire for revenge against the wolves who maimed him.
The Countess' advisor will not allow me to enter the manor and speak with her.  I will have to convince Chamberlain Gargast of the urgency of this matter.
Hopefully I will reach Katarin before she passes the weapon off again.
I have reached Aldcroft and found Katarin.  I hope I can retrieve the murder weapon and return it to Oron.
I have helped Alchemist Sylbenitte gather ingredients for vital potions and delivered them to the Magis Order.
I have successfully gathered the limbs from the zombies.

The house was not haunted... but there was an assassin.  He mentioned something about the "Shrouded Throne" and how I was close to uncovering it.  nnI will be sure to ask the Countess of this Shrouded Throne when I speak to her.
Guardian Caldrun will return to Countess Virolynn, now that we have slain Gargast.  He suggests I travel to Crosswych
The treacherous Chamberlain escaped, but the Countess is safe.  I will will track the Chamberlain down at a later time.
You've done it, you are so cool!

Oron seems to know more than he is telling.nnI returned to Camlorn and spoke with Oron.  He seems to know more than he is revealing.  He fears "what we are going to uncover by finding the murderer will endanger us all."
Before arresting Lord Sebastien, Oron wants to speak with him first.
King Vincintian informed me that the Shrouded Throne must not break through the defenses at Eagles Watch.  I have travelled here to help in its defense.
Oron suspects there are agents of the Shrouded Throne in Crosswych.  I must work with Warden Godwin to find them.
I have aided Doctor Marris with providing the soldier's peace.

I revealed Varik Maen as a coward, unfit to be Captain of any watchtower. In light of this vacancy, the Warden was more than willing to give Saul Azeer a chance, which he accepted.  Crosswych's City Watch is now another man stronger.

Warden Rielle believes the children are being held in the camp by a hostile force we have not yet encountered. She wants me to help her convince the children to return home, to the caravan, and requested my help in finding a way to make that occur.
I collected the Lady's Mantle as Doctor Gillibert requested.
I delivered medical supplies to the camp outside of Crosswych.
Oron asked that I speak to Baron Avon and Inquisitor Danain.  These two individuals attended the dinner on the night of Lord Ranser's murder and he believes they will confirm two of his suspects.
Oron asked that I speak to Baron Avon and Inquisitor Danain.  These two individuals attended the dinner on the night of Lord Ranser's murder and he believes they will confirm two of his suspects.
It seems that an agent of the Shrouded Throne is behind the undead that walk in the graveyard. There must be something bigger going on as the Acolyte didn't want me to survive my investigations.
I delivered a shipment of silver from Crosswych to Wayrest for Seth.
I recovered Keet's missing shipment of glass, but was forced to slay her best merchant, who had fallen victim to some dark magic.
I helped the Magis Order rescue some of their patrollers in Camlorn.

Baron Winoc was nonplussed to find Camlorn's people fairly divided between the Magis Order and Hands of Northmoor, and believes he must do more to promote the organization. He thanked me for my work in gathering data about public opinion.
I left the recruits to their duties. All that remains is to report what happened to Capel.
I have helped drive back risen undead attackers in Northern Ykalon.
I returned the intact curaisses to Alborn. He was grateful to receive the armor and thinks it can be put to good use armoring Northmoor soldiers.
The order has been delivered to Blacksmith Oges in Camlorn, and the Hands of Northmoor will help escort the smith's supplies to the camp when they're ready.
Inquisitor Roche asked me to handle a dangerous witch, Elsie Dunlop.nnAfter speaking to the people of Grayborne, I asked Elsie to leave the village and not return.
I left the recruits to their duties. All that remains is to report what happened to Capel.
Capel was not happy with Ames' defection, but believes his force is stronger with Ames gone. He assured me I did as well as could be expected.
Capel was suspicious of Ames' 'death', but did not question me further. Even so, he did not seem pleased with the outcome of my patrol.

Capel knew his recruits would freeze up in battle, and thanked me for protecting them during their first real battle experience. He believes that by following my example, both will soon grow into fine soldiers.
I have helped the Hands of Northmoor exact justice against the Magis Order patrollers who killed one of their agents.
I returned the spectres' pendants to the Priest of Ar'kay, so he can put the spirits to rest. He thanked me and gave me Ar'kay's blessing.

Tactician Veraul wishes to study the scraps of information I retrieved from the dead Shornhelm soldiers. He hopes he may see something he missed with further study. He thanked me for my help and told me to report to High Inquisitor Averos.
I've found Oron and I am ready to render what aid I can in the investigation of the murder.
I've found Oron and I am ready to render what aid I can in the investigation of the murder.
I informed Tarrant of my findings on the Biren farm. The possible implications frightened him, but he was at least relieved that his friend Aquil was innocent of any wrongdoing.
I helped Roche in his inquisition against the witches of the Beldama Wyrd. Hopefully, they'll reconsider before they interfere with the people of Grayborne again.
I blew the Howling Pipe, which frightened off most of the goblin camp.  Then I killed their king and his henchmen.
Capel was intrigued by the charm I found in the zombie's skull, but cannot say for sure what it represents. He plans to look into the matter further and see what else he can find out.
Caretaker Villas was extremely grateful to hear that the spirits of Eagle's Watch are now at rest. I do wonder, however, about the blank book he found in the tower so long ago
I found several of the refugees' belongings in Westtry and returned them to Iven of Westtry in Grayborne.
I returned to Camlorn and spoke with Oron.  He seems to know more than he is revealing.  He fears "what we are going to uncover by finding the murderer will endanger us all."
I killed a number of wolves around the village of Grayborne, making it safer for the villagers and travelers on the roads.
While I was embattled with Frey's gang, Constable Barre found Morgan Frey and killed him.  nnThough she herself was killed in the attempt, at least she died knowing her family was avenged.
I saved Doctor Sevarain, so no arcane test was necessary to prove my loyalty. Warden Godwin was pleased that I saved his friend, and welcomed me into Crosswych with open arms.
I have killed the bears as Teddy asked.
I've recovered all of Ahlotica's missing papers.
I used the curative Thetis provided me on Isaac's wound. He looks much better now, and I believe he will recover.
Oron suspects there are agents of the Shrouded Throne in Crosswych.  I must work with Warden Godwin to find them.
I failed to return to Isaac in time. It would appear he expired during my absence.
Doctor Holcombe was pleased with my success and paid me handsomely for my work. Should he require additional assistance, he promised to call upon me again.
I presented the letter to Oron Nassir and have agreed to help him investigate the murder.

Once we reached Aldcroft, Aurore Bagot thanked me for my work in helping her reunite her family. With Aurore's strong sword arm to protect them, I believe their family will be fine once Tristan recovers enough to walk again.
Baron Avon is convinced Averos, the leader of the Magis Order, is Lord Ranser's murderer.  This was an act of vengeance since Lord Ranser slew the founder of the Magis Order - a man named Ulorion.
I helped Adrienne Vanne, a shopkeeper in Aldcroft, obtain supplies for her shop from Aldcroft Habor.
Medic Stanwood complimented me on my work bandaging the injured lumberjacks. He thanked me for my help and told me my efforts had made his job easier.
With their captors slain, we should be able to get the children out of the murkling camp if they're willing to leave.
With their well water horribly sour, the children at the murkling camp will hopefully be all too eager to return home.
With their supplies burned, the children now have no choice but to look elsewhere for food. With luck, they'll allow us to bring them back to the caravan.
I have helped Amelie and her family to keep warm by finding Drythistle to make a fire.
I delivered Veris' son, Balen, from the clutches of the bandits assaulting Aldcroft Harbor.

I agreed to help Odette and the other murklings find their parents. When I spoke to Warden Rielle about the matter, she referred me to Doctor Holcombe, a famed monster hunter who happens to be traveling with the caravan.
I found Nathaniel Varle's kitty, Sweetling out in the forest of Grayborne.nnI'm not sure she needed my help with the wolves after all but I saw her home safely.

Doctor Holcombe analyzed the lake water using his own devices and concluded that Mother Murk's lair must be almost directly beneath the Greenfoot Root growths, beneath the surface of the lake. We now know where she may have been nesting.
I killed the bandit leader and freed the prisoners they had aboard their ship. Aldcroft Harbor is on its way to being recovered.

I agreed to help Odette and the other murklings find their parents. When I spoke to Warden Rielle about the matter, she referred me to Doctor Holcombe, a famed monster hunter who happens to be traveling with the caravan.
Arnand's supplies consisted of paraphenalia the likes of which I am unfamiliar with. Perhaps he is a chemist.
I helped the alchemist in Aldcroft get ingredients for his special potion and in return he provided me with one of them.
Serge was overjoyed to see his dire wolf alive and safe, and promised to never let Grit out of his sight again.
Odette says she doesn't remember much about her life before she came to the murkling camp, which is odd. Perhaps the spell that enchanted the dire wolves has enchanted the children as well.
I have found evidence of the werewolves where abouts and reported my findings to Dr. Holcombe.
I have taken out the werewolves in this area, but I'm sure thats not the last of them.
By slaying Jha gra-Muzgob, I prevented her from raising an army of dead to attack Eagle's Watch from the rear. King's Guard is much safer with this orc necromancer in the ground.
By slaying Jha gra-Muzgob, I prevented her from raising an army of dead to attack Eagle's Watch from the rear. King's Guard is much safer with this orc necromancer in the ground.
By slaying Jha gra-Muzgob, I prevented her from raising an army of dead to attack Eagle's Watch from the rear. King's Guard is much safer with this orc necromancer in the ground.
I've found Gui at Camp Mercy, and enlisted his help in the investigation into the missing bodies from Cath Bedraud.
With the help of the Hands of Northmoor, I will get to the bottom of this graverobbing.
With the help of the Magis Order, I will get to the bottom of this graverobbing.

The Werewolves have kidnapped Annalynne, Warden Godwin's fiancee. He has decided to gather what watchmen he has to launch an all out offensive on the main Werewolf camp northeast of town. I have pledged my assistance.
Inquisitor Roche is going to make arrangements for what to do with the courier's body.  He suggested I assist him with other issues in the interim.
Inquisitor Roche has prepared a ritual which will summon the courier's spirit.  This will be the only way for me to discover where the murder weapon was hidden.
After I help Gargast push the Magis Order out of Aldcroft, he will let me speak with Virolynn.

The documents prove Gargast is working with Shornhelm agents in Dwynnen. The courier also mentioned 'The Shrouded Throne'. Unfortunately, Virolynn will decry any evidence we present as fake. We must find another way to reveal Gargast's true nature.

Inquisitor Spencer revealed the purpose of the rare Elixir of True Nature. Upon touching the skin of a subject, it temporarily forces the subject to speak nothing but the truth. He believes we can use it force Gargast to incriminate himself.

After Gargast revealed himself as a werewolf and wounded Virolynn, I decided to track him along the road to Crosswych and slay him before he reaches it. When I spoke to Caldrun, he mentioned ominous rumors about the 'Shrouded Throne'.
I helped Master Metalwright Sinderon forge a magical protection onto the core of Auri-El.
Oron has asked me to go to Grayborne to pursue the murder weapon. I am to speak to Brennoc Hursh who usually frquents the outside of the Inn in the town.
Brennoc's scouts discovered the courier.  He is being held in a 'make-shift' prison to the east of town.
I've identified two potential assassins: Lady Virolynn and Averos of the Magis Order.  Vizier Oron agrees.
While on the Maormer-held island of Sunhold, I killed Rahoeri, the commander of the enemy camp. I turned Rahoeri's head over to Battlereeve Tariella, and was duly rewarded for his death.
I have met with Inquisitor Danain.  It appears he suspects Countess Virolynn was involved in Ranser's murder.
I have found the Redoubt Camp in northern Ykalon, and ensured that Lieutenant Emeric's girlfriend is all right. She was pleased to hear from him.

I have found the Redoubt Camp in northern Ykalon, and passed on news of Camlorn to Laeran Jes. He is going to redouble his efforts to establish a relationship between the Hands of Northmoor and the Magis Order.

I helped fend off the werewolf assault on Crosswych. It turns out Godwin's betrothed, Annalynne, was in fact the alpha werewolf in the region. He seems characteristically stoic about this tragic turn of events.
I've gotten caught up on events at Eagle's Watch and have spoken to Tactician Veraul. He should be able to direct me further in this area.
Inquisitor Danain was glad to have the wraiths vanquished, and emphasized the perils the Magis Order faces defending Camlorn from evil.

Chamberlain Gargast is certainly a spy for Shornhelm, and Countess Virolynn is in danger as long as he remains in her court. Spencer and I will expose Gargast for the traitor he is. Then I should be able to speak to Virolynn.

After my successes against the Maormer at Sunhold, High Kinlord Maldarawo summoned me to his Kinhouse. As I have reduced the threat to his people, he has agreed to support High Queen Ayarynne's policies.

I have cleansed the lake of the goblin sludge and provided Grayborne with a clean water source once again. It did disturb a Vile Dweller that moved in with the sludge, but I took care of it. The tainted water nor the vile creature should bother anyo
High Kinlord Maldarawo of Isque sent me on to Orrery. The Maormer have devastated the magickal construct that gives the region its name. There is much work to be done.

After Gargast revealed himself as a werewolf and wounded Virolynn, I decided to assist Priestess Eliana and help heal Virolynn. When I spoke to Caldrun, he mentioned ominous rumors about the 'Shrouded Throne'.
I've delivered the Magis Order potions to Daenia on behalf of Inquisitor Bieller.
I have killed the infamous Scar and returned his head to Goodwife Mallory in Grayborne.

After Gargast turned into a werewolf and wounded Virolynn and fled, I decided to track him along the road to Crosswych and slay him before he reaches it. When I spoke to Caldrun, he mentioned ominous rumors about the 'Shrouded Throne'.

After Gargast revealed himself as a werewolf and wounded Virolynn, I decided to assist Priestess Eliana and help heal Virolynn. When I spoke to Caldrun, he mentioned ominous rumors about the 'Shrouded Throne'.

I have hunted down and slain the beast known as Gargast. His very presence implies greater forces at work behind the scenes. I should travel to Crosswych and see if I can uncover any further secretive workings.
Countess Virolynn seems to be on the mend. She asked me to search for
I spoke with Inquistor Roche at Brennoc's behest.
I reunited Pierric with Guendeline. Pierric was upset at me playing matchmaker with his betrothed, but at least they're together now.
With the Wyress' help, I terrified the goblins with the Howling Pipe and killed their king.nnNow it's possible that the goblins will disband and leave Grayborne in peace.
I met with King Sebastien, and he has agreed to help Warden Godwin by allowing Godwin to go directly to Fahara'jad.
I've identified two potential assassins: Lady Virolynn and Averos of the Magis Order.  Vizier Oron agrees.

When I shared my story with Commander Blarae, he was unsurprised. It seems this hooded figure has been plaguing the Redoubt as well. I must stop whatever plans the hooded figure has for Camlorn, and for Ranser's body.
I administered Stanwood's poultice to the diseased lumberjacks, and eased their suffering.  The Lumberjacks can get back to work.
At Foreman Maston's behest, I killed several of the undead wolves. They are clearly unnatural, a threat to both the men at the Mill and everything in the forest.
I successfully lured out and killed Necanis, the creature that leads the undead wolves. They should no longer threaten the lumber camp in any organized way.
I was correct King Ranser was assassinated before I arrived. I've offered my help to King Sebastian to investigate the murder.

High Priest Canning believes we can summon Ranser's soul using the Chalice of Gwedrun and Soulstone of Brall. He is now preparing himself for the ritual, and advised me to prepare myself as well. I must speak to him again when I am ready.
Though relieved to known Simine and Bovie were safe, Jes was angered to learn of Dalomar's fate. Jes is convinced the Magis Order murdered Orator Dalomar to silence him.
I delivered the document to Claudette. She recognized it as belonging to her betrothed, Jerome Roux, who went missing several days ago. She prayed for his return, but it was not to be.
Inquisitor Danain seems eager to take credit for my patrol and paint me as a loyal servant of the Magis Order. As it seems this will help Camlorn stay peaceful, I have not corrected this impression.
I infiltrated the Bandit Camp and retrieved his Masolaude's trunkload of valuables. He was less than gracious in accepting its return.
I've given the Chalice of Gwedrun to High Priest Canning. Canning can use Chalice of Gwedrun and the Soulstone of Brall to summon Ranser's spirit and ask who murdered him.
I've given the Soulstone of Brall to High Priest Canning. Canning can use the Chalice of Gwedrun and the Soulstone of Brall to summon Ranser's spirit and ask who murdered him.
I traveled to the Lumber Camp south of Camlorn to investigate Amaury's concerns. He has good reason to be worried; the men of the mill are under attack from the undead!
I have slain five of the bandits troubling Camlorn's merchants. It may not stop the attacks, but it will at least curb them somewhat.

High Priest Canning has survived the mysterious assassin's attack, but the ritual's failure unleashed evil spirits upon Camlorn. High Priest Canning is too weak to face the fiends himself - I must stop them.
I have consecrated three of the spawning sites of the undead invaders. Hopefully their forces are weakened.

I've agreed to help Oron, an emissary to King Fahara'jad, investigate King Ranser's murder. We must prove Sebastian innocent, or Northmoor and Shornhelm could go to war - such strife could destroy the Adamant Crown.
I've agreed to work with High Priest Canning of the Order of Arkay to summon Ranser's spirit, so Ranser's shade can name his killer.
Though Inquisitor Danain agreed to give me the Chalice of Gwedrun, but he wants me to prove myself to him and the Magis Order first.
Though Jes of Wayrest agreed to let me borrow the Soulstone of Brall, he asked me to do a favor for him first.
I have traded the Fine Spider Silk that I have found to Outfitter Benoit in Camlorn. He will continue to trade stacks of 5 Fine Spider Silks that I find for a reward.
I've killed Vorgo, the Red Rook. Doubtless some other brigand will take his place, but with luck, perhaps one not so cruel as he.

I brought four Dark Acolytes to the central altar in Glaes Maar, where they were overcome by spirits.  In gratitude for my actions, Claude combined the souls within Crystalwan with the Maarsword, giving me an item of great power.

When I shared my story with Commander Blarae, he was unsurprised. It seems this hooded figure has plagued the Redoubt as well. nnI must thwart the hooded figure's plans and recover Ranser's body. I hope Commander Blarae can help.
Canning was pleased with my efforts to exorcise Camlorn's citizens, and now believes that between the two of us, we should be able to minimize the damage from the failed ritual in Camlorn's temple.

I brought four Dark Acolytes to the central altar in Glaes Maar, where they were overcome by spirits.  In gratitude for my actions, Claude combined the souls within Crystalwan with the Maarsword, giving me an item of great power.

I brought four Dark Acolytes to the central altar in Glaes Maar, where they were overcome by spirits.  In gratitude for my actions, Claude combined the souls within Crystalwan with the Maarsword, giving me an item of great power.
At Blanche's request, I found the vengeful spirit of her beloved Coren and sent her to her final rest.
Captain Blanche Geves, unable to leave the Redoubt camp to locate her missing squad members, sent me to locate them. The four squad members I found are now safely back at the Redoubt.

Inquisitor Blarae praised my efforts with rallying his defenders - he believes the Redoubt will now hold against the undead. With Camlorn saved, I must now go to Thrandor's Portal and stop Morholdt from sending Ranser's body to Oblivion.

We have lost Ranser's body, but Oron believes we still won a victory by slaying Morholdt and thwarting his master's plans for Camlorn. I gave Oron the note I found on Morholdt's body, hoping he could make some sense of it.

Brennoc said a man from Shornhelm, Varic Aston, arrived in Grayborne recently to visit his cousin, Bruno. Bruno and Varic were attacked by a 'giant wolf' shortly after Varic arrived. Though Varic survived the attack, Bruno did not.
At the behest of Questgiver, I killed a number of goblins and was rewarded.

Though Wyress Jacinta managed to keep Varic alive, she lacks the power to heal him. The Beldama Wyrd was recently forced out of their home, something called the Wyrd Tree. I've agreed to help Jacinta recover the Wyrd Tree so she may heal Varic.
I found Thetis at his house midway between Grayborne and the lake. Once I mentioned Jacinta's request, Thetis agreed to help me clean the lake of goblin poison for her sake.
I have set up several barricade along the river. That should keep the Maormer Zombies out for some time.

After examining the sludge in the barrel I retrieved from the lake, Thetis concluded two things - first, the mixture is too complex for goblins to make, so someone must have made them poison the lake. Second, he can mix a remedy.
I located Michael Herbert in Westtry.
While I was able to remove several goblins from Thetis the Poisoner's garden, there are still some goblins left that might do more damage.
With the ingredients I gathered, Thetis was able to complete his remedy for the poisoned lake.
Thetis is confident the lake will be pure in a matter of days, and does not need further help.
I have burned the witchroot, and it had an effect on the goblins, but I don't know how long it will last.
Wyress Jacinta was grateful for my help cleaning the lake, and Thetis will have it purified in a few days. Jacinta said there was now another threat that requires our attention.

Wyress Jacinta thanked me for returning the Wyrd Tree to her and her sisters. She has promised to do all she can to wake Varic from the sleep he entered after he was almost slain by the 'giant wolf' that attacked him.
I helped Wyress Jacinta find the imposter amongst the Wyrd that caused them so much trouble. With this decieving hag out of the way, the Wyrd should be able to regain thier defenses.

Jacinta has heard only whispers of the Shrouded Throne, but she offered another clue. The evils I've fought were controlled by a powerful spirit plaguing Westtry - the One Who Hungers. It may serve this Shrouded Throne.

Wyress Zoe and her sisters work to keep Westtry's tormented spirits from escaping and wreaking havoc in Grayborne, but they are fast losing ground. They need my help to stop the One Who Hungers, which is behind the evils I've fought in Daenia.
Wyress Zoe now believes she and her sisters have the grip they need to draw the One Who Hungers from the shadows - but it will not be easy, and the spirit will be greatly angered by such an act.
Wyress Zoe believes that with the One Who Hungers exorcised, she and the Beldama Wyrd can finally help Westtry's tortured souls find peace - though it will take time.

When I reached Aldcroft, I found that Oron had preceded me there - and he believes the Bloodstone is in the town, in the possession of Countess Virolynn. He also said that the Magis Order suspects Virolynn's Chamberlain, Gargast, of treason.
I've found Mirielle's locket and brought it to her sister, Saelle.  When I gave it to her, she transformed in front of my eyes from an old haggard crone to a young woman again.
Despite its destruction, Westtry's place in the Viralaine family heart is strong. By returning Mari's parents's ashes to their home, I've given her peace of mind and spirit.
With the addition of the pure poison sample I gathered, Thetis was able to complete his remedy for the poisoned lake.
Melusine Darte asked me to pick Blood Nettle Flowers for Thetis the Poisoner. She did not realize how allergic she was to them when she agreed to his task.
I killed the goblins' Chieftain. There should be fewer goblins to bother Thetis the Poisoner now.

Constable Ailsa Baird is dying. While chasing down a murderer who escaped justice in Camlorn, she was afflicted with the poison on the murderer's blade - a poison powerful enough to leave her beyond help. Shava asked me to grant Ailsa's dying wish.

Brennoc said a man from Shornhelm, Varic Aston, arrived in Grayborne recently to visit his cousin, Bruno. Bruno and Varic were attacked by a 'giant wolf' shortly after Varic arrived. Though Varic survived the attack, Bruno did not.
I returned the empty purse to Lady Dalomar, who seemed unhappy with its lack of coin.nnAt least she didn't blame me for stealing.

High Priestess Vendialara invited me to assist her in a ritual to bless the Starglass Bell I forged in the cave of the Liriel Nereids. In addition to preparing the ritual space, I played a musical accompaniment to her psalm.
I've reduced the Maormer supplies on Sunhold Island, weakening their position.
Inquisitor Danain seems eager to take credit for my patrol and paint me as a loyal servant of the Magis Order. As it seems this will help Camlorn stay peaceful, I have not corrected this impression.
I have recieved the blessing of the damned from Princess Aurais at Castle Silvermist. All that remains is binding the source of the evil here.

I have destroyed one of the vampires in Silvermist Castle. The Mistress of the Castle still survives, but it will be up to me to put together a force capable of combating her. Even the Ashen Order thinks that this may be a lost cause.
I delivered a work report from the lumber camp when I went to Camlorn.
I discovered the poachers have been using cheap curses to kill local deer, and issued them a warrant.  They must report back to the forester's guild or be considered fugitives.
I discovered the poachers have been using cheap curses to kill local deer, but chose not to issue them a warrant.  Forester Brehat accepted my decision as her deputy.

When I returned to the abandoned Atois household, Tomas' spirit joined his wife, Vivienne. The two are reunited at last.nnVivienne said they'd be leaving soon to 'join relatives." This may mean they're finally ready to move on.
Lord Alain Diel may be free from politicians, but he's still surrounded by harpies. nnAt least the fishing is good.
Squire Maddoc's not quite sure how to handle the harpy eggs I brought him. That's a problem he'll need to solve for himself.
The spirit of Claire Lirlane was grateful to me for destroying the spirits of those warriors who slaughtered the people of Westtry, and hopes now to find absolution... and rest.

The grandparents of Colette Atois lived in Westtry. They were slain during skirmishes between the armies of feuding lords. Colette lost her locket when she was a little girl. Now she's a grown woman, and she's grateful to have it back.
Outside of Daggerfall, I was able to help<<1>> by recovering his lost tools. Rootlings had scattered them by the roadside.
Lord Magister Averos agrees that a Reachmage with necromantic powers could be responsible for the troubles in Glenumbra. It seems we share a common enemy: Angof.

I delivered goblin hearts to Wyress Adelle. She cast her spell and vowed to abduct goblins from all over Daenia. She plans to replace their hearts with the ones she's ensorcelled. Then they'll hate each other as much as they hate us.

Wyress Zoe can sense the rightness returning to her glen. She feels my work in pruning away the Corrupted Wyrd Saplings has eased the way to recovering the purity the Beldama Wyrd lost when their tree was stolen.
I took the foresters' tools to Ormax's foremen  in the forest around Deleyn's Mill.nnIt's a wonder they can work at all with the spriggans attacking constantly.

Wyress Laure thanked me for freeing the captured wolves and killing their cruel goblin masters. She hopes that tales of wolves turning against their masters will convince the goblins to stop enslaving them.

When Wyress Ileana touched the spriggan limbs, she immediately sensed Reach magic, a perversion of nature. Their magical aura matches emanations from the center of the Dresan ruins. This confirms that the ruins spawned more spriggans.
I've harvested some hawthorn seeds for Wyress Paulette. She hopes she can restore hawthorn bushes to the land after we've found the source of the forest's corruption.

The Nereids of the Liriel River were infected by the Catagious Cadavers Maomer siege engines hurled into Isque.nnI slew some of the Nereids infected by the Maormer corpses. Hopefully this will prevent further spread of the disease.
Wyress Ashtah assured me that burning the idols would weaken the goblins' resolve discourage them from invading Daenia. She hopes one day to push all of the goblins out of Glenumbra.
Wyress Jacinta was glad to know the source of the spriggan uprising, but she's worried about the role of the Bloodthorn adepts. They're corrupting spriggans, and that can't be good.
Wyress Zoe thanked me for returning the Wyrd Tree to the wyresses. She's promised me that by restoring their glen's purity, they can drive out the Reach magic that has overwhelmed Glenumbra.
I delivered High Priestess Vendialara's blessed bell to High Kinlord Maldarawo, head of the Isque Kinship.

When I returned to Wyress Janett after destroying the barrels of goblin poison, she offered one last warning. Janett doesn't believe the goblins could devise such a poison on their own. She believes someone powerful is pulling their strings.
Warden Rielle feels her deputy learned much from shadowing me while we slew monsters around Aldcroft, and thanked me for helping her train one of Aldcroft's newest protectors.

When I told Wyress Gwen the spirits' words, she realized the corruption's source. Angof, the man the spirits mentioned, is a powerful Reachmage. Necromancy has tainted his Reach magic. nnAngof is the true source of High Rock's corruption.

Lord Magister Averos complimented me on my success in slaying the Prowling Werewolves threatening Aldcroft. He believes my talents will be of great help in retaking the plagued city of Camlorn and removing the threat to High Rock.
When I returned the missing silk bedsheets to Chamberlain Weller, he seemed glad to have them.

I destroyed the mortal bodies of the fallen as Aldridge asked. Now they can't be raised as undead.nnFather Aldridge worries about the words of the spirits and the corruption of the tarn. This blight could have caused the undead wolves.
I found and killed several bog lurchers and harvested rare ingredients for the Alchemist Shava. My bag still smells of the nasty stuff.
I spoke with Sibellec on behalf of Duke Sebastien. She will aid him by distracting the swamp creatures only  if I help her first.
Sibellec the Swamp Witch, driven from her home by Bog Lurchers, asked for my assistance in slaying them.nnBy killing these creatures, I am enabling the Magis Order to concentrate on retaking Camlorn.

Sibellec mixed a potion in my absence - the Cinnabar Yellow Caps were the final ingredient. Sibellec believes that if I use the potion to see into the past, to visit the memories of the dead, I may find a clue that will lead us to Ehlnofic Lens.
While investigating the Mud-cloaked Hags' Dens in the swamp, I found a Thorn which Sibellec found very interesting.
I collected Mandrake Roots for the Alchemist Shava.  The swamps were too dangerous for her to venture into alone.
I located the Order's Alchemist, Thetis, at Lord Magister Averos' request.nnI'll help the alchemist in any way I can.

The spirit of Coty Danain told me about the Cave of Penance, an ancient place where Raven Direnni often went to meditate. Some time after she passed, it became a haven for Namira worshippers.nnCoty believes the thief fled there with the Werereaver.
According to Sibellec, the Unusual Thorn I found in the swamp is infused with Angof's Reach magic. Angof, a Reach mage of great power, is somehow spreading a corruption throughout High Rock.

When I recovered Werereaver from Angof's thief, a vision of Raven Direnni spoke to me from ages past. She asked me to keep the legendary sword, so I could wield it against Faolchu and his spawn. She entrusted the safety of the kingdom to me.
After I slew the wild boar that had drawn off all of the trappers' pigs, they assured me they will no longer poach deer.

Forester Seleine Brehat sent me to check on poaching in the Daenia woods.  I found a poacher's arrow, and was told it belonged to Felix Glenan, who I chose to let go with a warning.nnFelix sent me to his wife for some stew as a thank you.

<<1>> was very pleased to hear that I stopped Red Rook bandits from stealing corpses. He gave me a bit of coin for my trouble, and he promised to pass on word of my efforts to <<2>> when he returns to camp.

I've given a valuable ring back to Didier Panoit, who then informed me that Warden Moreau had something to do with it being stolen. I've confirmed this with Moreau, who claims to feel sorry for what he has done, and has begged me to keep his secret.

<<1>> was pleased to hear I dealt with the undead wolves attacking the Lion Guard camp. He's certain that because I've dealt with them, it should be easier for the Lion Guard to concentrate on retaking Camlorn.
I spoke with Telenger, as Langdruun requested.
I spoke with Telenger, as Langdruun requested.

Ashby was shocked to hear the news about Marie. Apparently, they're sisters. Ashby thought Marie was dead for five long years, but now that Ashby knows Marie is alive, she has vowed to find her and lift her curse.

Thetis and I discovered that his redwort potion will kill undead wolves. Armed with this knowledge, Thetis is preparing a plan to cleanse the tarn and remove the scourge of undead wolves from Glenumbra.
I found the rightful owner of the Thierry family ring. Warden Thierry seemed very grateful for its return.

Magus Commander Danain contacted me via a magical projection once I placed the last beacon. Though grieved by Nightblade Channing's death, he thanked me for activating the beacons. They provide a clear view of Camlorn, making invasion easier.

I have used Thetis's redwort potion on the thorny vines around the tarn to begin the cleansing. Thetis thanked me for my help. He'll remain at the Cambray Tarn to mix more potions and complete the cleansing over the next few days.
With the powerful Magis Order sighting gem at my disposal, I called down fireballs on the Werewolf Behemoths of Camlorn and then slew them, opening a clear path to Danain's soldiers.

I was able to clear the marshes near Aldcroft of a number of Will-O-the-Wisps.nnIf they have any connection to Anghof remains to be seen, but at least the marshes are safer for soldiers and travelers.
I made an offering for the spirit of Raymond Geotene. He was killed by Namira, despite his faithful worship. Despite this, she will forgive him, and his spirit will never rest.
I found a functioning Varla Lens in the wreckage of Landbreaker and brought it back to the High Kinlord. He was immensely pleased.
While I recovered the book Ameralee requested, I returned to find her turned to stone. In her stead, I brought the book to the High Kinlord.

Velanya told me that one of the items needed to repair the Var Lens was a chapter from the tome "Varlines and Vartisans."nnThe book sprang to life when I touched it! After subduing it, I was able to rip the relevent pages out.

Vartisan Ameralee brought Varyllis' damaged Varla Lens to her old mentor Hainen, seeking his help with the repairs. Instead, he turned her to stone, and retreated to his Sanctum bearing the Lens. Fortunately, I was able to recover it.
When I located Vartisan Ameralee, she had been turned to stone by her mentor, HainennnAt the suggestion of her student, alcantar, I created an elixir of nimbleberries to cure her condition.
I used the Focuser on the Varla Lens. With Ameralee's help, the Lens rose into its proper place, restoring the Varyllis Varline.
I found Telenger overlooking the beach at the Deadsands. Indeed, there seems to be a horde of dripping Zombies lurching up from the depths.
I have killed five Drowned Zombies, as Liralen requested.
I recovered Fulgurite from the Deadsands and brought it to Telenger, who used it to power his Sload-luring device.
I used Telenger's Lure to dispatch the Sload troubling Varyllis. Hopefully its death will staunch the flow of Drowned Zombies onto the beach.
I destroyed several Sload Larva Sacs in the shoals near the Pearls. The presence of the Sacs proved that a Sload is behind the Zombie menace.
At Telenger's request, I notified Kinlord Langdruun that a Sload was behind the evils of the Deadsands.
Battlereeve Heldarmo expressed his pleasure at receiving any help he could get, although he seems doubtful of my ability.
I dispatched several Maormer Scouts using the Irradiant Jewel to spot them.
I put five Earth Atronachs out of their Maormer-induced misery, burying their souls in Mundus Fissures, thus giving them the peace they desired.
I mined Dawnshards from Nodules on the ridge of he Stonewake and brought them to Sorceress Andria, so that she might continue supporting the Verdant Grove Tower unassisted.
Melodian Fiannalor was grateful to see I have arrived in Isque. The region could benefit from my support.
I slew Stormwitches on the Tessellated Shores.The defenses are safe for the nonce.
I charged the Tesselated Grid with Imbued Stones, channeling magicka into our defenses.
The Maormer will repair the pillars, but they are not a threat for now.
The Mage thanked me for delivering Daedric Soul Gems to him. I can count on his cooperation with the Serpent.
I returned the stolen Varla Lens to the Vartisan Urselor.
Kinlady Genivra was grateful for my help with restoring Nirn.
The Thief was grateful for my deliver of Fire Salts. He promised they would be put to a hazardous yet entertaining use.
Skyharker Nureva was able to glimpse the planet and explained that it is made of the same materials as their own planets. She also mentioned she felt something or someone was inside of Orgnavar...
I retrieved the Irradiant Jewel from the Landbreaker and delivered it to Battlereeve Heldarmo.
The Mage is eager to examine the debris I brought him, though now the Rogue Discarnates may be re-bound so that he can no longer harvest their Daedric Soul Gems.
The Atronach is thankful to be whole again. It claims a Stormwitch destroyed it.
Vartisan Urselor was pleased to hear one more threat to the Orrery has been removed.
Skyharker Vilmo was saddened by the death of his former teacher. He hopes her soul will find solace in knowing that they both sought the same goal: the restoration of the Orrery.
Vilmo read Suuniqwe's book he seems confused, frightened. He seems the same as the Starblind Altmer.
Vartisan Urselor explained the artifact was in fact a Maormer Snake-Wizard's staff, and is probably all that remains of the Snake-Wizard.

When I met Magus Commander Danain at the Redoubt, he was grateful for the offer of help. He stated that the greatest threat facing the Magis Order right now is General Faolchu, an undead werewolf king who has conquered Camlorn.
I was able to find the Meteoric Glass Melodian Fiannalor needs to begin to craft a Blessed Bell, a magic weapon.
Battlereeve Nenwe was impressed with my delivery of the Serpent's Heart. He vowed this deed would be long remembered.

Magus Commander Danain thanked me for aiding the Magis Order against General Faolchu's mindless werewolf army. Though Faolchu's plague of lycanthropy has not ended, Danain feels we have taken a significant step against it.

Battlereeve Artulion asked me to help train one of his young soldiers. With the boy at my side, we slew many Maormer on their sourthern beachead in Dusk.nnAfterwards, Artulion had another task that required my attention.

Now that General Faolchu is dead, the Lion Guard can retake Camlorn in short order. Magus Commander Danain praised my heroism in saving Camlorn. He says he'll speak to the High King himself of my deeds.
Warden Rielle feels her deputy learned much from shadowing me while we slew monsters around Aldcroft, and thanked me for helping her train one of Aldcroft's newest protectors.
The Warrior thanked me for protecting his soul gem from the Maormer invaders.

Battlereeve Artulion asked me to board the Maormer Flagship and slay one of their commanders. With the help of the Sorcercess Rolantae, I was able to complete his mission, throwing the Maormer in southern Dusk into confusion.
Muriel Eardswulf's old Breton cure of Wolfsbane mixed with Liquid Silver cured the Magis Order soldier and prevented him from turning into a Werewolf.
I escorted the traveler safely back to Aldcroft.nnWarden Rielle speculated that he was lured out into the moors by Will-O-the-Wisps.
I bathed the Starglass in the Sky-Well, then delivered it to the Isquer Kinhouse.
I took Medallions from the Maormer Marines on the south beach of Dusk, and gave them to Battlereeve Artulion to raise the morale of his soldiers.
Maormer siege engines on Sunhold have been hurling Contagious Cadavers into the Orchestrated Gardens of Isque. At the request of Priestess Meloria, I put many of the Cadavers to the torch.

Now that I've slain Coren's risen body and returned his locket to Blanche, she believes Coren is finally at peace. Though she will never forget him, Blanche can go on with her life. One day they will meet again... beyond Aetherius.
Apothecary Bella's cure of Foxglove Nectar mixed with Liquid Silver did not cure  the Magis Order soldier. He immediately turned into a Werewolf.
I braved the Aldmeri Crypts and recovered the ancient pieces of the shattered Triumvial Crown.
I have convicned Optimate Illira not to end her life. She has rejoined her daughter, Exultant Elleste at the Felballin Kinhouse.
Optimate Illira was resolved to join her son in death. She asked me to respect her choice, and I did exactly that.
Benedict was put at ease when I told him I spread the flowers from his father's birth tree on his father's grave in Cath Bedraud.
I located Gerard Tenant's Pick-ax in the Crosswych Mine. Although it is filled with undead now, soon the people of Crosswych hope to retake the mine and bring prosperity back.

Sapiarch Lilia asked Declaen to collect a toxin called Opalescence from Gem Spiders. Declaen, who is afraid of spiders, asked me to do this in his stead.nnLilia mentioned the toxin would be used to poison the blades of Altmer soldiers.
Apothecary Bella's cure of Foxglove Nectar mixed with Liquid Silver did not cure  the Magis Order soldier. He immediately turned into a Werewolf.
Muriel Eardswulf's old Breton cure of Wolfsbane mixed with Liquid Silver cured the Magis Order soldier and prevented him from turning into a Werewolf.

The Priestess Vendialara asked Melodian Liriondion of the Isque Kinhouse for Isque Roses.nnLiriondion sent Discarnates, but a tremor in the Varline caused them to become rogues; they attacked the roses instead. I cut and delivered the blossoms.
The spices that Colette the Alchemist poisoned were meant for the Magis Order. I destroyed the spices and informed the Wardens in Aldcroft.
I delivered the Requisition to Vartisan Taarifil as requested, but learned that the Varla Lens had recently been stolen.
Marcel was pleased by the bones I gathered from Angof's undead creatures, and will use it to create a good supply of bonemeal for the Magis Order to use against the rest of Angof's undead.
I've burned the zombies of Cath Bedraud. The lieutenant complimented me on my work. He said my heroic actions earned his respect and impressed the soldiers at the redoubt.
Not only was Mother Murk very real, she was unhappy that the people of Crosswych no longer believed in her.  I killed her just in time to stop her perpetuating worse mischief than she already has.
I dispatched Rogue Discarnates who had stolen from the Anquillius Forge, and returned the valuable ores to the rightful owner.
I slew an innocent Kirin and contributed its Horn to create an echanted weapon.
I slew a Giant Sea Serpent and contributed its Fang to the forging of an enchanted weapon.

Priestess Ahlotica at the Fane of Breath asked me to find the missing book "Psalms of Old Ehnolfey." Unfortunately, another young priestess found it first, and was driven mad by it. I was forced to defend myself from her crazed assaults.
I returned the completed rubbings to Lith, who thanked me for my excellent work. She told me that should I ever need work, I should speak to the Mages Guild.

The Lion Guard doesn't rely purely on magic. They also enchant items to enhance their potency against the undead. Knight Adept Dolbanitte claims that a Lion Guard's blessed arrow can drop an undead with a single shot.
Darene Charascel's son Arturo died within Crosswych's mine. He apparently died a hero's death, fighting to the end. Darene was grateful to finally know what happened to her son.
I retrieved the smithing tools from the maze, much to the relief of Apprentice Braefurn.
Marcel was pleased to see the dormant Midnight Talisman. He believes that he can reactivate it. It should finally give us the power we need to defeat Angof.
Magus Commander Panoit and his soldiers were inspired by my defense of the Lion Guard banner. nnAngof must certainly know that our triumph heralds his destruction.
I've harvested mort flesh from risen miners in the Crosswych Mines.
Outside the Dwynnarth Ruins in High Rock I met Scholar Lael Corgine. She asked me to enter the Ruins and return with a collection of Welkynd Stones which she needed for her research into the undead.
I found Battlereeve Artulion and offered him my assistance.
I located the Midnight Talisman in Crosswych Mine. Arnand Murrell told me the power of the talisman is dormant. It must be reactivated. To do this, I must head to the Lion Guard redoubt.
Darene Charascel's son Arturo died within Crosswych's mine. Darene was grateful to finally know what happened to her son.
Ahlotica asked me to inform High Priestess Vendialara that one of the other young priestess was driven mad, and tragically died.

Magus Commander Panoit was surprised to see the Midnight Talisman restored, but pleased to hear that I can wield it against Angof. He's pledged that his forces will support me in our final push, so we can defeat Angof once and for all.
I have killed more Noxious Nereids from the Liriel River.

I assisted Scholar Lael with her research in the Ruins. She asked me to defend a Welkynd Stone but it mysteriously vanished after a minute. She theorized that these Stones summoned the undead but we discovered Spectres actually seek to destroy them.
It appears Suuniqwe survived the attack on the Steed's Constellation. I gave her the Steed's soul gem for safe keeping.

Many of the Nerieds in the Liriel River of Isque have fallen prey to diseases spawned by Contagious Cadavers the Maormer send into Isque.nnI fought Thoe, an unusally old and powerful Neried, and delivered her head to Melodian Liriondion.
When I used the Potion of True Nature on the citizens of Camlorn, I revealed several werewolf spies. Averos was relieved to know the spies are now gone.
High Priestess Vendialara at the Fane of Breath was preparing a Blessed Bell for the Kinlord of Isque. She asked me to forge starglass in a cave protected by Nereids.
I checked the Crosswych Mine's support beams for Miner Marthe Yvienne. They appeared in relatively good repair.

Magus Commander Panoit was alarmed to learn that the Angof was a minion of Malog Bal, a Daedric prince. Even so, he believes Angof's death has foiled Molag Bal's plans for Glenumbra. For today, at least, we'll celebrate.

In Crosswych, a man named Verick asked me to deliver his notes on Welkynd stones and the Ayleid ruins to Scholar Lael. When I arrived at the ruins southeast of Crosswych, Lael said she might have more work for me.
Ackers was pleased to hear I recovered the Thornbane Cloak. He believes it will aid us in the fight against Angof.
<<1>> was pleased to hear that I resolved the dispute between Al'kari and Gulitte. He expects it will only be a temporary solution, but for the moment, Derran can concentrate on bigger threats.

Watchman Derran was pleased to hear that I resolved the dispute between Al'kari and Gulitte. He expects it will only be a temporary solution, but for the moment, Derran can concentrate on bigger threats.
I killed Gem Spiders to thin out the exploding population for Head Keeper Calnemin in the Phidian Menagerie.
I delivered the core of Auri-El to High Kinlady Astraela.
I tracked down a wild Kirin and lured it back to the Phidian Menagerie. It is now the crown jewel of their extensive wildlife collection.
The plans I found could only mean one thing: the Aldmeri Dominion is invading Glenumbra.
With the support of the Guardian Exemplars, I will now attempt to retrieve the Varla Lens from the belly of the Serpent.

I've found Nightblade Ackers at the edge of some ancient ruins. He has found out a bit about the artifact Magus Commander Danain believes may be Angof's bane - the Midnight Talisman - but will need my help to retrieve it.
Suuniqwe believes she still has much to teach Skyharker Vilmo. She believes he can be "enlightened".
