I spoke to the courier, who told me of a "Great House" that House Dres served. I should inform Naryu of what I've discovered.
I spoke to <<1>> about purchasing new guar for <<2>>at the Nipperkin plantation.
I escorted Arnoit Sidrey to Eagle's Gate. Then I realized that he and his beloved are ghosts.
I found an Imperial ambassador in Blacksap Village. He was negotiating with the treacherous Blacksap Bosmer.nnI also found a cultist statue of Molag Bal and freed an Altmer prisoner.
I've killed some goblins and discovered the fate Brek's crew. He's got another task for me: kill the Dremora that killed his crew.
Brek and his crew no longer have to worry about Daedra threats.  Brek says they'll be able to take back the mine eventually.
The <<1>> told me how the Balac can be restored. Now I must undertake a new journey, traveling to the Anchor Towers of Tamriel, in order to fix the broken staff.
I found <<1>>. She had stayed behind to rescue some of the other students.

I traveled to the Crystal Tower of Summerset Isle and navigated through magic traps and ghostly guardians until I came upon the tower's foundation stone, Crystal-like-Law. I then charged the Balac upon the stone, filling it with power.
I delivered water to the watchtower. The guard thanked me and offered me a reward for my time.
<<1>> gave me a sack of kindlepitch to burn Imperial supplies on the beach west of Southpoint.
I recovered the <<1>> from the Imperial Landing and presented them to MONSTER:2132)<<.>>
I've broken the link for the zTestContent propylon network informed Miner Brek of my exploits.
I ventured into the depths of the Canulus Refuge and secured the magical staff known as the Balac.nnI then returned to Lyris Titanborn's hideout and handed the staff over to the Prophet.
I traveled to the capital city and eventually found the hideout of <<1>> and the Prophet.
I helped the Altmer by driving off spriggans and wisps. They were disrupting Altmer rituals in Spritedancer Marsh.
I retrieved several power crystals from an Imperial Scout camp in Spritedancer Marsh.
I helped <<1>> protect the farm by burning many of the carcasses that littered the fields. Hopefully the sickness from Evermore will stay within the city walls now.
I've reactivated the wards. That should prevent the Imperial Army from moving through Spritedancer Marsh into Elden Root.

Nerien'eth, the Architect of the Crypt of Hearts, has been using stolen corpses in his necromantic experiments. Delia was glad I solved her mystery except the answer was worse than anyone could have imagined.
The spirit wardens need my help east of the abbey at the Moonlit Maw.

I found an old letter from an ancestor of the Perroult family to her son, warning him of dangers in the fabled city of Heartland. There was a relative still living in Hoarfrost Downs. She was grateful to have this missive, even many years late.
I helped the farmhands at Evermoor Farms recover some of their lost cattle though my farm dog friend did most of the work.
I advised Queen Arzhela about possible candidates to act as the Regent of Evermore. In the end, she chose her sister, Lady Nadine Lia.
I safely escorted the Minister of War out of Evermore's dungeon.
I defeated Evermore's tax collector in single combat. The Bjoulsae Queen did not have to pay taxes this time.
I defeated the Bjoulsae Queen's sailor in single combat. The ship must pay Evermore's taxes.
With <<1>> out of the way, <<2>> will need to clear up the problem of where the bodies of the Evermore's dead have gone.
I helped Wyress Reinette perform a curative ritual. She summoned a spirit, and it told us Evermore's hope lies in curing Princess Elara.
I found Gurles Edier in the Viridian Woods.
I poured Clemence Silain's potion into the Evermore Farms well.

The Singer claims that she didn't willingly lure villagers into the cave. Instead, she says a Dremora, Kynreeve Bakar, enslaved her and forced her to lure new followers for Bakar's master, Hermaeus Mora.
I sold the clannfear claws I collected to Edouard.

After I killed The Singer, Kynreeve Bakar was waiting for me outside the room where she was trapped. He thanked me for stopping her. Then he promised me that all who wish to worship Hermaeus Mora can do so now without being lured away.

After I killed Kynreeve Bakar, I found The Singer waiting for me outside the room where he was hiding. She thanked me for freeing her. She promised no more villagers would be lured under the sway of Hermaeus Mora.
While I was investigating the attacks made on Evermore Farms, the area was once again assaulted by Reachmen. I was unfortunately unable to save the farmer and his people.
I destroyed abandoned cargo and killed looters around Emberquay for <<1>>.
You did it!! That Pesky Wolf man got his butt kicked!! Would you happen to have picked up my laundry?

The mysterious afflliction plaguing Stonefalls infected the Grenstick kwama mine. At the behest of <<1>>, I investigated to see how deeply the disease ran. As it turned out, every kwama in the mine was infected.
I sold the clannfear claws I collected to Edouard.
I crossed the River Bjoulsae and found evidence of the Reachmen there.
After slaying the <<1>>, I recovered an egg from her corpse with signs of the affliction plaguing Stonefalls. <<2>> was grateful I brought it to her attention.

Gurles Edier, the former Viridian Sentinel, sacrificed his life in order to save Princess Elara of Evermore. By making Elara the new Viridian Sentinel, Gurles was able to at last cure her of the sickness which would have otherwise killed her.
The crew of the abandoned ship at Emberquay were skooma dealers. They fled overboard with their merchandise when they learned House Redoran ordinators were planning to examine their cargo.
Abandoned shipments of skooma are leaking their contents into the tide pools. They're causing Dreugh and mudcrabs at <<1>> to behave strangely.
<<1>> proved that the chitin samples showed signs of disease. That means <<2>> is not safe.
I collected crab legs for <<1>> and his family during their quarantine.
I discovered that Hlorin's daughter, Adrusa, was killed in the eruption of Mt. Senie. Her father will be devastated.
I killed Reachmen, then reported to Constable Didier. He thanked me and offered me a reward for my service to Bangkorai.
I found the Chief Constable tied up in the lighthouse. He's too injured to move, but he thanked me for saving his villagers.
I found one of the slaves at the kwama mine locked in a cage. <<1>>  begged me to escort him out past afflicted kwama and vicious guards.
I found the lighthouse lamp and destroyed it. The  Chief Constable thanked me for my efforts to protect Bangkorai.

I found a chewed up piece of parchment carried by a forest troll, which turned out to be a map. Following the map's directions, I traveled to the Ayleid ruins in northern Bangkorai and there uncovered a buried crate packed full of Ayleid relics.
I returned the four tomes of ancient knowledge to Elmedros. He paid me for my trouble and bid me leave, claiming he needed to prepare himself mentally to absorb the knowledge in the recovered books.
I found Jharad's journal in the lighthouse. Now that it's been destroyed, no one can use the information Jharad collected against Bangkorai.
I've set fire to the inn, the pub, and the Mayor's house in Dunkarn Haven. I've reported to a constable at the camp southeast of Dunkarn Village.
I've confronted the two people responsible for the state of the northern district. I discussed this with Miluru Redoran in the Mages Guild to the east.
I've found Savure's wife and children. I should return to him in the Tribunal temple and make sure they made it there safely.
I met Gurles Edier in his house in the Viridian Woods. He expressed sadness that the spriggan, whom he called "Greenthing" was dead. He suggested we work together to find a cure for the plague.
I destroyed many of the Bloodthorn creatures which infest the fishing village along the Bjoulsae River, north of Evermore.
Hayz was pleased with my success in placing the false orders in the Reachmen camp. He says that every day we keep the Reachmen confused is one more day Evermore has to prepare to eventual attack.

Barkul was greatly pleased by my victory over Brinarch, the Soultaker. She believes the now leaderless will fall apart in short order, allowing Evermore's remaining forces to push them back into the north.

I searched the Reachmen-occupied village and found a cure to the wasting disease they've introduced here. However, when I returned to the sick villager who asked me to find the cure, he had already passed away.
I traveled to Dunkarn Haven in order to warn them of the marauding Reachmen. Unfortunately I was too late; the town was already taken.
The box has been clicked, meaning has flooded your life.

I fought off angry Reachmen while a comrade in arms set fire to the unconsecrated corpses of several unfortunate villagers. With the corpses turned to ash, the Reachmen will no longer be able to raise them as undead monsters.
I hid a magical listening stone inside a house occupied by Reachmen. With the stone in place, Evermore will be able to overhear everything those Reachmen are planning.
Victims of the plague afflicting Stonefalls fill the valley around the Kagesh village. Some of them have become angry and violent. I burned their shelters to drive them away.
I set fire to several carts full of corpses, to fulfill the dying wish of a villager. Now the Reachmen will not be able to use the deceased for necromancy.

My warning came too late. Bangkorai Garrison fell to the Imperials long before I arrived. King Eamond is dead, and the Evermore army is in retreat.nnA few soldiers seem willing to fight on, but the rest want to return to Evermore.
I collect sufficient sigil stones and returned them to Kastus Valtieri in Evermore. He was pleased and offered me a reward.
I collected all of the ancient lore books and returned them to Thorley Masterston in Evermore. He thanked me and gave me a reward.
<<1>> had a guar herd. Her animals died in the eruption of Mount Senie .I gathered harnesses from her dead guar and slaughtered scamps nearby.
Barkul gra-Shugurz was grateful to me for killing the Hands of the Reach, and promised to use what I've learned against other Reachmen in Bangkorai. Without his Hands, Brinarch is crippled.
I returned the box to the old hermit. He spoke to it like a pet, and promised it there would be "plenty of souls for you when the Planemeld comes."nnBefore I could ask him what he meant, he vanished!
I've found Erena's spirit and informed her of Taros' vigil in Othrenis. Taros' undying love was not unrequited. Though they both harbored regret, they've found a measure of solace. They're happy now.
I killed many trolls in the Viridian Woods, to help protect an old healer named <<1>>.
I gathered ingredients from the Viridian Woods for an herbal tonic. The drink managed to wake Princess Elara from her fever.
I collected rations and gave them to a prisoner in the pens.
After finding an injured traveler named <<1>> in the Viridian Woods, I traveled north to the town of Dunkarn Haven to inform his wife of what befell her husband.
I killed the slave bosses and returned to the prisoners. They thanked me for avenging their mistreatment.
<<1>> was ravaged by the disease. Whatever is spreading the sickness is infecting both Ashlanders and House Dunmer.

When I confronted Father Ergend with his own skull, he was shocked. Though he denied it at first, he gradually remembered how he was murdered by Daedraphiles. Now moved on, and taken his congregation with him, including Barahar.
I collected proof of my deeds and returned to <<1>> in Evermore. He thanked me and gave me a reward.
After freeing several captives, I returned to <<1>>. She's been taken captive again.
I collected trophies and returned them to Pierre Dupree in Evermore. He thanked me and gave me a reward.
I administered the antidote to <<1>> before it was too late. She thanked me for all of my help and offered me a reward.
<<1>> asked me to search a wise woman's yurt for a cure to a deadly illness. I didn't find one, but I did find religious writings suggesting that the Kagesh worship the Daedric Prince Boethiah.

I found the master of which the keening box, an old hermit.nnHe spoke to whatever was in the box like a pet. He promised it there would be "plenty of souls for you when the Planemeld comes."nnBefore I could ask him what he meant, he vanished!
I found the last will and testament of Lord Orlane Lia on the body of Grigoros, a necromancer. I took the will to its beneficiary, Lady Nadine Lia of Evermore.
I helped Father Ayham ward the remaining unguarded doors to Pelin Temple's deep crypts. Those interred there are no longer in danger. The roaming undead can no longer defile their graves.
Acting on behalf of one of the city's residents, I petitioned Wyress Reinette of Evermore for healing
I've taken the journey to Ebonheart. It's west of Davon's Watch and Emberquay. The harbormaster needed to know that Alva Bedenia won't be picking up her shipments.

I stopped the evil spirits of the Ripper, the Crusher, and the Feeder. They're bound again, safely locked away. Father Hurrent told me Stenric's grandmother was a priest of Arkay who hunted evil spirits. They've watched over her captives ever since.
The Kagesh tribe tend a shrine for the Daedric Prince Boethiah. Tribunal ordinators blocked Kagesh pilgrims from visiting the Shrine. At the wise woman's behest, I asked them to leave.
I've collected several enlistment medals from the soldiers' bodies around Fort Arand. I brougtht them to Ivulas Vir within the fort, so he can arrange a memorial service.
I've immolated nests about Fort Arand. The mender who sent me was pleased.
The mender was alarmed at the state of the cliff racer hearts, and asked me to inform the captain. She said the cliff racers carry some vile disease, and that might be the cause of their madness.
I've delivered medical supplies to Erenen Sals, the captain of the fort.

I agreed with Sir Dencent and gave him the parts he needed to raise King Eamond as a revenant. Sir Dencent gave me a charm I can use to call to King Eamond at Bangkorai Garrison. Once there, he'll aid me against the Imperials.
I agreed with Father Hurrent and Queen Therese. Father Hurrent gave me a charm I can use to summon Queen Therese at Bangkorai Garrison. Once I'm there, she can aid me against the Imperials.
I've delivered the cliff racer to Ralmas. The captain is waiting for the results of his examination.
I found one of the slaves at the kwama mine locked in a cage. <<1>> begged me to help him escape, but I returned him to his legal owner, <<2>>.

I met an Evermore soldier named Awyeh. She's convinced that Evermore's surviving soldiers should retake Bangkorai Garrison, rather than retreating to Evermore. She thinks the Imperials have overextended themselves and are vulnerable.
I freed <<1>> from the Orlishkaarn Ashlander camp.
I recovered supplies from an Orlishkaarn Ashlander camp and redistributed them to the Dunmer workers.
I helped Kerbol's Mill by clearing out many wolves near his mill in Bangkorai.
I gained Hircine's blessing and the tonic that will keep Evermore's soldiers from becoming werewolves. Loraine thanked me for my help.

After Agnes turned into a werewolf, a guard attacked out of fear. I stopped the attack. Captain Renoit thanked me for sparing the soldiers. He's almost convinced Virgil has a cure, but he accepts that his orders are orders.
Loraine Themond thanked me for gathering silver bark and making the ashes she needed for her poultices. She said I've helped many injured people.
I found Raiyad at the Fallen Grotto and delivered the offering from Kerbol's Mill. Raiyad promised to sacrifice it to Hircine on their behalf, and he thanked me for bringing it.
The Orlishkaarn Ashlanders won't lay claim to the murder of the House Redoran Hortator. <<1>> believes the truth is only known by the Hortator. Talking to the dead may prove difficult.
I spoke to <<1>> in Othrenis. I told her <<2>> sent me to help.
I went to the Conclave of the Inoculates and returned a pendant to <<1>>.
I've slain Orlishkaarn outside Fort Virak. Urvian's comrades have been avenged.

I met a magical storyteller who showed me the Legend of Fallen Grotto. She enabled me to assume an Aspect of Hircine, Daedric Prince of the Hunt. In his guise, I chased down servants glamoured as the children of Edam and captured them like animals.
I've delivered wayward correspondence to men stationed at the fort. I should let the captain of Fort Virak know.
I've travelled to Senie to tell House Cousin Rerynia she won't be getting aid from Fort Arad anytime soon.
I've freed Lieutenant Eris and her men.
<<1>> revealed he had purposefully sent corrupted medicine all over Stonefalls. I defeated him, but he's not the only one involved.
The shipments leaving Fort Virak are contaminated with a virulent disease.

I killed the Imperial centurion commanding troops on Bangkorai's northern wall. The Imperials are disorganized. Now Evermore's army can launch a counterattack. I must lead them in retaking the garrison courtyard.

<<1>> had no desire to end the standoff at the Shrine of Boethiah with a slaughter. He sent me to negotiate a solution with <<2>> of the Kagesh tribe. Unfortunately, she refused to abandon the shrine or allow the Tribunal ordinators to destroy it.
I met Archmage Suriel at the entrance to Bangkorai Garrison's southern wall. With Imperial leaders dead, the Imperial ranks are already disintegrating.

I met Arch-Mage Suriel at the entrance to Bangkorai Garrison's southern wall. She said I made the right choice in destroying the ballistae. We could't risk the possibility the Imperials would use them against Evermore's army.
I met Archmage Suriel at the entrance within Bangkorai Garrison's southern wall. She thanked me for burning the Imperial banners. She's confident their loss has lowered the morale of our enemies.

I met Loraine Themond in Kerbol's Village. She's been caring for the soldiers in Kerbol's Village since the attack. She can mix the cure that will save the soldiers, but she warned me the cure will soon be useless.

Captain Baridan and Archmage Suriel credited my heroism and bravery. I led Evermore's forces retaking Bangkorai Garrison. Evermore is now safe, and the Imperials will think twice before making another attack.
I found the wood wisps hiding around the Viridian Woods and spoke with them of the troubles in the forest. They all had varying opinions, but agreed that the Sentinel was doing nothing to stop it.

I gave the parts I collected to Sir Dencent. He promised to remember my service to Evermore. He'll complete the ritual to deal with the undead after settling an argument with Father Hurrent, a priest of the temple.
The Ordinators will be pleased with the passing of <<1>>.nnI hate to get involved in matters of the spirit, but a contract is a contract.

Unable to negotiate a peaceful solution, Ordinator Ulden's troops attacked the Kagesh tribe at the Shrine of Boethiah.nnThe Ashlanders prevailed, driving the Ordinators off with heavy losses. The ordinator camp is filled with wounded mer.

Unable to negotiate a peaceful solution, Ordinator Ulden's troops attacked the Kagesh tribe at the Shrine of Boethiah.nnOrindators prevailed, slaughtering the Ashlander tribesmen. The shrine is now in the hands of Ulden's men.
I interrogated a <<1>> and learned that the Imperial Army is having trouble resupplying <<2>>.
I identified two spies tampering with the Evermore soldiers' supplies and dealth with them for <<1>>.
King Eamond of Evermore died in the battle at Bangkorai Garrison. His body was taken to Pelin Temple.
When I went to Kerbol's Mill to check on a lumber shipment, I found that some of Evermore's soldiers are holding the Mill's workers captive.
I've helped many of the Redguards soldiers rest in peace and returned to the Redguard immortal. He thanked me for easing his fellow soldiers' suffering.
This mage thought throwing away his illegal wares would save him. He's been ranting to Saajin about "legality" and "proof," but Saajin can see the evidence with his own eyes.

I made an offering to the Huntsmen within the Fallen Grotto, in the form of a severed head belonging to a legendary beast. Now they have accepted me as a hunter like them, and will forever after allow me to pass through the Fallen Grotto unharmed.
I found a letter from <<1>> to Davon's Watch. I returned it to her.
The medicine the apothecaries were selling had no effect on the disease. I delivered a soothing tea to <<1>>, but his wife had already passed on.
I helped a man avenge his wife.
I found evidence of a skooma den in Ebonheart. I've reported it to <<1>>.
The escaped Dres slaves burned their own shelters during the revolt. <<1>> asked for my help collecting wood to keep everyone warm.
I fulfilled the dying wish of a young Redguard named Raiyeem. I slaughtered the crocodiles that killed him and harvested meat from their carcasses.
I found evidence against Harbormaster Irano and delivered the warrant for his arrest to <<1>>.
I discovered that shipments of skooma may be tainted with the disease.
I delivered a letter to <<1>> at the shrine to Boethiah.
I delivered supplies to <<1>> at Vivec's Antlers.

I found Malumud, one of the few able-bodied Redguards capable of protecting the Redguard refugees. Many of the refugees are old, sick, or injured. Only a few heroes like Malumud and Ruhsul are able to protect them.

The Imperial spy I discovered carried a personal journal, which revealed plans for a raid on the mustering camp's supply depot. <<1>>, the Lion Guard's commander, believed it was a fake. When the raid arrived, I was able to handle it myself.

At the request of <<1>>, I infiltrated the Dres compound to slay the cruel <<2>>.nnFortune had already seen to her punishment, however. nnShe had caught the affliction plaguing Stonefalls. She was locked within her chambers, mindless and raving.
I carried out Jahtinjah's plan: stealing Reach banners and planting them on slain ettins.

<<1>> was interviewing soldiers wounded in the battle at Bangkorai Garrison. He wants to gain intelligence on the Imperials. I helped and turned in my notes to <<2>>.nnWhile conducting interviews, I  revealed an Imperial spy.
With my help, the three sisters escaped the curse laid by a powerful mage. They've moved on. Their weeping will no longer bother the refugees.

When I returned the rock salt to Malumud, he told me a thief had raided their food supplies while I was away. Malumud was certain it was a refugee. If the culprit isn't found, the others will have enough food.
To punish him for stealing food from the other refugees, I've exiled Zad from the Cave of Many Tears. Malumud has accepted my judgment. He believes the other refugees are safer now that Zad is gone.

I kept Zad's secret. Malumud was disappointed and angered by my actions. He said I had been too kind, and he believes my actions have endangered the others. However, Zad's regret seemed genuine, and I doubt he will steal again.

I found Wasafa in the Reachmen camp. He claims he can escape at any time, but he's stayed behind so he can find a way to free the other captives. He refuses to leave until the others are free. He needs my help.
I found the slave's missing mother in Hallin's Stand. She's joined the army, and she's been defending the land. She promises to retrieve her son soon.

Abandoned shipments of skooma were leaking their contents into tide pools near Emberquay. That's probably what caused the irregular behavior of the local Dreugh and mudcrabs. However, I still need physical proof.
I should travel south of Fort Virak to Heimlyn Keep. It's on top of a great mountain. Then I can question a trader named Sedrethi.
Ula-Tei and I pacified the waves of dreugh swarming the coral. He's asked me to escape the heart before the coral is disturbed once again. I should find the closest way out and leave.
I've destroyed  wanted posters for Arven the Fingers around Ebonheart and its docks.
I've collected some of the debts owed to Ferise.

I uncovered Shavari's chest and burned it. It burned far more quickly than I expected. A terrible growl came from within the chest when I ignited it. It's probably for the best that the chest was never opened.
I uncovered Shavari's chest and burned it. Something emerged. The chest is empty now, and it doesn't appear to contain any further threats.

The Dremora infesting <<1>> were summoned by an Orc sorceress named <<2>>. Following the advice of a Daedric noble, <<3>>, I rampaged through her lab until she was distracted from her experiments. Then I killed her.
At the request of a Redguard named Zunaida, I killed many Deadra in the Nilata Ruins.
I fulfilled the dying wish of a young Redguard named Raiyeem. I butchered the crocodiles that killed him. Then I took their flesh to his father, Rai'ud, in the Cave of Many Tears.

I met Loraine Themond in Kerbol's Village. She's been caring for the soldiers in Kerbol's Village since the attack. She can mix the cure that will save soldiers from becoming werewolves, but she warned me they won't have long until it's useless.
I destroyed several fire salt crates placed under the Elden Tree by the Wood-Orcs.nnBy doing this, I may have foiled a plan to destroy the Great Tree itself.

I slew <<1>>, but the portal on the surface remained open, allowing Dremora and Watchers to infest the <<2>>.nnTo end the threat, I broke the bindings protecting the portal, then flooded it with Daedric energies until it exploded.
I defeated the deranged sorceress responsible for the Daedra infesting Nilata Ruins. Then I decided Troggit was too dangerous to release. I left him trapped beneath the ruins.

Captain Renoit accepted the werewolf skulls as proof. He promised to take his soldiers back to Evermore, where he'll report the werewolf threat has been resolved. It's fortunate both Renoit and Moric Kerbol were able to see reason.

I found Janise Malyne alive and well. Constable Myn, one of Dunkarn Haven's defenders, helped her escape. Janise was relieved to find out her husband was alive. She promised to join Barnabe at the mill as soon as it's safe.
I collect sufficient sigil stones and returned them to Kastus Valtieri in Evermore. He was pleased and offered me a reward.
I recovered some medicine that was really skooma.
I exposed evidence against the harbormaster of Ebonheart Wharf.
I killed <<1>>and turned in his eyepatch in for a reward.
I rid Ebonheart of a corrupt harbormaster.
I delivered a bundle of unsent letters to <<1>> in Sugar Cove.

I freed Ala from an Imperial trap. Ala claims the Imperials have taken over the aerie and are setting traps to capture gargoyles. He was also concerned about getting all the tongues Heba requested. He claims she never lets up.

After I returned to Ala with news of the gargoyle tamer's death, he thanked me for helping Redguards everywhere. Then he gave me a small reward from Aunt Heba's collection of trinkets. He and Heba will soon move on to safer country.

<<1>> believed House Dres still trafficked in Argonian slaves, despite the laws of the Ebonheart Pact. At her request, I entered the canyons east of Omaynia and recovered proof of this, helping several captive Argonians escape in the process.
I sold the tongue to Heba, who said she could make good use of it.
I found Ufa the Red Asp. He leads a group of Redguard resistance fighters called The Hidden. They're an underground movement dedicated to pushing the Imperials out of Hallin's Stand.
I met Tribune Abheh, one of several Tribal Elders leading the nomadic Redguard desert peoples. She and her fellows are determined to drive the Imperials out of Bangkorai.
I found <<1>>. He told me about the Imperials' desecration of the Bone Fields.
I collected blossoms and offered them to the priest. He thanked me for my help and offered me a reward.
I gathered the bodies and brought them to graves the priest has prepared.
<<1>> had a plan to raise the dead and kill them. His plan is complete. He assured me they're safe now.
Bangkorai Garrison fell to attacking Imperials, who killed King Eamond of Evermore. The garrison's soldiers retreated.
<<m:1>> intends to launch a rebellion in <<2>>, but he needed more fighters to support the cause. I took to the streets with a drum to gain the attention of like-minded citizens.
I brought news to an advance scout fighting for Evermore. I told him his army will be returning to Bangkorai Garrison.
<<1>> thought someone as well-equipped as me would have no trouble killing the well-armed Dres. He was right.

One man I freed is staying in Hallin's Stand. He wants to join The Hidden in fighting the Imperials. He told me a tyrant named Vedius Curio often sent prisoners to die in the lion pits. Then he rewarded me for saving his life.
I found <<1>>, but he was fatally wounded.
I stopped a necromancer at Fort Threndr.
I delivered a flower to <<1>> in Vivec's Antlers for <<2>>.
Ufa confirmed that they key I took off <<1>> will open the door to Governor Seius' mansion on the west side of town. With the key in our possession, Ufa says it's time to rise in rebellion.
I collected mountain tail samples for <<1>>.
I defeated <<1>> to expose the obelisks in Fort Threndr. They're maintaining necromantic enchantments in the area.

While I dealt with Governor Seius, Ufa and The Hidden fought off the Imperials and retook Hallin's Stand. All Imperials in the city have fled or been killed. The city is once again under the control of the Redguards and the Daggerfall Covenant.

In Paggler's Hollow, I found a Daedric staff on the corpse of an adventurer. The staff was a terrible burden, not only because of its weight, but also because of the scamps that followed me around while I bore it. I left it on an altar to Sheogorath.
I met <<1>> in a back room at the inn at Hallin's Stand. He seems to be connected with some form of resistance to the Imperial occupation, though he remains guarded with me.

I met a Redguard merchant named Heba on the road to the aeries. She confirmed that both gargoyles and Imperials are present in the aeries. I wouldn't be surprised if the Imperials were actually training them.
I met Tribune Abheh, one of several Tribal Elders leading the nomadic Redguard desert peoples. She and her fellow s are determined to drive the Imperials out of Bangkorai.
I collected the bounties and returned them to <<1>> in Wayrest. He thanked me and gave me a reward.
I collected proof of my deeds and returned to <<1>> in Wayrest. He thanked me and gave me a reward.
I collected all of the pieces of ancient lore and returned them to <<1>> in Wayrest. He thanked me and gave me a reward.
I collected sufficient sigil stones and returned them to <<1>> in Wayrest. She was pleased and offered me a reward.
I found Danea and killed hostile creatures for Ranora.
I traveled from Nilata Ruins to a Reachmen camp in southern Bangkorai to find a Redguard. I approached <<1>> and offered my help.

<<1>> tries to keep the street lamps of Kragenmoor lit. The criminals in the lower portions of the town are constantly breaking them. I helped by fixing and lighting the lamps again.nnI fixed several, which angered the criminals.

I found a letter in a dungeon below Nilata Ruins and delivered it to an Orc named Mogra in the ruined city of Volenfell. When asked of the whereabouts of the letter's author, I lied to the Orc, claiming her sister was alive and well.

I found a letter in a dungeon below Nilata Ruins. I delivered it to an Orc named Mogra in the ruined city of Volenfell. I had the unfortunate task of telling the Orc that her sister, the letter's author, was dead.
I freed the spirits of the two brothers and restored peace to the land.

I found a letter in a dungeon below Nilata Ruins. I delivered it to an Orc named Mogra in the ruined city of Volenfell. I had the unfortunate duty of telling the Orc that her sister, the letter's author, died by my hand. She didn't believe me.

I found a letter in a dungeon below Nilata Ruins and delivered it to an Orc named Mogra in the ruined city of Volenfell. The Orc wanted to know where the letter's author was, but I told her I didn't know.
I delivered a message to <<1>> in Kragenmoor.
I collected a reward offered for the death of <<1>>, an Argonian guilty of heresy and public indecency.

I assaulted the Imperials in their dig site in Southern Bangkorai, and I seized weapons from them. Then I gave the weaponry over to Amjahan, a captive Redguard and leader of the resistance inside the camp.
At the Imperial dig site, I created a fiery distraction that allowed the Redguard captives to flee the camp and regain their freedom.
I searched the Imperial dig site for an ancient sword. One of the Redguard captives unearthed it and subsequently hid it. My search revealed the sword was missing, taken by the Imperials.
In the impoverished Gutter of Kragenmoor, I found the body of an Akaviri War veteran who had become addicted to skooma. I brought his belongings to his daughter.
I recovered an ancient sword from the Imperials at their dig site. Then I dropped it down a fissure in the earth. Now the sword is once again hidden away where no one will find it.
I found the Eeder in a cage in Calypsi's Foothold. I should free him.,
I destroyed a necromantic font in Necris.
I helped a deceased father ensure his fortune went to his daughter.
Gerarde made it to Master Muzgu safely. Muzgu refuses to return to the abbey, insisting that Gerarde should return alone.

Muzgu asked me to kill him to stop the Omen from possessing him. I refused. Instead, we agreed to capture a Supernal Dreamer and trick the Omen into possessing them instead.nnVaermina will take the Supernal Dreamer and lock them in eternal nightmare.
Gerarde was furious with both himself and me. He doesn't believe I made the right choice and ultimately blames himself for Muzgu's death.
I have destroyed the Daedra. It no longer threatens Stormhaven. nnMuzgu has promised he would return to Pariah Abbey when no trace of the Daedra remained.
Gerarde was furious with both himself and me. He doesn't believe I made the right choice and ultimately blames himself for Muzgu's death.

I assaulted the Imperials within their dig site in Southern Bangkorai, and I took many weapons from them. I then gave the weapons over to Amjahan, a captive Redguard and leader of the resistance inside the camp.
The spirit thanked me for closing the Gate Barrier, saying that I've set his spirit to rest, and rewarded me for my labors.
I agreed to help <<1>> break the curse on his men. He said I could call on him when I'm ready to attack the Imperials at Bangkorai Garrison.

Gerarde says that Master Muzgu is being kept inside the cave on the northern part of Moonlit Maw. He worries that, while he is inside saving Muzgu, the portals outside will cover Moonlit Maw with Daedra.
Safia was saddened to hear of Muzgu's death, but she still thinks stopping the Daedra and the Supernal Dreamers is a victory.
Safia was glad to hear that Muzgu is alive. Now she knows we've thwarted the Supernal Dreamers' plans.

Ala has discovered the Imperial archmage in charge of training gargoyles. He's training them as pets. The other mages only command the gargoyles. If the archmage dies, no more gargoyles can be trained.

When I returned the book, Aunt Heba revealed herself as a Redguard spy.nnShe pretends to be a merchant so she can move freely through occupied territory.nnShe told me the ledger has hidden directions to rebel camps. She's glad to have it back.

When I returned the book, Aunt Heba revealed herself as a Redguard spy. She pretends to be a merchant who moves freely through occupied territory. She told me the ledger book has hidden directions to rebel camps. She's glad to have it back.
I helped <<1>> summon the spirit of <<2>> to prove his guilt.
I helped a lost apostate of Tribunal Temple renew his faith.
I killed cliff racers around Iliath Temple and burned their hearts in sacrifice to the Tribunal.
I infiltrated the Imperial encampment at the Necropolis of Heroes. Then I made contact with a Redguard spy posing as an Imperial soldier.
I killed Imperial necromancers. Inadan assured me they deserved no mercy.

I returned dreugh eggs to their nests and killed the dreugh encroaching on Wayrest. That's significantly reduced the chance the dreugh will invade the slums again. Soon, they'll go back to their spawning pools and leave the slums alone.

The spirit is named Mazira. She is an ancient Redguard warrior buried in the necropolis. When the Imperials desecrated her tomb, she found her way back to our world and fought them off. Unfortunately, many other honored dead were not so lucky.
I anointed several afflicted pilgrims with sacred oils from Iliath Temple.
The barkeep gave me a package in exchange for the letter from Giden. I delivered the package to Braso Endise in the merchant square. I still haven't found out what's inside it.
I collected sigil stones and delivered them to the Mages Guild. They offered me a handsome reward.

House Redoran plotted to accuse House Dres of enslaving the poor of Kraganemoor. A House Dres bureaucrat named <<1>> asked me to retrieve a set of census records. I was forced to defend myself against an ambush of Redoran agents.

Outside the Danarkus Dwemer Ruin, I encountered a stranger who babbled about his failure to repair the waterworks. At his urging, I collected the parts necessary and completed the task that killed his team.
I collected proof of my deeds and returned to <<1>> in Wayrest. He thanked me and gave me a reward.
I collected proof of my deeds and returned to <<1>> in Wayrest. He thanked me and gave me a reward.
I collected proof of my deeds and returned to <<1>> in Wayrest. He thanked me and gave me a reward.
I collected proof of my deeds and returned to <<1>> in Evermore. He thanked me and gave me a reward.
I collected proof of my deeds and returned to <<1>> in Evermore. He thanked me and gave me a reward.
I collected proof of my deeds and returned to <<1>> in Evermore. He thanked me and gave me a reward.
I agreed to help <<1>> regain her family honor. She asked me to call on her when I'm ready to attack the Imperials at Bangkorai Garrison.

At the entrance to Danarkus, I found an explorer's body. The remains of his journal were scattered throughout the complex. The pages revealed that <<1>>, the Dunmer who asked me for help, was here when the explorers arrived.

<<1>>, a dying Ashlander, believed Dwemer godlessness created the affliction in Stonefalls. Her tribe came to Danarkus to cleanse its corruption. I tested the quality of the water throughout the ruin, but found no evidence of the affliction.
I returned two sets of disinterred Redguard bones to their tombs. When I was done, the spirit of a Redguard hero named Jhanaida appeared to thank me. Now her spirit can rest eternally.

I returned the two sets of disinterred Redguard bones to their tombs. When I did so, the spirit of a Redguard hero, Jhanaida, appeared and thanked me for restoring her to her tomb. Her spirit can rest once more.

We've raised a grand army of the dead. In addition to the spirits I summoned, others have joined us. Now we're finally ready to march on Legatus Verro's troops, kill him, and free the spirits he's enslaved.
I travelled to Fort Virak and spoke to the captain there. The nobility of Omaynia needed military reinforcements to bring peace to their town.
I travelled southwest of Omaynia to find an alchemist named Erja.
I was unable to save <<1>>. The freed soldier thanked me for trying and offered me a reward.
I was unable to save <<1>> or her son. The freed soldier thanked me for trying and offered me a reward.
I went to Kragenmoor to find a former slave owner from Omaynia for Sting-Lash.
<<1>>, a Dunmer from Kragenmoor, asked me to deliver an anniversary gift to his wife at the Thovasi Sanatorium.
An acolyte from Iliath Temple asked me to take word of her resignation to the Diviner within the temple.
<<1>> noticed the volcano near Heimlyn Keep stirring. I told tell the residents they're welcome to take shelter in Kragenmoor.
I delivered a letter from <<1>> to <<2>> in Narsis.
I found a valuable item: a beetle covered in jewels. I returned it to a Bosmer named Handolor the Handy.
I defeated the champions of the Ministers of the Treasury and War. I've chosen the Minister of Health as the new Regent of Evermore.
I defeated the champions of the Ministers of War and Health. I've chosen the Minister of the Treasury as the new Regent of Evermore.
I defeated the champions of the Ministers of the Treasury and Health, choosing the Minister of War as the new Regent of Evermore.
I made an old lady's birthday wish come true by giving her a lovely bouquet of flowers. Unfortunately she took this gift the wrong way. Now she believes I'm romantically interested in her.
I found the book's owner, an old Redguard named Elhamud. He told me he no longer needs the book. He's memorized the devotion, but he asked me to keep the book with his blessing.
I killed Legatus Verro and freed the Redguard souls he enslaved. They are at peace again. The spirit of Mazira told me I would always be the champion of the Redguards entombed here.

I made an old lady's birthday wish come true by giving her an old hunk of blood pudding I found in her house. Fortunately she really likes blood pudding, and didn't seem to notice it was from her own pantry.
I should travel to Omaynia and speak to whoever is in charge of the freed slaves there. They may know of Half-Tail's fate.
I met a lonely old woman on her birthday, and decided to give her a troll's tooth for a present. She was not happy.
I met an old lady living in an abandoned house who asked me to give her a birthday gift. I refused, only to find out the woman was a vampire. She attacked me as retribution.

Queen Arzhela told me her city has fallen upon dark times. A plague grips the city, and it afflicts her daughter. Her husband is at war. She was impressed with the way I dealt with her ministers, and she asked for my counsel.
I found <<1>> near one of the entrances to the Pens. She thanked me and asked for my help freeing the other captives.
I recovered some medicine that was really skooma.
<<1>> was concerned about the food supplies of the Ashlanders. They're besieged within the Shrine of Boethiah. <<2>> gladly accepted the food, but she said she had no cure for the affliction.

<<1>> was concerned about the food supplies of the Ashlanders. They're besieged within the Shrine of Boethiah.  We gathered food, but the ordinators had already taken over.nn<<2>> accepted the food, saying Almalexia could use it to feed the poor.
I met a pair of saboteurs that have been harrassing the Reachmen. They were glad to see me, and they asked for my help.

<<1>> was concerned about the food supplies of the Ashlanders besieged within the Shrine of Boethiah.  We gathered food, while the Ashlanders  broke the siege.nn<<2>> accepted the food, but said the Ashlanders had no cure for the affliction.
I helped a deceased father ensure his fortune went to his daughter.
After drinking the poison, the Nest-Mother appeared for a moment. I should journey to the top of the enclave and speak to her, now that I have passed her test.
The captains ended the rioting once I provided proof to all of them.nnOne clue of note is the name Owafa; it appeared on the suspicious note I found. Owafa may be the one organizing the uprising.
The captains ended the rioting once I provided proof to all of them.nnOne clue of note is the name Owafa; it appeared on the suspicious note I found. Owafa may be the one organizing the uprising.
The captains ended the rioting once I provided proof to all of them.nnOne clue of note is the name Owafa; it appeared on the suspicious note I found. Owafa may be the one organizing the uprising.
The Reachmen are keeping many Redguards as slaves in a large prison. Tribune Kabra at-Shadr and others have been freeing many, but they need my help freeing more slaves.
The Reachmen are keeping many Redguards as slaves in a large prison. Tribune Kabra at-Shadr and others have been freeing many, but they need my help freeing more slaves.

I believe I've found the assassin who returned from Alten Corimont. He spoke of hearing the voice of Sithis and killing his own brothers before he attacked me. I should speak to the Nest-Mother and tell her what occurred.
I combed the ruins of Salas En looking for Altmer relics, then handed them over to an Altmer researcher named Telenger.
I killed several of the beetles troubling the Rain Catcher Fields and collected the desert grubs they were feeding on. I gave the grubs to <<1>>, one of the water gatherers.
Within the depths of Salas En, I sought the remains of slaughtered Altmer. Then I consecrated their bones.
A Sand-born tried to run past Guard Captain Zafira. She cut him down, saying he claimed the Sand-born were promised a reward for being at the docks. The Sand-born did not live long enough to say who.
I saved the rain catchers from destruction by a Withered Hand saboteur, securing the water supply for Sentinel.
I've found some notes that were dropped by some suspicious Argonians. They all seem to be written in the same strange code. I should take them to the Listener and see if he can decipher them.
I reached Dock Master Bahir. He told me the Withered Hand kidnapped him because he was about to uncover their plans. He's convinced they're behind the unrest on the docks.

I summoned "Sithis" but saw nothing but a vision of a cloaked figure. When it realized I was no Shadowscale, it called upon the Children of Sithis to attack me.nnI must tell the Nest-Mother someone masquerades as the voice of Sithis.
The Children of Sithis have taken up arms against the Shadowscales. I should ask the Nest-Mother how she will recover from this blow.
At the request of Telenger the Artificer, I travelled to the ancient site of Ancestor's Landing and offered my help.
I freed Azah from his captors. Apparently, he heard the Withered Hand talking while he was held captive. They have plans beyond a simple kidnapping.
In the ruins beneath Salas En ,I discovered an Orc imprisoned for centuries within magical bonds. Then I found a way to dispel the magic and set him free.
Guard Captain Zafira was pleased to hear Salmaran is dead.

<<1>> wanted the people of Burrower's Chasm to rejoin the outside world. He believed the best way to do that is by exposing them to delicious foods none of them have experienced before.nnI collected and passed out the food, delighting the villagers.
I helped <<1>> discover the Shadowscales are innocent.
Dock Master Bahir was not pleased to hear the ships would be landlocked. He said this will cripple the Redguard navy.
Dock Master Bahir was not pleased to hear the ships would be landlocked and declared that King Fahara'jad must know of the damage the Withered Hand has caused.
I did some things for <<1>>.  He seems pretty happy now.
I killed many shalk infesting Stormhold's Hist Tree.
I found and killed Garron the Red, a notorious criminal wanted in Wayrest.
I dispersed some violent mercenaries from Stormhold.
I travelled to Tu'whacca's Throne and spoke with a Throne Keeper. He told me tales of a necromancer taking over the temple and defiling it with undead.
The thief thanked me for my mercy. He plans to leave Sentinel entirely so as to escape the Withered Hand, who are threatening to harm beggars unless they start stealing things.
I turned the would-be thief over to the city guard. He says he's a first time offender. He'll probably spend a week in the dungeons before he's set free.
I infiltrated a house of Archeins and learned they are not responsible for the assassinations in Stormhold.
I helped return several deserters to <<1>>.

I met a doomsayer in Burrower's Chasm, who insisted that various signs proved the people would meet a bad end if they opened their valley to trade.nnI discovered that he had caused the "signs" himself, and I denounced him to several of his followers.

I met a doomsayer in Burrower's Chasm, who insisted that various signs proved the people would meet a bad end if they opened their valley to trade.nnI discovered that he had caused the "signs" himself, to convince the people his visions were true.

By using a magical orb, I was able to hear memories of the spirits which haunt Ancestor's Landing. I then reported my discoveries to Telenger the Artificer, who realized the spirits anger was caused by the presence of him and his Altmer colleagues.

I led a group of Altmer historians out of Ancestor's landing to escape the hostile spirits there, only to be ambushed on the way out. The spirits demanded payment for the trespass, and I offered Artirinwe as sacrifice.
I was able to find a necromantic text that may describe the ritual.
I have found <<1>> in Sanguine's Demesne.  He was enthralled into endless revelry.
I killed a <<1>> who was enthralling people into an endless party.  They were freed once it was dead.
With the chaos of the Fervor, the Wayrest sewers have been overrun by dangerous beasts. I killed a number of these at the request of Contable Lienne.
The city guard was glad to hear that I had dealt with the monkey overpopulation throughout Sentinel, and awarded me some coin for my trouble.
I discovered <<1>> was really the Archein Noble, <<2>> and killed him.
I've found <<1>> in Alten Corimont.  He is part of the underground there.
I travelled to Shadowscale Enclave and spoke with a <<1>> about the unsanctioned assassinations taking place in Shadowfen.
I found a package of odd trinkets in the stomach of a crocodile at the bottom of Burrower's Chasm. The creature turned out to be "<<1>>," a supposed Daedroth that <<2>>'s followers made offerings to.
I found a package of odd trinkets in the stomach of a crocodile at the bottom of Burrower's Chasm. The creature turned out to be "<<1>>," a supposed Daedroth that <<2>>'s followers made offerings to.
Dock Master Bahir thanked me for my assistance. I brought him the note I found on the Withered Hand minion. He suggested the king should see it.

I led a group of Altmer historians out of Ancestor's landing to escape the hostile spirits there, only to be ambushed on the way out. The spirits demanded payment for the trespass, and I offered Erramenya as sacrifice.

I led a group of Altmer historians out of Ancestor's landing to escape the hostile spirits there, only to be ambushed on the way out. The spirits demanded payment for the trespass, and I offered Cirundelie as sacrifice.

I led a group of Altmer historians out of Ancestor's landing to escape the hostile spirits there, only to be ambushed on the way out. The spirits demanded payment for the trespass, but I refused and fought them myself.
I met Guard Captain Zafira at the Sentinel Docks. She says the revolt that's currently going on is the bloodiest she's ever seen. She suspects something may be amiss.
I travelled to the ruins of Salas En. I spoke with Telenger the Aritificer at his base camp.

I found an ancient scroll hidden within Ancestor's Landing, and brought it to Telenger the Aritficer. He was able to tell me the scroll was written in the high elf language, and bore a message of welcome to the Yokudan who lived here.

I found an ancient scroll hidden within Ancestor's Landing, and brought it to Telenger the Aritficer. He was able to tell me the scroll was written in the high elf language, and bore a message of welcome to the Yokudan who lived here.

<<1>>, a resident of Burrower's Chasm, wondered if the Argonian trading post of Ten-Maur-Wolk on the river to the west still existed. I met an Argonian fisherman along the river's edge who told me there had been no trade for many years.
I should bring Vivendus' cargo and idol back to him so he can recover from the loss of his riverboat caravan.
I found a dead sheep in the ruins of Ancestor's Landing. I took its collar to its owner at Rain Catcher Fields. However, the owner was upset because I didn't bring back the sheep.
I've found the Archein contact for the necromancers. I should speak to him to find out exactly what he's supplying to the necromancers.

I've freed the captives of the Archeins in Bogmother. They spoke of one of their number who went to find out what the Archeins and the necromancers were doing at the shrine itself. I should find her and see what she's discovered.
Nagas have taken over the village of Ten-Maur-Wolk. The Archeins of Alten Corimont are trying to keep them contained. I helped by eliminating the Naga <<1>>
I reached Dock Master Bahir. The Withered Hand kidnapped him because he was about to uncover one of their plots. He's convinced they're behind the unrest on the docks.
<<1>> sent me in search of an Archein diplomat in Ten-Maur-Wolk, whom she feared had been captured or killed. Instead I uncovered a plot by more extremist Archein to wipe out more moderate members.
I ventured into Salas En and spoke with Rinlan. Telenger the Artificer hired him to protect his excavation.
I've killed the necromancer dealing with the Archeins in Bogmother. I should let Neekta know the negotiations are over.

I found a woman named Neyali caring for a sickly goatherd. Neyali said the goatherd was poisoned when he drank from a johad.. She gave him milk, but that will only slow the effects of the poison. The goatherd desperately needs a cure.
I was able to give Neyali the reagents in time for her to save Marimah's life. Neyali was overjoyed. She'll use this cure to prevent more deaths.
I was too late. Marimah died. Neyali thanked me for trying. She'll use her curative to prevent more deaths.
I spoke with <<1>> who taught me about the Cult of the Fang and has asked me to help them further.
I recruited several merchants and prisoners to join the Cult of the Fang.
I collected vital supplies for <<1>> of the Cult of the Fang.
I trained the members of the Cult of the Fang in combat.
I challenged and defeated <<1>> for leadership of the Cult of the Fang.

The Nagas were supplied with flammable pitch by extremists among the Archein. I stole several barrels of the pitch, and poured it over the naga campfires. The result was a massive conflagration that burned the raiders from the river.

The Elder Throne Keeper said the keys I've collected will allow him to cast a powerful spell. The incantation will open Tu'whacca's Shrine. Unfortunately, doing this will weaken him greatly. I'll have to destroy Owafa without him.
I found an ancient Yoku sword in Ancestor's Landing. I used a Soul Gem to drain spiritual energy from it. The spirit within revealed itself to be a young Yoku warrior with aspirations of greatness.
I killed several cultists and burned the stolen goods, then spoke to Dar'Virr, a smuggler captain.
On the road north of Morwha's Bounty, I discovered a dead goatherd. He stumbled from the south before falling in the sand. There are more bodies near the entrance to Morwha's Bounty.
I found a missive and spoke to the leader of Stillrise, <<1>>.
I offered a truce to the mercenary leader but he refused. As a result, I killed several of them at <<1>>'s request.
I helped drive away a band of mercenaries from Stillrise.
I helped a grave tender put his unearthed friends to rest.
I spoke to a member of the Cult of the Fang about expanding business but he wasn't interested.
I brought Soul Gems to each of Telenger's assistants in Ancestor's Landing, then helped them with their research. Along the way, I managed to destroy many hostile spirits roaming the ruins.
Kalas was already dead when I found him. The Withered Hand has already attacked Morwha's Bounty.

I found a Yoku smoking pipe in Ancestor's Landing. I used a Soul Gem to drain spiritual energy from it. The spirit within revealed itself to be an aging storyteller. He recounted histories of the Yoku people.
I found a worn Yoku hair-comb in Ancestor's Landing. I used a Soul Gem to drain spiritual energy from it. The spirit within revealed itself to be a Yoku mother fretting over her unhappy daughter.

Within the ruins of Ancestor's Landing, I was forced to make a choice. I could only free two of three Altmer from angry Yoku spirits. I decided to leave the kind and bubbly Artirinwe behind while I escorted the others out to safety.

Within the ruins of Ancestor's Landing, I was forced to make a choice. I could only free two of three Altmer from angry Yoku spirits. I decided to leave the young and sarcastic Erramenya behind while escorting the others to safety.

Within the ruins of Ancestor's Landing, I was forced to make a choice. I could only free two of three Altmer from angry Yoku spirits. I decided to leave the harsh, demanding Cirundelie behind while escorting the others to safety.
I've found the safehouse and was greeted by a gruff Nord. I should let him know Lei-Kai sent me.
I found an killed Inerri, the Blood Cat leader. Minglos thanked me and offered a reward.
I've freed the slaves before the slavers had a chance to regroup. I also discovered Riane had freed herself. She asked me to tell Scale-Shorn she will not be returning because of his betrayal.
I've told Shade-Tail the news of her brother. She was understandably upset, and vowed revenge.nnI should let Keira know what has happened.
I found Captain Dar'Virr's bird and returned it to him. He thanked me and offered me a reward.
<<1>> was determined to return to Sentinel. He saw his losses at Kulati Mines as a small price to be able to walk away alive.
In the ruined city of Ancestor's Landing, I met a High Elf named Telenger the Artificer. He claimed to be a researcher searching the ruins for evidence of the ancient Yoku people.
I located a survivor of the events at Murkvale.
I visited Bloodgutter and located a khajiit named Dar'Thid, who shed light on the events in Bloodgutter.
I spoke with Kasal. He was delighted to meet me, hoping I could help him in these dire times.
<<1>> realized she was foolish to attempt to trick a Daedra.
I gathered working amulets from the bandits and used them on the mad villagers, halting their insanity.
I've destroyed the bodies the Worm Cult necromancers were using in Alten Corimont. I should return to the safehouse and tell Shade-Tail of my success.
I've discovered that Hjarl was the one who betrayed Lei-Kai and his men. I should tell Shade-Tail the news.
Kee-Scale's master has agreed to let him go free, despite asking me to do his task for him. I should let Kee-Scale know he is a free Argonian.
I've mixed the venom in the amphora and tasted its contents. A strange vision spoke to me, a vision of a coiled snake rising from the fumes. Perhaps I can... speak back to it.
I found the corpses of Venosir's father and brother, rescued his wife, and was forced to kill his mother when she became a werewolf.
The worried villager thanked me for saving his cousin and bringing him to Soradenor's home.
I found a pile of stones in the ruins east of Murkvale that appear very similar to the stone bandit amulets.
I informed Dronoril about the events at Murkvale.
Tiela was pleased with my choice and seemed to appreciate the book of poetry. She asked me to speak with Casnar, who was happy with the news.
In the town of Tava's Blessing I helped ease the troubled mind of a survivor by recovering the treasured possessions of three of his friends.
You killed the Gideon River Pirates who had been collecting sap from the Hist Tree.
I gave <<1>> the supplies she needed for the sharxal salve.
I have killed many of the swamp-addled Argonians who were hatched without the blessings of the Elder Hist.
I licked the Elder Hist roots, rubbed the salve on the newly hatching eggs, and completed this season's hatching ritual.
I have informed Shamar that Tiela chose him as her suitor.

Captain Munada stated that Justice Istah is actually the killer. Her guards claim Istah murdered Inila, a server at the Thirsty Lizard inn. They caught him fleeing the scene. Istah's blades were found in Inila and Fakimal's backs.

I've cleared Justice Istah's name. I've proved that Captain Munada abducted and murdered the missing people from Bergama. The victims' bodies will be consecrated and buried so they cannot be raised by the Withered Hand.
I found Lenathil near the entrance to Gallowroot.
I was warned that Nagas took over the village of Ten-Maur-Wolk. I sought out nearby forces loyal to the Archeins, who are trying to defeat them.
I pieced together a journal explaining the events in the last days of the charred village and returned it to its author.
I collected dishes for a strange Argonian.
I killed murderers threatening the people in MIrewalk Village.
I killed <<1>>s for a paranoid Argonian.
I destroyed some gas that was poisoning the minds of a village.
I was able to find out the plans of the Maormer and defeated both Admirial Khamisin and Orgnum's protege, Nedir.nnThe coast of Tamriel is safe from Maormer invasion for now.
Within the stone-filled basin of Ogres End, I discovered a book indicating the Withered Hand could be planning to resurrect ogre bones to create a horde of undead monsters.
Within the stone-filled basin of Ogres End, I discovered a message indicating the Withered Hand could be planning to resurrect ogre bones to create a horde of undead monsters.
I slew Cingur and other werewolves in Gallowroot on behalf of Uurwen.

<<1>> was concerned the pirates that recently arrived at Sunscale Strand might attack and plunder the Argonian resort.nnWhile he sent me to ask the pirates their intentions, they attacked and plundered the resort.

I met Tribune Salida al-Natedan in the monument yard. She said my name came to her on the wind, and I am at the center of many events to come. She asked me to meditate with her. She hopes I will receive a vision from the Ansei.

I met Master Fadalia abd-Ahtar at the southernmost entrance to Anvil's Heart. She confirmed she has need of me, warning that the cabal of necromancers called the Withered Hand grows stronger every day.

I found Rashdi. His plan was to discover how the Withered Hand controlled the zombies. He was wounded, so he asked me to investigate in his place. I'll need a cultist disguise of my own to accomplish this task.

I met a Redguard scout named Halida near Sep's Spine. She came here tracking a massive undead army that has risen up against Alik'r. She says it is led by a necromancer named <<1>>. He may still have the Ansei Wards.
Within the stone-filled basin of Ogres End, I discovered a book indicating the Withered Hand could be planning to resurrect ogre bones to create a horde of undead monsters.
Within the stone-filled basin of Ogres End, I discovered a message indicating the Withered Hand could be planning to resurrect ogre bones to create a horde of undead monsters.
In order to prove I was not a spy of the Withered Hand, I killed many of their members in the stone basin called <<1>>.
I tried to reinforce the threat of Mannimarco to the Hissmir.
At the request of <<1>>, I entered the pirate camp at Sunscale Strand. While fighting, I found a Privateering Contract between the pirates and mannimarco's Cult of Worms.
I explained to Rashdi what I learned about the Withered Men. He has a plan for how to stop a Storm Wizard who draws his strength from Withered Men.

At Ogres End, Withered Hand necromancers used the petrified bones of long-dead ogres to create skeletal monsters. To stop this threat, I took the bones away from the necromancers, carried them into the desert and destroyed them in a fire.

<<1>> sent me to burn goods the pirates had stolen before they could use them, and pilfer a chest of cash to recoup the loss.nnThe chest, however, proved to have a jar of Hist sap in it - a discovery which drove <<1>> to apoplectic rage.
Using a Maormer snake charmer's ring, I was able to kill a number of snakes around Tempest Island.nnClearly the Maormer were breeding and taming them to aid in their invasion of Tamriel.
Rashdi mentioned that King Fahara'jad would learn of my victory over the WIthered Hand at Sep's Spine.
I returned to the Ghostly Magistrate and informed him that each of the four risen criminals had been dealt with.
I discovered everyone in the village succumbed to illness.
I found the ingredients for a Kothringi ritual.
I collected boar blood for a Kothringi ritual.
I reached Tava's Blessing, only to find it besieged by the Withered Hand.
I gave <<1>> the incorrect reagents for her elixir, resulting in her death.
Worm Cult necromancers were stealing Hist sap, poisoning it and shipping it off for use elsewhere. I destroyed the poisoned sap.
I traveled to Kulati Mines and spoke with the mine owner, who confirmed his mine was indeed infested by giant spiders.

I found a series of letters from Gathorian the mage to a lover of some sort in Root Sunder. He stayed for whoever it was long after the other Imperials fled, and one way or another he died here. His body was in a tree, either protected or consumed
I traveled to the town of Satakalaam to provide any assistance I can to the local citizens.
I was given a sapling by the dryad Shivaralai, to give to the children of her beloved Gatheron.nnRaolus Gatheron seemed very ...enamored... of her gift.
I ventured into the canyons below Lainlyn and slew many giant snakes there, proving my martial prowess to the people of Lainlyn.
I slew the huntsmen's leader on behalf of Lenathil in Gallowroot.

In the canyons surrounding Lainlyn I discovered clutches of giant snake eggs all over the place. I then destroyed the eggs to prevent the snakes from overpopulating, thus preventing them from overrunning the town of Lainlyn.
I visited Murkvale and delivered news about Gallowroot to Venosir.
I spoke to a merchant at Silvenar and told him about Gallowroot.

The Trader Idtrasin asked me to find treasure for him in the Alakad's Curse sinkhole. He claimed his workers were lazy and ran off.nnIt turns out he was swindling the beggars; I sold the treasure to them for a good price instead.

The Trader Idtrasin asked me to find treasure for him in the Alakad's Curse sinkhole. He said his workers were lazy and ran off.nnThere may be another story, but I was content to work for Idrasin, who treated me fairly enough.
Arad's revenge has been carried out.
I managed to find enough food to help the starving residents of Lainlyn.
I have supported Keethius' leadership of the Cult of the Fang and avoided exile.
I have supported Keethius' leadership of the Cult of the Fang and avoided exile.
I discovered everyone in the village succumbed to illness.
In Lainlyn, I disguised myself as a member of the Withered Hand, and interrogated two townsfolk who had dealings with the necromancer called Death's Consort.
I've killed several of the horrors haunting the sinkhole. I returned to Jarakhad to let him know his wife had been avenged, but it seems his wife has actually improved her situation

I all but wiped out the Gray Sail pirates to help an Altmer constable save face. I let Constable Harus take the credit, and told his Sergeant he had collected the pirates' rings and done the deed himself.
